INSERT INTO `ProfileBand` VALUES (271,271,'Chris Caffery',7,33,'www.chriscaffery.com','','','Long story short. If you don\'t already know I play lead guitar in the bands Savatage and The Trans-Siberian Orchestra. Savatage is still together folks, we are just not as busy as some of you would like at the moment! I have been with Savatage a very long time...my first tour was in support of the CD \"Hall Of The Mountain King\". The following CD was entitled \"Gutter Ballet\". The video for this song is played all the time on VH1 Classics. The band has sold millions of CD\'s and played for hundreds of thousands of fans world-wide. In 1995 I released a CD with Savatage singer Jon Oliva called Doctor Butcher. The CD was just re-released last year with new material world-wide on Black Lotus Records. Also in 1995 Savatage released a CD called \"Dead Winter Dead\". On this CD was a song called \"Christmas Eve Sarajevo-12/24\". This instrumental song was the spring board for the multi platinum Trans-Siberian Orchestra. I play lead guitar and M/C the live shows. We finished our 7th sold out tour...this year it was all in arenas...Madison Square Garden (Extra cool this year because our good friend Joan Jett came onstage and played \"I Love Rock And Roll\" with us during the encore!!), Palace in Detroit, etc. The last tour we sold over 700,000 tickets!\r\n\r\nIn January of 2004 I began pre-production for my very first solo CD ever. Recording began in February. \r\n\r\nJeff Plate took care of the drumming duties, Dave Z the bass and Paul Morris the keyboards and piano.\r\n\r\nThe CD was recorded at Spin Studios in Astoria, NYCity. I produced the CD with co-producer/engineer Nik Chinboukas. The recording and mixing were finished in May of 2004. I then flew to Athens, Greece for the mastering and CD photo shoot. Many of the phots you see here are from the shoot. Thanks to Seth at Seth Design!! Because of the abundance of material I decided to record 30 songs. There are 2 CDs recorded. Faces and God Damn War. \r\n\r\nIn August of 2004 I flew to Germany to be a special guest for Doro Pesch at the 15th Anniversary of Wacken. The premier Heavy Metal Festival in Europe. I played 3 songs with Doro and her Classic Metal Orchestra. The performance was very memorable. The next night I also appeared as a special guest with Saxon. I got to play Denim and Leather with the band. As a huge fan, this was a great honor! I have been blessed to have so many great friends, I even got invited onstage to play \"Killed By Death\" with Motorhead in Austria!!! Those guys are my favorite Rock and Roll Stars!!!\r\n\r\nThe first single for Faces was released on September 1st, 2004 in Europe. It was called The Mold. It contained 3 songs from the release and 2 unreleased bonus tracks. It was a limited edition that I believe it has just about sold out everywhere!\r\n\r\nI also released an EP called \"Music Man\". This CD has a few unreleased holiday songs I recorded. The sample for the one song \"What Child Is This?\" was downloaded over 300,000 on my web-site www.chriscaffery.com. The site is really cool and very active, our message board community is now over 3,350 people and growing rapidly. I keep studio diaries and daily thoughts there too as well as the main site which features many things including my photos, diaries and recipies!!!\r\n\r\nOn September 11th 2004 I headed to Florida to rehearse for a WOMD/Savatage appearance as the headliner of the Prog Power festival in Atlanta. The show was to feature Jon Oliva, former Savatage vocalist Zak Stevens, original Savatage drummer Steve Wacholz and myself. We were called Weapons of Mass Destruction because although we were to play all Savatage material, it was not all of the members of the current Savatage line-up.\r\n\r\nZak Stevens had a terrible accident the week prior to the show and lost part of his right middle finger. He was unable to appear. The show then featured the first lead vocal performance for myself ever. I sang Edge of Thorns and Power of the Night. The show was sold for months and the whole weekend was a ton of fun!\r\n\r\nI went back in the studio in early 2005 to finish the GDWar CD. The results were WARPED!!! This CD was released in Europe in June 2005, Sept. in the US. It is the full length version of my WAR CD! The CD contains 6 unreleased songs, one sung by Jon Oliva! It was a lost Doctor Butcher track called \"Iraq Attack.\" It is in stores in the USA and the rest of the world right now! I am currently working on new material for my next CD. I am going to call it \"Pins and Needles\". \r\n\r\nI did some European and American touring in support of \"Faces\" and \"WARPED\". The European tuor was in support of the legendary Metal Church. The US was a 3 band bill consisting of Jon Oliva\'s Pain and Ripper Owen\'s new band Beyond Fear. It was great to get out and play my solo stuff live. \"Pisses Me Off\" is always the crowd favorite!!!\r\n\r\nIn addition to the bands I listed I have recorded with or written songs for many bands and artists including Circle II Circle, John West, Joe Lynn Turner, Metalium, Eidolon, Jon Oliva\'s Pain and more...For a complete list of my discography visit this page. http://www.chriscaffery.com/discography.htm I have also had a few special guest appearances in many friends DVD\'s including Cradle of Filth and Doro! \r\n\r\nOn February 8th of 2006 I will enter the studio once again! I hope to have Pins out in October...in the meantime....My CD\'s are finally up on I Tunes if you are interested in downloading the samples you hear or the entire playlist! http://www.apple.com/itunes/ I will be launching a new ChrisCaffery.com soon! Keep an eye out! Thanks for all of your support!!! I hope you are all enjoying the new year and I will speak to you soon!!!\r\n\r\nFor booking and all business related inquiries contact my personal management... http://www.barleyandhopsmgmt.com Would you expect me to work with anyone else?<br/><br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=21\">Join the Chris Caffery discussion</a>',1,'',0,''),(329,304,'DJ Randy Bettis',5,27,'http://www.djrandybettis.com','57 W. 75th Street','646-827-9218','DJ/Producer Randy Bettis was just voted &quot;DJ/Remixer/Producer of the Year&quot; &amp; &quot;Best Circuit Tour 2007&quot; for his Gay DayS Tour 2007 by the members of JustCircuit.com, one of the nations leading source for the&nbsp; world&#39;s gay &amp; lesbian dance world. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nAfter leaving the bright lights of Broadway in 1998, as a dancer/singer 2004 was a breakout year for Randy Bettis, the New York based DJ/producer. Spring brought the national release of his first commercial mixed CD, Centaur Entertainment&rsquo;s official 2004 Orlando Gay Days CD (which he has subsequently been the mixmaster on the 2005 &amp; 2006 version and has been offered the 2007 CD compilation as well). The national exposure continued with Randy spinning at Denver&rsquo;s A Weekend in OZ, Palm Springs&rsquo; White Party, and Austin&rsquo;s Perfect Day. July found him in Fire Island Pines manning the turntables at Bliss, a spectacular day party that he also produced with partners Michael Metts of Drury Design Dynamics and Patty Rosado. In September, Randy spun Fairgrounds, an evening for the LGBT community at Six Flags Great Adventure.  He returned again in 2006 to share the turntables with one of his mentors, DJ Max Rodriguez. 2005 continued the momentum with Randy manning the turntables at 3 of New York City&rsquo;s biggest dance events: the Saint-at-Large Escape To Candyland; the Saint at Large Black Party&ndash;Lucha Libre: Rites XXVI; and the 19th Annual Heritage of Pride Gay Pride Pier Dance. And things just keep getting better. In 2006, Randy will took his third turn as mixmaster on Centaur&rsquo;s annual Gay Days CD for Orlando Gay Day.  DJRB, along with the BetBoyz Team, in association with Centaur Music and GayDays.com developed his first ever promotional tour &ndash; Gay Days Tour 2006.  This was also the year that Randy took his music to the sea on both the &ldquo;R Family Cruise&rdquo; and the &ldquo;RSVP Mexican Riviera Cruise&rdquo;. Beginning May 22, you can how hear Randy&rsquo;s mixed sets on every Monday evening on G.I.R.L. (GayInternetRadioLive.com).  In addition to all that Randy is proud to have been elected to the illustrious Billboard Panel, as part of a nationwide panel that ultimately is responsible for the charting of all the dance music released in the United States.  To cap off 2006 DJRB &amp; The Gay Days Tour was very honored to have been voted &ldquo;Best Circuit Tour of 2006&rdquo; by the members of JustCircuit.com. For some time now, Randy had been developing a devoted following in Manhattan nightclubs. Over the years, Randy has played in some of New York&#39;s most legendary night spots: Sound Factory, Limelight, Cielo, Splash, Element, Webster Hall, Avalon-NY, Life, SPA, Centro-Fly, XL, &amp; the Fire Island Pines Pavilion&mdash;just to name a few. Currently, he is a resident DJ at Splash Bar in NYC, with guest residencies at Pavilion/Blue Whale in Fire Island Pines, Pure in Philadelphia &amp; Paramount Ballroom in Provincetown, MA. In addition to paying the rent, Randy also pays it forward, regularly donating his talents as DJ and music producer. He is regular feature of Broadway Bares, spinning tunes between performances and providing music production and editing services for the annual spectacular benefiting Broadway Cares/Equity Fights AIDS. 2004&rsquo;s Bliss in Fire Island Pines, which Randy co-produced and spun, raised funds for the Stonewall Community Foundation and the Foundation for Integrative AIDS Research. Over the years, Randy has donated his services to raise funds for a number of other organizations including Dancers Responding To AIDS, New York Theater Workshop, and VisualAIDS. In 2001, Bettis teamed up with writer/arranger David Boyd to form BetBoyz NYC, a music/event production company. In the fall of 2002, Emerge Records honored BetBoyz by choosing their very first remix, the &quot;BetBoyz Vocal Dub&quot; mix of Taylor Daynes&#39; &quot;How Many&quot;, to be included on the commercial release of the CD maxi single. Recent projects include remixes for Aussie artist Karen Jacobsen, Broadway star Billy Porter, hot singing sensation Brian Kent and Junior Vasquez recording artist Jason Walker.  Additionally, BetBoyz recently completed a full-scale musical, The Groove Factory, which is being considered for various musical-theater festivals.  For more information go to <a href=\"DJRandyBettis.com\" target=\"_blank\">DJRandyBettis.com</a>. Demos and additional photos are available.   DJ/Producer Randy Bettis has been featured at a number of high-profile special events including: &Atilde;&cent;&Aring;&frac34;&Acirc;&cent;	Gold (2006, Phoenix Rainbow Festival After Party (Phoenix, AZ) &Atilde;&cent;&Aring;&frac34;&Acirc;&cent;	Broadway Bares (1998-2006, Webster Hall &amp; Roseland Ballroom, New York, NY) &Atilde;&cent;&Aring;&frac34;&Acirc;&cent;	White On Time &ndash; Love Parade Productions NYC White Party (2006, Element Club, NYC) &Atilde;&cent;&Aring;&frac34;&Acirc;&cent;	Dance 19 &ndash; Heritage of Pride Gay Pride Pier Dance (2005, Pier 54, NYC) &Atilde;&cent;&Aring;&frac34;&Acirc;&cent;	Lucha Libre: Rites XXVI - The Black Party (2005, Roseland, NYC). &Atilde;&cent;&Aring;&frac34;&Acirc;&cent;	Escape To Candyland- Saint-at-Large New Years&rsquo; Day Celebration (2005, Capitale, New York City). &Atilde;&cent;&Aring;&frac34;&Acirc;&cent;	David Flower&#39;s Silver &amp; Gold New Years Eve Celebration (2000 - 2004, Provincetown, MA) &Atilde;&cent;&Aring;&frac34;&Acirc;&cent;	Fairgrounds (2004, Six Flags Great Adventure, Jackson, NJ) &Atilde;&cent;&Aring;&frac34;&Acirc;&cent;	Perfect Day 2K4 / Candy (2004, Austin Music Hall, Austin Texas) - Main Event &Atilde;&cent;&Aring;&frac34;&Acirc;&cent;	Bliss...experience the journey! (2004, Fire Island Pines Community Center) - Producer/DJ &Atilde;&cent;&Aring;&frac34;&Acirc;&cent;	Jeffrey Sankers&rsquo; White Party (2004, Wyndam Hotel, Palm Springs, CA) - DJ Showcase &Atilde;&cent;&Aring;&frac34;&Acirc;&cent;	New York Theater Workshop Fundraiser (2004, The Marquee Club, NYC) &Atilde;&cent;&Aring;&frac34;&Acirc;&cent;	DRA Dance Festival - Dancers Responding to AIDS (1999-2003 Fire Island Pines, NY) &Atilde;&cent;&Aring;&frac34;&Acirc;&cent;	Summer Camp (2001-03, Provincetown, MA) &Atilde;&cent;&Aring;&frac34;&Acirc;&cent;	David Flower&#39;s Memorial Day After-Hours Cruise (2002, Provincetown, PA) &Atilde;&cent;&Aring;&frac34;&Acirc;&cent;	Red Party 2000/Epilogue (Columbus, OH) &Atilde;&cent;&Aring;&frac34;&Acirc;&cent;	Winter Party DJ Showcase (2000, Miami, FL) &Atilde;&cent;&Aring;&frac34;&Acirc;&cent;	Black &amp; White Party (2000, Hollywood Athletic Club, Los Angeles, CA)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=23\" target=\"_blank\">Join the DJ Randy Bettis discussion</a>\r\n',0,'Randy Bettis: DJ/Producer/Remix Arist/Billboad Panel Member:Dance Chart<br />\r\nDavid James Boyd: Producer/Arranger/Singer/Songwriter<br />\r\nErin Stacey: Manager/GayDayS Tour Manager<br />\r\nMichael Sniffen: Production Assistant/Assitant to DJ Randy Bettis<br />\r\nSean Dwyer: Business Manager\r\n',0,''),(302,291,'Eggmen',1,16,'eggmenmusic.com','','215-432-7685','In April of 2004, Philadelphia musicians Mike Cottrill and Dan Goldfedder were sitting in Cottrill\'s home project studio. The two were at a crossroad in regard to which musical project to take on next. In the studio background, Mike was playing an old demo tape of a vocalist who sounded very intense and somewhat uncharactoristic of many other male vocalists. Dan says, \"Wow, who\'s that singing?\" \"That\'s \'The Eyes\'\", says Mike \'The Eyes\', or Steve Shurelian, is a west coast based singer who has worked with Cottrill for several decades.\r\n\r\nThe project began to take shape when, during the following evening, \'The Eyes\' knocked on Mike\'s front door, unannounced, and out of the blue. He had made the drive from Seattle to Philadelphia. Steve surprised everyone with his presence, as he was basically out of touch with the others for over a year. He wanted to lay down some tracks and capture some of the music he had been working on. Philadelphia bassist Rick Terway adds melodic lines to the mix to complete the project called Eggmen.\r\n\r\nDrawing on their combined influences, the Eggmen weave an intense, lyrical journey through different genres of rock music.<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=30\">Join Eggmen\'s discussion</a>',1,'',0,''),(1856,1924,'Placid',1,61,'www.placidweb.com','','','\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\">Moody orchestration mixes with indie rock guitar and solid three part harmony. <?xml:namespace prefix = st1 /><st1:place>Nottingham</st1:place> guitar trio putting together layered anthemic tunes, exploring a Sgt Pepper era after gigging under different guises for nearly 10 years.<?xml:namespace prefix = o /><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\"><br/>Placid are:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br/>Paul Morton&nbsp;- Vocals, Bass, Acoustic Guitar, Piano<br/>Mark Godfrey - Vocals, Lead Guitars, Mandolin<br/>Chris Morton - Drums, Vocals, Orchestration&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br/><br/>A classic three-piece reunion of a Beatles inspired band turned Metallica tribute, come full circle back to their&nbsp;late nineties&nbsp;line up, once again writing original contemporary guitar music fuelled by thick vocal harmonies and killer melodies.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\">Placid cut their teeth on the </span><st1:place><span lang=\"EN-GB\">Midlands</span></st1:place><span lang=\"EN-GB\"> pub scene throughout the late 90s as rock/metal band \'The Calm\', playing their own selection of 90s rock and similarly inspired original tracks.<span>&nbsp; </span>Then still in their teens, their Beatles roots mixed with the likes of Nirvana, Metallica and Guns N&#8217; Roses which, whilst proving popular on the local scene, ultimately saw them straying from mainstream guitar music and the members going their separate ways by 2000.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\">After Paul&#8217;s stint fronting Metallica tribute band \'Moletallica\', the remnants of that band formed the first version of Placid with Chris joining on drums.<span>&nbsp; </span>Placid had some success and local interest in their new restyled approach to four-piece acoustic rock. With several line-up changes, Placid ultimately ended up with the current formula in 2004, seeing Mark rejoin Paul and Chris to form a three piece guitar band fusing their old vocal harmonies with their fully matured song writing chemistry.<span>&nbsp; </span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\">This long-anticipated maturing has turned out anthemic tracks such as \'Joe Robinson\' and \'Freak Show\', which whilst retaining the contemporary guitar band sound, smack of the depth and texture of classics from Pink Floyd or Fleetwood Mac.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\">Taking time out from gigging to question where and why they are going, Placid have had the time to perfect their self-produced debut album -&nbsp;layering it into a classic eclectic rhapsody full of moody E.L.O style orchestration and powerful guitar and vocal melodies.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\">Still in their twenties, Placid feel like they have been there and back again without coming to the attention of the wider public, and now know that in&nbsp;their long awaited (and very imminent!) debut album, they&nbsp;have real magic to offer when they do.</span></p>',1,'',0,''),(305,288,'DJ Brenda Black',5,27,'www.djbrendablack.com','','','NYC based award winning DJ, music journalist and producer www.djbrendablack.com<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=24\">Join Brenda Black\'s discussion</a>',1,'',0,''),(306,287,'Zane Banks',7,33,'myspace.com/zanebanks','','','I have 25+ years playing guitar, Tons of experience roading,running lights,and event coordination. I\'ve also done benefits for Toys4Tots,MDA,Vietnam Vets,and Dreams 2002(A benefit for under priveledged children). I\'m currently working on my first EP/Album.In my home recording studio, I\'m dedicating it to all the kool people that have touched my life in a postive way.. You could say it\'ll be a tribute album. The first 2 songs I have posted are my first attempts at laying drum and bass tracks using a midi keyboard...(I\'m still learning how to use PC recording software) They\'re not completed to my standards. I\'m hoping to find some of the hottest musicians in the business to work and tour with. Growing up in&nbsp;Taylor (Now living off 8 mile). I\'ve had the opportunity to jam with ALOT of kickass musicians back in the day Layin\' down the law of Metal. Former members of Bands such as Raff,Steel Soldier,Universal Stomp,Helicon,Chapter 13,Razor(Bassist),Sweet Revenge, Just for starters I\'ve had the opportunity of jamming in local Detroit bands with. These just a SMALL portion of the number of talented bands that Detroit has to offer,and has offered. Growing up in the 80\'s I listened to alot of classic rock,metal,thrash,black metal,& neo-classical fusion. I\'ll come back and update this as time goes by as I remember some of the guys I\'ve been in bands with. until then .. back to recording and making the dots dance.<br/><br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=22\" target=\"_blank\">Join the Zane Banks discussion</a>',1,'',0,''),(307,295,'TENEbRAE',7,33,'www.myspace.com/tenebrae','Po Box 6','631-332-6057','<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=45\">Join TENEbRAE\'s Discussion</a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(310,303,'DJ Mag Cruz NYC',5,27,'','206 NE 29th Street','(646) 234-0533','DJ Mag Cruz!<br/><br/>',1,'',0,''),(327,338,'helpimarock',1,17,'','','','',0,'',0,''),(413,422,'Jumping For Joyce',1,66,'www.myspace.com/jumpingforjoyce','','','We\'re JUMPING FOR JOYCE and we like playing music and shit like that.\r\nWe started jamming together, oh, about a year ago in the spring of \'06.\r\n<br/>\r\nCHECK OUT: our shows, as we play \'round town a lot + our EP recorded in 2006.<br/>\r\nMessage us to get yours.<br/>\r\nOur new EP is going down this August so check back soon for new tunes!<br/><br/>\r\nYour pals, <br/>\r\nJ4J<br/><br/><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">MEMBERS:</span><br/>\r\nMatt Pfalzer-Vocals/Guitar<br/>\r\nMike Horvatits-Drums<br/>\r\nAndy Freeman-Lead Guitar<br/>\r\nColin Pallas-Lead Guitar<br/>\r\nDerek Reid-Bass<br/><br/>\r\nCheck us out on:<br/>\r\n<br/><a target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); color: rgb(0, 0, 255);\" href=\"http://www.myspace.com/jumpingforjoyce\">Myspace</a><br style=\"background-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); color: rgb(0, 0, 255);\">\r\n<a target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); color: rgb(0, 0, 255);\" href=\"http://www.purevolume.com/jumpingforjoyce\">Pure Volume</a><br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=27\">Join Jumping For Joyce\'s discussion</a>',1,'',0,''),(1056,1282,'Lost Armada',1,66,'www.lostarmada.com','','','<span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman=\"\" ;=\"\">Hailing from Chicago, Illinois, Lost Armada\'s\r\nsound is as polarizing as the weather in the city they call home. From raucous\r\nfour-on-the-floor rock to boot-stomping swagger to bar room sentiment, they are\r\nwell on their way to hooking ears, gathering attention, and causing a surge of\r\nclinking beer bottles across the Midwest. Their debut, <i>Empty Houses</i>, is\r\na perfect illustration of the band&#8217;s personality. Crafted in pure DIY ethic and\r\nengineered completely by themselves, the E.P. equates to Preachers building the\r\nChurch. Solid songwriting meshes with intelligent arrangements, only to form a\r\npowerful return to form that is reminiscent of The Replacements, Whiskeytown,\r\nand the dustiest 45&#8221; you can find in the jukebox of the dirtiest dive bar. With\r\nan endless output of songs and plans for a future full-length, it seems that\r\nLost Armada is starting to make strides in the music world.</span>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=234\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Lost Armada\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(386,399,'Robert Dante',1,61,'www.robertdante.com','1101 SW 144 Court','305-803-2647','<span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: black;\">    Robert Dante is a name to remember so that when the face of pop rock is forever changed you can call to mind who was responsible for the paradigm shift.  Hailing from Miami, Dante brings with him an incomparable talent for writing catchy rock and roll that nonetheless resonates with thoughtfulness and honest emotional presentation.<br/>\r\nSinger/songwriter Robert Dante discovered and began developing his talent for playing piano at the early age of 6.  As a teenager, he acquired a taste for early jazz standards, inspiring him to further explore his creativity.  Robert trained in both classical and jazz theory and performance, studying under the tutelage of renowned jazz pianist Tamir Hendlemen.  His exceptional talent earned him numerous, prestigious awards and scholarships including the following: The David Alpert Scholarship at Los Angeles City College, The Leslie P. Clausen Scholarship, also at Los Angeles City College, and The National Honor Society at the University of Central Florida.<br/>\r\nRobert Dante\'s credits include composing and producing soundtracks for such independent films as \"Bloodline\" and \"Little Things\".  He has also enjoyed working with a variety of internationally known artists such as Nas, Ray Ruiz, Salaam Remi, Faith Evans, and Matchbox 20.  With an eclectic variety of influences and a broad range of well-developed talents, Robert Dante\'s music displays both intelligence and sensitivity with an infectious pop element to support its potential for mass appeal.  Inspired by the deep harmonies of THE BEATLES, the melancholic moods of SARAH MALACHLAN, and the funky, soulful nature of FIONA APPLE, Robert Dante offers a remarkably ambitious and delicious cocktail of musical taste.  His amazing vocal range and passionately melodic piano playing delivers a unique sound that both inspires and intoxicates the senses.  Robert Dante is a true artist on many levels whose talents are numerous, and whose potential is limitless.<br/><br/>Check out the video:<br/></span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: black;\"><br/>\r\n</span>\r\n<object height=\"350\" width=\"425\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/d_92AFcBIs4\"/><param name=\"wmode\" value=\"transparent\"/><embed \r\nsrc=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/d_92AFcBIs4\" \r\ntype=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" wmode=\"transparent\" width=\"425\" \r\nheight=\"350\"/></object><br/><br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=28\">Join Robert Dante\'s discussion</a><br/>',0,'',0,''),(390,408,'Slowest Train in the World',1,17,'','912 Riverside Drive','','You should probably listen to this alone, with headphones, in a fetal position, under a table, in the dark. There are some strange stories around this band which in some strange and mysterious way predicted the events of 9/11. The fact that this album is of middle-eastern influence may or may not have had an influence on the visions of terror yet to come, but the music is full of life, love, loss, depression, and most every other emotion you can muster.<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=46\">Join Slowest Train in the World\'s discussion</a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(395,413,'Psychostasia',1,16,'http://psychostasiarock.com','','+52 (376) 762-0403','<strong><span>About Psychostasia</span></strong> \r\n<p>\r\n<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Back in the early &lsquo;90s, three American musicians headed south of the border &mdash; packing little more than their instruments, their rocker attitude and a sense of adventure. These three guys have now spent more than a decade in the high Sierra Madre mountains of Mexico, honing their skills and defining what they believe in, while absorbing the music, language and culture of their latin friends. <br />\r\n</span><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; After many years of friendship, jam sessions, and performing every genre imaginable in other groups, Psychostasia came together in January 2007...three Mexicanized American rockers and one Mexican drummer with a passion for ROCK. That&rsquo;s Psychostasia.</span> <br />\r\n<strong><span><br />\r\nPsychostasia&rsquo;s songs...</span></strong>&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; No single song epitomizes Psychostasia&rsquo;s sound. You get sweet riffs (a la Floyd) one minute and a raw and ruthless adrenaline rush (Metallica-esque) the next. <br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Melodies and lyrics reflect modern-day conflicts and challenges ... realism infused with a dose of optimism. Expect a lot of ups and downs, multiple textures, rhythm changes, and climactic endings,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; According to the band, &quot;The tracks are raw and potent, from the cradle to the grave. We go for VIBE rather than technical perfection.&quot;<br />\r\n</span>\r\n</p>\r\n<span></span>\r\n<p>\r\n<strong><span><img src=\"../uploads/413/07-PsychostasiaGroup.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" width=\"346\" height=\"241\" align=\"bottom\" /><br />\r\nFAQs Answered by the Band</span></strong> <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><em><span>Q. </span></em></strong><span><em>What does Psychostasia mean?</em></span> <br />\r\n<strong><span>A. </span></strong><span>&ldquo;We get asked this a lot. Psychostasia is an ancient Greek word referring to a spiritual plane where souls are weighed prior to battle to determine each combatant&rsquo;s worthiness. The word just seemed to parallel real life, so we went with it. Also, everything else seemed to already be taken!&rdquo;</span> <br />\r\n<strong><em><span><br />\r\nQ. </span></em></strong><em><span>What is the biggest challenge in promoting your band?<br />\r\n</span></em><strong><span>A. </span></strong><span>&ldquo;Probably the same thing that has made our music different ... isolation from the world music scene, so our songs come from inside us.&nbsp;And thanks to the web and sites like Best of Bands, even a group from a tiny <em>pueblo</em> in Mexico is able to&nbsp;reach out.&rdquo;</span> <br />\r\n<strong><span><br />\r\nFavorite Quote, according to the Band:<br />\r\n</span></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <span>&ldquo;At the moment, Beno Albarran, host of Channel 2 / Televisa&rsquo;s <em>Leyendas del Rock</em> (Rock Legends) program, who recently called Psychostasia &lsquo;the best rock group in Mexico.&rsquo; That meant a LOT to us!&rdquo;</span> <br />\r\n<strong><span><br />\r\nBIO: Daniel Cordero</span></strong><span> (Lead singer, rhythm guitar, keyboards)<br />\r\n</span><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Zodiac Sign: Libra</span> <br />\r\n<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Favorite Hobby: Inventing</span> <br />\r\n<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Heroes: Bob Marley, Steven Tyler </span><span><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Philosophy: I&rsquo;ll live while I&rsquo;m alive and sleep</span> <br />\r\n<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; when I&rsquo;m dead!</span> <br />\r\n<img src=\"../uploads/413/08-PsychostasiaBioDan.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" width=\"252\" height=\"256\" align=\"bottom\" /><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',\'serif\'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; When not playing in Psychostasia, Daniel performs solo at restaurants, bars and special events, singing originals and all-time rock, blues, reggae and latin favorites in both Spanish and English &mdash; using a classical electric acoustic guitar.<span>&nbsp; </span>Songs from his 2006 unplugged album can be heard at <u><span style=\"color: blue\"><a href=\"http://www.danielcordero.com/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.danielcordero.com/</a></span></u>.</span> <br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',\'serif\'\">Although hearing impaired, Dan plays ten instruments and is one of those rare and gifted individuals who can &ldquo;feel&rdquo; the vibrations of sound. It is this special ability which led him to explore the dynamics of sound frequencies and their effect on the human body, mind and psyche. <br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',\'serif\'\">Daniel&rsquo;s passion is music. He loves to perform &mdash; which he invariably is asked to do wherever he goes &mdash; so much so that during performances he must usually be reminded to take a break every few hours. Daniel is very laid-back and mellow off-stage. Onstage, he transforms into a compelling, dynamic performer.<br />\r\n</span><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',\'serif\'\"><br />\r\nBIO: David Cordero</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',\'serif\'\"> (Lead guitar &amp; harmonies)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',\'serif\'\">Zodiac Sign:<span>&nbsp; </span>Scorpio<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',\'serif\'\">Favorite Hobby:<span>&nbsp; </span>Design, Writing<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',\'serif\'\">Heroes:<span>&nbsp; </span>Joe Satriani, Slash, SRV, Jimmy Page<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',\'serif\'\">Philosophy:<span>&nbsp; </span>The &ldquo;Golden Rule&rdquo;</span> <br />\r\n<img src=\"../uploads/413/09-PsychostasiaBioDavid.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" width=\"248\" height=\"252\" align=\"bottom\" /><br />\r\n<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; David brought his electric guitar across the border, and devoted every spare moment to exploring its possibilities. His favorite pasttime is what he calls &ldquo;noodling&rdquo;... experimenting with different sounds, chords, and techniques.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span>In 1995, David and brother Daniel started an in-house recording studio. Over the years in their adobe-walled home studio, the brothers have recorded numerous jingles, commercials, and bands in a variety of genres.</span> <br />\r\n<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; David is a graphic designer and certified Photoshop expert. Most of Psychostasia&lsquo;s design work is done by him. </span><span><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Off-stage, David might be seen as the most serious member.However, anyone who has seen him get down and party can tell you that impression is deceiving!</span> <span><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; On-stage, David definitely puts the introverted, serious image to rest with body contortions and flying, waist-length hair. He throws himself into his performances, playing for sheer enjoyment, and it&rsquo;s payoff time for all those hours spent &ldquo;noodling.&rdquo;</span> <br />\r\n<strong><span><br />\r\nBIO: Bryan James</span></strong><span>(Bass, vocals)</span> <br />\r\n<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Zodiac Sign: Leo</span> <br />\r\n<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Favorite&nbsp; Hobby:Video editing</span> <br />\r\n<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Heroes: Flip Nicholson, George W. Bush (NOT!)</span> <br />\r\n<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Philosophy: If there&rsquo;s grass on the field, play ball!</span> <br />\r\n<img src=\"../uploads/413/10-PsychostasiaBioBryan.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" width=\"248\" height=\"253\" align=\"bottom\" /><br />\r\n<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bryan</span><span> is the youngest member of Psychostasia, but also the one with the most performing experience. Tall, blonde and long-haired, Bryan is often mistaken for a 3rd Cordero brother, until one sees those baby blue eyes.</span> <br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <span>Born in Colorado, Bryan has lived most of his life in Mexico. At the age of only four, Bryan began appearing with the house band in the family nightclub. &ldquo;I remember playing a 1979 Gibson Les Paul that weighed more than me.&rdquo; he says, &ldquo;I could only make it through about four songs before I had to sit down.&rdquo; <br />\r\n</span><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Today, Bryan plays multiple instruments and owns a music store / recording studio where he gives lessons and helps his students start bands of their own. <br />\r\n</span><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Offstage, Bryan is spontaneous and outgoing. He cracks jokes, and makes no bones about liking the girls. Onstage, he plays a mean bass with great moves.</span> <strong><span><br />\r\n<br />\r\nBIO: Diego Rivera</span></strong><span> (Drums)</span> <br />\r\n<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Zodiac Sign: Libra</span> <br />\r\n<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Favorite Hobby: Painting &amp; drawing</span> <br />\r\n<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Heroes: John Bonham, my mom </span><span><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Philosophy: Keep it simple and real!</span> <br />\r\n<img src=\"../uploads/413/11-PsychostasiaBioDiego.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" width=\"248\" height=\"252\" align=\"bottom\" /><br />\r\n<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Diego is the oldest of (gulp!) 12 siblings born in Jalisco to a multi-generational family of accomplished musicians. By age 13, he was already playing in established bands.</span> <br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <span>Off-stage, Diego is humble, but always the jokester.On-stage he is deadly serious and doesn&rsquo;t hesitate to get flamboyantly wild. He has been known to dye his hair any color, cut or style it in whatever crazy look he&rsquo;s into at the moment, pierce anything, and twirl and toss his drumsticks with skillful abandon.</span> <br />\r\n<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Like his namesake, one of Mexico&rsquo;s most famous painters, Psychostasia&rsquo;s Diego is a talented artist; his murals can be seen in public plazas and businesses around the area.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</span><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Diego helps support his family by giving drum lessons at Bryan&rsquo;s music store/studio and as an electrical contractor. He is the true athlete of the group, giving him almost unlimited stamina when on Psychostasia&rsquo;s drum throne. <br />\r\n</span><strong><span><br />\r\nFor more on Psychostasia, check out:</span></strong> <br />\r\n<a href=\"http://www.psychostasiarock.com\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.psychostasiarock.com<br />\r\n</a><a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/psychostasia\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.myspace.com/psychostasia</a> \r\n</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<object classid=\"clsid:6BF52A52-394A-11D3-B153-00C04F79FAA6\" codebase=\"http://activex.microsoft.com/activex/controls/mplayer/en/nsmp2inf.cab#Version=5,1,52,701\" name=\"MediaPlayer1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\">\r\n	<param name=\"name\" value=\"MediaPlayer1\" />\r\n	<param name=\"width\" value=\"1\" />\r\n	<param name=\"height\" value=\"1\" />\r\n	<param name=\"src\" value=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/uploads/413/PSYCHOSUB-01.WMV\" />\r\n	<param name=\"url\" value=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/uploads/413/PSYCHOSUB-01.WMV\" />\r\n	<param name=\"url\" value=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/uploads/413/PSYCHOSUB-01.WMV\" />\r\n	<param name=\"pluginspage\" value=\"http://www.microsoft.com/Windows/MediaPlayer\" />\r\n	<param name=\"autostart\" value=\"false\" />\r\n	<embed type=\"application/x-mplayer2\" name=\"MediaPlayer1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/uploads/413/PSYCHOSUB-01.WMV\" pluginspage=\"http://www.microsoft.com/Windows/MediaPlayer\" autostart=\"false\"></embed>\r\n</object>\r\n<a name=\"video\" title=\"video\"></a><br />\r\n&nbsp; <br />\r\n<div>\r\n<object classid=\"clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000\" codebase=\"http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0\" width=\"425\" height=\"350\">\r\n	<param name=\"width\" value=\"425\" />\r\n	<param name=\"height\" value=\"350\" />\r\n	<param name=\"src\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/vUNa6DWHhQs\" />\r\n	<embed type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" width=\"425\" height=\"350\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/vUNa6DWHhQs\"></embed>\r\n</object>\r\n</div>\r\n',1,'',1,'http://www.cdpulse.com/artist/page/Psychostasia/Inside+The+Mirror/1'),(838,1011,'Guitars Dont Fly',1,0,'www.myspace.com/guitarsdontfly','','','<p>Guitars DonÃ¯Â¿Â½t Fly. Its true. Try throwing one and you\'ll see that\r\nol\' Isaac Newton was right. Just ask Scotty (but be prepared to have to\r\nwipe away his tears of sadnessÃ¯Â¿Â½itÃ¯Â¿Â½s a long story) </p>\r\n<p>Anyway, back to business. </p>\r\n<p>The Guitars which Do Not Fly of this story, are a 5 piece band which\r\nhails from the sunny town of Alexandria. Sunny? Well, more like grey\r\nand depressing- but that description wouldn\'t really get you to come\r\nlook at our site would it? </p>\r\n<p>Currently we\'ve been together for about&nbsp;2 years, playing and\r\npracticing out of Beatts Inc studio, which is down near Polaroid for\r\nyou yokals and in the Vale of Leven Industrial Estate for the Rest Of\r\nThe World (getting a bit optimistic there thinking anyone from the Rest\r\nOf The World will be reading this, but you never know) </p>\r\n<p>We\'re trying to avoid getting into the rut of performing covers and\r\nhave been writing our own stuff since we got together. Currently we\r\nhave&nbsp;a load of *finished* tracks (the list of unfinished grows ever\r\nlarger by the day, fuelled by Andys bitterness at lost loves and anger\r\nat nothing). We\'d like to say that we sound like some other well known\r\nbands, we really would, but the truth of the matter is, they sound like\r\nus. No, really. They stole all our ideas. We came up with them first.\r\nHonest. </p>\r\n<p>Well thatÃ¯Â¿Â½s our story for the copyright lawsuits anyway. </p>\r\n<p>The band consists of Andy (trying to be lead vocal), Scotty (just\r\ntrying), Captain (percussion- er, drums), Bones (*probably* the only\r\none with any talent amongst us) and Richie (*really* the only one with\r\ntalent amongst us). With our power combined, we should really be\r\nrunning the country by now, but alas, Blair still manages to win the\r\nelections. How, we donÃ¯Â¿Â½t know. </p>\r\n<p>Oh and if anyone mentions a connection with the names of the band\r\nmembers and Star Trek, expect violence. Its purely coincidental. No\r\nreally, it is. </p>\r\n<p>Well, if your still reading this (is anyone still reading this?),\r\nthen you should really have a listen to the tracks. They\'re not bad.</p>\r\nAnyway go and listen to the songs! ThatÃ¯Â¿Â½s why your really here, right!?\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=204\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Guitars Dont Flys fans</span></a><br/>\r\n ',1,'',0,''),(839,1012,'High 5s All Round',1,68,'www.myspace.com/high5sallround','2 holliday close','07934647901','<p align=\"justify\">Hi there! </p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">We are High 5s All Round a 4 piece punk rock band from Bury St Edmunds England. We have been together for about a year and a half and have written a full album of 12 songs, most of which have been recorded in some way but only 6 have been recorded proffesionally on our self titled E.P. We are greatly influenced by American pop/rock/punk bands like The All-American rejects, Yellowcard, Sum 41 and Blink 182 and these influances ae reflected in our music! </p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">Our band name \"High 5s All Round\" came from a drunken chant one of our friends started to yell at a party, we thought it was cool and It stuck. </p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">We hope you like our music as much as we enjoy playing it! </p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">High 5s All Round!....... </p>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=205\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with High 5s All Round\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(841,1018,'Undone',1,71,'www.rockwithundone.com','','','<strong>We are currently looking for record companies and booking agents. If you like what you hear please contact us. <br/><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Thanks, Undone</strong><br/>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=206\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Undone\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1194,1491,'A.D.D.',1,14,'http://www.addloud.com','','','<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" color=\"#640606\">Today&#39;s audiences are searching for something fresh...something new...something different...<strong>A.D.D.</strong>, from humble Lockport, IL welcomes this challenge and gives rock fans hope of what&#39;s been missing in today&#39;s cookie-cutter world of music. This quintet, led by Margaret Young&#39;s words of real-life&#39;s hopes and failures, covers a cross-section of influences from the 70&#39;s to the present. As heard on their 7 song CD, produced by Tadpole (3 Doors Down, Disturbed), their mix of lyrical passion and superb musicianship, make for a great recipe for success.</font><font color=\"#993300\"><br />\r\n</font><br />\r\n<a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=292\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt\">Interact with A.D.D.&#39;s fans</span></a> \r\n',1,'<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" color=\"#800000\">Margaret Young - Vocals<br />\r\nDave Adams - Guitar<br />\r\nJeremy Sparta - Guitar/Vocals<br />\r\nRandy Berg - Bass<br />\r\nRon Bailey - Drums</font> \r\n',0,''),(430,447,'March Across The Graves',7,36,'myspace.com/marchacrossthegraves','','','We\'re a Metal Band from Jersey.<br/>\r\nWe have a vocalist: Jon<br/>\r\nTwo guitarists: Chris(guitar1) Jeff (guitar2)<br/>\r\nA bassist: Georg<br/>\r\nand a Drummer: Alex<br/>\r\n<hr style=\"width: 100%; height: 2px;\">We are currently looking for shows to play in the jersey philli area so if any body knows about some tell us so we can play.<br/>\r\nThanks,<span style=\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\"> <span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">Stay METAL<br/><br/><br/></span><a style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 255);\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=19\">Join the March Across The Graves discussion</a><br/></span>',1,'',0,''),(419,431,'Kimmy Jo Country',8,37,'www.kimmyjocountry.com','502 E. Cherry St.','618-643-3740','I have been back on the stage for three years solid. I love it! This is my job. It is not a nine to five job, it is twenty-four/seven. I was given this talent at birth. It is passed down from my dad, he is the original rocker. When music is born into you it is different from being learned. I am not saying it is any less or any more, but you can not deny what is in your body, mind, and soul. You can not put it down and pick it up when you feel like it. My mom would tell me stories of when my dad would have jam sessions at our house (when she was pregnant with me) and I would not stop jumping around inside her. I suppose that reflects my on stage performance. I am an entertainer, very energetic where there is music I can\'t sit still. I want the audience to leave with a smile on their face and wondering where I will be next. It\'s not about the traveling, it\'s not about the money, it is about the next show and the performance. It is where I can best convey my feeling and love for music. My musical experiences growing up vary from both ends of the spectrum. My mom would listen to traditional country, and my dad played southern rock. I soon developed my own favorites ranging from Barbra Streisand, Frank Sintra, Nat King Cole, to Gun\'s N Roses, Poison, to The Judd\'s, and of course Garth Brooks. My voice has been described as versatile, so the question has been asked many times,why country? I am country! I was raised and still live in a small town in Southern Illinois. It is what I know. The lyrics and melodies of every country song are familiar to me. I can relate to all of the songs on country radio. I\'ve either seen it, heard it, or done it. Some of the songs are so clever that I laugh out loud. That is the type of music I want to put out there. When you hear it, you know it, cause you\'ve lived it. I have a husband, and a daughter. They too, have a love for music. We have yet to see all of my daughters music abilities but they are there. My entire family supports my music career 100%. My mom had me in the studio recording a demo at age thirteen. Of course at thirteen it\'s is more their decision than yours. You come to learn though, they have your best interest at heart. I have won numerous awards, and talent shows. I was in choir in school and sang in church. I have been in many Country Showdowns, and performed all over the US. In the summer of 2005 I opened for Buddy Jewell, and last summer I was invited to do the Taste Of Chicago, and performed in front of a crowd of 10-15,000 people. I opened for Phil Vasser, Jo Dee Messina, and Shedaisy. It has been the highlight of my career thus far. As I continue on my journey, there are ups and downs. I continue my trips back and forth to Nashville to try and soak up as much knowledge as I can. I have met so many interesting people that travel the same road, we all have a dream that we are striving to make a reality. Being from a small town, a dry county, population 2500, a town well away from any major city, I SIT. The internet, the phone, and snail mail are my tools. Why would I pick this dream? For love, for passion, and maybe I\'m a little crazy. It\'s my music, my most passionate form of communication to those around me. I am not alone, we are an army. Performers in small towns everywhere. To our right and to our left are those who believe in us. Those whom we trust to tell us we are doing this for the right reasons. Why when there are so many searching for that #1 hit and break into the music biz, why would we pursue this dream, day after day, relentlessly? Because we love it, its our life, it is born into us. We eat, sleep, and drink lyrics and melodies. I wouldn\'t trade it for anything, and there are a lot easier roads to take. There\'s room, if you have enough determination and persistence to shove your way in. I am a performer--make room! Kimmy Jo<br/><br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=18\" target=\"_blank\">Join the Kimmy Jo Country discussion</a>',1,'',0,''),(436,454,'ADEPT',7,33,'www.adeptnmm.com','3606 s scatterfield rd','317-525-3855','We are four guys from Anderson,Indiana who over the last five years have honed our skills and created what we believe to be great melodic in your face metal, We are ready to take the next step in the evolution of our band. We are professional, energetic and determined to set the music world on fire........<br/><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ADEPT<br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=16\" target=\"_blank\">Join the Adept discussion</a>',1,'',0,''),(427,440,'Audio Weapon',7,84,'http://audioweapon.com','','','<p>\r\nAudio Weapon has risen from the dark forest foothills of the New Hampshire White Mountains.&nbsp; All through these years, never satisfied with playing others music, I took on the need of being the mad composer, writting, refining&nbsp;abilities and direction of tastes.&nbsp; With a unique approach has fused the styles of progessive, metal, and hard rock to form a different and&nbsp;unique take on composing music. <br />\r\nAll aspects of the production are controlled by &quot;AUDIO WEAPON&quot;. From the initial concept of melodies and rythms to the recording, mixing and post production. No fancy studios or aid or desire for the presentation of perfection in sound. Music in it&#39;s being and instincts are imperfect as with the human existance. It is heard exactly as it was recorded with all the imperfections that make it a truly human experience of unseen art. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<br />\r\nRobert - Five, Six, and Seven-String Guitars,<br />\r\nSynths, Percussion, and Vocals. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=17\" target=\"_blank\">Audio Weapon Forum Discussion<br />\r\n</a>\r\n</p>\r\n<br />\r\n',0,'',0,''),(439,456,'Autumn',9,41,'www.myspace.com/autumnsongs.com','408 Warren','501-831-6884','I&nbsp;have been singing since I was 11. I have been in many talent contests. I tried out for All-Region and All-State and made it. After high school I performed here locally with a band called Alphabet Soup, performing top40 hits. I wanted to create my own songs so I hooked up with a wonderful, talented musician named Rob Perry owner of Hound Sound Productions and we wrote together and made 2 cd\'s.1 is available on houndsound.biz where I perform Adult Contemporary music,Jazz, Blues and Pop.<br/>I then hooked up with a local artist Clint G, a rap artist, and have been performing with him locally here for about 4 months now. I am producing a R&B cd now but it will not be released until next year. I write all my lyrics and melodies but I get the beats from variouse artists.<br/><br/>Here is a song for year 2007. Hope you like it.<br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=15\" target=\"_blank\">Check out my forum thread!</a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(440,457,'Miles of Empty',1,61,'www.myspace.com/milesofempty','325 North Maple','773-459-6544','\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n<br/><br/><table style=\"width: 503px; height: 431px;\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"border: medium none rgb(236, 233, 216); padding: 0in; width: 377.25pt; background-color: transparent;\" width=\"503\">\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Verdana;\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Garamond;\">Miles of Empty is a Chicago born alternative rock trio in the sonic arena of STP and Foo Fighters, and although classified in this genre, the group is hardly typical of it. You don\'t have to dig deep to reveal the band\'s unique qualities, and simply listening to the CD or catching a live show will do that.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Garamond;\">Miles of Empty\'s retains a sound all its own. The bands live sound is every bit as powerful and polished as its studio sound, and performing live is really where the band exceeds your expectations for a three-piece act.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>Fans will confirm, \"you can\'t believe this much music comes from only three musicians!\" <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Garamond;\">Miles of Empty formed in 2000 and is comprised of Mario Kaehn on vocals and guitar, James Kaehn on bass, and Carlo Cooper on drums. Answering an ad from a drummer looking for a \"serious band\", the Kaehns met up with Carlo. After two jam sessions,<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>\"we all decided this was a winning union,\" said James. Miles of Empty is currently working on new music that will be released &#8220;digitally&#8221; this Spring of 2007. </span><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Verdana;\"><span style=\"\">&nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></span></p><br/><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><br/></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=29\">Join Miles of Empty\'s discussion</a><br/><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Verdana;\"></span></p></td></tr></tbody></table></div>',1,'',0,''),(441,458,'Outspoken',1,68,'www.myspace.com/outspokenrock','41 Robb Drive','6472806552','\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText\" style=\"text-indent: 0.5in; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Outspoken consists of four members: Alex (Drums,\r\nPercussion), Justin (Lead Guitar, Harmonizer) Fab (Bass), and Anthony (Guitar,\r\nVocals). We as Outspoken have been a band since we can remember. Having the\r\nnotion in elementary school (grade six to be exact) we wanted this to work. We\r\nstarted off with a guitar in Anthony\'s bedroom, a fake drum set and maracas. We\r\nwanted it so much that we did anything (ditch friends, families&#8212;at times,\r\ngirlfriends, etc). And guess what happened? Eventually, as we grew as friends,\r\npartners, and musicians, our music, equipment, priorities and musical ability\r\ngot stronger and better. This led to our first signing with Mushroom\r\nProductions (our first Indie label). Now, here we are today in the year 2007\r\ndoing what we love while growing and learning in trying to turn this dream into\r\na reality. With self-booked tours and shows past and present, we bring it all\r\nto the table. We finally realized we were one step closer to this dream when we\r\ngot the opportunity to open up for much lager bands such as The New Cities, Surplus\r\nSons, The Pettit Project, Socialight and Cauterize. During the process we have\r\nreleased one demo, and a new album (full-length) in the works. In March we\r\nembarked on a mini tour of shows across Ontario and the Eastern parts of\r\nCanada.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText\" style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">There\r\nis nothing more or less to say rather than wanting to make history with you\r\nall. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText\" style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><!--[if !supportEmptyParas]-->&nbsp;<!--[endif]--><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText\" style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Thank\r\nyou for your time and consideration.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText\" style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><!--[if !supportEmptyParas]-->&nbsp;<!--[endif]--><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText\" style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Outspoken,</span></p><br/><p class=\"MsoBodyText\" style=\"line-height: 150%;\"></p><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=26\">Join the Outspoken discussion</a><br/><p class=\"MsoBodyText\" style=\"line-height: 150%;\"></p><br/>',1,'',0,''),(1908,459,'120 DECIBELS',1,14,'www.myspace.com/thenew120decibels','','','',1,'',0,''),(471,510,'DARKSEID',1,14,'http://www.myspace.com/darkseidband','','','<p>\r\n<strong><font face=\"helvetica\" size=\"3\">DARKSEID IS A HARD ROCK BAND FROM OUTSIDE OSLO, NORWAY. THE BAND WAS ORIGINALLY FORMED AND ENDED DURING THE 1990&#39;S. IN THIS PERIOD, THE BAND RELEASED AN ALBUM CALLED &quot; A NEW DAY RISING &quot;.<br />\r\nDARKSEID WAS STARTED ONCE AGAIN IN 2006. WITH IMPROVED QUALITY ON THE SONG WRITING AND LIVE SHOWS, DARKSEID IS NOW A MORE COMPLETE BAND THAT IT EVER HAS BEEN!<br />\r\n</font></strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<p>\r\n<a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=47\" target=\"_blank\">Join DARKSEID&#39;s discussion</a> \r\n</p>\r\n',1,'<h4>Mr.Forest : Rythm and lead vocals <br />\r\nS.H.Castillo : Drums<br />\r\nThunder Thor : Bass and backing vocals<br />\r\nZiggy : Lead guitars<br />\r\n</h4>\r\n',0,''),(473,512,'Jonah Brockman',1,61,'www.jonahbrockman.com','PO Box 147','','<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=48\">Join Jonah\'s discussion</a><br/>',0,'',0,''),(443,460,'Dame',1,76,'http://www.myspace.com/dameband','','416-705-dame','<strong>Dame, recently seen on Entertainment Tonight Canada, &nbsp;is a bone-crushing rock trio with big choruses, hard- hitting guitar riffs and power-house vocals. At 15, and 17 ears of age, their playing and songwriting is more than mature: It kicks ass. <br />\r\nRecommended if you like Audioslave with chunks of Iron Maiden.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</strong><strong>REVIEWS</strong><br />\r\n&quot;I listen to a lot of music... She can sing!&quot; <br />\r\n<em>George Stroumboulopoulos. THE HOUR -CBC</em> <br />\r\n<br />\r\n&#39;As far as I&#39;m concerned their age and gender doesn&#39;t factor into the overall equation. They can play, sing, and write as good if not better than most acts in their musical genre. These guys(?) rock!&quot;<br />\r\n<em>Greg Godovitz. CFRB ROCK RADIO, founder of Goddo<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</em>&quot;This band can seriously lay down a groove and kick out some serious sound with ease. IF there is a young band out there today that can thrust women into the spotlight in the rock scene it will be Dame!&quot; <br />\r\n<em>Bob Donovan, www.indieintune.com </em><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&quot;It&#39;s not often that a band or vocalist can perform live and so closely imitate their studio recordings. But Dame managed to do just that, so I was blown away, especially by Katee&#39;s vocal prowess - what a set of pipes!!! These girls have it all - energy, personality, and most of all, raw talent.&quot;<br />\r\n<em>Laurie Lonsdale, journalist, TORONTO EXCLUSIVE MAGAZINE, author WILD SIDE<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</em>Damesm song INTERVENTION cleaned up with with Rock reviewers songs of the week for last week of 2007. And Best OVERALL for the site for Best Female Vocals and Best Lyrics. AWESOME<br />\r\n<br />\r\nGARAGEBAND.COM AWARDS<br />\r\nIntervention - TRACK OF THE DAY Dec 25 2007<br />\r\nCyclops - TRACK OF THE DAY Feb 5 2008<br />\r\n<br />\r\nINTERVENTION GARAGEBAND AWARDS<br />\r\nTrack of the Day on 25Dec2007 in Progressive Rock<br />\r\n<strong>Best Female Vocals overall</strong>, week of 31Dec2007<br />\r\nBest Female Vocals in Progressive Rock, week of 31Dec2007<br />\r\nBest Guitars in Progressive Rock, week of 31Dec2007<br />\r\nBest Drums in Progressive Rock, week of 31Dec2007<br />\r\nBest Bass in Progressive Rock, week of 31Dec2007