on numerous Mixtapes & DVDs. This young man has worked hard at becoming the best at what he does. So when you meet him for the first time its no wonder why people fall in love with him. UniQuE was Born Christopher Morton In Atlantic City NJ. At a early age UniQuE began to display a strong interest in entertainment so at the tender age of 5yr his mother enter him in a school play. By the time UniQuE enter middle school Hip hop, Gospel, R&B,& music in general began to play a big part in his life. By the time UniQuE was to go into High School he began Writing & Singing music. During this time UniquE was introduced to all different styles of music and he began singing in groups. Tired of what direction the group was going UniQue began to come up with a style of music all his own. After leaving the group UniQuE set to develop his own brand of music witch most people call Street but Sweat. He took all the styles of all the music he enjoyed & his great ability of story telling & Songwriting to put together his first CD title: \" Point Of No Return . This CD outlines the things UniQuE has seen & some of the things he\'s been through in life. This Cd is a testimony & a new beginning for UniQuE.<br/><br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=34\">Join Unique\'s discussion</a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(455,475,'Stone Marmot',1,61,'www.stonemarmot.com','','','Our music is the result of not watching TV for over 25 straight years.<br/><br/>That\'s right! The person who writes all our songs hasn\'t had a working television in his house since January, 1982. Scary, isn\'t it! That could explain the somewhat retro, rather experimental feel to the music, which has been described as sounding somewhere between Buddy Holly, The Ramones, The B-52s, and They Might Be Giants. This CD is an object lesson in how warped and depraved a television-starved mind can get.<br/><br/>And that\'s not all! To make matters worse, since no self-respecting human would stoop low enough to play this stuff, he suckered four poor, innocent cartoon characters into recording his music. Cartoon characters have it tough enough as it is, with people laughing at them all the time, without having to be subjected to this! His poor, unfortunate victims, who refer to themselves collectively as Stone Marmot, are:<br/><br/>Cindy: Guitars<br/>Sid: Keyboards, guitars, lead and backup vocals<br/>Sammy: Bass, lead and backup vocals<br/>Bruce: Percussion, backup vocals<br/><br/>This quartet played their little paper hearts out as the ignoble fiend who created them and their music practically produced and engineered them to death. Therefore, for the sake of the cartoons, we hope you give their music a good listen and try to appreciate their tireless and selfless efforts.<br/><br/>Please! Don\'t let this happen to you or someone you love! Be sure you and your loved ones receive a healthy minimum dose of television each and every day.<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=49\">Join Stone Marmot\'s discussion</a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(456,477,'ONOFFON',11,92,'www.onoffon.com/','12059 Hoffman St. #104','8187607607','<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=50\">Join OnOffOn\'s discussion</a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(457,461,'Terell',9,44,'www.DATBoyzent.com','PO Box 3216','732 221 5616','\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify;\">A classic sound capturing the essence of Marvin Gaye, Stevie Wonder, and Donny Hathaway combined with angelic harmonies, hypnotic melodies and heartfelt vocal delivery.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify;\">He comes from a family of vocal and instrumental musicians and was first discovered by producer Vincent Herbert of 3 Boyz from <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Newark</st1:place></st1:city>.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify;\">By the time he turned 14, he appeared on several recordings and signed a contract with Whitney Houston&#8217;s label, Better Place Records.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify;\">Terell&#8217;s extensively studied the artistic points of classical music, gospel, pop, and R&B music styles over the years.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify;\">Terell completed his first professional recording at the age of 10, singing background vocals for Hi-Five under the name Little Anthony Carr on the song &#8220;Fly Away&#8221;. He later appeared in Hi-Five&#8217;s Greatest Hits album on the song, &#8220;That Was Then, This Is Now&#8221;.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify;\">At age 11, he appeared on Me-2-U&#8217;s self-titled debut album singing background vocals on the song &#8220;Me-2-U&#8221;.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify;\">Perhaps his greatest experience comes through his working with pop sensation Whitney Houston. He spent most of his summer break between eight and ninth grads on the road with <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Houston</st1:place></st1:city>, and the opportunity to work on vocal arrangements for his own music presented itself while signed to her label.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify;\">Terell&#8217;s musical talents are fine-tuned as the result of years of practice, starting early in life when he wrote song lyrics in a journal, transforming them into today&#8217;s life-inspired &#8220;Love of a Lifetime&#8221; EP, released 2001, &#8220;Love of a Lifetime Special Edition&#8221;, released 2006, and &#8220;Mission: Education The Demo&#8221;, released 2006.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify;\">Terell has also reached a Top 3 rating in the Dick Clark Presents the Coca Cola New Music Award Competition in 2002 and returned the following year as Top 10.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify;\">&#8220;Havin&#8217; &#8216;U &#8216;Round&#8221; has been placed in Microsoft&#8217;s 2003 release of Project &#8220;Gotham Racing 2&#8221; for xBox.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify;\">After making Top 10, Terell returned to <st1:state w:st=\"on\">New Jersey</st1:state> to find himself invited to compete in <st1:state w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">California</st1:place></st1:state> at the World Championships of Performing Arts where he walked away with two gold medals and one silver medal.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify;\">Along with his family, Terell credits his idols Marvin Gaye, Stevie Wonder, Donny Hathaway, Shawn Stockman of Boyz II Men, 112, Faith Evans, Karen Clark, Rashaan Patterson, Craig David, Tevin Campbell, Marc Anthony, and Evanescence as some of many sources of musical inspiration, but he labels Kenny Lattimore as his most influential male artist idol.</p><br/><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify;\"></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: justify;\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=51\">Join Terell\'s discussion</a><br/></p>',1,'',0,''),(458,421,'The WestSide Kings',5,25,'www.myspace.com/The WestSideKings','','','<a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=52\" target=\"_blank\">Join The WestSide King\'s discussion</a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(460,479,'Irreverents',1,75,'myspace.com/irreverents','2230 Ontario St','778-329-6613','<div class=\"datawrap\">IRREVERENTS - Their\r\nguitars, bass, and lyrical prowess combine into a lethal blend of\r\ncontagious power-pop-rock that explodes with thunder and currently has\r\nthe band scoring as Top 20 Finalists in CFox\'s Vancouver Seeds\r\ncompetition! Compared favorably with bands like The Foo Foo Fighters,\r\nQueens of Stone Age, Sound Garden and The Red Hot Chillipeppers, the\r\nband is influenced By bands like Rage Against Machine, Box Car Racer,\r\nRed Hot Chilli Peppers, The Stooges & U2.<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=53\">Join the Irreverents discussion</a><br/></div>',1,'',0,''),(461,480,'Elliot Is Getting Fatter',1,0,'www.elliotisgettingfatter.com','','','<font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: arial\">Take 4 passionate people who share the same goals and you get Elliot , wich is in my mind the person that is created when we 4 come together to create and play music. We are still young and have still alot to learn , there for Elliot is getting fatter.<br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=54\" target=\"_blank\">Join Elliot\'s discussion</a><br/></span></font>',1,'',0,''),(462,481,'underbelly',7,33,'www.myspace.com/underbellypa','3252 BridlePath Lane','215-884-4606','Underbelly is a five-piece female fronted hard rock/metal band Underbelly has been together since March, 2001, and in just a short time , We have played the Electric Factory with the Misfits. It was a benefit show,(Children with Aids in America). Right now our music can be heard on one of the top radio stations in the country, 94.1 wysp Philadelphia. Radio personalities and fans have responded exceptionally well to us. Underbelly believes in giving our fans all we have. Once Shawn (guitar) gave a fan the shirt off his back, just because the fan said I like your shirt . We take the time to talk to everybody and sign everything, our fans are the most important people to us. The Misfits enjoyed us so much that they gave us, all access backstage passes for their 2001/2002 25th Anniversary tour, witch includes, Dez & Robo from Black Flag as well as Marky Ramone from the world famous RAMONES. We met Megadeth for their promo tour (everybody needs a hero), as well as Metallica, and hung out with them (pictures available upon request).Thus far we have given out 400 plus cd\'s to fans as well as radio stations, management companies, agents, local and national press. Thank you for your time sincerely, UNDERBELLY. Now in 2006 UNDERBELLY is back with a new look, Some new members, Most of all a new sound. We are hell bent on making great music that most will enjoy & love. Thank you to all who have seen us in the past & wait till you see & hear what we do next.<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=55\">Join Underbelly\'s discussion</a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(465,483,'Sam Rhansum',3,0,'www.myspace.com/samrhansum','','','\r\n<p align=\"center\"><span>Sam Rhansum is a multi-threat artist.As MC, producer, trackmaker, lyricist, and club DJ&#8230; not much lies outside the realm of his capabilities.His music is already being featured on such high profile outlets as EA SPORTS, MTV, NIKE endorsed DVDs, XM Satellite Radio, Promo Only (Rhythm Radio), and the major motion picture &#8220;Prisoner&#8221; (Arclight Films).</span></p>\r\n<p align=\"center\"><span>Stylistically, Rhansum falls along the lines of Chingy, Kanye, Timbaland, and Lil&#8217; Wayne.His lyrics shine with the intelligence of Jay Z, the wordplay of Eminem, and the smart mouth of Ludacris.His tracks are certified club bangers.</span></p>\r\n<p align=\"center\"><b><span>.The following is a short list of recent career highlights:</span></b></p><b><span>- \"There Goes The Neighborhood\" featured in EA Sport\'s \"NFL STREET 3\"<br/></span></b><b><span><br/>- Music featured in MTV\'s \"Real World vs. Road Rules: Gauntlet II\"<br/></span></b><b><span><br/>- Music featured on MTV\'s \"Real World: Denver\"<br/></span></b><b><span><br/>- Co-writer and performer of end-title song in Arclight\'s upcoming</span></b><b><span>theatrical release, \"Prisoner.\" (Spring 2007)<br/></span></b><b><span><br/>- \"There Goes The Neighborhood\" featured on a PROMO ONLY Rhythm Radio CD (ONLY UNSIGNED artist on the disc).<br/></span></b><b><span><br/>- Airplay on XM Radio, after being featured on their show, \"The Futures\"(highlights XM\'s top 12 up-and-coming artists).<br/></span></b><b><span><br/>- Selected by Music Connection Magazine as one of 2006\'s TOP 25 demos<br/></span></b><b><span><br/>- Winner in Discmaker\'s 2006 \"Top 14 unsigned artists of the Southeast\" (as voted by Billboard and Taxi)</span></b> \r\n<p align=\"center\"><b><span>www.samrhansum.com</span></b></p>\r\n<p align=\"center\"><br/><b><span></span></b></p>\r\n<p style=\"TEXT-ALIGN: center\"><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=56\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Join Sams\' discussion</span></a><br/></p>',1,'',0,''),(464,482,'40 Mile Road',8,78,'www.40mileroad.com','10105 aragon','254-214-6966','<strong>Born out of Texas\'s legendary roadhouses, 40 Mile Road cut their teeth playing a mix of rock, blues, outlaw, and their own southern roots-rock. 40 Mile Road can play small to large venues with ample power and presence. Covering all of Texas as their play ground, 40 Mile Road has been billed with artists such as Mark Chestnut, Gary P. Nunn, Kritikill, Brandi Carlile, and Edgewater to name a few. 40 Mile Road has played large rallies(ex. 2006 Lonestar, the 2006 Twisted Tators Book Run et al.) to the Dallas music Fest 2005 & 2006 , a shot at Cabo 2005, as well as many notable charity functions ( 2005 Waco Cattle Barrons Ball, 2004 - present Project Angeltree benefit, Susan G Koman Walk 2006, Miracle Match Marathon 2006 et al.). Influenced by Cash, The Beatles,SRV, Willie, Waylon &the Boys, all the way to ZZ Top. 40 Mile Road is THE Texas party band. </strong><br/><!--end heading_1--><br/><font size=\"2\"><!--begin text_1--><span id=\"hide_text_1\" style=\"display: none;\"></span><span id=\"text_1_wrapper\"><span id=\"text_1\"><span><span>\r\n</span></span></span></span></font><br /><br /><a target = \"_blank\"href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=107\"><span style=\"font-size:8pt;\">Interact with 40 Mile Roads fans</span></a><br />',1,'',0,''),(509,551,'Russ Krauch',5,28,'kunaki.com/msales.asp?PublisherId=112114','','','Electronica Composer and Guitarist. Been involved in Computer Music recording for about 4 years. CD\'s released include \"Reise Durch Europa\" and \"For Duty And Humanity\".<br/><br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=57\">Join Russ\' discussion</a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(469,496,'10th Degree',1,16,'www.10thdegree.net','1776 N Sycamore ave','323 540 3172','Marco is italian but currently lives in Los Angeles. He writes Rock music, by guitars. <br/>Favorite songs are: Wanted dead or alive By Bon Jovi and Whole lotta Rosie By AC/DC. <br/>The last work is the 10th degree album called Bad dreams. www.myspace.com/10thdegree <br/>Currently he is working for the second album with the 10th degree,&nbsp; he got the hard rock top 10 on Broadjam<br/>The song Love and shadow got the LAMA nomination. <br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=58\">Join 10th Degree\'s discussion</a>',1,'',0,''),(466,467,'Kara Clark',1,66,'walkermusic.org','1512 Nuview St','615-793-4406','Kara Clark never knew that her grandfather once played and sang with the great Hank Williams Sr. nor did she know that music was part of her destiny. She was much to busy being a paramedic in Huntington West Virginia. It was only thru her entering a local singing contest where she discovered where her reals talents were. She writes as well as she sings.<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=59\">Join Kara\'s discussion</a><br/>',0,'',0,''),(467,486,'Dyonisis',1,77,'www.dyonisis.info','','','The others were arguing over which genre to inhabit... We danced out of the musical Pandora\'s Box whilst no-one was looking. Most new bands claim to have an original sound then dissapointingly re-hash the genre-du-jour. We\'ve heard it all before, and it was better the first time around. Dyonisis are a genuine breath of musical fresh air. We play with layering etherial soundscapes driven along by pulsing basslines. Two voices individual from each other, yet blending together, weaving emotion, memories and impressions into unique songs embroidered by haunting guitarlines that soar and take our music to another level. Formed in 2005 when Marcus & Lou joined the song writing duo of Tom & Nel, the band hit the live scene running, building a following and playing with the likes of Manuskript & Killing Miranda. The journey has involved ever bigger shows, alongside a number one in the Pzaaz download chart and footage on a soon to be released live DVD. Along the way the band have taken time out to record their first self titled & funded album, to be released 2007. Dyonisis - electrifying a venue near you soon...<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=60\">Join Dyonisis\' discussion</a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(470,504,'Clara Lofaro',9,43,'www.claralofaro.com','748 Glengrove Ave W','732.485.4333','<font size=\"2\">\r\n<p><!--StartFragment --> </p>\r\n<p><strong>Clara Lofaro</strong>,<strong> Winner of Indie Week Toronto 2006</strong>, is destined to become a household name as the buzz spreads about her music in the U.S. and Canada, with a charging fan base in her twin home towns of Toronto and New York City. &#8220;Influenced by artists such as Annie Lennox, Patty Griffin and Bill Withers, Lofaro&#8217;s music is hard to pigeonhole, and blends several genres including soul, rock and jazz. Her songs are laced with soulful grooves, and her vocals ooze with both vulnerability and defiance.&#8221; - <em><strong>Amanda B. Haupt</strong>, <a href=\"http://claralofaro.com/images/_clippings/METRO.pdf?id=22876\" target=\"_blank\">METRO TORONTO</a> <br/></em><br/>Lofaro now runs her own independent label, ComeTrue Records, Inc., under which she released her self-produced sophomore masterpiece, <em>Black & Blue Pearl</em>, a top-seller on CD Baby. It is currently <strong>spinning on WLIR</strong> commercial radio and college radio across the Northeast. &#8220;One True Thing&#8221; was recently chosen as <strong>&#8220;#1 Song of the Year&#8221;</strong> for 2006 on Ithaca&#8217;s 106 VIC Radio by listener poll. In 2007, CL will be performing at Bamboozle Festival at Giants Stadium. She is the<strong> voice of Disney\'s famous \"What\'s Next\" commercial</strong> airing every year after the Super Bowl for the past twenty years. Clara and her band won against 367 other bands in Toronto for Indie Music Week in October 2006.<br/><br/>Lofaro&#8217;s artistic talents and ambition earned a scholarship to the prestigious Berklee College of Music. There, musicians, producers and film composers sought after her deeply powerful vocals, songwriting ability, and charismatic personality. She wrote songs and lyrics in various styles ranging from jazz to pop to jingles. CL was a desired vocalist for session work, and played the Boston club scene with musicians like Rie Tsuji (keys, Beyonce), Mathias Kunzli (percussion, Lauryn Hill) and John Shannon (guitar, Sonya Kitchell). In college, early tracks for her first album, <em>Night Light</em> were recorded with some of the world&#8217;s best musicians. </p>\r\n<p align=\"center\">&#8220;Every once in a while, there&#8217;s a refreshing break from the monotony of Top 50 pop and Clara Lofaro is one of them.&#8221; -<em> <strong>Noah Ruede</strong>, THE AQUARIAN </em></p>\r\n<p>A musically versatile artist, she effortlessly transitions from self-penned infectious pop ditties to emotionally heavier songs during her live shows. Her songwriting style and broad range are uniquely captivating as her audience stands transfixed through an entire performance or CD listen. Lofaro truly loves her hard-won fan base, and each heartfelt performance is guaranteed to ensure they leave knowing it. </p></font><u><br/></u><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=61\">Join Clara\'s discussion</a><u><br/></u>',1,'',0,''),(475,518,'Mark of the Sage',1,14,'myspace.com/markofthesage','4100 cunningham dr','405-313-4739','Flowing like ice water through the veins of America\'s heartland, Mark of the Sage unleashes a raucous mix of revival and rebellion. With maniacally driven six-stringed chaos and a rhythm section that hits with the power of a wrecking ball yet the precision of a jeweler\'s mallet, the senses are primed for the melodic twists and turn of phrase that are equally impressive and depressive. The underlying motif of change and the need to adapt push and pull the audience through a myriad of emotions from pre-emptive surrender and submission to bloodlust and revolution. Whether on their first full length album, 2004\'s Within and Without, or their latest e.p., To Have and To Hold Down, Mark of the Sage take you on a trip down Amnesia Lane, blindfolded, at 120 mph. Angst for the memories. Mark of the Sage.<br/><br/>Join the discussion!<br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=38\" target=\"_blank\">Mark of the Sage</a>',1,'',0,''),(476,519,'malyce',1,14,'myspace.com/therealmalyce','141 balaclava st','705 653 4262','\r\n<p style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><em>Malyce is a three piece rock/alternative band hailing from Campbellford, ontario ca.<br/><br/>lead vocals/bass- sheldon renouf<br/><br/>guitars- erin sarson<br/><br/>drums/back-up vocals- dave fischer<br/><br/>To date&nbsp; we have 15 origonal songs<br/>and have just started recording our first cd release, hopefully to be available by dec 2007.<br/><br/>We have placeed 2 samples of what to expect on the upcoming cd.</em></p><p style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><br/><em></em></p><p style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=62\">Join Malyce\'s discussion</a><br/></p>',1,'',0,''),(1358,1687,'The Model Village',1,71,'www.myspace.com/themodelvillageband','48 Shakespeare Road','07948371474','<strong><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Courier New;\">Born and raised in Portsmouth, Hampshire, The Model Village strive for perfection. They ooze charisma and on-stage charm whilst focusing all the attention on the listener, making sure that every song will be loved just as much as the last.<br/><br/>If you like your music served straight and tidy, with a side dish of talent, garnished with a hearty sprig of intellect, look no further. We will deliver!</span><br/></strong><br/><a href=\"http://www.themodelvillage.net\"><strong>www.themodelvillage.net</strong></a><br/><a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/themodelvillageband\"><strong>www.myspace.com/themodelvillageband</strong></a>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=343\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with The Model Village\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1364,1694,'Mortalent Harmonoize',0,0,'www.myspace.com/mortalentharmonoize','','','',1,'',0,''),(479,522,'Don Moore',1,66,'www.Don-Moore.com','','','<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"2\">\r\n<p>Don Moore, having grown up in the 70&#8217;s in Beaver Falls, Pennsylvania, had always been a fan of the 80&#8217;s hard rock guitarists George Lynch, Chris Olivia, and Jake E. Lee. Later he was introduced to the guitar works of master solo artists such as Andy Timmons, Eric Johnson, and Joe Satriani. It was then that Don&#8217;s love for music, his respect for these musicians took over, and his passion for playing guitar evolved. </p>\r\n<p>He exploded onto the music scene in 2006 with his self-released debut album, Axe Attack. It was immediately apparent to listeners that this guy was no ordinary axe slinger, but a guitar player of great talent and melodic ability. Clearly a musician with deep emotions and respect for his guitar playing, as well as the guitar itself as an instrument. </p>\r\n<p>Don&#8217;s debut album is gaining him immediate attention and acclaim with fans and professionals in the music industry resulting in endorsements, interviews, Internet, and National airplay such as being played on national radio station The Buzz 89.9 FM in New York. </p>\r\n<p>Be sure to place Axe Attack among your top music purchases this year, you wont be sorry--you are guaranteed to be touched by his passion, moved by his inspiration, and above all, entranced in a new dimension of Guitar Wizardry.</p><br/>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=63\" target=\"_blank\">Join Don\'s discussion</a><br/></p></font>',0,'',0,''),(480,409,'tylerbernhardt',1,66,'www.myspace.com/tbernmusic','','','<br/>Tyler Bernhardt is a new and upcoming&nbsp;singer/song writer&nbsp;out of&nbsp;Fairfield, CT. His sound&nbsp;blends elements of indie rock and jazz to produce a unique&nbsp;tone all his 