 />\r\nI started playing guitar at 14 years of age and quickly decided that songwriting was what I enjoyed more than just playing other artist and band songs. I had some interest from record companies but nothing came through for me . I kept writing and playing for my own enjoyment ,then in2006 I decided to set up a home studio and write and produce my songs. I feel my music has something to offer and with the new recording tools I can now get my music out there to the listeners . I love writing ,playing and producing my songs and I hope you enjoy my efforts.\r\n',0,'',0,''),(486,532,'Dani Lee Dawson',8,38,'www.showcaseyourmusic.com/DaniLeeDawson','','','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12pt;\">If you like what you hear ,\r\nplease go to myspace and buy my songs!! www.myspace.com/danileedawson.com <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nDani was born on the outskirts of the Everglades in <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:city w:st=\"on\">Naples</st1:city> <st1:state w:st=\"on\">Florida</st1:state></st1:place>\r\non November 7th, 1984. Almost immediately she was singing before even talking.\r\nHer big debut came when performing her favorite Christmas tunes for the whole\r\nfamily around the holidays. As she grew into her teen years, Dani studied under\r\na variety of vocal instructors as well as modeling and acting classes. With a\r\ndesire to bring her talents to the next level, Dani spent some years developing\r\nher song writing and studio skills with accomplished producer and family friend\r\nJon Bainter.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12pt;\">\r\nAt seventeen nearing eighteen, Dani responded to a talent search from Collier\r\nEntertainment that involved thousands of applicants. The company that had been\r\nresponsible for major bookings in southwest <st1:state w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Florida</st1:place></st1:state> now desired to enter into artist\r\nmanagement. Her talent, looks, strong desire and commitment impressed the\r\ncompany to abandon the idea of immediately working with many artists and\r\ndecided to place all artist management efforts towards Dani.<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nIn the following year, Dani performed a variety of venues from a Clear Channel\r\nradio sponsored contest (which awarded her the privilege to open for Confederate\r\nRailroad in front of thousands of fans) as well as numerous headlining club\r\ndates. Dani also went back into the studio to have the opportunity to show\r\nothers the new material she had been collaborating on with her friend and\r\nsongwriter Robbie Quinn. She enlisted the help of many fine musicians including\r\nveteran guitarist Michael Blassucci who has accompanied the likes of Randy\r\nTravis, Ricky Van Shelton and Pam Tillis among others.<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nNow pursuing the next step of what she feels destined to do, Dani has found her\r\nnew home in <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Nashville</st1:place></st1:city>.\r\nShe feels as if a part of her has always been there waiting for the rest of her\r\nto show up. Quick to make friends, Dani has already found some loyal fans when\r\nshe has been called up on stage to perform and looks forward to meeting many\r\nmore, very soon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"color: navy;\"></span>\r\n\r\n</p><font color=\"#000080\"></font><font color=\"#000080\"></font><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12pt;\">\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12pt; font-weight: bold;\">Check out the video!&nbsp; Singing one of my songs at Aaron Tippin\'s show!<o:p></o:p><br/></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12pt; font-weight: bold;\"></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: black;\"><br/>\r\n\r\n</span>\r\n\r\n<object height=\"350\" width=\"425\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/NaQ95RhYRjo\"/><param name=\"wmode\" value=\"transparent\"/><embed \r\n\r\nsrc=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/NaQ95RhYRjo\" \r\n\r\ntype=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" wmode=\"transparent\"\r\nwidth=\"425\" \r\n\r\nheight=\"350\"/></object><br/><br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\"></a>\r\n\r\n<br /><br /><a target = \"_blank\"href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=108\"><span style=\"font-size:8pt;\">Interact with Dani Lee Dawsons fans</span></a><br />',1,'',0,''),(488,507,'J-RHEL',3,0,'www.j-rhel.com','','678-413-0065','\r\n<p class=\"MsoHeader\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Century Gothic\';\">Busting out of Atlanta&#8217;s underground rap scene, J-RHEL is a lyrical force of nature on the mic, with expert wordplay and unique beats that bring candor to the dance floor.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>He&#8217;s the kid everybody knows from the hood, not from selling drugs or being a gansta, but from always being himself.<span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Unafraid of taking chances and crossing the boundaries of Rap and R&B, J-RHEL has lived what he spits, and his new record, <i style=\"\">You Know My Name, </i>explodes with fresh, head-turning rhymes that make you hit replay.<span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Part of the new generation of Hip Hop spearheaded by visionaries like Kanye West and Jay-Z, J-RHEL has already shared the stage with the likes of Pastor Troy, Young Joc, Young Dro, Fabo of D4L, JT Money, and Cherish.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>His music appeals to the projects and the suburbs, the new school and the old school, by keeping it fly, keeping it honest, and keeping it real.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoHeader\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Century Gothic\';\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoHeader\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Century Gothic\';\">The youngest of six brothers and sisters born on the west side of Charlotte, North Carolina, J-RHEL credits the strength and guidance of his mother and father for keeping him off the typical neighborhood path of drugs, gangs and jail, and into the discipline and honor of playing sports and being part of a family. At three years old, J-RHEL lost his older brother Boogie to a street shooting.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>His family managed to stay strong, and as a kid growing up, J-RHEL sang in church choirs and played any instrument he could get his hands on, enjoying the blessing of a loving family.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>At age nine, J-RHEL started watching his brother V rhyme and battle other MCs, and spent hours in the studio with him whenever V would baby-sit. However, his world was turned around once again when his brother Gary died from an AIDS infected needle, and at only eleven years old, J-RHEL turned to a tape recorder as the only way to express his grief, anger, and frustration through rhymes.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoHeader\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Century Gothic\';\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoHeader\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Century Gothic\';\">Learning from the mistakes of his brothers, J-RHEL went on to become the first member of his family to go to college, with a football scholarship in West Virginia.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>Though he was being groomed for a career in the NFL, he became more serious about music, and transferred to continue school in Atlanta where a classmate heard his home-recorded rhymes and introduced him to Supasize Entertainment in 2003.<span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>They encouraged J-RHEL to write and record more material and helped him get started with live shows in Atlanta&#8217;s underground rap scene. His early recordings, like the popular &#8220;Carolina Juke,&#8221; were passed around on mix tapes, but when demand for more music became overwhelming, J-RHEL got back into the studio with producer Kamal aka The Element to record <i style=\"\">You Know My Name</i>, which will is available through online retailers worldwide.</span></p><br/><p class=\"MsoHeader\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><br/></p><p class=\"MsoHeader\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=66\">Join J-Rhel\'s discussion</a><br/><span style=\"font-family: \'Century Gothic\';\"> <o:p></o:p></span></p>',1,'',0,''),(489,535,'Bob Porembski',1,61,'www.p-h-a-m.com','','','\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: center;\" align=\"center\"><b style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">BOB&nbsp;POREMBSKI<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: center;\" align=\"center\"><b style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">aka \"Bobby Guitar\"<br/></span></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: center;\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><o:p><br/></o:p></span></p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font size=\"3\"><span style=\"\">&nbsp;</span>Legendary songwriter and producer Van Dyke Parks has said: <o:p></o:p></font></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font size=\"3\">&#8220;Bob&#8217;s ecumenical approach to music &#8211; his understanding of popular idioms, how they are developed and exploited &#8211; and his fundamental discipline in literary musical works give him an informed enthusiasm in the focus of songwriting.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>Bob Porembski&#8230; is contributing to our American musical heritage&#8221;.</font></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: center;\" align=\"center\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p></span>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">A songwriter/composer, recording artist/performer, music producer and music educator, Bob has taught music business, independent record production and music publishing for over ten years at </span><st1:place><st1:placename><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Mercy</span></st1:placename><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"> </span><st1:placetype><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">College</span></st1:placetype></st1:place><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">, </span><st1:place><st1:placename><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Queensborough</span></st1:placename><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"> </span><st1:placetype><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">College</span></st1:placetype></st1:place><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">, and </span><st1:place><st1:placename><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">New York</span></st1:placename><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"> </span><st1:placetype><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">University</span></st1:placetype></st1:place><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">His song, &#8220;Feelin&#8217; More Like Christmas&#8221; is a seasonal TV hit that has been featured on the CBS daytime drama, &#8220;The Young and the Restless&#8221;, USA Networks&#8217; &#8220;Twelve Days of Christmas&#8221;, BRAVO&nbsp;and the TRIO Network.&nbsp; The song has been heard internationally in Canada, England, Norway and Australia.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Bob has written music for Special Olympics (official theme song, &#8220;Take A Hand, Make A Friend&#8221;), HBO,&nbsp;Rocher Candy and Captain Morgan.&nbsp;<br/><br/>His latest CD, \"ac-ro-nym...\" with the rock and roll trio PHAM! has received critical acclain, was nominated for CD of the year and is in rotation on a number of radio stations.&nbsp;&nbsp;The first song,<br/>&nbsp;&#8220;Good Morning, I Love You&#8221;&nbsp;was featured on The Oxygen Network\'s edgey comedy, &#8220;Good Girls Don&#8217;t&#8221;.<br/><br/>It\'s 16 tracks of jingly jangly rock guitar earned him the nickname, \"Bobby Guitar\".<br/>&nbsp;<br/>His music was featured on&nbsp;the SPIKE TV mini-series &#8220;Invasion Iowa&#8221; and most recently his composition&nbsp;\"Jungle Friends\" was featured on The Learning Channel\'s award-winning documentary, \"The Face of Yulce\".</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Believing strongly in the healing power of music, he performs regularly with his group, &#8220;City Rhythm&#8221;, for Hospital Audiences, Inc., bringing rock and roll music to those who would otherwise not be able to experience it. <br/><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><o:p><br/>He also just completed his \"World Tour\" (band members include drummer, Dan Goldfedder and keyboardist Steve Ward)&nbsp;which included&nbsp;performances at the famed Cavern Club (birthplace of The Beatles) in Liverpool, England.<br/>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Bob&nbsp;is the owner of Robert Porembski Music, a full service music production house in NYC and was recently inducted into the Cathedral Prep Sports Hall of Fame for outstanding achievement on the basketball court.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Bob has a Master&#8217;s degree in Music Technology from </span><st1:place><st1:placename><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">New York</span></st1:placename><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"> </span><st1:placetype><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">University</span></st1:placetype></st1:place><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">.<br/><o:p><br/>He is proud to be a Knucklehead Guitar Strings Endorsed Artist.<br/><br/>To hear more rock and roll visit:<br/>www.myspace.com/phamband<br/>www.myspace.com/cityrhythmband</o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><br/><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=67\">Join Bob\'s discussion</a><br/></p>',0,'',0,''),(491,537,'Foretold',1,14,'www.Foretoldmusic.com','','443 286 7108','&nbsp;Foretold evolved in late 2004 with the entrance of Andrew Dugan as\r\nvocalist to the existing lineup of members. At that time, Matt Pukach\r\nand Eric Pindell were playing guitar, with Aaron Patz at bass. After\r\nexperimenting with an Acidhead, an Alcoholic and a Mullet-master in the\r\ndrummer slot, everyone came to their senses. It was &#8220;foretold&#8221; by\r\nAndrew that Matt would eventually be playing drums, and in 2006, it\r\ncame to be.<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nIn less than a month Matt was caught up to speed\r\nand everything began to fall into place. For the first time in nearly 2\r\nyears the band felt right and the music really began to take shape into\r\nwhat it is today. With Eric and Andrew concentrating on lyrics and\r\nmelody, Foretold began writing music at a much faster pace and recorded\r\na 4 track E.P just three months after the transition.\r\n<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nNine months later, the band had played every major local\r\nmusic venue in the Baltimore area. Recently Mike Kane was added to the\r\nlineup as a guitarist and backup singer. Mike added production\r\nexperience and his connections have allowed the band has played on a TV\r\nshow against drunk-driving that aired several times weekly in May. In\r\nrecent months, they have been interviewed several times in the local\r\nnewspaper, and have repeatedly appeared and received airplay on 98\r\nRock&#8217;s Noise in the Basement program.\r\n<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nForetold has truly become a band on the cusp of moving\r\ninto the national spotlight as they plan to tour in the fall of 2007.\r\nCurrently they are continuing production of their first full-length\r\nCD-&#8220;Just the Tip&#8221;, which is expected to be released in late fall/winter\r\nof 2007.\r\n<br/><br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=68\">Join Foretold\'s discussion</a><br/>\r\n\r\n',1,'',0,''),(507,550,'Old 80\'s Guy',1,16,'','2031 Paradise Dr.','931-270-8259','\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\">I was born in <?xml:namespace prefix = st1 /><st1:place><st1:city>Detroit</st1:city> <st1:state>Michigan</st1:state></st1:place> many moons ago, and was exposed to a lot of different music. My mother and father listened to the big bands and my older sisters were bobby sockin&#8217; around the house to Elvis, the Big Bopper and so on. </p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\">I started playing drums at 15 years of age for a local basement band; we played mostly Motown songs. A bit later on Jimi Hendrix and Ted Nugent came along and I wanted to start playing guitar and that has remained my first love in music ever since. </p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\">I played in several bands in the <st1:city><st1:place>Detroit</st1:place></st1:city> area for many years, then in 1993 I moved to the <st1:city><st1:place>Nashville</st1:place></st1:city> area, not to become a star..lol.. but because my job dictated it.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\">As far as influences the list would be way too long, but I give credit to Ted Nugent for getting me started playing guitar and as for bands, I&#8217;d have to say, The Dixie Dregs, and Dream Theater rank at the top of my list.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\">As most musician&#8217;s, my interment is an avenue of self-expression. I don&#8217;t care to copy or sound like anyone else, I just play what my feelings tell me to play. That surly doesn&#8217;t mean I wouldn&#8217;t like to play like Eric Johnson and the like, technically, but that&#8217;s lack of practice on my part! </p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\">Two of the dreams I had when I was young have come true, being able to record affordably at home with good quality and a way to collaborate with other musicians, which this site makes possible. </p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\">With that said, I&#8217;d like to thank the great musicians that I&#8217;ve had the great fortune to collaborate with, such as &#8220;Ralan Guyer&#8221; an incredible singer/writer/musician,&nbsp;you can find him here at Best of Bands.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\">John McCormack who played the saxophone on &#8220;Sexy Sax&#8221; <a href=\"http://www.jamwave.com/artist.aspx?AID=1210\">http://www.jamwave.com/artist.aspx?AID=1210</a> , Storyteller guitar AKA Arpi a fantastic guitarist from <st1:country-region><st1:place>Romania</st1:place></st1:country-region> <span>&nbsp;</span><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://www.jamwave.com/artist.aspx?AID=636\">http://www.jamwave.com/artist.aspx?AID=636</a>, and Roscoe Peterson another incredible guitarist. <span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://www.jamwave.com/artist.aspx?AID=1831\">http://www.jamwave.com/artist.aspx?AID=1831</a></p><?xml:namespace prefix = o /><o:p></o:p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><br/>And of course the management of this site for making all of this possible.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\">Respects,</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\">Dave <span>&nbsp;</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span> <br/></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><br/><span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=69\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Join Dave\'s discussion</span></a><br/></p>',0,'',0,''),(496,536,'Ralan Guyer HarmonicDistortion',1,66,'http://www.reverbnation.com/ralanguyer','2623 nation rd','864 456 2111','<div style=\"text-align: center\">\r\n<div align=\"justify\">\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center\">\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n</div>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold\"><font size=\"6\" color=\"#0000ff\">A</font> little bit about me... I&rsquo;ve been singing and playing bass for over three decades now... I started by  playing the drums at the age of 8 in 1970... I found myself venturing out in the 80&#39;s grabbing songs of impact, and alot of hard rockers, now finding myself mellowing out a little...    I&#39;ve spent 15 years as a studio musician, and assistant to the engineer. Singing, playing Bass, mixing new ones, old ones, covers, and originals. <span style=\"font-size: 14pt; color: #990000\">We were in the studio one day in Ohio and this black kid comes walking in. Tom the engineer looks at me and says, &quot;do you know who that is?&quot; I said &quot;have no clue&quot;. He said thats Anthony the drummer for &quot;The Back Street Boys.&quot; All of you have heard of the all boy pop band right... Well Tom said, why don&#39;t you have Anthony put the drums on your new song &quot;My Life&quot; well I&#39;m thinking (is this kid any good.) So Tom asked Anthony, and he said, &quot;SURE,  why not...&quot; So we get the tape out, play the song one time and Anthony says &#39;&#39;OK lets do it...&#39;&#39; I said what!? And he starts walking to the drum kit in the next room!!! Now keep in mind he was listening to a bad live recording of the song in it&#39;s infancy with a bad drummer on it! I said to Tom, there ain&#39;t no way this guy&#39;s gonna do this after only hearing it one time and do it live all the way though... Tom just smiled and said &quot;WE&#39;RE ROLLIN&quot; then laughed... So heres the deal, if you take the time to listen to &quot;My Life&quot; it&#39;s Anthony on drums and he did it the first take, NO KIDDING!!! It took me 3 months to write this song and Houdini learns it in 5 minutes then plays his ass off at the end... Oh well, your the best Anthony.......</span>  I grew up in a big city in Ohio (The Great White North!) and found myself always listening to a band called Rush in the late 70&#39;s. Buying a $50.00 bass at a local flea market I went home to see if I could play long enough to learn at least one song all the way through... I picked an easy Chicago tune called 25 or 6 to 4, and figured it out after about an hour of playing, but man my fingers had enough ! ! ! Then I knew I could move on to Rush&#39;es Workin Man... I was only 16 at the time and it was Geddy Lee from Rush that inspired me to write my own songs. In 1980 I discovered a band called &quot;Journey&quot; I was hooked, it was then I decided to jump into the music biz head first and learn every song, on every album that Journey ever put out...  So in 1980 I joined my first band. The bio of the band I jumped into was intense ! The band ended up learning over 56 songs in less then 6 months, which put me on center stage to be the front man since all the other guys in the band wouldn&#39;t sing, (only backup...) It was then I had my homework cut out for me, trying to learn the bass lines, memorize the lyrics, then trying to put both parts together was difficult at the time but I never really thought about how difficult it was, I just wanted to keep rockin... The Harmonic Distortion CD was really never to be... It was two years ago when I had an idea to rekindle my old passion for singing. After a long four year break from my music, I decided to sing an old love song by Elton John called &quot;Your Song&quot; and give it to my girlfriend as a gift of gratitude. When I finished with the mixing at the studio, I wanted more... So I kept singing and thus become &quot;some&quot; of the songs listed on here .... Titling the CD was then easy, the mixing is something I wouldn&#39;t wish on anyone!  Thats why we called it (dont try this @ home.)  Geddy Lee from Rush, Rik Emmett from Triumph, Klaus Meine from the Scorpions, and Steve Perry from Journey, &quot;My so-called teachers&quot;... Thanx to Primetime recording studio where &quot;Lovin Someone, My Yyz for Geddy Lee, Vital Farewell, My life, Love of a lifetime, and Cruel Passages,&quot; were recorded, but mixed at my studio Stealth Sound &amp; Recording. Also thanks to my studio players Scott sheppard and Dave Elgin on drums, Dave Chilson (Old 80&#39;s Guy) and Bobby Wilson on Guitars, my parents for their tolerance of all the loud music when I was growing up, and my children for having my loud screaming vocals in there face as they were growing up..... And YOU for taking the time to listen ! ! !  And most of all, Uncle  Les...  ROCK ON BROTHERS ! Ralan...      </span><span style=\"color: #990000; text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold\">Take a look</span><br />\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n<span style=\"color: #990000; text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold\"> \r\nat this incredible video of my friend Nick at 19 years of age\r\nrehearsing to Limelight... Don&#39;t blink or you&#39;ll miss him at his\r\nbest!!!  To  view more video&#39;s of Nick just click on this video... RUSH\r\nLimelight &quot;Drums by Nick Cesarz&quot;</span>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold\"></span><br />\r\n<div>\r\n<object classid=\"clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000\" codebase=\"http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0\" width=\"425\" height=\"355\">\r\n	<param name=\"width\" value=\"425\" />\r\n	<param name=\"height\" value=\"355\" />\r\n	<param name=\"wmode\" value=\"transparent\" />\r\n	<param name=\"src\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/8b9jR6GOeqo&amp;rel=1\" />\r\n	<embed type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" width=\"425\" height=\"355\" wmode=\"transparent\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/8b9jR6GOeqo&amp;rel=1\"></embed>\r\n</object>\r\n</div>\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<div style=\"text-align: left\">\r\n<a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=41\" target=\"_blank\">Join Ralan Guyer&#39;s Discussion</a><br />\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n',1,'<a name=\"&lt;a mce_thref=&quot;http://www.reverbnation.com/c./a4/166577/23060/Artist/23060/Artist/link&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;Ralan Guyer  (Me and my big Mouth)&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; mce_tsrc=&quot;http://www.reverbnation.com/c./a3/166577/23060/Artist/23060/Artist/res.gif&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a mce_thref=&quot;http://www.quantcast.com/p-05---xoNhTXVc&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img mce_tsrc=&quot;http://pixel.quantserve.com/pixel/p-05---xoNhTXVc.gif&quot; style=&quot;display: none&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; height=&quot;1&quot; width=&quot;1&quot; alt=&quot;Quantcast&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;visibility:hidden;width:0px;height:0px;&quot; border=0 width=0 height=0 mce_tsrc=&quot;http://counters.gigya.com/wildfire/CIMP/bT*xJmx*PTEyMTYzNDI5MTk4NDMmcHQ9MTIxNjM*MjkyODE3MSZwPTI3MDgxJmQ9YmFubmVyJTVGZmlyc3QlNUZnZW4mbj*mZz*x.jpg&quot; /&gt;\" title=\"&lt;a mce_thref=&quot;http://www.reverbnation.com/c./a4/166577/23060/Artist/23060/Artist/link&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;Ralan Guyer  (Me and my big Mouth)&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; mce_tsrc=&quot;http://www.reverbnation.com/c./a3/166577/23060/Artist/23060/Artist/res.gif&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a mce_thref=&quot;http://www.quantcast.com/p-05---xoNhTXVc&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img mce_tsrc=&quot;http://pixel.quantserve.com/pixel/p-05---xoNhTXVc.gif&quot; style=&quot;display: none&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; height=&quot;1&quot; width=&quot;1&quot; alt=&quot;Quantcast&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;visibility:hidden;width:0px;height:0px;&quot; border=0 width=0 height=0 mce_tsrc=&quot;http://counters.gigya.com/wildfire/CIMP/bT*xJmx*PTEyMTYzNDI5MTk4NDMmcHQ9MTIxNjM*MjkyODE3MSZwPTI3MDgxJmQ9YmFubmVyJTVGZmlyc3QlNUZnZW4mbj*mZz*x.jpg&quot; /&gt;\"></a>\r\n',0,''),(524,564,'dj paradox',5,28,'www.myspace.com/paraphoenix','1142 Cleveland Ave','17083051476','Damian Noonan was born in 1988 in Konin,Poland. He was then adopted in 1990 where it wasnt long until he discovered the world of music and where he began to learn as much as he could about music 24/7. In 99 he discoverd trance music and he was hooked. He bought every cd imaginable and learned as much about trance music.Come eight grade Damian took up Turtablism for about a year before he got into just hardcore mixing. He then took up the name (D.J. Paradox). His Arsenal comes With Two Stanton Direct Drive Turntables, Two Numark Cdx\'x, And A Behringer DJX 700 Mixer. What is it about his mixing at a show maybe its his connection throguh his music to the people or the connection of the people to him. Whatever it is when D.J. Paradox is performing its a site to see. When i had a chance to ask damian about waht it is he looks for at a venue he said \" I look for a vibe and then i build the energy up from there\". Paradox has always found his groove no matter where he goes and performs it just comes so natural to him In early 2002 he started to work as a dj sharing his passion for trance music with his community.Then in 2004 he started producing music by starting with mix cds and then ion 2005 he started producing his own trance music. His debut album True Trance will be released in a few months. He also is working with Axion another Trance Producer in hopes of releasing a collaboration cd sometime next year. <br/><br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=70\" target=\"_blank\">Join Paradox\'s discussion</a>',1,'',0,''),(502,546,'tim pont',10,48,'www.myspace.com/timpontmusic','','','I have been playing in bands for as long as I care to remember untill about a year ago I decided to put the electric down for a while and give the acoustic a go. These few tunes are the result.Enjoy!<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=71\">Join Tim\'s discussion</a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(503,541,'Ron Fattorusso',11,96,'http://secretformularecords.com/Ron.html','1441 Garden road','954-349-8662','<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 6pt; text-align: left\" class=\"MsoBodyTextIndent\" align=\"left\">\r\n<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"2\">Ron&#39;s career was launched with his first solo CD skyrocketing into the smooth jazz world with great reception and rave reviews from jazz critics<span> </span>and his own peers from around the globe. This CD has been on international radio and TV since it&rsquo;s debut.&nbsp;Ten songs have been on the air from The Weather Channel, DMX radio, over 100 radio stations, smoothjazz.com and TV&rsquo;s Musicchoice.com.</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 6pt; text-align: left\" class=\"MsoBodyTextIndent\" align=\"left\">\r\n<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"2\">A multi-talented instrumentalist, Ron is one of the few who can play each instrument equally well having mastered Soprano, Alto, Tenor Saxes and flute. He has been passionately working on his music for the last 2 years, end result; a great 15 track jazz CD featuring hit singles &ldquo;Up All Night&rdquo;,<br />\r\n<span>&nbsp;</span>&ldquo;I Know You&rsquo;re There&rdquo;, &ldquo;Grover, Thanks&rdquo; and &ldquo;Jamaican Blue&rdquo;.</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\" class=\"MsoNormal\">\r\n<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"2\">Ron performed with such stars as Bing Crosby, Shirley Bassey, Steve Lawrence, Edie Gorme, Hal Linden, Joan Rivers, Mitzi Gaynor, Julio Iglesias, Celia Cruz, Rodney Dangerfield, Milton Berle, Henny Youngman, Olga Guillo, Willie Chirino, Lissette, Lola Flores, Iris Chacon, Susy Leman, Robert Carlos, Tony Orlando &amp; Dawn, Vicki Carr, Peter Allen and Eddie Arnold. By the 1980&#39;s he backed up Desi Arnez, The Temptations and<span>&nbsp; </span>jazz giants Ira Sullivan, Joe Diorio and Eddie Daniels.<span>&nbsp; </span>From 1981-83 Ron went on &#39;sold out&#39; concert tours with El Puma. In 1980, while working as a musician, he opened a recording studio in South Florida (Star Track Recording). Having recorded countless of talented musicians over a 20 year span, he has been able to use his experience, knowledge and apply it to his first solo jazz cd, Up All Night.</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 10pt\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none\"><u><font face=\"Arial\">&nbsp;</font></u></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial\">Retail distribution and Internet Stores: The CD is available at Amazon.com, CDBaby.com, Tower Records, SecretFormulaRecords.com, CDUniverse, CDStreet.com, Napster, Apple iTunes, Rhapsody, BuyMusic, Emusic, AOL&rsquo;s MusicNet, AudioLunchbox, Lindows, MusicMatch and a total of 32 digital downloads.</span><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"2\">&nbsp;</font><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\"><font face=\"Arial\">Live Show: Ron debuted his new CD LIVE with his eight piece band at <span style=\"color: red\">Sunfest 2004</span> on April 30<sup>th</sup> 2004 sharing the bill with Cyndi Lauper, Michael Buble and Peter Frampton. He currently is performing in the Caribbean and South Florida area.</font></span><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"2\">&nbsp;</font> \r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; line-height: normal\" class=\"ReferenceLine\">\r\n<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"2\">To request an interview with Ron and receive free &ldquo;Up All Night&rdquo; giveaways contact Gary Farr at gary@secretformularecords.com.</font> \r\n</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; line-height: normal\" class=\"ReferenceLine\">\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; line-height: normal\" class=\"ReferenceLine\">\r\n<a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=93\" target=\"_blank\">Join Ron&#39;s discussion</a>\r\n</p>\r\n',0,'',0,''),(2482,1000299,'Pale',1,66,'http://www.myspace.com/palerocks','','713-294-7918','',1,'<font size=\"3\"><strong>Calvin Stanley - Vocals, Guitar<br />\r\nRobb Moore - Guitar<br />\r\nStephen Wesson - Bass<br />\r\nTravis Middour - Drums</strong></font>\r\n',0,''),(2483,1000300,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2484,1000301,'The Mourning Sickness',1,76,'http://www.themourningsickness.com','P. O. Box 140484, Edgewater, CO  80214','303-555-1212','<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color: #660000; font-family: Times; font-size: 16px; line-height: normal\">\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;<img src=\"../uploads/1000301/mslogo.GIF\" alt=\"\" width=\"263\" height=\"269\" align=\"right\" />\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\r\n<span style=\"color: maroon\"><strong><sup>The&nbsp;</sup>Mourning Sickness</strong></span><span style=\"color: navy\">, progressive power-trio from Denver, Colorado, has been gigging extensively for the last fifteen years, and has been completely ignored by both the local media and the underground scene:<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><strong>The invisible band</strong></span><span style=\"color: navy\">.</span>\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\r\n<span style=\"color: navy\"></span><span style=\"color: navy\">Playing music that must seem confusing to the management and patrons of clubs and theaters around the world,&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: maroon\"><strong><sup>The&nbsp;</sup>Mourning Sickness</strong></span><span style=\"color: navy\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></span><span style=\"color: navy\">continues to be forgotten.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>Nonetheless,&nbsp;<strong>it refuses to die</strong></span><span style=\"color: navy\">.</span>\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\r\n<span style=\"color: navy\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: navy\">No provocateur of music wants to hear the same old tired piles of clich&eacute;.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>Trend watchers and teenage wannabes aside,&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: maroon\"><strong><sup>The&nbsp;</sup>Mourning Sickness</strong></span><span style=\"color: maroon\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: navy\">will continue to venture forth, pushing the boundaries back, despite the overwhelming evidence that no-one is listening.</span>\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\r\n<span style=\"color: navy\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: navy\">Sisyphus the king was condemned throughout eternity to push a rock up a hill, only to see it fall back to earth before reaching his goal.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>He had no choice.</span>\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\r\n<span style=\"color: navy\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: navy\">We do have a choice.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>And it is in the futility of music that&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: maroon\"><strong><sup>The&nbsp;</sup>Mourning Sickness</strong></span><span style=\"color: navy\">&nbsp;revel.</span>\r\n</p>\r\n</span>\r\n',1,'<div>\r\n<br />\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color: #660000; font-family: Times; font-size: 16px; line-height: normal\">\r\n<p>\r\n<img src=\"../uploads/1000301/dsc00214.GIF\" alt=\"\" width=\"96\" height=\"53\" align=\"left\" /><strong>Jeff Dunn</strong>, joined&nbsp;<strong><sup><font size=\"-2\">The&nbsp;</font></sup>Mourning Sickness</strong>&nbsp;in 1997. An accomplished bassist, his influences include The Beatles, Beethoven, John Entwistle, and Guinness Extra Stout.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<img src=\"../uploads/1000301/dsc00216.GIF\" alt=\"\" width=\"72\" height=\"96\" align=\"left\" /><strong>Joe Wilkinson</strong>, joined&nbsp;<strong><sup><font size=\"-2\">The&nbsp;</font></sup>Mourning Sickness</strong>&nbsp;in 1999 as drummer/percussionist. Joe&#39;s influences include Stravinsky, Scooby Do, and Hong Kong Phuey.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<img src=\"../uploads/1000301/dsc00217.GIF\" alt=\"\" width=\"72\" height=\"96\" align=\"left\" /><strong>Matthew Maher</strong>, founder of&nbsp;<strong><sup><font size=\"-2\">The&nbsp;</font></sup>Mourning Sickness</strong>, took up guitar to channel the torrent of disturbed ideas erupting from his psyche. He has been influenced by Marx, Freud, and Metallica.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n</span>\r\n</div>\r\n',0,''),(504,526,'Darkangel',5,27,'http://www.myspace.com/iamyourdarkangel','','','started in 2004&nbsp; now 2008 cooming out to the public , my goal is to write epic trance with some new twists. i am heavly into writting love songs that are yet very danceable,somtimes happy somtimes alittle sad, but as long is the music is good does it matter. :) , i love female vocals so if there are any female singers out there leave me one :)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/iamyourdarkangel\">www.myspace.com/iamyourdarkangel</a> <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=72\" target=\"_blank\">Join Darkangel&#39;s discussion</a>\r\n',0,'',0,''),(505,549,'Captain Black',1,17,'','','','Captain Black isn\'t a band.. it\'s an alter-ego.<br/><br/>The tunes are produced on a 350 MHz G3 iMac using a variety of software, including but not limited to:<br/>Ableton LIVE.. <br/>Cakewalk Metro.. <br/>Mackie Tracktion.. <br/>and a bunch of software synths and effects. <br/><br/>Some of the music is recorded live, then sliced up for use as loops and samples.. Other times it might be used as is.. It\'s all muse dependent. <br/><br/>Instruments include a Sears short scale bass.. a no name Strat copy.. a couple Casio keyboards used as MIDI controllers.. a pair of Mountain Dulcimers.. a \'First Act\' Lap Harp.. Various \'circuit bent\' toys.. and anything else that can make a semi-controllable noise. Studio1031 also uses, abuses and recommends Radio Shack Microphones, Cables and Adapters.. <br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=73\">Join Captain Black\'s discussion</a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(511,553,'The Underground Rebels',1,74,'www.theundergroundrebels.com','','','<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=74\">Join Underground Rebel\'s discussion</a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(512,554,'A. W. Cobb',1,69,'http://www.myspace.com/jakeburt','520 hullave.','419-423-5673','<a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=75\" target=\"_blank\">Join A.W.&#39;s discussion</a> <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<font size=\"5\">\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"book antiqua,palatino\" size=\"3\" color=\"#3366ff\">Anthony&rsquo;s first guitar belonged to one of his brothers and he lent it to his dad. His Dad rarely played it and after a year it sat in the corner of their living room collecting dust. One autumn Saturday morning Anthony thought he would give it a try. His dad tuned it and showed him a couple of chords. By the time the next weekend came around he was sure that he wanted to learn how to play. They were not a wealthy family so his dad bought him a simple chord book, there would be no lessons. <br />\r\nHe made up his mind he was going to practice at least one hour every night. He practiced every night for a month and soon found that he had no desire to learn other peoples songs. He started stringing chords together and humming melodies. Anthony had never attempted to write anything before, but one night he sat down and put lyrics to a chord run he had been playing over and over. He got up the nerve to sing it for his mom and that&rsquo;s where things started for Anthony at age 13. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"book antiqua,palatino\" size=\"3\" color=\"#3366ff\">Anthony has formed a couple of bands over the years, Wilderness, Robinson Vail and Graysville Skyview. Unfortunately they did not work out too well as most of the members wanted to do covers. Anthony did not want this, he wanted to write and play his own material. He recorded his first cd in 1996 called An Eyeful of Words. It wasn&rsquo;t until 2001 that he picked up his guitar again and recorded Beneath a Wounded Sky. Anthony has recently finished recording All Lights &nbsp;on the Myth, his 3<sup>rd</sup> cd and is now working on his 4<sup>th</sup> called&nbsp; Somewhere Out there, which he hopes to release this summer. <br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"book antiqua,palatino\" size=\"3\" color=\"#3366ff\">Anthony believes that perhaps music is the one common ground that we all can share. It makes no difference what type of music you like, its the love of music that its all about! <br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n</font>\r\n',0,'',0,''),(513,556,'Abuzed-1',7,36,'www.abuzed1.com','','626-824-8221','\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong style=\"font-size: 18pt;\"><font style=\"font-size: 36pt;\" color=\"#ff0000\"><embed width=\"100\" height=\"50\" autostart=\"true\" showcontrols=\"true\" showstatusbar=\"true\" pluginspage=\"http://www.microsoft.com/Windows/MediaPlayer\" type=\"application/x-mplayer2\" src=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/uploads/556/Faith%20Killer.mp3\" name=\"MediaPlayer1\"/><br/><br/>Abuzed-1<br/></font></strong><br/><br/><br/><img title=\"JEV\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/uploads/556/JEV.jpg\" align=\"bottom\" border=\"0\" height=\"128\" width=\"170\"/>&nbsp;<img title=\"GT\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/uploads/556/GT.jpg\" align=\"bottom\" border=\"0\" height=\"128\" width=\"170\"/><br/><br/><br/>Abuzed-1 started near LA California. Formed by GT and JEV with the soul purpose of making music that\'s heavy musically and lyrically. Our priorities are playing what we want to play. We don\'t care about what trends are in and what rules others feel we should have to follow. If we have to label ourselves, we are DARKKORE! </p>\r\n<p align=\"center\">We welcome anyone who wants to listen and bang there head regardless of race, gender or religion. \r\n</p><p align=\"center\"><font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong>JEV <br/></strong></font>is the musical engine of the project grinding out riffs that are deadly, dark, melodic, and chaotic all in the same mix. \r\n</p><p align=\"center\"><font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong>GT</strong></font> <br/>bleeds out lyrics that are hypnotic conscious mind blasts stemming from living life\'s highs and lows. This project is not about fame and fortune. It\'s about doing what we love and experiencing life\'s travels SOBER! \r\n</p><p align=\"center\">Abuzed-1 is currently on their own independent label Mind Switch Records, but is currently looking to sign with a major label.</p><br/><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=76\">Join Abuzed-1\'s discussion</a><br/></p><p align=\"center\"></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p></p><p></p><p></p>',1,'',0,''),(2146,2286,'Syck-Ness',3,18,'www.myspace.com/sycknessp2','','','What Can Be Said About Anthony Fludd(Syck-Ness). Its Along Story But Hears A Shorter Version. Well He Is Number Five Out Of Ten Brothers And Sisters(5 Sisters 4 Brothers). At The Age Of 12 He Was Sent Away Due To Behavior Problems, And Has Been In The System Until The Age Of 17. Throughout That Time All The Young Rapper Was Doing Was Writing Rhymes. He Felt It Was The Only Thing He Was Good At. His Purpose Was To Prove Everyone Who Said He Wouldn\'t Make It.... Wrong. Mainly His Mother. But Losing His Mother At The Age Of 13 Would Force Him To Set Out For A New Goal In Life.So He Focused On Rapping And Started To Create A New Purpose To Do The Trade And That Purpose Was Called Passion. He Discovered The Name Syck-Ness Because He Wanted A Name That Had A Meaning Behind It And Not Just A Name Anybody Could Think Of. There Are A Few Reasons For The Name. 1. Is A Simple Reason Its Because Everybody THat Heard Him Rhyme Would Say That He Was Sick. 2. Was Because When He Rapped Word About His Skills Spread From One Person To Another, Like A Sickness. And 3. Is Because Every Time They Came Out With A Cure For A disease A New Disease A Worse Disease Would Arise So Every Time They Come Out With A Song To Cure One Of His Songs (Make A Better Song) He Comes Out With One Thats Even Better Then The Last One He Put Out. After Finding His Name He Would Spend The Rest Of His Time Battling, Writting,Freestyling, And Recording To Get A Buzz On The Streets And In The Music World. The Rest You Can Find Out Through His Music. So Here\'s Your Breath Of Fresh Air. Here\'s<br/><br/>SYCK-NESS&nbsp; ',1,'',0,''),(516,558,'This Grand Design',1,76,'','','','\r\n<p>\"i\'m not cocky. i\'m just confident.&nbsp; so when you tell me i\'m the best, it\'s a compliment.\" - Jadakiss.<br/><br/>i\'m a 1 man army. i play whatever instrument i can get my hands on. learned to play by ear since i was a kid. also learned how to loop when i was young. play, pause, rewind, etc......i know i\'m not the only one who learned the tape-deck trick. wink, wink....<br/><br/>basically, i play whatever comes to mind or heart. Heart does seem to rule in the matter, though. i like to rely on emotion.<br/><br/>you\'ll either love my stuff, or hate it. either way.....thanks for listening.<br/>- words</p><br/><p><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=77\">Join This Grand Design\'s discussion</a><br/></p><p><br/></p><p></p>',1,'',0,''),(518,559,'Scott Dunford',8,0,'myspace.com/scottdunford','','','\r\n<p>Scott comes from a long line of musicians and singers. He began playing guitar at family jams and singing in the school show choir at age fourteen. When Scott turned twenty-three, his Dad introduced him to dim lights, thick smoke and Honky-Tonk Music. </p>\r\n<p><br/>Scott has always listened to a wide range of music growing up. His musical start was in the early 90s playing guitar for Hard Rock Bands. In the mid 90s, a new sound called Young Country was taking heed.&nbsp; Brooks-n-Dunn, Tracey Lawrence and David Ball were a few of the&nbsp; country artists that caught his ears and eyes. Shortly there after, Scott&nbsp; formed a country band that would allow him to experiment with his&nbsp; vocal, playing,writing and creative style. With his years of hard work&nbsp; on and off the stage, Scott has ended up where he belongs, With the Honky-Tonk Crowd\".<br/>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>With the years of experience fronting Midnight Rain, Scott has&nbsp; developed into a solid country picker, singer and song-writer. His&nbsp; dedication and drive has given him and his band, Midnight Rain, a well&nbsp; recognized name in the Tri-State area. </p>\r\n<p>Scott writes his songs from the heart and life experiences. His voice and&nbsp;stage presence tells the stories behind his&nbsp; songs. The most important goals to Scott&nbsp; are to remain true to country music and&nbsp; have people hear and relate to his&nbsp; music......</p>Scott dreams of hearing his songs played across&nbsp; the airwaves. Whether hes playing a small or large venue, he loves to connect with the crowd. Scott hopes one day people will be singing his&nbsp; songs while theyre driving or playing in the clubs.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br /><br /><a target = \"_blank\"href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=109\"><span style=\"font-size:8pt;\">Interact with Scott Dunfords fans</span></a><br />',1,'',0,''),(519,561,'Lard Hand',1,76,'www.lardhand.com','','','',1,'',0,''),(522,563,'Mr. DaLicks',3,20,'www.divinesoundsmusic.com/mrdalicks','','','<object width=\"300\" height=\"290\"><embed src=\"http://media.imeem.com/pl/VfAH8qKwz5\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" width=\"300\" height=\"290\" wmode=\"transparent\"/></embed/></object><br/>\r\n<p>Mr. DaLicks was destined to pursue and make his mark in the music industry. Born in Houston Texas into a family of musicians, he was constantly surrounded by music and<br/>instruments.&nbsp; Eager to learn, he made a drum-set out of old pot\'s and pans and began sculpturing his unique style of rhythm.&nbsp; By the age of 5 he got his first drum-set and <br/>began playing at his church as the lead drummer, with his mother on piano and his father on lead guitar. Through out his Elementary, Jr. High and High School years, he learned to play many percussion instruments including Clarinet and Piano. While attending Lynwood High School he was part of many organizations such as Gospel Choir, <br/>Entertainment Club, Marching Band, Jazz Band, The Lynwood High School Chorus, and Stage Crew.&nbsp; As a member of these organizations, he learned the fundamentals of live recording, lighting and sound, and motion picture/audio synchronization.&nbsp; With music embedded in his soul, he started producing music for a local rap group.&nbsp; It wasn&#8217;t long after teaming up with the group that he started to compose lyric&#8217;s of his own and recorded his very own demo adopting the name \"Mr. DaLicks\".&nbsp; After many, many meetings with A&R directors and record company executives he decided to venture off and start his <br/>own recording company.&nbsp; With the financial help of a family member, he bought a studio and began working on his album.&nbsp; Mr. DaLicks freshman album entitled, &#8220;My Struggles&#8221; has been labeled as a \"G-Funk Classic\". His unique style and sound has provided him with the <br/>opportunity to work with many celebrities, such as, Ice Cube, Coolie O, Domino, Bad Azz, Public Announcement, Ricky Bell, Mc. Smooth, Daz, E White, RBX, Snoop Dogg, Kurupt and Jayo Felony and more. To hear his music and see him perform is a marvelous sight to see.&nbsp; He has always known that the music industry and entertaining is where he belongs, so he works very hard to make sure the public sees him and his musical talent as one. <br/></p><br/>\r\n<p><br/></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=79\" target=\"_blank\">Join Mr. Dalicks\' discussion</a><br/></p>',1,'',0,''),(525,565,'Power 2 Move',5,27,'www.myspace.com/power2move','','','<font color=\"#990000\"><strong>Power 2 Move</strong> </font>\r\n<p><font color=\"#990000\"><b>Power 2 Move</b> is the dynamic duo of producer <b>Themi Charalambous</b> (from Electrik Pulse) and vocal powerhouse <b>Amber Dirks</b>, who have brought their unique talents and extensive musical experience to the table to form the hottest, fastest rising group in the dance music industry today. </font></p>\r\n<p><font color=\"#990000\"><b>Themi&#8217;s</b> remix of <b>Chris &#8220;The Greek&#8221; Panaghi&#8217;s</b> &#8220;The Time&#8221; soared to the #5 spot on the Billboard Club Play Dance Chart in 2007 as did his remix of <b>Chris &#8220;The Greek&#8221; Panaghi</b> track&#8220;Pump&#8221;. Themi has also worked his remixing magic on producing and remixing singles by numerous dance recording artists including <b>Collage</b>, <b>Damian Wild</b>, <b>Matheos</b>, and <b>Raquela</b>. </font></p>\r\n<p><font color=\"#990000\"><b>Amber</b> has performed extensively as part of the legendary singing group <b>&#8220;Sister Sledge&#8221;</b> and her soaring unique &#8220;rip the roof off&#8221; vocal style has earned her international acclaim. She has performed with an array of notable entertainers including <b>Roberta Flack</b>, <b>Gladys Knight</b>, <b>Michael Bubl&eacute;</b>, <b>Destiny&#8217;s Child</b>, and <b>Macy Gray</b>. </font></p>\r\n<p><font color=\"#990000\"><b>Power 2 Move</b> has been hard at work in the studio finishing up their debut E.P. release entitled the <b>&#8220;Passions EP&#8221;</b>. Recently the new songs from this EP were featured prominently on the hit Fox series show &#8220;Nanny 911&#8221;, which led to the up and coming group inking their current recording deal with <b>Amathus Music</b>. </font></p>\r\n<p><font color=\"#990000\"><b>Power 2 Move</b> is now working on a full length album project to be released in the near future. </font></p>\r\n<p><font color=\"#990000\"><b>ABOUT THEMI</b> </font></p>\r\n<p><font color=\"#990000\"><b>Themi Charalambous</b>, aka <b>Electrik Pulse</b>, discovered his passion for music as a kid growing up in Queens, NY, a passion fueled by the funky sounds of artists such as <b>Afrika Bambaataa</b> (Zulu Nation), <b>C&C Music Factory</b>, <b>Jam Master Jay</b>, <b>David Morales</b> and <b>Todd Terry</b>. <b>Themi&#8217;s</b> childhood dreams of one day creating his own music were soon destined to come true. </font></p>\r\n<p><font color=\"#990000\"><b>Themi&#8217;s</b> professional career started at the age of 15 when his mixing skills as a local house party DJ began to create a buzz, and the young aspiring DJ soon found his considerable skills in great demand. At 17, he decided to try his hand at writing some original melodies and lyrics and realized that it was not enough - he also wanted to be able to create and produce the backing music to complete his compositions, so he picked up a keyboard and taught himself how to play by ear. </font></p>\r\n<p><font color=\"#990000\"><i>\"It is amazing when you can sit in front of a keyboard or piano and just play what you&#8217;re feeling at that moment\"</i> <b>Themi</b> says. </font></p>\r\n<p><font color=\"#990000\">This one man dynamo soon taught himself to play other instruments as well, including the piano, and it wasn&#8217;t long before he was writing and composing songs, arranging music, and engineering and mixing his own tracks. </font></p>\r\n<p><font color=\"#990000\">One of <b>Themi&#8217;s</b> first professional endeavors, as half of the production team known as <b>&#8220;Big City Groove&#8221;</b> led to his contract with <b>Amathus Music</b> and resulted in the international hit, &#8220;Cries In The Night&#8221; featuring guest vocalist <b>Ezra Blue</b>. &#8220;Cries In The Night&#8221; debuted to rave reviews and was featured in clubs and DJ mixshows worldwide, as well as being included on the Abercrombie & Fitch retail in-store playlist and receiving coveted airplay on the nation&#8217;s # 1 Dance Music Station, New York City&#8217;s WKTU FM. </font></p>\r\n<p><font color=\"#990000\">After several subsequent singles, <b>Themi&#8217;s</b> remix of <b>Chris &#8220;The Greek&#8221; Panaghi&#8217;s</b> &#8220;The Time&#8221; soared to the #5 spot on the Billboard Club Play Dance Chart, and in January of 2007, Themi&#8217;s remix of the scorching <b>Chris &#8220;The Greek&#8221; Panaghi</b> track &#8220;Pump&#8221; debuted in the #1 Breakout spot on the Billboard Dance Chart. He has collaborated with several notable producers and record labels in the dance genre, including <b>Sweet Rains</b> and <b>Chris &#8220;The Greek&#8221; Panaghi</b>, (who has worked with major artists including <b>Celine Dion</b>, <b>Jessica Simpson</b> and <b>Christina Aguilera</b>). <b>Themi\'s</b> collaboration with <b>Chris \"The Greek\"</b> and artist <b>Raquela</b> landed him a spot on the hottest trance compilation of 2006, &#8220;Working The Mix&#8221; on the Water Dance Music label through <b>Universal Records</b>. </font></p>\r\n<p><font color=\"#990000\"><b>Themi</b> is currently working on new material with international recording artist <b>Damian Wild</b>, and the hit Fox series <b>&#8220;Nanny 911&#8221;</b> prominently featured several of <b>Themi&#8217;s</b> tracks in February 2007. Themi has also partnered with spectacular vocalist <b>Amber Dirks</b> to form the group <b>Power 2 Move</b>. Amber has performed extensively as part of the legendary singing group <b>&#8220;Sister Sledge&#8221;</b> and her soaring unique &#8220;rip the roof off&#8221; vocal style has earned her international acclaim. <b>Power To Move</b> is working on a full length album project to be released in the near future. <b>Themi</b> is a true believer that hard work, determination and not letting go of your dream are key factors on the road to success. </font></p>\r\n<p><font color=\"#990000\"><i>\"It\'s all for the love of music,\"</i> <b>Themi</b> explains. From a humble beginning in Queens to the number one spot on the Billboard chart, <b>Themi</b> has truly found the power to move as he continues to rise to new heights in the dance music world. </font>\r\n</p><p><font color=\"#990000\"><b>ABOUT AMBER</b> </font>\r\n</p><p><font color=\"#990000\"></font>\r\n</p><p><font color=\"#990000\">Vocal powerhouse <b>AMBER DIRKS</b> was born in Holland and raised in New York City. While still in her teens, <b>AMBER</b> decided to leave the bright lights of New York City and head out west in search of fame and fortune. It wasn&#8217;t long before her strong, &#8220;rip the roof off&#8221; vocal style whisked her through the door and the professional singing career she had always dreamed of had finally begun. </font></p>\r\n<p><font color=\"#990000\"><b>AMBER&#8217;S</b> cross-country gamble paid off in the studios of Phoenix and Los Angeles where she quickly began working for several hit-making producers including <b>Richard Shear</b> (Stephanie Mills, Brenda K. Starr) and <b>Nick Trevesick</b> (5 Star). Her considerable vocal skills impressed producers and remix masters <b>R.K. Jackson</b> (CeCe Peniston) and <b>Marcus Schulz</b>, who eagerly recruited AMBER as the vocalist on the Plastik Records release \"Do You Want Me\". <b>AMBER</b> was also a featured vocalist on <b>Motown</b> recording artist <b>Eddie Minninfield\'s</b> Christmas album.</font></p>\r\n<p><font color=\"#990000\"><b>AMBER</b> has provided backing vocals for an array of notable entertainers including <b>Roberta Flack, KC & The Sunshine Band and A&M recording artist Malaika</b>. As a touring member of the classic group <b>Sister Sledge</b>, <b>AMBER</b> has traveled extensively in the US and abroad, performing in front of tens of thousands of adoring fans. With <b>Sister Sledge</b>, <b>AMBER</b> has had the pleasure of sharing the stage with some of the music industry&#8217;s premiere recording artists including <b>Gladys Knight, Michael Bubl&eacute;, Destiny&#8217;s Child, Macy Gray, Martha Wash (C&C Music Factory & The Weather Girls)</b> and <b>Chic</b>. <b>AMBER\'S</b> musical experience also includes a lengthy tour of South America with Latin recording sensation <b>Raphael,</b>. With <b>Sister Sledge</b>, <b>AMBER</b> appeared at the <b>\"Disco Fever to Race to Erase MS 2006\"</b> and along with superstar <b>Natalie Cole</b>, helped kick off the Grand Finale, \"Lean On Me\". After hearing <b>AMBER</b> lead off the second verse, industry legend <b>David Foster</b> singled out <b>AMBER\'S</b> voice for praise. </font></p>\r\n<p><font color=\"#990000\"><b>AMBER</b> has also appeared on <b>BET</b>, <b>VH1</b> and has sung the National Anthem at numerous major televised sporting events. Her exotic blend of talent and beauty won her a spot as a former <b>Miss Black USA</b> finalist representing the state of Arizona. </font></p>\r\n<p><font color=\"#990000\">Some of <b>AMBER&#8217;S</b> earliest influences growing up were the soulful stylings of strong female artists including <b>Whitney Houston</b>, <b>Anita Baker</b>, <b>Toni Braxton</b>, <b>Etta James</b>, <b>Chaka Khan</b> and <b>Aretha Franklin</b>. </font>\r\n</p><p><font color=\"#990000\"><b>AMBER</b> is currently recording with dynamic hitmaster <b>Electrik Pulse</b> (aka Themi Charalambous). Together they have formed the group <b><a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/power2move\">Power 2 Move</a></b> and are collaborating on material for a full length album. <b>AMBER</b> has also contributed vocals on upcoming projects by artists including <b>Heathrow Project</b> and <b>Joni Sledge</b> (Sister Sledge), and on a remake of the mid-90&#8217;s dance hit &#8220;Sweet Dreams&#8221; by <b>LaBouche</b>. <b>AMBER&#8217;S</b> strong, smoky vocals on Sweet Dreams 2007, on the German-based <b>Fahrenheit-Music</b>, bring a new 21st century flavor to the classic dance track. </font></p>\r\n<p><font color=\"#990000\"><b>AMBER</b> continues to prove without a doubt that with a combination of talent, drive and determination, sweet dreams really do come true. </font></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=80\">Join Power 2 Move\'s discussion</a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(526,478,'Ashton Zyer',1,61,'','','','I don&#8217;t want to bore you with the details of how or when I started\r\nplaying. Just like I could care less if you knew I won some\r\ninternational songwriting competition or if I opened for a multi\r\nplatinum recording artist. And if I did tell you that, would it make\r\nyou like me more? If so then I have failed as an artist. You see I\r\nwanted you to come feel what I was thinking, or to be part of my mind\r\nfor about 3:50 sec or so, just enough for you to hang out and\r\nunderstand the journey. I am not the kind of person who sits around all\r\nday and writes song after song after song. The songs usually take some\r\ntime to form in my head or on paper. When I sit down to write, I\r\nusually want to work out some issue that is unresolved. This could be\r\nabout me, but it most likely could be about you. Maybe something you\r\nsaid to me yesterday that has made me think things are not as they\r\nseem. The Queen of paper trails sounds like a great way to describe me\r\nwhen it comes to the way I compose lyrics. I may write something one\r\nway and feel it&#8217;s not quite right and will cross out idea, after idea,\r\nafter idea. Any piece of scrap paper will do. This means I could have a\r\nridiculous mound of paper by the time I finish a song. A piece of paper\r\nmay only contain one line of lyrics. Words seem to come and go so\r\nquickly in my head and I refuse to take the time to write in a linear\r\nfashion. I have lost brilliant lyrics because I didn&#8217;t have a piece of\r\npaper and pen handy. I think sticky notes were Gods gift to women. I\r\ndon&#8217;t have any musical influences. In fact sometimes I will go without\r\nlistening to music for days, and I very rarely listen to the radio. I\r\nam a misfit in a band of musical Pop Culture goo roos. There are days\r\nwhen music distracts my own creating process, and times when it\r\ninspires. When I finish a piece I very rarely go back to it. I try and\r\nforget the melody and chord progressions completely so I can be free\r\nand open for a new way of thinking and writing. I fail a lot of times,\r\nwhich makes success taste so much sweeter in the end. I hope you come\r\nvisit me often, on-line and in concert. I hope you feel free to come\r\nand tell me a good story. Everybody needs a good story to save them\r\nfrom their own reality. Who knows, your story could be my next\r\ncreation. And if you love this music, please share it with everyone you\r\nknow. Music has little to no purpose if it can&#8217;t be felt or heard in\r\nthe mind or heart.<br/><br/><br/><br/>\r\n<object height=\"350\" width=\"425\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/WyhMYLRDrgQ\"/><param name=\"wmode\" value=\"transparent\"/><embed \r\nsrc=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/WyhMYLRDrgQ\" \r\ntype=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" wmode=\"transparent\" width=\"425\" \r\nheight=\"350\"/></object><br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=81\">Join Ashton\'s discussion</a><br/>',0,'',0,''),(527,566,'Ball in the House',9,41,'www.ballinthehouse.com','','','Following in the path of classic harmony groups like Boyz II Men, the Temptations and Take 6 but with a modern, urban, post-millennial twist, the five member vocal band Ball in the House brilliantly blends a wide range of influences, from classic R&B to pop, hip-hop and gospel. Ball in the House is a five-man soul-pop/R&B vocal a Capella group from Boston. With their extensive tour schedule (averaging 250 dates a year), Ball in the House reaches millions and is arguably one of the most successful indie bands working today. They have opened and performed with such artists as Gladys Knight, 98&deg;, Jessica Simpson, Blondie, The Temptations, Smokie Robinson, Kool & the Gang, and numerous others. They can be heard on national TV and radio as the voices behind the Cool Whip commercials. Their first radio single, Something I Dont Know, charted for six (6) consecutive weeks in the Top 100 on the national AC Charts, peaking at ..17. Their single, Change Face, from the Think About It EP, is currently receiving radio adds all over the country as well as international and local video adds. \"Get It Together\", their latest single released exclusively online through burnlounge soared to the ..1 slot for the week March 7th, 2006. With burnlougne.com\'s song catalog of over 1.5 million songs including artists like Black Eyed Peas, Coldplay, Kelly Clarkson and James Blunt, this is an unprecedented achievement for an independent band.<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=82\">Join Ball in the House\'s discussion</a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(528,567,'Jay Durfey',1,71,'virb.com/jaydurfey','','','\r\n<p class=\"style2\" align=\"center\">Jay has been playing guitar for about 28 years now, but has added computers and synths to his lineup just about 5 years ago. He has found that merging different technologies and sounds has greatly amped up the creative process. </p>\r\n<p class=\"style2\" align=\"center\"><span class=\"style7\"><em>With no combination off limits, I like to blend genres as well as organic and electronic sounds into one track. A mix of loop based beats and sequences with live guitar, electric violin and keyboards.</em></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"style2\" align=\"center\">\"Jay Durfey seeks to convey a feeling of intimacy through intricacy. Exploring the creative freedom of composing and recording with his guitars and a vast array of virtual instruments, Jay strives to strike a balance between organic and electronic musical elements. The result in this is an eclectic mix of guitar-infused electronica which evokes vast and verdant soundscapes of the imagination. From the brightly illuminated to the dark and brooding, from the lightly ethereal to the bold and intense, each sound, each melody and ambient effect is united to create a panorama of sounds in seasons, of flowing waters and aquatic life, and of the ever-present contrast between the dynamics of nature and those of the world of technology. The music is powerful, thought provoking, and ultimately comforting as it brings these diverse elements together into a deep and enriching listening experience.\" <br/><br/><br/><em><strong>Scott </strong></em><a class=\"style7\" href=\"http://www.darkryders.com/darkryders/Indexx.html\"><em><strong>\"Dark Ryders\"</strong></em></a><em><strong> Graves, CREEM Magazine contributing writer, 1976-78.</strong></em></p><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=83\">Join Jay\'s discussion</a><br/>',0,'',0,''),(530,571,'Cosmic Silk Project',1,77,'www.myspace.com/cosmicsilkproject','959 Mocksville Hwy.','704-872-2621','\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\">Hello and Welcome. I hope you enjoy your visit here to my site and will leave a comment so we may become friends. But please PASS ME By if you have No interest in reviewing each others music and writing talents, want to post cursing on my site, are full of hate, practice RACISIM, or just adding numbers to your site. I like all creative ideas, have many varied friends and styles of musical tastes. That being said for those who don\'t already know me from my many sites here on the web, Cosmic Silk Project is my brain running amuck. I play all the instruments, write the lyrics and write all the music parts. I do all the production work myself on my in home studio. I use a Boss BR-1600 CD Workstation. A Focusrrite Trackmaster Pro preamp, a Lexicon MX-400 reverbs and delays unit, a BBE Dual Compressor with built in Sonic Maximizer and a Audio-Technica 3035 microphone for all vocals. I use various effects pedals to achive the Guitars with no preamps (I uesed only my Oldfield Marquis 50) and run the Bass through the BR-1600 amps with no preamps. The only instrument I do not play is drums. For this I use Discrete Drums drum loops that came with the Boss BR-1600. I do my own production work and my wife designs all of the art I use on our sites. Yes, she is a big part of this too. Any time you want to email me with your ideas or thoughts or post them here on my site you are most welcome to do so. In fact I love hearing from each of you. Special thanks to Paul @ Oldfied Tube Amps (www.oldfieldtubeamps.com) for making the best amp I have ever played thru (the awesome Oldfield Marquis 50 w/ Tone Tubby Hempcone speakers that Paul put in) and Charlie @ Tone Tubby Hempcone Speakers (ttub@abrown.com) for his patience in answering all my questions.<?xml:namespace prefix = o /><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: \'Times New Roman\'\">Member of ASCAP<br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=84\" target=\"_blank\">Join Cosmic Silk Project\'s discussion</a><br/></span>',1,'',0,''),(542,584,'Machine',1,71,'www.machineband.com','','','<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=110\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Machine\'s fans</span></a>',1,'',0,''),(531,573,'Simple Life',1,61,'www.simple-life.de','Gumbertstr.102','00492112201400','Simple Life, these are easy to remember and emotional melodies which are stamped, above all, by the unique voices full of character of Bernd Barano and James T. Jackson jun. With a soulful interpretation of her songs it creates the duet to appeal to the listeners.<br/><br/>Bernd Barano - the guitar belongs since the 6-th year to the life of Bernd Barano and his voice was laid to him in the cradle. As a head of his band Missing Link founded in 1985, he celebrated results in whole Europe. With the song \"Claim of Love\" Missing Link was more than 52 weeks in the charts. The album \" World of fantasy \" went for 235,000 spots about the store bar. In the year 2000 Bernd Barano and James T. Jackson jun. founded Simple Life. <br/>James T. Jackson jun. grew up in New York, in the Bronx. His life is stamped since that time by the music. His voice is not to be imagined as not existing by Simple Life any more. In the USA he <br/>cooperated as a singer and percussionist with musical projects with Aretha Franklin, George Benson and Chaka Khan.<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=85\">Join Simple Life\'s discussion</a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(534,576,'AJ SLICK',6,106,'WWW.AJSLICK.NET','8328 ridgeway street','267-269-4875','Hi my names is A.J. Slick i\'ve been playing guitar all my life.i ve played with acts such as Rick Danko from the Band, Cinderella,Tommy Conwell,Richie Havens,Sonny Rhoads,and many more artist.I try to take my style of playing from my biggest influences, which are very many&nbsp;artist&nbsp;such as Jimi Hendrix,Eddie Van Halen,Randy Rhoads,Stevie Ray Vaughan,Yngwie Malmsteen,B.B.King,Albert King,Skynyrd, JoeSatriani,Steve Vai,Jimmy Page,Frank Marino,and like i said over the years ive seen many great guitar players who&nbsp;inspired me to want to get better at my art.I try to play my own style of blues rock by taking a little from every guitar player i just mention.I hope who ever listen to my music that &nbsp;they really get what im trying to exspress i try to always play from my heart and in this crazy&nbsp; music bissness sometimes when you play from your heart it is very hard to get any where cause i refuse to sell out and play bubble gum music.<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Peace A.J. Slick<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=87\">Join AJ\'s discussion</a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(535,575,'Shadows Lie',1,74,'shadowslie.com','117 Hester Street','(917) 312-5829','<pre><tt><tt><br/><br/><br/><span style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-weight: bold;\">Rising from the New York City underground, the music<br/>of Shadows Lie is a dark, intense blend of heavy<br/>guitars reminiscent of Staind, Portishead-like<br/>electronics, <span style=\"border-bottom: 1px dashed rgb(0, 102, 204); cursor: pointer; height: 1em;\" id=\"lw_1184874807_0\">Days of the New</span> type acoustic guitars and<br/>vocal stylings ranging from <span style=\"border-bottom: 1px dashed rgb(0, 102, 204); cursor: pointer; height: 1em;\" id=\"lw_1184874807_1\">Tori Amos</span> to Incubus. The<br/>songwriting is distinctive and intensely emotional,<br/>yet concise and mature at the same time.  <br/><br/>Singer/songwriter Kira Leigh and producer/songwriter<br/>C.T. have been described as \"Talented songwriters who<br/>fuse guitar rock with electronica\" by Bob Leone,<br/>Director of the Songwriter\'s Hall of Fame and were<br/>selected to perform in the SHOF Showcase in 2005. <br/>They also have worked with Multi-platinum<br/>Producer/Engineer, Bill Klatt (Days of The New,<br/>Garbage, <span style=\"border-bottom: 1px dashed rgb(0, 102, 204); cursor: pointer; height: 1em;\" id=\"lw_1184874807_2\">Jay-Z</span>) who said about Shadows Lie, \"This is<br/>one of the most talented and promising new rock acts<br/>to come out of <span style=\"border-bottom: 1px dashed rgb(0, 102, 204); background: transparent none repeat scroll 0% 50%;    cursor: pointer; height: 1em;\" id=\"lw_1184874807_3\">New York City</span> in years. They are a<br/>truly talented songwriting duo with a unique sound<br/>that is all their own.\"<br/><br/>Their 2007 debut LP entitled \"Echoes\" is written,<br/>recorded, produced and performed by Kira and CT. The<br/>fusion of Kira\'s  lyrics and vocal melodies and CT\'s<br/>guitar, bass, programming and production work form the<br/>basis of a fresh sound that uniquely melds sonic<br/>strength and emotional vulnerability.  Kira and CT<br/>site among their diverse influences, <span style=\"border-bottom: 1px dashed rgb(0, 102, 204); cursor: pointer; height: 1em;\" id=\"lw_1184874807_4\">Tori Amos</span>, Tool,<br/>Incubus, Alice In Chains, <span style=\"border-bottom: 1px dashed rgb(0, 102, 204); cursor: pointer; height: 1em;\" id=\"lw_1184874807_5\">Bjork</span> and The <span style=\"border-bottom: 1px dashed rgb(0, 102, 204); cursor: pointer; height: 1em;\" id=\"lw_1184874807_6\">Crystal<br/>Method</span>.  The often times aggressive yet hauntingly<br/>beautiful music  that results, invokes comparisons to<br/><span style=\"border-bottom: 1px dashed rgb(0, 102, 204); cursor: pointer; height: 1em;\" id=\"lw_1184874807_7\">Alanis Morissette</span>, fellow female-fronted rock bands<br/>Evanescence and <span style=\"border-bottom: 1px dashed rgb(0, 102, 204); background: transparent none repeat scroll 0% 50%;    cursor: pointer; height: 1em;\" id=\"lw_1184874807_8\">Lacuna Coil</span>.  <br/><br/>For their live show and for the music to come, Kira<br/>and CT are joined by Frank Grullon     on guitars and<br/>Marco Britti on Drums.<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.shadowslie.com/\"><span id=\"lw_1184874807_9\">www.Shadowslie.com</span></a><br/><br/><br/><br/></span></tt></tt><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=88\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Join Shadows Lie\'s discussion</span></a><tt><tt><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.shadowslie.com/\"><span id=\"lw_1184874807_9\"></span></a></tt></tt></pre>',1,'',0,''),(536,579,'Dan Morgan',8,40,'','','603-540-9909','\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font size=\"3\">Dan Morgan. Has been described as one of the best singer song writers in <st1:place>New England</st1:place>.</font></h3>\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font size=\"3\">He has won numerous national awards i.e. Song writer of the year, male entertainer, male vocalist, and country cd of the year. He has been playing and writing music from the age of 6 years old when his father showed him his first chord. He will not tell you he&#8217;s a great guitar player. He just likes to play, write songs and take the audience on a musical journey with him.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span></font></h3>\r\n<div style=\"border-style: none none solid; padding: 0in 0in 1pt;\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"border: medium none ; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; padding: 0in;\"><o:p><font size=\"2\">&nbsp;</font></o:p></p></div>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><o:p><font size=\"2\">&nbsp;</font></o:p></p>\r\n<h1 style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font size=\"3\">Dan Morgan <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">has performed for audiences across the </span><st1:country-region><st1:place><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">U.S.</span></st1:place></st1:country-region><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\"> and overseas, and has opened for the following featured acts:<o:p></o:p></span></font></h1>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><o:p><font size=\"2\">&nbsp;</font></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font size=\"2\">Johnny Cash<span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>John Berry</font></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font size=\"2\">Sawyer Brown<span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Ricky Scaggs</font></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font size=\"2\">Willie Nelson<span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Pam Tillis</font></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font size=\"2\">Linda Davis<span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Lori Morgan</font></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><o:p><font size=\"2\">&nbsp;</font></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><b style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Dan Morgan&#8217;s</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"> music can be described as a mix of folk and acoustic rock. With acoustic guitar and undeniable rhythm, this combination of cadence and creative lyrics is displayed at his live performances.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font size=\"3\">The unique sound, with guitar riffs attacked from every angle, addictive rhythms and compelling changes, represents a wealth of country and folk music styles. Dan has the instinctive ability to connect with many genres of music, thereby shaping and molding it into his own making.</font></h3><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=89\">Join Dan\'s discussion</a><br/><br/>',1,'',0,''),(538,581,'saintoutprojects',11,52,'www.showcaseyourmusic.com/SAINTOUTPROJECTS','','','<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=94\">Join Saint Out Projects discusson</a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(537,580,'Jam City Revue - featuring LadyG',6,31,'www.jamwave.com/ladygtx','104 w emory st.','9039349880','Hi, my name is Gloria Lady_g Hall I was Born and raised in a small city called Marshall Tx I\'m the youngest child of three my mother raised three children alone, two girls one boy. we didn\'t have a lot growing up cause it was very hard back then for a woman to raise and keep four fed and clothed but my moms did it. I remeber one thing we always had and never ran out of and that was music and lots of love my mother loved to listen to blues every chance she got so I guess you could say the I grew up on the blues. I remember listening and learning the words to all the songs she played, my sister and brother liked them too, but for me it was more than just listening I became a walking jukebox full of the blues. As a teen I had developed my vocal skills, in school I took any and everything that had to do with music like choir and band. I\'m living the single life and loving it.. Other than singing around the house I joined several Gospel groups. Then I joined my church and <br/>became a member of the choir this is where I really gained alot of exposure I loved it, yet I still longed for something and I believe it was that old&nbsp; trying to resurface The Blues. So I came in contact with some sweet and carring people who heard me sing the blues and said to me, girl you been sittin down on your gift so then I thought to myself let me give this a try so I sat down one day and decided to do some writing and before I knew it I had written 8 songs. I knew this guy kin kin Kinny Miles who composes music and he got busy and came up with the music I needed for my songs, so now I\'m getting ready to go into the studio and record my first CD intitled Tell Me What You wanna Do I\'m really excited about it and believe it can be a success, pray with me and for me. So look for me soon because as Dianna Ross said in the lyrics of one of her songs I\'m comming outtttttttttt.&nbsp;<br/>&nbsp;<br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=90\">Join Jam City\'s discussion</a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(539,578,'Boggy Creek',8,38,'http://www.boggy-creek.com','PO Box 121783','3525363105','<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 11pt\" class=\"MsoBodyText\">\r\n<strong><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Book Antiqua\'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Craig Wise and Jamie Lee Beland are the main performers for Boggy Creek.&nbsp;They take their show to the next level by breaking off from the conventional, and taking the show straight to the audience.&nbsp; This allows them to bring the audience into the spotlight and on the stage with them. Which in turn will get the people involved, and this make a very entertaining and rewarding show. Their type of performance has been well received by all who attend.&nbsp; </span></strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 11pt\" class=\"MsoBodyText\">\r\n<strong><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Book Antiqua\'\"><span>&nbsp; </span><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>There original music is modeled after a more traditional style, with a new country edge to it. The songs have catchy rhythm and jingles in them that stay with you even having never heard it before. They have captivated a variety of different audiences throughout the southeast</span></strong><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Book Antiqua\'\"></span></strong><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Book Antiqua\'\">. At live shows, there songs gain momentum with a few improvised sections added, to give the audience a memorable and high energy show for all.<span>&nbsp; </span></span></strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 11pt\" class=\"MsoBodyText\">\r\n<strong><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Book Antiqua\'\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span>&nbsp;</span>Craig Wise is at the end of the production of their first CD. He has test marketed their music in several local night clubs. The DJ&rsquo;s have said they have been well received and that two of his songs have line dances written to them. Their live performances have also been well received throughout </span></strong><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Book Antiqua\'\">the south</span></strong><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Book Antiqua\'\">. Boggy Creek has built a substantial fan base in the area and have excellent response at all their shows. They have been able to fill the clubs to capacity for the last several years.</span></strong> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 11pt\" class=\"MsoBodyText\">\r\n<strong><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Book Antiqua\'\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Boggy Creek has been performing&nbsp;</span></strong><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Book Antiqua\'\"> for over six years. They have played at several different types of venues, from small clubs, to the larger Night Clubs, to corporate parties, colleges,&nbsp; festivals and fairs. Boggy Creek has collected a number of fans in the last six years.&nbsp; They are a six piece country band that has one male and one female that front the band. They also have a strong three and four part harmonies.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n</span></strong><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Book Antiqua\'\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Boggy Creek has signed with All Wise Records go to <a href=\"http://www.dandmrecords.com\">www.allwiserecords.com</a> to check us out.&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n</span></span></strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 11pt\" class=\"MsoBodyText\">\r\n<strong><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Book Antiqua\'\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></strong><strong><font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Book Antiqua\'\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></font></strong> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\" class=\"MsoNormal\">\r\n<strong><font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Book Antiqua\'\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n</span></span></font></strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\" class=\"MsoNormal\">\r\n<strong><font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Book Antiqua\'\"><span><a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=91\" target=\"_blank\">Join Boggy Creek&#39;s discussion</a>&nbsp;</span></span></font></strong> \r\n</p>\r\n',1,'<p>\r\n<font face=\"Courier New\"><br />\r\n</font>&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n',0,''),(1373,989,'bfm',1,14,'','','','<body>test</body>',1,'',0,''),(540,583,'Blind Revenge',1,14,'myspace.com/blindrevenge1','49 Soldier Pond Road','207-834-3499','Blind Revenge is a three member band comprised of 15 year old drumming sensation Shawn Parker, 16 year old bassist and lead singer Curtis Collin, and 16 year old lead guitarist Jesse Pinette. Formed in January 2006, these young musical phenoms have already gained a huge following within the music circuit. With musical influences such as Unlucky Joe, Atreyu, Breaking Benjamin, Godsmack, Slipknot, Ozzy Osbourne, and Chiodos, this self-proclaimed Rock/Metal trio has a repertoire that suites all ages.<br/><br/>On April 20, 2006, Blind Revenge\'s original demo, \"Love Me\" was featured in \"The Backyard Buzz\" on radio station 101.9FM. Their second original \"Better Mistake\" was featured a few weeks later.<br/><br/>In May, 2006, Blind Revenge was awarded the title of \"Battle of The Teen Bands Grand Champions\" for Maine\'s Rock The Valley, \"St. John Valley\'s Greatest Rock Music Extravaganza!\" This win entitled Blind Revenge the opportunity to become the opening band for the \"Rock The Valley\" festival in July, 2006, and share the same stage as National Recording Artists Blue Oyster Cult, and Dead Season. For more information, visit <i>www.rockthevalley.org</i><br/><br/><br/>\r\n<center><i>\"You guys went all out. It looks like you really wanted to win this competition. If you keep it up, you\'re going to make it big.\"</i> <br/>- <b>\"Rock The Valley\" Judge.</b><br/><br/><i>\"I don\'t know any of you, but I love your music. Can I have your babies?\" </i><br/>- <b>Kristen, Vermont</b><br/><br/><i>\"All I can say is \'wow\', and... I just peed myself.\"</i> <br/>- <b>Justin Michaud (RTV Judge)</b><br/><br/><i>\"Blind Revenge makes me all warm and fuzzy on the inside.\"</i> <br/><b>Mary, Illinois.</b><br/><br/><br/>\"We\'re just three guys who love music, and playing it. That\'s about it.\"<br/></center><br/>\r\n<center><big><b><font size=\"3\">Bands we\'ve shared stage with:</font></b></big></center><br/>- Cafeen <br/>- Neverstood <br/>- Unforgiven Memories<br/>- Everyday Fallout<br/>-The Geeks <br/>- Vice Grip <br/>- Black Noise <br/>- The Geeks<br/>- Ryven<br/>- The Avery Project<br/>- Colorblind<br/>- The Fallside<br/>- Stash<br/>- Under Pressure<br/>-Stunt Machine<br/>- Downstar<br/>- Last Stitch Failure<br/>- Remedy<br/>- Django <br/>- Burnsteen<br/>- <b><u>Dead Season</u></b><br/>- Dominic & The Lucid<br/>- Comadose<br/>- <b><u>Unlucky Joe<br/>- <b><u>Believer</u></b><br/>- United Jumbo Band<br/>- Zig-Zag<br/>- Relapse<br/>- <b><u>Thornbird</u></b><br/>- <b><u>Blue Oyster Cult <br/><br/></u></b></u></b><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=92\">Join Blind Revenge\'s discussion</a><b><u><b><u><br/></u></b></u></b>',1,'',0,''),(543,587,'Fear Of Clowns',7,83,'www.fearofclownsband.com','','','<p align=\"center\">Gripping vocals, shredding lyrics and a strangely optimistic melancholy are the twisted backbone of Fear Of Clowns debut effort, \"Coulrophobia\". A percussive, jagged metal album capable of leaving emo fans shaking, punkers with their jaws on the floor, housewives quivering, and alterna-kids feeling hip for a second or two, \"Coulrophobia\" is as pure and emotional as metal gets. With thick layers of intrumentation combining the rhythmic force of a runaway freight train and a vocal style that\'s brutal, beautiful, and pure. In your face, sophisticated, controlled, mayhem. All while crafting a tightly produced, hook-laden metal album. </p>\r\n<center>\r\n<center>The live show that is Fear Of Clowns, takes you on a frantic rollercoaster ride that is pure adrenalin. Performances are visually stunning, theatrical, and sonically cohesive. Using their performance knowledge to the fullest to draw the crowd into a heightened state of aggression, only to erupt in a full on meltdown of spent humanity. \r\n<center>Fear Of Clowns has leveled audiences throughout the Midwest and continues to increase their fan base through hard work, determination, and most important, an undying passion for metal. \r\n<center>This is the band you\'ll always come back to when you need release. This is the genius of Peoria, Illinois\' Fear Of Clowns! <br/>Can also be seen on YOUTUBE.com<br/>www.myspace.com/fearofclownsband<br/><br/>CD\'s can be purchased @ www.CDBABY.com<br/>or on Apple iTunes and many other digital distribution sites including Napster, AudioLunchbox, Mp3 Tunes, MuchMusic, Rhapsody, GroupieTunes & Muze. \r\n<center><br/><br/>&nbsp;</center></center></center></center></center><script type=\"text/javascript\"     src=\"swfobject.js\">\r\n</script>\r\n<div id=\"flashcontent\" align=\"center\">\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: bold; font-size: 14pt;\">You need to upgrade your Flash Player to at<br/>least version 7 to view this video content.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.adobe.com/flashplayer/\">Click here to download the latest version of Flash Player</a>.</p></div><script type=\"text/javascript\">\r\n// <![CDATA[\r\nvar so = new SWFObject(\"flvplayer.swf?theFile=http://www.bestofbands.com/uploads/587/PullYouDown.flv&defaultImage=graphic.jpg&theVolume=100&startPlayingOnload=no&popUpHelp=no&bufferSeconds=2&videoSmoothing=yes\",\"flvplayer\",\"320\",\"255\",\"7\",\"#000000\");\r\nso.addParam(\"movie\",\"flvplayer.swf?theFile=http://www.bestofbands.com/uploads/587/PullYouDown.flv&defaultImage=graphic.jpg&theVolume=100&startPlayingOnload=no&popUpHelp=no&bufferSeconds=2&videoSmoothing=yes\");\r\nso.addParam(\"bgcolor\",\"#000000\");\r\nso.write(\"flashcontent\");\r\n// ]]>\r\n</script>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=111\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Fear Of Clowns\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1504,1886,'KADEN',9,41,'http://myspace.com/kadenmusic','','','Here&#39;s my attempt at letting you in. \r\nIf you don&#39;t know me yet, you might be thinking that I&#39;m just another one of those struggling artists who ended up in Hollywood. You might be half right on that but there is so much more to me. As much as I&#39;d like to change your mind, I do realize that virtually everyone has labels hung over them and would like to remove them. The truth is we are all larger than the labels people give us to confine and define us. So who needs them, I try not to put myself or others in a box, even though this about me area is for doing just that. Instead of defending myself, I would like to give you the opportunity to find out a little about me. \r\nIt&#39;s hard to put your finger around what you&#39;d have to do in order to feel you are a success in life, the answer is different from person to person. For me, I need to use my voice to help, sing words that come from my soul, perform, and never let the passion in me die. I will try to be aware of my impact on others and find ways to improve the lives of those I love. I will always fight to spread light into a world that at times looks very dark, that&#39;s where my phrase &quot;Keep it Burning&quot; came from. That&#39;s also the title I have given to my upcoming album.<br />\r\nWhen writing, I draw from a life filled with great happiness and deep pain. I truly understand many of the struggles facing people in this world today. I know what it&#39;s like to feel abandoned and to feel unloved. Sometimes the only thing you need is to know that someone understands and has been in your situation, that alone can give comfort. \r\nI am truly living the American dream. From rags to- we&#39;re working on the riches, but you get the point... I feel so fortunate to be working with an amazing list of producers and professionals that just keeps growing and I will continue to work hard and reach my goals. There is so much to come...<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor any inquiries please feel free to contact/<br />\r\nGerry Garica- 818.921.5453 <br />\r\nKeepItBurning@gmail.com<br />\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1505,1830,'Quarterfly',1,71,'www.myspace.com/quarterfly','382 Forest Ave.','864-205-8157','Quarterfly is one of the most electrifying and stunning modern rock bands in the Southeast! The seasoned musicianship and song writing skills puts this band in a class of their own. From the minute front man Kip Darby belts out his first note and the band kicks in, there is no denying that you are at the show, for the whole show. As a former tour manager for a major label band, Kip realized his passion and began writing songs that earned him a membership with ASCAP. The group is made up of four incredibly talented musicians, Jeff Jennings- Lead Guitar, Tim Morelock- Bass, backup vocals, Casey Culbreth-Drums and of course, Kip Darby- vocals and guitar, who all have tons of experience in the business. The resume of these band members is striking. Each has played in top regional bands such as Socket, JC Activator, and have played at the Atlantis Music Conference. They have shared the stage with Marv 3, Drivin\' and Cryin\', Stabbing Westward, Cowboy Mouth, Sister Hazel, Finger 11, SR-71, Chevelle, Earshot and Shinedown. The modern rock sound along with the sincerity and energy of their live performance, coupled with incredible, strong, song writing skills and musicianship, puts this group in a class of their own. Quarterfly will light it up during a full blown electric show or blow the venue up with their full band acoustic show. Either way, you will know you have been to a Rock Show! With a new album coming soon, Quarterfly is bound for greatness and would love for nothing more than to bring YOU along for the ride. Catch Quarterfly LIVE! ',1,'',0,''),(1506,1887,'brazilian contemporary classic music',12,56,'www.robsound.mus.br','(/)','55 031 31 9676-7223','Robson dos Santos brazilian contemporary classic music composer&nbsp;was born in Belo Horizonte, Minas Gerais, Brazil, on may, 1963. <br/>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>He began his musical studies at Cl&oacute;vis Salgado Foundation (P&Aacute;LACIO DAS ARTES) Flute course with teacher Juvenal Dias - 1982/1986. <br/>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>Robson studied musical composition in a self-taugh way. Since 1988, the artist has compositions played in important contemporary music festivals, like \"Ciclo de M&uacute;sica Contempor&acirc;nea\". \r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>He recorded in 1990 an album named: <a href=\"http://www.robsound.mus.br/en/discography01.htm\"><strong><font color=\"#003399\">EUTHANASIA?! the music </font></strong></a>with his own compositions. <br/>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>Nowadays, he works at Symphonic Orchestra of Minas Gerais as a maintenance technician instruments and going on his works and researches about contemporary music. ',1,'',0,''),(1507,1889,'Bill Anderson',1,77,'www.lordsnarebottom.com','100 River Road Apt C34','12016371250','<i>Dreams should never be reduced in potency by subjecting them to reality.</i><br/><br/>\r\nBill Anderson a/k/a Lord Snarebottom has been performing live since the\r\nage of 9. Since his awakening 20 years ago, he has been steadily\r\nwriting some of the most unique music in the world.<br/><br/>\r\nHe has toured the US and has performed with such legendary performers as Paul Simon.<br/><br/>\r\nHe textures his sonic palette with flavors of rock, jazz, classical and\r\npopular music to create a unique signature sound: when you hear a Bill\r\nAnderson song, you <i>know</i> who it is right away.<br/><br/>\r\nHis powerful voice and passionate delivery blaze a trail of personality and soulful sincerity that has become increasingly rare.<br/><br/>\r\nHe is a self-taught dynamo of brilliant creative genius, and his music\r\nis delivered with a strength, sensitivity and maturity that belies his\r\nalmost complete lack of any formal musical training. He consistently\r\ncreates complex musical constructs with the ease that only a true\r\nmaster can conjure, and delivers with each performance the\r\nuncompromising conviction to make you believe that he intimately\r\nunderstands the things he sings about, that he has indeed lived through\r\nthem, and conquered them.<br/><br/>\r\nHis upcoming CD release, <i>The Wet Album</i>,\r\nis chock full of the spark of creative genius so sorely lacking in\r\ntoday\'s music. It is due for release in the 4th quarter of 2007, on the\r\nNaked Hoof&reg; label.',0,'',0,''),(545,589,'Czar',1,15,'','','4782381741','This is a song from the Musical I wrote called \"Runaway\" about runaway kids trying to survive&nbsp;an urban jungle. We used local high school kids and the community went nuts! We had to turn people away the last few nights. The girl singing in this video went on to study opera.<br/><br/>I have to press the \"play\" button twice to get it going. If it doesn\'t go on first press, hit it again. The song is recorded live during performance one night so the mix is a little tricky, but you get the gist.<br/><br/>Thank you Nick and Tyler&nbsp;for making this work... we are not worthy - * he said bowing down on his little prayer rug *<br/>\r\n<object height=\"350\" width=\"425\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/1nkhfpS6GX8\"/>\r\n   <embed src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/1nkhfpS6GX8\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" width=\"425\" height=\"350\"/>  </object><br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=209\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\">Interact with Czar\'s fans</span></a>',0,'',0,''),(546,591,'T