So&nbsp;Loved the world that he gave his only begotten paycheck just to buy that new fucking guitar.....&nbsp;Rock-n- roll, &nbsp;is not all evil. Good is what beholds a brighter future.&nbsp;Work hard,&nbsp;Fuck the bullshit.&nbsp;&nbsp;Thorn4Memory Bitches.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=112\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with THORN4MEMORYs fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(547,592,'Justin lanning',1,15,'www.justinlanning.com',' P.O. Box 691306','','<p align=\"center\"><b>\r\n  <object enablejsurl=\"false\" enablehref=\"false\" saveembedtags=\"true\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowscriptaccess=\"never\" allownetworking=\"internal\" data=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/FVZXjdo-_78&autoplay=1\" height=\"350\" width=\"425\">\r\n  <param name=\"allowScriptAccess\" value=\"never\"/>\r\n  <param name=\"allowNetworking\" value=\"internal\"/>\r\n  <param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/FVZXjdo-_78&autoplay=1\"/>\r\n</object>\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://justinlanning.musicnation.com/\">Justin Lanning</a></h2>\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://musicnation.com/browse/artists?distance=5&postal=90210\">Beverly Hills, CA</a> &#8211; <a href=\"http://rock.musicnation.com/\">Rock</a> </h3>\r\n<p class=\"user-description\" style=\"display: block;\">Justin lanning Press Kit Bio If you had to label singer jmulti-instrumentalist Justin Lanning with just one word, it\'d be \"positive.\" It is his indomitable spirit that defines him and his music.<span class=\"more-text\" style=\"display: inline;\"> Lanning is not just confident about his future and the effect that music can have on people\'s lives; he\'s so self-assured that it is absolutely infectious. This optimistic spirit permeates his debut CD Behind These Eyes. Behind These Eyes references many of the twenty-one year-old Lanning\'s idols: the glossy, power-pop sheen of Bryan Adams; the storytelling prowess of Billy Joel; the classic harmonic sophistication of the Beatles and the Beach Boys; the youthful exuberance of James Blunt; and the energy of blink-182. But like those musical heroes, Justin is his own man, and his personal songs come from a deep emotional well that is unique to him. The debut single \"Take My Breath Away\" perfectly captures the innocence of finding a new love and the overwhelming allure of female beauty. More universal issues are tackled on \"Voices,\" where Lanning takes the listener along his search for meaning in the cosmos, highlighting the depth of his spiritual consciousness as the simple melody gradually builds to a multilayered peak centered on an urgent guitar riff. The album\'s title track encapsulates Lanning\'s uplifting message of self-esteem, personal growth and championing your inner child. But don\'t mistake Lanning\'s honesty and positive vibes as inexperienced or unsophisticated. Los Angeles born and bred, Lanning exudes \'California cool,\' and while his speech is peppered with new age aphorisms like references to spirit guides and light healing, he is a shrewd businessman in full control of his career and destiny. Self-taught from a young age on a variety of instruments, including guitar, piano, bass and drums, Lanning not only writes and performs his songs but also owns the publishing rights and masters and acted as his own A&R rep. Lanning even co- produced two tracks along with seasoned veteran Jeff Bova (Michael Jackson, Billy Joel, Joe Cocker) and acted as financial backer for his upcoming album, which features additional songs produced by Steven Miller (Dave Matthews Band, Pink, Mandy Moore) and will be released on Lanning\'s own King George Records with promoRecords is \"named after my father,\" says Lanning, \"for his loving support when I was a young kid, paying for acting classes and driving me to auditions... which, essentially, gave me the jobs that helped to fund my record!\" While finishing the recording of his self-financed debut release Behind These Eyes, Lanning came up short on funds for laying down a few additional vocal tracks. Rather than leaving the record as simply \"good enough,\" he took his Chevy Trailblazer to the pawn shop, and 15 minutes later walked out with just enough cash to finish the tracks. When asked about what he\'s going do for a car, Lanning joked, \"I\'ll just drive my Mom\'s for a while or I\'ll sell a bunch of CDs.\" While he might have to borrow a car for the time being, he is satisfied that his creative vision has been fully realized. Betting his car on his future was a calculated risk for any performer I but Lanning is insistent on maintaining full creative control. The young singer/songwriter puts so much of his heart and soul into the music that he is unwilling to let anyone else water it down. Lanning turned down lucrative offers from several major labels in favor of establishing his own independent label. Lanning sees himself as a multi-media artist as well. A visit to his MySpace highlights the various episodes of justin\'s World, webisodes that feature the life and times of the enthusiastic sprit of Lanning as he heads through a variety of Left Coast adventures. justin\'s World has already gathered a cult following, with tens of thousands of viewers watching each and every episode. To the delight of those online fans, Lanning plans to take his live show on the road in the spring. His electrifying presence on stage is bolstered by his experience as an actor with over 20 commercials and TV shows to his credit, including winning MTV\'s \"Score\" with Ryan Cabrera and a recent role as a murderer on \"CSI: Las Vegas.\" Looking towards the future, Lanning is supremely optimistic. He\'s made a record that he loves; he has a single shipping to radio; he\'s assembled a crack band of players for an upcoming tour in the spring; and surrounded himself with a business team consisting of industry insiders who he now considers friends. Can you think of any better reason to be optimistic? www.JustinLanning.comtion and distribution through MesajBluemoon Recordings. King George</span></p></b>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=113\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Justin Lanning\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',0,'',0,''),(548,593,'Junkbox',1,68,'www.myspace.com/junkbox69','','','Junkbox is a LOUD rockin 5 piece garage/alt/pop/punk band fronted by 2 HOT CHICKS! Started in aug 2004 by Sarah and LULU. They have played shows in the MIDWEST and LOS ANGELES (HOME). The songs are bold, in your face and at times brutally honest. Their live shows are not to be missed!!<bold><br/></bold>\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=114\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Junkbox\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(549,594,'twisted phenomenon',5,91,'www.twistedphenomenon.com','','','<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=115\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with twisted phenomenon\'s fans</span></a><br/><br/>',1,'',0,''),(550,597,'Scott Wilson',1,74,'http://www.metalogicmusic.com','','','Scott Wilson <br />\r\nBass, Acoustic and Electric Guitar <br />\r\nLead and background vocalist <br />\r\nProducer/Singer-Songwriter <br />\r\n<br />\r\nVFX. Produced and played bass on two compact discs with the band. The\r\nfirst self-titled compact disc from VFX played on radio stations across\r\nthe country, including heavy rotation on Salt Lake&#39;s City KBER-FM. A\r\nvideo for &quot;Myriad Arising&quot; was aired worldwide. The second disc: &quot;the\r\nnext step&quot; hit Number 1 on the Imports Charts of Kerrang Magazine in\r\nEngland, and received rave reviews in the European rock press. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nCruel World. Released a self-titled disc, featuring Scott Wilson as\r\nlead vocalist/bassist. Cruel World toured Europe, playing in Germany,\r\nBelgium, and the Netherlands. A live acoustic version of &quot;Broken Chain&quot;\r\nwas included on a PopKomm cd-rom promoting the convention in Cologne\r\nGermany. Cruel World also played in clubs around Los Angeles. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nScott Wilson. In 2005, released a new solo album, called Kaleidoscope&#39;s\r\nEnd. Played bass with Seven Music in San Diego. Playing acoustic gigs\r\nin Los Angeles and San Diego where he recently relocated. Was one of\r\nthe founding members of The Gandhi Method, a local San Diego acoustic\r\nvocal group. Also, he is a former member of The Cathryn Beeks Band. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nScott Wilson has extensive recording experience, in various analog\r\nstudios, in Pro Tools digital environments, and also in his own digital\r\nhome studio. He is a prolific songwriter, having written and recorded\r\nover 150 songs. Scott Wilson is an versatile aggressive, and melodic\r\nbassist, and a heartfelt vocalist and performer. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nStyles: Modern Rock, Pop, Blues, and Alternative. <br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=116\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt\">Interact with Scott Wilson&#39;s fans</span></a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<object classid=\"clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000\" codebase=\"http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0\" width=\"425\" height=\"350\">\r\n	<param name=\"width\" value=\"425\" />\r\n	<param name=\"height\" value=\"350\" />\r\n	<param name=\"flashvars\" value=\"id=475044&amp;emailUrl=http%3A%2F%2Fvideo.yahoo.com%2Futil%2Fmail%3Fei%3DUTF-8%26vid%3D80022&amp;imUrl=http%253A%252F%252Fvideo.yahoo.com%252Fvideo%252Fplay%253Fei%253DUTF-8%2526vid%253D80022&amp;imTitle=Scott%2BWilson%2B%2526quot%253BCoffeehouse%2B101%2526quot%253B&amp;searchUrl=http://video.yahoo.com/search/video?p=&amp;profileUrl=http://video.yahoo.com/video/profile?yid=&amp;creatorValue=bWV0YXB1bms%3D&amp;vid=80022\" />\r\n	<param name=\"src\" value=\"http://us.i1.yimg.com/cosmos.bcst.yahoo.com/player/media/swf/FLVVideoSolo.swf\" />\r\n	<embed type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" width=\"425\" height=\"350\" flashvars=\"id=475044&amp;emailUrl=http%3A%2F%2Fvideo.yahoo.com%2Futil%2Fmail%3Fei%3DUTF-8%26vid%3D80022&amp;imUrl=http%253A%252F%252Fvideo.yahoo.com%252Fvideo%252Fplay%253Fei%253DUTF-8%2526vid%253D80022&amp;imTitle=Scott%2BWilson%2B%2526quot%253BCoffeehouse%2B101%2526quot%253B&amp;searchUrl=http://video.yahoo.com/search/video?p=&amp;profileUrl=http://video.yahoo.com/video/profile?yid=&amp;creatorValue=bWV0YXB1bms%3D&amp;vid=80022\" src=\"http://us.i1.yimg.com/cosmos.bcst.yahoo.com/player/media/swf/FLVVideoSolo.swf\"></embed>\r\n</object>\r\n',0,'',0,''),(551,598,'J.R. & Th\'FARM',8,37,'www.myspace.com/jr&th\'farm','2030 popcorn ct','503-551-3066','<h4>\r\n</h4><h2>\r\n</h2><h1></h1>J.R.& Th\'FARM<br/>OUTLAW COUNTRY &&nbsp;RAGING ROCK<br/>Pacific Northwest band&nbsp;unleashes there way of life on America,&nbsp;taking no&nbsp;prisoner\'s and&nbsp;making no apologies.<br/>We are who we are, love us,hate us,fight us or hug us, we respect your opinion and will defend it to the death...After all...This IS still America!\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=117\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with J.R. & Th\'FARM\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(554,603,'Daniel J. Sweigert',10,45,'www.guitaristworks.com/daniel%20j.%20sweigert/','417 W Main Street','270-898-7264','<p><strong>Daniel J. Sweigert</strong></p>\r\n<p>Dan Sweigert, singer-songwriter of 30 years , has been writing Christian ballads for many years now.&nbsp; An accomplished acoustic guitarist, he aims to paint&nbsp;a picture with his style of playing and his&nbsp;creative writing.</p>\r\n<p>In recent years he has been collaborating with many fine talents across the United States and other countries.&nbsp; He is most proud of \"<strong>Road of Forgiveness</strong>\", a very different Christmas song which takes the listener through the early Old&nbsp;Testament to the birth of the Christ Child...take a listen.</p>\r\n<p>Dan\'s goal is to touch as many lives as he can through his music. \"I am only on this earth for a short time; I\'ve been given a gift; and I need to use it in Faith.\", Dan says.</p>\r\n<p>In addition to his Christian bend with his music, Dan has also struck&nbsp;some very&nbsp;unique chords in other Americana tunes and Country songs as well.&nbsp; We hope you enjoy the magic.</p>\r\n<p>Blessings</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=118\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Daniel J. Sweigert\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(555,605,'Geno & Bill',8,79,'www.myspace.com/genobill','70 N. Cliff St.','860-859-1388','&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Like a fine wine, some things just get better with age. Such is the case with New London County musicians, Geno Champagne and Bill Thibeault. The two&nbsp; played together in a local cover band in the early 70\'s, then drifted apart, each working on and off in different area bands. Then, in early May, 2006, the two crossed paths one night at a local bar, and began discussing music. They decided to get together to possibly do some writing and recording. It turned out to be a magical pairing.&nbsp; Champagne has quite a backlog of song material he had written over the years. Thibeault took a look at some of the material and made some minor changes here and there. The end result is an irresistible&nbsp; mix of rock, folk and country. One of the highlights is a song Geno co-wrote in the early nineties called &#8220;Where&#8217;s the Glory?&#8221; The song was written after the Gulf War, primarily for the Vietnam veterans. The inspiration was the difference in the treatment of the returning war veterans on the home front. The song was also written to be sung by a veteran.&nbsp; Thibeault happens to be a&nbsp; Vietnam veteran, and immediately connected with the song. He is a survivor of the USS Frank E. Evans, a U.S. destroyer which collided with an Australian aircraft carrier, June 3, 1969, which suffered a loss of 74 crewmen. Thibeault has since learned that none of the 74 lost that day are on the Vietnam Wall.<br/><br/>&nbsp; &#8220;Geno and Bill....Wow...This is fantastic...I&#8217;m so glad these guys joined forces...I&#8217;ve been<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; a fan of both of their separate projects over the&nbsp; years. &#8220;Where&#8217;s The Glory&#8221; is an&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; excellent tune, and the lyrics will mean so much to so many people.&#8221;....Ron Apicelli,&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ron&#8217;s Guitars, Groton, CT<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In July, 2006, Thibeault had another chance encounter in the same local bar with Andy Stackpole, a professional sound engineer who occasionally did sound for Thibeault&#8217;s band Random Access in the late eighties and early nineties.&nbsp; Stackpole is now a&nbsp; front of the house sound engineer, working for artists such as Living Colour, Mos Def, Busta Rhymes, Steven Segal and many others. When he is not touring he is at home in Norwich, working as a recording engineer. One thing led to another, and in September, 2006, Geno & Bill began recording a four song EP titled &#8220;A Long Time Coming,&#8221; with Stackpole&nbsp; producing and mixing. The CD was released Nov. 27,2006 and is currently available in CT, at The Other Side, 29 Franklin St., Norwich, Mystic Disc, in Mystic, and Tumbleweeds, in Niantic. It is also available online at CD Baby. http://cdbaby.com/cd/genobill\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=119\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Geno & Bill\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(557,606,'Los Diablos',8,37,'www.losdiablosmusic.com','','','<div style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">Their music and performance are built upon classic country rock rhythm and straight up punk rock ethics... loud guitars and laid back acoustic harmonies underneath tales of dishonesty, jealousy, and greed.<br/><br/>The boys in the band have been involved in some of the most influential and important bands in the South Florida underground scene for the past two decades, cutting their teeth in such seminal punk bands such as the Johnsons, the Hang Up\'s, and the Holy Terrors and gaining hard fought critical acclaim in such alternative underground bands like Amazing Grace, Nuclear Valdez, The Comatones.<br/><br/>Some call them \"Americana\"... some label \'em \"alternative country\"... they just like to call it&nbsp; wearing their influences on their sleeves and their wounds as proudly as they show the scars... unafraid to share that with anyone.<br/></div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=120\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Los Diablos\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(558,608,'The Chapmans',10,48,'thechapmansonline.com','','','<h3 style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt;\"><font color=\"#561b15\">\"...the Chapmans have arrived. They deserve to be mentioned from now on with all the \'first tier\' bands in bluegrass, if they aren\'t already.\" </font><font color=\"#561b15\"><strong><span>Tim Stafford ~ Blue Highway</span></strong></font></span></h3><font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\"></font></h3>\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\"></font></h3>\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\"></font></h3>\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\"></font></h3>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\" align=\"left\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\"></font></h3>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\" align=\"left\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\"></font>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">The Chapmans have taken their place among the best and brightest in a new century of American bluegrass by balancing a demanding touring schedule with an award-winning recording career.</font></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\"></font>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">Brothers Jeremy, Jason and John, together with their father Bill, have taken their efforts in the studio to new heights of emotion, storytelling and musicianship with &#8220;Simple Man,&#8221; the band&#8217;s third album for Pinecastle Records,(due out in early 2005). &#8220;Simple Man&#8221; fulfills the promise of 1999&#8217;s &#8220;Notes From Home&#8221; and 2001&#8217;s &#8220;Follow Me,&#8221; which established the Chapmans as rising stars in the genre and earned them the Emerging Artist of the Year award from the International Bluegrass Music Association. </font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\"></font>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">The honor meant so much to the Chapmans because IBMA award winners are chosen by the votes of industry professionals: musicians, songwriters, radio programmers and journalists. It meant that a group begun as a way of having some family fun had been accepted by their peers in the bluegrass world as one of their own. With &#8220;Simple Man,&#8221; the Chapmans prove they are more than worthy of that praise.</font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\"></font>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">The band&#8217;s musical journey begins in the early 1990s in Colorado where young fiddler John Chapman won a statewide junior division championship in his early teens. Inspired by his son&#8217;s interest in music, Bill took up the banjo and the two started a bluegrass band with some family friends. Eventually John would switch to guitar and begin singing lead vocals. When younger brothers Jeremy and Jason took up mandolin and bass respectively, a hobby turned into a full-on family passion.</font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\"></font>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">The Chapmans honed their skills through shows at county fairs and bluegrass festivals throughout the 1990s. They moved to the Missouri Ozarks in 1995 to make nationwide travel easier. In 1998 the Chapmans jumped into the national spotlight when they won the International Bluegrass Band Championship held by the Society For the Preservation of Bluegrass Music in America (SPBGMA). Along with the critical success of the band&#8217;s first independent album, &#8220;Love&#8217;s Gonna Live Here,&#8221; the win paved the way for the Chapmans to sign a record contract with independent roots and bluegrass label Pinecastle Records.</font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\"></font>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">The band&#8217;s first album on Pinecastle, &#8220;Notes From Home,&#8221; was produced by IIIrd Tyme Out bassist Ray Deaton and became a critical and commercial success. Besides earning rave reviews from Bluegrass Now and Bluegrass Unlimited, the genre&#8217;s leading publications, &#8220;Notes From Home&#8221; landed in the Top 5 of Bluegrass Unlimited&#8217;s radio chart and was nominated by SPBGMA for Album of the Year. In 2000, John won the first of three honors as SPBGMA&#8217;s Guitar Performer of the Year, and the Chapmans picked up endorsements from several well-known sponsors including Gibson Instruments and GHS Strings.</font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\"></font>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">The Chapmans released &#8220;Follow Me&#8221; in 2001, which included the muscular &#8220;Losing Again&#8221; and an a cappella version of soul singer Sam Cooke&#8217;s classic &#8220;You Send Me.&#8221; Once again the album reached the Top 5 of Bluegrass Unlimited&#8217;s radio chart and was nominated by SPBGMA for Album of the Year. It also led to the Emerging Artist honor from the IBMA voters, an award the Chapmans say they were sure they had no chance of winning right up until the moment their name was called. </font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\"></font>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">&#8220;Everybody had a grin on their face until about 5 in the morning that night,&#8221; John recalls.</font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\"></font>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">The hard-won success opened the door for the Chapmans to work with some of their heroes who, it turned out, were just as eager to work with them. </font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\"></font>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">&#8220;One of the most exciting things about our career is all the support we&#8217;ve received from other artists, from our heroes,&#8221; Jeremy says.</font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\"></font>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">Producer Darren Vincent, brother of fellow Missourian and bluegrass innovator Rhonda Vincent, raised the bar for quality and musical craftsmanship on the recording without compromising the Chapmans&#8217; artistic vision. Union Station guitarist Ron Block, whom John describes as &#8220;my personal guitar hero,&#8221; plays backing guitar on three songs, &#8220;The Photograph,&#8221; &#8220;Runaway Kind&#8221; and &#8220;Sometimes You Just Can&#8217;t Win.&#8221; Singer Sonja Isaacs, guitarist Rob Ickles, and fiddlers Stuart Duncan, Andy Leftwich and Aubrey Haynie also lent their talents to the album.</font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\"></font>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">&#8220;Simple Man&#8221; was mixed by recording engineer Gary Paczosa, who has worked on six Grammy-winning projects, including Nickel Creek&#8217;s &#8220;This Side,&#8221; the Dixie Chicks&#8217; &#8220;Home&#8221; and Dolly Parton&#8217;s &#8220;The Grass is Blue.&#8221; Although his skills are of the behind-the-scenes variety, the highly sought Paczosa was near the top of the Chapman&#8217;s wish list when they began planning the album.</font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\"></font>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">The result is an album of stellar musicianship, haunting melodies, tight family harmonies and, most important, great songs. Choosing songs was no easy task given that the Chapmans began the process with some 3,200 songs at their feet. The final set they is anchored by songs like &#8220;Ode To A Simple Man&#8221; by Kim Fox, one of the band&#8217;s favorite songwriters. Originally written as a modern country song, the tale of hard working, everyday people becomes a powerful piece of Americana in the hands of the Chapmans. &#8220;Runaway Kind&#8221; exhibits the band&#8217;s ability to capture the rootsy, lonesome feeling that is the essence of bluegrass, yet it is also the song the Chapmans believe has the greatest potential for crossover into the country radio format. &#8220;The Photograph,&#8221; a lost-love ballad with a lyrical twist, is nothing short of haunting.</font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\"></font>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">With their work in the studio finished, the Chapmans are now on the road, giving their fans across the country a taste of these songs live. Averaging about 140 shows each year, the Chapmans keep a busy schedule that takes them to bluegrass festivals from Maine to Texas and even Europe.</font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\"></font>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">Now a group of seasoned performers with a well-respected recording career to their credit, the Chapmans are ready to go wherever the music takes them. To hear them tell it, they&#8217;re just getting started.&nbsp;</font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\"></font>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"3\">&#8220;We feel like this is where we wanted to be all along, and we&#8217;re just now getting there,&#8221; Jason says.</font></p></font></h3></span></font>\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=121\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with The Chapmans\' fans</span></a><br/>\r\n\r\n',1,'',0,''),(559,609,'Socialites',1,66,'www.myspace.com/areyousocial','','','<p>The band got together in just June 2007, but Socialites intend to get things moving quickly.&nbsp; Please help us by adding&nbsp;Socialites to your myspace friend list and telling friends about us.&nbsp; We\'re nothing without our fans and we appreciate all that ou do for us!<br/><br/>...Jaunty melodies, charming drums, and a reference or two to some jazz classics; this music will turn your mind on. This is what music with an education sounds like: the soul of Sam Cooke, the mind of Monk, and the passion of Mingus played by a group of tragically meticulous guys. A year after beginning to form the band, Socialites - (&#8216;The&#8217; optional) - are finally pieced together. Listening to their music is like taking a walk through the musical landscape of days past. Aspiring gypsies with a clear and pure passion for rock &#8216;n&#8217; roll, The Socialites pull off this blend of new and old musical styles. Sounds can move from smart to playful through the course of one song; and the one defining thing about The Socialites is they know how to play.<br/>&nbsp;<br/>- Stacy Hoover (Camerata Productions and sister to many) </p>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=122\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Socialites\' fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(560,474,'Rain of Kings',1,14,'www.geocities.com/rainofkings','','1 732 770 0356','&nbsp; \r\n<table style=\"width: 470px; height: 328px;\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\">\r\n<p><span>The name of our band - RAIN OF KINGS,&nbsp;we are a&nbsp;4 member group and&nbsp;have been performing together since 1993.&nbsp; </span><span>With a vibe echoing back to the great arena rock bands of the \'70\'s, \'80\'s & \'90\'s such as Black Sabbath Nine Inch Nails, Yes, Kings-X & Van Halen to name a few. <br/><br/>Rain of Kings, is on a mission to bring <b><i>big guitar rock, </i></b>back to the radio and live stage. Playing in halls & clubs in the NY/Tri State area such as CBGB\'s; Kenny\'s Kastaway; Webster Hall; Lion\'s Den;&nbsp;The Continental; Trash Bar; Wild Spirits;&nbsp;Don Hill\'s; Coda;&nbsp;Black Thorn; ACME Downunder; The Pyramid; The Spiral&nbsp;and The Elbow Room.. </span></p>\r\n<p><span>We have developed an intense live show over the past 2 years, exciting audiences with huge guitar sound, pristine vocal harmonies, and driving rhythms, these four musicians from diverse, artistic and creative backgrounds, blend an intense sonic brew in which some people have described as</span><span>...<b><i>Heavy Melodic</i> </b></span></p>\r\n<p><span><br/></span><b><i><span>RAIN OF KINGS is definitely rooted in rock\'s old school and in rock\'s future.</span></i></b></p></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\">\r\n<p><span></span></p><br/></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt; color: black; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\"><v id=\"_x0000_t75\" stroked=\"f\" filled=\"f\" path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\" coordsize=\"21600,21600\" spt=\"75\" preferrelative=\"t\"><v joinstyle=\"miter\"></v><v><v eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"></v><v eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"></v><v eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"></v><v eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"></v><v eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"></v><v eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"></v><v eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"></v><v eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"></v><v eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"></v><v eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"></v><v eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"></v><v eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"></v></v><v gradientshapeok=\"t\" extrusionok=\"f\" connecttype=\"rect\"></v><o:lock aspectratio=\"t\" v:ext=\"edit\"></o:lock></v></span><br/>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=123\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Rain of Kings\' fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(562,611,'Samuel Storm',10,48,'http://www.myspace.com/mourningstorm','','267-424-4605','Samuel is a 34 year old Singer/songwriter in Eastern PA (Bucks County) who&#39;s musical style fits in a cross between Acoustic Rock, and Alternative / Goth. Neither genera completely fits the description of his music, but his lyrical imagery is both dark and heartfelt, while his rhythmical talent lies on the acoustic/rock side of the spectrum. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nBorn in Rochester, NY, Samuel began to play music at an early age by banging pots and pans together in the kitchen and singing. At the age of 8 he started learning to play the Drums and had waited till the age of 16 to pick up the guitar and teach himself how to play. Both his parents encouraged him musically to find his own way. He favors a 12 string guitar named Amber, 6 string electric guitar named Raven, a set of hand drums, and a Keyboard to express himself.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIt wasn&#39;t till the loss of his sister that he began writing. After that his lyrical design took on a life of it&#39;s own. Samuel made his music his release, and his therapy. As one fan put it &quot;There&#39;s something for everyone to relate to within his music...&quot; <br />\r\n<br />\r\nSamuel&#39;s music didn&#39;t start coming together till the fall of 1998 while living in Fargo, ND. On October 11th of that year (the 6th anniversary of his sister&#39;s passing) he wrote &quot;Six Long Years&quot; which has received numerous reviews and compliments on it&rsquo;s simplicity and intensity. Soon after the release of &ldquo;6 Long Years&rdquo; others followed. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn Early 2004 another life change had hit Samuel&#39;s path and he moved to Eastern Pennsylvania, where he currently resides. He is currently involved in the Bucks County/Lehigh Valley Music Scene, and plays at Open Mics quite frequently. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nHe is currently involved in preparing his Next CD for release, sometime this year.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSamuel Storm has had his music played on The Phil Stahl Show (90.3 FM WXLV), 93.7 FM WSTW&#39;s Hometown Heroes, WMDR Internet Radio, Pirate Radio Networks Twisted Radio, and Roads Ends Radio. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPast performances include: <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n09/07 Wagon Wheel Tavern<br />\r\n12/06 Wagon Wheel Tavern<br />\r\n11/06 Wagon Wheel Tavern (Quakertown, PA) <br />\r\n8/05 Byer&#39;s Choice (Chalfont, PA)<br />\r\n3/05 Chambers (Doylestown, PA)<br />\r\n3/05 WXLV Radio Appearance<br />\r\n3/05 Candlewyck Lounge (Buckingham, PA)<br />\r\n2/05 Candlewyck Lounge <br />\r\n11/04 Between The Worlds Conference, Willmington, DE<br />\r\n10/04 Harvest Faire, Virginia Beach, VA<br />\r\n9/04 Rochester Pagan Pride, Rochester, NY<br />\r\n9/04 Dover Pagan Pride, Dover, DE<br />\r\n5/04 Common Grounds Coffee House, Moorhead, MN<br />\r\n4/04 Common Grounds Coffee House, Moorhead, MN<br />\r\n4/04 Spring Jam 7, Moorhead MN<br />\r\n3/04 Common Grounds Coffee House, Moorhead, MN<br />\r\n8/03 Playmaker&#39;s (Upstairs), Fargo, ND<br />\r\n6/03 Playmaker&#39;s (Upstairs), Fargo, ND<br />\r\n3/02 Borna&#39;s Bagel Bakery, Fargo, ND<br />\r\n10/01 ValleyCon 2001, Fargo, ND<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<object classid=\"clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000\" codebase=\"http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0\" width=\"340\" height=\"290\">\r\n	<param name=\"allowfullscreen\" value=\"true\" />\r\n	<param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\" />\r\n	<param name=\"scale\" value=\"noscale\" />\r\n	<param name=\"height\" value=\"290\" />\r\n	<param name=\"width\" value=\"340\" />\r\n	<param name=\"src\" value=\"http://player.stickam.com/stickamPlayer/176006245-5946296\" />\r\n	<embed type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" scale=\"noscale\" height=\"290\" width=\"340\" src=\"http://player.stickam.com/stickamPlayer/176006245-5946296\"></embed>\r\n</object>\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nCatch my on-line concert series right in the player above!<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=124\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt\">Interact with Samuel Storm&#39;s fans</span></a> \r\n',0,'',0,''),(564,613,'Romeo Falls',1,14,'www.myspace.com/romeofalls','','910-728-8841','\r\n<p>Romeo Falls is a Heavy \"radio\" Rock band from Fayetteville North carolina. Taking our favorite sounds and combining them to create what we feel to be our souls for all to hear. </p>\r\n<p>The name Romeo Falls comes from the idea of someone that falls upon bad luck or bad times. At any given time a good person can stumble and fall to their vises. We write about how bad things can happen and how it is up to you to make them better. The people around you or the world you live on is not responsible for where you find yourself each day. Get off your ass and make something of yourself and stop crying about how you are tied down. Yes you have fallen, but you and only you can get back on your feet. </p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=95\" target=\"_blank\">Join Romeo Falls\' discussion</a><br/></p>',1,'',0,''),(578,629,'ALLFLAWS',3,18,'www.myspace.com/allflaws','','','<p>One of the freshest new acts to come out of the Bristol underground scene.&nbsp;Allflaws&nbsp;consists of Deep original abstract lyrics over a hybrid of Guitars, Synths and driving&nbsp;electronic beats.&nbsp; Moving from Criptic poetic&nbsp;flows to raw&nbsp;sinister&nbsp; verses,&nbsp;&nbsp;the allflaws sound has depth, diversity and a non confromist attitude towards making music.&nbsp; They&nbsp;do&nbsp;provide something different compared to your conventional music genres,&nbsp;and they try not to be&nbsp;dictated by the lastest trend or urban style.</p>\r\n<p>Allflaws&nbsp;won\'t be for everyone but they certaintly&nbsp;have something which they can call their own........................................................................</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=125\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with ALLFLAWS\' fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(566,616,'POKE',1,77,'www.myspace.com/thejudges','14893 s fork church rd','859-663-5172','we started dancin\' to that fine, fine music ...\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=126\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with POKE\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(567,618,'STEWBOSS',1,69,'www.stewboss.com','22287 Mulholland Hwy #192','8183813589','HERE ARE SOME OF THE NICE THINGS THAT HAVE BEEN SAID ABOUT STEWBOSS AND THEIR MUSIC...<br/><br/>\r\n&#8220;It made me laugh, dance, sing along and sit down to pore over the song\r\nlyrics and liner notes like I haven\'t done since I was a kid&#8230;it\'s\r\nalive, vibrant and genuine. Sweet Lullabye is a masterpiece.&#8221; &#8212; Sam\r\nWereb, Rockzilla magazine<br/><br/>\r\n&#8220;True American music, comparable to Springsteen and Tom Petty.&#8221; Bob Harris, BBC Radio2<br/><br/>\r\n&#8220;Sarfaty&#8217;s earnest, reedy vocals deliver the goods with unselfconscious\r\npassion, and the band boasts more than enough firepower to drive it all\r\nhome.&#8221; &#8212; No Depression<br/><br/>\r\n&#8220;One of the most pleasing pieces of underplayed but authentic American\r\nmusic I&#8217;ve come across in many a long month.&#8221; &#8212; Dorset Echo<br/><br/>\r\n&#8220;An elegantly simple brew of earnest guitar pop and homespun\r\nmelody&#8230;(Sweet Lullabye) is a fine, unfussy little masterpiece of an\r\nalbum.&#8221; &#8212; Manchester Evening News, UK<br/><br/>\r\n&#8220;Stewboss&#8217; first album Wanted A Girl &#8211; a glorious piece of sepia-toned\r\nAmericana &#8211; became a firm favourite with listeners to Bob Harris on\r\n(BBC)Radio2.&#8221; &#8212; Jim McGhee, Daily Record<br/><br/>\r\n&#8220;The tremendous Wanted A Girl album was one of the most overlooked,\r\ngreat LPs of the year, so it is good to see that (Stewboss) has\r\nmaintained the same high standard. 4 stars!&#8221; &#8212; Bristol Eve Post<br/><br/>\r\n&#8220;Straddling the lines between love and hate, anger and calm, and joy\r\nand sadness, Stewboss delivers a turbulently emotional album of\r\nroots-rock songs for a whiskey-swilling Saturday night.&#8221; &#8212; The Music Box<br/><br/>\r\n&#8220;At several points during their show, the songs were so good people\r\nwere shaking their heads in reverence to them.&#8221; &#8212; Music Connection<br/><br/>\r\n&#8220;Singer/songwriter Gregg Sarfaty is the unknown, undiscovered Van\r\nMorrison, Robbie Robertson, and Adam Duritz all in one.&#8221; &#8212; Lazyeye<br/><br/>\r\n&#8220;An extraordinary record&#8230;complete with intelligent lyrics and some great sound quality as well.&#8221; &#8212; hEARd Magazine, Australia<br/><br/>\r\n&#8220;By the end of the night there was no doubt they could have played it\r\nall again and still have had a packed house. If you missed them this\r\ntime round, next time you have no excuse - you&#8217;ve been told.&#8221; &#8212;\r\nManchester Evening News\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=127\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with STEWBOSS\' fans</span></a>',1,'',0,''),(568,620,'BONE TRIGGER',7,85,'http://myspace.com/bonetrigger','','416-912-9228','<h1 align=\"center\"><u><font color=\"#000000\">Bone <font style=\"background-color: #ffffff\">Trigger</font></font></u></h1><span style=\"font-weight: bold\"><em><font face=\"Comic Sans MS\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #ffffff\"><font size=\"4\">\r\n<p>\r\n<font size=\"2\">Bone Trigger &mdash; A four-piece rock band from Toronto, Ontario.</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font size=\"2\">Vocals and Rhythm Guitar: Cee Dee (Carlos Demelo) </font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font size=\"2\">Lead Guitar: Satoshi </font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font size=\"2\">Bass Guitar: J.D.</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font size=\"2\">Drummer: Bonhomme.</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font size=\"2\">Experience, dedication, and well-written music form the backbone of this extraordinary live band.</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font size=\"2\">Their sound is a synergistic explosion of intelligently layered heavy grooves and emotionally charged vocals complimented by melodic leads and subtle overtones. Their harnessed passions and high energy find release in dynamic performances that leave audiences suspended on an endless wave of musical invention. </font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font size=\"2\">Carlos Demelo, Bone Trigger&#39;s front man and songwriter, wrote and performed as lead guitarist for Toronto&rsquo;s Hellz Kitchen Show. During this time, Carlos developed his strong stage presence. Hellz Kitchen opened for acts such as Marilyn Manson, Dope, Not By Choice, Danko Jones, Robin Black and the IRS, LA Guns, and Nash the Slash. </font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font size=\"2\">Carlos fine-tuned his writing and studio skills working with industry respected producers such as Rick Anderson, Dan Reed, and Sean Gregory.</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font size=\"2\">Bone Trigger&rsquo;s recently released demo CD consists of 4 original tracks that are receiving attention on Garageband.com, Myspace.com, and have charted in the top ten on Reverbnation.com.</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font size=\"2\">Bone Trigger is currently in the studio recording their debut CD titled</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font size=\"2\">&quot;Who&rsquo;s On Top Now Bitch!&quot; Scheduled to be released in the latter part of 2008 coupled with an array of merchandise, and plans of a music video, Bone Trigger is well on their way of a steady rise to the top in 2008. </font>\r\n</p>\r\n</font></font></em></span><a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=128\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt\">Interact with BONE TRIGGER&#39;s fans</span></a>\r\n',1,'<p>\r\n<font size=\"2\">Vocals and Rhythm Guitar: Cee Dee (Carlos Demelo) </font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font size=\"2\">Lead Guitar: Satoshi </font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font size=\"2\">Bass Guitar: J.D.</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font size=\"2\">Drummer: Bonhomme.</font>\r\n</p>\r\n',0,''),(569,621,'roi and the secret people',1,16,'http://myspace.com/mikeroi','','','<p style=\"font: normal normal normal 14px/normal Times; margin: 0px\">The incredible Brooklyn-based American rock band Roi and the Secret People are proud to announce the release of their new CD &ldquo;Dog St.&rdquo;&nbsp; Combining the down and dirty vibe of the Stones and the southern soul of the Black Crowes and Neil Young, Roi and the Secret People features the beautiful, mesmerizing voice of Mike Roi (formerly of Brother Grimm and Roi) and the high-octane slide guitar of Noel Rockwood (lead guitarist for the Snapdragons, Shiny Mama, and The New Professionals).&nbsp; RSP have generated an ardent following in the NYC area and have played such renowned clubs as The Tin Angel in Philadelphia and Arlene&rsquo;s Grocery in New York City.</p><p style=\"font: normal normal normal 14px/normal Times; min-height: 18px; margin: 0px\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"font: normal normal normal 14px/normal Times; margin: 0px\">Produced by LABATOMIX here in NYC by Dose and Donny Rock of SHOOTYZ GROOVE fame, the CD features artwork by award-winning illustrator and artist Tony DiTerlizzi whose latest project is the blockbuster film, The Spiderwick Chronicles.</p><p style=\"font: normal normal normal 14px/normal Times; min-height: 18px; margin: 0px\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"font: normal normal normal 14px/normal Times; margin: 0px\">Soulful, gritty, and true-blue, RSP is a band that carries on the tradition of the best American rock has to offer.</p><p style=\"font: normal normal normal 14px/normal Times; min-height: 18px; margin: 0px\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"font: normal normal normal 14px/normal Times; margin: 0px\">To celebrate the release of Dog St., RSP will hold their CD launch party, which will be broadcast live, on March 22<sup>nd</sup> at Arlene&rsquo;s Grocery.&nbsp;</p>',1,'',0,''),(577,630,'Not My Day',1,66,'http://www.myspace.com/notmydayoxford','16 Abingdon Road','07890 986185','<span style=\"font-family: arial\">\r\n<p><font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong style=\"font-size: 14pt\">\"...a brand new talent\"<br/></strong></font><em>DJ Kevin Hughes on the \'Music Control\' UK network radio show, May 31st, 2007</em></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt\"><strong><font color=\"#ff0000\">\"...a great band with good songs and energetic renditions\"<br/></font></strong></span><em>Allesandro Rolim De Moura; Oxford Mail, April 20th, 2007<br/></em><br/>We\'re an Oxford, England-based four-piece consisting of brothers Adam & Ben Cook on guitar&nbsp;& vocals, drummer Dan Cahill and bassist JB. </p>\r\n<p><em>Taken Too Much</em>,<em> Dickie Kay</em> and <em>Happiness</em> <em>Will Spell The End </em>are taken from our up-and-coming [as yet untitled] LP which will be finished... well, when it\'s finished I suppose! Keep an eye on this page to see the fruits of our labours!</p></span><span style=\"font-family: arial\">Finally, here\'s our new video; please tell us what you think - the feedback is much appreciated.</span><br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.msplinks.com/MDFodHRwOi8vbXlzcGFjZXR2LmNvbS9pbmRleC5jZm0/ZnVzZWFjdGlvbj12aWRzLmluZGl2aWR1YWwmdmlkZW9pZD0xNTgwNjU1MQ==\">Happiness Will Spell The End</a><br/><br/><object type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowscriptaccess=\"never\" allownetworking=\"all\" height=\"386\" width=\"480\" data=\"http://lads.myspace.com/videos/vplayer.swf\">\r\n  <param name=\"allowScriptAccess\" value=\"never\"/>\r\n  <param name=\"allowNetworking\" value=\"all\"/>\r\n  <param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://lads.myspace.com/videos/vplayer.swf\"/>\r\n  <param name=\"flashvars\" value=\"m=15806551&type=video&v=2\"/>\r\n</object><br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.msplinks.com/MDFodHRwOi8vbXlzcGFjZXR2LmNvbS9pbmRleC5jZm0/ZnVzZWFjdGlvbj12aWRzLmFkZFRvUHJvZmlsZUNvbmZpcm0mdmlkZW9pZD0xNTgwNjU1MSZ0aXRsZT11bmRlZmluZWQgTm90IE15IERheSAtIEhhcHBpbmVzcyBXaWxsIFNwZWxsIFRoZSBFbmQ=\">Add to My Profile</a> | <a href=\"http://www.msplinks.com/MDFodHRwOi8vbXlzcGFjZXR2LmNvbS9pbmRleC5jZm0/ZnVzZWFjdGlvbj12aWRzLmhvbWU=\">More Videos</a><br/><br/>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=130\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt\">Interact with Not My Day\'s fans</span></a><br/></p>',1,'',0,''),(571,622,'Dr. Pants',1,66,'www.doctorpants.com','261 NW Eubanks','4058227715','<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=131\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Dr. Pants\' fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(572,624,'Brent Pierce',8,37,'showcaseyourmusic.com/brentpierce','','','Having been born and raised in small town Indiana, needless to say John Mellencamp was a common fixture on the home stereo. Throw in some Tom Petty, CCR, Neil Young and it\'s easy to see how I migrated to an alternative country sound. I enjoy The Old 97\'s, Ryan Adams, Wilco, Son Volt, Uncle Tupelo and select 90\'s rock, such as the Gin Blossoms. I\'d like to think my music has been influenced by each of these artists, so, enjoy and let me know what you think.<br/><br/>All songs copyright 2007 - Brent Pierce Music<br/><br/>www.myspace.com/brentpiercemusic\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=132\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Brent Pierce\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(580,632,'SWEAR ON YOUR LIFE',1,14,'www.myspace.com/swearonyourlife','','','SWEAR ON YOUR LIFE was formed by MilitiA., Ed Strohsahl and Marc Reischer in the Spring of 2005.&nbsp; Songwriting partners for several years, bassist Strohsahl and guitarist Reischer found themselves working with an endless parade of singers, never quite finding the one that fit.<br/><br/>Thanks to Craigslist.org, they meet MilitiA., a stunning force of nature who already established herself as a fixture on both the local, national and international rock scene, with appearances on FUSE, MTV2, VH1 and as a lead in Dee Snider&#8217;s horror-rock opera, Van Helsing&#8217;s Curse.&nbsp; (MilitiA. has also shared the stage with Sandra Bernhard, Cyndi Lauper, Nancy Sinatra and Taylor Dayne, to name a few!)<br/><br/>Within months, the three had written an album&#8217;s worth of material and with original drummer, Jim Spengler, began forging a reputation as a vicious live band, re-inventing the three minute rock song as a bruising, sweat-soaked battle cry.<br/><br/>After parting ways with their original drummer, Swear On Your Life entered 2006 determined to move forward, and began recording their debut EP, Burn My Crosses, that Spring.&nbsp; The rest of the year proved to be the hardest test faced by the band, with the pressures of creating a debut record forcing the band to become an even tougher, more tight-knit family.&nbsp; Swear On Your Life came out of 2006 bloodied, but far stronger than before.<br/><br/>The addition of Chip Thomas, a powerful local drummer, was the missing piece to this puzzle.&nbsp; Joining the band in December 2006, Chip fit into the lineup seamlessly and SOYL never looked back.<br/><br/>Scrapping everything they had recorded in 2006, Swear On Your Life went into Spin Studios (Queens, NY) in February 2007 and recorded the Burn My Crosses EP, live, in 2 days.&nbsp; Engineered by Nick Cipriano and mastered by Steve Kadison (Sony Music Studios), Burn My Crosses is the definitive statement of what Swear On Your Life is: punishingly heavy grooves, anchored by the near-telepathic rhythm section of Thomas and Strohsahl... Reischer&#8217;s blistering guitar work, switching instantly between crushing riffs and evocative, melodic textures... and of course, the voice of MilitiA., covering every inch of ground between a whisper and a scream with the authority of an unrepentant badass.<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br/>SWEAR ON YOUR LIFE is here.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br/><br/>Brace yourself.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=133\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with SWEAR ON YOUR LIFE\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n\r\n',1,'',0,''),(574,625,'February State',1,61,'myspace.com/februarystate','4316 W Morrow Dr.','602-327-1275','<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:placename w:st=\"on\"><b style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">FEBRUARY</span></b></st1:placename><b style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"> <st1:placetype w:st=\"on\">STATE</st1:placetype></span></b></st1:place><b style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></b></font></div>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><o:p><font face=\"Times New Roman\">&nbsp;</font></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-indent: 0.5in;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">With a unique blend of pop, piano, and hard rock, <st1:placename w:st=\"on\">February</st1:placename> <st1:placetype w:st=\"on\">State</st1:placetype> has exploded onto the <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:state w:st=\"on\">Arizona</st1:state></st1:place> music scene, quickly capturing the attention of recording giant Sony Music. The band members include Drummer Jason Slocum, bassist Jess Miller, pianist/lead vocalist Sam Hoffman, and lead guitarist David Welch. The groups members come from diverse musical backgrounds and have blended their styles to create magical waves of sound that delight their rapidly growing fan base. The band is led by drummer Jason Slocum who along with bassist Jess Miller were two of the key members of the extremely popular group Sunrise Elementary. Jason is a cut above other drummers in both speed and constantly changing fills and is respected by musicians throughout the region. Jess Miller adds a deep driving rhythm and signature voice to help carry the vocals. Pianist and lead vocalist Sam Hoffman has a distinctive vocal style and writes lyrics that are both memorable and mesmerizing. David Welch, the newest member of <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:placename w:st=\"on\">February</st1:placename> <st1:placetype w:st=\"on\">State</st1:placetype></st1:place> was formerly the lead guitar player for the heavy metal group The Sleep City Massacre and brings just the right amount of edginess to keep the sound interesting and fresh. The strengths of <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:placename w:st=\"on\">February</st1:placename> <st1:placetype w:st=\"on\">State</st1:placetype></st1:place> are their fresh new sound, memorable songs, and distinctive vocal style. You can find us on </font><a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/februarystate\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">www.myspace.com/februarystate</font></a><font face=\"Times New Roman\"> or e-mail us at februarystate@yahoo.com.</font></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><o:p><font face=\"Times New Roman\">&nbsp;</font></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><b style=\"\"><u><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Influences & Musical Styles:<o:p></o:p></font></u></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><b style=\"\"><u><o:p><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">&nbsp;</font></span></o:p></u></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><b style=\"\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">-Jacks Mannequin<o:p></o:p></font></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><b style=\"\"><o:p><font face=\"Times New Roman\">&nbsp;</font></o:p></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><b style=\"\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">-Mae<o:p></o:p></font></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><b style=\"\"><o:p><font face=\"Times New Roman\">&nbsp;</font></o:p></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><b style=\"\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">-The <st1:place w:st=\"on\">New Amsterdam</st1:place>&#8217;s<o:p></o:p></font></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><b style=\"\"><o:p><font face=\"Times New Roman\">&nbsp;</font></o:p></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><b style=\"\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">-Jimmy Eat World<o:p></o:p></font></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><b style=\"\"><o:p><font face=\"Times New Roman\">&nbsp;</font></o:p></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><b style=\"\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">- The Starting Line<o:p></o:p></font></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><b style=\"\"><o:p><font face=\"Times New Roman\">&nbsp;</font></o:p></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><b style=\"\"><u><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Quotes<o:p></o:p></font></u></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><b style=\"\"><u><o:p><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">&nbsp;</font></span></o:p></u></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">-<b style=\"\">Byron Filson of Villain Recording studio- &#8220;</b>This band has such potential, great songs with unique vocal styling&#8221;.</font></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><b style=\"\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">-Pulse Studios- &#8220;This is the feel good music of the summer&#8221;.<o:p></o:p></font></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><o:p><font face=\"Times New Roman\">&nbsp;</font></o:p></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div id=\"hotbar_promo\"></div><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',1,'',0,''),(579,633,'10 stone dead',1,66,'www.myspace.com/10stonedead','','01254 829897','welcome to 10 stone dead..formed in 2000 in a small town in lancashire by pete norman...the band set their sights on drawing from guy chadwick,ian curtis,morrissey and combining them into there own unique style,with pete doin all the writing and mick bamford the melodys the band just gelled into what you hear now,a striking sound that uplifts your day and creates any mood you desire..although pete uses session musicians now 10 stone dead are very much alive and demo\'s have been done for new tunes...the rest my friends is history...\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=134\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with 10 stone dead\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(575,627,'Wilhelm',5,25,'web.mac.com/aaroncwilhelm/iWeb/Aaron%20Wilhelm/Home.html','','','I am a solo \'artist\', but I use that term loosely. I come from the\r\nworld of radio production, writing and producing commercials and promos\r\nfor over ten years. Music didn\'t touch me profoundly until the rise of\r\nNew Wave. I was spellbound by the limitless possibilities of the\r\nsynthesizer. Its technological dispassionate pretenses belie the depth\r\nof its emotions. I have no delusions that my music is unique or\r\nspecial... or even very well played. I do, however, put all of myself\r\ninto all that I create. I am fascinated by the interplay of light and\r\ndark in music. I have always been drawn to the darkness, and my style\r\nis therefore decidedly dark- yet darkness holds no interest or depth\r\nunless it is contrasted against the light. Through these works, I\r\nexplore my vast insecurities, shyness, compassion-- and the\r\nunreconciled emotional dark streets of my interior world. It serves as\r\na wondeful sort of self-therapy I suppose- and hearing it helps me\r\nbetter understand who I am. If it touches you in some way, I am equally\r\nhappy. Thanks, and I always welcome any honest feedback.\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=135\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Wilhelm\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(576,623,'The Advisors',1,71,'','','503-786-7068','<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Rod Tucker</span> - Vocals, Guitar<br/><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Ed Gelmetti </span>- Guitars, Bass, Synths<br/><br/>Rod and I reunited as music partners after ten years after the breakup of our previous band Josephine Ocean in 2006 to form The Advisors.<br/><br/>In our previous band, we were too preoccupied with our \"sound\". Frequently jumping from one supposed style to another in search of what we already had, but were unaware of.<br/><br/>This time around, being older and wiser, there is no sound...and it is our sound. You can\'t see the forest through the trees, yet you\'re already in the forest. And the forest is what it is.<br/><br/>Our influences are such that one song may be rock-ish, and one may sound like Lounge. But, that is what we are, there\'s no point worrying if we confuse anyone.<br/><br/>What\'s that campy saying? No matter where you go, there you are...<br/><br/>We are The Advisors<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=136\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with The Advisors\' fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(582,635,'Lenny Pierce',1,71,'myspace.com/LennyPierce','','','<p><br/>Lenny Pierce is the first artist of his kind.&nbsp; He is the beginning of a new generation of solo artists that today\'s stagnant industry desperately needs.&nbsp; He introduces a sound that fully tests and exceeds the limits of today\'s alternative-rock-pop music.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; As a writer of all original music and lyrics, Lenny stands out from the rest in many ways.&nbsp; Musically, lyrically, and vocally there is no one artist or band that Lenny can be directly compared to.&nbsp; With musical influences such as No Doubt, Marilyn Manson, Garbage, Kidneythieves, and Orgy, along with growing up listening to Hip Hop and R&B, Lenny has created a truly unique blend of music that is proving itself in its ability to reach out to a very diverse audience.&nbsp; His musical versatility is just one of the major aspects that sets this artist apart from all others.&nbsp; Lenny\'s ability to master different styles of music is remarkable.&nbsp; <br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; \"When I write, I don\'t really think about what I want the music to sound like in the end.&nbsp; It just starts with a thought that\'s usually brought on my something I am feeling really strong about that the moment, and it all sort of falls into place from there.&nbsp; It kind of makes itself, and I just help it along by putting it together.&nbsp; I like to see where it goes without limiting myself to one specific musical style.\"<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; From&nbsp;keyboard driven electronic alternative to upbeat rock pop to piano based ballads, Lenny\'s songs are strong, unique, powerful, fun, catchy, and most importantly, meaningful.&nbsp; Built on his emotions, Lenny pours his heart out and writes about his personal weaknesses, flaws, insecurities, losses, hopes and cares.<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; \"I just hope people will be able to relate to the things that I feel and the things that I\'ve been though.&nbsp; I really want to make a connection with people through my music.\"<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Aside from being the sole writer and singer of all his own music, Lenny personally performed, recorded, produced, and completed all the tracks on his demo, \"Everything Inside\".&nbsp; This 24 year old artist, with an image as strong as his sound will undeniably be in it for the long run.&nbsp; Lenny Pierce is sure to make a huge impact on today\'s popular music scene.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=290\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Lenny Pierce\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',0,'',0,''),(583,636,'Always Taken',1,61,'http://www.myspace.com/alwaystakenonline','','','<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: Verdana;\"><font color=\"#2e43dd\"><font color=\"#000000\"><strong>About Us</strong></font><br/></font>Luke and I met through RAVE Magazine and have been writing together since March 2005, though only 1 song has been written while we were both in the same room, \'Anarchy\'. Each song is transfered back and forth to each other over the internet until a final demo has been created.<br/><br/><font color=\"#000000\"><b>Luke Damsma </b><br/></font>Since the age of 16 I have always submersed myself with playing & writing original music, but now I spend most of my time concentrating on writing compositions. I started on the drums, then I dropped the sticks&nbsp;to learn the guitar. I dabble and create all the music from the home studio set up on the Gold Coast. <br/><br/><font color=\"#000000\"><b>Tayler Reid</b><br/></font>I have been writing in one form or another since high school, though I didn\'t start writing lyrics till I was 22. All my lyrics are inspired by things that have happened in my life and the lives of those around me. Every now and then I will pick up the guitar and compose, but I generally leave that part up to Luke .. as for the singing .. was never meant to .. but I caved in to the pressures of those around me.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=137\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Always Taken\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(586,642,'Anthony Z\'sler',1,71,'www.myspace.com/anthonyzsler','','','<p>In process........</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=138\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Anthony Z\'sler\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',0,'',0,''),(587,641,'ANCA',1,61,'www.anca-online.com','North London','','<p><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><font color=\"#000099\">Born in Bucharest, Anca relocated to The UK in 2003 in order to pursue her career as a Singer/Songwriter/Producer. Anca has created her own style, mainly pop orientated, spiced up with funky guitars and modern drumbeats. Amongst favourites are: Queen, U2, Maroon 5, Scissor Sisters, Faithless, Massive Attack, Jocelyn Brown, Cher, Annie Lennox, Seal, George Michael. While being greatly influenced by some of the above, her sound still retains its uniqueness. Possessed of a distinguished voice, not to mention an intriguing tone which gives it an enigmatic and ethereal quality, her sound is both easy to recognise and remember. Often Anca has been described as a cross between Gwen Stefani and Madonna. All of Anca&#8217;s recordings and can be heard via her website: www.anca-online.com or www.myspace.com/ancaonline. Available for Sessions, Radio Ads and jingles, etc, just email for details, also check out on www.anca-online.com samples of Anca&#8217;s productions made for TV / Films / Adverts. She is primarily concentrating on writing and recording new material, in addition to playing some live dates and currently doing a Foundation Degree in music production and music business with www.cmsounds.com / Westminster University &#8211; London. </font></span></p>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=139\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with ANCA\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(588,643,'5daysandcounting',1,68,'www.myspace.com/fivedaysandcountingband','9 pine wood green ave','00353857064270','<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=140\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\"></span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(607,669,'86 Superhero',1,76,'www.86superhero.com','','','<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=199\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with 86 Superhero\'s fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(589,644,'DJ HALO, DJ IVTV',104,0,'','','9184275530','<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=141\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with DJ HALO, DJ IVTV\'s fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(591,646,'miss marie',9,43,'http://myspace.com/marienyc','a treehouse','3472495913','<object classid=\"clsid:6BF52A52-394A-11D3-B153-00C04F79FAA6\" codebase=\"http://activex.microsoft.com/activex/controls/mplayer/en/nsmp2inf.cab#Version=5,1,52,701\" name=\"MediaPlayer1\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\">\r\n	<param name=\"width\" value=\"300\" />\r\n	<param name=\"name\" value=\"MediaPlayer1\" />\r\n	<param name=\"src\" value=\"http://youtube.com/watch?v=lhCm5or69Y4\" />\r\n	<param name=\"url\" value=\"http://youtube.com/watch?v=lhCm5or69Y4\" />\r\n	<param name=\"pluginspage\" value=\"http://www.microsoft.com/Windows/MediaPlayer\" />\r\n	<param name=\"autostart\" value=\"false\" />\r\n	<param name=\"height\" value=\"300\" />\r\n	<embed type=\"application/x-mplayer2\" width=\"300\" name=\"MediaPlayer1\" src=\"http://youtube.com/watch?v=lhCm5or69Y4\" pluginspage=\"http://www.microsoft.com/Windows/MediaPlayer\" autostart=\"false\" height=\"300\"></embed>\r\n</object>\r\n<img style=\"width: 208px; height: 200px\" src=\"http://www.reverbnation.com/data_public/artist/userfiles/8789/marie-logo3.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"208\" height=\"200\" /> \r\n<p align=\"center\">\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;<font color=\"#993300\">&nbsp;<strong><font face=\"Verdana\">As voted number 9 in MySpace&#39;s Top Unsigned Artists for Neo-Soul, Miss Marie&#39;s uniquely soothing voice brings to the table a smooth groove with an urban rhytm twist. Currently working on her first album, hear her play throught NYC, coming soon is her first single titled, &quot;Melody of Love.&quot;<br />\r\n</font></strong></font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"Verdana\"><strong><br />\r\n</strong></font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"Verdana\"><strong>Biography</strong></font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"Verdana\"><strong><span class=\"epktxt\">Marie comes from a pretty diverse background, having half her roots from New Orleans, the other half from Greece, and being raised in Brooklyn and Athens. Her earliest musical influences are Motown, New Orleans Jazz &amp; Funk, Eastern Ethnic Music, and Old School NY Hip Hop. She started learning classical piano, dance, and singing in a church choir at a very young age, till at 15 she decided to pick up the guitar and has been playing ever since. Her early years of playing rock and blues with various garage bands slowly grew into a more specific and &quot;mature&quot; sound, and she teamed up with the duo Andy and Simon of Hyplar (les disques aquatic). As a vocalist, rhythm guitarist, and co-writer for Hyplar, Marie experimented with a fusion of what she describes as &quot;liquid electronic crooning music that makes you want to roller skate&quot;. Parallel to performing with Hyplar, Marie was working with another recording band called Indaba with musicians Black Moses and Simo, also as a vocalist, rhythm guitarist and co-writer. Before leaving Greece, Marie teamed up with a producer and worked with him as a co-writer for many Greek pop artists on some funky soul and r&amp;b music that today are hits. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nSince moving back to NYC, Marie has been working on completing the production of her solo album &quot;Melody of Love&quot;. Playing weekly shows throughout the city with her band and building a good following.. She was voted into the Top 10 in Myspace&#39;s Top Unsigned Artists for Neo-Soul for NYC, as well as featured artist and finalist in the &#39;Make My Music Video&#39; competition for BestOfBands.com. More recently, Miss Marie has been recording for a compilation album &quot;Rhythms of the Diaspora&quot;&nbsp; for which she collaborated with legendary artists such as LL Cool J, Gil Scott Heron, The Last Poets, Stanley Clarke, Sidney Mills, Larry McDonald, Trouble Funk, Swiss Chris (drums John Legend),&nbsp; and more to be relased Feb. &#39;08. Miss Marie also is an active volunteer and devotes time for charity work. She is involved with humanitarian organizations such as Musicians On Call (www.musiciansoncall.com) where she performs for patients at hopsitals around NYC, Greek Aid (www.greekaid.org) raising money for the victims of the fires which devastated Greece in Aug &#39;07, and other charity concerts and events.<br />\r\n</span></strong></font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"Arial\"><font face=\"Arial\"></font></font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p align=\"center\">\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <a href=\"http://www.reverbnation.com/missmarieband\"><font color=\"#7f9aba\">www.reverbnation.com/missmarieband</font></a> \r\n</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p align=\"center\">\r\n<a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/missmarieband\"><font color=\"#7f9aba\">www.youtube.com/missmarieband</font></a> (live shows)\r\n</p>\r\n<p align=\"center\">\r\n<a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/marienyc\"><font color=\"#7f9aba\">www.myspace.com/marienyc</font></a>\r\n</p>\r\n<p align=\"center\">\r\nbooking: <a href=\"http://www.sonicbids.com/missmarie\"><font color=\"#7f9aba\">www.sonicbids.com/missmarie</font></a>&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p align=\"center\">\r\ncontact: <a href=\"mailto:miss_marie@musician.org\"><font color=\"#7f9aba\">miss_marie@musician.org</font></a>\r\n</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=142\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt\">Interact with miss marie&#39;s fans</span></a>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(592,647,'Southern Mischief',1,16,'http://www.SouthernMischiefBand.com','3990 Woodland CIR SE - Conyers, GA 30013','678-768-4028','<p align=\"left\">\r\n<font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong><img src=\"../uploads/647/southern%20mischief%20band.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"486\" height=\"600\" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nABOUT:</strong> </font><strong>SOUTHERN MISCHIEF</strong> <br />\r\n<br />\r\nFormed in February 2007, Southern Mischief began with a simple statement of purpose: <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>&quot;We are on a Mission to bring back the glory days of Southern Rock &amp; Roll. When </strong><span style=\"border-bottom: #0066cc 1px dashed; height: 1em\"><strong>Lynyrd Skynyrd</strong></span><strong>, 38 Special, </strong><span style=\"border-bottom: #0066cc 1px dashed; height: 1em\"><strong>Molly Hatchet</strong></span><strong>, The </strong><span style=\"border-bottom: #0066cc 1px dashed; height: 1em\"><strong>Allman Brothers</strong></span><strong>, etc... ruled the airwaves and made everyone fall in love with that wonderful Southern Rock groove!&quot; <br />\r\n</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\">\r\n<img src=\"../uploads/647/band.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"375\" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><font color=\"#ff0000\">ABOUT: </font>THE BAND MEMBERS</strong> <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src=\"../uploads/647/th_craig1.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Craig Maxim\" title=\"Craig Maxim\" width=\"108\" height=\"150\" align=\"left\" />&quot;<strong>Craig Maxim</strong>&quot; (<font color=\"#ff0000\">Lead Singer, Rhythm Guitar &amp; Keyboards</font>) became a professional musician, singer and songwriter at age 12, performing across the country with his mother&#39;s Top-40 band. Since then, he has formed several bands of his own, including &quot;Enough Said&quot;, &quot;Narrow Is The Way&quot;, &quot;The Guild&quot; and most recently &quot;Southern Mischief&quot;, performing across America and in other countries, with audiences reaching tens of thousands. Craig resides in <span style=\"border-bottom: #0066cc 1px dashed; height: 1em\">Conyers, Georgia</span>. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src=\"../uploads/647/daniel.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Daniel LeFever\" title=\"Daniel LeFever\" width=\"150\" height=\"113\" align=\"left\" />&quot;<strong>Daniel LeFever</strong>&quot; (<font color=\"#ff0000\">Bass</font>), is quickly becoming a veteran of the music biz, having performed in several successful projects. Being a musician has always been his life long dream, and he pursues it with a vengeance. Daniel resides in <span style=\"border-bottom: #0066cc 1px dashed; height: 1em\">Covington, Georgia</span>. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src=\"../uploads/647/gary.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Gary Esslinger\" title=\"Gary Esslinger\" width=\"150\" height=\"113\" align=\"left\" />&quot;<strong>Gary Esslinger</strong>&quot; (<font color=\"#ff0000\">Lead Guitar</font>), comes from a long line of musicians. His father&#39;s band opened for the Kinks. When you hear those sweet riffs coming from his Fender Strat, or his Gibson SG, you just know he was born to make the guitar sing! He is a veteran of the music biz, having been a member of several successful bands as well as pursuing solo projects. He is a lead and rhythm guitarist as well as a singer and songwriter! Gary resides in <span style=\"border-bottom: #0066cc 1px dashed; height: 1em\">Covington, Georgia</span>. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src=\"../uploads/647/brian1.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Brian Griffin\" width=\"150\" height=\"113\" align=\"left\" />&quot;<strong>Brian Griffin</strong>&quot; (<font color=\"#ff0000\">Drums/Percussion</font>) knew he wanted to be a drummer from age 7, and since that time has been a member of several groups, including: The Griffins, Battlecreek, Doug Binder and the Midnight Express. For the last several years, he has been a veteran of the <span style=\"border-bottom: #0066cc 1px dashed; height: 1em\">Chattanooga</span> music scene, but wanting to branch out into the Atlanta area, Brian joined &quot;Southern Mischief&quot; and as they say, &quot;The rest was history!&quot; Brian resides in Ft. Oglethorpe, Georgia. \r\n</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<img src=\"../uploads/647/Mike%20Grant.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" align=\"left\" />&quot;<strong>Mike Grant</strong>&quot; <br />\r\n(<font color=\"#ff0000\">Lead Guitar / Vocals</font>) is a veteran of the music business, having performed in several successful bands. In addition to guitar, Mike also sings and plays drums. Southern Mischief is proud to welcome Mike as our newest member! Mike resides in Covington, Georgia.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=143\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt\">Interact with Southern Mischief&#39;s fans</span></a> \r\n',1,'',0,''),(2642,1000902,'in shadows embrace',7,83,'http://www.myspace.com/inshadowsembracelv','henderson nevada','(702)927-3429','<p>\r\nwe&#39;re still a pretty new band but we have a solid line-up and have things gonig pretty well. we are in the middle of recording&nbsp; and should have a 5 song demo pretty soon \r\n</p>\r\n',1,'walter-vocals<br />\r\ncasey-vocals<br />\r\nadam z.-guitar<br />\r\nmike z.-guitar<br />\r\nsteve-bass<br />\r\nnick-drums \r\n',0,''),(594,652,'Brian Van Meter',1,61,'www.myspace.com/brianvanmeter','','','<p align=\"left\"><br/><a href=\"http://click.linksynergy.com/fs-bin/stat?id=0GYvJ0fg08g&offerid=78941&type=3&subid=0&tmpid=1826&RD_PARM1=http%253A%252F%252Fphobos.apple.com%252FWebObjects%252FMZStore.woa%252Fwa%252FviewAlbum%253Fi%253D213570800%2526id%253D213570533%2526s%253D143441%2526partnerId%253D30\"><img style=\"width: 391px; height: 67px;\" src=\"http://www.tone-box.com/myspace/bvm/bvmbanner.jpg\" height=\"60\" width=\"345\"/></a></p>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=145\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Brian Van Meter\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',0,'',0,''),(596,654,'Bushman Boy & the Flats',11,96,'www.myspace.com/bushmanboyandtheflats','','','<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=146\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Bushman Boy & the Flats\' fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(601,662,'Middlebrook',1,66,'www.myspace.com/middlebrookmusic','','','<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=272\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Middlebrook\'s fans</span></a>',1,'',0,''),(602,663,'Poetic Reasoning',1,69,'http://Myspace.com/PoeticReasoning','556 Summerview Dr.','614 395 9979','<p>\r\nSeparately, it&rsquo;s hard to believe these guys came from the same broken home. However, when they are together doing what they do best their differences put them in tune with each other. When together any person can easily be swept up and taken to a different place. A total of five siblings, they were raised together by their mother alone. They had to move every couple of years while they were young, so making friends and adjusting to new circumstances and surroundings eventually came easy for them. During their adolescent years&rsquo; believing that there is a reason for everything was essential.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nChad, the lead guitarist and the eldest, probably grew up faster than any of them. Becoming the man of the house happened around the age of 10. His responsibilities consisted of keeping peace between the younger ones and just being there to watch over the family. Responsible and self-sufficient he left the family to go out on his own at an early age. He moved to Mississippi, married, and settled down with two sons. Chad&rsquo;s musical talent and interest has always been a part of who he is, so he found satisfaction playing with various small town bands while living in the south. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nDustin, the lead vocalist, has been a natural entertainer since the day he picked up the guitar. When in company the guitar is always by his side. Very talented and very modest about his capabilities, his music comes from the heart. Determined to be his own man he also left the house in his late teens. Dustin settling down at an early age and taking his responsibility as a spouse and father very serious was not a surprise to anyone who knows him well. He knew as a preteen that he is family orientated and would one day have one of his own. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nBrett, the rhythm guitarist and the youngest, definitely drives this band. The absence of his siblings during his teen years left him alone with his thoughts and dreams. Brett stayed at home and finished school with goals of becoming a law enforcer, at the same time believing in the dream he has for himself and his family. His gift of awareness goes hand and hand with his understanding of life. Compassionate, soft spoken and extremely loyal Brett thrives on good times, family and friends.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nAfter ten years Chad&rsquo;s marriage came to an abrupt and unexpected end. He moved back to Ohio to be with his family for moral support. Together these brothers found an outlet for expressing who they are through music. They connect with the listener by singing about real life. Chad&rsquo;s old school rock, Dustin&rsquo;s new age or alternative sound, and Brett&rsquo;s melody combined gives this band their unique sound. Their differences compliment each other in spirit and in talent. Their mothers&rsquo; determination and motivation to do her best set in play for them that with these two attributes anything is possible. To this day they believe that there is a reason for everything, and Brett&rsquo;s vision began to take place. &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;Poetic Reasoning.\r\n</p>\r\n<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"2\"></font><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=147\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt\">Interact with Poetic Reasoning&#39;s fans</span></a>\r\n',1,'Dustin Webb- Vocals<br />\r\nChad Terry- Lead Guitar<br />\r\nBrett Webb- Rhythm Guitar\r\n',0,''),(598,656,'Bru',10,45,'','','','<h4>A few of my friends told me \"write me a song... write me a song\",\r\nso i did just that. If I were to die tomorrow, this song would be my\r\ndying last words. </h4><hr>\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" width=\"100%\">\r\n\r\n\r\n</table> \r\n         \r\n           \r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=148\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Bru\'s fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(595,653,'Bob Hausler',8,37,'bobhausler.com','','989-799-8360','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-indent: 0.5in; text-align: center;\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: Arial;\">Bob Hausler<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-indent: 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-indent: 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-indent: 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial;\">Award winning singer, songwriter, guitarist, and entertainer Bob Hausler has entertained thousands of people in his career. Working with such artists as Cheryl K. Warner, Laurie Middlebrook, Brenda Cole, Jen Cass, and many more. He has opened for such artists as; Eric Church, The Mavericks, Neil McCoy, Sawyer Brown, Tracy Lawrence, Diamond Rio, Chris Cagle, and many more. As a session guitarist he has played on hundreds of recordings. As a songwriter his songs have been pitched to or recorded by artists like: Alabama, Jon Anderson, Randy Travis, Laurie Morgan, Laurie Middlebrook, Cheryl K. Warner, and others. He is currently working on his first solo recording project. An emotional singer, Bob loves to let the song come from the heart. At home in front of a crowd of thousands or in the intimate setting of a small club, he performs with energy and soul.<span>&nbsp; </span>Known for his high-spirited performance and endless energy, Bob reaches out to his audience in a very personal way. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-indent: 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial;\">He is currently at work on his first solo recording project, as yet untitled. Recording some of the songs that are very close to him. This project is sure to be a highlight of an already productive career.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-indent: 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial;\">As the founder and current president of the Mid-Michigan Songwriters Guild, he spends a lot of time helping others develop their songwriting skills. A devoted husband and father of two. He is a member of BMI and NSAI (Nashville Songwriters Assoc. International).</span><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-indent: 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial;\">Just a small list of some of the bands and artists he has worked with: <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 178.5pt; text-indent: -142.5pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial;\">Cheryl K. Warner<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>(CKW recording artist with several #1 hits)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-indent: 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial;\">Laurie Middlebrook<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>(LAMB recording artist)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-indent: 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial;\">Brenda Cole<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>(Melody Dawn recording artist)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-indent: 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial;\">Melba Montgomery<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Nashville recording artist<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-indent: 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial;\">Marty Haggard<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Nashville recording artist<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-indent: 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial;\">Bronco Billy<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-indent: 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial;\">Larry McCray<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>(Point Blank recording artist)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-indent: 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial;\">The </span><st1:state><st1:place><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial;\">Tennessee</span></st1:place></st1:state><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial;\"> Fat Cats (</span><st1:city><st1:place><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial;\">Columbia</span></st1:place></st1:city><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial;\"> Records)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-indent: 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial;\">Randy Preston<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-indent: 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial;\">Desperado<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-indent: 0.5in;\"><st1:city><st1:place><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial;\">Phoenix</span></st1:place></st1:city><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-indent: 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial;\">Billy and The Beertones<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-indent: 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial;\">Richard (Dick) Wagner<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>(Atlantic Records)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-indent: 0.5in;\"><font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Owner of Bit-By Bit Studios in </span><st1:place><st1:city><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Midland</span></st1:city><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\"> </span><st1:state><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Michigan</span></st1:state></st1:place><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-indent: 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\"><font size=\"2\">Feature writer for Tune-Up Magazine.</font></span><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=149\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Bob Hausler\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(603,664,'Green Room',1,17,'www.greenroomband.co.uk','','','Green Room are a 5-piece band from England. Featuring haunting, sultry\r\nvocals, a watertight rhythm section and gorgeous piano & guitar\r\nriffs and hooks, they have earned praise from record industry insiders\r\nand music fans alike.\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=200\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Green Room\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(604,665,'Insinu',1,71,'www.purevolume.com/0001insinu','22 Old Redding Road','(203)-431-3661','<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><font style=\"font-size: 12pt;\" color=\"#ffffff\" size=\"1\"><font color=\"#000000\">The Members \"the</font> <font color=\"#000000\">Gods\"<br/><br/>Richie Hume------Lead Vocals, Guitar<br/>Drew Arcoleo---Lead Guitar, Back up vocals<br/>Steve Budlong-- Drums<br/>Jon Borden------Bass<br/></font></font><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"1\"><strong><br/><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>===========================================================<br/></strong></span></strong></font></span></p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><b><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"1\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"1\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><b><font style=\"font-size: 8pt;\" color=\"#000000\" size=\"1\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><br/></span></strong></span></p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><b><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"1\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><font color=\"#000000\" size=\"1\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">\r\n<p><b><font style=\"font-size: 8pt;\" color=\"#000000\" size=\"1\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Insinu is a four piece band who are all going to be sophmore students at RHS. They recorded and cut their 1st CD which you can listen to on the pure volume playlist. This CD is now just over one year old and we are working on our next!! INSINU\'s members all have the passion for their instruments, and love the music they play. We are planning on hitting the studio very soon!.</span></strong></span></font></b></p></span></strong></span></font></span></font></b></span></span></strong></span></span></span></strong></span></font><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><font style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" color=\"#000000\" size=\"1\">here\'s a fellow quote from Drew Arcoleo:<br/>\"We have been blowing peoples minds with our blessed music since the 6th grade. With that said, if you are ever given the glorious chance of hearing us play live, you will be blown away so much you will probably go insane. In fact, twenty percent of the people who attend our shows, were said to have been running off with their faces on fire from our shredding guitar riffs, punching basslines, ear warming vocals, and heart thumping drums. so, my fellow music lovers, listen to us if you dare\"<br/></font></span></span></strong></span></b></span></strong></span></font><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"></span></strong></span><strong>======================================================</strong></b></span></strong></span></span></font><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><b><strong>=====<span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"></span></strong></b></span></strong></span></b></span></span></strong></span>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=273\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Insinu\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1853,1920,'The Starseed Project',1,76,'www.thestarseedproject.com','','','The StarSeed Project is a new band in the South Eastern U.S. that draws from a wide range of styles to create our own signature sound. We started with a core of three, Tom Bright, Jeff Morgan, and Eric Bright, and began writing our own style of original music over a period of almost 2 years. We searched for another guitarist to join us and a vocalist to take the stage. After many excruciating auditions and let downs, we were joined by our old friend Robb Winde on guitar who had just become a free agent again. A short time later we brought on our new front man Marc Shipley. All of us have performed at some time or another in front of music fans in the South East. Some of the bands that we have performed with include Fetish, Verloren Hoop, Day One, Doc Ellis and 5 Minute Major. With the combined years of music experience, a variety of musical talent, and a natural bond we began The Starseed Project. With the drive and determination that we as a band possess GREAT things are going to happen',1,'',0,''),(1502,1883,'Sal Gambino',1,14,'','8 seaglade','646-372-1853','Sal Gambino a pro caliber instrumental guitar player that has a passion for writing and playing instrumental rock guitar music. Sal is currently writing more music and has&nbsp;many more songs completed. Sal is looking for bass players and drummers to help complete future songs and recording. P.S sal is in search for a music contract.',0,'',0,''),(605,666,'6 DICE',1,71,'www.6DICE.com','','','<p><span class=\"rvts1\">6 DICE, one of Atlanta\'s premier all originals rock and roll bands. 6 DICE is composed of five solid musicians who have a dedicated passion for writing and performing music.&nbsp; The band is Joel Bartlett, Matt Ferguson, Gary Lynn Goller, Rick Slavens and Larry Wood.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"rvts1\">After tearing off a piece of our roots, 6 DICE puts it together with the modern music of today. Having being compared to the Foo Fighters, the magic of sound is rejuvinated with the combination of accoustic and electric crossing the lines together into a whole new realm.&nbsp; Solid bass and drums are the backbone with tremendous vocals bringing the music to life.&nbsp; From slow melodic danceable songs to quick, highly charged and energenized rock and roll, there is something that will appeal to everyone.&nbsp; <br/><br/></span><span class=\"rvts1\">The enthusiasm is always evident at their performances for 6 DICE are more than musicians...they are performers and entertainers. The energy that 6 DICE brings forth will tear you from your seat and carry you to the dance floor.&nbsp; You can always expect to be kept intrigued, engaged and moved at every show.&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"rvts1\">6 DICE released their debut album \"Tree Full Of Branches\" in the fall of 2006 and has received an overwhelming positive response to it. 6 DICE continues to perform their exciting shows around the Atlanta area and beyond. Look for&nbsp; 6 DICE in your area and be sure not to miss out on the next performance.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"rvts1\"></span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=150\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with 6 DICE\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(606,668,'1989',1,71,'www.myspace.com/1989band','','33855838','\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 36pt\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">Brisbane artists have been loudly announcing their talent to the world with an energy and enthusiasm that is infectious. Acts like Regurgitator, The Veronicas and Powderfinger have inspired a whole new wave of young talent who also aspire to become music legends. <br/><br/>Brisbane 5-piece 1989 are no exception. Formed in late 2006 by 22 year old singer Simon Vermeulen, 20 year old bassist Jason Fuller, and 18 year old guitarist Thomas Sheldrake, the band came together to launch their dream of making music that would touch people, and pull them back in time to the 1980&#8217;s. <br/><br/>The bands musical genre could best be described as an 80&#8217;s rock sound with modern sensibilities. Each member of the band has been strongly influenced by the distinctive sound of 80&#8217;s rock, and because of that influence they called their band 1989, as that year signified the end of 80&#8217;s rock. <br/><br/>The boys of 1989 are still living in that year&#8230; but thankfully their fashion sense and hair styles have moved on with the times! <br/><br/>While practicing and dreaming of getting a break into the music industry, the boys realised something was missing from their ensemble. As a three piece outfit they decided they needed a little extra rhythm and decided they would need to recruit a second guitarist. As the band&#8217;s vocalist, Simon, was pulling double duties by singing and drumming, they decided it might be a good idea to recruit a drummer also. That&#8217;s how Mark Haddon and Steve Tyssen came to join the band. <br/><br/>Mark was a 32 year old work colleague and friend of Simon, so he was the perfect choice for the band as his experience and talent on the guitar made him a certain shoe-in. <br/><br/>Finding 21 year old Steve was a little harder though. After many months of ads and auditions the boys started to think they were never going to find anyone talented enough to join their outfit. But, in the best mould of legendary bands everywhere, that&#8217;s when Steve answered an ad one day out of the blue. He blew them away and added that extra something to the mix. This is when the boys knew their search was over. <br/><br/>In late March 2007, the band 1989 was officially formed, and they jumped into rehearsing and writing new songs straight away. Since then they have self-recorded and produced their original debut 6-track EP completely out of the drummer&#8217;s shed. <br/><br/>1989 are just a group of ordinary boys with big dreams, but they actually have the talent necessary to make it, and the dedication required to sustain it. Rehearsing out of Tommy&#8217;s father&#8217;s garage (Tyrepower Redcliffe), they crank the sounds out as they perfect their chosen art and bring their dreams closer to reality. <br/><br/>Look out for the lads at a gig near you soon. You won&#8217;t be disappointed.</span><br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=201\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\">Interact with 1989\'s fans</span></a><br/></p>',1,'',0,''),(610,675,'Alex P. Taylor',1,73,'www.alexptaylor.com','137 Mayflower Street','860-518-3267','\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt\"><font face=\"Arial\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img height=\"192\" alt=\"icon\" src=\"http://www.alexptaylor.com/images/alex_icon2.gif\" width=\"191\"/><br/><br/><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <a href=\"http://www.alexptaylor.com\">www.alexptaylor.com</a><br/><br/></font></span></p><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt\"><font face=\"Arial\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt\">Alex P. Taylor is currently residing in <?xml:namespace prefix = st1 /><st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:City w:st=\"on\">West Hartford</st1:City>, <st1:State w:st=\"on\">CT.</st1:State></st1:place> He graduated from <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:PlaceName w:st=\"on\">Central</st1:PlaceName> <st1:PlaceName w:st=\"on\">Connecticut</st1:PlaceName> <st1:PlaceType w:st=\"on\">State</st1:PlaceType> <st1:PlaceType w:st=\"on\">University</st1:PlaceType></st1:place> with a major in Communications and a minor in Journalism. Attending quite a few different schools during his youth, he has learned the true value of a smile and how that simple gesture can give birth to many new friendships.<?xml:namespace prefix = o /><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt\">He wrote the lyrics to his first song when he was nine, but it wouldn&#8217;t be until early summer of 2005 that he would rediscover and truly embrace his passion for songwriting. Going through some old boxes in his basement that summer, he came across a dusty folder of songs he had written as a teenager and decided to share his lyrics with a couple of his good friends. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt\">One of those good friends, Adam Stevenson, he worked with at The Corner Pug. Adam was a guitar player and after reading through Alex&#8217;s folder asked him, &#8220;Why aren&#8217;t you doing anything with these songs?&#8221; Perhaps it was fear of rejection, maybe he thought it was too late, whatever the reason, the question made Alex think again. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt\">Sadly, one terrible night a few weeks later, he would see his friend Adam, only twenty-one, for the last time. He would die of an accidental drug overdose, and it would be at his funeral that Alex&#8217;s life would change dramatically.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt\">His mother, a very strong woman, gave a powerful eulogy to a church full of Adam&#8217;s peers. &#8220;Now is the time to look at your life,&#8221; she said. &#8220;Let this be a wake up call to all of you&#8230;&#8221; She stated how Adam no longer had the opportunity to follow his dreams and if there had been something in our lives that we have wanted to do, make it happen. Do it with Adam in mind&#8230;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt\">That night, for the first time in ten years, Alex sat down and wrote the lyrics to a new song with Adam in mind. It&#8217;s was called &#8220;On My Floor.&#8221; The next day he feverishly purchased several books about songwriting and soon after started attending music seminars to find his musical counterpart, someone that would transcribe the music to his melodies and lyrics. After going through several musicians, he would meet producer Jamie Sherwood of <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:City w:st=\"on\">Southington</st1:City>, <st1:State w:st=\"on\">CT</st1:State></st1:place>, who would turn out to be a perfect match to his dream.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt\">From Adam&#8217;s death, Alex&#8217;s dream of becoming a performing songwriter had been reborn. Through tragedy, he found light. Adam&#8217;s mother&#8217;s words had truly been his wake up call, a wake up call to follow his destiny&#8230;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p></font>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.5in\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt\"><font face=\"Arial\"><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The name of his first album is entitled Stop Signs and Red Lights. It is now available on iTunes and at www.cdbaby.com/cd/alexptaylor<br/><br/><o:p></o:p></font></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><o:p><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"2\"><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/alexptaylor\">www.myspace.com/alexptaylor</a>&nbsp;<br/>&nbsp;<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; <img height=\"192\" alt=\"icon\" src=\"http://www.alexptaylor.com/images/alex_icon2.gif\" width=\"191\"/></font></o:p></p><br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=151\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\">Interact with Alex P. Taylor\'s fans</span></a><br/></span>',0,'',0,''),(611,677,'Against The Season',1,76,'www.myspace.com/4ats','','','<font size=\"5\">\r\n<p align=\"center\">A sibling rock band determined to share their message and experiences to the world. Writing, singing and expressing their thoughts through songs that are simply real. Against The Season originally hailing from California now resides in Salt Lake City, Utah. Tiare,16,Lead guitarist was inspired by rock music at an even earlier age and discovered her musical talent on the guitar. Kelela,18, Shared the music playing the bass guitar. Both young teens also contributed the lyrics on all of the songs. Donnie,21, playing the drums starting at the age of 8 years old has become a prodigy at his age. Mika,23, the eldest of the four and newest member of the band plays the rhythm guitar and shares his talent of arranging the music. Together they are out to share their music to all who love and respect rock music and in the midst of this gigantic music industry, Against The Season truly stands for one thing.....Be Yourself!!</p>\r\n<p align=\"center\">A.T.S.</p></font>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=303\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Against The Season\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(612,678,'RIAH',4,23,'http://www.myspace.com/shedhouserecords','','520 805 1818','RIAH is an M.C. who has been doing music for a very long time. His style which he calls &quot;Dark Rap&quot; is sometimes hard to follow. He raps about the many dark sides of life. Not exaclly wicked but just the dark side. During his live sets he has been known to yell out the most random things. He also does stuff on stage like spit fire. Everyone enjoys him on stage because he has alot of energy and is able to grab his audience. he loves lyrics in music and beats have to be right aswell. He is still a struggling musician and waits for the day he makes it. He says &quot;Failure is no option, music has always been my 1 love and always will be. I will continue till I die&quot;. This is the man, the M.C., RIAH<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div>\r\n<object classid=\"clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000\" codebase=\"http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0\" width=\"425\" height=\"350\">\r\n	<param name=\"height\" value=\"350\" />\r\n	<param name=\"width\" value=\"425\" />\r\n	<param name=\"wmode\" value=\"transparent\" />\r\n	<param name=\"src\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/sFs6iRM1mL0\" />\r\n	<embed type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" height=\"350\" width=\"425\" wmode=\"transparent\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/sFs6iRM1mL0\"></embed>\r\n</object>\r\n</div>\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=152\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt\">Interact with RIAH&#39;s fans</span></a><br />\r\n',0,'',0,''),(615,660,'Bjorn Lid',1,61,'www.myspace.com/bjrn1','6240 Orskog','45423869','Hi there.<br/>So... what&nbsp;can&nbsp;I tell you about myself, without bore you to death??? Well, I\'ll try to keep it short and concise.&nbsp;<br/>My name is Bj&oslash;rn Lid. I was born in a (very) small town in Norway on&nbsp;December 13th, 1976. And I still live in the same small town today. I\'m a singer, or that is; I sing, and wanna become a singer.&nbsp;I have&nbsp;written some songs, but I\'m definitely not a very productive song-writer. When it comes&nbsp;to&nbsp;taste&nbsp;in music,&nbsp;I like a lot of the old stuff; The Doors, The Rolling Stones, The Beatles.... Roy Orbison\'s voice brings tears to my eyes.<br/>I like groups such as Deep Purple, Black Sabbath, Led Zeppelin, and Guns\'n Roses. But I also like a lot of the \"newer\" groups and singers; Travis, Oasis, R.E.M, Kula Shaker, U2, Lisa Marie Presley, Amy Whineheart is great. I like an amazing Norwegian group called Madrugada and an other Norwegian group called AHA. But NOTHING... compares to Elvis!!!&nbsp;<br/>I don\'t know how relevant hobbies and stuff like that are, but&nbsp;what the heck; I like to work out. I lift weights 3-5 times a week.<br/>I\'m interested in a lot that has to do with science, or in the grey-zone between science and science fiction. The supernatural and occult. I suck up anything I come across of books and&nbsp;movies about UFOs, The Bermuda Triangle, The Great Pyramids of Giza, ghosts and hauntings and so forth.&nbsp;I love animals, especially cats. I have three.&nbsp;<br/>In late August, I\'m entering a studio to start working on my first album/CD with my own material... my own songs. As soon as that album is ready to be released, I will promote it for all that it\\\'s worth. Both on my music MySpace site, my showcase and off course... here!!!<br/>I hope there\'s something here that you find worth listening to. I have a Live-Album/CD ready to be released in a couple of weeks.<br/>One Night At \"Cinderella\"-Benefit For Natalie (02. 03. 2007).&nbsp;It is a recording of a&nbsp;benefit I did, to raise money&nbsp;for a young girl named Natalie. Her father got shot and killed in Thailand, right before New Year 2006. We didn\'t have enough time to gather a full band and singers, and put together a show; so I had to use \"Sing-Back\". It didn\'t seem to matter to the audience though. They were absolutely fantastic!!! The show lasted almost three full hours. I\'ve added 12 tracks, just to give you an idea of how the CD will sound like. When it\'s ready, all 39 songs from the show will be on it. The&nbsp;CD&nbsp;can&nbsp;be&nbsp;bought&nbsp;for&nbsp;179.50 NOK. That\'s about 32$. I hope you like some of the&nbsp;tracks I\'ve added&nbsp;so far!!! ENJOY:)<br/><br/>I can\'t think of anything more to add right now. I think&nbsp;that&nbsp;just about&nbsp;sums it all up.&nbsp;<br/><br/>Thank you for taking the time to drop by, and check out my music. <br/><br/>LOL, Bj&oslash;rn<br/><br/><br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=202\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Bjorn Lid\'s fans</span></a>',0,'',0,''),(619,685,'Act Naturally',1,66,'www.myspace.com/actnaturallyrock','','','<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=153\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Act Naturally\'s fans</span></a><br/><br/>',1,'',0,''),(621,672,'aDORE',1,66,'www.myspace.com/adoreuk','','07732082363','aDORE are a creative five piece hailing from London and surrounding towns, who met through various mutual friends and musical collaborations.<br/><br/>aDORE have played a&nbsp;large number of successful shows in and around London (which are getting bigger, along with the venues)&nbsp;and are currently looking for management.&nbsp; They are also looking to perform in their respective home towns and other cities around the UK.<br/><br/>Their songs have a dark, emotional resonance and lyrics that find the beauty in pain. The band create dream-like ambient textures and melodies to die for. This is enhanced with spontaneity, intensity and intimacy which aDORE conjure live.<br/><br/>This is music that can \'t be pinned down!<br/><br/>Recently, aDORE have successfully recorded 8 tracks at a studio in London which&nbsp;have been&nbsp;mixed and mastered to be sent to eagerly awaiting producers and record labels.&nbsp; aDORE are also playing larger gigs and are looking to return to the studio to record more amzing songs!<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<u>aDORE are:</u><br/>Ramy - vocals<br/><a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/prodmusicuk\">Prod</a> - guitar &&nbsp;backing vocals<br/><a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/neilsinclair1\">Sinky</a> - guitar<br/><a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/drunknmunkyuk\">Chris</a> - bass<br/>Sam - drums\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=203\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with aDORE\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(628,696,'Canine feline',1,61,'www.myspace.com/caninefeline','22 winifred road, cobholm, Great yarmouth','07786115893','The band members are:<br/>Becs: Vocals<br/>James: Guitar<br/>Arron: Bass<br/>Steve: Drums<br/><br/>We are a 4 piece female fronted band from the East of the UK. We formed in December 2006 and have since been busy writing, recording, performing and promoting our origial music. We pride ourselves on our exciting and entertaining live performances while writing and recording great music that everyone can enjoy. We got together after all our the local cover bands we were in ended at roughly the same time. When we got together we all had the same vision of creating a band that wanted to take thier music to the top. Becs is a powerful and passionate singer & has a great stage image and personality, James is a very talented guitar player with a unique style and great showmanship, Arron is a solid bass player who makes every song his own and Steve is a superb drummer who writes the drums to fit the style of each indivual song perfectly. We are all 100% passionate about what we do and have great fun doing it...we want to make music our lives and are determind to get there! <br/><br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=154\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\">Interact with Canine feline\'s fans</span></a>',1,'',0,''),(654,729,'Apathy',1,71,'www.myspace.com/garagebandapathy','','','<font style=\"font-size: 18px;\"> Apathy <br/>\r\n\r\n<br/> The grunge-tinged indie rock assault of Apathy is sure to induce\r\nanything but apathy in the listener. Immediate, exciting and\r\nartistically confrontational, the music of Apathy is a post-modern\r\nexpression of humanity in the here and now. It&#8217;s also a helluva potent\r\nsource of entertainment. <br/>\r\n\r\n<br/> Another Realm <br/>\r\n\r\n<br/> Music may intersect with this world but it exists in a place all\r\nits own. It is, in fact, a place all its own. At least that&#8217;s what the\r\nmembers of Apathy will tell you. Its power is transcendent and its\r\nability to whisk the listener away to another place is proof enough of\r\nits status as a universe in its own right. &#8220;It&#8217;s another realm, and\r\nwhile we&#8217;re playing, we care about nothing else. Thus the name Apathy.&#8221;\r\nInterestingly enough, those who have heard Apathy say the same thing\r\nabout the band&#8217;s music &#8211; when Apathy is playing, the fan has no\r\nconcerns other than wallowing in the transportational exuberance of\r\nApathy. <br/>\r\n\r\n<br/> Impact <br/>\r\n\r\n<br/> &#8220;We try to make our songs very powerful,&#8221; says Clint VanSciver of\r\nApathy, who states that impact on the listener is a prime goal of this\r\nband&#8217;s songwriting. He says that lyrically the group offers a hint of\r\nambiguity mixed with relatively concrete ideas in order to give the\r\nlistener something with which to relate while allowing the audience to\r\nfind the specific meaning therein. Musically, it&#8217;s all about attitude.\r\n&#8220;There is an attitude about every Apathy song that makes it very\r\ncharismatic, just hooky enough to draw you in but gritty enough to get\r\nyou going.&#8221; <br/>\r\n\r\n<br/> The Artist at Work <br/>\r\n\r\n<br/> The song &#8220;Anything You Want&#8221; was played for three solid days on\r\nGeorgetown&#8217;s 93.5 The Beach during Chris Steele&#8217;s program. Apathy\'s\r\noriginals also nab regular airplay on Ocean City, Maryland&#8217;s X106.9. In\r\na little more than a year, the group has played almost 40 shows in a\r\nvariety of venues, with more gigs still to come. The Worcester County\r\nTimes gave the band front page press and Apathy has also appeared in\r\nthe Delaware Beachcomber, the Seaford Leader, the Morning Star, the\r\nDaily Times, the Dispatch/Maryland Coast Dispatch, the Sussex Post, the\r\nCape Gazette and the Delmarva Youth Magazine. The group is currently\r\nworking with A&R Select, the hottest indie A&R firm in\r\nHollywood, CA. &#8220;Apathy, as well as many who have experienced our music,\r\ntruly believe that we&#8217;re the next big thing.&#8221; And these musicians have\r\nthe work ethic to pay off for the label with the faith to offer them to\r\nthe world as that next great rock act. <br/>\r\n\r\n<br/> Review <br/>\r\n\r\n<br/> &#8220;While Apathy certainly embraces elements of grunge rock, the\r\ngroup is NOT to be understood as dwelling in the past. If anything,\r\nthis band is carrying rock-n-roll into the future.&#8221; &#8211; A&R Select <br/><br/>\r\n\r\nQuotes about Apathy:\r\n\r\n\"[Apathy produces] strong rock tracks with a diverse array of sounds to\r\nbring to the table ranging from classic rock to indie rock to grunge.\"<br/>\r\n\"Apathy comes in with high energy and great drum grooves and in the pocket strength.\"<br/>\r\n\"The vocals are a good fit for the music.\"<br/>\r\n\"The band has a certain attitude about them which gives them more depth and energy all around.\"<br/>\r\n\"Well written songs\"<br/>\r\n\"Great acoustic and clean sounds.\"<br/>\r\n\"Great straight up rock band with good\r\nsongwriting.\"<br/>\r\n\"Catchy choruses and unique\r\nrock song writing.\"<br/>\r\n\"Great band for the genre.\"</font>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=207\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Apathy\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(663,755,'Maxim Sound',6,31,'','','','<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=304\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Maxim Sound\'s fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(2405,1000144,'Human Vibe',1,68,'http://myspace.com/humanvibe','','514-966-7771','<span><font face=\"Times New Roman\" size=\"3\"></font></span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\"><span>&nbsp;</span><span>Human Vibe is a combination of Nicko&rsquo;s soul-filled voice and music and the talent of professional musicians Luc on drums and Karine on bass.<span>&nbsp; </span></span><span>Their lyrics and rock music are highlighted with several colourful styles such as funk, reggae and folk.<span>&nbsp; </span>The group&rsquo;s influences come from a wide variety of musical styles, from hard rock and alternative rock such as Tool and Alice in Chains, to British groups like The Police, Genesis and Yes. Human Vibe also enjoys injecting their creations with sounds of their current inspirations, Ben Harper, Daniel Lanois, Coral Egan, Afro Celt <font color=\"#000000\">Sound System, Dead Can Dance, Susheela Raman and other world beats.</font></span><span>&nbsp;<br />\r\n</span><span><br />\r\nThe central force of Human Vibe is singer-songwriter Nicko, whose guitar sounds and warm moving voice are delightful for the ears and uplifting for the soul.<span>&nbsp; </span>His career started years ago when he worked solo writing and composing for his first projects, Tempramentum, Aphobia.<span>&nbsp; </span>Inspired by his expanding creativity, Nicko set aside his other musical projects to follow his intuition and concentrate exclusively on his personal material, thereby giving birth to Human Vibe.<br />\r\n</span><span><br />\r\nEmerging for Montreal, Human Vibe is planning to expand worldwide.</span> \r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; text-align: justify\" class=\"MsoNormal\">\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n</span>\r\n',1,'<p>\r\n&quot;Nicko&quot; Nicolas Guibord - Lead singer, guitars, percs<br />\r\n&quot;Catl&quot; Luc Catellier - Drums, back vocals, percs<br />\r\n&quot;Lady*K&quot; - Bass, back vocals, percs \r\n</p>\r\n',0,''),(680,777,'a mad game',1,69,'my space.com/amadgame','','3332919118','\r\n<table id=\"HB_Mail_Container\" unselectable=\"on\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" height=\"100%\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr width=\"100%\" unselectable=\"on\" height=\"100%\">\r\n<td id=\"HB_Focus_Element\" unselectable=\"off\" background=\"\" height=\"250\" valign=\"top\" width=\"100%\">\r\nwe\'re a band living for the music that\'s all<br/>listen and hit me back!</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr unselectable=\"on\" tag=\"1\">\r\n<td style=\"font-size: 1pt;\" unselectable=\"on\" height=\"1\">\r\n<div id=\"hotbar_promo\"></div><br/></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=168\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with a mad game\'s fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(705,818,'City redefined',1,68,'www.myspace.com/cityredefined','18500 S. Dalton Ave','845-926-6738','Half of the band&nbsp;comes&nbsp;from Gardena, CA... while the better half hails from NY. Theresa may look like a girl...but if you cut her, motor oil comes out because she is <em><u>just a machine</u></em>. We\'ve been a group for 5 months now and are signed to&nbsp;<span id=\"_de_spell_word_1\" style=\"background-color: yellow;\">Oravan</span> Records. <strong>Check out our tunes and see ya at our next show near you!!</strong>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=169\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with City redefined\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(706,820,'Faded at Four',1,14,'http://www.fadedatfour.com','','707-272-6514','<p>\r\n<font face=\"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=\"3\">From the hills of Lake County in Northern California comes a thunderous rock sound that can only be.. <font size=\"4\" color=\"#ff0000\">Faded At Four.<br />\r\n</font></font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=\"3\"><br />\r\nFaded At Four presents our listeners with <strong>strong beats, powerful lyrics and intense songs</strong> straight from the souls of this 5-member crew. Through our music, we seek to share not only our music, but also our lives. We believe that music is more than a mix of sounds, it is a compilation of life experiences and emotions that we have been given the gift and ability to share with our fans. Each member of our band brings their own talents and views and it is a mix of all of these that makes Faded At Four the powerhouse rock band that we are. Individually we are musicians, together we are a band with purpose. </font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" size=\"3\"><br />\r\nWith every performance, we seek to have our listeners not only hear our song but take away a sense of who we are and what we stand for. We vow to put all of us into each and every note and provide those who truly listen with a sense of who we are as a band and as well as individuals. In return, we ask only that audiences listen and understand that we are not an ordinary rock band. <strong><font size=\"4\">We are a culture, a way of life.. we are Faded At Four!</font></strong></font>\r\n</p>\r\n',1,'<font face=\"impact,chicago\">Jon Foutch&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Vocals<br />\r\nBrian Kenner&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Guitar<br />\r\nChris Murphy&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Guitar<br />\r\nMartin Scheel&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bass<br />\r\nChris Sanders&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Drums</font>\r\n',0,''),(2545,1000571,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(713,829,'habit forming',9,41,'http://Reverbnation.com/garywilliams','5119 Lance Loop','361-524-5122','My music is one of the most trying but the rewards are priceless the feeling of accomplishment knowing that youv,ed touched someone life in someway is my gift to you my fans and thank you up front we are in this together. \r\n',0,'',0,''),(716,833,'After Never',1,71,'www.myspace.com/afternever','','1-815-685-8895','\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\nAfter Never was formed by five people who were tired of playing cookie cutter music. All of the members have the goal of not being shy to explore any musical possibility. They display this with their use of a vintage Rhodes, tambourines, and distinct progressions on their latest EP. They have a &#8220;Hey, let&#8217;s try this&#8230;&#8221; mindset, and are not content until each part has its own defining signature.<br/><br/>The band headed into Chicago\'s Gallery of Carpet studios with engineer/producer Brian Zieske (The Hush Sound, The Academy Is..., The Audition). They set out to create a record where each song had an individuality and distinct groove, yet still contributed to the overall feel. With both verses and choruses containing strong melody, their sound is captivating. The Hopeless Romantic EP was completed in early January 2007. After Never is using this to make their stamp in the swelling Chicago music scene.<br/><br/>After Never was founded in 2006 by Artie Woods (drums), Michael Murphy (bass), and Dennis Mitchell (guitar). The three friends wanted to accomplish their collective dream, to make music their life. The trio set out in search of a voice, B.J. Radigan was happy to fill that role with his unique, smooth style. Adam Cieslak (Mitchell\'s childhood friend and former band mate) then joined (guitar) to add further dynamic to the group.<br/><br/>The band has quickly landed shows with nationwide major label acts such as Kill Hannah (Atlantic) and the Pink Spiders (Geffen) and indie acts like Valencia (I Surrender Records) and Four Letter Lie (Victory). Armed with a rapidly growing fan base and catchy songs, After Never displays no signs of stopping soon. They have gained sponsorships from Random Clothing and C&C Drum Company. The members of After Never are on a mission to make their music heard, if you haven&#8217;t yet, they will make sure it&#8217;s only a matter of time. </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=172\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with After Never\'s fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(717,834,'Everyone Must Win',1,66,'www.myspace.com/everyonemustwin','','','Everyone Must Win is the 11th commandment. Yes, check it out, it&#8217;s in the bible, sandwiched between all that stuff about the world beginning and us all going straight to hell. <br/><br/>We could be cool and tell you that our influences are The Doors, The Velvet Underground, Frank Zappa and The MC5, but they are not, so we won\'t. We want a life that&#8217;s not automatic. <br/><br/>You are unlikely to find Everyone Must win in skinny jeans. We have nothing against fashion; we just like to be able to use the pockets on our trousers. And you wouldn&#8217;t know it, but we cut our hair long. <br/><br/>We will, at some stage, do something that you may regard as \'selling-out\'. Let&#8217;s just say that the day we sign a record deal will be the day we \'sell\' our music. Just pointing this out now so you don\'t feel like we are stabbing you in the back somewhere down the line when you hear our music played in the cafe on Eastenders. <br/><br/>We will beat you at Pro-Evo. <br/><br/>Guitar music isn\'t new, so sorry if you think that you have heard this one before. Everyone must win are just so over-rated, and everything you have heard is probably true. We have seen St. Marys Street on a Saturday night, and we do not condone that sort of thing. It doesn&#8217;t matter if it&#8217;s out of tune, cos you&#8217;re cool. DiG! Will Smith is king. Haribo rule. Bananas are not a fruit. You shouldn\'t talk to strangers. Make trade fair. Hope Is Important. Everyone Must Win.........<br/><br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=173\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\">Interact with Everyone Must Win\'s fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(718,836,'ClusterheaD',7,33,'www.clusterhead.com','Zum Fuchsenbuegl 6','','<font face=\"Times New Roman\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">\r\n<p>In 2005 ClusterheaD was born and combine musical influences of the modern music scene and last decades in Rock and Heavy Metal. With Leadsinger Rene, guitarist Frank Stadlbauer, bassist Andreas Meyer and Ruediger Tonn on the drums, finds ClusterheaD at least the optimal cast, their creativity and enthusiasm no more borders are set. The Heavy - Sound only created exclusively by itself, and is recorded, produced and mastert in our own studios. The new 5 track EP, HOLE IN MY HEART was finished in April 2007, the material is presented this year at a lot of festivals live. And, by the way, we work on new ideas.</p>\r\n<p>Hope you enjoy the music, on all metalbrothers have a great time!!!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>ClusterheaD</p></span>\r\n<p>Discography:</p>\r\n<p>THE FIRST ATTEMPT 2005</p>\r\n<p>REFLECTION 2006</p>\r\n<p>HOLE IN MY HEART 2007</p></font>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=174\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with ClusterheaD\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(719,839,'Amberdeen',1,66,'www.myspace.com/amberdeenrock','','','<strong><font color=\"#0030cc\" size=\"4\">Looking for where to buy our EP \"Not Forgotten Freedom\"? You can pick up a copy from Repressed Records, Penrith or Resist Records, Newtown! OR ONLINE!<br/><br/><br/></font></strong>\r\n<center><br/><font size=\"2\">AMBERDEEN IS: <br/><br/><b><font size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/brendofaf\"><font color=\"#003399\">Brendan Vocals/Guitar</font></a> <b><font size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/scottah\"><font color=\"#003399\"><br/><br/>Scott Guitar/Vocals</font></a> <b><font size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/twentyteen\"><font color=\"#003399\"><br/><br/>Leigh Drums</font></a> <br/><b><font size=\"2\"><br/><a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/ryanfaf\"><font color=\"#003399\">Ryan Bass/Vocals</font></a> <br/><br/><font style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" size=\"1\"><br/>Amberdeen are an independent, four piece, acoustic/indie/punk band out of Sydney, NSW. Amberdeen mix and experiment with both indie and punk genres. With comparisons to Anti-Flag, Hot Hot Heat and Kisschasy (killyourstereo.com), Amberdeen are different to anything else you&#8217;ve heard. By using both electric and acoustic guitars they have captured a sound that is truly unique. <br/><br/>Amberdeen began carving out a presence in the Sydney scene in 2006. Throughout the year Amberdeen played HOME Nightclub, The Lansdowne, The Attic, The Embassy Hotel plus youth festivals Enliven and Ignite. They supported Behind Crimson Eyes on their Shakedown Tour in October and also graced the stage with the likes of The Valley, Another Day Down, The Veld and Fingerprint Resistant. <br/><br/>In October Amberdeen independently recorded and distributed their debut EP titled &#8220;Not Forgotten Freedom&#8221;. The first track &#8220;Stay Where You Are&#8221; was instantly added to rotation of FBi 94.5 and graced the airwaves of Triple J, SWR, B Rock (Bathurst) and other community stations. The indie rock track was so infectious that it was chosen out of thousands by Sony reps as one of ten Sony BMG &#8216;Hottest Picks&#8217; in the currently running &#8216;Uncharted&#8217; Competition. <br/><br/>Amberdeen kicked off 2007, by going to Orange to play the Get Punked Festival. The reception of the all ages crowd was so fantastic that they returned in March for another all ages show. In between however they found the time to support Something With Numbers at the Embassy Hotel and begin work on a new release for late 2007. So consequently the story continues&#8230; <br/><br/>Some things that have been said about Amberdeen and their debut EP&#8230; <br/><br/>&#8220;Amberdeen have created a unique sound, which slowly grows on you. Dying Breed, is by far the best track on the EP; it is the epitome of Indie-Punk, with a great riff, dance-inducing verses and a punchy chorus. Track Three, For Tonight, follows \'Dying Breed\' like a one-two punch&#8221; &#8211; KILL YOUR STEREO.COM <br/><br/>&#8220;Their EP Not Forgotten Freedom is one worth picking up.&#8221; &#8211; FASTERLOUDER.COM <br/><br/>&#8220;Amberdeen are Sydney&#8217;s alternative punk kids&#8221; &#8211; THE BRAG <br/><br/>Contact: <br/>Nadia at Dying Breed Management - nadia(at)dyingbreedmanagement(dot)com <br/><br/>\r\n<center><br/></center></font></font></b></font></b></font></b></font></b></font></center>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=175\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Amberdeen\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(720,840,'*67',1,68,'myspace.com/67yourmom','4218 Sunshine Ave.','317-828-5335','\r\n<div>*67 has been together since the beginning of November 2006. We are a 3 piece,&nbsp;Pop-Punk&nbsp;band from <span id=\"lw_1189622285_1\" style=\"CURSOR: hand; BORDER-BOTTOM: #0066cc 1px dashed; HEIGHT: 1em\">Indianapolis, Indiana</span>. AJ Adams&nbsp;is the lead guitarist and lead&nbsp;vocalist, with Nick Harvey on the drums, and&nbsp;Alex&nbsp;Ford&nbsp;on the bass guitar and backing vocals.&nbsp;Each member has about 4 years of music experience. </div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>In out time together we\'ve put out a 10 track demo which has all original songs. Played at many local <span id=\"lw_1189622285_2\" style=\"CURSOR: hand; BORDER-BOTTOM: #0066cc 1px dashed; HEIGHT: 1em\">Indianapolis</span> venues such as The Emerson Theater, The Attic, Club Logos, Rhino\'s All Ages Music, and the Irving Theater. Not to mention many basement and private party shows.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We are a band that is influenced by many bands like <span id=\"lw_1189622285_3\" style=\"BACKGROUND: none transparent scroll repeat 0% 0%; CURSOR: hand; BORDER-BOTTOM: #0066cc 1px dashed; HEIGHT: 1em\">Green Day</span>, Blink 182, Rancid, NOFX, Mest, and etc. Most say that we resemble a style that of Blink 182 and New Found Glory.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>*67 is one band that when seen live will keep your sweat dropping and your adrenaline pumping, with colorful lyrics, awesome beats, and catchy tunes, we\'re a band that keeps people coming back for more.</div>\r\n<div><br/><br/>AJ\'s Bio - <strong>i\'m the Guitarist/singer for the band. <br/>I was taught guitar by my best friend Romes of the band diStiLL! He tought me everything I know about playing and singing. My favorite bands/influences would be Green Day mainly and of course diStiLL. I also like Blink 182, New Found Glory, Hoobastank, and a few others like that.<br/><br/><br/>Nick\'s Bio - What up, I\'m the drummer for the band. I\'ve been playing drums since I was about 12, but I didn\'t get serious bout it till I was 14 years old. I love all kinds of music. My favorite band is Rancid. Pennywise and Nofx are great bands too. I like going to car shows, skateboarding, and hangin out with friends.<br/><br/><br/>Alex\'s Bio - Hey kids it\'s Alex, I play bass for *67 and&nbsp; I\'m the one who really puts a good twist in our&nbsp;music with all the good stuff a bassist can do....anyways I have been playn in the band and have been havin\' a great time with these guys (literally lol jk) \'cause they both know how great music should sound. So if you come watch me make an ass of myself on stage....you\'re going to have to come out to one of our shows so yeah later kids!</strong> <br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=176\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\">Interact with *67\'s fans</span></a><br/></div>',1,'',0,''),(725,844,'BAKUKU',4,22,'www.myspace.com/bigghenny','','','<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">BAKUKU...rapper, family man, producer, hustler...working for his\r\nmoney...never bull-shittin\'...strong ass muther-fucka\' who does not\r\ntake shit from ANYBODY...not even his momma\'...\r\nHe\'s been rappin\' since he was 16 and living in the heart of South\r\nCentral...he started out with his brother...then met up with a few\r\nhomies and went on to start the group, Big Onez...they made an album\r\ntogether called \"TESTOSTERONE\" (check it out on &lt;a\r\nhref=\"www.cdbaby.com\"&gt;CDBABY.COM&lt;/a&gt;)...they\'ve since branched\r\nout to do solo projects...BAKUKU has an album coming out in late \'08\r\ncalled W.A.R...be sure to peep it out and give some honest feedback...\r\nNow a family man, he hasn\'t stopped his rap hustle...he hasn\'t given up\r\nhis dreams...and he sure ain\'t gonna stay out ya\'ll ear...<img title=\"\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/uploads/844/Copy%20of%20Picture%20043.jpg\" align=\"bottom\" border=\"0\" height=\"120\" width=\"160\"/><img title=\"\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/uploads/844/Picture%20106.jpg\" align=\"bottom\" border=\"0\" height=\"360\" hspace=\"0\" vspace=\"0\" width=\"480\"/><img title=\"\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/uploads/844/Copy%20of%20Picture%20050.jpg\" align=\"bottom\" border=\"0\" height=\"640\" width=\"640\"/><img title=\"\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/uploads/844/Copy%20of%20Picture%20051.jpg\" align=\"bottom\" border=\"0\" height=\"159\" width=\"112\"/><img title=\"\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/uploads/844/Picture%20735.jpg\" align=\"bottom\" border=\"0\" height=\"120\" width=\"160\"/><img title=\"\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/uploads/844/Picture%20737.jpg\" align=\"bottom\" border=\"0\" height=\"120\" width=\"160\"/></span>\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=177\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with BAKUKU\'s fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(731,860,'SESSION 9',1,14,'http://www.session9band.com','4002 madison pike','513-615-4194','<p>\r\nSession 9 was formed in the spring of 2005 in cincinnati, oh.With charisma and the integrity of their lyrical and musical content, session 9 purges the boundaries of rock. Down low riffs, almost punk aggression and the power of ballads doesn&#39;t always fit together naturally. This group of five musicians have pulled them together to contradict and cast away any stereotype that a band can only belong to one specific genre of music. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nCountless shows and self-inspired writing have harnessed a loyal and growing fan base. with their debut album&nbsp; &quot;volume&quot; just ready for release, that fan base will only continue to grow. the blend of opposite boundaries, volume encapsulates the attention of all who listens to it by provoking inner thoughts and self reflection.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSession 9 is truly a band of brothers bound together by a commom goal, making music that is emotional and meaningful enough to invigorate everyone across the board. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nSession 9 starts with matt beach pounding the heart pulse of the music on the drums, scott evans delivering the boom on bass, ryan todd selling his soul on vocals, larry harris hammering the axe into oblivion on lead guitar, and jason webb smashing the strings on rhythm guitar.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nJust like any other formulas, the end result for completing a successful equation is on proud display at every show Session 9 plays.A die hard fan base full of fantstic supporters that only continues to grow.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=210\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt\">Interact with session 9&#39;s fans</span></a> \r\n</p>\r\n',1,'RYAN ROSENBERGER /&nbsp; LEAD VOCALS<br />\r\nLARRY HARRIS / LEAD GUITAR, VOCALS <br />\r\nJASON WEBB / GUITAR ,VOCALS<br />\r\nSCOTT EVANS / BASS <br />\r\nMATT BEACH/ DRUMS \r\n',0,''),(743,875,'Freedom and Whiskey',1,16,'myspace.com/freedomandwhiskey','3309 Acorn Lane','(502)-376-9140','<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\" align=\"center\">Freedom and Whiskey </h1>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype\r\n id=\"_x0000_t75\" coordsize=\"21600,21600\" o:spt=\"75\" o:preferrelative=\"t\"\r\n path=\"m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe\" filled=\"f\" stroked=\"f\">\r\n <v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"/>\r\n <v:formulas>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 1 0\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum 0 0 @1\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @2 1 2\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @3 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @0 0 1\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @6 1 2\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelWidth\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @8 21600 0\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"prod @7 21600 pixelHeight\"/>\r\n  <v:f eqn=\"sum @10 21600 0\"/>\r\n </v:formulas>\r\n <v:path o:extrusionok=\"f\" gradientshapeok=\"t\" o:connecttype=\"rect\"/>\r\n <o:lock v:ext=\"edit\" aspectratio=\"t\"/>\r\n</v:shapetype><v:shape id=\"_x0000_i1025\" type=\"#_x0000_t75\" style=\'width:150pt;\r\n height:75pt\'>\r\n <v:imagedata                        src=\"file:///C:/WINDOWS/TEMP/msoclip1/01/clip_image001.jpg\"\r\n  o:title=\"Embosed Eagle\"/>\r\n</v:shape><![endif]--><!--[if !vml]--><img  src=\"file:///C:/WINDOWS/TEMP/msoclip1/01/clip_image002.jpg\" v:shapes=\"_x0000_i1025\" height=\"100\" width=\"200\"/><!--[endif]--></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Location<o:p></o:p></span></h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial; color: black;\">Freedom and\r\nWhiskey is from the Louisville, Kentucky / Jeffersonville, Indiana area in the\r\nheart of the Ohio Valley. The style of music is a mix of classic / modern /\r\nsouthern rock and blues. </span><span style=\"color: black;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Musical Influences\r\n<o:p></o:p></span></h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText\">Led Zeppelin, Pink Floyd, AC/DC, Steely Dan, Sound Garden,\r\nFleetwood Mac, Robin Trower, Muddy Waters, Walter Horton and many more.<b><o:p></o:p></b></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Members<o:p></o:p></span></h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText\" style=\"text-indent: 0.5in;\">The group consists of:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText\" style=\"margin-left: 0.5in;\"><br/>\r\n<b><u>Mark Hoekstra</u></b> <b>&#8211; Vocals and Harmonica</b>; formerly with &#8220;Legendary\r\nBlues Band&#8221;, &#8220;Homesick James&#8221;, and &#8220;West side Heat&#8221;.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText\" style=\"margin-left: 0.5in;\"><b><u>Chuck Mingis</u></b> <b>&#8211;\r\nLead Guitar</b>; formerly with &#8220; Days of the New&#8221;, &#8220;Spanky Lee&#8221;, and &#8220;Eden\r\nStreet&#8221;.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText\" style=\"text-indent: 0.5in;\"><b><u>Mike Huettig</u></b> &#8211; <b>Drums\r\nand Vocals</b>; former <br/>\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; bassist with &#8220;Days of the New&#8221;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText\" style=\"text-indent: 0.5in;\"><b><u>Bill Goins</u></b> &#8211; <b>Bass\r\nGuitar and Vocals</b>; <br/>\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; formerly with &#8220;Rude Awakening&#8221;.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText\" style=\"text-indent: 0.5in;\"><!--[if !supportEmptyParas]-->&nbsp;<!--[endif]--><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText\">Bill and Mike wrote, produced, recorded and composed most\r\nof Freedom and Whiskey\'s material on their first two albums. Currently the band\r\nis working on their third album with all four members taking equal share writing\r\nthe material.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText\">Freedom and Whiskey is currently playing in the Louisville\r\narea.<br/>\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText\">Freeom and Whiseky CDs are available from CD Baby at: http://cdbaby.com/all/montero<br/>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h1><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Contact Freedom\r\nand Whiskey at:<o:p></o:p></span></h1>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText\" style=\"text-indent: 0.5in;\"><b>Web site</b> - <span style=\"font-size: 14pt; color: windowtext;\"><a href=\"http://myspace.com/FreedomAndWhiskey\"><span style=\"color: windowtext; text-decoration: none;\">http://Myspace.com/FreedomAndWhiskey</span></a></span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText\" style=\"text-indent: 0.5in;\"><b>Email</b> &#8211;\r\nwlgoins@insightbb.com<span style=\"color: windowtext;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=178\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Freedom and Whiskey\'s fans</span></a>',1,'',0,''),(745,877,'(funk-sion)',1,71,'myspace.com/funksionsound','2825 Forehand Dr','757-651-6877','\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">(funk&#8226;sion)&nbsp;is the definition of concentrated energy.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp; </span>A four piece modern rock band out of <?xml:namespace prefix = st1 /><ST1:PLACE><ST1:CITY>Virginia Beach</ST1:CITY>, <ST1:STATE>VA</ST1:STATE></ST1:PLACE>, this explosive group of men will send any audience home happy.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp; </span>For the last three years,&nbsp;(funk&#8226;sion) has unmercifully set the standard for the local talent in Hampton Roads, playing venues from the Hampton Roads area, <ST1:CITY><ST1:PLACE>Richmond</ST1:PLACE></ST1:CITY> to&nbsp;the<ST1:STATE><ST1:PLACE> Carolinas</ST1:PLACE></ST1:STATE>, <ST1:STATE><ST1:PLACE>Maryland</ST1:PLACE></ST1:STATE> and <ST1:STATE><ST1:PLACE>Delaware</ST1:PLACE></ST1:STATE>.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp; </span>They have quickly distinguished themselves in this competitive market with their brilliant songwriting abilities and superb musicianship.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><?xml:namespace prefix = o /><O:P>&nbsp;</O:P></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Lyrically,&nbsp;(funk&#8226;sion) stands out among the rest of the local rock bands with their vocalists aggressive attack on subject matters.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp; </span>Their songs capture audiences with melodic vocal hooks, aggressive guitar work and hypnotizing rhythmic harmony.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp; </span>Its easy to see the immense talent of each member and what they bring to the table.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp; </span>Among the four members, they have an incredibly diverse musical background and aren&#8217;t afraid to throw something out there and see how it is received.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp; </span>With their creative original songs,&nbsp;(funk&#8226;sion) captures the audience&#8217;s attention from the first line and doesn&#8217;t give it back until closing time!</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><O:P>&nbsp;</O:P></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>The distinct and dynamic stage presence of&nbsp;(funk&#8226;sion) can rival any band.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp; </span>For a live performance they leave nothing to be desired-this band has fun on stage and their energy is infectious.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> The band&nbsp;has been invited to showcase at spots outside of their area including venues in <ST1:STATE><ST1:PLACE>North Carolina</ST1:PLACE></ST1:STATE>, <ST1:STATE><ST1:PLACE>Delaware</ST1:PLACE></ST1:STATE>, <ST1:STATE><ST1:PLACE>Maryland</ST1:PLACE></ST1:STATE>,<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp; </span>and<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp; </span><ST1:PLACE>S. Carolina</ST1:PLACE>.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp; </span>After months of airplay on <ST1:PLACE><ST1:CITY>Ocean City</ST1:CITY>, <ST1:STATE>MD</ST1:STATE></ST1:PLACE> radio station X106.9 and&nbsp;Norfolk\'s FM99, the guys were invited to play several live&nbsp;radio shows&nbsp;on those stations.&nbsp; (funk&#8226;sion)&nbsp;is a band ready to change the face of rock, continually making their name among venues and attracting new fans.</p><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=179\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\">Interact with funk-sion\'s fans</span></a>',1,'',0,''),(757,891,'Facing Winter',1,69,'facingwinter.com','','630-212-4595','&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Facing Winter is an acoustic-rock trio from West Chicago, Illinois. The group\'s passionate sound is crafted by three long-time friends whose thoughtful songs appeal to many audiences.<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The band sounds like a blend of Elliott Smith, Radiohead, and Sunny Day Real Estate. Facing Winter\'s music combines inviting vocals and crisp guitars with an earthy rhythm section for a textured, yet simple sound.<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The trio\'s frontman is Justin Birchard, whose melodic voice and guitar are complimented by bassist Liam Doyle and drummer Jeff Goluszka. They\'ve been together since late 2003.<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Facing Winter is currently performing in the Midwest U.S., and has played at Illinois venues such as the Elbo Rom, Beat Kitchen, Pint, Pontiac Cafe, Gunther Murphy\'s, Fireside Bowl, Wheaton Grand Theater, and Phyllis\' Musical Inn.<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;For more about the band, visit facingwinter.com or myspace.com/facingwinter.<br/>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=180\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Facing Winter\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(763,896,'Falling Closer',1,14,'www.fallingcloser.net','','','<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=181\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Falling Closer\'s fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(771,923,'Closer To The Real',1,71,'www.myspace.com/closertothereal','','','<span style=\"font-family: Georgia; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 153); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline; font-style: italic;\">BAND BIO:</span><br/><br/></span><div style=\"margin-left: 40px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Georgia; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 153);\">* Former members of Pain Factor Randy and Hank and members of Mad at Sam and Heathen, Larry and Dave have joined together to create &#8220;Closer to the Real&#8221;. </span><br/><span style=\"font-family: Georgia; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 153);\"></span><br/><span style=\"font-family: Georgia; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 153);\">A crushing new attack of sound, out of Oakland CA. hitting the Bay Area scene. </span><br/><span style=\"font-family: Georgia; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 153);\"></span><br/><span style=\"font-family: Georgia; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 153);\">* Sounds Like: Aggressive Alternative Hard Rock. </span><br/><span style=\"font-family: Georgia; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 153);\"></span><br/><span style=\"font-family: Georgia; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 153);\">* Record Label: Unsigned </span><br/><span style=\"font-family: Georgia; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 153);\"></span></div><span style=\"font-family: Georgia; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 153); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br/><br/><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;\">BAND MEMBERS:</span><br/><br/></span><div style=\"margin-left: 40px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Georgia; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 153);\">* <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Randy Markham</span> - Lead Vocals, Guitar </span><br/><span style=\"font-family: Georgia; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 153);\"></span><span style=\"font-family: Georgia; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 153);\">* <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Larry Hatchett</span> - Lead Vocals, Guitar </span><br/><span style=\"font-family: Georgia; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 153);\"></span><span style=\"font-family: Georgia; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 153);\">* <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Hank Alva </span>- Bass, Vocals </span><br/><span style=\"font-family: Georgia; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 153);\"></span><span style=\"font-family: Georgia; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 153);\">* <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Dave White</span> - Drums, Vocals </span><br/><span style=\"font-family: Georgia; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 153);\"></span></div><span style=\"font-family: Georgia; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 153);\"><br/><br/></span><hr style=\"width: 100%; height: 2px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Georgia; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 153); background-color: rgb(204, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"></span></span><div style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-align: justify;\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: Georgia; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 153);\"><img title=\"\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/uploads/923/Earbuzz.jpg\" align=\"bottom\" border=\"0\" height=\"144\" width=\"288\"/></span><br/></div><span style=\"font-family: Georgia; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 153);\"></span></div><ul style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-align: justify;\"><li><span style=\"font-family: Georgia; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 153);\">Our first CD Review at <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; font-style: italic;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 255);\">www.earbuzz.com</span></span> which is selling our music. </span></li></ul><ul style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-align: justify;\"><li><span style=\"font-family: Georgia; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 153);\">Go there and buy our stuff over the net at: <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; font-style: italic; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);\">http://www.earbuzz.com/closertothereal</span></span></li></ul><div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: Georgia; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 153); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">A metallic bronze bass string pumps the first few moments of \"Closer to the Real\"\'s self titled 6-track record in \"She\'s a Little Different\" and we were sucked in. Guitars are upfront and full of presence and chugging beauty - played in unison and panned left and right. Dissonant chord progressions half step their way to a blend between dark metal, punk, and Scorps-ish Zoo movements in the opening track, \"Shes a Little Different\". The entire recording, done in Apple\'s GarageBand program, is a testament to the tools of the day and the end result is an album that has the passion of metal with the alternative attitude of Nirvana. Vocals are hypnotically mixed back a bit - and the equalization is absent of high end which adds a darkness to the music. Track 3, \"Cousin Jed\", starts out with a distorted harmonica, and moves into the strongest rock groover on the record. The story goes \'let me tell you \'bout my cousin Jed, at a young age he was dropped on his head, it\'s all good when the family gets together. .Jed loves his truck. .he\'s the Marlboro Man, with a big brim cap and his Coors in his hand, that\'s my cousin Jed\'. Closer to the Real blends a hiphop delivery with pure metal that is a refreshing blend that takes us back to the walk this way days. Nice. In track 4, \"Snap Shots\", the band moves as one in musical passages that are tight and inventive. The tune pays respect to the snap shots we take in our heads won\'t forget. The final track, \"Let it End\", opens with a cymbal, that metallic bronze bass line perfection, and moaning meandering swelling guitars. The substantial metal groove of the guitars is compelling as the left/right tightness of their recording occasionally departs independently of the other into harmonies and spaces. The tune is about the end of a dead relationship - but we were hardly requesting the same of the sixth track on the CD as it is one of the more haunting and interesting tracks on the record. We look forward to more. </span><br/></div>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=182\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Closer To The Real\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(774,926,'A Dance With Jack Ketch',1,73,'www.myspace.com/dancewithjack','','','Started in the Fall of 2006 in Troy, Ohio, A Dance with Jack Ketch is comprised of five amazing musicians. Despite its short life span, Jack Ketch doesn\'t fail to impress. With two members of 8 Steps 2 Glory joining up with a few others, A Dance with Jack Ketch was created as a new outlet for stellar rock music. The band faces a promising future career and looks forward to your support. <br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=183\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\">Interact with A Dance With Jack Ketch\'s fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(2406,1000145,'Sun Dagger',1,16,'http://myspace.com/sundaggermusic','P.O. Box 646 Hixson,TN','423-320-5827','Sun Dagger was formed in the summer of 2007, when Dave Cheek (guitarist) met Doug Winesburgh (drums).Dave having recently moved from Tuscaloosa, Alabama was a former member of local favorite &ldquo;Chinese Dentist&rdquo;. Dave had recently married and relocated to Chattanooga, TN. Having hit it off, the two enlisted the help of Doug&rsquo;s former &ldquo;Quasimojo&rdquo; band mate Scott Stewart (guitarist) and old &ldquo;open mike night&rdquo; pal Jason Branum (bass) formerly of &ldquo;Soul Crush&rdquo;. After 3 months of rehearsals the band tentatively titled &ldquo;The Last Minute&rdquo; was declared &ldquo;Sun Dagger&rdquo;. Now the rest is left to history. \r\n',1,'Dave Cheek: (guitar) Scott Stewart :(guitar/vocals) Jason Branum : (bass/vocals) Doug Winesburgh :(drums/vocals) \r\n',0,''),(2407,1000146,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2408,1000148,'SLAY BOOGIE',3,86,'http://WWW.MYSPACE.COM/SLAYBOOGIEALBUM','715 m.h.p lot 214 belle glade fl.33430','561-692-2097','From da bottom so ain&#39;t no where to go but up.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOut of a familt of talented musicians emerges Jermaine D. lovely also known as Slay Boogie. born on June 29, 1981 in South Bay fl.<br />\r\nJermaine is very familiar with the miami bass sound that put florida on the music industry map. Now, in 2008 and beyond, Slay Boogie plans to shake the stereotype associated with florida&#39;s hip-hop scene and display this skills as a flo(w) rida(h). He welcomes u along for the rhythmic ride!<br />\r\n<br />\r\nJermaine attended the footballmecca Glades Central High School in Belle Glade fl. After finishing high school Jermaine went off to college in Daytona Beach fl. where he became a Bethune-Cookman Wildcat.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn the year 2004 Slay Boogie stepped his game up and join a group by the name of konfuzion the group had only 4 members then drop to 2 members. Slay boogie&nbsp; &amp; O-low Da Dizasta. The kausin konfuzion album is still on sale on cdbaby.com/konfuzion if u lookin to get a copy. In 2005 Slay stepped up another level by touchin everyproject in the area he needed to0. Now hs he is a house whole name. Slya boogie has worked with alot of underground artists that or on fire now in florida.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSuch as Papa Duck from florida-hit singles ( Fuck Boi &amp; Good Pussy) , B.S.G album called (outh.eer!) the hit singles ( Tryin To Fuck Sumthing &amp; What U Lookin At),Killa Kim ( Know What I&#39;m Talkin Bout feat. Dirty Redd out of DADE. Rarebreed,Haitian Fresh,O-low Da Dizasta and more...<br />\r\n<br />\r\nso if u lookin forward to workin with Slay Boogie and get these Monster Tracks&nbsp; holla&nbsp; 561-692-2097 ask for the man himself...........\r\n',0,'',0,''),(785,936,'Garrison Green',1,61,'www.myspace.com/garrisongreen','','07843244522','<span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: arial\"></span><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Arial\">Garrison Green are no more....... :-( Instead, head over to <a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/Intervention\">www.bestofbands.com/Intervention</a> :-)<br/><br/></span><br/>&nbsp;',1,'',0,''),(794,946,'Vintage',7,33,'www.vintageband.us','7665 Sally Dr','616-813-0669','Vintage is a 5 piece band, best described as Rap Metal.<br/>Quick comparison would be: a less-political Rage Against the Machine, or Linkin Park with guitar solos.<br/>Vintage is the creation of Steve Shelley(Lead/Rhythm guitar), R.O.B. (Lead/Rhythm gutiar), Aaron Veen (Bassist), Steven Striegle (Drummer), & John Lee (Rock Vocalist/Hip Hop Lyricist).<br/><br/>Vintage has been together since Spring of 2004 and have performed at a variety of venues.<br/>Since forming Vintage has opened for Regional & National acts, at multiple concert venues.<br/>ie. 08/14/2006 Opened for Afro Man at The Groundsphere in Allegan, MI. 08/10/2006 Opened for Coin at Ten Bells in Grand Rapids, MI.<br/>They have Headlined at Bars that feature live music as well as All-ages venues. ie. BC Sound Venue in Battle Creek, MI. Teazer\'s in Grand Rapids, MI.<br/>Showcased at music Festivals. ie. 06/04/2006 Festival of the Arts in Grand Rapids, MI. 07/04/2006 Dorr, MI 4th of July Celebration. <br/><br/>Vintage has recorded and released a 6 track Demo \"America Incorporated\".<br/>Vintage has also released a 17 track Full Length album, entitled \"Efxor\".<br/>Efxor (a 2 disc set) comes with a DVD featuring the \"Empathy\" Music Video, a Band Interview, Their Live Performance at Ten Bells, & Photo Gallery.<br/><br/>Vintage is currently working on reaching Venues outside of the West Michigan Area and plan to begin touring Regionally in the coming year. <br/><br/>Live performances by Vintage are captivating, energetic, and interactive.<br/>The crowd is invited to participate, sing along, and have a good time.<br/>The show is naturally fun and the aptmosphere is similar to hanging out with friends at a house party.<br/>A Vintage show may, on occasion, contain multiple cover songs as well as orginals spanning the band members\' multiple influences.<br/>They span from Eminem & Metallica, to Tom Petty & Drowning Pool. While the covers are well executed the originals are generally the fan favorites.\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=185\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Vintage\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(799,956,'A1 Sound Effects',67,0,'www.myspace.com/a1freesoundeffects','','','Sound Effect Recordings ',1,'',0,''),(1163,1444,'Gayle Force Wind',1,69,'www.gayleforcewind.com','2030 Blue Ave.','740-454-1316','<br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=291\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\"></span></a>Our name is Gayle Force Wind and we are an unsigned 4 piece Alternative Rock band with female vocals.&nbsp; Gayle Force Wind was formed in 2004 in Zanesville Ohio and consists of the following members:<br/><br/>* Gayle Gardner ~ Vocals/Acoustic Guitar/Songwriter<br/>* Matt Hutchins ~ Lead Guitar/Mandolin/Songwriter<br/>* Joe Bowman ~ Bass<br/>* Scott Hillis ~ Drums/Percussion<br/><br/>Currently we perform live with a mixture of originals and cover songs.&nbsp; We have played at several venues around Southeastern Ohio including participation at many area festivals and benefits.<br/><br/>In the spring of 2006, we went into the studio and self recorded our CD *Storm*, released September 2006.&nbsp; The CD contains 10 original songs with our music style ranging from Alternative to Classic Acoustic Rock. <br/><br/>Gayle Force Wind has been reviewed and accepted to sell our CD on itunes.com, CDbaby.com and others.&nbsp; You can find access to these sites through the following links:<br/><br/>http://cdbaby.com/cd/gfwind<br/>http://www.itunes.com<br/>http://payplay.fm/gfwind<br/>http://www.tradebit.com/filedetail.php/1734213<br/>http://musicishere.com/artists/Gayle_Force_Wind/_Storm<br/><br/>Recently we were featured as artist of the week at The Big Break Music Podcast.com & Hollyscope.com.&nbsp; We also have been featured and playing in the regular \"on~air\" rotations of the following Internet Radio Stations:<br/><br/>GirlsRockRadio.com<br/>Live365.com<br/>TheAmericanHeartbeat.com<br/>CrossFireRadio.com<br/>Radiomaxx.net<br/>RadioXnetwork.com<br/>LivinRocksRadio.com<br/>HeadCaseRadio.com<br/>WomensRockRadio<br/>Radiofreecanton.net 90.7fm<br/><br/>We hope you enjoy listening to our CD.&nbsp; Thank you for taking the time to read our bio and we appreciate you supporting our music. <br/><br/>Gayle Force Wind<br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/>',1,'',0,''),(808,970,'Funkynash',1,76,'www.myspace.com/funkynash','','','I do not think to be able to insert myself in one style only. The base\r\nis however rock like my spirit. Currently I am working again on the\r\ntraditional rock, blues and southern after to have spaced for little time in\r\nfunky, electronics and afro music. I\'m perhaps a little unstable\r\nregarding the musical profile but I have always followed with much\r\ninterest and attention other musical genres like jazz, fusion, blues,\r\ncountry in all its shapes, from the bluegrass to the country rock,\r\ntherefore in my head they meet different kind of music, that sometimes\r\nintercrossing itself create strange alchemies. Personally I am\r\navailable to cooperate via Internet with other artists. For any contact\r\nor information you can write to me here and I\'ll be glad to reply you.\r\nHave a nice life and Rock be with you forever !!',1,'',0,''),(815,979,'The Electric Artificial',1,105,'www.myspace.com/theelectricartificial','','07855879566','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\">Formed in December-ish 2006, and comprising of Tim Burgum(Electric Guitar), Alex Rees(Vocals and Electric Bass) and Jimbob Jones(Ginger Drums), The Electric Artifical are a rock/blues/jam band with a difference! Defined by the general public as \"Thrash Blues\", and with influences as diverse as Metallica and Paolo Nutini, their eclectic combination of popular rock and blues is exciting and a surefire hit! Once described as sounding like \"A Monkey on Cocaine\", The Electric Artificial\'s brand of accesible rock pleases and delights audiences everywhere... <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\">The Electric Artificial record and master all of they&#8217;re own tracks<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\"><a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/theelectricartificial\">www.myspace.com/theelectricartificial</a><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\">Alex Rees &#8211; Vocals / Bass Guitar<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\">Tim Burgum &#8211; Electric Guitar<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\">Jimbob Jones &#8211; Drums<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\">\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\">song Bio&#8217;s<o:p></o:p></span></p><p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; color: black; font-family: Verdana;\">Plainfield</span></strong></st1:place></st1:city><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; color: black; font-family: Verdana;\">&#8217;s - </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; color: black; font-family: Verdana;\">I saw a film on TV called Ed Gein. Something possessed me to write this song about him. The chorus is inspired by Eddie Murphy\'s live show \"Delirious\". Ed Gein was a serial killer in the fifties in <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">America</st1:place></st1:country-region>. He is the inspiration for The Texas Chainsaw Massacre, Psycho, Silence of the Lambs, and a host of other gory horror films. And I wrote a happy song about him. I dont know which one of us would be seen as more disturbed. Complete plagiarization of the intro drum riff from Enter Sandman in the middle too... Tim reckons it would sound better with an extra beat. I think we\'d avoid copyright jail if it had an extra beat. Roll on re-masters.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; color: black; font-family: Verdana;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; color: black; font-family: Verdana;\">The Grip Of The Fool - </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; color: black; font-family: Verdana;\">erm... \'tis about people taking advantage of other people\'s weaknesses and personality traits.&nbsp;The rap at the end was fun to write. Especially seeing as when it came down to mastering this, we had a choice. Over the accelerando at the end, we had to choose between a man who discovers his lover is a transvestite. Or a rap. We chose the rap. God knows what the song would be like with the antics of Jolene/Adam instead of someone who stole everything from you...<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=186\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with The Electric Artificial\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1212,1502,'People on Trial',1,68,'http://www.myspace.com/peopleontrial','','630-849-4653','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: center;\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt; font-family: Jefferson;\">We the People<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16pt; font-family: Forte;\">Formed in the winter of 2006, People on Trial combine the elements of rock & roll, punk, and reggae to create a sound all their own.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>Following the lead left by their influences, (i.e. Sublime, The Clash and NOFX), People on Trial bring songs filled with tales of woe, weed smoking and drunken nights followed by forgetful mornings.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16pt; font-family: Forte;\">People on Trial is Derek Scott, lead vocals and guitar&#8230;Jason Winter, vocals and bass and James Hurley on drums.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>Since their conception in 2006 People on Trial or P.O.T. have played countless Chicago and suburb venues including The Double Door, Otto&#8217;s Nite Club, Subterrainien and The Note and also have shared the stage with national acts including Local-H, The Tossers and Lucky Boys Confusion.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16pt; font-family: Forte;\">In the spring of 2007 People on Trial began working on their first album entitled &#8220;Suppressed & Underdressed&#8221;...some tracks have already been leaked but the entire album is set for release in the fall of 2007 on People on Trial&#8217;s own record label &#8220;On Trial Records.&#8221;<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16pt; font-family: Forte;\">Already with a very large fan base in the Chicagoland area, People on Trial continue to attract attention and new fans with every show and every note&#8230;bringing an electric stage show that challenges an audience to get involved, dance and sing along.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>Crowds seem to hang on Derek&#8217;s every word while Jason is running around the venue dancing with the crowd and Jim (the human drum machine) is beating his drums like they owe him money.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16pt; font-family: Forte;\">Here to stay, People on Trial continue to play everywhere while writing new music and constantly improving their live show.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>Soon to be on tour look for them in a city near you soon or you can find them on the web @ <a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/peopleontrial\">www.myspace.com/peopleontrial</a> <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=310\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with People on Trial\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(845,1022,'Jake Daniel',8,79,'','1600 Rice Rd Apt 624','9035616084','I am first and foremost a SONGWRITER. My goal is to find a publisher who can market my songs to performing artists. Honey Wagon is my registered band name. Currently I AM the band (writer, producer, vocalist, guitars, bass, keyboards, and drums). My goal is simply to write and record enjoyable songs for a wide audience, as well as to sell those songs to viable recording artists. Music has been a part of my family and my life from my earliest years. I have over 30 songs written and recorded, in a variety of styles (country, rock, blues, alternative and instrumental). All of the songs here were recorded in my apartment \"studio\"(see my pics).&nbsp; I look forward to building my network of musicians and friends. Enjoy the tunes!\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=187\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Jake Daniel\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(849,1014,'Ten 