ve made music their entire life. Their music is a part of their souls, a part of their essence, and very much a part of their existence. These four men, who range from the ages of 21 to 25, have given everything that they are and sacrificed everything they have to create a name for themselves. Fronted by a strong and raspy voice that gives depth to their material, Faded Hope?s heavy sound and deep lyrics pulls you into a musical euphoria that touches your very soul. They have a deep connection with their fans, and each of their supporters connects with their music in a way that is profound. It?s almost as if they are giving voice to your inner thoughts and feelings, and that is something that sets them apart from all the other bands out there. Faded Hope has incredible drive that will take them to the top of the music industry. Their do or die attitude and dedication to their craft is what will take them far, and whether they conquer their small little corner of Ohio, the entire state, or the entire nation they will do so by staying true to who they are and continuing their deep connection with their fans. To Faded Hope no matter where they go, they play with pride and respect, honoring who they are and where they came from. influences- staind,nickleback,pantera,trapt,closure Places played are: Peabody&#8217;s in Cleveland. Voodoo in Akron, Chameleon club in Kent, R.E. club in Akron, Goddard&#8217;s in Millersburg, Homesville Inn in Homesville, Wooden Nickel in Apple Creek, and lots of house parties and graduation parties. All of which are in the state of Ohio. Faded Hope is currently played on local Radio Stations on weekends. 98.3, 102.3, and 107.7 (www.foxclassicrock.com) &#8220;We&#8217;ve been told our sound is very commercial and sellable.&#8221; They are currently working on their first studio album in Canton OHIO. Once again THANK YOU!!! --------',1,'',0,''),(912,1099,'Julien Laurence',10,45,'http://www.julienlaurence.net','Geneva','','<span style=\"font-size: 12pt; color: windowtext; font-family: Calibri\"><font face=\"verdana,geneva\"><font size=\"2\">Imagine.<br />\r\n</font></font></span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; color: windowtext; font-family: Calibri\"><font face=\"verdana,geneva\"><font size=\"2\">It all started with a John Lennon&#39;s song.<br />\r\n</font></font></span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; color: windowtext; font-family: Calibri\"><font face=\"verdana,geneva\"><font size=\"2\">Imagine at 4 you discover the piano, at 6 Stevie Wonder. <br />\r\n</font></font></span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; color: windowtext; font-family: Calibri\"><font face=\"verdana,geneva\"><font size=\"2\">Imagine that during 10 years you travel around the world while your passport is your guitar.<br />\r\n</font></font></span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; color: windowtext; font-family: Calibri\"><font face=\"verdana,geneva\"><font size=\"2\">Now imagine you&#39;re 30 and finalist of a broadcast TV<br />\r\n</font></font></span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; color: windowtext; font-family: Calibri\"><font face=\"verdana,geneva\"><font size=\"2\">Imagine then you refuse to deal with a major to assume your own music<br />\r\n</font></font></span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; color: windowtext; font-family: Calibri\"><font face=\"verdana,geneva\"><font size=\"2\">Imagine and you&#39;ll have an idea of whom Julien Laurence is.<br />\r\n</font></font></span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; color: windowtext; font-family: Calibri\"><font face=\"verdana,geneva\"></font></span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; color: windowtext; font-family: Calibri\"><font face=\"verdana,geneva\"><font size=\"2\"><br />\r\nSinger-songwriter he spent years travelling around the world with the sole aim of meeting people. Meeting people to meet himself:<span>&nbsp; </span>&quot;I feel rather &quot;apatride&quot; and nomad. Somebody who find himself in an eclectic definition of music. For me blues, folk or pop music does not mean much. What matters is sincerity and genuineness that comes out from creativity.&quot;<br />\r\n</font></font></span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; color: windowtext; font-family: Calibri\"><font face=\"verdana,geneva\"></font></span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; color: windowtext; font-family: Calibri\"><font face=\"verdana,geneva\"><font size=\"2\">Music is for him the most beautiful way to express feelings. A way of living. A way of breathing. So when I asked him if he had ever imagined living his life without music, the words he used were: &quot;Of course I did. Even deaf I would hear it.&quot;</font></font></span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; color: windowtext; font-family: Calibri\"><font face=\"verdana,geneva\" size=\"2\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</font></span><strong><em><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri\"><font face=\"verdana,geneva\" size=\"2\"><br />\r\nPhil Collins</font></span></em></strong><em><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri\"><font face=\"verdana,geneva\" size=\"2\">: &laquo; I am producing Julien Laurence because he is a gifted and generous young man. Someone sent me his demos and I thought he was amazing, it is as simple as that.&raquo;<br />\r\n</font><br />\r\n</span></em><br />\r\n<div>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.julienlaurence.net\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://www.julienlaurence.net/images/ban-myspace2.gif\" alt=\"Julien Laurence Website\" width=\"435\" height=\"56\" /></a> \r\n</div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/julienlaurence\" target=\"_blank\"><font face=\"verdana,geneva\">Julien Laurence&#39;s Official Myspace</font></a><br />\r\n<a href=\"http://www.julienlaurence.net/newsletter.htm\" target=\"_blank\"><font face=\"verdana,geneva\">To follow the current events, join the Newsletter</font></a> \r\n</div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/julienlaurence\" target=\"_blank\"></a>\r\n</div>\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=195\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt\"><font face=\"verdana,geneva\" size=\"2\">Interact with Julien Laurence&#39;s fans</font></span></a> \r\n',0,'',0,''),(913,1100,'3rd Rock Revolution',1,105,'www.myspace.com/3rdrockrevolution','Kings Road','07999 270899','\r\n<p><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Arial\"><strong>3 Essex boys, 1 Londoner & a Welshman who like to play Blues, Funk & Rock n Roll sometimes all at once. The idea to form a band came about in Dec\'05, we completed the line up in Feb\'06, we recorded a 5 track demo in late Oct\'06 down at Musicktek Studios in Dagenham, Essex.</strong> Gigs so far : Bar Monsta, Camden - 6th April \'07 : MusicTek Music Festival, Dagenham - 7th May \'07 : MusicTek Studios, Dagenham - 2nd June \'07 : The George, Witham - 24th June \'07. <br/><br/>REVIEW FROM INDIESTORE.COM. \"I woke up this morning demanding to hear some blues. I was not requiring strictly a blues sound, but if I did not hear a guitar that tipped its hat to country boys in Memphis, TN, then I was going to go crazy. Well, it took three Essex boys, one Londoner and a Welshman to nourish me. The band, 3rd Rock Revolution, is playing the genre of music that the boys of Cream handled perfectly. Allowing the reverb to sneak in this funkadelic-blues, their song, Non Starter, owns me. (DR)\" </span></p><br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=196\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\">Interact with 3rd Rock Revolution\'s fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(1923,1997,'Blue Louie',6,30,'','115 E. Houston St','9032455213','<font size=\"2\">A rockin\' Texas blues band. This band has toured places including Moscow Russia, Paris France, Madrid Spain and from coast to coast in the U.S. They have opened for artists all the way from Elvin Bishop, Koko Taylor, Kenny Wayne Sheppard, Dr John to Nazareth and Head East. True Texas roadhouse blues.</font> ',1,'',0,''),(1937,2015,'Maryline',1,61,'www.marylineblackburn.com','','770-849-8533','\r\n<p><strong><img title=\"\" height=\"0\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/uploads/2015/Studiorusky.jpg\" width=\"0\" align=\"baseline\" border=\"0\"/><font color=\"#ff0000\">Ability. Beauty. Charisma. Energy. And a clear, powerful voice that&#8217;ll flat knock the earpads off your iPod. </font></strong></p>\r\n<p><font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong>Meet Maryline Blackburn&#8230;an INTERNATIONAL CITIZEN. One of those artists who comes along once in a Blue Alaskan Moon and simply personifies the word \"Entertainer.\" </strong></font></p>\r\n<p><font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong>Born in Europe, Maryline spent her formative years in Fairbanks , Alaska . In the mid-1980\'s, she won the Miss Alaska Pageant and then went on to represent Alaska in the Miss America Scholarship Pageant where she was a talent finalist. She is a singer with a wide spectrum of performing experiences. She has performed with and opened for such legends of entertainment as Bob Hope (USO/Department of Defense), Cab & Chris Calloway, The Platters and contemporary icons like Celine Deon, Peabo Bryson, Phyllis Hyman and the group Exile. Maryline has appeared in venues as varied as Barry&#8217;s Place in Cancun , Mexico , The Famous Bluebird Caf&eacute; in Nashville , Tennessee , and The Buckboard Country Music Showcase in Marietta , Georgia where she performed country music classics. She has toured the Ritz-Carlton Hotels nationwide and shared her talents with international audiences in Spain , Argentina , Switzerland , Portugal , England , Ireland , Mexico , Costa Rica , Philippines , Diego Garcia , Honduras , Guatemala , Japan and Russia . </strong></font></p>\r\n<p><font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong>Maryline\'s talents have also made it on to both the large and small screen. She appeared in the movie \"Made in Heaven\" with Kelly McGillis and Timothy Hutton, Spike Lee\'s \"School Daze\" with Laurence Fishburne, as well as the daytime television drama, \"Sweet Auburn.\" Her commercial credits include Ford Motor Company, Gold\'s Gym, IBM and Chick-fil-A. </strong></font></p>\r\n<p><font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong>Her musical style can best be described as progressive, incorporating elements of Urban Contemporary, Mainstream Pop, Country and Western, Old School Romantic R&B, with a touch of the power and deep spiritual intensity of Southern Gospel Music. </strong></font></p>\r\n<p><font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong>Maryline\'s first CD is entitled \"Maryline,\" for which she wrote and composed seven songs. Her second CD -- \"Russian Rhapsody\" -- is a funky upbeat collection of pop music that Maryline co-wrote, performed and recorded in Moscow, Russia. </strong></font></p>\r\n<p><font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong>Hard to classify, engaging, entertaining, captivating. When you put it all together you have Maryline Blackburn, a consummate professional able to effortlessly meet the entertainment demands of any audience, regardless of the setting, be it an intimate night club or lounge, a concert hall, an arena or a large convention. </strong></font></p>\r\n<p><font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong>Once you\'ve heard her voice, you, too, will be a believer in the warmth, energy and uncompromised talent of Maryline Blackburn</strong></font>!</p>',1,'',0,''),(920,1105,'Junkvine',1,14,'www.junkvine.net','','','Junkvine was formed in the summer of 2002, when guitarist Shain Lloyd, bassist Mike Myers, and singer Trevor Johnson turned their attention from being a cover band into an original band. The 3 wrote 10 original songs, Shain built a studio, and they recorded them with the help of drummer Brad Dutton. The \"Junkvine\" CD was released in March of 2003. The band supported the album throughout the year playing gigs throughout Southern Illinois and some select shows near St. Louis, MO. In 2004, guitarist Shain Lloyd quit playing live to devote time to his family and newborn baby. Trevor followed in late 2005. Mike and Brad continued to play shows under the Junkvine name throughout the area with various line-ups. Recently, Mike quit the latest line-up to return to making original music with Shain and Trevor. They have added Ross Lloyd on drums and are currently writing and recording their follow up CD. The new CD should be released this summer(2007). We will let you know the exact release date soon.\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=198\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Junkvine\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(943,1133,'DIRTY DIAMONDS',1,14,'www.myspace.com/dirtydiamondslive','','','In 2006 saw the creation of Dirty Diamonds. 2 brothers, Kurt and Lincoln started Dirty Diamonds in early 2006 because they were bored of the music currently on the radio and wanted to change the music industry from what we know it today. With there influences of bands such as Motley Crue, Metallica, AC/DC, Gun&#8217;s and Rose&#8217;s and anything else from that great era of music, they created a rock sound that is hard to beat and easy to rock out to. Chris Moss, drums, was bought up playing jazz drums with his father and brings a phat rhythmic sound to the rhythm section of the band. Craig Vincent or &#8216;Vincent Fury&#8217; as we know him stepped onto lead guitar in Dec. 2006. Vincent Fury is the former Wretched Child guitarist and brings the quickest, most unbelievable shredding to be heard. Shane Finney was called up one Tuesday morning in Jan. 2007 and asked to audition for Dirty Diamonds and after just one song, the band knew that this was there man to take the front of the band. Shane, former Darkshot lead singer has a huge vocal range, melodic sound and the capability of writing anything from a lovesick ballad to a top of the charts rock song. Their first single, EMO was written by Shane in late 2006 and as soon as Shane heard the sound of Dirty Diamonds knew that the two would go together greatly. EMO is written for anyone that has ever felt like they had no one. Each verse tells a story and takes you through one young mans trip through the voices inside his head. Following in the steps of other great local S.E .Queensland bands such as Powderfinger, The butterfly Effect, Chasing Gravity(formerly Elephant Mojo) butterfingers, Japunga and many more, Dirty Diamonds will not stop until they have reached stardom and a top ten single on the Aria charts. Make sure you come and check out Dirty Diamonds, gaurenteed a good night.&nbsp;',1,'',0,''),(998,1205,'TRUEMAN',1,66,'www.myspace.com/truemanuk','542 ACKLAM ROAD','01642282184','<strong><u>TRUEMAN</u></strong> ARE IAN ERVING - GUITAR & VOCALS, SIMON ATKINSON - GUITAR, BASS & VOCALS, MIKE MACKIN - DRUMS.<br/>FORMED IN MIDDLESBROUGH , ENGLAND 2006 TRUEMAN HAVE JUST RELEASED THEIR DEBUT ALBUM TITLED<em> <strong>DUE TO BLOW</strong>&nbsp; </em>WHICH WILL SOON BE AVAILABLE TO BUY ON ITUNES.\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=212\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with TRUEMAN\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(944,1134,'Epic Tragedy',7,36,'www.myspace.com/epictragedy','9745 maple sugar leaf pl','5056936999','<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=224\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Epic Tragedy\'s fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(1127,1387,'Home Run Heroe',1,61,'myspace.com/homerunherouk','','','<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=256\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Home Run Heroe\'s fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(973,1176,'Jon Robert',1,61,'www.myspace.com/jonroberttour','40 Winchester Lane #18','9785004467','<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=213\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Jon Robert\'s fans</span></a><br/>',0,'',0,''),(976,1178,'KIK',1,71,'www.myspace.com/kikuk','','','<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://i70.photobucket.com/albums/i89/Flixx76/past_title.gif\"/><br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 8pt;\"> <span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">You\r\ncan blame the love of music for the relationship of the five\r\nlike-minded souls known as KIK. After dabbling in various bands,\r\nstudios and nightclubs over the last five years, it was inevitable that\r\nthese guys would stumble across each other at some point in their\r\nmusical journey. With influences from many genres, KIK collaborated in\r\n2003 and began to develop a very unique sound. Each member emerges from\r\na completely different musical background, with diverse influences such\r\nas Bowie, Depeche Mode, The Red Hot Chilli Peppers, Nine Inch Nails,\r\nTi&euml;sto and INXS to name but a few, its not surprising KIK have created\r\na unique, 15 track album, entitled </span><span style=\"font-style: italic; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\'RockScar\'</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">. </span><br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> <br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> <img style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://i70.photobucket.com/albums/i89/Flixx76/present_title.gif\"/><br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-style: italic; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\'RockScar\' </span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">has taken 2 years to complete. Written, produced and engineered by the band themselves, KIK&#8217;s </span><span style=\"font-style: italic; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\'RockScar\' </span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">is\r\ninfluential, no doubt about it. Delivering a blend of rock guitars and\r\ndirty synths, delivered in a way that is totally unique. KIK also\r\nbelieve that a bands look is as important as the music, they have a\r\nsleazy rock n\'roll glamour about them that transcends all genres. </span><br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> <br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">KIK Live is an experience that should not be missed. A visual and musical onslaught and always entertaining. <br/><br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"></span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">KIK\r\nhave a growing alternative following but have the ability to cross over\r\ninto the mainstream with music that is accessible to all. </span><br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> <br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><br/><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://i70.photobucket.com/albums/i89/Flixx76/future_title.gif\"/><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Kerrang!\r\nFM are very supportive of the band and to date have played 19 KIK\r\ntracks on air and have showcased the entire album plus additional\r\nmaterial. They have named </span><span style=\"font-style: italic; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\'Crack-Whore-Barbi\' </span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">as\r\none of their \"Modern Classics\" and play-listed the song in their\r\nunsigned show. Kerrang! FM have selected KIK as their \"Band to Watch\r\nfor 2007\". </span><br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> <br style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">KIK\r\nare in the process of finding the right deal for \'RockScar\'. If any\r\nlabels and management companies want a press pack than please contact\r\nKIK via myspace.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=214\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with KIK\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1001,859,'Anonymous',1,66,'','','07904368235','<p align=\"left\">\r\n<strong><font color=\"#993300\" style=\"font-size: 12pt\">TAME THAT BEAST<br />\r\n<font color=\"#000000\">T&#39;evenin we&#39;re Anonymous, a 5 piece band from the good old county of Lancashire UK. We are Rick Wilson (vocals), James Grant (lead guitar), Mick Lund (bass), James Wilson (rhythm guitar) and Chris Grant (drums). Creating music is our life and we hope that our music makes others feel as good as we do. Listen 2 our music and let us know if you like it! AV A DABBLE and TAME THAT BEAST</font></font></strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=218\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt\">Interact with Anonymous&#39; fans</span></a>\r\n',1,'Vocals: Richard Wilson<br />\r\nGuitars: James Grant<br />\r\nGuitars: James Wilson<br />\r\nBass: Michael Lund<br />\r\nDrums: Chris Grant\r\n',0,''),(983,1187,'Kelly Allyn',8,79,'www.kellyallyn.com','731 Harpeth Trace Drive','615-507-9761','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\">I was raised in Wyoming surrounded by family who never missed a chance to nurture and <span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">encourage my ambitions.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>Growing up, choir class was my favorite and it taught me that I needed a creative outlet.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>When High School graduation rolled around, I didn&#8217;t question what the next step in my life would be.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>I was taught that with a good education success would come out of a respectable job.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>So I went off to college and pursued a degree, even though I wasn&#8217;t quite sure where I fit into the world. But I stayed true to my creative side and earned a Bachelor of Fine Arts in Interior Design.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>Eventually, I moved to the East Coast certain that the big city was the life for me, but shortly thereafter my husband joined the United States Navy and my aspirations took a backseat to his duty orders.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>I learned to make do wherever we landed and stayed flexible to suit the priority of his career.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>Inevitably he was deployed to the Arabian Gulf and I was left alone to reflect. I realized that I had never really taken the time to get to know myself.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>I was happily married, had a great job, and yet something about me was still incomplete. But I knew that if I were going to survive the next 6 months, it was my passion in life that would pull me through. And I began to sing again. <span style=\"\">&nbsp;</span>Over the next year, I worked on a demo album that I hoped would get recognition and invite me to the next level.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>My prayers were quickly answered upon meeting my producers.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>Meeting them kicked off the greatest adventure of my life and for the first time I believe that I have purpose to my life. We immediately began creating my debut album, recording at the famous Chelsea Studios. And now, one year later, I&#8217;m looking at the launch of my dreams.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>Now that my album is complete I am getting prepared for touring and promoting my music all over the country.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>People say &#8220;timing is everything&#8221; and &#8220;all in God&#8217;s time&#8221;, well, I thank God for giving me this time, and for fulfilling my dreams with love, lots of laughter, and awesome music. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=215\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Kelly Allyn\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(989,1198,'Nuclear O\'Reilly',3,18,'www.planetofthegrapes.com','','','&nbsp;&nbsp; How did two rock musicians end up producing off-kilter electronic music and rapping to it? It\'s simple: unlike many others who talk the talk but can\'t walk the walk, they just do what they feel, always have, to hell with expectations and social codes. Frankly, we need more of that these days. Always collaborating in some way, when Jared DiDomenico and Brad Naprixas got together to write music, this is what came out. It started in 2001 as an occasional diversion, but gained momentum in 2006. The two were having fun, were proud of the music, and called it Nuclear O\'Reilly. \r\n\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Planet of the Grapes Media is a colorful and forward-thinking collective of several diverse creative projects, and Nuclear O\'Reilly serves as its resident music production team. PlanetoftheGrapes.com releases a new track produced by Nuclear O\'Reilly every second Tuesday of the month. They release small batches to the music portals every few months. In 2008, releases will also begin to present the rock music they write individually but still produce (make the recording sound the way it does) together. As you may be figuring out, Planet of the Grapes is one big party and its main identity and focus is the pure expression of those who use it as a vehicle. Welcome to a piece of its world.\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=216\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Nuclear O\'Reilly\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(996,1200,'Kuai Zi',1,105,'www.kuaiziband.com','','','<img title=\"\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://i133.photobucket.com/albums/q49/skottyfrombc/KuaiZiBioBig.jpg\" align=\"bottom\" border=\"0\" height=\"800\" width=\"566\"/><br/><br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=340\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Kuai Zi\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1000,1208,'LANE',1,61,'','','(321)213-1740','<font style=\"font-size: 12pt;\" color=\"#ff9900\"><strong>Once described stylistically as a cross between Alice Cooper and Debbie Gibson, 19 year old singer, songwriter, and multi-instrumentalist Lane has been a \"square peg\" for as long as she can remember. &#8220;It was traumatic to say the least,&#8221; she confesses when asked about her childhood growing up in the sleepy backwoods East Tennessee town of Strawberry Plains. &#8220;I was never into hip-hop or country so I didn&#8217;t exactly fit in with any of the other kids at my school. I guess I was kind of a loner. I was an outcast, the weird girl listening to rockers like David Bowie and Freddie Mercury. I used to tell kids in my first grade class that Steven Tyler was my father (We both have big mouths!). And I didn&#8217;t dress like my peers either. In fact, by the time I graduated from Carter High School in 2006 everyone thought I was a complete \'nut job.\' My parents admitted me to a hospital for a psychiatric evaluation when I was 16 and even my Shrink at the time said that I had \'issues.\' I thank God that I could escape through my music or else I never would have survived high school.&#8221; Fortunately, however, Lane&#8217;s life would soon change. In the summer of 2006 she met artist manager Christopher E. Long by chance backstage at a rock show in Nashville and the two kindred spirits clicked immediately. Lane soon relocated to the fast-paced East Coast Florida surf community of Satellite Beach where she joined Long and began pursuing her music career full-time. She now finds herself where she has always belonged, on stage performing live and working in the studio, developing her unique, radio friendly pop/rock songs. CONTACT: CHRISTOPHER E. LONG ARTIST MANAGEMENT / 379 HARWOOD AVENUE / SATELLITE BEACH, FL 32937 / MRPINK74@AOL.COM</strong></font>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=219\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with LANE\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1126,1360,'Mark Kerr',6,106,'www.markkerrltd.com','6942 Howell Street','318-938-8963','<p>Mark Kerr of Greenwood, Louisiana- never found success beyond his grasp.<br/><br/>From the age of twelve his course was clear, and from his earliest days in music he has built bridges that have connected him,not to his peers alone, but to the world at large.<br/><br/>Mark picked up the guitar at the age of twelve and before long, he was receiving recognition for his musical abilities.Where as many kids at twelve years of age may be content to watch television or to hang out with others of their own age.<br/>&nbsp;<br/>Mark had one singularly focused ambition. He wanted to become a musician. And so devoted was he to this pursuit, he would often fall to sleep at night with his guitar \"strapped on.\"<br/><br/>By the time he graduated from high school, he would be rewarded for his ambition.<br/><br/>Mark would eventually play with Percy Sledge and Rock and Roll Hall of Famers Curtis Mayfield\'s Impressions.<br/><br/>After thirteen years of touring, Mark attended Northwestern State University where he studied music theory,while working very diligently on his jazz, blues and rock skills.<br/>&nbsp;<br/>Mark was nominated for Musician of the Year in 2006 by The Academy of Texas Music, for his guitar work on One Drink Away From The Blues.<br/><br/>Mark was inducted into the National Heritage Foundation Blues Hall of Fame on March 13th 2007. He is the Ambassador to the Blues for the state of Louisiana.<br/>&nbsp;<br/>Mark\'s CD has been aired on 300 plus radio stations worldwide. And has charted in the top 25 on many of these stations.<br/><br/>Mark finished in the top 1500 of the 2007 Billboard World Songwriting Competition out of 5,500 entries.<br/><br/>Mark\'s title cut, One Drink Away From The Blues, finished as a second place winner in the 2007 Unisong International Songwriting Competition.<br/><br/>Mark achieved these great accomplishments as an independent artist. In the short eighteen months since the release of his CD One Drink Away From The Blues.<br/><br/>As Mark tells it, \"I want to continue to be a positive influence in the independent arena.\" \"And a role model, for all independents to see that through hard work, and a positive attitude, most anything can be achieved.\"<br/><br/>Today Mark can say reflecting back, \"I no longer drink, I started to see if I was going to be what I wanted to be in the music business as an independent, that there was no longer room for that.\"<br/>&nbsp;<br/>\"A person can go a lot farther with a clean, clear, non-polluted brain than with one.\"The road to success is a long and arduous one, but to steer it effectively, you have to have a clear head.<br/>That one drink could be \"One Drink Away From The Blues.<br/><br/>Check out Mark Kerr\'s Radio show called, \"Mark Kerr\'s Blues Nation.<br/>&nbsp;<br/>Mark\'s radio show was inducted into theNation Heritage Foundation Blues Hall of Fame on June 16, 2007 as a \"Great Blues Radio Show.\"<br/><br/>The show is currently the #3 blues rock show on the net.<br/><br/>Mark features the best in hard hitting indie blues and blues rock from around the globe.<br/><br/>Mark Kerr\'s Blues Nation can be heard 24/7&nbsp;at, <a href=\"http://www.markkerrltd.com/bluesnation.htm\">http://www.markkerrltd.com/bluesnation.htm</a><br/><br/>And every Saturday evening on Kansas City Online Radio from 5:00 to 7:00 p.m. CST <a href=\"http://www.kconlineradio.com\">http://www.kconlineradio.com</a> </p>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=257\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Mark Kerr\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1005,1168,'Pivot',1,71,'','','','&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pivot is a group in relentless pursuit of perfection and constant\r\nchange. Its members share more than just a passion for their work. They\r\nhave a sense of urgency in re-inventing themselves with every word put\r\nto paper or note put to tape.\r\n<br/><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Dream: A 4 song E.P. that brings to light a band with a story\r\nto tell and the skill to tell it. Driven rhythms, colorful riffs, and\r\nfluid harmonies intertwine throughout this latest release.\r\n<br/>\r\n<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Dream is not only a collection of songs, but also a live\r\nconcept. Their live show incorporates simplistic visual effects that\r\ntie sight and sound into one. Pivot will leave its audience making\r\nplans to see the next show. This band is quite simply interested in one\r\nthing...creating good music.\r\n<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\n\r\nBrian Kelly: <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">Vocals</span><br/>\r\nPhil Cicco: <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">Drums</span><br/>\r\nMike Hambright: <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">Bass</span><br/>\r\nEric Hambright: <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">Guitar</span><br/>\r\n<br/><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">\r\nAccomplishments:</span>\r\n<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\n\r\n- Performed @ The Dorton Arena for the &#8220;Carolina Roller Girls&#8221; Roller Derby in     front of 2,500 people. 9-16-06<br/>\r\n- Opened for Sony/Epic recording artist &#8220;MuDvAyNe&#8221; <br/>\r\n- Opened for Sony recording artist &#8220;Fingertight&#8221;<br/>\r\n- Opened for Columbia recording artist &#8220;Crossfade&#8221;<br/>\r\n- Opened for Wind Up Records recording artist  &#8220;Boy  Sets Fire&#8221; <br/>\r\n- Opened for Solid State Records recording artist &#8220;Beloved&#8221;<br/>\r\n- Opened for Sony recording artist Magna-Fi<br/>\r\n- Opened for National recording artist Confessor <br/>\r\n- Opened for National recording artist Jimmies Chicken Shack<br/>\r\n-#2 for 2 months at USA Network\'s FarmClub<br/>-#1 for the third\r\nand final month of USA Network\'s FarmClub. Announced on USA network for\r\n3 months as one of the top 5 unsigned bands in the nation by Matt\r\nPinfield from MTV<br/>\r\n- Accepted to showcase at The Masquerade for the Atlantis Music Conference 2004 in Atlanta, GA.<br/>\r\n- Accepted to showcase at the Millennium Music Conference 2004 in Harrisburg, PA.<br/>\r\n- Sponsored by Pork Pie Percussion, Dirt Bag Clothing, and partial JagerMeister sponsorship.  \r\n- Played the Ernie Ball Local Heroes Tour<br/>\r\n- Sound bites were recorded and used by a National franchise (Krystal Burgers)      for a nation wide commercial.<br/>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=220\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Pivot\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1010,1219,'Laurie Ann',1,61,'myspace.com/laurieannfessler','3019 72 street','516-508-8455','<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=221\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Laurie Ann\'s fans</span></a><br/>',0,'',0,''),(1020,1231,'NexXzit',9,44,'http://www.nexxzit.net','','','<p>\r\nWe are <em><strong>NexXzit </strong></em>(pronounced - next exit).&nbsp; Michael&nbsp;- aka -&nbsp;Ge&#39;down (sounds like &quot;get down&quot; but without the &quot;t&quot;) - <em>Ge&#39;down</em> plays rhythm and lead guitar, keyboards, engineers, mixes, songwriter and composer.&nbsp; &quot;Ge&#39;down Brown Productions&quot; has worked with many local artitsts i.e. N.I.T.T.I., Stinky-Dink (One Track Mind), Tony D, High Maintnence, Phaze II,&nbsp;Dedo, Lil&#39; Benny, Spellbound, Mouse Trapp, 99% and many more.&nbsp; Ge&#39;down&nbsp;is from Washington, D.C.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Marguerite&nbsp;-aka -&nbsp; <em>Margo,&nbsp; </em>writes the lyrics, plays keyboards, does lead and background vocals,&nbsp;vocal arrangement and plays percussions. She has performed/recorded with Spellbound, Experience Unlimited/EU, Sunrise and The Prajekt to name a few. Her single releases include &quot;Hard Core Party&quot;/Big City Records, &quot;Real Love&quot;/Big City Records and &quot;My Summertime&quot;/Alias Records.&nbsp; Margo is from Washington, D.C.&nbsp; We are the <em>original</em> founding members and despite personnel changes throughout the years remain dedicated to creating music with lots of soulful funk and meaningful lyrics.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Our&nbsp;style is Alternative R&amp;B/Funk and Soul with Rock undertones.&nbsp; Ohhhhh, &quot;O&quot;riginal.&nbsp; Ge&#39;down brings the rock edge with a natural&nbsp; groove and funky soul,&nbsp;and Margo brings&nbsp; jazziness to our melodies with soul stirring lyrics.&nbsp;&nbsp; I&#39;d say we fit in right about here - Alternative R&amp;B/Neo-Soul/Funk.<br />\r\nWe are dedicated musicians and soungwriters and we take&nbsp;our talent and art very seriously while having a great time doin&#39; it.&nbsp; We want to do music; front stage or behind the scenes.&nbsp; \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nOur group motto is: <em>&quot;What lies behind us and what lies before us are tiny matters compared to what lies within us.&quot;</em> \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nTo get to the party - &nbsp;take the&nbsp;<strong><u>&quot;<font color=\"#000000\">NexXzit</font>&quot;</u></strong>!&nbsp; \r\n</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=225\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt\">Interact with NexXzit&#39;s fans</span></a> \r\n',1,'',0,''),(1023,1234,'Eric Dodd Band',1,61,'myspace.com/ericdoddband','','','With his roots in Athens, Georgia, Eric Dodd has been a student of songwriting since\r\nthe age of 15.&nbsp;Eric Dodd and his band have played over a hundred shows in\r\nthe last two years around the Southeast and are looking to take their popular\r\nsounds to the national level.&nbsp;Eric&#8217;s southern, soul-filled stories of break-ups, heartache, re-kindling of relationships, freedom, and &#8211; finally &#8211; hope fill his debut album. The emotional trip of the album is enough to remind even the\r\noldest of souls of the memories of young, raw emotion. <o:p></o:p>\r\n\r\nAfter seeing the band live, you will agree that Eric has an uncanny knack of making you feel as though you are a part of something new and energetic and you alone are a vital part of the show.&nbsp; The band looks to release their debut album in October and have high expectations shortly thereafter.<br/>MYSPACE.COM/ERICDODDBAND<br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/EricDoddBand\"><img src=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/Templates/images/BestofBandsPromote4.gif\" height=\"100\" width=\"99\"/></a>\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=305\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Eric Dodd Band\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1024,1235,'Sex & Patriotism',1,16,'','','','<span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-style: italic;\">Strong and lean, <br/>One bad machine, <br/>You\'ll know what I mean! <br/>Runnin so hot, <br/>Got one shot, <br/>Never gonna stop! <br/>Full on speed, <br/>We got what you need! <br/>This is a Rock N\' Roll Dream!</span> <br/><br/><br/>Formed\r\nin early 2004 Sex and Patriotism have given the Michigan music scene a\r\nshot in the arm with their return to upbeat, melodic songwriting,\r\nsoaring vocals, and electrifying leads. They bring the high energy rock\r\nshow back to the stage. Their debut album To Die For has gotten rave\r\nreviews and developed the band a healthy following with fans in every\r\nstate of the Union and many fans overseas as well. Besides performing\r\nlive the band is also currently working on their follow up cd\r\ntenatively titled, \"RIOT\", or \"Secret Service\" depending on which way\r\nthe wind blows! Look for it in the Spring/Summer of \'07!\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=226\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Sex & Patriotism\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1025,1236,'Volume Water',1,14,'www.volumewater.com','','','VOLUME WATER is a Canadian-based rock band whose name can only be associated with extreme sonic energy. <br/>Check out their website www.volumewater.com. To purchase VOLUME WATER \"Underneath the Sun\" on cd visit www.amazon.ca or cdbaby.com. <br/><br/>Download all of Volume Water\'s songs for your ipod by going to http://phobos.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewAlbum?playListId=199980654 <br/><br/>Hailing from Hamilton Ontario, John Mamone has a background in vocal theatre, as well as a vast ability to play all the essential rock instruments with proficiency. John is the principle songwriter in the group. His compositions create the basis of Volume Water\'s sound. Toronto born Paul Salini is an experienced session drummer who has travelled as far as Nashville, L.A. and Texas to play his drums for professional songwriters. Salini along with Mamone played together prior to Volume Water in a band known as Dragonfly. Ancaster Ontario raised Mike Walker is an experienced and talented guitarist who is completely devoted to his instrument. Mike joined Dragonfly for a brief period, then re- joined Mamone and Salini after a brief hiatus to form Volume Water in June of 2003. 2005 saw the release of their debut album, &#8220;Underneath the Sun&#8221;, a powerful and exciting collection of heavy, riff-driven compositions that stand out amongst current rock- radio fare. The band have a video for the track, Underneath the Sun(which can be viewed above), produced by 1976 Films. Volume Water continues to perform their brand of power-rock to satisfied audiences on an ongoing basis.\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=233\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Volume Water\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1021,1233,'Left Standing',1,71,'http://www.myspace.com/leftstandingband','','702-400-9506','Left Standing was established in 2002. This Las Vegas original rock act is assembled by determination, motivation, and the love of music. Driven by different influences, Left Standing transforms into one energy on stage. The band consists of 5 members, Danny Pino (lead vocals), Chris Pino (bass, vocals), Beau Stewart (guitar, vocals), Jesse Pino (guitar, vocals), Zak Weidle (drums).<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLeft Standing serves up a welcome dose of rock &amp; roll. The performance and sound production of the guitars, bass and drums are first-rate and create vibrant and memorable rock rhythms. They are a group that knows no boundaries and whose apparent mission is to entertain their audience. This act puts their mark on several different styles, making each their own. Definably a rock act, they also venture into pop, alternative, punk and even a little hip-hop.<br />\r\nHowever, what&rsquo;s most impressive is that there strong in every style and give their all on every song. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n&ldquo;We set out to make music we enjoy and can feel proud of playing &mdash; music that we like and want to listen to. As soon as you start thinking beyond that &mdash; about wanting to keep up with the Joneses or about fitting in with somebody else&#39;s format &mdash; that&#39;s when you lose the map. So we&#39;ve just done what we do, and tried to have fun doing it.&quot; <br />\r\n<br />\r\nLeft Standing is endlessly new and unique as time goes by. Always delivering for the fans, show after show. They are one of the few groups whose versatility does not hurt them. Indeed, it makes them a phenomenon and a must see act.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=227\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt\">Interact with Left Standing&#39;s fans</span></a> \r\n',1,'Danny Pino (lead vocals), <br />\r\nChris Pino (bass, vocals), <br />\r\nBeau Stewart (guitar, vocals), <br />\r\nJesse Pino (guitar, vocals), <br />\r\nZak Weidle (drums).\r\n',0,''),(2036,2146,'Kevin Navis',1,16,' http://www.myspace.com/kevinnavis','641 aint happening','6512241212','\r\n<p>Well about 30 yrs of playing producing and just plan loving music so much its my every waking thought but its been a great run I still can keep up with the kids my main influence&nbsp; johnny winter, eric clapton, allmans. csny ,eagles </p>',0,'',0,''),(1028,1239,'Lenny Revell',1,61,'www.myspace.com/lennyrevellband','','(561) 558-3426','<div class=\"detail\" eventbits=\"125\" onload=\"null\" onerror=\"null\" onchange=\"null\">Lenny Revell\'s musical roots started in Buffalo, NY where at the age of nine, he started piano lessons. At sixteen he wrote his first song, and at nineteen, started singing lessons. He began playing various piano recitals in nursing homes, churches, and institutions in the WNY area. In his late teens, he started playing at the Lewiston Art Fest in Western New York for many years as well as the Canal Fest of the Tonawandas, NY for the past two years where he was brandished as the \"next Elton John\". <br/><br/>Many other cities followed with appearances in Branson, MO, and a tv appearance in Nashville, TN, and opening up a model show in Toronto, as well as many of the more popular piano bars and clubs in the NYC circuit including \"Don\'t Tell Mamas\", \"Rosa\'s Turn\", George Keeley\'s, The Duplex, and many more. <br/><br/>He has also acted in two operas within the Greater Buffalo Opera Company under world renowned opera director Gary Burgess: Carmen and The Flying Dutchman, and modeled for Rova in NYC. Lenny\'s discovery of Elton John was at the age of eighteen, and the turning point of his life. Now with a focal point to shoot for, he devoted his energies to writing piano rock songs influenced by Elton\'s signature style. More artist\'s influences started to come to the forefront: The Beatles, Billy Joel, Ben Folds, Vanessa Carlton, Tori Amos, Coldplay, etc. <br/><br/>Now with a new album entitled \'Lessons\', Lenny plans to unveil a new charasmatic performer in the singer-songwriter genre of rock. Aside from his musical accomplishments, Lenny is also into nutrition, alternative medicine, eastern philosophy, and a certified instructor in Bruce Lee\'s art of Jeet Kune Do under Sifu Shane Dixon.</div>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=228\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Lenny Revell\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',0,'',0,''),(1029,1242,'Impulsive Decision',1,71,'myspace.com/impulsivedecision','','856 649 4618','\r\n<center>\r\n<center>\r\n<center>\r\n<center>\r\n<center>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">This five-member band, Impulsive Decision, is a group that has a very edgy and forceful experimental sound. Their music represents exactly what they call themselves, impulsiveness. Bridging all of the musical elements through heavy drums, Ripping guitars, bass, and perfect vocals with the right kind of melodic structure, Impulsive Decision has the right ingredients to make the perfect kind of sound.</p><br/><br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=229\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\">Interact with Impulsive Decision\'s fans</span></a><br/></center></center></center></center></center>',1,'',0,''),(1042,1261,'Kennedy Road',1,14,'www.myspace.com/kennedyroadband','','','Kennedy Road is a hard rock band that utilizes melodic hooks to spark an original feel in the minds and hearts of their fans. Fans that in a short a<a href=\"http://www.pimp-my-profile.com/\" target=\"_blank\"></a>mount of time went from dozens to hundreds, who are soon to be thousands and will eventually become millions. These fans are infected by the energy that Kennedy Road puts into every song whether it\'s on a CD, on the radio or at a show. Kennedy Road has been described many times over as \"...a 3 piece band that hits you with so much sound and energy, you would swear they\'re a 5 piece if you weren\'t looking.\" and that brings a smile to their faces. Originally formed in 2005 under the name Niteshift, Kennedy Road has performed many high profile shows and gained a great amount of exposure in the process. Kennedy Road has opened for such nationally touring bands as Drowning Pool, Ra and 10 Years. In the winter of 2006 Kennedy Road was chosen to perform in The Rave Bar (www.therave.com for more info) as a pre-show opener for the then current Sevendust tour. By doing this Kennedy Road has joined a long list of bands who have since gone on to do great things in the world of music. Most currently Kennedy Road has been building their fan base on the homefront. The Back Bar in Janesville, WI has been Kennedy Road\'s \"home\" for the better part of the last year (www.thebackbar.com for more info). Through their shows at The Back Bar, Kennedy Road was chosen to open for Caroline\'s Spine, a nationally touring band from Oklahoma (www.carolinespine.com for more info). This was a sold out show that exposed the Kennedy Road style to hundreds of people. Along with this, Kennedy Road is currently being filmed as one of the feature bands in a documentary about the rock music scene in Rock County, which is where the band originates from. This project is still in the early stages of filming and delopement, but the main goal for the future is to have this video shown and distributed across the country. Kennedy Road is very excited about this project and hopes that it will expose them to many people who normally would not get a chance to see them. What the future holds for Kennedy Road is anyone\'s guess. With a little help they hope to rock bigger venues, record a full length CD and tour with other amazing bands and artist\'s. Kennedy Road will keep pushing, working, writing and rocking until they reach their goals and there\'s nothing that can stop that. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=230\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Kennedy Road\'s fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(1053,1259,'Leighton',1,72,'leightonband.net','','','<p><font style=\"background-color: rgb(214, 223, 247);\">\"Leighton\", was formed in Nov. 2006. But four of the members have been performing together in many projects for many years.&nbsp;&nbsp; The newest member is lead vocalist, Dino Johnson.&nbsp; He was the lead singer in a local band around the Detroit area, called the Ride.&nbsp; Eddie Leighton seen him perform many times, and loved his vocal ability. He can sing anything he wants, from Journey to Nickelback, and he sounds great.&nbsp; So Eddie&nbsp;gave him a contact number, and Dino&nbsp;called it, and here he is. The first thing we did was put a original song together. The band was blown away by how good it came out.&nbsp; We new we had something going here!! So in Jan. thru March,2007, &nbsp;we kept on recording new originals. WCSX radio DJ Steve Kostan, has been jamming with Eddie Leighton for about three years.&nbsp; He would use Eddie\'s last project, (The Eddie Leighton Project) for special events. Concerts, festivals, ect.&nbsp; He loved the new band, and has helped us with priceless promotion within the Detroit metro area. Just in the pass 2 months, we have performed with national, and international bands such as: STYX, Paul Rodgers, Reo Speedwagon, Kansas, Blue Ouster Cult, Mark Farner(Grand Funk Railroad), Asia, and many more.&nbsp; Things are working out great, because the band can work together as a business. We have been around the block many times, and now it is time to go around the world. Check us out, we are solid rock band, and we have great originals.&nbsp; We are looking for a professional manager and booking agency. I mean PROFESSIONAL!&nbsp; We know what we are looking for, and what it is going to take. A solid comitment. I want to thank, Best of bands, for there work at getting this site together for all of us bands.&nbsp; We need people like this. Thank you from&nbsp;the members of \"Leighton\"<br/>Website: <a href=\"http://www.leightonband.net\">www.leightonband.net</a> </font></p>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=235\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Leighton\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1057,1283,'State The Obvious',1,71,'statetheobvious.weebly.com','','','<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b style=\"\"><i style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 16pt;\" lang=\"CY\"></span></i></b><span style=\"\" lang=\"CY\"> State The Obvious are Chris\r\nHicks (Vocals, Guitar, Songwriter), Laura Fear (Lead Guitar), Isi Vincent\r\n(Drums) and Dave Collard (Bass). <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"\" lang=\"CY\">Chris, Lau and\r\nIsi started off as a small acoustic band in Cardiff, practicing under the name\r\n&#8216;Strange Beginnings&#8217; in September, 2005. Eventually after a few line-up and\r\nname changes, they became State The Obvious, with Dave on Bass. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"\" lang=\"CY\">The band are\r\ninfluenced by grunge and alternative acts like Nirvana and Pearl Jam, and\r\nproduce a &#8216;post-grunge&#8217; sound.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"\" lang=\"CY\">Their first gig\r\nwas at the popular all-ages club &#8216;Teen Spirit&#8217; in September 2006. With a\r\nsubstantial crowd and a good review, the band set off to implement themselves\r\ninto the Cardiff music scene. They built up an international fan base through\r\nmusic networking sites and played more gigs throughout Cardiff. They played\r\n&#8216;Under Construction Festival&#8217;, a music festival organised for young people by\r\nyoung people and were heavily involved in promoting and organising it.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"\" lang=\"CY\">In June 2007,\r\nthey released their independently produced debut EP &#8216;Yesterday&#8217;s Photograph&#8217; to\r\ncritical acclaim and radio coverage around the country.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"\" lang=\"CY\">All members of\r\nthe band stayed 100% committed to the future, many gigs have been planned, an\r\nalbum is in the future and they plan to tour the UK and try a stint in the USA\r\nas well.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=236\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with State The Obvious\' fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(1060,1286,'Ghetto Flame',4,22,'www.myspace.com/ghettoflame','','','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=237\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Ghetto Flame\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1061,1288,'LOSTrockband',1,71,'http://www.lostrockband.com','','','<p align=\"left\">\r\n<font size=\"2\" style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: Georgia\"><br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<br />\r\n<font color=\"#000000\">LOSTrockband is a modern, classic, and original rock band out of Waterbury, CT. The band was formed in June, 2005 and has been growing strong ever since.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLOSTrockband is comprised of five diverse musicians that bring their own personal flair which is blended to create the bands unique style and sound. These five talented members are driven by their love for music and a desire to play what people like to hear.</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\">\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=238\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt\">Interact with LOST&#39;s fans</span></a>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(2465,1000267,'Blue Coyote Band',8,40,'http://bluecoyoteband.com','805 S Dexter Dr','517-719-0096','<font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"4\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"2\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"2\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"4\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</font></font></font></font><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"4\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"2\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"2\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"4\"><a style=\"text-decoration: none; color: Red\" href=\"http://www.b93.com/cc-common/artist_submission/player.html?art=147176\"></a></font></font></font></font><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"4\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"2\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"2\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"4\"><a style=\"text-decoration: none; color: Red\" href=\"http://www.b93.com/cc-common/artist_submission/player.html?art=147176\"><img id=\"mytracksBanners_r1_c1\" src=\"http://www.bluecoyoteband.com/b93beehat.gif\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" width=\"83\" height=\"68\" /></a></font></font></font></font>\r\n<h1><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"4\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"2\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"2\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"4\"><a style=\"text-decoration: none; color: Red\" href=\"http://www.b93.com/cc-common/artist_submission/player.html?art=147176\">B 93 FM Radio</a></font></font></font></font></h1><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"4\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"2\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"2\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"4\"><br />\r\n</font></font></font></font><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"4\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"2\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"2\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"4\"><a style=\"text-decoration: none; color: Red\" href=\"http://www.b93.com/cc-common/artist_submission/player.html?art=147176\"></a></font></font></font></font><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"4\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"2\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"2\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"4\"><a style=\"text-decoration: none; color: Red\" href=\"http://www.b93.com/cc-common/artist_submission/player.html?art=147176\">Please EVERYONE...Click the BANNER ABOVE to hear us on B93 and also submit a vote for Louie Longoria and the Blue Coyote Band to get NATIONAL AIRPLAY on hundreds of CLEAR CHANNEL radio stations....Just a simple click to play...</a></font></font></font></font><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"4\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"2\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"2\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"4\"><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLouie Longoria began performing in 1991 with &quot;The Renegades&quot; a band in\r\nwhich he helped form. Playing the clubs around Mid-Michigan, they\r\nquickly became known for their style of music including both classic\r\ncountry and new country and 50&#39;s &amp; 60&#39;s rock. His relaxed humor has\r\nnever failed him at winning the hearts of his audience. Tommy Cash has\r\nhad Louie open his shows since 2002 when he tours Michigan. In 2006,\r\nLouie had the honor of singing a duet with Tommy called &quot;Six White\r\nHorses&quot;: A #1 hit for Tommy in 1969. Louie has also released two other\r\nCDs &quot;Wide Open Country&quot; and &quot;Tribute To The Legends&quot;.<br />\r\n<img src=\"http://bluecoyoteband.com/clearspacer.gif\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Great American Country Music, Pure Country Music by Louie Longoria and Blue Coyote\" width=\"100\" height=\"8\" /><br />\r\nNow Louie has formed a new group - Blue Coyote Band - bringing together\r\nthe talents of Scott Bates (formerly of &quot;Heirborn&quot; and &quot;LTD&quot;), Bob\r\nCottom (also formerly of &quot;Heirborn&quot; and &quot;Sawmill Road&quot;) and Gregg\r\nHammond (formerly of &quot;CrossRoads&quot;). <br />\r\n<img src=\"http://bluecoyoteband.com/clearspacer.gif\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Great American Country Music, Pure Country Music by Louie Longoria and Blue Coyote\" width=\"100\" height=\"8\" /><br />\r\nIf you like Great American Country Music from the 80s &amp; 90s, some\r\nnew country tunes, with a light mix of Southern Gospel, then don&#39;t miss\r\na single concert! Check out their <a style=\"text-decoration: none; color: #a3a8c8\" href=\"http://bluecoyoteband.com/tour.html\"><strong>Tour Page</strong></a>.  We&#39;ll see you at a concert SOON!<br />\r\n</font>\r\n<img src=\"http://bluecoyoteband.com/clearspacer.gif\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Great American Country Music, Pure Country Music by Louie Longoria and Blue Coyote\" width=\"100\" height=\"8\" /><br />\r\n<font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"3\">\r\n</font></font></font><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"4\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"2\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"3\"><strong>Blue Coyote Band - Pure Country Music!</strong></font></font></font>\r\n</font>\r\n',1,'<font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"4\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"2\"><font face=\"arial, helvetica\" size=\"2\">\r\nLouie Longoria<br />\r\nScott Bates<br />\r\nRobert Cottom<br />\r\nGregg Hammond<br />\r\nFred Udell<br />\r\nDanny Hullihen<br />\r\n</font></font></font>\r\n',0,''),(1068,1295,'mancabbage',1,76,'myspace.com/mancabbage','19 belmont avenue',' 02088825201','<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=239\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with mancabbage\'s fans</span></a><br/><br/>',1,'',0,''),(1069,1299,'Cimarroncito',7,84,'','','','Sim-u-ron-seat-oh\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=240\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Cimarroncito\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1070,1287,'Rude Punch',1,17,'www.myspace.com/rudepunch','','','Rude Punch is a Reggae/Rock band from the midwest.&nbsp; Heavily influenced by Sublime, 311, Slightly Stoopid, Pepper, Bob Marley, etc, Brady(Lead Guitar and Vocals), Adam(Drums and Back up Vocals) and Robb(Bass Guitar) started Rude Punch in Brady\'s parent\'s basement in 2005.&nbsp; It was there that they blended their musical influences into the unique Rude Punch sound.&nbsp; They rehearsed, wrote and rehearsed some more and after a few months decided to bring their music to the people.&nbsp; They played wherever and whenever they could, private partys, fundraisers, bars, clubs and the like, gathering a fan base and having a great time.&nbsp; They eventually began to get bigger and better gigs, opening for bands like Everclear, Pepper and The Wailers to name a few, and playing festivals and similar events.&nbsp; In late 2006, Rude Punch had written enough of their own music to go to the studio and begin production of their debut CD.&nbsp; At the time of this writing, the record is almost finished and will soon be available to the masses.&nbsp; In the mean time, Rude Punch continues to play gigs wherever they can find them, spreading their unique Reggae/Rock vibe far and wide, bringing the party to the people.&nbsp; So sit back, relax and grab yourself a cup of Rude Punch.&nbsp; Listen, enjoy, and tell a friend.&nbsp; There\'s plenty of Rude Punch to go around.\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=241\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Rude Punch\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1072,980,'Atypical people',1,71,'www.atypicalpeople.com','10, Rue Lafayette','+33556365311','<span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Verdana;\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; line-height: 20.4pt;\" align=\"justify\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: \'Calibri\',\'sans-serif\';\" lang=\"EN-US\">&#8220;At</span><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: \'Calibri\',\'sans-serif\';\" lang=\"EN-US\">ypical people\" A new name for a new start. Four musicians, Isa, Jean, Marcel and Pol. Before they were called \"P-pol\", but their manager who did more harm to the band than good forced them to change their name. Growing in strength from their experiences and not looking back are even more determined to push forward.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; line-height: 24pt;\" align=\"justify\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: \'Calibri\',\'sans-serif\';\" lang=\"EN-US\">After their first auto produced album &#8220;A part of Us\" they will be back with a brand new album Rock - Pop with more emphasis on Rock than before. Giving a veiled reference to the new beginning \"Like a Phoenix\" the title of their new album.<br/><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 61.2pt 3.6pt 0pt 0cm; text-indent: 36pt; text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: \'Calibri\',\'sans-serif\';\" lang=\"EN-US\">ISA : I\'ve been singing ever since I can remember. It\'s more than a passion to me<i>&#8230;</i>It\'s My reason for being<i>. </i></span><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: \'Calibri\',\'sans-serif\';\" lang=\"EN-US\">I don&#8217;t have any preferences in styles of music. The only criteria I have is that it gives me this \"gut\" feeling. Artistes like Aretha Franklin, U2, Ben Harper, Muse, or KT Tunstall. They give me real pleasure.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 25.2pt 7.2pt 0pt 0cm; text-indent: 36pt;\" align=\"justify\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: \'Calibri\',\'sans-serif\';\" lang=\"EN-US\">JEAN : A <span>total<b> </b></span>immersion in music since my childhood, have given me<i> </i>influences that are very divers from </span><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: \'Calibri\',\'sans-serif\';\" lang=\"EN-US\">classical to jazz, from Pop to Rock n\' Roll. Artistes that grab me by the b....s are: Nigel Kennedy, Steve <span>Lukather, Mike Landau, Eric Johnson, Petrucci, Van Halen, Pat M&eacute;theny, Mike Stern, George Benson, and Robert Ford. Guitarists, the majority of whom fuses my passion for music and gives me a thirst to reach </span>perfection with my guitars.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 25.2pt 0cm 0pt; text-indent: 35.45pt;\" align=\"justify\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: \'Calibri\',\'sans-serif\';\" lang=\"EN-US\">MARCEL: I belong to a family of artists for three generations, and music was always present during my childhood, <span>my influences <span>are<b> </b></span>very varied, Led Zep, Genesis, Peter Gabriel, Earth Wind and Fire, Prince, Larry Graham Central Parliament, Electric Light Orchestra, Tower of Power. Tears for fears, Joe Louis Walker, and much more. Very eclectic in my way of approaching music, with a great M, initially it\'s a good feeling.</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 25.2pt 3.6pt 16.2pt 0cm; text-indent: 32.4pt; text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: \'Calibri\',\'sans-serif\';\" lang=\"EN-US\">PAUL: A passion for music with the discovery of Prince, it was the catchy rhythms which gave me the desire </span><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: \'Calibri\',\'sans-serif\';\" lang=\"EN-US\">for learning drums techniques. Thereafter it was another aspect of this art, more creative which spurred me on <span>to composing <span>music.<b> </b></span>Today my preferences are those of Archive, Placebo, Travis, Elbow, and many others.</span></span></p></span>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=242\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Atypical people\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1074,1310,'Lowlander',1,68,'www.myspace.com/lowlanderband','','','Lowlander is the result of a lovechild between the Misfits, The Ramones, Tom Petty, Weezer, and Green Day. This truly different, unique, fresh band fuses the best parts of pop punk, rock, and alternative into a distinctive sound that challenges any label or category. The heart and soul of Lowlander is to write original music to introduce to the masses. We hope to continually gain the respect and interest from fans, peers, and other bands because we care about the people that listen to us! All three members are West Virginia natives with Scottish roots. The members being Jim Courtney as lead vocals/drums; Kris Boynes as lead guitar; and Sean Boynes on rhythm and bass guitars. Currently, we have just completed our debut album(\"We Need To Talk\") and it is available at www.cdbaby.com/cd/lowlander. We will continue playing as many shows as possible, and hope everyone will get a chance to see us, and enjoy our music. Thank you for checking us out, please listen to our music and let us know your thoughts. The only bad input is the one never stated, so speak your mind. KEEP ROCK AND ROLL ALIVE!!!\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=243\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Lowlander\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1075,1308,'Luca',1,73,'www.myspace.com/lucamusicuk','','','Luca are:<br/><br/>Adam - Vocals<br/>Mike - Guitar<br/>Jake - Guitar<br/>Wayne - Bass<br/>Andy - Drums<br/><br/>Formed in it\'s current incarnation from the ashes of a previous band (Seventh Story) in early 2007, Luca play an energetic, upbeat style&nbsp;of punky, emo, rock.&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=246\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Luca\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1076,1311,'Last Night',10,45,'www.lastnightmusic.com','','807 621 8871','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\">In November of 2005 the universe decided that Trevor Potts (vocals/guitar), Matt Lawrie (guitar/vocals), and Chris MacLeod (guitar), all from <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:city w:st=\"on\">Thunder Bay</st1:city>, <st1:state w:st=\"on\">Ontario</st1:state>, <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\">Canada</st1:country-region></st1:place>, would start something huge. Trev, Matt, and Chris jammed a few days and nights in a row - seeming like one long session - creating some music and laughing their brains out.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\">Last Night was born.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\">Since then the band has been completed, adding Mr. (Brent) Jones (bass) in April of 2006.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>The band enjoyed numerous successful shows with fellows Wax Philisophic and Doobsie&#8217;s Band, played at the 2006 and&nbsp;2007 Canada Day celebrations at marina park, performed&nbsp;out of province and internationally, and were chosen to open for Glass Tiger in &#8216;06.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>The summer of 2006 kept the band busy with a regular gig filling Tony and Adam&#8217;s restaurant in <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Thunder Bay</st1:place></st1:city>, while recording their now available CD, appropriately entitled, 7TRACKS.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>The show for the kids at <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:placetype w:st=\"on\">Camp</st1:placetype> <st1:placename w:st=\"on\">Quality</st1:placename></st1:place> also stands out as a highlight. </p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><o:p>&nbsp;<br/></o:p>Like many bands these days Last Night has difficulty comparing themselves to other acts, but notable influences include the likes of Jack Johnson, Led Zeppelin, Dave Mathew&#8217;s Band, Dispatch, silverchair, and pennywise.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\">Acoustic Rock is likely the best label for a band that has also been compared to OAR and Dashboard Confessional.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>Having three guitarists and 4 vocalists allows Last Night to seek limitless potential when combined with catchy lyrics and a driving rhythm section that currently includes drum kit, hand percussion, and dynamic bass riffs.<br/><br/>7TRACKS is currently available&nbsp;with<span style=\"\"> w</span>ork on the sophomore album currently underway.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>Writing should be complete this fall with a full length recording available in late 2007 or early 2008.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><b style=\"\">CONTACT</b><br/><br/>Trevor Potts </p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\">Phone (807) 621-8871</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><a href=\"mailto:lastnightmusic@gmail.com\">lastnightmusic@gmail.com</a> </p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/lastnightmusicspace\"><font color=\"#800080\">www.myspace.com/lastnightmusicspace</font></a></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><a href=\"http://www.lastnightmusic.com/\"><font color=\"#800080\">www.lastnightmusic.com</font></a></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><br/>Last Night is more than excited about the future of the band.<br/><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">Enjoy the music and <i style=\"\">Let Life Happen</i>!</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=280\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Last Night\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1080,1315,'max cady band',1,17,'http://www.maxcadyband.com','','708-837-6931','<a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=247\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt\">Featuring the veteran singer/songwriter&nbsp;&nbsp; Riche Pace&nbsp;&nbsp; and the guitar wizardry of&nbsp;&nbsp; ken erickson,&nbsp; the max cady band is a progressive mix of rock and blues with some jazz/funk&nbsp; overtone.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; real music,,not just a bunch of noise.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &quot;welcome to the 21st century&quot; <br />\r\n</span></a>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1206,1494,'Misguided',1,74,'www.misguidedmusic.com','','','<p><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">The genesis of <strong>Misguided</strong> began with their unflinching desire to create a band of diversity and power to frequent the London rock scene&nbsp;- A band to work in <strong>association</strong> with the like-<strong>minded</strong> to restore a yawning scene to full consciousness.<br/><br/>Successful dates in the recording studio and praised live <strong>performances</strong> has served to give direction and purpose to the band and its followers: Traits that are <strong>reflected</strong> in their particular blend of the intense, the alternative, and the elemental <strong>principles</strong> of rock, <strong>twisted</strong> to suit the artistic inclinations of the five piece from south London. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=311\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Misguided\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1208,1497,'Oversize',1,61,'www.showcaseyourmusic.com/oversize','','','<span style=\"font-style: italic; font-weight: bold;\"></span>We\'re not so great with words as far as the \"bios \" goes, because, actually we believe only the music can discribe a band in the best way. Everybody has different tastes, and no matter what we would write down here about the things we\'ve done with our band so far - the stages we\'ve been on or the places we\'ve been - (we were only on stages in Germany, so no we haven\'t played near your town yet-although it would be something we\'d love and be looking forward to do) -we still think it\'s best to just let you have a listen, and hope you like what you hear. And, of course, thank you for your time, that you dropped by our site. Be sure to stop by some of the other bands here too though. We do believe you\'ll find some great talents here. Let us send you on your way with these words that at least describe our feelings about what we do. A guy we know once said: \" <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">I can live in a world without shoes, but I could never live in a world without music.</span>\" P.S.: For a FREE DOWNLOAD of our songs check out: www.mp3.de<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=312\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Oversize\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1199,602,'Exit the Ride',1,74,'www.myspace.com/exittheride','','8282448465','<strong><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><font color=\"#003366\">The music of Exit The Ride is an intense and emotional blend of classic and modern rock injected with soaring vocals and shredding lead guitars. </font></p></span></strong><span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><font size=\"2\"><font color=\"#003366\">Guitar virtuoso Bill Peck has joined forces with singer/songwriter Samuel Stone and drummer Clint Larson to form one of the more formidable hard rock bands to hit the scene in years. <em>\"I want people to feel empowered by our music\" </em>says Stone. ETR is poised to be a part of a musical revolution. <br/><br/><strong>Samuel Stone\'s vocals</strong> take you on a melodic journey through peaks and valleys normally reserved for the likes of great tenors such as Chris Cornell and Scott Weiland. Stone brings Weiland\'s edge to the mix along with the influence of Myles Kennedy and others, forming his own unique brand of vocals.<br/><br/><strong>Guitar shredding master Bill Peck </strong>brings his guitar work to the forefront of a modern rock format, giving fans a chance to hear his true versatility with monster riffs and scorching solos. <strong>Alter Bridge\'s Mark Tremonti </strong>described Peck as a <em>\"whammy bar, tapping, and legato master\" </em>in the 2004 October issue of Guitar One magazine. <br/><br/>Peck draws his shred influence from the likes of guitarist\'s Steve Vai and Zakk Wylde, and open tunings and songwriting from his good friend Mark Tremonti. <strong>Drummer Clint Larson</strong> ties it all together with a beat that will have you nodding your head.<br/><br/>Exit The Ride has been performing and recording throughout 2005 and early 2006 and gained many new fans. Look for more songs from the guys in the coming months as well as exposure thru Dean Guitars and Guitar One magazine.<br/><br/><strong>Exit The Ride is influenced by</strong> older bands such as Led Zeppelin, Van Halen, and with some <em>new rock influence from guys like their producers Justin Thomas and Brett Hestla (Dark New Day/Virgos Merlot, former Creed touring bass), Creed, Zakk Wylde, Steve Vai </em>and plenty of others.<br/><br/><strong>Songs recorded for an upcoming EP include</strong> their latest three, <em>\"There for Me\", \"Reach\", and \"Not So Strange\".</em> Other tracks include \"Letters\", \"Everytime I\", \"Fallen to Fly\", and \"Solidarity\". </font><em><font color=\"#003366\">You do NOT want to miss hearing this band; if you\'re really fortunate, you\'ll catch them live :)</font></em></font></p><font size=\"2\"><em>\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><font color=\"#003366\"></font></p></em></font>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><br/><font color=\"#003366\">&nbsp;</font></p></span>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=313\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Exit the Ride\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1083,1322,'Scarred Theory',7,33,'www.myspace.com/scarredtheoryband','','','<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: Courier New;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Courier New;\">Scarred Theory is a Four piece metal band. A total original band and original composition. We are located in upstate Ny and have been together for over two years now. The history of each individual is not important and each individual is not important within the band. We are a team and as a team we are Scarred Theory. As the age of the great selfishness settles in we will fight to keep love alive and brotherhood. The Scarred Theory will be forever remembered for truth and love. We love what we do and each other. That is the key for our soon to come success. We will embrace those that discourage and champion those who believe. We are a metal band becuase the raw energy in metal music is an addiction and each one of feel it when we play it. We are different in the way that we dont view this as a hobby or click. This is religious to us and we pour our blood out for it. So keep it metal and check us out.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=248\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Scarred Theory\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1086,1330,'Rags to riches',1,71,'www.myspace.com/ragstworiches','Gamlegrensa 2b','+4792235861','\r\n<p><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; RAGS TO RICHES</p>\r\n<p><br/>With their debut release, &#8220;Picking Up The Pieces,&#8221; it is obvious that Rags To Riches is more than a Jimi Hendrix tribute band (which was their main focus early on).&nbsp; The band, originally called themselves &#8220;Black Pearl&#8221;-reformed with two new members to create Rags To Riches and they quickly realized there is a magic to their music.</p>\r\n<p>A review of their debut CD reveals their influences, Uriah Heep, Deep Purple, Pink Floyd and of course Jimi Hendrix, among others.&nbsp; Their melodic and fantastic mix of 70\'s rock/synth is new and refreshing, as they weave the progressive sounds of today&#8217;s music with the classic rock sound of yesteryear without sounding dated. </p>\r\n<p>The cut, &#8220;Diamond On A Ring&#8221; flows effortlessly, with a splendid mix of dreamy pop and mellow psychedelia, then explodes into a hard-rocker with Deep Purple-like guitars and a short guitar solo that is among rock&#8217;s best; one that you listen to, close your eyes and play along with.</p>\r\n<p>&#8220;Seize The Moment&#8221; sounds a bit like Steve Miller in his prime, then adeptly switches to an old Asia-like sound, all the while flowing with originality, flawless harmonies and a determined cohesiveness.&nbsp; There is more splendid rock with the song, &#8220;Guardian Of The Light&#8221; with ZZ Top-like riffs, more brilliant harmonies and dynamic guitar work.&nbsp; Another tune &#8220;Fire In The Sky,&#8221; captures the pure sound of Ritchie Blackmore and vintage Deep Purple and could have been a popular FM hit in the 70\'s with it&#8217;s stalwart drumming, blistering guitar and intoxicating keyboards.</p>\r\n<p>The boys from Skien, Norway have invited us to share and listen to their unique blend of rock, alt-rock and progressive rock and are burning up Internet radio and are finding the world&#8217;s audience is very accepting and thanking them for sharing their musicianship, all the while anticipating the great things to come.</p>\r\n<p><br/>Author Robert Benson writes about rock/pop music, vinyl record collecting and operates <a href=\"http://www.collectingvinylrecords.com\">www.collectingvinylrecords.com</a> where you can secure your copy of his ebook called \"The Fascinating Hobby Of Vinyl Record Collecting.\"<br/>Robert can be contacted at <a href=\"mailto:robert@collectingvinylrecords.com\">robert@collectingvinylrecords.com</a>.</p><br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=249\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\">Interact with Rags to riches\' fans</span></a>',1,'',0,''),(1119,1373,'Merrill',1,61,'merrillmusic.com','','503-449-4961','The band Merrill is led by singer/songwriter Chris Merrill, and the group manages a soulful past with a blend of rhythm and rock to form a sound that transcends categories. The band\'s music spans from rock to pop, blues to soul, and everywhere in between. There really are no limits to the kind of music they write. \r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div><br/>Chris began playing music in elementary school but stopped for many years when he hit middle school. It was during his sophomore year at Southern Oregon University where things started to take shape. First he took a beginning piano class from a very talented Russian concert pianist. He then started singing with friends as a way to impress girls at parties. Unfortunately it never really took off. When Chris turned 21, he started singing in karaoke bars where he noticed people responded well to his singing. It was those experiences that led him to start pursuing the idea of a career in music. Less than a year later he picked up a guitar, and with nothing but a chord book and some tabs, taught himself how to play. The rest, as they say, is history... \r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div><br/>The Band made it to the second round of the Bodog National Battle of the Bands contest in 2006 before they had to bow out because they lost their bass player. They have received airplay in Seattle on The End( 107.7) for their song \"Wonderful Nothing\". \r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div><br/>Merrill is also receiving accolades on garageband.com: \r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div><br/>The song Intervention received the Rocking Track in Pop Rock award, week of 25th of June, 2007. And the Song Back 4 More was selected as The Track Of The Day for July 28th, 2007. The song also has recieved two other awards; Feel Good Track in Pop Rock, week of 16th of July, 2007 and Rocking Track in Pop Rock, week of 2nd of July, 2007. \r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div><br/>Though very ambitious in it\'s pursuits of touring, the group\'s roots are in Portland. Chris has worked professionally with several schools in different aspects, including: admissions, student development, academic counseling, and helping to promote education. He also formerly owned and operated Synergy Music, a media production company in Gresham. \r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div><br/>Merrill has written countless songs and is looking to record and release their debut album in 2007. If you would like to know more about the band or would like to hear additional songs, please email them at info@merrillmusic.com\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=258\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Merrill\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1092,1337,'MeLoud',1,16,'myspace.com/meloudbandmkd','Marsal Tito 4-2/6','38971261846','<br/>The band \"Meloud\" was founded this year&nbsp;in Macedonia. The title \"Insomnia\" is our first recorded song wich, if well accepted, will be followed by others in the similar style. We plan to record the next songs in English too. We have 5 members in the band playing together for the first time, and who, prior to being part of MeLoud, were part of other bands and have great experience in live performances.&nbsp;We are very much interested in cooperation with a foreign publisher that would back us in fulfilling our aim which is to record and release an album in both English and Macedonian.<br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=251\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Meloud\'s fans</span></a>',1,'',0,''),(2506,1000347,'c',1,14,'','1160 franklin avenue','7656471249','',0,'',0,''),(2507,1000348,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2508,1000352,'The Six fingers',1,70,'http://www.myspace.com/thesixfingers','Lilas #257,  Col. Magnolias,      \" Apodaca, N.L.\", Mexico.','(044)8116129829','<strong>The Six Fingers formed in Monterrey, Mexico in the middle of 2007 by Marth and Aleco, they met at FAV college while Marth was recording the &quot;Rainbow Road EP&quot; in his home studio, thats when they decided to make a band,The Six Fingers name came out by &quot;no reason&quot;. </strong><strong>\r\n<p>\r\n<strong>The sound of The Six Fingers it..s a mix by the influence of many genres like the old Psychedelic Rock, Progressive Rock, New Wave, Pop and the later Indie. \r\n<p>\r\n<strong>The current EP from the band &quot;Rainbow Road&quot; has been recorded in Marth&rsquo;s home studio and could possibly be re-recorded in the future with better quality and much better sound. The band it..s now working on a different sound to release a new EP or possibly a complete album soon by this year (2008). </strong>\r\n</p>\r\n</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n</strong>\r\n',1,'Marth - Vocal/Guitar<br />\r\nAleco - Bass<br />\r\nAcid - Keyboard<br 