aspects that\r\nreflect on the visions of life as a being or in groups focusing on\r\nthings in reality that are not only forms of mind nor physical, but\r\nshowing that the negative neutral, and positive things in our lives can\r\nbe used to create this form of love we five take part in...<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe are products of our own environments therefore we strive to inject\r\nfive distinct personalities into songs we hope will take our listeners\r\non an epic journey into themselves. Often trying but never trivial the\r\ncomposition process tends to run rather smoothly as we are tasked into\r\ntouching those areas of our audience&#39;s psyches they didn&#39;t know existed.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWith members from extremely varied backgrounds and influences our band\r\nis proud to produce music with far-reaching impact and appeal - at\r\nleast that&#39;s our intent.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe invite you to delve into that which we ourselves are still trying to\r\ndiscover. Come with us as we explore the depths of our soul&#39;s\r\nexistence...&quot; (Jam)<br />\r\n<br />\r\nsoul eXistence began on December 16, 2002 and debuted with all five\r\ncurrent members in Bullhead City Arizona on January 17th 2004.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nsoul eXistence has a catalogue of more than 30 original songs.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe are currently looking for a vocalist. If anyone is interested please e-mail me at matt@soulexistence.com. Thanks.\r\n',1,'Matt Grosse - Lead Guitar<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLuke Portugal - Bass<br />\r\n<br />\r\nJam Arnold - Rhythm Guitar<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBilly Pippin - Drums\r\n',0,''),(1104,1354,'Killinoise',7,82,'myspace.com/killinoise420','420 killa dr.','309-258-5053','WE are the boyz from killinoise. we sleep in caves and ditches we bang our cocks on jagged rock we\'re mean son o\'bitches....<br/>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=252\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Killinoise\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1114,1367,'The Catch Blues Band',6,106,'www.thecatchbluesband.com','2227 Eoff St. #3','304-232-2646','\r\n<p>The Catch Blues Band&#8217;s sound has been described as the \" blues with a splash of rum\" where B.B. King meets Bob Marley, with Clapton-like vocals. This mixture of genres has earned The Catch Blues Band a dedicated following in the Upper Ohio Valley since the veteran musicians formed the group in 2006. </p>\r\n<p>The four-piece band&#8217;s distinctive rhythms create an expansive sound. The interplay between Dana Burkhart&#8217;s elaborate bass lines along with the Latin-influenced percussions created by John \"J.D.\" Daner gives the music a serious depth. When added to the unmistakably blues-like raunchiness of Kevin Brosh&#8217;s organ and piano accompaniment and topped off with Mike Roeder&#8217;s distinctive vocal and guitar stylings, The Catch Blues Band will give any blues-lover that back-street blues-battle house feeling.</p>\r\n<p>On August 11<sup>th</sup> 2007, The Catch Blues Band, in conjunction with their inaugural appearance at the Heritage Music Bluesfest in Wheeling, WV, released their first CD, \" It&#8217;s Not Right\" . \"It&#8217;s Not Right\" is the brainchild of lead singer and guitarist, Mike Roeder. \"I&#8217;ve had some of these tunes simmering in my &#8216;song box&#8217; since 1996, but it was the inspiration I took from my fellow band-members that really brought it to life \", he said. Roeder said his bassist, Dana Burkhart \"Dana and I have been jamming together since I was 8 years old, in fact, he was my first guitar teacher\". All are Wheeling residents, with the exception of Brosh, who currently resides in Shadyside, Ohio. </p>\r\n<p>All ten cuts of \"It&#8217;s Not Right\" were recorded and mastered in Wheeling at Jamie Peck Productions this summer. Peck, an accomplished saxophone player, plays a \"blood and guts\" tenor solo on the CD&#8217;s final song, \"Please.\" Roeder cited many inspirations for the CD, but \"especially the music I listened to while growing up in North Wheeling &#8211; the Allman Brothers Band, Eric Clapton, Santana and Bob Marley.\"</p><br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=259\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\">Interact with The Catch Blues Band\'s fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(1115,1368,'Sam Morrison Band',1,16,'www.sammorrisonband.com','PO Box 2123','714-745-2612','<a href=\"http:///cdbaby.com/cd/sammorrison/\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Photobucket - Video and Image Hosting\" src=\"http://i63.photobucket.com/albums/h124/convalian/smbbanner.jpg\" border=\"0\"/></a> <a href=\"http://www.sammorrisonband.com\">\r\n<p><font color=\"#00ff00\" size=\"5\"><b>Sam Morrison Band</b></font> </p></a>\r\n<p>\r\n</p><p><font color=\"#a00000\" size=\"4\">\r\n<p>The Sam Morrison Band is on a mission. Tired of all the corporate, &#8220;politically correct&#8221; processed music that is being spoon fed to the public, The Sam Morrison Band is determined to bring back something that is lost on today&#8217;s radio&#8230;&#8230;real music. Imagine that; real musicians, playing real songs, with real instruments for real people. No drum loops, no DJ&#8217;s, just 100 proof Rock and Roll.<br/><br/>Steeped in the Southern Rock tradition of bands such as Lynyrd Skynyrd and the Allman Brothers, The Sam Morrison Band is proud to carry on the message of true American values. Themes such as pride in God, Country, and the American Dream run throughout their music.<br/><br/>In the current state of the world, it&#8217;s no wonder that people are looking back, remembering when things were good and longing for any reminders of the &#8220;Good Old Days&#8221;. The music of the Sam Morrison Band does just that. It reminds us of when things were good and shows the promise that things can be good again.<br/><br/>Real Songs, Real Music&#8230;&#8230;&#8230;&#8230;&#8230;The Sam Morrison Band!<br/><br/>For the past few years the SMB has been traveling around the world spreading their gospel of 100 Proof Southern Rock and Roll, playing it the way it was meant to be played, dripping with Jack Daniels and BBQ sauce! Their high energy live performances and faithful recreations of the Southern Rock Classics have won them converts everywhere they go and earned them the title of \"Harley Event Specialists\" due to the large number of \"Biker\" events they have performed for.<br/><br/>With the release of their debut <b><a href=\"http://cdbaby.com/cd/sammorrison\"><font size=\"3\">CD</font></a></b> release on Convalian Records, the SMB is enjoying the rewards of performing their own music. They have had the opportunity to play with many of today\'s biggest stars including: Lynyrd Skynyrd, 38 Special, Marshall Tucker, Diamond Rio, Confederate Railroad. Their debut single, \"I Gotta Ride\" is quickly becoming a new \"Biker Classic\"!<br/><br/>The SMB spends most of their time on the west coast, however they have completed successful tours not only in Europe but in the Far East as well. They are currently recording their second <b><a href=\"http://cdbaby.com/cd/sammorrison\"><font size=\"3\">CD</font></a></b> titled \"Dig It or Don\'t!\" and are looking forward to a 2007 release and a national U.S. Tour to follow. </p><a href=\"http://www.sammorrisonband.com\"><font size=\"4\">www.sammorrisonband.com</font></a></font>\r\n\r\n</p><p></p>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=260\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Sam Morrison Band\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1116,1369,'SACRED',7,84,'www.sacredwebsite.com','','00-34-3-3811582','<font size=\"2\">\r\n<p align=\"justify\">SACRED, band from Barcelona founded in 2000 by 4 members from other bands of the region, Uri Canalias( Voice), Jose Manuel Nu&ntilde;ez (drums), David Trujillo (bass) and JC (guitar).</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">With this formation SACRED recorded its first Demo \"HIDDEN SECRETS\", its second Demo \"SACRED\" and its first official album called BEYOND THE END OF THE WORLD (mastered in Germany by Tommy Newton, famous by mastering the Keeper of the seven Keys of Helloween) with quite good acceptance from the audience, in fact, it was distributed at an international level.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">When things seemed to be working out, JC (guitar) leaves the band because of some music discrepancies with the rest of the members.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">After a lot of castings they decided to incorporate two new guitars to the band and that is when Albert Valiente and Francesc Coloma joined SACRED, really two monsters of the six strings. This is how the band become a quintet.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">SACRED waited for a period of time to compose and also get well connected before starting the recording of their album, \"TRANSITIONS\". This second album of the band has been mastered out of our frontiers, this time in the U.S.A., at the Sterling Sound Studios of New York, looking for an up-to-date sound but never loosing their identity as a band.</p><b><u>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">DISCOGRAPHY</p></u></b><u>\r\n<dir>\r\n<dir></dir></dir></u>\r\n<dir>\r\n<dir>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">\"Transitions\" (2006) &#8211; Recorded and mixed at the B+B studios from Barcelona, mastered at the Sterling Sound, New York City</p><b>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">\"Beyond the End of the World\" (2004)</p></b>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">&#8211; Recorded at Wheel Production Studios from Barcelona , Mixed at Music Factory Studios by Christian Shmid (Germany), Mastered at Area 51 Studios by Tommy Newton (Germany)<br/><br/>www.sacredwebsite.com<br/>www.myspace.com/sacred06<br/><a href=\"http://www.goriles.multiply.com\">www.goriles.multiply.com</a></p></dir></dir></font><br/><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Somebody\'s Shaking</span><br/>\r\n\r\n<object height=\"355\" width=\"425\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/vPaImDS2OZU&rel=1\"/><param name=\"wmode\" value=\"transparent\"/><embed src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/vPaImDS2OZU&rel=1\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" wmode=\"transparent\" width=\"425\" height=\"355\"/></object>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><br/><br/><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">She</span><br/>\r\n<object height=\"355\" width=\"425\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/yR8vlZ4vkoY&rel=1\"/><param name=\"wmode\" value=\"transparent\"/><embed src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/yR8vlZ4vkoY&rel=1\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" wmode=\"transparent\" width=\"425\" height=\"355\"/></object>\r\n<br/><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><br/><br/><br/>Making of: Transitions</span><br/><object height=\"355\" width=\"425\"><embed src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/pQiN87i-yFA&rel=1\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" wmode=\"transparent\" width=\"425\" height=\"355\"/></object>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=261\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with SACRED\'s fans</span></a>',1,'',0,''),(1117,1370,'Dennis Paul',1,16,'www.dennispaul.com','','807-727-3435','\r\n<p>Of modest Canadian origins, having worked in a gold mine for 25 years and raising a family, Dennis Paul didn\'t expect to resume his music career after all that time, his first album was simply recorded as a keep sake, an expose\' of talents, for his family and closest friends.</p>\r\n<p>Dennis Paul has recently exploded onto the global stage, with sustained top artist rankings on many Indie sites and with fans that straddle all age groups and genre, since the release of his album \"Hold On\" in January 2006</p>\r\n<p>While his influences may be extremely diverse, his stylings are genuine, edgy, and driven.&nbsp; Classic / Blues Rock with his own \"unique\" twist.</p><br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=262\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\">Interact with Dennis Paul\'s fans</span></a>',0,'',0,''),(1118,1372,'CORRODED',1,14,'myspace.com/corrodedsweden','PolerarvÃƒÂ¤gen 1','+46 70 3501136','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><v id=\"_x0000_s1026\" style=\"margin-top: -17.85pt; z-index: -2; margin-left: -12pt; width: 207pt; position: absolute; height: 729pt;\" strokeweight=\"4.5pt\"><v linestyle=\"thinThick\"></v></v><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; color: black; font-family: If;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">T</span><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; color: black; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">he backbone of the band started out in the summer of 2004. The root came from a long nursed dream of Niklas Kallstrom who wanted to play the bass in a band as oppose to his regular drum beating in several other successful bands. Niklas contacted his brother Martin also a very talented drummer and his band-mate from a local metal act, riff architect Peter Sjodin. Martin and Peter had been playing together for a number of years and with Niklas they decided that the assistance of an additional guitar player/singer would be required to make the day. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; color: black; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Enter Jens Westin, guitar player and singer extraordinaire and the brew began to simmer. <br/>After a couple of jam sessions the pieces of the jigsaw started to show a picture, it was dark, it was heavy, it was angry and it looked good.&nbsp;<br/></span><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; color: black; font-family: If;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">A</span><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; color: black; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">fter writing a couple of more songs it was clear that the path of the band would be in the heritage of the heavy rock acts of the 70s with additional layers of a more modern sound. Co-lead guitar player Fredrik Westin joined the band in the fall of 2005 and the line-up was complete. The band entered the well acclaimed Studio Soundcreation in Bollnas during two weekends in late fall of 2005 to record the self financed demo-EP titled &#8220;Heart of the Machine&#8221;. &nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; color: black; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Heart of the machine received good reviews in numerous magazines and web-zines all over Europe. A selection of these reviews can be found at <a href=\"http://www.corroded.se/\">www.corroded.se</a>.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; color: black; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">During the fall of 2006, the band decided to build a demo recording studio of their own. And in early 2007, Studio Ward 22, saw the light of day for the first time.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; color: black; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; color: black; font-family: If;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">W</span><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; color: black; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">ith a pack of strong tunes the band is now back with the new demo-EP &#8220;Sessions &#8211; ward 22&#8221;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; color: black; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><v id=\"_x0000_s1027\" style=\"margin-top: 173.75pt; z-index: 2; margin-left: -4.5pt; width: 184.5pt; position: absolute; height: 90pt;\" stroked=\"f\"></v><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; color: black; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;The band is:</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; color: black; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"> CORRODED</span>\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=263\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with CORRODED\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1120,1374,'THIRTEENTH STONE',1,16,'myspace.com/thirteenthstone','529 Clinton Dr','904-955-2203','<object height=\"355\" width=\"425\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/j8sxls5IxuM&rel=1\"/><param name=\"wmode\" value=\"transparent\"/><br/><br/><br/><br/><embed src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/j8sxls5IxuM&rel=1\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" wmode=\"transparent\" height=\"355\" width=\"425\"/></object>\r\n<br/><br/>check out our new live performance at the Black Piston\'s clubhouse in Jacksonville,FL.here is the url:<br/><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j8sxls5IxuM\">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j8sxls5IxuM</a><br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=264\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with THIRTEENTH STONE\'s fans</span></a>',1,'',0,''),(1123,1380,'Highwire Fiction',1,0,'www.highwirefiction.com','','','\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"COLOR: black\">Any good work of fiction includes enough truth to be believable. <?xml:namespace prefix = o /><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"COLOR: black\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><i><span style=\"COLOR: black\">Highwire Fiction, </span></i><span style=\"COLOR: black\">based in </span><?xml:namespace prefix = st1 /><st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:city w:st=\"on\"><span style=\"COLOR: black\">Phoenix</span></st1:city><span style=\"COLOR: black\">, <st1:state w:st=\"on\">AZ</st1:state></span></st1:place><span style=\"COLOR: black\">,<i> </i>calls upon more than the classic rock \'n roll formula to portray the life experiences of its members.<span>&nbsp; </span>While often compared to piano rockers the Fray and Coldplay, the band differentiates itself with raspy vocals and methodical melodies set against hard-driving, groove-laden drumbeats and bass rifts. <span>&nbsp;</span>While the subject matter of Highwire Fiction&#8217;s songs varies in both tone and urgency, the storylines explore everything from heartbreak to hangovers to time travel. <span>&nbsp;</span>Major influences cited by the band include Kool and the Gang, Lynyrd Skynyrd, the Beatles, Jeff Buckley, specials on Miller Lite, and heartless ex-girlfriends.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"COLOR: black\"><br/>Building on their success from a series of live performances at Sugar Daddy\'s Bar and Grill in <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Scottsdale</st1:place></st1:city>, <i>Highwire Fiction </i>sought to substantiate their local presence and capitalize on the ove<st1:personname w:st=\"on\">rwh</st1:personname>elming response. <span>&nbsp;</span>By continuing to hone their live act at some of the most popular venues in <st1:city w:st=\"on\">Scottsdale</st1:city> and <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Tempe</st1:place></st1:city>, a following emerged, eager to hear more.<span>&nbsp; </span>Aside from being featured in <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Tempe</st1:place></st1:city>\'s GetOut! magazine in February of 2007, the band has headlined Martini Ranch\'s SLAM (Support Local Artists and Music), and was selected from hundreds of local bands to share a bill with national touring act the Samples at Last Exit in Tempe.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"COLOR: black\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"COLOR: black\">In the spring 2007, <i>Highwire Fiction </i>recorded and produced their debut CD, \"In a Crowded Room,\" at Illuma Studios in <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Scottsdale</st1:place></st1:city>.<span>&nbsp; </span>Since recording the CD, a fifth member, Julie Martinez (Vocals and Keyboard), has been added to the group.<span>&nbsp; </span>Julie is a featured performer at The Big Bang, a dueling piano bar in <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Tempe</st1:place></st1:city>.<br/><br/>Meet Highwire Fiction:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"COLOR: black\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in\"><span style=\"COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma\"><span>-<span style=\"FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"COLOR: black\">Founding member<b> <st1:personname w:st=\"on\">Nick Mulholland</st1:personname></b> </span><span style=\"COLOR: black\">(vocals, keyboards, guitar) began classical piano training at age six and has written songs for fifteen years. After he picked up the guitar at age eighteen, his songwriting skills took on a frenzied pace, increasing his need for a supporting cast. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in\"><span style=\"COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma\"><span>-<span style=\"FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><b><span style=\"COLOR: black\">-Ted Pyrz, </span></b><span style=\"COLOR: black\">(bass guitar), self-taught rhythm and blues player, contributes elements of funk and jazz.<span>&nbsp; </span><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in\"><span style=\"COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma\"><span>-<span style=\"FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"COLOR: black\">After several years away from his Phoenix roots, longtime guitar player <b>Jake Cunningham</b> (lead guitar) returned home and joined Highwire Fiction, bringing with him over twelve years of blues and jam rock <span>&nbsp;</span>experience. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in\"><span style=\"COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma\"><span>-<span style=\"FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><b>Nick Segall</b>, (drums), <span style=\"COLOR: black\">longtime area drummer, has post-punk roots which<span>&nbsp; </span><span>&nbsp;</span>strongly support and influence<span> the band&#8217;s growing original<i> </i></span>repertoire. <o:p></o:p></span></p><br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=265\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\">Interact with Highwire Fiction\'s fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(1130,1375,'The Brink',1,71,'www.myspace.com/friendsofthebrink','962 Salisbury Rd','6142749218','<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=266\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with The Brink\'s fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(1131,1389,'Michele Ari',1,71,'http://www.micheleari.com','','','Michele Ari is a singer/songwriter of considerable standing. She&rsquo;s one of those open and honest people who wear their hearts firmly on their sleeves in the name of their art. Her incredible debut album &lsquo;85th and Nowhere&rsquo; had not only her homeland of America enraptured, it also caused genuine excitement throughout Europe. Respected music reviewers from revered music publications had nothing but genuine praise for her debut effort. The Swedish music press described her work as &lsquo;a confident collection of songs musically reminiscent of Nick Lowe&#39;s early 80&rsquo;s sound&rsquo;. In Scotland the press mused that she &lsquo;has a capability to evoke countless emotions&rsquo; and &lsquo;an intensity of unquestionable depth&rsquo;. The career dictating London journos were impressed enough to write &lsquo;sounding like Deborah Harry did when she was at her best in the 80&rsquo;s&rsquo;. &#39;85th and Nowhere&#39; also drew this comment courtesy of the &#39;Manila Standard&#39; in the Philippines: &lsquo;probably one of the most important artists that you have not heard yet&rsquo;. These quotes, and so many others, are genuine snippets from reviews by people who have been in the business long enough to separate the wheat from the chaff. Should further evidence of Michele Ari&rsquo;s talent be needed then surely an invite to perform at London&rsquo;s International Film and Poetry Festival alongside Patti Smith, or, &lsquo;1,000 Kisses&rsquo; being named song of the year by a WMNF dj or even, the inclusion of her songs on American and European radio play lists is enough to convince anyone of her worth. Michele is a catalyst for these times. Her voice is no fluke, her talent is as natural as breathing, and her grasp of song writing is uncanny. She remains a much needed transfusion of new blood for the veins of a genre quickly running out of ideas and direction. Half the world is unaware of her existence and the other half is unable to keep the secret! Expect many &lsquo;I discovered her first&rsquo; claims when she finally strolls onto the map that will place her alongside many other luminaries of this fickle industry. Don&rsquo;t take the word of the press, or the actions of a country, find out for yourself and be privy to the worst kept secret , but the best bet for success, this music industry currently has to offer. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=267\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt\">Interact with Michele Ari&#39;s fans</span></a> \r\n',0,'',0,''),(1132,407,'Tracee Noelle',9,43,'http://www.myspace.com/traceenoelle','','310 728 9956','<p>\r\n<em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The fresh faced optimism that drew R&amp;B singer Tracee Noelle to LA&rsquo;s music scene belies the dark tales of loss and disillusionment driving her music. Currently in the studio with multi-platinum producer &amp; Cherokee Studios founder Bruce Robb, Noelle has already captured the attention of several music notables. Only months after arriving in LA she grabbed the interest of songwriter Bishop Lamont at the &ldquo;I Create Music&rdquo; ASCAP EXPO &rsquo;07.</em> \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font face=\"Times New Roman\">Before even leaving her native Toronto Noelle had succeeded in working with Canadian R&amp;B Producer Marcus Kane; garnered praise from producer Tim of Tim &amp; Bob for a performance sung at his request during their phone conversation; been a back-up vocalist for famous Canadian soul singer Andrea Henry; and been accepted as a Soprano II into the prestigious &ldquo;University of Toronto Women&rsquo;s Chorus&rdquo; opera choir. Henry took notice of the young singer remarking that her &ldquo;unique tone &amp; style&rdquo; is what makes her so special.</font></em> \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font face=\"Times New Roman\">Despite these brilliant bursts of success her personal life has been a story of poverty, struggle and the will to overcome. After her parents separated early in her life she was raised by her single working mother. After finishing school Tracee got a one way Greyhound ticket to LA. No stranger to adapting amongst the unfamiliar she bounced through rough living, shelters and hostels in the skid row of LA before finding the job she calls a God-send.</font></em> \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n<font face=\"Times New Roman\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;As richly textured as her life is, her music is all the more so. Drawing upon reggae, hip hop, R&amp;B, Blues and Classical traditions to add depth to her sound; she draws upon a true blues background to speak about the roller coaster of life that we all experience. The authenticity of her music is testified to in her life&rsquo;s story as she talks about poverty, abandonment, and darkness, balanced against tales of hope, compassion and the power of a dream to carry you through.</font></em> \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font face=\"Times New Roman\">Keep an eye on Tracee Noelle&rsquo;s career as she continues to grow in the LA live music scene and in the studio</font></em> \r\n</p>\r\n',0,'',0,''),(1133,1385,'my soul to keep',1,71,'www.showcaseyourmusic.com/mysoultokeep','7230 south west 41st court','754-264-2563','MY SOUL TO KEEP Hails as South Floridas Premiere Rock and Rollers. With the Release of thier current hit \'WAIT\" and follow up video. They have been Receiving the highest Acclaims as the \"RETURN OF ROCK\" . With MSTK\'s International lineup, Each member brings a different set of influences. Combined create the blend of unique sound of MY SOUL TO KEEP........<br/>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=268\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with my soul to keep\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1135,1390,'outshine',6,106,'www.outshinerocks.com','79 hilltop drive','631-523-8034','<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=269\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with outshine\'s fans</span></a><br/><br/>',1,'',0,''),(1136,1391,'dneri',1,71,'','','754-224-9227','<font color=\"#7f4bff\">Born Providence, RI. starting playing guitar at the age of 14, and played clubs professionally at 15, and has written jingles, commercials, movie scores and has written music for other musical acts. Currently playing in the new metal band, My Soul To Keep finishing our debut CD, and planning a tour to promote our new CD.<br/></font>',1,'',0,''),(1137,1393,'MikMorley',1,61,'www.mikmorley.com','','0423046732','<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=270\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with MikMorley\'s fans</span></a><br/>',0,'',0,''),(1138,1392,'Mindefect',1,14,'http://www.myspace.com/mindefect','','','MINDEFECT<br />\r\n&ldquo;Hard rock is the best way to describe it,&rdquo; says Mindefect of its powerhouse sound. Mindefect&rsquo;s music dodges easy genre classification, but that&rsquo;s OK &ndash; it&rsquo;s the sign of originality and creativity. The group soaks up influences from a diverse array of sources and therein lies part of the appeal of Mindefect&rsquo;s music. &ldquo;We&rsquo;re too heavy to be rock but not heavy enough to be considered today&rsquo;s metal.&rdquo; The band&rsquo;s style reaches across years of rock-n-roll territory, culling ideas from classic flavors, contemporary sounds and much of what is in-between. It&rsquo;s a rich offering of aural excitement contained in a Mindefect performance. Not content to follow the yellow line down the middle of the road, these musicians have headed off the turnpike everyone else is driving, carving their own path, marking the way for tomorrow&rsquo;s hard rockers. &ldquo;Mindefect is everything from the arena to the garage, aggressive to progressive, funky and dirty bluesy, sleazy, sensual and emotional (but not emo), trashy and refined, energetic and jaded with hooks, headaches, harmonies, hairpin turns, hammering rhythm and, most importantly, soul without pretense.&rdquo; No posing allowed; thus read the signs you see as you head into Mindefect&rsquo;s strip of the musical world. <br />\r\nPurpose<br />\r\nMusic&rsquo;s fun. Hell, yeah! It&rsquo;s party. It&rsquo;s passing the time. It&rsquo;s catharsis. It&rsquo;s great for driving. Music is many things. But ultimately, it&rsquo;s a direction, a focus for one&rsquo;s being. It applies to the die-hard music fan as well as the devoted ones who make the music for the die-hard fans. And it&rsquo;s no secret that the musicmakers are fans of the stuff themselves. Why else go into the business. (Unless it&rsquo;s just for business, in which case, the whole point has been missed and the quality will suffer. Not so Mindefect &hellip;) &ldquo;Music makes us feel alive. It gives us purpose.&rdquo; And part of finding purpose is finding identity, marking off one&rsquo;s place in the world and defending one&rsquo;s individuality. That is vital for listener and artist alike. &ldquo;Music keeps us from becoming another number in the huddled masses that works just to come home and zone out in front of the TV.&rdquo; And it&rsquo;s a funny thing. Because looking inside, finding that purpose &hellip; that&rsquo;s also the place you look to find the source of music, the source of purpose. It&rsquo;s a circle spinning always, alive, breathing, thriving. Music hits its pinnacle when it&rsquo;s a labor of love pulled out from within &ndash; not surface varnish, not music for money without art. &ldquo;Let the music write itself. Don&rsquo;t try too hard with an idea. There&rsquo;s nothing worse than music that feels or sounds forced.&rdquo; The only force here, in the realm of Mindefect, is the music itself. And it is a force to be reckoned with. <br />\r\nThe Artist at Work<br />\r\nMindefect has seen two songs tapped for broadcast on 92.7 WLSR The Laser in Illinois. The band&rsquo;s first CD &ndash; &ldquo;Build Up to the Breakdown&rdquo; &ndash; is nearing completion. &ldquo;We&rsquo;re just waiting for the final mix so we can send it off to get it pressed.&rdquo; From therein, it&rsquo;s gigging. Anytime, anywhere. Mindefect is currently working with A&amp;R Select, the world&rsquo;s leading independent artist development firm, based out of Los Angeles, CA. <br />\r\n&ldquo;Mindefect is the chestburster in &lsquo;Alien&rsquo; &ndash; to wit, the chest is genre boundaries and Mindefect is the monster.&rdquo; &ndash; A&amp;R Select<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=253\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt\">Interact with Mindefect&#39;s fans</span></a>\r\n',1,'Kirk Walters &quot;Free&quot; -- Vocals<br />\r\nBrian Glasgow -- Guitars<br />\r\nRyan Canier -- Bass<br />\r\nKris Wingo -- Drums\r\n',0,''),(1139,1397,'BLACKSOMEDAY',7,85,'WWW.JAMWAVE.COM/MADMAN28472','','910-207-4021','<br/><br/><br/><br/><object enablejsurl=\"false\" enablehref=\"false\" saveembedtags=\"true\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowscriptaccess=\"never\" allownetworking=\"internal\" data=\"http://lads.myspace.com/videos/vplayer.swf\" height=\"346\" width=\"430\">\r\n  <param name=\"allowScriptAccess\" value=\"never\"/>\r\n  <param name=\"allowNetworking\" value=\"all\"/>\r\n  <param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://lads.myspace.com/videos/vplayer.swf\"/>\r\n  <param name=\"flashvars\" value=\"m=15165913&v=2&type=video\"/>\r\n</object><br/><a href=\"http://myspacetv.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=vids.addToProfileConfirm&videoid=15165913&title=suiside\"></a><br/><object enablejsurl=\"false\" enablehref=\"false\" saveembedtags=\"true\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowscriptaccess=\"never\" allownetworking=\"internal\" data=\"http://lads.myspace.com/videos/vplayer.swf\" height=\"346\" width=\"430\">\r\n  <param name=\"allowScriptAccess\" value=\"never\"/>\r\n  <param name=\"allowNetworking\" value=\"all\"/>\r\n  <param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://lads.myspace.com/videos/vplayer.swf\"/>\r\n  <param name=\"flashvars\" value=\"m=15203533&v=2&type=video\"/>\r\n</object><br/><br/><object enablejsurl=\"false\" enablehref=\"false\" saveembedtags=\"true\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowscriptaccess=\"never\" allownetworking=\"internal\" data=\"http://lads.myspace.com/videos/vplayer.swf\" height=\"346\" width=\"430\">\r\n  <param name=\"allowScriptAccess\" value=\"never\"/>\r\n  <param name=\"allowNetworking\" value=\"all\"/>\r\n  <param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://lads.myspace.com/videos/vplayer.swf\"/>\r\n  <param name=\"flashvars\" value=\"m=15259072&v=2&type=video\"/>\r\n</object><br/><a href=\"http://myspacetv.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=vids.addToProfileConfirm&videoid=15259072&title=300%20SUISIDE%20VID\"></a><a href=\"http://myspacetv.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=vids.home\"></a>\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=254\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with BLACKSOMEDAY\'s fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(1143,1403,'midori madness',1,66,'www.myspace.com/midorimad','','','Were a three peice girl band from Mount Gambier. We write about life, love, vanity and insanity. We hope you enjoy :)<br/>MM&nbsp;xxx<br/><br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=306\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with midori madness\' fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1457,1820,'Change it to Jack',1,61,'www.changeittojack.com','','360-991-5363','Change it to Jack is a rock band formed in Portland, Oregon in late 2005. Since 2005 we have played dozens of shows in different U.S. cities to a constantly growing fan base. If you haven&#8217;t heard us yet, give these songs a listen and let us know what you think. Our message is simple &#8220;One great rock show can change the world!&#8221; Our music goes out to everyone who screams at the top of their lungs when they&#8217;re alone in their car, to those who can&#8217;t get enough of rock music, to the broken and the beat down, to the lovers, to the lonely, to the loyal and the faithful&#8230; it goes out to anyone and everyone who can find some redeeming characteristic in what we do. We hope to see you at a rock show soon. We owe all of our successes so far to our fans and friends.<br/><br/>Photos in Slideshow courtesy of:<br/>Kelsey Steele<br/>Colby Stephens<br/>Kristen Elsberg<br/>Shelly Drew<br/>Mallory Farnsworth<br/>Spencer Valadez\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=389\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Change it to Jack\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1153,1428,'MIllsyeck',1,14,'www.myspace.com/millsyeck','','07731989737','So I thought I would give it a go ,but it wasn`t easy I spent what seemed like forever trying to get the right set up together ,eventually I found my way and here I am with an album done and another on the way,I am Millsyeck a musician songwriter from Dundee Scotland have played in bands for 15 years or so,but the pursuit never stops so am out there looking for fellow disciples who share the same ideas as myself ,its just the next step and they aint geting easier ,so if you like the tunes and want to come onboard theres room here for everyone .Cheers Millsyeck. <br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=274\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\">Interact with MIllsyeck\'s fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(1147,1406,'Rebel State',1,14,'www.rebel-state.com','','','As we are a Southern Rock band, we use the confederate flag quite frequently in \r\nour image. However, a few people tend to connect it with most things we don\'t. \r\nTo us the flag stands for rebellion, rock\'n\'roll, and the Southern States. \r\nRacism is something we take far distance from. Still, as mentioned, we play \r\nSouthern Rock, and we are grown up on rock and country that comes from... The \r\nSouth. We would never give up the flag and change to something less offending, \r\n\'cause one day we might have built up a better reputation for it, and told the \r\nworld what should be connected with that red, white and blue piece of textile \r\nwith a cross and stars on it.<br/><br/>www.rebel-state.com<br/>www.myspace.com/rebelstate70s \r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=275\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Rebel State\'s fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(1149,1418,'Last Hour',1,14,'www.myspace.com/lasthour','320 Goad Cemetery Rd. E','812-783-1530','Hi we are <font style=\"background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><font color=\"#ffffff\"><strong style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Last Hour </strong></font></font>and we have been together for a few years now! We work hard at what we do and love to make not only us happy in our music but the&nbsp;fans too! This is the only thing we love to do \"ROCKIN OUT\" and making music! We have around <u>15 originals</u> and many cover songs! Hope you like us! *peace and love*<br/><br/>- Last Hour\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=276\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Last Hour\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1150,1421,'M.A.D.I.S.O.N',1,61,'www.myspace.com/rockwithmadison','28 Wellington Road, Muxton','01952603649','',1,'',0,''),(1151,1423,'missFlag',1,61,'www.missFlag.com','','','<strong>missFlag</strong> is a Rock-Pop-Indie band from Jerusalem that creates music in English, influenced by new wave British rock music. They have now completed the creation of their debut album \'To Infinity\', which was produced by the talented and renowned L.A producer Guy Erez (The Gipsy Kings, Ryan Cabrera, \"Crash\" Soundtrack) and are ready to make their mark. <br/><br/>Within the last six months missFlag have toured twice over ten states in the US. These tours were funded by the Israeli Foreign Ministry who have chosen missFlag to represent Israeli culture and its ability to produce cutting edge western music. The reaction of the press to missFlag and their performances has been very exciting: <br/><br/><b>Jerusalem Post:</b> <i>\"With star-quality songs, stage presence and musicianship. Someday you\'ll be able to say you saw missFlag \'back when\'.\"</i> <br/><br/><b>L.A. Times:</b> <i>\"This band from Israel covers some of the same ground as Coldplay with the kind of sing-along choruses that could appeal to a large audience. Singer Ohad Eilam has an accessible sincerity and, in \"Hidden Thieves,\" when the keening guitar enters on the final chorus, providing a diversion from the center of focus (the piano) one can imagine a concert hall of swaying bodies.\"</i> <br/><br/><b>Boston Globe:</b> <i>\"missFlag brings a beautifully shambling sensibility to the epic chord changes and winsome melodies.\"</i> <br/><br/>The band has been receiving extraordinarily positive feedback from the international music industry since they completed the recording of their debut album: <br/><br/>* Nic Harcourt, the renowned DJ from KCRW who is known for breaking new acts in the US such as Coldplay and Dido, has been playing missFlag\'s song \'Hidden Thieves\' regularly on his radio show \"Morning Become Eclectic\", and has invited the band to perform live on his show on September 17th 2007. <br/><br/>* Universal Records invited missFlag to LA for a private showcase. <br/><br/>* CBS have placed their request to use two of missFlag\'s songs on the credits of their famous TV series CSI NY and CSI Miami. <br/><br/>* missFlag are now in the final stage of the big MTV competition \"Impossible is Nothing\". <br/><br/>* missFlag have been invited to perform a special show at the VIP Lounge of the well-known AFI Film Festival in Hollywood. <br/><br/>* On MySpace (the world\'s biggest and most influential international music website), the band has achieved great success, boasting tens of thousands of fans and hundreds of thousands of plays to date, and as such, missFlag are MySpace\'s biggest Israeli band. <br/><br/>Dedicated and determined to become the first Israeli band to reach widespread international recognition, missFlag continue to make huge progress and also blaze trails on the Internet, even though they are currently completely independent with no record label or other funding organization standing behind them.\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=278\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with missFlag\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1148,1415,'Tobacco Mosaic',1,14,'www.tobaccomosaic.com','','','The thick, guitar driven sound of Tobacco Mosaic is pushed to extremes by loud Les Pauls\r\nand mighty Marshall cabinets alongside a tight double bass drum and a\r\nthunderous low-end bass.&nbsp; All of this with the mighty roar of a melodic\r\nlead vocal.<br/><br/>Tobacco Mosaic began years ago in the mountains of West Virginia.&nbsp; Frankie Price, a research scientist unhappy with his surroundings, packed up his vision along with his guitars and moved to Boston with hopes of finding the best players to join his band and expanding his musical knowledge.&nbsp; <br/><br/>After attending Berklee College of Music, Frankie moved to New York City and now the time has come for the latest phase of the band.&nbsp; We are currently writing new material for our 8th and upcoming album.&nbsp; <br/><br/>Tobacco Mosaic has been heavily influenced by monumental bands such as Black Sabbath, The Beatles, Led Zeppelin, Pantera, Dream Theater, Lamb of God, Stevie Ray Vaughan, Prince, Guns N\' Roses, Eric Clapton, Motley Crue, Black Label Society, Van Halen, and AC/DC to name a few..<br/>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=279\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Tobacco Mosaic\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1155,1430,'Peter Moon Band',1,16,'petermoon.com','317 pullen ave','615 650 8615','<font size=\"3\">The Peter Moon Band is kinda like Train, Tom Petty & Sublime road trippin\' with the Dahlai Lama...Otis Redding is driving the bus.</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font size=\"2\"> <em>Dave Bartley WKXD FM</em></font><br/><br/><font size=\"3\">Singer / songwriter Peter Moon, drummer Jon Zoog and bassist \"Jumpin\' \" Jack Hartford are working hard to reach fans from every walk of life. Over the past year, they\'ve built a reputation as a great live act at clubs, colleges and casinos; opened for Grammy-winning pop stars and outlaw-country legends; and forged a classic yet contemporary Rock & Roll sound that is winning over music audiences throughout the Southeast.<br/><br/>With 3 original cds and over 6 hours of covers in multiple styles, the PMB can rock the house for any crowd!<br/><br/>This band straight up ROCKS!!!&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><font size=\"2\">Alan Blankenship, concert promoter & founder Skullbone Music Park</font></em></font> <br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=281\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\">Interact with Peter Moon Band\'s fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(1159,1434,'TOP JOHNNY!',1,16,'http://www.topjohnny.com','','','<p style=\"margin: 0pt\">\r\nEvery once in a while, a rock n&#39; roll band arrives with the nerve, ambition, and confidence to do something different, ambitious and wildly intriguing. That band is TOP JOHNNY! \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0pt\">\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0pt\">\r\nIt is no secret that people in the music industry are infatuated with labels. They want to neatly classify different types of music, putting all of it in little organized folders somewhere on a musical shelf. TOP JOHNNY!, however, is a band that would drive all of these label-crazed people up the wall. They are quickly developing a reputation as one of Montreal&#39;s most interesting acts by offering something new and innovative to audiences who are accustomed to the sometimes formulaic brand of today&#39;s rock. They are an all-original, high-intensity party band whose sound is forged from a blend of searing rock guitar riffs, catchy vocal hooks, and pile-driving dance beats. \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0pt\">\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0pt\">\r\nSounding as though KISS, C&amp;C Music Factory, Metallica, and Public Enemy befriended each other, TOP JOHNNY! is fronted by the magnetic TJ Star. The always intriguing singer claims that his concept of the band formed several years ago: &quot;I was always blown away by the energy and detail that bands like KISS put into their show. I guess TOP JOHNNY! became our way of doing more and giving more than most bands think is necessary.&quot; The band is receiving rave reviews for their immense wall of sound, which features TJ Star&#39;s powerful vocals and lead guitar, hard rockin&rsquo; bassist KARO, drummer Marc holding down a solid rhythm section while virtuoso guitarist Adam Pietrykowski adds yet another layer to the band&#39;s monumental soundscape. . \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0pt\">\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0pt\">\r\nTOP JOHNNY! want to be defined by their live shows. Theirs is a live performance which epitomizes energy and unpredictability with TJ Star regularly going out into the crowd to play his wailing lead guitar solos so he can get up close and personal with his fans. He and the band are fully committed to connecting with their audience: &quot;I am not in this business to show people what a clever boy I am, but to connect with our audience...hopefully with millions of people worldwide!&quot; \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0pt\">\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0pt\">\r\nIn an industry laced with deviant and degrading images and ideas, TOP JOHNNY! want to prove that rock n&#39; roll can be &quot;edgy and fresh without having to use profanity or crooked sexuality to get our point across&rdquo;. Already offering a live show and sound that is totally unique, this attitude further distinguishes TOP JOHNNY! from the rest of the crowd. \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0pt\">\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0pt\">\r\nTOP JOHNNY! share a common vision for what they are doing. They all believe in a strong code of business ethics, and the band actively supports ecological values. The band gives 10% of all their concert and CD sales to the Planet Alert! Foundation, a non-profit organization formed to fund globally recognized projects which have the best chance of achieving lasting solutions to our planet&#39;s ecological and humanitarian problems. Front man TJ Star&#39;s desire to positively impact people stems from his initial encounter with rock music. Upon hearing KISS for the first time, he realized that &quot;the band gave me something to hope for, something to look forward to. It kept me out of trouble and in the end gave me a ton of self-confidence. I hope one day my music will also inspire a young person to pick up a guitar instead of a gun.&quot; \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0pt\">\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0pt\">\r\nCoupled with the band&#39;s highly energized music, striking costumes, and creative choreography, this willingness to make a difference is further proof that TOP JOHNNY! are destined to make a name for themselves in modern rock. \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0pt\">\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<h5><font face=\"Trebuchet MS\">TOP JOHNNY! </font><font face=\"Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Sans-serif\">is the brainchild of triple-threat (composer, performer and co-producer) </font><font face=\"font-family:Copperplate Gothic Bold,Trebuchet MS\" size=\"2\">TJ Star</font><font face=\"font-family:Copperplate Gothic Bold,Trebuchet MS\"> </font><font face=\"Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Sans-serif\">and his long time collaborator and co-producer </font><font face=\"font-family:Copperplate Gothic Bold,Trebuchet MS\" size=\"2\">Mr. Positive(+)</font><font face=\"Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Sans-serif\">&nbsp;and is produced by </font><font face=\"font-family:Copperplate Gothic Bold,Trebuchet MS\" size=\"2\">StarBrite Productions</font>, <font face=\"Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Sans-serif\">Montreal, Canada</font>.</h5>\r\n<h6 style=\"font-weight: normal; color: #000000\"><font size=\"3\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\"><font face=\"font-family:Copperplate Gothic Bold,Trebuchet MS\" size=\"5\">TOP JOHNNY!&nbsp; BAND MEMBERS</font>:</font></font></h6>\r\n<h5>&nbsp;TJ STAR (lead vocals,&nbsp;guitars &amp; synths) </h5>\r\n<h5>KARO (bass, backing vocals) </h5>\r\n<h5>ADAM PIETRYKOWSKI&nbsp;(guitars, backing vocals) </h5>\r\n<h5>MARC PREVOST(drums)</h5>\r\n<h5>Mr. POSITIVE(+) (aka &ldquo;MR.P(+)&rdquo;) (tambourine, band manager)</h5><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=282\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt\">Interact with TOP JOHNNY!&#39;s fans</span></a>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1167,1448,'Love Dog',1,69,'www.lovedogmusic.com','','','<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"2\">One of our local favorites from right here in Colorado Springs, Colorado. &nbsp;For the last one and a half years Love <br/>Dog has been gracing us with over 40 of their own original songs. &nbsp;In the past 12 months they have performed <br/>more than 50 shows, and at each show they bring that energy that only Love Dog can supply.<br/><br/>With an acoustic rock feel, it&#8217;s hard to place a label on what type of music Love Dog brings to us, but I can tell <br/>you, their songs will be heard on at least 6 of our local stations, that is how versatile the music is. &nbsp;Jason is <br/>known for his original music but doesn\'t mind playing some cover tunes from artists like Johnny Cash, Seether, <br/>Nirvana, Cake, and Lynyrd Skynyrd to name a few...Love Dog is so easy to listen to, even your mom will like it!<br/><br/>In October of 2006, Love Dog released a 11 song CD titled &#8220;Letters to Myself&#8221; which sold out it&#8217;s first pressing of <br/>100 copies within the first month. &nbsp;Love Dog&#8217;s commitment to themselves and their audience is borne out of their <br/>desire to perform. &nbsp;From local bars to the Limelight in Austin, Love Dog &#8220;puts on one of the most exciting live <br/>performance of any band today.&#8221;<br/><br/>So don\'t miss your chance to see this upcoming artist and hurry to his next show! &nbsp;See you there!!!</font><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=285\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Love Dog\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1171,1457,'Me Versus',1,71,'www.meversus.co.uk','','','<a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=287\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\">Interact with Me Versus\' fans<br/></span></a><br/>\r\n<h3><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial\">This is your new direction.&nbsp; Our future lies not with regulation, chastity and idleness but with aggression, procreation and movement.&nbsp; Notions that all contribute to the music and style of Me Versus. \r\n<p>Driven by the energy and passion of such English bands that blur the line between &#8216;mainstream&#8217; and &#8216;underground&#8217;.&nbsp; Your distortion guitar,&nbsp; this deep throat bass,&nbsp; lyrically obsessive, poetry to be over analysed and misconstrued , &nbsp;a modern shift between indie beats and rock school rhythms.&nbsp; Or maybe not.</p>\r\n<h3>We are Me Versus.&nbsp; This is your new direction.</h3></span></h3>',1,'',0,''),(1174,1460,'Potion13',7,33,'http://www.potion13.org','','','<p>\r\nPOTION 13, Independent band from Montreal, Quebec.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nSo much is happening, visit our official website at <a href=\"http://www.potion13.org/\">www.potion13.org</a>&nbsp; to be up to date with all the action!\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe band is: Danielle Langlois (vocals), Brian Harps (guitar).\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nPotion 13 started in the year 2002.. Our first album &quot;Porte-bonheur&quot; (lucky charm) came out in november 2002. It was recorded at Media Musique studio in Montreal. Since then:<br />\r\n65 appearences on TV of our show (recorded nov. 2005) at the Metropolis.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nMore than 250 radio shows have played our songs. More than 300 websites host an artist page for our band, more than 350 host our MP3, so many have a link towards potion13.org, all that leaded to over 1,000,000 downloads of our mp3, all over the net, all over the globe.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nOur songs were on more than 100 charts grabbing first position on many of them.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n2 interviews on radio, one on Radio-Canada and one on CISM.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nAn interview for UrbaniaTV on TV5 World, One on Bande a part tv. Our music was featured on BikerTV season 3.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nWe made the front page of Revue On roule, Les Nouvelles de l&#39;Est and Journal de Rosemont.. More than 11 interviews (news papers, zines...) more than 15 supers reviews of our album Porte-bonheur that is distributed in Germany and also available in many Montreal stores like FreesonRock and on the net.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n26 shows, one with the Gala BoxeRock, in the sold-out Metropolis, one at the Molson Park, where, 5,000 people were &quot;quebecoitiser&quot; celebrating the Fete nationale de la St-Jean, The Freedom party, ...These shows attracted thousand of people. That made possible 4 supers nice reviews of our shows, one on Quebecpop.com.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThanks to all of you that helped us, from near or from far, in the rising of Potion 13. We, sincerely, appreciate it!!!\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nVERSION FRAN&Ccedil;AISE:\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nPOTION 13, groupe ind&eacute;pendant de rock lourd qu&eacute;b&eacute;cois!!! \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nLe groupe est compos&eacute; de Danielle Langlois (voix), Brian Harps (guitare).\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nLe groupe f&ucirc;t fond&eacute; en 2002. En Novembre 2002 arrive la sortie de l&#39;album Porte-bonheur, enregistr&eacute; au studio M&eacute;dia Musique &agrave; Montr&eacute;al. Depuis:\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nPlus de 65 apparitions &agrave; la t&eacute;l&eacute;vision du spectacle (enregistr&eacute; en nov.2005) au M&eacute;tropolis sur Canal Vox.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nPlus de 250 &eacute;missions de radio ont jou&eacute; nos chansons. Plus de 300 sites internet affichent une page d&#39;artiste pour Potion 13, plus de 350 h&eacute;bergent nos MP3, une multitude affichent un lien vers potion13.org..., ce qui a d&eacute;coul&eacute; &agrave; plus de 1,000,000 de t&eacute;l&eacute;chargements de nos mp3, un peu partout sur la plan&egrave;te.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nLes chansons de Potion 13 sont apparues sur plus de 100 palmar&egrave;s atteignant la position 1 sur plusieurs d&#39;entre eux.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nUne entrevue t&eacute;l&eacute; pour UrbaniaTV, TV5 Monde, une avec Bande &agrave; PartTV. On peut entendre nos chansons dans l&#39;&eacute;mission BikerTV saison 3\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n2 entrevues radio, une &agrave; Radio-Canada et une &agrave; CISM.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nLe groupe a fait la &quot;une&quot; de la revue On roule, de Les Nouvelles de l&#39;Est et du Journal de Rosemont.. Plus de 11 entrevues (journaux, zines...) et plus de 15 supers belles critiques de l&#39; album Porte-bonheur qui est distribu&eacute; en Allemagne et aussi disponible &agrave; Montr&eacute;al dans plusieurs magasins dont FreesonRock et sur le net.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n26 spectacles, dont un dans le cadre du Gala BoxeRock, dans la salle comble du M&eacute;tropolis, un, au Parc Molson ou 5,000 personnes furent qu&eacute;b&eacute;coitis&eacute;es dans le cadre de la F&ecirc;te nationale de la St-Jean, Le Freedom party,...Ces spectacles ont attir&eacute; des millier de personnes, au grand plaisir de tous! Ce qui a aussi permis 4 supers bonnes critiques de nos spectacles, dont une sur Qu&eacute;becpop.com.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nRestez branch&eacute; et partagez l&#39;ascension notre groupe de rock lourd francophone ind&eacute;pendant sur la sc&egrave;ne internationale!\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nPotion 13 est un groupe professionnel et &eacute;nergique avec des accessoires et un visuel unique! Leur but premier, offrir aux spectateurs une soir&eacute;e des plus m&eacute;morables! \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nPotion 13...boisson id&eacute;ale pour une soir&eacute;e ensorcellante!!!\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nEnvo&ucirc;tement guarantie\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nUn gros merci &agrave; tous ceux qui nous ont aid&eacute;, de pr&egrave;s ou de loin, dans l&#39;ascension de notre groupe, nous appr&eacute;cions beaucoup!!!\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=288\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt\">Interact with Potion13&#39;s fans</span></a>\r\n</p>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1394,1717,'b.forry',1,66,'www.myspace.com/bforry','','','b.forry is the name of St. Charles, IL&#8217;s soon-to-be claim to fame. Churning out dark folk music from the depths of her soul, b.forry embraces life in all its glory &#8211; and shadow &#8211; and translates that into a passionate self-expression of one seeking to understand one&#8217;s place in the universe. In the process, she helps other find their niche too. Music is inspirational, even the dark stuff. Sometimes, especially the dark stuff.&nbsp;<br/><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Consumption <br/>The right artist can make music that totally squeezes out <br/>&#8220;reality&#8221; and creates a world that is totally music. One of those is b.forry. For her music is &#8220;like my physical existence ceases to exist and all there is is music.&#8221; Her soulful experience as a songwriter is passed on to the listener, who finds him- or herself swept up in a spirit-sweeping experience. And b.forry&#8217;s music is also quite entertaining.&nbsp;<br/><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; From Me <br/>According to b.forry, music for her is not so much a conscience writing experience as it is a channeling. &#8220;I don&#8217;t control it. The music comes out of me the way it wants to. I sing from the emotion. The music is my journey.&#8221; Thankfully, fans are able to take this dark trek with b.forry, exploring other universes and the deep places within themselves as b.forry does the same via her songwriting and performing.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br/><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; No Rest <br/>Music is such a passion for b.forry that she is a slave to the pen. &#8220;I&#8217;m always writing; it won&#8217;t let me sleep.&#8221; She&#8217;s already recorded one album, an unplugged set that wows every listener. And a second&nbsp; &#8220;My Fairy Tales Bk:1&#8221; has just been completed and is now available and will present to the world the stunning power of b.forry.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br/><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Old Passion <br/>Her love of music goes back a long way, b.forry says. &#8220;I tried out for chorus in high school but I never had a voice. When I was 17 I had&nbsp;an accident where my throat was crushed. It took it several years to heal and when it did, I had a voice. By that time, I had damage to my left eardrum and I&#8217;m tone deaf. I learned to sing by matching the vibrations of the guitar to the vibrations in my throat.&#8221; She is<br/>currently working with A&R Select, Hollywood&#8217;s hottest independent A&R firm.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Review <br/>&#8220;While b.forry&#8217;s music is striking enough as it is, when one realizes her challenges as a musical artist, one sees that her songs are feats of Herculean fortitude.&#8221; &#8211; A&R Select <br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=388\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\">Interact with b.forry\'s fans</span></a>',0,'',0,''),(1175,1461,'Nausia',1,72,'http://www.myspace.com/nausiauk','','','From a small town in East Anglia critics describe Nausia as \"The Guns and Roses of Great Yarmouth.\" For over five years the band has packed out nights of blood sweat and tears all over the country. After releasing there debut album in 2004 \"reality bites\" the band sparked up interest with some top record labels. After some time out the band busted back in early 2007, allready the band has recorded there second album and hit europe touring Austria and Germany!\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=341\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Nausia\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1177,1459,'Val Gray',1,69,'valdigray@yahoo.com.au','3 Isabella St Balmain','02 98105548','<body>Val Gray is a singer-songwriter-guitarist based in Sydney Australia, with a colourful and varied history of hard rock/alternative and pop bands,some enjoying radio airplay and appearing on compilation CDs. He was signed to Dolphin publishing in the 90s but the company has since disolved.\r\nCurrently he is embarking on a solo career with the aim of securing a publishing and record deal that would suit his talents.\r\n    Val is capable of writing in a number of styles which reflect his sometimes diverse musical tastes,ranging from hard rock,blues and roots, alternative pop and singer-songwriter/folk. However his main focus at the moment is a melodic acoustic style perhaps in the same ballpark as such artists as David Gray,Ryan Adams,Richard Ashcroft and Ben Harper. He is currently demoing an avalanche of new songs at home which will be culled into some listenable form in the very near future!\r\n    Val plays Guild and Takamine acoustics and Gibson and Fender electrics. He also plays bass,very average keyboards and absolutely atrocious drums.\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=293\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Valdi Gray\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n</body>',1,'',0,''),(1179,1467,'Sangre Urbana',3,20,'myspace.com/sangreurbana','','','',1,'',0,''),(1180,1468,'My Sleeping Thoughts',1,61,'www.mysleepingthoughts.piczo.com','','+447748203964','<p><strong><font color=\"#ffffff\" face=\"Tahoma\"><font color=\"#000000\">On the distant horizon, the equator divided one country musically<br/>influenced by another. Glowing. Glowing in the manifestation of a mutual<br/>dream. The one part, with an almost fully arranged instrumental.The other, with lyrics, cried melodically by the voice of an unborn entity. Seperated at birth? Conspiringly, for both had the same title.<br/><br/>Glow.<br/><br/>Five years and the planets turn patiently. For one, five members have come and gone ; for the other, five bands. Three blue sides glow in the square, but the fourth flashing red like a tumor on our scanners.The droning menace. The lady with the cards was right.<br/><br/>One last attempt on a flight abroad.<br/>One last audition could blend in accord.<br/>Finally.<br/>The quest concluded, but only just begun.<br/><br/>My Sleeping Thoughts.<br/><br/>Obscurely accessible? Popping in darkness? Technically rocking?<br/><br/>\"Glow Angel glow, on the horizon.<br/>Come to our show behind the mountain.<br/>Hosted in that place we\'ll some day go.</font>..\"</font></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=295\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with My Sleeping Thoughts\' fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1188,1478,'Nushed Kruts',7,33,'myspace.com/nushedkruts','','','<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=307\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Nushed Kruts\' fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(1189,1481,'Jon Oliva\'s Pain',7,84,'jonoliva.net','','','And so the story continues... <br/><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; As most Savatage fans already know, Jon has always been plagued with the dilemma of trying to choose which songs to put on the next Savatage record, simply because there has always been too many songs to put on 2 cds, let alone one. Between the collaborations and the material Jon writes on his own, this daunting task has often left great songs in the closet. Hence, \"Jon Oliva\'s Pain\"! The Mountain King has been stockpiling songs for many a Savatage record and some of those songs, while not appropriate for the record at hand, were destined none the less to be brought to life. <br/><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; With the break between a new Savatage recording and the current 2003 TSO tour, Jon finally had the time to pursue the goal of bringing some of those songs to life. It was clear to him from the beginning that these songs were going to be a departure from the style and sound of the Sava-records of the past, and that was truly the point. <br/>Jon took his ideas into Audio-Lab recording studios in Tampa, Florida. With the help and expertise of engineer Greg Marchak, Jon began the process of recording the first seven songs to be featured on his solo release. He recorded every instrument on these demos, with the exception of the lead guitar solos, which were laid down by Matt LaPorte. The result was a compilation of songs that has been described as a cross between John Lennon and \"old school\" Savatage. Considering the fact that Jon is a HUGE Beatles fan, that comparison is a compliment to say the least. The music is bluesy, rich and full of the aggression that only Jon Oliva can deliver. The result was a great start to a potential solo release that Jon has wanted to do for a very long time.<br/>&nbsp;<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Criss Oliva Memorial Concert was quickly approaching. Thoughts and memories of Criss are clearly evident throughout this collection of great new songs, and it was only fitting that they be debuted at Criss\' benefit concert. Fans would attend this anniversary event from Japan, Greece, Germany, Holland, Norway and a host of other countries, as well as from across the US. All would be there to pay tribute to Criss\' legacy and the music that he created with Jon and the members of Savatage both past and present. <br/><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Since Circle II Circle was already scheduled to perform, Jon quickly seized the opportunity to recruit these seasoned musicians to join him on stage to deliver this new sound and his new songs. Joining Jon on stage that night were Matt LaPorte (guitar), John Zahner (keyboards), Jason Jennings (bass), and Christopher Kinder (drums). The set would consist of 6 songs from Jon\'s solo catalog plus \"In the Dream\" from Power of the Night, \"Hey Bull Dog\" by the Beatles and a classic cover of \"Wishing Well\" by the band Free. <br/><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Memorial concert was a once in a lifetime event. Everyone in attendance (almost 1000 fans) piled into The Masquerade and prepared themselves for this historic tribute to one of the greatest guitar players of our time. An incredible show in which no words would adequately describe the energy level, would take Savatage fans on a \"walk down memory lane\" and become one for the history books...never to be repeated again. <br/><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Jon and the band took to the stage following the performance of Circle II Circle. You could feel the energy in the air and the excitement of the audience to hear something new. They would not be disappointed. The band performed as if they had been playing together for years, and frankly most of them had. Matt and Chris have been playing together for nearly 10 years and were friends with both John Zahner and Jason Jennings. The relaxed, yet aggressive, mood on stage translated Jon\'s new material perfectly to the hungry ears below. Everything went as planned and now it was time to focus on what to do with this music and its future. <br/><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Soon after the memorial show, the band members parted ways with Circle II Circle. Realizing that he had a ready-made band, Jon quickly moved in on the opportunity to bring his solo material to the masses. The band embraced the opportunity without hesitation, and brought in former Circle II Circle bass player Kevin Rothney, to solidify the line-up. Rehearsals began immediately and within 4 short weeks \'Tage Mahal was hitting the stage in the Tampa, Florida area. The set included Jon\'s solo material and more than an hour of classic Savatage, some of which had not been performed live on stage in a very long time. <br/><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Jon\'s voice has once again emerged as one of the most original and powerful voices in rock music. Response from the fans has been nothing short of exciting and the band continues to play with determined intensity. Delivering the new material as well as the old, has to be done properly and judging by the response, they\'ve done just that! <br/><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Our newest addition to the band is Shane French, through the 90\'s he played with Teer which gained him a large fan base both locally and overseas. In early 2003 He was approached by our own Matt LaPorte to join the Zak Stevens-fronted Circle II Circle. After the bands breakup we asked him to join his old bandmates to complete Jon Oliva\'s Pain. He is also currently working with Teer to release a new cd. <br/><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The future of Jon Oliva has taken on a new and profound direction. His ability to write one great song after another present boundless opportunities. Whether it is Jon Oliva\'s Pain, Savatage, TSO, or any other form, Jon\'s music will continue to flow from him... to all of you!\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=296\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Jon Oliva\'s Pain\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1195,1388,'Memory Fade',1,14,'','','','Memory Fade picks up the pieces from a genre of music where emotion is expressed through aggressiveness, and oftentimes musicianship takes the back seat to the mainstream. Formed in 2003, it was inevitable then that this combination of ability, influences and ambition would soon be making waves in the regional hard rock scene with one goal in mind, to give the fans what they want; one hell of a show. Memory Fade has been at the forefront of the hard rock scene in Richmond, VA since their inception, taking over the East Coast with an undeniable and impeccable live show, and a unique sound, a delicate balance of unforgettable melodies, commanding guitar riffs, and chest pounding grooves. Memory Fade since has performed with national recording artist such as Breaking Benjamin, Taproot, and Magna- Fi. with they first EP \"From These Ashes\" released, the reparation of rock has begun. -----<br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=308\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\">Interact with Memory Fade\'s fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(1205,1214,'Pearl Seven',1,68,'www.pearlseven.com/','Swords','','From the sleepy suburbs of north Dublin, Pearl Seven are four individuals brought together by the urge to kick ass. With their hypnotizing guitars, hyperactive drums and undeniable sex appeal we create own own unique style of dark pop-punk, drawing from our wide, mish-mash of influences including Brand New, New Found Glory, Funeral For A Friend, Blink-182 Leftover Crack, Bring Me The Horizon, Paramore and even Reel Big Fish.<br/><br/>Coming to a town near you... <br/>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=315\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Pearl Seven\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1196,952,'Gypsies Watching TV',1,105,'','Eldridge St.','','A bunch of guys playing music for a long time.\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=309\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Gypsies Watching TV\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1210,1500,'Whyjacks',1,61,'www.whyjacks.com','','','<font style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt\" face=\"Arial\" color=\"#000099\"></font>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-pagination: none; tab-stops: 28.0pt 56.0pt 84.0pt 112.0pt 140.0pt 168.0pt 196.0pt 224.0pt 3.5in 280.0pt 308.0pt 336.0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none\"><font face=\" Times, Serif\"><font face=\"Monospace\" size=\"2\"><font color=\"#000099\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Georgia\"><font face=\" Times, Serif\"><font face=\"Monospace\" size=\"2\"><font color=\"#000099\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt\"><strong><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt\"><font face=\" Times, Serif\"><font face=\"Monospace\" size=\"2\"><font color=\"#000099\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia\">Whyjacks is a Pop/Rock band from<?xml:namespace prefix = st1 ns = \"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" /><st1:place w:st=\"on\"> <st1:State w:st=\"on\">Indiana</st1:State></st1:place> whose band members include Marty Janowiak, Phil Strantz and Steve Hagan.</span></font></font></font></span>&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia\"><br/></span></span></font></font></font></span><br/><strong>Our new CD, \"Shine and be Free\", is a cd of melody driven songs and has been created to connect and entertain. At times deep and soulful, but always fun and uplifting, there is something here for everyone. <br/><br/>Our music is fused with the variety that comes from being inspired by Rock, Pop, R&B, Blues, Jazz and Classical music.<br/></strong></span></span></font></font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia\"><font face=\" Times, Serif\"><font face=\" Monospace\" color=\"#000099\"><strong><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Georgia\"><strong><font color=\"#000099\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia\">Marty Janowiak:</span></span>&nbsp;<span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Georgia\"><font face=\" Monospace\" color=\"#000099\"><strong style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia\">lead vocals,lyrics, guitar,<br/>keyboards, percussion<br/><br/></strong></font></span></font></strong></span></strong></font></font><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Georgia\"><font color=\"#000099\"><font color=\"#000099\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Georgia\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt\"><font color=\"#000099\"><font color=\"#000099\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Georgia\"><strong><font color=\"#000099\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia\">Phil Strantz:</span></span>&nbsp;<span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Georgia\"><font face=\" Monospace\" color=\"#000099\"><strong style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia\"> guitar,keyboards,&nbsp; harmonica, percussion, bacground vocals, various sounds<br/></strong></font></span></font></strong></span></span></span></span></font></font></span></span></span></span></span></span></font><font face=\" Times, Serif\"><font face=\" Monospace\"><br/></font></font></font><font face=\" Times, Serif\"><font face=\"Monospace\"><font color=\"#000099\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\"><font face=\"Monospace\"><font color=\"#000099\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Georgia\"><strong><font color=\"#000099\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia\">Steve Hagan:</span></span><font size=\"2\">&nbsp;</font><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Georgia\"><font face=\" Monospace\" color=\"#000099\"><strong style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia\">bass guitar, percussion, background vocals, engineer</strong></font></span></font></strong></span></span></span></font></font></span></span></font></font></font></span></p>\r\n<div class=\"entry\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Georgia\">\r\n<div class=\"entry\">\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2></div></span>\r\n<div class=\"entry\">&nbsp;</div></div>',1,'',0,''),(1254,1558,'Penetrecion',6,106,'www.funender.com/music/penetrecion','','','<b>Improvisational Inspiration</b><br/><br/>\r\n\r\nThe headline best describes what you are listening to... these tracks are samples of my self expression with a guitar. Not everything is all pretty and refined to the point of being sterile and for good reason... music should live and breathe, it should not be copy/pasted in a synthetic environment. Not many artists share this same vision anymore. Gone are the days of Jimi Hendrix, The Allman Brothers, and John Coltrane to name a few of the masters. Every performance by these souls was unique, the song changed on their, or the audiences, mood... This is what drew me to guitar in the first place, the emotional affect of music.\r\n<br/><br/>Hello, my name is Chris Toutwid and I am an independant musician... guitar is my tool of choice but I have done some vocals (if you can call it that) and played a little bass. Everything you hear from me with the exception of one song (Losing Time) has been recorded live with some faults/defects. If there was a guitar solo I played it start to finish or not at all.\r\n<br/><br/> \'Losing Time\' was my one attempt to make a studio recording where the song was done in parts and each part redone until I was satisfied enough (a few takes).\r\n<br/><br/>Everything is being recording in my home on my personal computer so this is certainly \'low budget\' as the software was only $80 and the computer is my gaming rig.\r\n<br/><br/>Comments are greatly appreciated as feedback from the listening audience is what we musicians can grow from, thank you for your time.',1,'',0,''),(1259,1553,'Art Of Democracy',1,66,'','','','I will add this later',1,'',0,''),(1213,1207,'The Jersey Royale',3,18,'www.thejerseyroyale.com','','','<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=318\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with The Jersey Royale\'s fans</span></a>',1,'',0,''),(1842,1901,'Fact Not Fiction',1,66,'www.factnotfictiononline.com','','706-599-0518','<font face=\"Helvetica\" color=\"#ffffff\" size=\"1\"><font color=\"#000000\">Fact Not Fiction has never been satisfied with life exactly as it appears. Coming from a small town in Georgia known better for its UFO sightings than for its music scene, it\'s natural for their songs to exude an escapist quality. Zeke Sayer&#8217;s light vocals lift away from simple acoustic strums with an eerie haze, bringing to mind the likes of Elliott Smith or Iron & Wine. Poppier tracks cleverly build catchy melodies in the vein of The Beatles and Snow Patrol. Their latest release displays new experimentation that shows, despite its retro sound, that this is the kind of band that can only move forward. <br/><br/><br/>The band began after vocalist/guitarist Zeke Sayer left his high school. &#8220;I did a lot of things that made me wide up in trouble, and one of those situations caused me to leave school,&#8221; he admits. &#8221;But I believe that everything happens for a reason, and while I was in school, I had no direction in life. It took losing something for me to have a wake up call and realize I\'d better do something with my life. So I started the band.&#8221; <br/><br/><br/>Sayer found his passion not only in playing the music, but in production. After finding the right line-up, he produced the band&#8217;s debut \"Conversations With Eyes Closed\" album in a renovated mobile home. Some of the music from this album has even appeared on the soundtrack for indie film The Philosopher. <br/><br/><br/>In 2007, Fact Not Fiction began recording their second album, A Corporate Calling, with Jon Bryant on guitar, Justin Vickery on bass, and Adam Grant on drums. Unfortunately, time constraints led Vickery to leave the band before the album was finished, and Tyler Glenn took over for the rest of recording. The album leaves behind the more somber and somnambulant mood of their first, with the rockabilly-esque &#8220;Powder Bag&#8221; to saccharine love tale &#8220;The Ballad of Jack and Amy.&#8221; Before the album&#8217;s official release, &#8220;Electric City,&#8221; was already chosen to be the official city song of Anderson, SC.<br/><br/><br/>In addition to playing shows from rural Hartwell, GA to indie oasis Athens, GA to a festival in front of hundreds in Anderson, SC, Fact Not Fiction has assembled a solid online fan base. Critical acclaim and fans have all spoken: Fact Not Fiction is a must-listen band for this year and the next. <br/><br/><br/><br/>--Pauline Diaz, 2007</font> </font>',1,'',0,''),(1214,1503,'Metalllama',1,14,'www.myspace.com/metalllamarules','','','METALLLAMA One day this band will Rock In Rio, but for now, this rockin trio; \"METALLLAMA\", is a new rock n roll band from Hamilton, Ontario Canada. They are a three piece band who have only been a full band for about nine months, but have already done so much in the time provided. They&#8217;ve played several live shows; they&#8217;ve been featured on two different radio stations within a week, and have recorded their long awaited, 12 song, studio album &#8220;Drown Out The World&#8221;. The band consists of Joe Towers on lead guitar and lead vocals, Sean &#8220;Seabass&#8221; Kopal on the bass guitar, and P.J. Reynolds on the drums. They are three very good friends who are all musically connected with each other from playing together in separate bands and projects in past times. Each member already possess loads of studio and live stage experience, great passion, larger-than-life aspirations, positive mental attitude, strong unity, and most of all&#8230;A dream. &#8220;METALLLAMA&#8221; always promises to give their heart, mind, body and soul to make the best music they possibly can and entertain their audiences for assurance that everyone who listens to their music or comes out to see their shows always gets their time and money&#8217;s worth and nothing less, something that they&#8217;ll always guarantee. &#8220;METALLLAMA&#8221; would also like to personally thank everyone who has been supportive of their musical endeavors thus far and for future &#8220;METALLLAMA&#8221; heads as well, without the love, support and energy, &#8220;METALLLAMA&#8221; cannot exist, so with that being said&#8230;&#8221;Thank you all and rock on!&#8221; <br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=319\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\">Interact with Metalllama\'s fans</span></a>',1,'',0,''),(1222,1515,'Escariot',1,68,'www.myspace.com/escariotrock','Swords','','Escariot are a three piece Pop-punk/emo band from Dublin. They go together origionally 6 years ago in a different band (Pyros) through there nutual love for honest, well written Punk rock. The band decided to go their seperate ways due to personal reasons.\r\nAfter a two year gap, and several line up changes, the band decided to give it another go. They had found a new Passion for music due to certain side projects that were happening, but it just didn\'t feel right being in other bands, it didn\'t click like it did before.\r\nSo to acompany the new love for writing music, the band decided to rename themselves, to match the change.\r\nEscariot was born.\r\nAfter writing several songs and doing numerous gigs all over Ireland, Escariot thought it was time to record their debut E.P,\r\n\"One For Sorrow\".\r\nThe E.P is due for release independantly in late autumn on the indie Irish label, \"Jolly Rogers Records\".\r\nThe Current Escariot Line up is:<p></p>\r\n\r\nKrustovski - Bass <p></p>\r\n\r\nBunty - drums <p></p>\r\n\r\nJustin - Guitars/Vocals\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=320\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Escariot\'s fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(1226,1516,'Pascal Labillois',1,15,'www.pascallabillois.com','','416-873-5686','<span style=\"font-family: Tahoma; font-size: 8pt; color: rgb(153, 51, 0);\">Pascal Labillois - Singer, Songwriter & Guitarist <br/> <br/> It\'s\r\nbeen said that every artist is a link in a chain. Pascal Labillois was\r\ninfluenced by Melissa Etheridge, who adored Bruce Springsteen, who\r\nfollowed Woody Guthrie. Each of these artists has explored the lives of\r\neveryday, ordinary people, expressing their kinship through a\r\nroots-rock sound and strong, pop vocals. Labillois continues that\r\ntradition. <br/> <br/> The Quebec native first picked up a guitar at the\r\nage of 12, began writing songs at 14 and decided to fully pursue music\r\nat 17. He spent the next years traveling &#8211; Labillois performed in bars\r\nand clubs across Canada and jammed with George Strait&#8217;s band in Texas.\r\nThe life of a nomad &#8220;got me in a bit of trouble,&#8221; he says, &#8220;but I got\r\ngreat songs out of it. <br/> <br/>Labillois&#8217; first collection of his\r\nemotional, autobiographical songs, The Road to Yourself, earned him new\r\nfans in the US, Europe and Australia. Labillois had moved to Toronto\r\nand discovered a new creative path by performing with and producing\r\nalbums for other bands and singers. <br/> <br/>After another round of\r\ntravels &#8211; during which he toured the southern US states, learning\r\ncountry in Nashville and playing the blues in Memphis &#8211; Labillois began\r\nworking on new projects in 2006. Joined by Juno Award-winning guitarist\r\nWendell Ferguson and top Toronto drummer Gary Craig, Labillois crafted\r\nnew songs like &#8220;I Belong with you,&#8221; &#8220;Spring Rains&#8221; and &#8220;Burn&#8221; &#8211;\r\ntogether with his collaborators, Canadian music veteran Doug Blais and\r\nbrilliant engineers Michael &#8220;Dullboy&#8221; Langford. <br/> <br/> Labillois is\r\ncurrently recording his new album with Producer Brian Gagnon and\r\npromises a new CD in 2007 featuring his unashamedly-heartfelt lyrics, a\r\nmore acoustic-rock sound and &#8220;a few surprises.&#8221; The &#8216;road to himself&#8217;\r\nis now set to lead further ahead than ever before, as Labillois\r\ncontinues making music that celebrates Canada&#8217;s rich heritage, gifted\r\ntalents and ordinary heroic people.</span>\r\n\r\n<br /><br /><a target = \"_blank\"href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=321\"><span style=\"font-size:8pt;\">Interact with Pascal Labillois\' fans</span></a><br />\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1230,1520,'LOGAN 5',1,14,'wwww.logan5.ca','','','<span class=\"epktxt\">LOGAN 5 feels it\'s time to get our message out\r\nthere. We love to hear music that has high energy injected into it,\r\nsolid grooves and big fat raunchy guitar riffs. Top it off with a cool\r\nmelody that dares to stick with you.<br/>So enough with all this\r\n\"sweetened polished off radio friendly crap\". Get down to the basics\r\nand put out the \"raw\" power that we are all craving in music these\r\ndays. That\'s what we\'re trying to do<br/><br/>LOGAN 5 is a 4 piece unit based out of Toronto<br/><br/>Formed\r\nin 2003 Cam, Dave and Logan started out as a 3 piece/3 chord wonder who\r\nshared a love of hard music with an edge. During the heyday of early\r\nalternative modern rock forged a fire within the hearts of this trio.\r\nLooking to add the final piece of our hard and heavy puzzle, Logan had\r\nreconnected with a high school chum (Ray) that had also been a band\r\nmate in an outfit \"The Urge\"<br/>This union had launched our desire to write music with a solid foundation in \"groove\" and layer melody in a tasteful way.</span>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=322\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with LOGAN 5\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1234,1527,'Promise to Burn',1,71,'www.myspace.com/promisetoburn','','','<span class=\"epktxt\">Quickly becoming one of the most popular modern\r\nrock bands in the Midwest, Promise to Burn is defined by a distinctive\r\nsound born from combining extremely cohesive live performances with a\r\nvocalist who demands the listeners\' immediate attention with his\r\ninimitable voice and presence. <br/><br/>Promise to Burn as an original act began in 2004\r\nwhen they shifted all their focus to songwriting for a period of nearly\r\ntwo years. Another local musician took an interest in\r\nthe band and took their extensive catalog of original songs to his old\r\nfriend, Malcolm Springer. Malcolm happened to be one of the most\r\ntalented rock producers on the planet. Springer\'s credits are quite\r\nimpressive having engineered and produced countless major acts such as:\r\nMatchbox Twenty, Collective Soul, Fear Factory, Faith Hill, and the\r\nmultiplatinum Spiderman Soundtrack. Malcolm was also single-handedly\r\nresponsible for discovering, producing, co-writing with two very\r\nsuccessful bands: Full Devil Jacket, and the Grammy-nominated\r\nGreenwheel.<br/><br/>After an impromptu live tryout, Malcolm was quickly\r\nimpressed with the band\'s songwriting, work ethic, and potential.\r\nPromise to Burn immediately began pre-production with Springer within\r\ntwo weeks of the tryout in early 2006. By the end of April, the songs\r\nwere mixed at SoundStage Studios in Nashville. The debut EP, And\r\nEverything After, was released two months later.<br/><br/>After the\r\nrelease of the EP, Promise to Burn quickly developed a huge online\r\nfollowing while becoming a regional favorite in the Midwest through\r\ntheir live performances. The group has experience performing in\r\ncountless regional shows as well as headlining the world-famous Viper\r\nRoom and the Plush Lounge in Los Angeles, as well as headlining 12th\r\n& Porter in Nashville. The group has gathered various media\r\nattention in the Midwest by regional newspapers, radio stations, and\r\ntelevision news programs. The group has also warranted national\r\nattention when they had a rehearsal and interview filmed for Fox\'s\r\nAmerican Idol program in 2006 after lead singer, Heath Hartwell, made\r\nit to the late rounds in his first attempt to be the next American Idol.<br/><br/>In\r\nthe last few months, Promise to Burn has been playing a variety of\r\nregional shows where they played mix several well-known cover songs\r\nwith their growing collection of originals. To spice up their live\r\nperformances, Promise to Burn went to an extreme measure: they decided\r\nto let their alter-egos, an 80\'s glam metal group called Blind Lion,\r\nperform at many of their shows. Claiming to be the comeback of a hair\r\nband that dates back to 1983 (who composed every successful rock hit of\r\nthe 1980\'s), Blind Lion\'s delusions are a bit far-fetched. However\r\nthose delusions combined with the 1980\'s hair, attitudes, attire, and\r\npersona\'s transform a normal modern rock concert into a high-energy,\r\nunforgettable party that is guaranteed to entertain.</span>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=323\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Promise to Burn\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(2199,2357,'Balck Powder Revival',1,105,'reverbnation/blackpowderrevival.com','1913 n Banks','806-440-2273','Formed in may 2007. Power trio. Influences are anything southern, traditional blues, Zakk Wylde. Gigs are limited to festivals, big shows. We do not play clubs or bars!!!!!!! Mainly write and record.Lead guitar and vocals-Richard Spence, Bass and vocals-Ian Jones, Drums and percussion-Brian Bridwell.<br/>Contact richard @ <a href=\"mailto:rds7070@hotmail.com\">rds7070@hotmail.com</a>.',1,'',0,''),(1274,1530,'Perfectly Normal Beasts',1,17,'www.myspace.com/perfectlynormalbeasts','','0049-08445-928869','\r\n<h1 style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Sydnie; text-decoration: none;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; color: black; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"></span></span>&nbsp;</p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; color: black; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"></span></span></span></span></h1>\r\n<h1 style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Sydnie; text-decoration: none;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"></span></h1>\r\n<h1 style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Sydnie;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><u><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Perfectly Normal Beasts<o:p></o:p></font></u></span></h1>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; color: black; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; color: black; font-family: Verdana;\" lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Sydnie; text-decoration: none;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">The four beasts, who have strong inclinations towards understatement, irony and rib-knit underwear, are 75% german and 25% danish breed.<br/>With two lead-singers, lots of guitars and a solid, at times even furious rhythm-section, they create the characteristic pnb-sound.<br/>As the german language is excellent for speaking but not exactly the smoothest for singing whereas the english language has proved to be consequent upon the opposite, their song-lyrics are english, the humor danish, the (mens) hairstyle german and the guitars international. <br/>Makes sense, doesn\'t it? <o:p></o:p></font></span></p>\r\n<h1 style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Sydnie; text-decoration: none;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\"><br/>The band-members got together in 1996. <o:p></o:p></font></span></h1>\r\n<h1 style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Sydnie; text-decoration: none;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Since then, they\'ve played numerous concerts &#8211; almost everything from private parties and small club-gigs to live radio-broadcasting and big Open-Airs.<o:p></o:p></font></span></h1>\r\n<h1 style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Sydnie; text-decoration: none;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">They\'ve blown the capacity of several hard-discs with their song-files. <o:p></o:p></font></span></h1>\r\n<h1 style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Sydnie; text-decoration: none;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">But an album had to be made, - it wasn\'t easy choosing the songs from the many recordings of different styles. But at long last, in 2006 their constant work resulted in the album \"Not Naked Enough\".<o:p></o:p></font></span></h1>\r\n<h1 style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Sydnie; text-decoration: none;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">They are currently working on a follow-up, - the direction it is taking right now has a more acoustic character than the first album, - but who knows?!<span>&nbsp; </span><o:p></o:p></font></span></h1>\r\n<h1 style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Sydnie; text-decoration: none;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Anything can happen!<o:p></o:p></font></span></h1>\r\n<h1 style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Sydnie;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></font></span></h1><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Sydnie; text-decoration: none;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">\r\n<h1 style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Sydnie; text-decoration: none;\" lang=\"EN-GB\"></span></h1></span>\r\n<h1 style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><o:p></o:p></h1></span>\r\n<h1 style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;\">&nbsp;</h1><br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=324\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Perfectly Normal Beasts\' fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(1285,1589,'Nautcal Twilight',1,71,'http://www.myspace.com/asbill','','936-652-0508','Lead singer Doug Chumley is 26 and is currently an English teacher at Alto ISD. Bassist BJ Yates is 22 and attends college at Texas A&amp;M. Drummer Nathan Yates is 19 and also attends Texas A&amp;M. Guitarist Ethan Yates is 17 and attends Douglass High School. --------------------- Nautical Twilight started playing music together in 2003. Throughout childhood, Doug would often visit his grandparents in Douglass, Texas where he there met the Yates brothers. Little did they know that Doug would later move to the area and the four would begin spending time together. All four members were competitive runners and began training together. The time spent together led them to find their common interest in music. Since then, the band has written original songs and also became versatile by playing for a wide variety of audiences ranging from Sunday Morning Worship Services to Rock Concerts at Youth Lock-Ins and Coffee Houses in numerous places. ---------------------------------- &quot;What is Nautical Twilight?&quot; The name comes from a meteorological term that describes a time when visibility is very bad. When a ship is sailing on the ocean and the sun is almost completely set but not quite. The sailors can&#39;t see anything around them. The horizon becomes invisible and the navigational stars are only beginning to come out. ----------------- This name was chosen because there are times in life when direction is hard to find and it is easy to feel abandoned and desperate. But the Lord has said that He will never leave us. All throughout the Bible and in our own lives we can see that the Lord has given us His promises and that He is always faithful to keep them. Faith is being sure of what we hope for in the evidence of what we don&#39;t see(Hebrews 11:1). Faith comes from hearing the Lord&#39;s word(Romans 10:17). Even in the times we can&#39;t see, we know that the Lord&#39;s word is real. Check us out on purevolume! www.purevolume.com/nauticaltwilight \r\n',1,'Doug Chumley- Lead Vocals/Rythm Guitar<br />\r\nNathan Yates- Drums<br />\r\nEthan Yates- Guitar/ Vocals<br />\r\nBJ Yates- Bass\r\n',0,''),(1289,1596,'Vlad in Tears',7,36,'','','','<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=325\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Vlad in Tears\' fans</span></a><br/>',1,'',0,''),(1290,1597,'Ninja Dolls',1,68,'','','','Ninja Dolls was formed summer of 2001 by two very bored girls. Emma\r\nNorling on bass and Jenny Forsberg on drums. The young Victoria Holden\r\n(fourteen going on fifteen) joined the band soon after and Ninja Dolls\r\nhad now a voice. Jonas Asplind played the guitar while they were\r\nlooking for a girl guitarist, no girl guitarist was found and Jonas was\r\nasked to join the band on permanent bases. Jenny F lost interest and\r\nwas replaced by another Jenny, Jenny Juhlin. <br/><br/>\r\nBy now Ninja Dolls were in full swing with a bunch of own produced\r\nmaterials. Their first demo CD De e h&aring;rdrock det was recorded in March\r\n2002 followed in June the same year by the second demo CD Go were the\r\naction is. Ninja Dolls did now a string of live performances in and\r\naround their hometown Falun in Sweden. After all this time with a bunch\r\nof people on second guitar, they felt that they needed to add a\r\npermanent guitarist. Martin Djuse became a member in Ninja Dolls in the\r\nautumn of 2002. In March 2003 Jenny left the band and now followed a\r\ntime of various stand in drummers until May the same year when Sara\r\nKlingstedt picked up the drumsticks. In October 2003 Ninja Dolls went\r\nin to the studio and recorded their first full length CD Drive In and\r\nin December a music video was made. Unfortunately Sara left the band in\r\nthe beginning of 2004, and once again Ninja Dolls was one member short.\r\n<br/><br/>\r\nBut in April they found their savior, Gustav Bergkvist who started to\r\nplay with the Ninjas. Unfortunately he as well lost interest (how hard\r\ncould it be to have a permanent drummer?) in December of 2004 and soon\r\nafter Martin Djuse quit the band. <br/><br/>\r\nIn February of 2005 the Ninjas enter Studio Secured with their new\r\nguitarist, Martin B&auml;ck and a session drummer called Robban B&auml;ck to\r\nrecord their first album to be released by a label. The studio session\r\nlasted for about six months with studio work during the weeks and live\r\ngigs during the weekends. In November the album was finally finished\r\nwith the mastering. <br/><br/>\r\nbut a new drummer then? well in 2005 Ninja Dolls became a complete band with a new drummer (again) called Peter Bergman. \r\n<br/><br/>\r\nNinja Dolls started to record a new album \r\n2006, and due to be released Autumn 2007.\r\n<br/><br/>\r\nThey\'ve also (2006) been on tour in Germany\r\nhoping to come back soon!\r\n<br/><br/>\r\nStay tuned for more info. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=342\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Ninja Dolls\' fans</span></a>',1,'',0,''),(1291,1598,'Phil Common',1,71,'philcommon.com','100 Bank St.','646.853.2410','\r\n<table bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"1\" width=\"100%\"><tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\" bgcolor=\"#ebebeb\">\r\n<p><font class=\"body\" color=\"#333366\" face=\"ARIAL, HELVETICA\" size=\"-1\"><b>B</b>orn\r\nin NYC to a union leader and Juilliard graduate phil was steeped in\r\nmusic and the need to understand people and the issues that we all\r\nface. At a young age phil began to write music and philosophy, his\r\nfirst ideas were centered on the concept that almost everything about\r\nlife is the same for all things and that the differences are only a\r\ntiny part of the world we share. This philosophy he called commonhaÃ¯Â¿Â½s. </font></p><p><font class=\"body\" color=\"#333366\" face=\"ARIAL, HELVETICA\" size=\"-1\"><b>I</b>ncorporating\r\nthese ideas into his music he created the group commonhaÃ¯Â¿Â½s and played\r\nNYC and Chicago throughout the early nineties. During this time touring\r\nthe Midwest and meeting musicians from all walks of life, phil was\r\nfinding inspiration to be the musician he is today. </font></p><p><font class=\"body\" color=\"#333366\" face=\"ARIAL, HELVETICA\" size=\"-1\"><b>N</b>ow\r\non a solo project, phil has found a new freedom to create music from\r\nhis heart, delivering an ecclectic mix of gritty, thoughtful songs. You\r\nwill hear a wide range of styles and lyrical content in this music.</font></p><font class=\"body\" color=\"#333366\" face=\"ARIAL, HELVETICA\" size=\"-1\">  </font><p><font class=\"body\" color=\"#333366\" face=\"ARIAL, HELVETICA\" size=\"-1\"><i>\"We have different experiences in life, but we all hold hands in the void\" - phil common <br/></i></font></p><p><font class=\"body\" color=\"#333366\" face=\"ARIAL, HELVETICA\" size=\"-1\"><b>P</b>hil\r\nplays mostly in NYC, you can always find his performance schedule on\r\nthe website http://philcommon.com . He is currently putting a\r\nband project together and plans to launch a tour with the release of\r\nhis new album in the fall.</font></p><p><font class=\"body\" color=\"#333366\" face=\"ARIAL, HELVETICA\" size=\"-1\"><b></b></font></p><p><font class=\"body\" color=\"#333366\" face=\"ARIAL, HELVETICA\" size=\"-1\"><b>T</b>hank you all for your interest and we hope to see you at a show real soon!</font></p><font class=\"body\" color=\"#333366\" face=\"ARIAL, HELVETICA\" size=\"-1\"><br/></font>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr bgcolor=\"#ebebeb\">\r\n<td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p>\r\n<font class=\"body\" color=\"#333366\" face=\"ARIAL, HELVETICA\" size=\"-1\"><b>Members</b></font></p></td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\"> \r\n<font class=\"body\" color=\"#333366\" face=\"ARIAL, HELVETICA\" size=\"-1\">\r\n<a href=\"http://www.garageband.com/user/philcommon\"><img src=\"http://www.garageband.com/imgserver?%7Cpe1%7CXsLRPXLrvP2rY1e0amFsDo5raUvOd5ZjDNGHxsbG7IW2vgY\" alt=\"[philcommon]\" align=\"left\" border=\"0\" height=\"12\" hspace=\"2\" vspace=\"0\" width=\"12\"/></a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.garageband.com/user/philcommon\">phil comm</a></font></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=326\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Phil Common\'s fans</span></a>',1,'',0,''),(1294,1603,'Moses Cruz',7,33,'','','818-335-9430','Been playing metal for 7 years. Been drumming for about 2. I love metal and everything around it. Looking to join a good \"stand-out\" band to take out this mainstream crap out of the industry and radio. ',1,'',0,''),(1304,1610,'Plan Nine',1,71,'http://www.myspace.com/plannineband','','','Plan Nine are a four-piece band in a traditional mould with a sound all of their own. They write all their own music. This produces a fusion of classic rock with pop, metal and everything in between. <br/><br/>They are an energetic and exciting group live and in the studio. They are based in Norwich but are now looking to take their music to a wider audience and are seeking gigs nationwide. <br/><br/>Get a flavour of Plan Nine at a gig or follow the web-link to hear their music. <br/><br/>They currently have three tracks ready for release and will be in the studio in the summer to complete their first album, with release scheduled for November. <br/>\r\n<p>\r\n</p><hr>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=327\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Plan Nine\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1311,1620,'Fred Guggenberger',1,72,'fred-guggenberger.com','','','<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=344\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Fred Guggenberger\'s fans</span></a>',0,'',0,''),(1316,1629,'Earl Lewis & The Channels',9,44,'mypages.netopia.com/channels','','','<span id=\"artistHistoryInner\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">\r\n<div align=\"center\"><font face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"4\">\r\n<p>Earl Lewis & The Channels were known just as the Channels at the start back in 1956. They were from a combination of two vocal groups, the Channels and the Lotharios. When two member of the Channels left, bass singer Clifton Wright and Earl Michael Lewis of the Lotharios were recruited by the remaining Channels. The following became the Classic Channel lineup: Earl Lewis, Clifton Wright, Edward Doulphin, Billy Morris and Larry Hampden.<br/>&nbsp;<br/>This New York City group from Harlem had a unique style all to themselves; Edward, Billy and Larry would sing the verse in three part harmony while Clifton rounded out the bottom. Earl\'s lead and falsetto would take over the bridge. The Channels recorded their signature song \"The Closer You Are\" in 1956, which was penned by Earl Lewis. They would later record the \"Gleam In Your Eye\" which Earl wrote when he was working on his newspaper route. The Channels would record a string of hits such as \"My Love Will Never Die\", \"Altar Of Love\", \"My Heart Is Sad\", \"Gloria\" and Frankie Laine\'s \"That\'s My Desire\". <br/><br/>Over the last FIFTY YEARS, past venues have included; Beacon Theater (NYC), Benedum Theater (Pittsburgh, PA), Continental Airlines Arena (E. Rutherford, NJ), Ford Community Performing Arts Center (Dearborn, MI), Keswick Theater (Glenside, PA), Mellon Arena (Pittsburgh, PA), Mohegan Sun (Uncasville, CT), Radio City Music Hall (NYC), The Theater @Madison Square Garden (NYC), Westbury Music Fair (Westbury, NY) and two PBS Specials; to name a few. <br/><br/><font size=\"4\">The current group lineup consist of :&nbsp;&nbsp;<br/><u><br/>Earl Lewis</u></font><font face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"4\">&nbsp;&nbsp;(Lead Vocals) -&nbsp;Earl hails from NYC and began singing while working on his newspaper route as a boy. It was there where Earl began writing his own material. Earl\'s voice is still in rare form; he continues to sing his material in their original key. Earl is also a Christian.<br/><u><br/>Jack Brown</u>&nbsp;</font><font face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"4\">&nbsp;(Bass/Baritone & member since 1969) - Jack began singing in his church while his mother played the piano. This senior member, next to Earl, can be heard on the \"Take 1 & Take 2\" CD\'s as well as the Channels\' recent CD \"Especially For You\".&nbsp;<br/></font><font face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><font size=\"4\"><u><br/>Salahuddin Aziz</u> (1st Tenor) -&nbsp;Salahuddin (pronounced Sa-la-hoo-deen) has returned&nbsp;to the Channels.&nbsp;A member of The Roamers in 1954 and acapella group The Attributes&nbsp;he brings his fine tenor back to the Channels. A fan favorite who\'s number one request is \'My Heart Is Sad\'. <br/><u><br/>Joe Rivera III</u>&nbsp;(1st Tenor/2nd Tenor/Baritone/Bass) - Joe hails from the Bronx and began singing in high school. Joe plays keyboards and is a&nbsp;Christian who loves the LORD JESUS. His influences are Sam Cooke, David Ruffin, Eddie Kendricks and Billy Stewart. </font></font>\r\n</p><div align=\"center\"><br/><font face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"4\">The Channels\' Band are:<br/>David Camacho - Keyboards</font> </div>\r\n<div align=\"center\"><font face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"4\">Dante DeLemus - Lead Guitar<br/>John Eve - Bass Guitar<br/>Angel \'Soupy\' Zambrana - Drums </font></div>\r\n<p></p></font></div></span>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=345\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Earl Lewis & The Channels\' fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1324,1642,'PUCK',1,14,'www.myspace.com/puckrock','','','<em><strong><font color=\"#990000\">Biography??? Don\'t take our word for it....<br/><br/></font>\"Its hard to believe that PUCK only formed in October 2006. ... If the gritty no nonsense rock tunes are to shape the things to come, PUCK certainly have a very promising future.\" ****</strong> </em><a href=\"http://profile.myspace.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=user.viewprofile&friendID=45769\"><strong><font color=\"#003399\"><em>Black Velvet Magazine</em></font></strong></a><em>- August 2007 <br/><br/></em><em><b>\"Fantastic...real emotional rock...check out their myspace...PUCK ROCK - which they certainly do!\" <br/></b>- </em><a href=\"http://www.totalrock.com/\"><strong><font color=\"#003399\"><em>Total Rock Radio</em></font></strong></a><em> (Terry & Thekla\'s New World Order Show) - August 2007 <br/><br/>\"Thank you for adding me on myspace, I think your music is awesome. I originally listened to &#8220;All That You Are&#8217; and read your biography on unsigned.com before checking you out more on myspace. WOW is I believe the word I used to describe you. PUCK is truly amazing.\" <strong>BestofBands.com - September 2007</strong> </em><br/><br/><br/><i>\"To get an E.P of this quality, from a band formed less than a year ago really is testament to the combined musical talents of this Female fronted London 5 piece pop/rock troop.....these guys (and girl) could be huge.\" <b>Glitzine.net - September 2007</b><br/><br/><i>\"This female fronted melodic hard rock band could well prove to have been one of many people&#8217;s highlights of the weekend...Slightly punky in places, reminiscent of early Foo Fighters meets Slash, [PUCK] have it all...They went down well with the sizable audience, so much so, that the crowd called for the well-deserved encore...\" <b>Dave Hunter - Cambridge Rock Festival - August 2007</b><br/><br/><i>\"I have to say your performance [at the Cambridge Rock Festival] was one of the highlights for me...\" <b>Dave Randall - <a href=\"http://www.getreadytorock.com/\"><font color=\"#003399\">Get Ready To Rock Magazine </font></a>- August 2007<br/><br/></b><i>\"PUCK\'s debut is one of the most musical and confident sounding debuts I have heard in a very long time....There is so much potential on offer here that it is frightening just what this band could achieve. Their &#8220;sound&#8221; could be a hit both in the European market but also in the notoriously hard to crack American territories. <b>HardRockHouse.com - August 2007 </b><br/><br/><i>\"Yes, now that\'s what I call a guitarist, with the sleazy blues licks of Slash and noise drenched riffing of Navarro - PUCK are off to a great start, and 3/5\'s of the band haven\'t even played a note yet&#8230; It seems most rock bands with a female singer with lungs worth their weight in gold get the lazy journalist comparison to Evanescence, fortunately PUCK deliver one fuck-off riff followed by an emo-core influenced vocal line, her voice is ocean sized and adds a sense of crystal-like clarity to their music which takes the post-grunge line in anthems of early Foo Fighters and gives a post-hardcore zeal&#8230; \" </i><b>Subba Cultcha - EP of the Month - August 2007</b> <br/><br/><i>\"... The band have great musicianship and every word Jay sings seems sincere, heartfelt yet effortless, which is bound to catch the attention of major labels...They&#8217;re sat on the heavy to mainstream border, which means they will attract fans from all different walks of life. If PUCK carry on writing and recording songs like this they will have a long and successful career ahead of them...\"</i><b> Scene Slut - August 2007</b> <br/><br/><i>\"...this could be an exciting time for female-fronted metal; but while most of those bands in the ocean of monotony struggle to keep their heads above water, PUCK are gliding along the top on rocket-powered surf boards. Superb.\" </i><b>www.godisinthetvzine.co.uk - July 2007</b><br/><br/><i>\"...What a perfomance at the Metro bar last Friday...It\'s a good job the guys play so exceptional well otherwise AmyJay\'s vocals would leave them behind...What a powerful voice...As a doorman for 19 years I have been on stage and seen hundreds of bands and have to say that I actually got goosebumbs when I heard Shelters played live....\" </i><b>Fan gig review - Metro Club - July 2007</b> <br/><br/><i>\"...A commercial sounding release from a band who know where they\'re going. Well written and produced...\" </i><b>Atomic Duster - July 2007</b> <br/><br/><i>\"Beyond Reason is [PUCK\'s] debut 7 track EP and for once, the first thing that comes to mind isn\'t Evanescence (which makes a pleasant change)....Fresh, versatile and well worth checking out.\" ****<br/></i><b>Get Ready To Rock Magazine- June 2007</b><br/><br/><i>\"Hey guys u were fucking amazing that night it is even better hearing it the second time ... i am glad that i came 2 the bull and gate i am going to ur other up comming gigs and i am gunna bring people along so that i spread the word even more down here...\" </i><b>Fan gig Review - Bull & Gate - June 2007</b> <br/><br/><i>\"No two ways about it - PUCK are hard and heavy female fronted rock with a powerful sound, big choruses and staccato riffs\" </i><b>The Music Index - June 2007</b> <br/><br/><i>\"I strongly recommend you take a look at their site, catch a gig and BUY their album. It&#8217;s available on their site for only &pound;5....A totally fresh, young band with an all round great sound...I can&#8217;t see how they are going to stay unsigned for much longer.\" </i><b>BurnABox.com - May 2007</b></i><b> <br/><br/></b><i>\"...I have to admit, and I didn&#8217;t want to, that the most potent weapon in PUCK&#8217;s arsenal is singer Amy Jay. Looking past her obvious physical attributes, she&#8217;s got a great voice and it&#8217;s probably a bit special in a live setting.\" </i><b>Tasty Fanzine - May 2007</b> <br/><br/><i>\"This is a great refreshing new band that has the ability to write passionate songs about mature relationships with all the qualities needed to be noticed, \'Beyond Reason\' is good enough to have several singles cut from it and if the band can carry on writing strong material like this they could be going places.\" </i><b>Rock3 Music - May 2007</b> <br/></i></i></i>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=346\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with PUCK\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1327,1646,'BULLISTIC',7,33,'www.myspace.com/bullistic','7915 Bur Oak Lane','804-283-1872','<p align=\"center\">Blue collar beer metal! That&#8217;s how the members of the&nbsp;band Bullistic describe their brand of metal. Formed in 2001 and based out of Richmond, VA., the band is comprised of Doug Gibson (lead vocals), Ed Savoy (guitar), Shane Kellis (drums) and John Davis (bass & vocals). Bullistic&#8217;s 2005 independent release, \"Chronicles of Love and Hate\" was released on September 13, 2005 and received instant critical acclaim and charted in the top 10 on the CMJ Loud Rock charts. The band has steadily gained an international fan base through touring, radio/video airplay and a strong Internet presence. Bullistic has been concentrating on touring the East Coast/Mid-Atlantic Region and can be seen live in any number of cities and towns within a 12 State region. The band has toured and played along side of such bands as Black Sabbath, Shadows Fall, Alice Cooper, Queensryche, The Burning Brides, Godhead, Silverstein, Avenged Sevenfold,&nbsp;Metal Church, Drowning Pool, Dark New Day, Nonpoint, Ankla, Silent Civilian, House of Lords, LA Guns, MOD, Seven Witches, Chris Caffery, Diecast, Bulletboys, Red Right Hand, King\'s X, Mardo, Adema, Revelation Theory, Alston, Five Bolt Main, Dry Kill Logic, Brand New Sin, Flaw, Alston, Artimus Pyledriver, Fireball Ministry, Nashville Pussy, Marc Rizzo of Soul Fly, Sanctity and many more. Bullistic has recorded the follow up to Chronicles of Love & Hate and is shopping for a new record deal. Expect a new album this summer! </p>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=347\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with BULLISTIC\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1330,1648,'When November Fails',7,33,'www.myspace.com/whennovemberfails','','','We are a fairly new teenage band started about May 2007 our first show was the 2nd of June 2007. There are four of us. Rich on drums, Koby on guitar, Bryan on bass, and Nic on the mic! we have about 9 songs only a few recorded which are like the first songs we ever cameup with. Nic is 14 years old, Koby is 15 years old, Bryan is 15 years old, and Rich is 16 years old. Any questions just e-mail us at <a href=\"mailto:Whennovemberfails@yahoo.com\">Whennovemberfails@yahoo.com</a> or hit us up on Myspace!\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=348\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with When November Fails\' fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(2415,1000156,'Sharon Paquette',1,66,'http://www.sharonpaquette.com','P.O. Box 71746 Las Vegas, NV. 89170','7024961619','Combining haunting melodies reminiscent of Evanescence and the grittiness of blues singer-songwriter Joss Stone, Sharon Paquette showcases a voice that exhibits rich tonal confidence. Her fresh and honest lyrics cut the soul and breathe new life into relevant themes of hope and perseverance. Having grown up in Windsor, Ontario, across the motor-city Detroit, Sharon&rsquo;s environment inspired her to dream big, yet her songs carry a down-to-earth sexiness of an &lsquo;everywoman&rsquo;.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nUnlike many singers, Sharon has studied voice, classical singing, music theory, and composition at the University of Windsor. Having sung both opera and gospel, Sharon truly has a comprehensive understanding of what good music sounds like. For 10 years she taught this skill as a music teacher privately and at the Durham District School Board in Ontario, focusing on instrumental music, voice, and songwriting. She also taught many song-writing workshops through the S.A.S.S. organization, co-founded by Dale Russell of the Guess Who (&ldquo;American Woman&rdquo;).<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEducation, however, was not her only passion. In 2007, Sharon put together her first demo, which features the heartfelt &ldquo;Your Girl&rdquo; and the heart wrenching &ldquo;I&rsquo;m Afraid&rdquo;. Recorded at the acclaimed Armoury Recording Studios, operated by producer Bruce Fairburn&rsquo;s family in Vancouver, B.C. Working alongside Don McLeod (producer, co-writer), Murray Atkinson (guitar) and Tobi Duquette (drums) the demo showcases her mature vocal abilities and the alluring sincerity in her lyrics. The full-length album, is slated for a 2008 release.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSharon Paquette<br />\r\n<br />\r\nwww.sharonpaquette.com \r\n',0,'',0,''),(1343,1668,'Psyracuse Pyramid',1,66,'www.myspace.com/psyracusepyramid','','','<strong style=\"font-size: 24pt; font-family: Courier New;\">Psyracuse Pyramid are a no bullshit rock n\' roll band from Southsea who choose to do things the simple way by making as much beat driven noise as is possible. </strong>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=349\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Psyracuse Pyramid\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1344,1671,'Washington Rays',1,66,'www.myspace.com/washingtonrays','','','For years the Washington Rays have proved to be one of the most influential and creative bands in and around Stoke Newington. The Rays prolific songwriting gives them a catalogue of over 100 songs, each painting a different story, and each taking the band into a different dimension. But we still think that this is only the beginning, never convinced that \'this is the one\', as we continue our quest to write our best song ever. Its time for Washington Rays to give you all the opportunity to join in our quest, and enjoy the fruits of our songwriting, listen with love, and let us take you there. John Medzy\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=350\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Washington Rays\' fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1345,1672,'Andy Ebersole',1,76,'www.myspace.com/andyebersolemusic','','','Well i\'ve really loved music my whole life, I remember spending all of my free time when I was younger just sitting in front of the radio. I picked up a guitar about 2 years ago and everything just&nbsp;kind of snow-balled from there. I\'m currently not in a band but i\'m planning on getting something together in the summer of 08\'. For now i\'ll just be using this site to upload some of my personal recordings, maybe some poetry etc. So keep an eye out on the scene for me, and stay sexy! Haha later dudes!\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=351\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Andy Ebersole\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',0,'',0,''),(1368,1699,'Motus',1,14,'www.motusweb.net','','01132261248','<!--StartFragment --><font color=\"#000000\"><b>For the uninitiated, MOTUS are a four piece band from West Yorkshire, England. The Motus formula has always been one of being a damn good live band, first and foremost, and our audience continues to grow. Motus regularly plays the Yorkshire region\'s top venues, and has had great success on the local motorcycle club circuit. Motus are always on the look out for new venues to play, anywhere where we can find an audience! </b></font>\r\n<p><b><font color=\"#000000\">An independent EP \"Heads & Tales\" is available from our website and from all gigs. In 2006, the band established a relationship with an up and coming production partnership at Chunc Studios in Leeds. The recordings you can hear on this page are a result of the work at Chunc in 2006 and we are currently&nbsp;in the process of recording a further 5 tracks&nbsp;plus remastering the 2006 recordings (for the sake of consistency). </font></b></p>\r\n<p><b><font color=\"#000000\">The aim is to create an album\'s worth of music as near to release quality as budgets will allow. We invite any record labels who might be interested in putting the album out when complete to get in touch with us via this page.</font></b></p>\r\n<p><b><font color=\"#000000\">We write, play, perform, rehearse and record music because we all deeply love it. Everyone in Motus has a desire to become better at what they do and to achieve success. If you want to know more or if you would like to contact us, please email us at motus.music@ntlworld.com Thanks for looking!! </font></b></p>\r\n<p><b><b><font color=\"#000000\">Peace, Love and Stomp Boxes xx</font></b></b></p>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=352\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Motus\' fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1370,1703,'Pussy Sisster',1,14,'http://www.pussysisster.de','stefanstr.23','','<b><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"4\">\r\n<p>Bandstart: </p></font></b><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"4\">\r\n<p>October 2002</p><b>\r\n<p>Musikstyle: </p></b>\r\n<p>Sleaze - Glam - Hardrock</p><b>\r\n<p>Bandimage: </p></b>\r\n<p>wild, energy-full,explosive, hot, dirty, </p><b>\r\n<p>Gigs: </p></b>\r\n<p>international </p><b>\r\n<p>Bandmembers:</p></b>\r\n<p>Alex Sex - Vocals (22 years)</p>\r\n<p>Mark Heart - Drums (22 years)</p>\r\n<p>Joe Johnson - Guitar (21 years)</p>\r\n<p>Mr. Coma - Bass (22 years)</p>\r\n<p>Chris Nad - Organisation</p><b>\r\n<p>Discographie: </p></b>\r\n<p>September 2005 - Album \"Sleazy Things\"</p>\r\n<p>February 2007 - EP \"Hot like Hell\"</p>\r\n<p>July 2007 - CD \"Live in Karlsruhe\"</p><b>\r\n<p>References: </p></b>\r\n<p>-</p></font>\r\n<p>Song \"Sleazy Things\" is on the Hollywood Hairspray 6</p>\r\n<p>(Perris Records/USA)</p><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"4\">\r\n<p>-</p></font>\r\n<p>Song \"Broken Man\" is on the DEAD FAMOUS Vol.3</p>\r\n<p>(Astral Records/Australy)</p>\r\n<p>-Song \"Sleazy Things\" is on the Hitpack New Rock Vol.3</p>\r\n<p>(EDEL-MUSIC/EMG/Germany)</p>\r\n<p>-Song \"Vampires of Death\" is on TITUS SPORTS Vol.1</p>\r\n<p>-Song \"Broken Man\" stays 4 weeks at place 5 in the </p>\r\n<p>australian indie-charts</p>\r\n<p>-Song \"Vampires of Death\" stays 2 weeks at place 1 in</p>\r\n<p>the \"dirty thirty\" texas</p>\r\n<p>-Song \"Over the Top\" stays 3 weeks at place 2 in </p>\r\n<p>germanys radio swr 3 rockcharts</p>\r\n<p>-Songs from the band in radiostations in 12 countrys </p>\r\n<p>worldwide</p>\r\n<p>-TV REPORT about the band two in germany & one</p>\r\n<p>in argentina</p>\r\n<p>-Band was touring in march 2007 for 3 weeks around</p>\r\n<p>the UK</p><b><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"4\">\r\n<p>Support Act of: </p></font></b><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"4\">\r\n<p>Y&T, Stephen Pearcy, The Quireboys,</p>\r\n<p>Vixen, Gilby Clark, Dog&acute;s D&acute;Amour,</p>\r\n<p>Adam Bomb, Oomph and many more !!!</p><b>\r\n<p>Planning: </p></b>\r\n<p><font face=\"Arial\">Label-Deal, New Record \"City of Angels\" October 2007</font></p><font face=\"Arial\">\r\n<p>US-Tour 2008</p></font><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"4\"></font></font>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=353\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Pussy Sisster\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1363,1693,'World Is Static',1,71,'www.myspace.com/worldis','','','\r\n<p>Featuring the beautiful vocals of&nbsp; Heather Frances \'World Is Static\' is a band that fits somewhere between alt, rock, metal & gothic. Hailing from County Durham in the north east of England & formed in 2005 by award winning (BBC Blast) singer/songwriter Heather Frances & guitarist/songwriter Simon Chester. The duo were later joined by Sam Tuckett on bass & Susan Murray on drums.&nbsp; Taking their name from a song on the Static Prevails album by Jimmy Eat World the band play down tuned melodic tunes. <br/><br/>World Is Static were the first band to be played on the test transmission of UK based radio station Ne1fm. The band were also played on the first ever AlterNation show on the same radio station and described as \"County Durham\'s finest gothic rockers\". <br/><br/>The song Dying Inside was released by Hollywood-based record label 272 Records on the compilation album \'The Funeral Volume 1\'(2007).<br/><br/>Highlights of the <strong>W<em>i</em>S</strong> musical journey so far include playing various UK festivals & supporting top signed bands like Fables Last Stand (End Of The Trail Records) & Crud (Full Effect Records). \r\n<p>\r\n<hr/>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"mw-headline\"><u><strong>Band Members</strong></u><br/></span><font color=\"#000000\">Heather Frances - Vocals & guitar <br/></font><font color=\"#000000\">Simon Chester - Guitar & backing vocals <br/></font><font color=\"#000000\">Sam Tuckett - Bass <br/></font><font color=\"#000000\">Susan Murray - Drums <br/><br/></font>\r\n<hr/>\r\n<br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=354\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\">Interact with World Is Static\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n</p></p></p>',1,'',0,''),(1362,1689,'Rhen',1,61,'www.adrianrhen.com','','347-668-6092','<span class=\"epktxt\">Brooklyn, NY is home to Buenos Aires-born artist\r\nAdrian Rhen, an accomplished songster who presents acoustic-rooted\r\npop/rock with infusions of Hispanic flavor, incorporating violin and\r\ndelectable percussion rhythms in a finely-tuned sound that speaks with\r\nallure and honesty, reaching out for the common strains of the human\r\nspirit in all of us.<br/><br/>Imperfect World<br/><br/>Nobody would argue\r\nthat the world is a perfect place. Certainly Rhen would make no such\r\nassertion. Rhen realizes the struggles that confront people every day\r\nand writes music to provide an outlet, the creation of a perfect place\r\nthrough song in which people can find a temporary home, an escape from\r\ntension. \"There are times in life that we must do things that we don\'t\r\nwant to be doing and our minds wander off to dream of what we would\r\nlove to be doing instead. Music, for me, is one of those times in my\r\nlife that I am exactly where I need and want to be. I am home.\" A fan\r\nof Rhen could say the same.<br/><br/>Others<br/><br/>Song is ultimately\r\nabout finding a way to touch others and be touched, about creating a\r\nsymbiosis of the human spirit. Rhen embraces music\'s unique qualities,\r\nit\'s ability to forge a pathway that links humans to each other. His\r\nimpeccable and emotive songwriting is just the perfect yellow brick\r\nroad to bring this about. \"I try to connect with others on such a human\r\nlevel using nothing but music, which proves that therein lies a special\r\npower in this language.\"<br/><br/>Fight<br/><br/>Every human being\'s\r\ndestiny is to struggle to find his own niche, a place for the\r\nexpression of his own passions. Rhen has done this for himself and his\r\ncompelling music brings the gift of this ability to his listeners\r\nthrough music\'s distinct mode of inspiration. \"Mostly I am inspired by\r\nseeing others fight for their passion, be it an athlete, writer, or\r\nmountain climber, the struggle to reach beyond one\'s own limitations\r\nand share that experience.\" Self-empowerment emanates from every song\r\noffered the public by songwriter Adrian Rhen.<br/><br/>Always on My Mind<br/><br/>Rhen\'s\r\nforthcoming release, Always on My Mind, will be an emotive display of\r\nthis artist\'s power. A tour promoting the new album will send Rhen to\r\nthe East Coast this spring and summer, with trips to the West Coast and\r\nArgentina following in autumn. Rhen\'s musical muse strikes at\r\nunexpected moments and results in refreshing and surprising songs. \"I\r\nhave always tended to be very impulsive with my writing. I\'ll see a\r\nmovie that blew me away and I need to write a song. Then that idea will\r\nbe introduced to the band in that raw form and worked on and perhaps\r\neven performed in order to give it proper breathing space until it\r\neventually becomes the final version song that everyone will hear on\r\nthe album.\" Recording is an equally galvanizing experience, says Rhen.\r\n\"The recording process is both exciting and nerve-racking at the same\r\ntime. You\'re trying to revel in the fact that you have the privilege of\r\nrecording this moment in time of your life and also there is this voice\r\nin your head saying \'What if this doesn\'t turn out right?\' and \'What if\r\nI can\'t shape this into what I hear in my head?\' But once you realize\r\nthat these questions are asked by even the most respected artists, you\r\nstart enjoying the whole recording experience a whole lot more.\" Rhen\r\nis currently working with A&R Select, the leading indie A&R\r\nfirm in Hollywood, CA.<br/><br/>Review<br/><br/>\"Rhen\'s accomplished mix of pop rock with Spanish-language infusions is remarkable.\" - A&R Select<br/><br/><br/></span>\r\n\r\n<span class=\"epksubheading\">Discography<br/></span>\r\n<span class=\"epktxt\">Always on My Mind (2007)<br/>Runaround (2005)<br/><br/>Streaming & radio airplay:<br/>\"Home\"<br/>\"Luz\"<br/><br/><br/></span>\r\n\r\n\r\n<span class=\"epksubheading\">Links<br/></span>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/rhen\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.myspace.com/rhen</a>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=355\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Rhen\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',0,'',0,''),(1378,1715,'Justus Prevails',1,71,'','','','This duo spans the gap of two generations, Keith being the old guy along side his younger counterpart, Ray. Keith\'s musical background includes several years with the Royal Conservatory of Music, a member of Up With People, and involvement with several other groups. His Mother was his greatest influence because of her formal musical training and involvement in music as a vocalist. She\'s always had a good ear and offers constructive criticism when needed. Keith plays keyboard, guitar, harmonica and flute, while Ray plays guitar, and provides the lead vocals. Ray is also showing great promise as a drummer. <br/><br/>With a song in their voice this duo started out doing just A cappella. Soon instruments showed up, with things to plug them into and what followed was a meld of true voice/instrument integration. The duo retains it\'s roots of voice as the principle instrument. Each song typically features fine three or four part harmonies, complimented by rich instrumentation and rock solid rhythms. <br/><br/>\"We will always evolve,\" says co-founder Keith. \"Music is an expression of life, and life is an evolutionary process. We cannot remain the same and still say we are alive.\" <br/><br/>Both members are from a small town in the mountains of Western Canada. And both still make their homes there. They are entrenched in the community of which they live and like the closeness of knowing their neighbours and the people passing by. But the guys have their sights set on a larger audience and plan to travel with their music to help spread pozitive vibrations wherever they go.\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=356\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Justus Prevails\' fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1407,1722,'Blackwood Company',1,66,'www.myspace.com/blackwoodcomp','','','<span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial\">Email: <a href=\"mailto:blackwood.company@gmail.com\">blackwood.company@gmail.com</a></span><br/><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial\">See <a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/blackwoodcomp\">www.myspace.com/blackwoodcomp</a> for our show schedule and song lyrics!</span><br/><br/><strong><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Arial\">The past...</span><br/></strong><br/><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial\">Stephen \"Sven\" Shirl was born and raised in Lower London, the bastard child of a French duchess and a smooth-talking chimney sweep. The day before his eighth birthday, he encountered a sleeping Gypsy from whom he stole a guitar. Finding his mother\'s royal pretension stifling and his father\'s occupation \"downright gloomy,\" Sven left home to master the guitar and shed his \"unfortunate\" cockney accent.</span><br/><br/><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial\">Born of clowns, John Stuart grew up among nomadic circus folk in and around the Midwest. Although he felt destined to become the \"best damned trapeze artist since&nbsp;Jules L&eacute;otard,\" he fell tragically in love with a pair of Bulgarian conjoined sisters named Georgia and Estonia. Unable to choose between them, he fled with barely more than a packed lunch and a harmonica in the key of Bb major.</span><br/><br/><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial\">After wandering aimlessly searching for \"the scene,\" Sven and John met at a Nickelback concert and eventually formed a pop band.</span><br/><br/><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Arial\"><strong>The present...</strong></span><br/><br/><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial\">We are currently recording an album at&nbsp;Hound Dawg Studio (<a href=\"http://www.hounddawgstudio.com\">www.hounddawgstudio.com</a>), featuring drums by owner Dan Hassay. </span><br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=390\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\">Interact with Blackwood Company\'s fans</span></a>',1,'',0,''),(1417,1757,'Bob Boyce',1,61,'www.myspace.com/robertboyce','','','Two Drag Club is the first solo cd from Bob Boyce, drummer for the Omaha Nebraska band Grasshopper Takeover. Bob took on a new role with this project as he wrote, played, recorded and mixed the cd himself. With more hooks then a tackle box, this 14 song cd contains great melodies, harmonies and catchy riffs at every turn. If you like toe-tappin\', butt-kickin\' pop rock, this cd is a must for your collection. <br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=391\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\">Interact with Bob Boyce\'s fans</span></a>',0,'',0,''),(1404,1723,'Blacksmith',1,66,'','','','<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=392\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Blacksmith\'s fans</span></a>',1,'',0,''),(1405,1730,'Blue Cloud Ruffians',1,61,'www.myspace.com/bluecloudruffians','','','Everyone\'s heard some version of the rock n roll fairy tale: Boy starts band with dreams of leaving small town. The chemistry that is BCR was born one hazy evening in the not-so metropolis of Barnwell, SC back in 2005 when an earlier version of the band first jammed with singer Ed Lemon. Since then, founding members Randy (guitar) and Johnny (drums), along with Ed and new bassist Jason have taken what they\'re given and come up with their own tasty, sonic home-brew. BCR\'s songs are what happens when you grow up in South Carolina\'s heat and share a common love for Ramones, Pearl Jam, Jane\'s Addiction, The Cure, The Beatles, The Rolling Stones, CCR, Kings Of Leon, Skid Row, The Black Keys, and catfish. ..\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=393\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Blue Cloud Ruffians\' fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1409,1747,'Bofus',1,17,'www.myspace.com/goatbeats','','','<font size=\"2\">\r\n<p>Bofus is made up of 5 friends, Oliver (singer,dj), Steve (guitar), Scotty (guitar), Jason (bass), Myki (drums), They have been together for a little over a year. Influences range from Black Crowes, Raging Slab, Chili Peppers, Beatles, old school Incubus, and Oliver&#8217;s love of Motown. They gig regularly in and around their hometown of Las Cruces, NM, averaging 10-15 shows a month. </p></font>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=394\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Bofus\' fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1414,1107,'James Alan Gourley',10,45,'http://www.myspace.com/jamesalangourley','','','<strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">\r\n<p class=\"main\" align=\"left\">\r\n<font size=\"2\"><strong><font color=\"#990000\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\"><strong style=\"font-size: 10pt\"><em>Dreamy, haunting, ethereal, thought-provoking, wistful, spiritual, melancholic, uplifting...A few words that can be used to describe the music and songs of James Alan Gourley...A highly original fingerpick style, poignant, emotive and powerful lyrics, strong and heartfelt vocal presentation&nbsp; and a distinctive guitar sound combine to leave the listener with a lasting impression of genuine quality, real talent and musical integrity.<br />\r\n</em></strong></span><br />\r\n</font>James Alan Gourley is an electro-acoustic guitarist / singer / songwriter / poet &nbsp;based in the West End of Glasgow, Scotland, UK.</strong></font> \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"main\" align=\"left\">\r\n<font size=\"2\"><strong style=\"font-size: 10pt\">Guitarist and songwriter for many years with&nbsp;iconic&nbsp;Glasgow based hard rock band Liars Edge&nbsp;Alan (one of those awkward people who prefers to be&nbsp;called by their middle name!)&nbsp;has spent the last year or two re-familiarising himself with the acoustic guitar and experimenting with a wide variety of alternative tunings having, for the time being at least, hung up his electric to concentrate on a solo acoustic&nbsp;career.</strong></font> \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"main\" align=\"left\">\r\n<font size=\"2\"><strong>Having just recorded his first solo album &quot;Ten Miles Out Of Midnight&quot; Alan is currently in negotiation with several&nbsp;local labels, publishers and distributors with regard to release of his album and has already attracted significant interest from&nbsp;other artists, listeners, podcasters&nbsp;and music-industry personnel on myspace and other websites.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</strong></font><strong><font size=\"2\">Having developed a highly original style of guitar fingericking - an eclectic mix of rock, folk, classical&nbsp;and celtic influences - &nbsp;&quot;Ten Miles Out Of Midnight&quot; is a stripped down, no frills recording featuring only electroacoustic&nbsp;guitar and vocals. Containing seven songs and four instrumentals the album is a very personal one - confessional even - reflecting many of Alan&#39;s opinions on life and its trials and tribulations. From the intense and haunting opening instrumental &quot;The Things In The Attic&quot; to the hearfelt and emotion laden cynicism of the albums&#39; closing track &quot;A Place In The Sun&quot; Alan takes the listener on a musical and lyrical&nbsp;journey through many emotions including sadness, hope, despair, love and anger. His instrumentals speak to the listener&nbsp;of both beauty and pain in a dreamy and ethereal way with no need for words.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font><font size=\"2\">Alan is currently playing a series of gigs in and around Glasgow with plans to&nbsp;tour further afield&nbsp;later in 2008&nbsp;and then record his second album. Although currently playing solo he is looking at recruiting a cellist, pianist and possibly a double bass player for some larger shows.&nbsp;</font></strong> \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"main\" align=\"left\">\r\n<font size=\"2\"><strong>Alan is also hoping to publish a book of poetry/lyrics at some point in 2008 and will post some&nbsp;of this material&nbsp;on subsequent blogs on this site. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen he&#39;s not writing songs, lyrics&nbsp;or poetry Alan enjoys sleeping, reading&nbsp;(especially related to&nbsp;philosophy, psychology and cosmology), beer, playing WW2 FPS&#39;s and travel. Did I mention he is left handed? That explains a lot.......</strong></font> \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"main\" align=\"left\">\r\n<strong>Many thanks to those who have already expressed interest in Alan&#39;s work and he hopes you enjoy the three songs ( full album versions) posted&nbsp;here on Best Of Bands! &nbsp;Please note the fourth song &quot;The Last Day Of Earth&quot; is NOT a forthcoming album track but an instrumental trance track mixed by Alan from samples from eJay software and samples created by himself using Reason software.&nbsp; The fifth song is a live bootleg of Liars Edge anthem &quot;Doing The Damage&quot; at Glasgow Cathouse.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf you wish to pre-order a copy of &quot;Ten Miles Out Of Midnight&quot; please contact <a href=\"mailto:jamesalangourley@hotmail.com\">jamesalangourley@hotmail.com</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n</span></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=395\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt\">Interact with James Alan Gourley&#39;s fans</span></a> \r\n',0,'',0,''),(1420,1760,'Brian Lauri Project',1,74,'brilauri@brilaurimusic.com','','','Brian Lauri has played for over 20 years with many musicians from all over the world. He has also opened for national acts including Soulive, Percy Hill, Strangefolk, Deep Banana Blackout, and the Samples. If you like hip-hop, dub reggae, groove, keyboards, drums and bass, I think you will find this music to be enlightening. <br/>Brian has played keyboards with: Phil Lesh, Darkstar Orchestra (tryout), Channel 2 dub band (Vermont Reggae Fest), Miracle Train, Liquid Dead, Green Tea, and The Trilogy.\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=396\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Brian Lauri Project\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1421,1761,'Candygram For Mongo',1,61,'www.candygramformongo.com','','310-600-7888','If Cheap Trick were moderating a debate between Social Distortion and the Dropkick Murphys over which was better: internet vs. home video pornography - it would sound like Candygram For Mongo!<br/><br/>Candygram For Mongo began in late 2005 when Tony Shea, vocals, and Gary Sharp, drums, started ripping through tunes out in the back shack of G&#8217;s house in North Hollywood.&nbsp; With original powerpop tracks that remind you of a football game between Social Distortion and the Dropkick Murphys in Cheap Trick&#8217;s backyard, Gary and Tony brought on two more outstanding musicians &#8211; Johnny D, guitar, and Dan Cohen, bass - to round out the group and begin production on their debut album, &#8220;The Red Pill.&#8221;<br/><br/>Candygram For Mongo are now taking their show on the road, first hitting Los Angeles by storm with regular appearances at world famous venues like The Viper Room, The Cat Club, and The House of Blues.&nbsp; The response has been phenomenal!&nbsp; Skratch Magazine writes, &#8220;Hooks for days, sugary yet shouted choruses and a versatile knowledge of the rock &#8216;n roll playbook...set Candygram For Mongo way ahead of the rest of the whiners, poseurs and talentless but popular acts on the scene.&#8221; Candygram For Mongo&#8217;s song, INTERMISSION, was featured on the hit cable show, &#8220;Battlestar Galactica.&#8221; They have won the award for &#8220;Male Singer/Songwriter of the Year&#8221; at the 16th Annual Los Angeles Music Awards.&nbsp; Their track, HAPPY, has been accepted into the Clear Channel Discover New Music Program and is featured on hundreds of Clear Channel Radio Station Websites, and Black Angel Promotions writes, &#8220;the music is absolutely brilliant.&#8221;<br/><br/>Although Candygram For Mongo has only been together for a relatively short time, each member is an experienced musician. TONY SHEA, grew up on a steady diet of punk music and prep school mind control. Tony&#8217;s first band, Columbian Necktie, was part of the Washington DC club scene for years, and particularly renown for their outlandish live shows. Tony&#8217;s misadventures have resulted in numerous broken bones, multiple concussions, and literally hundreds of stitches.&nbsp; JOHNNY D graduated Harvard (Illinois) Music Academy with a minor in Lead Glockenspiel.&nbsp; He quickly became bored with hippy chicks that are attracted to Glockenspiel players, and picked up the guitar.&nbsp; After 6-years on the road, Johnny moved to Nashville, TN and played with musicians from The Allman Brothers Band, Rev. Al Green, Cinderella, Vince Neil Band, Dolly Parton Band, Garth Brooks Band, and Lorrie Morgan. GARY SHARP considers Candygram For Mongo the only real band worth mentioning.&nbsp; However, Gary is no stranger to playing the drums.&nbsp; Having been a part of various Drum & Bugle Corps for the entirety of his teenage years, Gary weeps every time he thinks of the sheer amount of parades he&#8217;s marched in, due to its constant reminder of his inner (and outer) nerd-ism. Having strummed his way through Seattle for most of the 90s, DAN COHEN moved to L.A. in 2000 to experience the Y2K apocalypse, as well as compose, produce, and perform for commercials, film, radio, internet, and corporate events.&nbsp; Dan has played and recorded with musicians from bands such as Heart, Gigolo Aunts, Manray, Happy Stars, The Posies, The Rembrandts, Dog&#8217;s Eye View, and many more. <br/><br/>Tired of James Blunt and Jack Johnson?&nbsp; Well Nevermind that Sh*t...Here Comes Mongo!<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=397\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Candygram For Mongo\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1423,1754,'Boxkar',1,61,'www.boxkar.com','2637 Templeton Place','920-428-9478','\r\n<p>Boxkar started in 2001 with the convergence of Chris Szebeni(lead singer/songwriter) and Bryan Bremer(rhythym guitar/songwriter). Even before they cemented their line-up, Bryan and Chris had already gained the attention of producers, agents, managers etc. People seemed drawn to Chris\' stylistic, energetic stage presence and vocal ability and Bryan\'s songwriting skills that appealed to listeners of all kinds. The attention they received landed them in a studio in Tampa, FL to record their first CD titled \"Rockstar Weekend\". This CD was well received and helped Boxkar to hook up many great shows in the midwest. </p>\r\n<p>They rode this momentum into their second album, which was self titled. Coming out of an area that was known mainly for cover music, Boxkar was standing out with their originals. As for their live shows, Chris Szebeni was turning Boxkar gigs into a true event that audiences couldn\'t get enough of. A true front-man, entertainer and well trained vocalist, Chris was bringing back a vibe to the live music scene that\'s been missing for quite some time. In the summer of 2006, Boxkar grabbed themselves two WAMI(Wisconsin Area Music Industry) awards. The \"Male Vocalist of the Year\" went to Chris, and Boxkar was named \"Best Band in 2006\". Because of this growing attention, Boxkar nailed down some of their best gigs up to that point. They were now picking up shows headlining well known festivals around the midwest, including the Harley Rally and Summerfest. They also played the infamous Viper Room in LA and caught the attention of many people on the west coast. In January of 2005, Boxkar was invited to play the Presidential Inauguration in Washington, DC. They were on the bill for \"The Future Rocks Today\" concert, held at the DC Armory with artists such as Fuel, Ryan Cabrera, Ruben Studdard, Hillary Duff and Three Doors Down. This achievement caught the attention of Geoff Barton(Chief Editor) from Classic Rock Magazine out of London, England. Mr. Barton personally reviewed the CD in the Magazine and gave it incredible marks. He personally contacted the band and did a full page spread in the 2006 March issue. </p>\r\n<p>This leads us into the third and most recent CD, \"Comin\' out Swingin,\" which was eagerly reviewed in the 2007 January issue of Classic Rock Magazine by Mr. Barton, who rated this album near the top of his scale. Also, this CD took home the WAMI award for \"Album of the Year\" in 2007. This was a great accomplishment since Boxkar was going up against several great bands, including Skillet, which is a band that was nominated for a GRAMMY in 2007.</p>\r\n<p>Boxkar\'s success has pleased many, but they are not finished yet. Chris and Bryan, along with fellow bandmates Matt Hammen on bass,&nbsp;Brian Saunders&nbsp;on lead guitar and Matt Gieseke on drums are in it for the long haul. Come and take a listen!</p><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"2\"></font><br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=398\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\">Interact with Boxkar\'s fans</span></a>',1,'',0,''),(1425,1764,'Private Nation',1,74,'www.myprivatenation.com','3202 Echodale Ave','410-258-7886','<a href=\"http://www.sonicbids.com/epk/epk.asp?epk_id=121884\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><font color=\"#003399\">View Private Nation\'s EPK</font></strong></a> <br/>FOR BOOKING INFORMATION CALL 1 877 633 4849 EXT. 2 or visit www.touraband.com and simply click booking inquiry! <br/><br/>In early 2002 bassist Mike Nealis got his former Martian Soul singer/guitarist John Adams out of an early retirement to form a new project. Enter former Modern Ruins timekeeper and longtime friend Chris Phillips. \"Chris was always on our radar\" says Mike. Now they were ready for whatever came their way. In early 2003 they set out as a 4 piece under the temporary moniker Clone\". \" That was a fun time for us\" says axeman John Adams. \" We were a Starleigh cover band getting our chops down, playing every club in town. \"We got to open for lots of great acts including SR-71 and Funny Money and ended our summer by kicking ass to a packed house at Seacrets in Ocean City Maryland.\" In 2006 vocalist /guitarist Jon Mickey decided to join Sugarjack and the three piece Private Nation was born. With the rebirth was a new found optimism by all 3 members and a dedication to writing songs that will get you hooked. \"I am excited about the album in a good way.\" Says drummer Chris Phillips of the bands forthcoming self titled debut. Private Nation has endured all the ups and downs that come with the music business, but look for them to break out in a big way in 2007\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=399\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Private Nation\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1430,1772,'Charles David Sharp',8,79,'','','','Charles David Sharp a.k.a. The Mississippi Troubadour, singer/songwriter/guitarist from Pascagoula, Mississippi.\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=400\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Charles David Sharp\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1433,1776,'Tito Hinojosa Navarro',8,40,'','','','Tito Hinojosa Navarro lives on the bank of the biggest Lake in Mexico, Lake Chapala. He\'s a musician who makes his living performing daily in the Chapala -&nbsp;Ajijic area. His powerful voice is requested by every venue, restaurant, wedding reception, Mariachi party, and club in the Guadalajara area, but Tito has a family and devotes as much time to them as possible.&nbsp; He is well known by local and national musicians who constantly ask him to play in their bands or as a back-up singer/player, despite this he is a humble and decent man who will play at your home just for the pure joy of it.<br/><br/>The CD cover on this site is his latest work: \"A Tribute to Javier Solis\"&nbsp;a respected and beloved&nbsp;Mexican singer whose success is unparalelled in the history of Mariachi Music.<br/><br/>I am proud to say - I am his friend.\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=401\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Tito Hinojosa Navarro\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(2219,2403,'Joe Hero',1,74,'http://www.joehero.com','','','Joe Hero was formed in 2005 by three longtime musicians and friends from Appalachian State University in North Carolina.&nbsp; They recorded a 4-song demo that summer, and in December 2007 released their debut CD titled &quot;A Hero&#39;s Welcome&quot; which is available at cdbaby.com.\r\n',1,'Linc Butler - guitar/lead vocals<br />\r\nRyan Terrell - bass/vocals<br />\r\nScott Hardesty - drums/vocals \r\n',0,''),(1437,1728,'Blue Flashing Light',1,0,'www.blueflashinglight.net','','','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\">Ian Schwarber- Lead Vocals<br/>Josh Schwarber- Keyboardist<br/>Sheldon Wolfe- Bassist/Background Vox<br/>Adam Monica- Guitarist/ Background Vox<br/>Ryan Cattie- Guitarist/ Background Vox<br/>J.J Bower- Drum Guru<br style=\"\"><br style=\"\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\">As Blue Flashing Light (taken from the song by the <st1:country-region w:st=\"on\">U.K.</st1:country-region>&#8217;s Travis) continues to bring their Proper Rock Show to venues throughout the South, each arrival provides a rebirth, having already generated an incredible buzz in the rockbed of <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:city w:st=\"on\">Athens</st1:city>, <st1:state w:st=\"on\">Ga.</st1:state></st1:place> A steady performance roster and new professional guidance continues to season this six member dynamic and propel them toward inevitable success. <br style=\"\"><br style=\"\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\">With Since I Caught You, Shadowboxing and Wasn&#8217;t it Real, the band has just released their debut album ShadowBoxing on which is sure to finally land them on the charts and in the ears of Music Industry movers and shakers.<br style=\"\"><br style=\"\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\">Somewhere in the distance just beyond the setting sun, if you tune in and look closely-you can catch a glimpse of the Blue Flashing Light on the horizon.<br/><br/>Have You Seen The Light????<br/>Proper Rock Show Tour Dates:<br/></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9.5pt; font-family: Arial;\">Blue Flashing Light<br/><st1:city w:st=\"on\">Antones- Austin</st1:city>, <st1:state w:st=\"on\">Texas</st1:state><br/>9:30pm<br/>9/15/07<br/>On the bill:<br/>Black Angels<br/><br/>Blue Flashing Light<br/>11pm<br/><st1:city w:st=\"on\">Buffingtons-Milledgeville</st1:city>,<st1:state w:st=\"on\">Ga.</st1:state><br/>9/22/07<br/>On the bill: Taxi<br/><br/>Blue Flashing Light<br/>The 40 Watt- <st1:city w:st=\"on\">Athens</st1:city>, <st1:state w:st=\"on\">Ga.</st1:state><br/>11pm<br/>9/28/07<br/>ShadowBoxing Album Release<br/><br/>Blue Flashing Light<br/>9/29/07<br/>5pm<br/>Market Days Festival<br/><st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:city w:st=\"on\">Washington</st1:city>, <st1:state w:st=\"on\">Ga.</st1:state></st1:place><br/><br/>Blue Flashing Light<br/>9/29/07<br/>Rhino\'s-Columbus, Ga.<br/>10pm<br/>On the bill: TXRX<br/><br/>Blue Flashing Light<br/>Field of Greens Festival<br/>Walnut Grove, Ga.<br/>10/6/07<br/>4pm<br/><br/>Blue Flashing Light<br/>The Bear Cave-Marietta, Ga.<br/>10/13/07<br/>10pm<br/><br/>Blue Flashing Light<br/>High Note Lounge-Birmingham, Al.<br/>10/26/07<br/>On the bill: April Cover<br/><br/>Blue Flashing Light<br/>The Mission- Augusta, Ga.<br/>10/27/07<br/>11pm<br/><br/>Blue Flashing Light<br/>The Guitar Bar- Savannah, Ga.<br/>11/10/07<br/>10pm<br/>On the bill: TXRX<br/><br/>Blue Flashing Light<br/>Vinyl- Atlanta, Ga.<br/>11/24/07<br/>10pm<br/>On the bill:<br/>The Usual Suspects<br/><br/>Blue Flashing Light<br/>The Melting Point-Athens, Ga.<br/>Thursday, 12/6/07<br/>10pm<o:p></o:p></span></p><span style=\"font-size: 9.5pt; font-family: Arial;\">\r\n</span>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=402\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Blue Flashing Light\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1448,1802,'3 Hours of Darkness',1,14,'http://www.3hoursofdarkness.com','','580-399-8019','<p>\r\n<font size=\"2\">They call it &quot;SOUTHERN METAL&quot;... BBQ, bikers, beer, whiskey, fishing, rednecks, rebels and southern women! Music that is laced with hard rhythms, dark and heavy tones, and covered with soulful (sometimes blistering) guitar leads... all delivered with a flair that is uniquely southern. This groove and balance of vocals influence us and drive us to be proud of our roots and deliver a show that people can easily relate to. <br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font size=\"2\">Our sound and style is focused towards the commercial side of rock and metal without allowing ourselves to be cast into the &quot;sellout&quot; category. Oklahoma is the South... last time we looked. We enjoy our sound and seek those that identify with it and we&#39;re proud of what we&#39;ve accomplished. At the end of the day our fans drive us to carry on and hopefully with our music we&#39;ve entertained them, inspired them and changed them.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>3HOD Members:</u><br />\r\n</strong><br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<font size=\"2\">\r\n<p>\r\n<u><strong>Rick Davis<br />\r\n</strong></u>Guitar &amp; Vocals<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>John Hale<br />\r\n</u></strong>Guitar &amp; Vocals<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>Jared Adams<br />\r\n</u></strong>Drums<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>Eli Starkey<br />\r\n</u></strong>Lead Vocals<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>Trei Smith<br />\r\n</u></strong>Bass \r\n</p>\r\n</font><!-- End_Module_368 --><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"../forums/showthread.php?t=403\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt\">Interact with 3 Hours of Darkness&#39; fans</span></a> \r\n',1,'Rick Davis<br />\r\nEli Starky<br />\r\nJohn Hale<br />\r\nJared Adams \r\n',0,''),(1438,1783,'Camilla K',10,45,'myspace.com/camikmusic','','','Hello :) <br/>I\'m a singer/songwriter from Denmark. I\'ve been singing and playing music all my life, and I can\'t imagine a life without it. I\'m half deaf, but that has never stopped me from doing anything, especially music. Beside music and school, I help and support a handicapt young man and even though it can be hard sometimes, I really enjoy it.<br/>I\'ll soon be going to Texas to study and I\'m really looking forward to new experiences and new friends.\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=404\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Camilla K\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1449,1803,'mel white',9,43,'www.myspace.com/melwhite77','','+41 79 771 34 22','',1,'',0,''),(1450,1785,'Change the Station',1,71,'myspace.com/changethestation','157 Hemlock Street','','<span class=\"epktxt\">In the winter months of 2005, in Brooklyn, Change\r\nthe Station began practicing and writing their music together.&nbsp;\r\nInfluenced by the endless subjects and creativity that surrounds them\r\nin NYC, the trio began developing a sound that is as mysterious and\r\nintroverted as the subway, yet powerful and thriving like the millions\r\nof commuters, performers and workers who fill them everyday.&nbsp; The\r\nunconventional-power trio consists of: Lisa Poole (Drums), Michelle\r\nFeliciano (Bass, Synth), and Ian Jacobs (guitar, vocals).&nbsp; One reviewer\r\ndescribes the band\'s energy and ideas as: \"Your high school romance\r\nwritten as an Edgar Allen Poe story,... that belongs on DGC Records\".<br/><br/>Only\r\nsix months after their original conception, in the summer of 2006,\r\nChange the Station made their first recordings.&nbsp; From the aggressive,\r\nnew wave rhythm of \"Remember to Forget\", to the blues influenced \"My\r\nWill\", to the introspective and melodic \"Dethrone\", the 7-song EP\r\nrepresents the many different moods of the group.&nbsp; The EP was reviewed\r\nby hundreds of listeners on garageband.com and three of the tracks were\r\nvoted \"track of the day\" and featured on the web site\'s home page.&nbsp; The\r\nlisteners compared Change the Station\'s sound to a number of bands\r\nincluding Joy Division, The Pixies, Trail of Dead, Nirvana, The\r\nStrokes, and Blur, to name a few.&nbsp; One review noted the opening track,\r\n\"Get Me\", as \"Dark and decadent.&nbsp; Menacing, imaginative and out of the\r\nordinary.\" <br/><br/>CTS have performed in many of NYC\'s most notable\r\nclubs, such as Pianos, Crash Mansion, CBGB\'s, The Delancey, and Lit.&nbsp;\r\nLive performances are extremely energetic and more importantly,\r\ngenuine.&nbsp; They attack their songs completely and mercilessly, unfolding\r\neach song before their crowd humbly and without inhibition.&nbsp; NYC\r\npromoter Amy Chase wrote, \"Change the Station is a swelling ocean,\r\npoised to pull out a tidal wave, they are a slowly closing fist that\r\npacks a punch\".&nbsp; In their endeavors, the trio has been fortunate enough\r\nto share the stage with The Fatales, Abigail Warchild, Lolita Bras,\r\nObject, Salt & Samovar, and many others.<br/><br/>As time passes,\r\nChange the Station continues to get more and more attention from their\r\nsurroundings in NYC.&nbsp; CTS will also be recording new material for a\r\nforthcoming album as the group\'s vision is becoming increasingly\r\nclear.&nbsp; The three incorporate elements of alternative music, indie\r\nrock, electronic, and blues seamlessly.&nbsp; In doing so, they\'ve created a\r\ndistinct and textured sound that is full of integrity.&nbsp; The songs\r\ndisplay an appreciation for both pop songwriting and the traditions of\r\nthe underground music scene. Their arrangement and style makes Change\r\nthe Station as individual as any one of their influences.</span>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=406\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Change the Station\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1452,1809,'Chauvette',1,61,'www.chauvette.com','3404 Tuscany Village Drive','7022106900','<p><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\">Marc started working the circuit in 1976 at the age of 17. His first paying gig was at a biker bar in Watertown NY (then known as Jammer\'s Tavern) with half-brother Robin Davis where he played keyboards, guitar, lead vocals, and wrote original music for the popular upstate NY group \"Wirlwind\". During this period, he turned down an audition in NYC as a guitarist with the king of the twist \"Chubby Checker\". He later joined up with the 8-piece horn band \"Contraband\" and toured Florida with the group in the late 1970\'s. <br/><br/>While with \"Wirlwind\" and \"Contraband\" he shared the stage with such other acts as \"Blue Oyster Cult\", \"Chubby Checker\", \"Benny Mardones\", and \"Leslie West\" of \"Mountain\". \"Contraband\" returned to upstate NY in 1981 where the group disbanded, and a new \"Wirlwind\" band was formed. Wirwind disbanded in 1989. <br/><br/>Marc became interested in electronic music composition as a hobby. He later teamed up with Bob Watts to form \"Chauvette and Watts\" who would later become a staple in resort entertainment in the Thousand Islands in upstate NY. It was there that he would first meet \"The Scintas\", who were already legends in the Alex Bay region. At this time, Frankie Scinta told Chauvette \"If we ever make it big in this business, we\'re going to give you a call\". Marc was flattered but thought nothing would ever become of that. Chauvette was asked to join up with \"The Scintas\" in Las Vegas, Nevada in December of 2000 where he currently resides.<br/><br/><font style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\" face=\"Times New Roman\">In March of 2005, Chauvette caught up with Michael Mustizer, an aspiring film director/producer from the East coast. Chauvette, hoping to land a movie composing/scoring deal, agreed to score the music for a full-length action/ adventure feature called \"The Coldest Winter.\" He spent an entire year with trial and error mixes and re-writes. Finally in January of 2006, the film was released to be viewed at several indie film festivals and would pick up the Hollywood DV Film Festival\'s \"Best Action/Adventure Feature Film\" award, and the Fargo Fantastic Film Festival\'s \"Best Action/Adventure Feature Film\" award as well. The movie is currently under consideration for distribution. Also in the works in 2007 are tracks for the HARPO Sounds Catalog in Chicago. Chauvette\'s instrumental composition \"Osia Con Intensita\" was added recently to the catalog for future production considerations. Chauvette is currently in his own studio composing works for his new project \"702,\" a \"power-pop\" compilation of songs with ideas from a journal kept about moving from a small-town suburb to \"Sin City\".</font></span></p>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=407\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Chauvette\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(2169,2315,'Alberto Daglio',10,45,'','','','',1,'',0,''),(1454,1810,'A Cadence Paradigm',1,74,'freewebs.com/acadenceparadigm','','803 665 3008','<font color=\"#000080\" size=\"4\">A Cadence Paradigm, or ACP, is an up-and-coming band from Columbia, South Carolina with an original sound and a dedication to changing people\'s lives through their music. Hard to categorize, their music features characteristics of rock, jazz, and indie music.</font><br/><br/><br/>Members Include:<br/><br/>Evan Farinholt (Drums/Percussion): Hailing from Washington, DC, Evan is an extraordinarily talented, self-taught drummer who is very dedicated to his skill. A few of Evan\'s many influences include: Jon Theodore, Peter Erskine, Will Calhoun, Sam Fogarino and Terry Bozzio.<br/><br/>Adam Kerr (Guitar): Born and raised in Columbia, SC, Adam has been playing guitar since his childhood. Adam writes much of the music for A Cadence Paradigm as well as his trademarked solos that leave the crowd wanting more ACP. Some of his influences are: The Mars Volta, John Mayer, Wes Montgomery, and Coldplay.<br/><br/>Jeff Saul (Vocals and Guitar): Jeff was also born in Columbia, SC, and began playing guitar and singing at a young age. Jeff writes most of the lyrics for ACP as well as much of the music. Some of his many influences include: Wes Montgomery, Coldplay, Ben Folds, Third Eye Blind, RHCP, John Mayer, and Bob Dylan.<br/><br/><br/>ACP are not your typical band. They are not motivated by fame, by money, or by lust for celebrity status. The common desire among the members of ACP is to emotionally empower their listeners through the emotional charge provided by their music. We have all had an emotion or feeling enhanced or reversed by the power of a song. The goal of ACP is to use this mysterious power of music and the messages of their lyrics to impact the lives of their listeners.\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=408\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with A Cadence Paradigm\'s fans</span></a><br/>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1458,1821,'Downfire',1,14,'www.downfire.net','','845-569-3068','<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Band:</span><br/>David Diaz &#8211; Vocals/Guitars<br/>Carlos Vega &#8211; Guitars<br/>Mark Parisi &#8211; Bass<br/>Dave Gerlach - Drums<br/><br/><br/><span style=\"font-family: Georgia; font-size: 10pt;\">Since releasing their first full-length 13-track album &#8220;Redemption&#8221;. This Hard Rock/Metal band has been selling out shows and merchandise to an eager ever growing fan base in the Tri-state area. Harboring influences such as Metallica, Black Sabbath, White Zombie, Black Label Society & Red Hot Chilli Peppers Downfire is expanding it&#8217;s shows to patient fans along&nbsp; the east coast in the summer/Fall of 2007. <br/><br/>Downfire has shared the stage with national acts such as <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Testament, Zebra, W.A.S.P.,&nbsp; Metal Church, The Misfits & This Oct Overkill</span> from venues as close to home as the well known &#8220;Chance&#8221; in Poughkeepsie, NY to clubs in surrounding states from Massachusetts to Virginia.<br/><br/>In a world of music where it&#8217;s impossible to sound uninfluenced we embrace our diverse tastes in music ranging from one members love of old school metal, vocal and guitar harmonies to another members love of the accents and unpredictable structure of The Red Hot Chilli Peppers and Black Eyed Peas. This has allowed us to reinvent our sound into a band that when listening to you can hear the various influences but not define by only one.</span><br/><br/><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">www.downfire.net</span><br style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">www.myspace.com/downfire</span><br/><br/>Contact:<br/>Carlos Vega<br/>carlos@downfire.net',1,'',0,''),(1461,1828,'Collinz Room',1,71,'www.myspace.com/collinzroom','','','<b>Hello everyone a little news on whats going on!\r\nFirst off this year has been an exciting year for us so far we are\r\ncurrently in pre-production right now working on our new record! We are\r\nlocked it up for the month of July at <a href=\"http://www.chessvolt.com/\"><u>The Chess Volt!</u></a>\r\nWe have been working extremely hard, preparing and finalizing! This\r\nrecord is going to be an amazing record for us. Alot of emotion and\r\nstruggle along with what we believe in!\r\nAlot of this record has to do with walking threw hardship and\r\nchallenges as we grow up in our lives! Which makes it worth all the\r\ntime we have been spending on it! We want to express to you how we feel\r\npoint blank! Get ready for us</b>',1,'',0,''),(1465,1832,'David Harbuck',1,105,'www.DavidHarbuck.com','','9122241211','<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=409\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with David Harbuck\'s fans</span></a>',0,'',0,''),(1467,1834,'Fire with Fire',1,14,'myspace.com/firewithfiremusic','139 Buffalo Ave.','609-593-3627','<span id=\"ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_lblBio\"><br/>Fire with Fire is more than a band, it\'s everyone and everything. It\'s what we see happening in the world that surrounds us. Five musicians playing for one cause...to connect. What started as a hobby grew into a way of life. So join us in our effort to spread the fire, let\'s grow together. <br/><br/>-Tommy Conwell,&nbsp;on-air personality&nbsp;for 94.1 WYSP, Philadelphia\'s top rated rock station says, \"this band has alot of marketing potential, very catchy tunes!\"<br/>-After a recent show review, Philadelphia\'s Origivation Magazine (August 2007)(www.origivation.com) had this to say about the band: <br/>\"Fire with Fire possesses the potency of the noonday sun!\" <br/>\"Flip, Dave, Rudy, Matt, and Ant are a serious band, visible from the calm, focused diligence with which they set up their equipment on stage.\" <br/>\"This kind of ferocity is akin to what permeated the American punk/hardcore movement of the early 1980\'s.\" <br/>\"The uncharacteristically poignant and sentimental \"Heartbreak\"\" \"..tightly-constructed and catchy \"20 more to follow\"\" <br/>\"If the biggest understatement ever made is that the Frech Revolution was a little bloody, then a close second is that a Fire with Fire performance is, uh...rather lively.\"</span> <br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=410\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 8pt\">Interact with Fire with Fire\'s fans</span></a>',1,'',0,''),(1469,1296,'J James DiNardo',1,0,'','','','<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"color: blue;\"><span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span>At age 7 I was performing on stage. I played at expo 67 when I was 11. Since then music has been a driving\r\nforce in my life. My parents have been my greatest influence and it doesn&#8217;t\r\nhurt to be a member of a musically talented family. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"color: blue;\"><span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span>Some of my musical influences are:<br/>\r\n<span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>The Beatles<br/>\r\n<span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>The Rolling Stones<br/>\r\n<span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Chicago<br/>\r\n<span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Stevie Wonder<br/>\r\n<span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Bonnie Raitt<br/>\r\n<span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>James Taylor<br/>\r\n<span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Jimi Hendrix<br/>\r\n<span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Ray Charles<br/>\r\nBecause of my eclectic ear it is difficult to pigeonhole my music into just one\r\ngenre. In addition to working solo I have also performed with:<br/>\r\n<span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Dan Hill &#8211; &#8216;Sometimes When\r\nWe Touch&#8217;<br/>\r\n<span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Retro &#8211; &#8216;Badfinger&#8217;<br/>\r\n<span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Heavier &#8211; &#8216;Triumph&#8217;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"color: blue;\">I&#8217;m always interested to hear what\r\npeople think of my music and always open to a collaboration!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=411\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with J James DiNardo\'s fans</span></a>',0,'',0,''),(1471,1837,'MIKE BORGIA',1,69,'www.mikeborgia.com','','917 658-7127','<br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=412\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with MIKE BORGIA\'s fans</span></a>',0,'',0,''),(1472,1838,'The Kin',1,71,'www.thekin.com','','','\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"TEXT-ALIGN: center\" align=\"center\"><em>The Kin blends the atmospheric musical wave of old school U2 and groove pop sensibilities of Duran Duran with the vocal soul of Jeff Buckley.<span>&nbsp; </span>The Kin juxtapose dark melodies with catchy hooks and solid musicianship, garnering comparisons to everything from the Cure to Coldplay.</em><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>&#8211; BMI</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText2\" style=\"TEXT-ALIGN: left\" align=\"left\"><?xml:namespace prefix = o /><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText2\" style=\"TEXT-ALIGN: left\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt\">Quietly considered one of <?xml:namespace prefix = st1 /><st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">New York City</st1:place></st1:city>\'s most promising independent acts (sold out at the Bowery Ballroom, Mercury Lounge, and Pianos), The Kin&#8217;s sound is a dynamic exchange between Australian brothers <strong>Isaac and Thorry Koren</strong>. These multi-talented musicians not only write their own material, they also play multiple instruments, creating a rare and audibly stunning experience.<span>&nbsp; </span>The duo is currently promoting their fourth album, &#8220;Rise & Fall,&#8221; scheduled to release this summer on Aletheia Records. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText2\" style=\"TEXT-ALIGN: left\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText2\" style=\"TEXT-ALIGN: left\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt\">The Kin&#8217;s music is a layered experience combining raw passion and the poetic. <em>The New York Times</em> describes them as \"bombastic,\" <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:city w:st=\"on\"><em>TimeOut</em></st1:city><em> <st1:state w:st=\"on\">NY</st1:state></em></st1:place> calls their music \"soulful,\" and <em>Billboard Magazine</em> raves, \"The Australian siblings have a radiant gift for songwriting and performing...hearing their partnership is a humbling experience.\"<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText2\" style=\"TEXT-ALIGN: left\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText2\" style=\"TEXT-ALIGN: left\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt\">The Koren brothers came to settle in NYC in 2001 and immediately hit the bar and lounge circuit as an acoustic duo.<span>&nbsp; </span>In 2003, they added on a drummer, keyboardist and bassist with whom they produced three albums:<span>&nbsp; </span>&#8220;Live at the Pussy Cat&#8221; (October 2006), &#8220;Black&#8221; (Sept. 2005), &#8220;Red&#8221; (April 2005), and their debut album &#8220;Tracing&#8221; (May 2004).<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText2\" style=\"TEXT-ALIGN: left\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt\"><br/>The talented siblings first discovered their musical abilities as teenagers.<span>&nbsp; </span>Originally from <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:city w:st=\"on\">Adelaide</st1:city>, <st1:country w:st=\"on\" -region=\"\">Australia</st1:country></st1:place>, they grew up in a musical household (their mother, Madeleine McRae, was a cast member of the original touring production of &#8220;Hair&#8221;.)<span>&nbsp; </span>Thorry, the younger Koren, began studying music at age 10, taking jazz guitar and voice lessons, while Isaac just picked up singing and taught himself to play a Fender Rhodes piano about 4 years ago.<span>&nbsp; </span>It wasn&#8217;t until their late teens that they first collaborated on a song together.<span>&nbsp; </span>&#8220;We were writing this song as a gift for someone,&#8221; says Thorry, &#8220;and when we started singing it together in harmony, we were like, &#8220;Whoa!&#8221;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText2\" style=\"TEXT-ALIGN: left\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText2\" style=\"TEXT-ALIGN: left\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt\">Being so close and having musical genes has certainly contributed to their spectacular songwriting.<span>&nbsp; </span>In addition to their voices blending so smoothly, they have a &#8220;kindred&#8221; spirit and vision in their creative process.<span>&nbsp; </span>&#8220;The songs just come out of us,&#8221; Isaac mused.<span>&nbsp; </span>With the two of them seldom disagreeing about their musical choices, their songs sort of write themselves.<span>&nbsp; </span>The songs have an ethereal, almost epic feeling to them, that there is something much more profound than mere love ballads or folk rock tunes.<span>&nbsp; </span>The brothers insist they have no agenda to promote, only to create a blank canvas on which their listeners can project their own emotions. &#8220;Each person gets something different out of them,&#8221; says Thorry. &#8220;They are not political or even spiritual.<span>&nbsp; </span>They&#8217;re about being human.&#8221;<span>&nbsp; </span>Isaac adds, &#8220;We want people to be uplifted, to feel a heightened sense of self.\"<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText2\" style=\"TEXT-ALIGN: left\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText2\" style=\"TEXT-ALIGN: left\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt\">Whatever it is, it&#8217;s definitely paying off.<span>&nbsp; </span>They are selling out box offices regionally from <st1:city w:st=\"on\">Boston</st1:city> to <st1:place w:st=\"on\"><st1:city w:st=\"on\">Washington</st1:city> <st1:state w:st=\"on\">DC</st1:state></st1:place>. Their songs are also featured on both commercial, specialized programming (Q104.3 NY, 104.7 MA, WMMR) in addition to independent radio stations (WZBC Boston, XM Radio.)<span>&nbsp; </span>Between touring, grassroots promotion, and the support of Tower Records and independent stores across the Northeast and Mid-Atlantic, The Kin has developed a solid underground following and sold over 12,000 units independently. <br/><br/>What&#8217;s most striking is how incredibly approachable and compassionate they are.<span>&nbsp; </span>In addition to entertaining audiences, The Kin use their music to raise money for worthy causes such as the Save Darfur Coalition and the Madison Square Boys and Girls Club.<span>&nbsp; </span>Not to mention their extreme good looks and charisma have helped win the intense loyalty of several hundred fans, most of which have stuck by them for the past 3 or more years.<span>&nbsp; </span>One fan/friend remarked, &#8220;They not only look beautiful, they&#8217;re beautiful inside.&#8221;<span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>',1,'',0,''),(1473,1839,'Alexa Wilkinson',10,45,'www.alexawilkinson.com','','','<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><br/>Debut album &#8211; &#8220;Lullaby Appetite&#8221;<br/><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Biography</span><br/></div>&#8220;I think a lot of what makes music great is the story behind the artist. All artists have a shared passion for music, but every single person has a different story and a different experience to share.&#8221; &#8211; Alexa Wilkinson<br/><br/>ALEXA WILKINSON is more than meets the eye.&nbsp; Her pretty, girl-next-door face on a petite 5-foot 4-inch frame suggests nothing of the emotional maturity displayed in her debut album &#8220;Lullaby Appetite,&#8221; now available on iTunes and scheduled for public release this July through DNK Records.&nbsp; Alexa&#8217;s evolution into a musical artist originated from common childhood experiences. <br/><br/>&nbsp;I first got into music because of a boy. Yes, that\'s right. I was about 10 years old and I had myself a little elementary school boyfriend who was taking trumpet lessons. So I decided I would take them too. Sadly for him, I got good really fast and he just kind of stayed bad. So I started playing the trumpet in band. Then I asked my dad for a guitar for my birthday when I was 11, he got me one, and the first song I ever learned was \"Hotel California\" (which my dad taught me). My family was a huge influence on my love for music. My sister who has always been good at finding awesome music taught me everything I know about alternative music. The first tape I remember buying was Nirvana \"Nevermind.\" Anyway, so by age 12, I had come to love everything from Sublime, to Shawn Colvin, to The Eagles. I realized I could sing around 13 when moving to a new state not only spurred new emotions but talents as well in writing. I started writing poetry and fell in love with free form. One day in the shower I think I started humming a tune and turned a poem into a song. Everything pretty much evolved from that moment when I fell even more in love with song writing.<br/><br/>Lullaby Appetite consists of 11 songs that display a unique of blend of music from jazz, rock and folk influences.&nbsp; Penned and performed by Alexa herself, these songs represent her own personal journey through life, love, acceptance, and lessons learned. Her fresh, smooth vocals slide easily around the extremely memorable melodies, toe-tapping rhythms and sprite guitar playing.&nbsp; The lyrics are rich with expression, exposing a vulnerability and honesty without na&iuml;vete.&nbsp; Rather there is an emotional maturity of looking at life with an optimistic eye, accepting one&#8217;s mistakes, and moving on.&nbsp; <br/><br/>From the jazz inspired &#8220;Sad Eyed Annabelle, to the upbeat and edgy &#8220;Good Fight,&#8221; Alexa&#8217;s songs center around love and relationships, something which everyone can relate to.&nbsp; In &#8220;Sad Eyed Annabelle,&#8221; Alexa portrays an unhealthy relationship where the girl is manipulating the boy whereas &#8220;Good Fight&#8221; reveals Wilkinson&#8217;s more playful side, such as picking a fight in a relationship. Fan favorite and Alexa&#8217;s first single, &#8220;Of Graves&#8221; depicts a young woman reminiscing about a past lover, while &#8220;Lullaby Appetite&#8221; talks about a long-distance friendship.<br/><br/>Half of the songs on &#8220;Lullaby Appetite&#8221; were produced and co-written by singer-songwriter Josh Kelley.&nbsp; So naturally, Kelley would have Wilkinson along on tour with him.&nbsp; Alexa opened for Josh in 10 cities across the US, from April 10th through May 4th, 2007.&nbsp; Being a fan of Alexa himself, Kelley stated &#8220;I was immediately impressed with Alexa&#8217;s music&#8212;she is an extremely talented singer and songwriter whose unique sound will no doubt propel her to the top.&nbsp; She&#8217;s got such a natural, easygoing style to her music that anyone from all ages can relate to it.&nbsp; I&#8217;m proud to have her on tour with me.&#8221;<br/><br/>www.myspace.com/alexawilkinson<br/>www.alexawilkinson.com<br/><br/><br/><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/forums/showthread.php?t=413\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Interact with Alexa Wilkinson\'s fans</span></a>',1,'',0,''),(1499,1878,'Kate Voegele',1,61,'www.katevoegele.com','','','<span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: \'Times New Roman\'\">The musical landscape is teeming with singer/songwriters, many of them quite capable, but only a handful have something truly distinctive to offer. Kate Voegele belongs in the latter category. Don&#8217;t Look Away, Voegele&#8217;s first full-length album (MySpace Records), is a revelation, as the 20-year-old writer/singer, belying her tender years, delivers songs of depth and insight with a powerfully seductive voice that maintains a fierce presence amid dynamic rock grooves and infectious pop hooks. Produced by the veteran Marshall Altman (Matt Nathanson, Mark Broussard), Don&#8217;t Look Away is a bravura effort from an old soul with a youthful spirit; think of her album as a female parallel to John Mayer&#8217;s Room for Squares&#8212;at once a zeitgeist-capturing landmark and the launchpad for a viable career.<br/><br/>The tracks range from the rootsy acoustic ballad &#8220;Wish You Were,&#8221; with its mandolin and accordion filigree, and the sparse, piano-based &#8220;Kindly Unspoken&#8221; to the widescreen heartbreak anthem &#8220;Only Fooling Myself&#8221; and the ironically titled &#8220;It&#8217;s Only Life,&#8221; a soaring expression of female empowerment, which Voegele describes as &#8220;a motivational, uplifting song about dealing with situations rather than trying to hide from them.&#8221; &#8220;One Way or Another&#8221; is an edgy rocker about romantic victimization, while the punchy &#8220;<?xml:namespace prefix = st1 /><st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Chicago</st1:place></st1:city>,&#8221; she says, &#8220;is a metaphorical representation of any kind of escape, about just needing to get away. The line at the end of the chorus is, &#8216;I&#8217;ll be on the seven o&#8217;clock to <st1:city w:st=\"on\"><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Chicago</st1:place></st1:city>,&#8217; so it refers to a specific city, but it&#8217;s universally applicable.&#8221;<br/><br/>While the concerns Voegele touches on in her songs are contemporary, her sensibility is deeply rooted. Growing up surrounded by the music of seminal singer/songwriters like Carole King, James Taylor, Joni Mitchell and Eric Clapton, thanks to her musician father, Voegele absorbed everything she heard as if by osmosis, and began writing her own songs at 15. &#8220;It&#8217;s my personal goal to continue the standard set by those before me,&#8221; she says of her timeless approach. &#8220;No matter how a song develops, my main goal is to reach people, because there were so many musicians who spoke to me, and still do, to help me to deal with situations. It\'s so easy nowadays with all the technology for people to fake it. For me, it&#8217;s just so important that the true musical talent and passion for the songs be there.&#8221;<br/><br/>Voegele, a Cleveland native now in her sophomore year at Miami of Ohio, is no neophyte; indeed, before she&#8217;d finished high school, the youngster had notebooks filled with songs and was regularly performing live with the poise of a veteran. Kate was 16 when some rough demos she&#8217;d recorded with her father led to an opening slot at a stop on John Mayer and Counting Crows&#8217; 2003 shed tour, followed by second-stage appearances in front of Patty Griffin, Aimee Mann and Mindy Smith. She subsequently opened for Dave Matthews, the Wreckers, Howie Day, John Mellencamp and Jamie Cullum, as well as performing at two consecutive Farm-Aid concerts, Summerfest, SXSW, CMJ and dozens of club shows at venues including New York&#8217;s Bitter End and the House of Blues in Chicago. Additionally, her song &#8220;I Won&#8217;t Disagree&#8221; took first place over 4,000 entries to the New York Songwriters&#8217; Circle, winning Pop Song of the Year, while &#8220;Only Fooling Myself&#8221; was the winner of the USA Songwriting Contest. One early admirer from the A&R world asserted that Kate could be &#8220;the commercial Patty Griffin,&#8221; in reference to the emotional and intellectual depth of her writing and singing. <br/><br/>Ambitious by nature and powerfully motivated by these gratifying early experiences, Voegele continued to write, including collaborations with pros like Jim McGorman (Michelle Branch) and Peter Zizzo (Avril Lavigne), and to record, working up a set of impressive demos in L.A. with Altman in 2004, marking the beginning of what has turned out to be a fruitful partnership. Inevitably, the music Voegele was turning out caught the ears of a number of A&R reps and label heads, leading to showcases and a number of offers, none of which felt right to the canny and discerning young artist. But after meeting with the staff of MySpace Records at the request of A&R man Jon Pikus, who&#8217;d wanted to sign her during a previous stint at Columbia, Kate knew she&#8217;d found the right label to partner with.<br/><br/>&#8220;When I walked into MySpace, I really didn&#8217;t know what to expect because the label was just starting out,&#8221; says Kate. &#8220;But the atmosphere was really cool and so different from the other labels I&#8217;d been to, a lot of which were cold and intimidating. MySpace wasn&#8217;t like that at all. Tom [yes, the original &#8220;friend&#8221; does really exist; Tom Anderson is the site&#8217;s co-founder and the president of the label] and Jon were really easy to talk to, and right away I felt comfortable there. The icing on the cake was that everything about the label was something I felt was right for me. I&#8217;d been looking for a label where I&#8217;d have artistic freedom and where they&#8217;d appreciate the music in its original form and not try to make it anything it wasn&#8217;t. That&#8217;s what I found at MySpace, along with an innovative approach to marketing, which is something I didn&#8217;t see at any other label. The people at MySpace are taking an approach that&#8217;s really different, and I&#8217;m excited to be part of it.&#8221;<br/><br/>Voegele signed with MySpace in October of 2006, choosing to work once again with Altman. &#8220;She met with me and said she was talking to Jon at MySpace,&#8221; the producer recalls. &#8220;I love the idea of MySpace&#8212;I think it&#8217;s a great marketing platform&#8212;and I knew Jon would allow Kate to pursue her artistic vision, which had really evolved over the last couple of years, so I told her I&#8217;d love to produce her record.&#8221;<br/><br/>Soon thereafter they went into Track Record Studios in <st1:place w:st=\"on\">North Hollywood</st1:place> where Emmylou Harris had cut a number of classic LPs, and laid down 12 tracks live off the floor in a three-day burst of sustained inspiration. Among the A-list players who worked on the project (drawn by the strength of Voegele&#8217;s songs, according to Altman) were guitarists Dino Meneghin (Liz Phair, Ani Difranco, Broussard) and Michael Chavez (Sarah McLachlan, Mayer) Eric Robinson, bass player Jonathan Ahrens (Rosie Thomas, Warren Barfield), drummer Aaron Sterling (Liz Phair) and percussionist Chris Lovejoy (AM, Charlie Hunter Quartet), with the renowned Niko Bolas (Neil Young, Fiona Apple, Rachael Yamagata) engineering.<br/><br/>&#8220;Kate is a pop artist, but she has much more soul and integrity than the word &#8216;pop&#8217; would suggest,&#8221; Altman observes. &#8220;Her music is organic and has a strong lyrical perspective with a lot of emotional currency to it. It&#8217;s so refreshing to hear a female artist as young as Kate is who has such a deep perspective as a writer. She&#8217;s got it, and I think this record is pretty special.&#8221;<br/><br/>Poised, beautiful, armed with unforgettable songs and a voice to match, Kate Voegele is poised on the brink of something big indeed.</span>',0,'',0,''),(1474,1840,'New Professionals',1,66,'www.myspace.com/newprofessionals','123 you wish','9173340613','\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1476,1843,'Sub Rose',1,71,'www.subrosemusic.com','','','Jason Jones, vocalist has written and recorded music with many\r\ndifferent artists. Skills in production, recording, and songwriting,\r\nthis was his soul project he wanted to accomplish. From then on he\r\nvouched to create this band and push it forward. You will hear\r\neverything in this music. It\'s got a touch of hip hop, jazz, pop, rock,\r\nfunk, and all of that combined into one catchy and unique sound.',1,'',0,''),(1517,1876,'John Willemse',10,48,'','','','Recently received an honorable mention in the VH1 song of the year competition, for his single Wages of War. This competition is judged by top managers, producers and artists working in the music industry, such as; Stephine Wright the A&R Manager of Universal Music, singer Norah Jones who is an eight time Grammy winner, Bon Jovi, Paul Dellafiora the Senior Director of Artist Development at Capitol Records, and many others. In 2006, John recorded one of his songs entitled &#8220;A Home Within Myself,&#8221; with pianist, Jeremy Wall, a founding member of the Grammy winning Jazz band, Spyro Gyra. <spacer type=\"horizontal\" size=\"50\">In the past months he has been working on a demo entitled, A Pocket of Secrets & A Six String Smile, with 10 songs completed and 11 more in progress. \"Many of my songs are the bandages for wounds, and when I\'m done singing or writing a song I\'m healed,\" says John Willemse. With songs ranging from his personal grief, such as &#8220;A Home Within Myself,&#8221; to the political and social issues in \"Marionette\" where he sings, &#8220;I read the head lines yesterday, and sighed&#8230; well even my breath felt out of place&#8230;16 died in enemy fire and a celebrity decided not to tie the knot.&#8221;<spacer type=\"HORIZONTAL\" size=\"50\"> Currently John Willemse is finishing up his Bachelor of Arts degree for music industry at the State University of New York, College at Oneonta. There he can be found performing at The General Clintons Pub or The SEGO Wine Bar. When he&#8217;s not at college he performs in his hometown, Warwick, NY, at John Martins restaurant, or GW&#8217;s Bar.',1,'',0,''),(1481,837,'A Thousand Lies',7,84,'http://www.myspace.com/athousandliesrock','','','A Thousand Lies are a 5-piece Newcastle based heavy rock band. They came together in January 2005 as individuals who all wanted to form a band that was new and exciting, but most of all special. With&nbsp;Dave McQuillan&nbsp;providing elaborate, solid drum rhythms and Steve Bagnall complimenting these on bass guitar. Steve Barclay and Andrew Bright on duelling lead guitars and all fronted by lead singer Chris Nesbitt. With hard-edged riffs, blistering solos, memorable melodies and complex arrangements, coupled with the awesome live performances. A Thousand Lies are a force to be reckoned with. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nAlways wanted Dragonforce to be slightly less ridiculous? Always wanted Dream Theater to be slightly more interesting? Think Soil getting a blow-job from Iron Maiden and you&#39;re getting close. a bloody, sweaty, stomping workout of the finest order. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nwww.44caliber.co.uk \r\n',1,'',0,''),(1482,516,'Samuel OBie',9,0,'','','','\r\n\r\n<h1>Samuel OBie</h1>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\">Born & rased in the small town of\r\nHillsborough, it seems as if we&#8217;ve always sang.<span style=\"\">&nbsp;\r\n</span>Our late mother, Joyce Long OBie stood us on a table & trained us to\r\nshare w/audiences. After her passing in &#8217;71, Samuel, the eldest showed the\r\ncapacity for leadership & @ age 17 & a senior @ Orange High, landed the\r\ndream job as keyboardist w/Shirley Caesar.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\">Moved to Charlotte in \'92 at the advice of John\r\nKee, then released CD entitled \"VISION & A MESSAGE\" in \'96.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>A new style of writing from the earlier\r\n\"just church music\" gave life to \"HILLSBOROUGH (NC) USA\"\r\n(story of growing up in the \'70\'s w/country sound), \"TRAGEDY\" (title\r\ntrack to solo project about 9-11-01), \"YOUR LOVE\" (a jazz\r\ninstrumental), \"GREAT THINGS\" a swing with scriptural text &\r\n&#8220;DESTINY&#8221; addresses a recent divorce & loss of minister of music position.\r\nOther songs have been recorded by Edwin Hawkins (DO YOU KNOW HIM, THE BLOOD\r\n& MAKE A JOYFUL NOISE), Shirley Caesar (PSALMS 34) & John Kee (COUNT IT\r\nALL JOY). <i><u>Moved back home December &#8217;06</u></i>. \"Hillsborough (NC)\r\nUSA\" performed as part of the opening of \"Hog Day\" &#8216;07. Hometown\r\nguy working hard @ his craft w/his talented family/band (Paula, Lyle, Ricky\r\n& Ravon OBie).<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>We feel it is our\r\ntime & season to continue showcasing our talents & fulfill the dream of\r\nour mother through original Christian/Gospel Music.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>We love being together.<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>Music & singing just makes that\r\nexperience much sweeter.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\">Music\r\nResume/Website-SamuelOBie.com/Link:Allmusic.com-Samuel OBie<o:p></o:p></span></u></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\"><o:p><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">&nbsp;</span></o:p></span></u></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\">Distribution/CD Baby.com &\r\nRadio/RadioDirectX.com/GMA Member<o:p></o:p></span></u></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\"><o:p><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">&nbsp;</span></o:p></span></u></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\">Industry Work:</span></u><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\">John P. Kee/New Life, Bobby Jones/Las Vegas\r\nArtist Retreat (\'99-\'01), Edwin Hawkins Music & Arts Seminar\r\n(\'86,\'87,\'94,\'95 &\'97), Shirley Caesar (\'71-\'80), \'07 Carrboro July 4th\r\nFestival,\'07 Festival for the Eno, &#8217;07 Voices/Praise & &#8217;07 Carrboro\r\nMusicFest.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\">Songs Recorded</span></u><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\">:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\">\"All Things In Jesus I Find\" by Bishop Jeff\r\nBanks & Revival Temple/Savoy<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\">\"I Never Shall Forget\" by John Howard\r\nCaravan/ Savoy<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\">\"Do You Know Him?\" by Edwin Hawkins\r\nToledo/Bellmark<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\">\"Psalms 34\" by Shirley Caesar/Word<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\">\"The Blood\" by Edwin Hawkins\r\nTampa/Harmony<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\">\"Make A Joyful Noise\" by Edwin Hawkins<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\">Discography:</span></u><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\">\"More Things Are Wrought Thru Prayer\"\r\n(1981) Independent<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\">\"Love\" (1984) Morada Records/Nashville,\r\nTN<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\">\"Vision & A Message\" (1996) Salexo\r\nMusic (Samuel\'s label)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\">\"Samuel OBie/\"Unity\" Choir (2003)\r\nIndependent<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\">\"Tragedy\" (2007) Salexo Music<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" verdana=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\">&#8220;Special Times&#8221; (2008) Salexo Music</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" arial=\"\" ,=\"\" sans-serif=\"\" ;=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1483,1853,'Princess Riot',1,0,'www.myspace.com/princessriot','','','Princess Riot don&#8217;t want to be the new queens of the cloned age. They are no Barbie girls, no wobbly Avril Whibley. No, your Little Mermaid is about to trade in her tail and not for no pink assed Daisy guitar. They are chained to the Rawk now and like the siren voiced Evanescence these sisters (plus one guy) in sonics are doing it for themselves. You can&#8217;t grow up in Ajax , the corner suburb of Sum 41, Not By Choice and Protest The Hero, and not learn how to give it and give it hard. It&#8217;s a battle hard town named for a battle hard ship. Sure they&#8217;re gurls and they have a soft side, velvet pajama parties of cuddlecore and it peeks into the songs. Just remember Princess Riot wear the pants. They ain&#8217;t playas but they have your number, don&#8217;t look to this band to shine at the Mallmart coffee slinging McJob routine, work until your womb takes you to the tomb, Daddy calls the shots until he hands your hand over. Thanks but no thanks. Princess Riot know the road to Dreamville is as pitted as Highway 66, they know it doesn&#8217;t even go all the way&#8230; but they are taking it because what is the point of being a girl in the 21st century if you can&#8217;t. What is the point of girl power if its merely token power. Were the Spices just cute or was there a message in their tedium. The songs of Princess Riot take chances so PR follows. The O.G. of Riot Girlz, Kim Deal of Sonic Youth, the Babes In Toyland, L7, they are the ladies in the Princess&#8217;s posse. They are the Godmothers of the Riot. The Made It aunts. These Princesses are not looking for love, they are expecting respect and when you hear their songs you will agree they can also expect success. Just remember it will be on their terms. The line up consists of not your average everyday Joes, but intriguing characters you may find quite animated. Fronted by the band you have the demonic cheerleader Lindz Riot taming the lead vocals and bass guitar. Her partner in crime and the child of punk Val Knox who knows how to rock the old skool vocals and guitar. There\'s also the electric Jules with her youthful attitude and almost-ADD shining through in the guitar she writes and plays. And with not much to say, but making up for it on the drums you have the bashful Darcy. Combining all their forces together they believe that with each song comes a new story to be told that should rock to the fullest. They will not quit until they have something epic. They will not rest until they have music fans leaving the venues with a catchy tune in their head and a starvation for more candy flavoured rock. With every band comes a journey and quite a few stories to be told from every adventure. For the 5 years now this band has been together they have quite abit to put onto their musical resume. Their biggest achievement so far with the most memorable stories is playing the Vans Warped Tour in 2005 in Quebec City, Quebec and then again in 2006 in Barrie, Ontario. In 2005 they were discovered in one of Toronto\'s rockhouses by producer Joel Kazmi. He took this project into the studio to record a 3 song demo which is a sample of what&#8217;s to come so far. They have plans to record a full album together by the end of 2007. Also in 2005 Daisy Rock guitars discovered these scraping by musicians and were awesome enough to sign an endorsement deal. You can see the lovely Bass Guitar known as \"Jinx\" making an appearance at every show. Passion, Drive, Blood, Sweat and Beers. The future of Princess Riot is bright, at times almost blinding. Everyone gets what they deserve, so watch your back. Expect the unexpected, but expect something historic from the artists of Princess Riot. ',1,'',0,''),(1484,1850,'Crow Hollow Blonde',1,71,'crowhollowblonde.com','','270-799-5599','Crow Hollow Blonde plays rock music.',1,'',0,''),(1487,1860,'Mo chedda records',4,22,'www.myspace.com/mocheddarecords949','27961 lucero','949-206-1958','',1,'',0,''),(1489,1862,'Rotten Cheri',1,71,'www.rottencheri.com','','','Amongst a music scene filled with pretense, Rotten Cheri keep it simple by writing irresistible, hook laden songs infused with a sense of fun and sensuality that is resonating with a new and expanding base of fans.&nbsp; <br/><br/>The Brooklyn, NY rock trio&#8217;s new album, 02, is both a statement of purpose and a labor of love that required some very real sacrifices to be made on the band&#8217;s part.\r\n\r\nThe seeds of Rotten Cheri were planted with the partnership of guitarist/keyboardist Kee Chung and drummer Howard Alper.&nbsp; The two were playing together when Howard became friendly with co-worker Stephanie St. Hilaire, who would soon become Rotten Cheri&#8217;s vocalist.&nbsp; Recounts Howard, &#8220;Steph and I were working at the same gym together and she knew I was working on a project with Kee.&nbsp; She kept bothering me at work, telling me that she could sing.&nbsp; She was so relentless about it that finally we had her rehearse with us &#8211; and she was perfect.&#8221;&nbsp; <br/><br/>Kee and Howard immediately asked Stephanie, a California native, to join the band. \r\n\r\nWith the addition of Stephanie, the band, now named Rotten Cheri, began to find their sound, a mixture of Kee and Howard&#8217;s love of hard rock and Stephanie&#8217;s &#8220;California girl&#8221; influences of No Doubt, Blink-182, swing and ska.&nbsp; They also began playing the NYC club circuit where they quickly gained a reputation as a high-powered and dynamic live act, in part due to Stephanie&#8217;s sense of drama, honed in her background in theater and years of performing experience.\r\n\r\n<br/><br/>After a couple of years of constant rehearsing and playing in New York clubs, the band settled down to write and record.&nbsp; Recording at Sugar Box studios, they quickly realized that if they were going to be able to pay for the album, some sacrifices would have to be made.&nbsp; Kee discovered that he would have to find a cheaper place to live in order to continue paying the studio, so he moved into a cheaper apartment.&nbsp; Howard sold his baseball card collection for studio time, and Stephanie, well, Stephanie made the most rock n&#8217; roll sacrifice of all; she sold her eggs.\r\n\r\n<br/><br/>That obvious devotion to the music is evident in the band&#8217;s debut album 02.&nbsp; Intense and hard rocking, lyrically, the songs reflect the ups and downs the band was going through while recording.&nbsp; As Stephanie explains, &#8220;At the time I first start writing, everything is so serious. I write about serious things, but with the music we make fun of it and make light of it.&nbsp; My lyrics complement the music that Howard and Kee write perfectly.&#8221;\r\n\r\n<br/><br/>&#8220;Things I Hate About You&#8221; captures the musical and lyrical vibe of the band to a &#8220;T.&#8221;&nbsp; Stephanie&#8217;s vocal is immediately engaging, telling the tale of her relationship with her former roommate, a small town girl, who, as Stephanie recounts, &#8220;started working at a fashion magazine and started to change.&nbsp; She dumped her old life and who she was so should could accomplish things.&#8221;&nbsp; And as that first verse ends, the song explodes into a Kee&#8217;s guitar and Howard&#8217;s drums, supporting and expanding upon Stephanie&#8217;s immensely catchy and melodic chorus.\r\n\r\nKee&#8217;s ominously sensual guitar and keyboard riffs highlight &#8220;Before It&#8217;s Over,&#8221; a lament of an off and on and off again relationship.&nbsp; As Stephanie says, &#8220;I wrote about a past relationship that never ended, even though I thought it was kaput.&nbsp; He promised that he wanted to spend the rest of his life with me.&nbsp; It was all one promise after another broken promise.&#8221; &nbsp;\r\n\r\n<br/><br/>The beauty of Rotten Cheri is that they are the perfect mixture of lightness and darkness &#8211; dark enough to have depth and resonance that one can sink into, light and catchy enough that one can forget about the darkness and just sing along to their irresistible melodies and choruses.&nbsp; <br/><br/>The band is now working to take their music and career to the next level &#8211; to an indie label, to music conferences and to film and television.&nbsp; The more that this band&#8217;s music is exposed, the brighter their future will be.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;\r\n\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1490,1863,'Clown Sack',1,14,'myspace.com/clownsack','','','\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><u><span style=\"color: red;\">Schloppy:<o:p></o:p></span></u></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"color: red;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"color: red;\">As an infant, Edward Sebastian\r\nMontague, was kidnapped from his parent\'s mansion in </span><st1:city><st1:place><span style=\"color: red;\">Prague</span></st1:place></st1:city><span style=\"color: red;\">. The crime was committed by his trusted and loved nanny. The\r\nnanny felt forced to kidnap the young boy, because she did not receive enough money from Mr. Montague to feed her eight children, or pay for her small dilapidated home. She felt it would be easy. After a reward was posted, the nanny would say\r\nshe found young Edward and return him to his parents. However, the plan went <br/>\r\nterribly wrong. Mr. and Mrs. Montague did not post a reward; rumor had it that the couple had thoughts of abortion before Edward was born, but chose not to at\r\nthe last minute. Some say young Edward was destined for great things, for his life had been spared, but the boy\'s parents saw the kidnapping as a blessing so\r\nto speak. The Montague\'s, being incredibly wealthy and focused solely on their\r\nfortune, felt a child was a distraction to them. When the nanny realized that there\r\nwould be no reward, she panicked and left young Edward behind a dumpster at the Gypsy Carnival Circus. With only a blanket and the clothes on his back, young\r\nEdward\'s life hung in the balance. <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nAs fate would have it, the Circus was in town, performing one more show before packing up and moving to the next city. Edward was found by a young female\r\ncircus performer named </span><st1:city><st1:place><span style=\"color: red;\">Alice</span></st1:place></st1:city><span style=\"color: red;\">. Not knowing where he came from, she took him in as her own.\r\n</span><st1:city><st1:place><span style=\"color: red;\">Alice</span></st1:place></st1:city><span style=\"color: red;\"> named him Vladimir, after her beloved grandfather. He loved\r\nto sing as a child, because </span><st1:city><st1:place><span style=\"color: red;\">Alice</span></st1:place></st1:city><span style=\"color: red;\"> loved to sing. He was enraptured with her voice and she sang\r\nto Vlad whenever they were together. <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\n</span><st1:city><st1:place><span style=\"color: red;\"></span></st1:place></st1:city><span style=\"color: red;\">Life was good for Vlad; he was old enough to earn his keep as part of the clean\r\nup crew for the animals. The circus owner nicknamed him Schloppy, because he always had to clean up the sloppy mess made by the animals. Vlad accepted his new name and relished in his work. He would sing to the animals in cages at\r\nnight. Finally, he had something to call his own. Schloppy would watch the circus performers night after night, town after town. He truly wanted to be a clown; he admired the clowns for always being happy, and he too wanted to make people laugh. The only family he ever knew was </span><st1:city><st1:place><span style=\"color: red;\">Alice</span></st1:place></st1:city><span style=\"color: red;\">\r\nand the circus. Schloppy continued upon this path for four more years, until he was eighteen. <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nOne night after clean up, two drunk and dirty mimes decided to pay Schloppy a visit. </span><st1:city><st1:place><span style=\"color: red;\"></span></st1:place></st1:city><span style=\"color: red;\">They despised Schloppy for reasons unknown. They threw a burlap sack over his head, and proceeded to beat him unmercifully with a pipe\r\nuntil he was unconscious. He managed to get a glimpse of whom it was, and his heart was forever changed. As Schloppy lay in his own puddle of blood clinging to life, he found himself being transported; on a cart, behind a\r\nhorse, down a bumpy road, he closed his eyes for what he thought would be for the last\r\ntime. <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nWhen Schloppy opened his eyes two weeks later, he was surrounded by familiar looking people. These people however were no ordinary group of folk. They were vampires. The vampires made Schloppy an offer he couldn\'t refuse. His internal organs had been damaged during the attack and his kidneys stopped working. <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nA man named Necriba asked him, \"Do you wish to die here before your life\r\nis complete or do you want to live forever?\" <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nThere was so much more Schloppy wanted to do in life. Necriba explained, that once he became immortal, he would never be able to coincide with mortals, and would have to hide in the shadows forever. Schloppy agreed and became a <br/>\r\nvampire. He continued to travel with a circus of vampires across </span><st1:city><st1:place><span style=\"color: red;\">Budapest</span></st1:place></st1:city><span style=\"color: red;\"> for several years. He continued to work the cleanup crew, but was eventually\r\nallowed to become a clown in the show, which is what he truly wanted to be. Over the <br/>\r\nyears, he experienced many strange, aberrant, thoughts and emotions. Being a vampire made Schloppy feel very powerful. This was a new feeling for him that\r\nhe had to embrace. Having to prey on mortal humans to survive, he constantly\r\nstruggled <br/>\r\nwith this in his mind. Schloppy was a part of many unusual rituals. The rituals would be unfathomable to a normal human. The images haunted him and\r\nhis emotions became uncontrollable. Schloppy wrote poetry to express his thoughts, and keeps these writings with him always. <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nHe yearned to share his thoughts and feelings with someone, anyone! In life he was alone and longed to find others like him. <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nFinally, his chance has come.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"color: red;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><span style=\"color: red;\"><o:p></o:p></span><u><span style=\"color: red;\">ButterCookie:<o:p></o:p></span></u>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><u><span style=\"color: red;\"><o:p><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\"></span></o:p></span></u></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"color: red;\">The sole survivor of a tragic plane\r\ncrash over the </span><st1:place><span style=\"color: red;\">Northwestern United\r\n States</span></st1:place><span style=\"color: red;\">, John Prentice Wolfgang VII, was left orphaned and alone in the forest. Left to fend for himself, no one could guess what fate would belie this young child. Some would say fortune shined. Others mutter how God hath no mercy. Either way, young Master Wolfgang was taken in by Keebler elves, and christened\r\nButter Cookie. <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nRaised as if one of their own, Butter Cookie enjoyed a typically mundane elf upbringing. Learning the ways of the Elf, and mastering the skills of a baker, he enjoyed life. Working diligently within his thriving community, a young Butter Cookie rose to the top of the Fudge Stripes Production Division.\r\n<br/>\r\nIt was from there the pseudo elf became one of the leading developers for the elves. In an attempt to make a super sugar cookie, tragedy struck for a second time. The main test kitchen tree was burned down and the elder elf was\r\nkilled in a horrific fire which will live forever in Elf lore. Horribly disfigured, Butter Cookie was sent into exile and never returned to the forest.\r\n<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nWith no experience in the humanized world, a grotesque Butter Cookie sought refuge in the circus. Working as a clown, he was able to hide his deformity and\r\nfind a niche in society. Butter Cookie delighted in the life of a circus clown and found plenty of time for his new love, the guitar. The other circus <br/>\r\nperformers disliked this, because they felt musicians were the lowest form of entertainers. Butter Cookie ignored the rebuffs of his fellow troop, and continued in his pursuit of music. One day while jamming through a red hot </span><st1:city><st1:place><span style=\"color: red;\">Marshall</span></st1:place></st1:city><span style=\"color: red;\"> tube amp, some loose hay caught fire. The fire spread\r\nthrough the caravan, killing three and maiming seven. Butter Cookie was driven from the circus and blackballed from the clown community forever. <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nButter Cookie drifted from job to town like snow on a windy day. Smelling of&nbsp; smoke, and terrified of a world in which he would never belong, he reached an end of sorts in </span><st1:place><span style=\"color: red;\">Southern Louisiana</span></st1:place><span style=\"color: red;\">. Lying drunk in the gutter, J. P. Wolfgang VII, <br/>\r\nwould take his final breath. <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nEXCERPT TAKEN FROM THE MIND OF BUTTER COOKIE <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nLestat moved swiftly and softly spoke to me, \"You are a Wolfgang\r\nyes?\" <br/>\r\nI could only look into his eyes feeling both an intense elation combined with a\r\nfear I have never felt. I guessed at who he was and replied, \"Yes, John\r\nPrentice Wolfgang.\" \"Your family once did me a great service.\" Lestat spoke. \" I will offer to repay it now. Do you want to live forever?\" <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nAfter meeting Lestat, Butter Cookie toured with the famous rocker as a roadie and later as a guitar tech. He was easily able to assimilate into the crazy smoke, mirror, and hallucinogenic ensemble that is rock-n-roll. Where else\r\ncould <br/>\r\na horribly disfigured Elf/Clown/Vampire fit in? Always lurking in the umbra, the thing once known as John Prentice Wolfgang, learned all it could about the music. Feeling confident, Butter Cookie set out on his own to find a group of&nbsp; guys that he could really relate to. Some would say fortune shined. Others mutter how God hath no mercy. <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nENTER CLOWN SACK<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"color: red;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><u><span style=\"color: red;\"><o:p><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\"></span></o:p></span></u></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><u><span style=\"color: red;\">Slappy:<o:p></o:p></span></u></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><u><span style=\"color: red;\"><o:p><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\"></span></o:p></span></u></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"color: red;\">Walking around aimlessly in\r\nKamchatskaya Oblast, with no recollection of where he came from, or who he was, Slappy was found by a group of circus clowns In 1849. The clowns took him under their wing and toured </span><st1:country-region><st1:place><span style=\"color: red;\">Russia</span></st1:place></st1:country-region><span style=\"color: red;\"> in the \"Kamchatskaya Oblast Circus\". Slappy learned\r\nvery <br/>\r\nquickly in the art of clowning, and the name \"Slappy\" was bestowed\r\nupon him by his new found family. <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nThings were looking up for the happy clown, until he discovered the dark secret of the K.O. Circus. It was early 1850, when the troop decided to make Slappy a full member. Ring Leader Kasyanov had the other clowns bring Slappy to the center of the big top. As the other performers watched, Kasyanov revealed his true form as a vampire. Slappy turned to seek help from his clown family, but to his frightening discovery realized everyone in the circus revealed themselves as well. He now knew what the initiation into the family <br/>\r\nreally was. The Ring Leader sank his teeth deep into the frightened clown\'s neck and started draining the life out of him. Kasyanov was extremely strong. Slappy, getting weaker by the second, couldn\'t stop what was happening. He believed death was upon him. Then the taste of warm blood filled his mouth and throat, warming his entire body. <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nWhen Slappy woke two days later, it felt like his insides were coated with razors, and the hunger was unlike any he had ever experienced. The wagons moved in the daylight. He was trapped. The wagon contained only a coffin filled with earth and a cage filled with living rats. He helped himself. Slappy knew the scam now, keep traveling through </span><st1:country-region><st1:place><span style=\"color: red;\">Russia</span></st1:place></st1:country-region><span style=\"color: red;\"> preying on all the unsuspecting little towns. The troop was feeding on <br/>\r\nweak humans, who wanted to watch the circus, see the clowns, and laugh. Slappy was sickened by this and wanted no part of it, but at this point there was no alternative. In order to survive, he did what his masters said and fed on the leftover humans to keep from going insane from the hunger. <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nThis went on for two years until one night in late 1852, he overheard his clown family talking about the night they found him, and how they killed his true family. This enraged Slappy, but he knew he must wait for the right time to strike. In a small town called Alexandrov, Slappy developed a plan of attack. Once a month, the vampires like to have a special feast. <br/>\r\nThe unread performers dress in mime costumes, and feed on caged victims captured in a past show. In Alexandrov, the troop put on a free evening show for orphan children, At the end of the show, the children were rounded up and put in cages for the feast. <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nSlappy saw many haunting things in the previous two years, but this crossed the line. Wile the vampires dressed in their Mime costumes, Slappy entered the tent and threw back the tarp covering the cages. The children screamed and cowered to the back wall of the cage. Slappy put a finger to his clown lips and made a shhhhhh sound. He told the children he was here to help. Astonishing, the children listened and became silent. Slappy ripped the locks off with his bare hands and told the children to follow him quickly, but be very quiet. After Slappy led the children to safety, he went back to the tent. No one <br/>\r\nnoticed the children were missing. He poured lamp oil over the sides of the tent, on the tarp, and anything else that could have lamp oil poured on it. Slappy finished the job, ran out of the tent, and hid to wait for the others to enter. As the mimes funneled into the tent, he counted them. All present, but the Ring Leader. From the tent came a commotion. Slappy <br/>\r\ndecided he couldn\'t wait for the Ring Leader, set the tent on fire, ran, and stood in front of the tent door holding a wooden stake in each hand. Most of the vampires burned to death and the few that tried to make it out received a stake in the heart. After the slaughter, Slappy went to the Ring Leader\'s wagon to end this once and for all, but Kasyanov was nowhere to be found. Slappy went into the wagon and opened a huge trunk <br/>\r\non the right of Kasyanov\'s coffin. Inside, hundreds of gold watches, earrings, rings, all types of jewelry and coins glittered. It was all the spoils of all the innocent humans that were brutally killed over the years. After filling his pack as much it allowed, Slappy headed North and never looked back. To this day, whenever Slappy sees a mine, he can\'t help but think that its Ring Leader Kasyanov. <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nSlappy made his way to Saint-Petersburg, traveling at night and ducking into cold dark places during the day. From there he moved to Kemijarui </span><st1:country-region><st1:place><span style=\"color: red;\">Finland</span></st1:place></st1:country-region><span style=\"color: red;\">, then </span><st1:city><st1:place><span style=\"color: red;\">Bergen</span></st1:place></st1:city><span style=\"color: red;\"> </span><st1:country-region><st1:place><span style=\"color: red;\">Norway</span></st1:place></st1:country-region><span style=\"color: red;\">. During this time\'1850\'s national consciousness waxed strong in the wake of the French Revolution. Furthermore, economic <br/>\r\ngrowth in </span><st1:country-region><st1:place><span style=\"color: red;\">Norway</span></st1:place></st1:country-region><span style=\"color: red;\"> stimulated cultural development in music. By the 1860\'s, Slappy studied music with Ludvig Mathias Linderman and Halfdan Kjerulf. The clown/vampire seemed to be a natural in the string area, it could have been a vampiric gift from Kasyanov, or just a talent he never tapped into before. In the 1870s and 80s Slappy was working with Norwegian composers Edward Grieg, and Johan Svendsen. <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nOne night during a concert in 1888, Slappy saw mimes entering the concert hall. The audience started freaking out. These mimes didn\'t look normal; they looked evil. Slappy knew the day would come when the Ring Leader put <br/>\r\nanother group of blood suckers together and hunted him down. The mimes dowsed the audience and walls with a flammable liquid, and lit it all up. Luckily for Slappy, he helped build the hall and knew where all the passages were. He grabbed Svendsen and pushed him thru a trap door and got him to safety. The rest of the audience died that night in a huge blaze. Hopefully, Kasyanov believed that Slappy died as well. He gathered all the valuables he could carry and chartered a ship to the </span><st1:country-region><st1:place><span style=\"color: red;\">United Kingdom</span></st1:place></st1:country-region><span style=\"color: red;\">. Then the clown hopped another <br/>\r\nship to </span><st1:country-region><st1:place><span style=\"color: red;\">Ireland</span></st1:place></st1:country-region><span style=\"color: red;\">. Slappy stayed in </span><st1:city><st1:place><span style=\"color: red;\">Dublin</span></st1:place></st1:city><span style=\"color: red;\"> until 1912, then moved to Southanton where he met Wallace Hartley. The clown answered an ad for a bass violinist. Fortunately, Wallace mistook him for a man named Clarke; a renown bass <br/>\r\nviolinist. Wallace needed to get a band ready for a cruise ship traveling to </span><st1:state><st1:place><span style=\"color: red;\">New York</span></st1:place></st1:state><span style=\"color: red;\">. This was to be the biggest and fastest ship ever made,\r\nnamed Titanic. Slappy believed this would be a great opportunity to get further away from his past and start over in </span><st1:place><span style=\"color: red;\">North\r\n America</span></st1:place><span style=\"color: red;\">. The plan; take Clarke\'s identity until reaching </span><st1:state><st1:place><span style=\"color: red;\">New\r\n  York</span></st1:place></st1:state><span style=\"color: red;\">, then disappear\r\ninto the huge city. Once <br/>\r\nagain, Slappy packed his things. <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nDuring the voyage, feeding wasn\'t a problem. A few years back, Slappy discovered that one of his inherited vampiric abilities; he could survive on beer instead of blood, but only for a few months before requiring a blood transfusion. When the Titanic hit the iceberg that night, Gigantic was playing in the Grand Ballroom. All the other musicians fell to the floor, <br/>\r\nbut Slappy didn\'t miss a beat. It was four hours until the crew realized how serious the damage was and started evacuating. The evacuation was quite insane. All the passengers were panicking, so Slappy and the other band members stayed in a group. Then Slappy had an idea, taking out his violin, <br/>\r\nhe started to play. The other musicians quickly joined in. Time went on and the end was near, the last song they played was \"Near My God to\r\nThee,\" then the band shook hands and separated. Slappy never saw his fellow band members\r\nagain. <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nAfter the ship disappeared into the cold dark ocean, Slappy headed Northwest. By using his vampiric abilities, he was able to run very fast on top of the water by night and rest under the dark ocean during the day. To this day, Slappy has no idea how long he was out there, because by the time he reached <br/>\r\nthe shoreline his hunger for blood and beer he was borderline insane. He fed on the first living thing he came across; the rumor is, it was a mime. <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nFollowing the event that almost took his life, Slappy decided to go underground\r\nand stayed until 2005. While underground, he could hear things on the surface like people talking, weird mechanical sounds, and construction, but there was one thing that really got his attention. There was a strange music that he never hear before; he liked it, but it seem to be missing a bass sound. Slappy listened to this band for about two months and started to imagine bass lines for each song. Then finally one day, he re-entered the top side and met the guys that were making this interesting music. Slappy surfaced, walked to the <br/>\r\nhouse where the music was coming from, and knocked on the door. The music stopped and the door opened. To Slappy\'s surprise three clowns stood before him in full gear. <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nThe clowns said, \" Hey man, if you\'re here to try out for the bass playing\r\njob you got it, because you are the only one to show up\". <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nIn the first practice with Scratchy, Schloppy, and Butter Cookie, the songs came easy for Slappy. He already had the bass lines in his head from listening to them practice for the last few months. <br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nIntroducing Clown Sack.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n',1,'',0,''),(1495,1872,'Deep Rising',1,76,'deep-rising.com','','631-766-6925','<body>Formed as a recording project in 1998, Deep Rising has evolved into a rock band with a prog edge featuring excellent singing, playing, and song writing that draws from influences as varied as Stone Temple Pilots, Kings X, Alice In Chains, Rush, Jane\'s Addiction, Peter Gabriel, Seal, Led Zeppelin. Deep Rising music is visceral and meaningful, drawing from the best of their influences and creating their own style which has been described as immediately accessible, interesting and deep, and definitely unique. Hard rockers are drawn by the powerful guitars. Proggers are drawn by the vocal melodies, arrangements, and meaningful lyrics. There is a power in their live shows that is not measured in decibels, but in passion and style. Critically acclaimed on Long Island, they are now reaching out across the world to spread their music and have gained a growing fanbase throughout North America, Europe, South America, and the Middle East.</body>',1,'',0,''),(1493,1870,'SEVEN DIRTY WORDS',1,14,'www.sevendirtywords.net','','','',1,'',0,''),(1497,1874,'Rise Phoenix Rise',1,71,'www.myspace.com/rprmusic','','','For Updated Tour Listings Go To:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.risephoenixrise.com/tour.html\">http://www.risephoenixrise.com/tour.html</a>',1,'',0,''),(1500,1879,'Josh Kelley',1,61,'http://www.joshkelley.com/main/','','','\r\n<p>Singer&#8211;songwriter Josh Kelley is eager to announce the July 25th release of his third album, \"Just Say the Word.\" Entirely written, produced and performed by Kelley, \"Just Say the Word\" demonstrates an eclectic range of the artist\'s recent musical and personal evolution: \"I often heard people say that sometimes you just wake up in life and realize that you want to be better &#8211; well, that\'s what happened to me about one year ago. I became a better guitar player, drummer, piano player, bass player, singer and songwriter. I found a new love in my life and an extra spark to my passion for music. \"Just Say the Word\" is a direct reflection of my growth. I had a vision for this record and finally there was only one cook in the kitchen.\"</p>\r\n<p>Kelley has independently partnered with manager Debbie Wilson of Wilspro Management to market and distribute the new material in a unique way. On June 6th, the album made a very successful pre-release launch on iTunes that lifted Kelley to the #1 position among all iTunes folk artists. On June 13th, \"Just Say the Word\" boasted a #27 position on iTunes Top Albums. In addition, a series of headlining club dates kicked off on May 28th in Las Vegas at the Suncoast Hotel and Casino and Kelley will continue to tour throughout 2006 in support of the album. \"This is my rebirth,\" Kelley noted, \"I am ready to explore new and different ways of getting my music out there and go to the next level.\"</p>\r\n<p>\"Almost Honest,\" Kelley\'s last release, received wide acclaim from critics. Entertainment Weekly praised the CD for being \"soulful, folk-informed, and unflaggingly melodic.\" People Magazine called Kelley, \"the real deal, a genuine talent who brings sincere emotion to his straight-forward pop rock.\" And, Good Morning America dubbed Kelley \"a breakthrough artist.\" The CD topped the Billboard New Artist Chart upon release and had been on the iTunes home page for several weeks.</p>\r\n<p>The first single from \"Just Say The Word\" is the infectious \"Pop Game,\" a song that allows Kelley to comment on American pop culture and his place in it: \"I was sitting at my girlfriend\'s house in LA, chillin\' - when I grabbed a celebrity magazine sitting on the table - showing John Q. Public how the stars live and how much easier life is as a celebrity. I put the magazine down and turned on the TV, only to find the E! Channel showing lives of the rich and famous. I realized that our modern culture is hypnotized by the consumption of simple pop culture pleasures. Make no mistake, I\'m not knockin\' it &#8211; I\'m a sucker for the pop game just as much as the next person, and would love to live in it as a huge star. But the song, \"Pop Game,\" is not about my life in music, but rather about our modern day obsession with the world of popular culture.\"</p>\r\n<p>The title track, \"Just Say the Word\", is a song that deals with the frustrations and memories of past love and also features an encore at the end of the album. Josh speaks about the track: \"Just Say the Word\" is a last attempt at letting a past lover know that they are not forgotten, and that they are still loved and safe in friendship, even though it\'s time to make the next step in the direction of moving on with your life. I chose an encore for the song, because I love the track and the way it makes me feel, and because a lot of my favorite albums have an encore that bookends the record. It\'s a message that just needed to be revisited. And what better way to engrave the title track message than to have an encore.\"</p>\r\n<p>Working with people like the Matrix and Robert Randolph in the past, Kelley decided to keep his collaborators local this time around: \"I worked a great deal with my younger brother and our mutual friend, Dave Haywood. This was important to me because these two musicians are in that early, untainted stage of their promising writing careers. Their type of no filter attitude was just what the doctor ordered.\"</p>\r\n<p>Just as \"Almost Home\" presented so many different musical styles, \"Just Say the Word\" continues to establish Kelley\'s wide range of musical ability and tastes. The listener can enjoy the soulful and deep \"How the Story Goes\" to a stripped down, almost bluegrass \"Bound to Keep Movin\'\" to the pop-driven \"Pop Game.\" Whatever the situation, Kelley proves with \"Just Say the Word\" that he is committed to stretching himself creatively in order to present a varied array of musical and personal expression: \"I believe a great artist is an eternal student. Most of the songs on the record were inspired from sights and sounds that I had heard when traveling the world for the last 2 years. Keeping my eyes and mind open to all facets of information kept me constantly inspired with new ideas and a reinvented perception of life and love. People will say that you can never stretch yourself too far, but I think that\'s ridiculous. There is a certain point in stretching yourself creatively where you lose the reason you got into it in the first place. I\'ve overstretched myself on multiple occasions - alienating my friends, family and lovers from my life. Now, if I want to have something to write about, I try to live true.\"</p>\r\n<p>Josh Kelley has maintained a high media profile over the last several months, appearing on the Emmy Award-winning NBC talk show Ellen, performing on Good Morning America and delivering a soulful rendition of the national anthem at NASCAR\'s Sony HD 500 as well as the home opener world champion Chicago White Sox game. He performed most recently on ESPN\'s Cold Pizza, and is scheduled to perform on CBS Saturday\'s Second Cup Caf&eacute;, August 5th. The touching title track of Almost Honest was also featured in the March 30th episode of the hit series \"Smallville.\" Kelley will also be featured in the digital soundtrack for the hit TV show \"Scrubs.\"</p>\r\n<p>Kelley broke through in 2001 on Hollywood Records with \"For The Ride Home,\" an album that showcased his no-nonsense expressiveness and disarmingly genuine delivery. These qualities were exemplified in the top five smash \"Amazing,\" and follow-up top ten hit \"Everybody Wants You.\" In early 2004, he left Oxford, Miss. for Los Angeles where he interacted with fellow songwriters and players, further refining his skills while determining where he wanted to take his music next. It all culminated with the sessions for his second Hollywood Records album, \"Almost Honest.\"</p>',0,'',0,''),(1511,1893,'Circuit Theory',1,74,'www.circuittheorymusic.com','','','The music of Circuit Theory has been described as dark, inward looking, and rustic. With inspirations of love, hate, life, lies, anger and bliss combined with a very broad range of musical influences, a new sound is created with the idea of taking the listener somewhere a little out of the ordinary. Formed at the cusp of 2005/06, Circuit Theory has already gained quite a bit of attention since stepping out into the public eye in August 2006 by playing some of the area\'s most popular hot spots. Among those venues were Rex\'s in West Chester, PA, and The Rusty Nail in Ardmore, PA. More recently, Circuit Theory has appeared on both the main stage and balcony stage of the legendary Trocadero Theater in Philadelphia. Other accolades include their song \"Mother, May I\" garnered a 100% positive review streak on mixposure.com and held the top spot in their Hard Rock genre for 2 weeks immediately after release on their website back in September of 2006. The song &#8220;Cynical Optimist&#8221; also proved to be successful on mixposure.com, staying in the top 20 hard rock songs for a solid month. Now the band is preparing to release their long-awaited debut EP amidst much buzz and anticipation, at which time Circuit Theory hopes to go out and spread their music as much and as far as possible. ',1,'',0,''),(1512,1894,'Gina Cutillo',1,61,'http://www.ginacutillo.com','','631-786-0057','Awarded Best Female Vocalist of Long Island and Best Original Song on NBC&#39;s Star Tomorrow &#39;AP,&#39; recording artist Gina Cutillo lures us in with her catchy melodies, passionate voice, and outstanding live performance.&nbsp; Full of emotion and extremes Gina&#39;s sound is unique, sensual, powerful and feverish giving a new seducing figure to the genre of Pop and Rock<br />\r\nAll members have there own unique style, professionalism and experience that give much depth to Gina&#39;s songs.&nbsp; Currently living in New York, Gina and the guys are ready and started to reach out to fans everywhere with there chorus infected songs and energetic live performances.&nbsp; Gina Cutillo will give all it takes to accomplish worldwide success through what&#39;s moved her from day one: A Memorable Song. \r\n',1,'',0,''),(1518,968,'Independent drummer.',1,16,'http://www.myspace.com/kellydrums','','423-227-2324','<div align=\"center\">\r\n<font color=\"#0000ff\"><font size=\"3\"><font face=\"verdana,geneva\">&#39;Looking for a gig or drummer position with other pro musicians. I&#39;ve been running into a lot of &quot;drama&quot; in the Chattanooga area and need to find some seasoned musicians who can actually get along with each other on and off the stage.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nI will play just about any type of music that people will get off their feet to, but really love blues. You know 1-4-5 type stuff.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nI have all the gear I need to play stage, mics, cords and a pro attitude.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nGive me a shout if you need a drama free drummer.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font></font></font><br />\r\n</div>\r\n',0,'',0,''),(1912,1983,'Triggered Impulse',7,33,'myspace.com/triggeredimpulse','','','',1,'',0,''),(1858,1774,'brittle',1,71,'www.myspace.com/brittlerock','','0448 536 421','<font color=\"white\" size=\"3\"><font color=\"red\">BRITTLE<font color=\"black\"> is a four piece Rock band with the determination to make it big as an international band. \r\n<br/>\r\nBRITTLE is going to explode and hit your stereo and ipods like a PUNCH to the teeth but like SEX to the ears.<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nBRITTLE have been playing shows for over 5 years and we have shared the\r\nstage with some iconic international and national bands such as <font color=\"red\">Grinspoon, Kisschasy, Bodyjar, Something With Numbers, Avalon Drive, The Veronicas<font color=\"black\"> and many more. \r\n<br/>\r\n2006 saw BRITTLE play a variety of venues including the main stage at <font color=\"red\">Splendour In The Grass, The Hard Rock Caf&eacute;<font color=\"black\"> during Indy Week as well <font color=\"red\">Schoolies Week<font color=\"black\">.\r\n<br/>\r\nIn October 07 BRITTLE played on the Sea FM Stage at the <font color=\"red\">Lexmark Indy 300<font color=\"black\">, with video and radio airplay to over 100,000 people. \r\n<br/>\r\nBRITTLE currently have a 5 track E.P out called <font color=\"red\">\'\'Speak Ya Mind\'\'<font color=\"black\"> which is distributed through MGM/Green Media. Earlier this year BRITTLE toured to Sydney and Melbourne(<font color=\"red\">the Espy<font color=\"black\">), to support the launch of their CD. \r\n<br/>\r\nContacting Brittle:\r\n<z>brittlemusic@hotmail.com</z>\r\n</font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font>',1,'',0,''),(1865,1934,'lourissa wright',8,38,'www.myspace.com/lourissawright','','9407993615','I am a small town girl with big dreams and a big heart. I love all types of music and always have. I am a hard worker and am willing to do anything to get my music out there and heard. I wrote my first song \"First Sight\" in July of 2006 in about 5 minutes or so. I have always liked to write poems and stories so one day I just grabbed a pen and paper and started writing and didn\'t stop. ',1,'',0,''),(1894,1965,'billcartermusic',8,39,'www.digitalrodeo.com/billcartermusic','springbird','','Born in texas,raised in the midwest,bill\'s roots are deep in country music. bill started writing songs back in the 80\'s just<br/>for fun and to entertain friends and family,that was then, now&nbsp;&nbsp; <br/>he wants to share them with the world.<br/>His lyrics are honest and to the point,no hidden meanings.He<br/>writes about what he knows, life experiences,good and bad.<br/>\"I want to leave behind a part of me in my songs\"',1,'',0,''),(1983,2072,'johnny rox',1,71,'','','541-844-4737','johnnyrexford@yahoo.com John Eastman: Started playing guitar at age 12. John\'s Uncle Rex immediately noticed his natural ability and gave him his first guitar and amp, a Gibson SG and a Fender Twin Reverb. Johns love for music soon led him to the piano, drums and took vocal lessons. Only after a year of playing he started writing songs and formed his first band, \"Dark Angel\". It wasn\'t long after that Dark Angel played at his own High School followed by Nightclubs and staging their own Concerts. In the 80\'s musicians and band names came and went so John named his act \"Eastman\" which still holds today. When you go to an Eastman concert the first thing you notice is show looks and sounds great! like their CD. It\'s no mistake. John is also an ace behind the mixing console and surrounds himself with the best musicians, equipment and technicians available. . Danny Bridges a seasoned veteran and local Studio Session Player provides the Bass and stage antics. Go see an Eastman Concert and your sure to see a show also check us out on myspace for more songs <a href=\"http://profile.myspace.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=user.viewprofile&friendid=282100255&MyToken=14e6ec68-b3dc-4d9b-af9f-898260f2c17e\">http://profile.myspace.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=user.viewprofile&friendid=282100255&MyToken=14e6ec68-b3dc-4d9b-af9f-898260f2c17e</a>',0,'',0,''),(1976,1115,'Kristina con Vita',1,17,'www.kristinaconvita.com','','','<p style=\"text-indent: 0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Segoe Media Center\'; mso-fareast-font-family: Batang\">Kristina Marie and Vita Izabella have created a unique sound with their opposing backgrounds and styles of singing. Vita Izabella is a classically trained singer who has been greatly influenced by the classical and jazz greats. Kristina Marie is a rocker through and through, having been influenced by artists such as Janis Joplin, Patti Smith, and Pat Benetar. Although their voices are seemingly on opposite ends of the color spectrum, when blended together they become one fascinating splash of sound. They have become heavily influenced by each other over the past few years of performing and writing music together. In fact, it is now difficult at times to discern one voice from the other. <?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = \"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office\" /><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-indent: 0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Segoe Media Center\'; mso-fareast-font-family: Batang\">Over the past few years, Vita Izabella and Kristina Marie have been working closely, writing and recording with good friend and producer, Paul Umbach (Nine Days, Aaron Carter, Britney Spears). They have been showcasing their original music, both individually and together, at NYC venues such as The Knitting Factory, The Bitter End, The Sidewalk Cafe, Pete&#8217;s Candy Store, The Lion&#8217;s Den, Kenny&#8217;s Castaways, CBGB&#8217;s Gallery and The Back Fence. They have also showcased their music at the nationally recognized Chick Singer Night, at The Bitter End, hosted by Deena Miller. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-indent: 0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Segoe Media Center\'; mso-fareast-font-family: Batang\">In November of 2006, Kristina con Vita&#8217;s duo act <strong>won first place at <?xml:namespace prefix = st1 ns = \"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags\" /><st1:place w:st=\"on\">Harlem</st1:place>&#8217;s legendary Amateur Night at The Apollo Theater</strong> with their original song entitled, &#8220;Everything About You.&#8221; <br/><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In August of 2007, their original song \"In Between\" (produced & caressed with passion by Paul Umbach, featuring smokin\' guitar riffs played by Andy Bassford) <strong>won first place in the&nbsp;GoGirls&nbsp;Songwriting Competition</strong>. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-indent: 0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Segoe Media Center\'; mso-fareast-font-family: Batang\">They are currently writing and recording songs for their first full length album. <o:p></o:p></span></p>',1,'',0,''),(1980,2067,'Intervention',1,66,'www.myspace.com/Interventionuk','','','<span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Arial\">Antony and Daniel were born and raised in Cornwall, England. They grew up together and lived in each other\'s pockets until it was time to leave for University. Daniel, 24, studied music at the University of Middlesex, Antony, 23, studied Software Engineering at the University of Portsmouth. During the University years, something exciting happened and&nbsp;Intervention was born. <br/><br/>The lads meet on a regular basis to write and record new material and 2008 will see the boys reunite in London (the city Daniel calls home). So it\'s to London where the quest for world domination will begin.<br/><br/><img title=\"\" height=\"336\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.bestofbands.com/uploads/2067/welcomeNoteBOB.jpg\" width=\"250\" align=\"baseline\" border=\"0\"/></span>',1,'',0,''),(1989,2080,'Homecookin\'',8,40,'www.homecookinbluegrass.com','','6092900356','<strong>Home Cookin\'</strong> offers up a tasty serving of bluegrass and traditional country music. The band blends material from a wide variety of sources to create it\'s own special sound. In addition to traditional sources, the group draws material from diverse genres and gives it a bluegrass twist. All the members write music and contribute original material to the band. Based in southern New Jersey, the band performs throughout the eastern US.',1,'',0,''),(2008,1103,'Johnny Panic',1,75,'myspace.com/johnnypanic','','','Life threatening hospitalisations, band members and managers lost to medical conditions and breakdowns, hellish record label machinations, prostitutes, cage fighting, strange corporate lifelines, lost weekends in foreign countries and all underscored by friendship and an unshakeable ambition and belief in the music. The story of Johnny Panic so far is enough for a 110 page screenplay let alone an 800 word press biography. <br/><br/><br/><br/>We haven\'t got time to get into all the gory details now, so let\'s just get the salient details out of the way first. While still at school Rob Solly (vocals, guitar, songwriting) met Jonny Shock (drums, drinking, comedy) on a bus in south east London bonding over a shared love of music and they\'ve been playing together ever since. A few guitarists later they struck gold with Matt James who they found right on their own doorstep and after the amicable departure of long time bassist and friend Nash Francis they drafted in Sean Mannion (Rob: \"the most natural musician out of all of us\"). <br/><br/><br/><br/>Drawing inspiration from the glorious history of artists that have meant something in the last 50 years of rock and roll, any triangulation of where they\'re coming from would have to include The Clash, Guns n Roses and the early American punk scene (they\'ve covered The Nerves/Blondie and The Ramones to spectacular effect). <br/><br/>In 2005 Johnny Panic released their debut \'The Violent Dazzling\', an album of stadium sized hooks and melodies wrapped around concerns of mental health, prostitution, drugs and prisoners of conscience. A typical quote from Rob at the time went thus, \"There\'s an ethic missing from a lot of bands\" he explains. \"We live in a society that refuses to question. That\'s where rock \'n\' roll comes in. We\'re not here to shove them down people\'s throats, but every single one of our songs is trying to get something across.\" <br/><br/>It &iacute;s the sort of record that makes much more sense in a post-\'American Idiot\' and \'Welcome To The Black Parade\' world. Of those that heard it, many fell for the passion and scope of the likes of \'Burn Your Youth\' (subject: young male suicide) and \'Automatic Healer\' (prostitution), however the record labels inability to get their head around what the band had delivered coupled with some dark financial shit meant that the album never really stood a chance. <br/><br/>They managed to extricate themselves from their record label but it was a blow that would have KO\'d lesser bands. Many will be surprised to hear Johnny Panic are about to come out fighting again. <br/><br/>But then front man Rob Solly, knows a thing or two about fighting. From the age of 14 he\'s been practising Tae Kwon-Do, reaching a level that found him competing in the US and Australia, he\'s also done Thai Boxing in Thailand and trained in Brazilian Ju Jitsu and boxing as well. The last two years have found Rob training and fighting in mixed martial arts - yes, that\'s Ultimate Fighting Championship and Cage Rage stuff to uninitiated. In fact Rob\'s first paid fight is on September 30. <br/><br/><br/>It\'s fair to say that he\'s in pretty good shape which probably helped when he was hospitalised with septicemia, a complication brought on from peritonitis (which, lest we forget, was enough to finish Houdini off). Having been rushed to hospital four times to be cut open and have parts of his damaged intestines removed, the thick scar running down his abdomen is the only tell tale signs that things have not always been so rosy. \"I lost three and a half stone in three weeks because they were feeding me through a tube in my neck\". Struck down while on tour in Aberdeen, the rest of the band would come visit to keep his spirits up. \"Septicemia is incredibly painful, you\'re basically poisoning your own body, but that\'s nothing compared to having Jonny sitting on your wound bag and sending all the fluid straight back onto the wound. It would have been a lot worse if I hadn\'t been in charge of my own morphine drip.\". <br/><br/><br/><br/>Its being able to maintain a sense of humour about things and this fighting spirit that found the band not giving up. Scoring a British Arts Council grant to travel and play at this years South By South West festival, winning ten grand from the Windows Live Spaces competition and covering The Turtles \'Happy Together\' for NPower\'s 2006 cricket sponsorship. All of this helped keep the band afloat and enabled them to self finance the recording of their second album, inevitably and appropriately called \'The Good Fight\'. Rob even collared Biffy Clyro and Therapy? producer Chris Sheldon in the street and talked him into producing and mixing the record. <br/><br/><br/><br/>Head and shoulders above their debut \'The Good Fight\' is the sound of a band hitting the ground running. One hell of a comeback, key to it\'s success is the emergence of Matt James as one of the most distinctive guitarists in the UK. Hype? Check out the solos on \'Stay\' and \'M-19\' for the evidence, or just listen to the whole album. First single \'Dislocation\' is an anthem to frustration with a refrain of \"Boredom turns me on\", while rumbling bass, squealing guitars and shouted backing vocals explode the tightly wound tension at the heart of the song. Musically the album is broader that its predecessor and along with the aforementioned influences The Stooges (\'Gone\'), Green Day (\'Never Me\') and Morrissey (\'Heroes Of Villains\') get at least a nod. <br/><br/><br/><br/>Rob\'s lyrics are once again a mixture of the personal and the political, but whether it\'s a Colombian guerrilla movement or a dig at those that turn thugs into folk heroes it\'s never forced down your throat. \"I like to think of it as amazing songs, with depth if you want it\" says the front man. After everything the band has been through to get to this point they\'ve got an album that sounds amazing, their goal now is to get the music out there to as many people as possible, to keep writing and playing the music that matters to them, basically to keep fighting The Good Fight. ',1,'',0,''),(2002,2095,'Gary Bloom Band',1,16,'www.tinybluemusic.com','','','',1,'',0,''),(2011,2078,'HOLLYWOOD',1,14,'http://www.hollywoodrocks.net','PO Box 1423','803-568-5227','Hard rock band from South Carolina who is creating a buzz overseas with their music.&nbsp; Starting in 2005, the band has the sounds of GNR, Aersomith and Whitesnake. \r\n',1,'Lex Scott -vocals/guitar<br />\r\nAubrey Rucker-drums bg vocals<br />\r\nBill Rivers-lead guitar/bg vocals<br />\r\nTy Allen-bass/bg vocals \r\n',0,''),(2012,1452,'7 Days 2 Perfection',1,71,'http://www.7d2p.com','1404 Bancroft Drive','905-608-8105','&quot;Natural Charisma and Killer Sound&quot; says reviewer of&nbsp; VII Days II\r\nPerfection - it&#39;s a fresh original gut driven Rock band that is winning\r\nfans with great&nbsp; songwriting, catchy melodies, wicked vocals and great\r\nguitar solos.\r\n',1,'',0,''),(2014,2111,'10 ton wreckin\' ball',7,0,'','','','',1,'',0,''),(2015,2112,'Adam I.N.N.P',10,48,'www.princeofcats.co.uk','','','Coming soon',1,'',0,''),(2016,2113,'At Large',1,69,'atlargenation.bravehost.com','48 Friend St 2Fl','9788794192','Kevin\"Doc\"Burgess--12 String/Lead Singer<br/>Keith\"Khaki3rd\"Rose--Drums<br/>Len Pal--Bass',1,'',0,''),(2047,2157,'Rex P Clem',6,32,'http://myspace.com/rexpclem','','','Well now, let me try and think. I started playing the guitar at 10 when I begged for one to my Father. I formed my first band, Euphoria, the following year. We played a couple of shows for our school and I was offered the spot of Bassist with the local cool High school group. Being twelve at the time, I jumped at the chance. I borrowed a Bass from a friend and that was that. By the time I hit High school, I was playing in a country band that ran &quot;the Animal Circuit&quot; around Indiana. After graduation, we travelled the US and Canada in an old GM Coach. It&#39;s never a good idea to let a group of 18 year old boys loose playing bars on the road. After several years of motel rooms, road women and, various addictions, I returned to Indiana. Had two fine sons and tried to work for a living. Well, now I&#39;m playin&#39; the Blues in Nashville, Tennessee. You can&#39;t take the music out of the boy! I have had the pleasure of performing with and opening for some great musicians and artists. Some well known and some that should be. Some of the groups that I have been in are: The Aces, the Swinging Johnsons (my favorite name of all time), RebelStorm, Dixie Flyer, Wild at Heart, Gary West and the Wild West, Bigg Country. Some of my favorite memories include; the first time I got to open for David Allan Coe, opening for Keith Whitley, Marshall Tucker, Holly Dunn, Blackfoot, Saywer Brown, Brad Paisley, Doug Stone, and some others that escape my mind at this moment. Playing with Tommy Cash and Mark Cash was a hoot. Doing &quot;Star Search&quot; was pretty cool. Lost though, that sucked. Getting kicked out of Jamestown, North Dakota! That&#39;s a story in itself. Performing on the Charlie Daniels show, Midwest Country. Over all, I have been blessed by God to get to do what I love and be where I am in life. Thanks to all who have had a hand in that. Thanks to my wonderful Wife for everything you do. How I ever got lucky enough to find you, I will never know. You are the world to me. Thanks to my two wonderful sons. You are the reason I exist. God Bless\r\n',0,'',0,''),(2049,2162,'victor scalise',1,16,'','','','A LITTLE ABOUT ME: I HAVE BEEN PLAYING DRUMS AROUND 25 YEARS NOW AND JUST LOVING IT. OVER THE YEARS I HAD A CHANCE TO PLAY WITH MANY GREAT MUSICIANS WHO LET ME SHARPEN MY TEETH ON THEIR TIME ( THANKS GUYS). AFTER PLAYING IN COVER BANDS FOR MANY YEARS I AM GROWING TIRED OF THE SAME OLD THING . SO IT\'S TIME TO GET SOMETHING ORIGINAL IN THE WORKS.&nbsp; I SEE MY SELF PLAYING IN A CLASSIC ROCK/HEAVY BLUES BAND WHO WRITES MUSIC LIKE,&nbsp; BAD COMPANY, WHITESNAKE, LED ZEP, JOE BONAMASSA, BLACK CROWES . SOMETHING SEXEY, SOULFUL,BLUESY&nbsp; AND POWERFUL. I\'AM NOT MUCH INTO RADIO MUSIC AS TO ME MUSIC BECAME ABOUT MONEY AND LOST IT\'S FEELING. MY STYLE IS ON THIS TYPE OF MUSIC AND I THINK THIS IS WHERE I WILL BE AT MY BEST, SO PASS THE WORD. THANK YOU, VICTOR',1,'',0,''),(2061,2173,'Funk God Prophecy',10,45,'http://www.myspace.com/funkgodprophecy','','','Funk God Prophecy is Guitarist/Singer/Songwriter/Engineer Patrick Bryant. Started as a project to do when I was between bands, it is now my main focus. I\'ve created my own sound and style and have released many Eps. ',1,'',0,''),(2098,2225,'Just Us',10,0,'stacyandteresawilson.com','14822 May Rd','423-298-6902','\r\n<p><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt\">JUST US is an exciting band from East Tennessee featuring traditional, contemporary and gospel bluegrass music. Although, we are a newly formed group, the members of JUST US have many years of on stage experience. JUST US has the ability to perform many different styles of music with that added bluegrass flair. The band prides itself with strong vocals, tight harmonies and solid picking. <br/></span></p>',1,'',0,''),(2184,2336,'Mistakes In Shadows',1,71,'myspace.com/mistakesinshadows','','','',1,'',0,''),(2186,2338,'Blame It On Cain',1,14,'www.blameitoncain.com','','','\r\n<p><strong><b><i>Blame It On Cain </i>formed in the outskirts of Milwaukee in January 2007. The all-original quartet\'s straight-forward hard rock and pop songs have been compared to acts like<i> Stone Temple Pilots</i> and <i>The Smithereens.</i> \r\n<p>The band cut it\'s \'live\' musical teeth playing opening slots for local favorites Fadeback, but really caught attention during an acoustic gig with Brian Vander Ark of the <i>Verve Pipe</i>, during summer 2007. \'Cain\' even sat in on a couple of songs with the multi-platinum selling artist. \r\n</p><p>BIOC released two singles on the Australian-based mp3.com.au in the fall of 2007. The song, \"Yesterday\'s Happy\", peaked at #16 on the Top 100 Pop & Rock Track charts. That same week, \'Cain\' reached #12 on the Top 100 Pop & Rock Artist charts. Also, \"Yesterday\'s Happy\" was picked for inclusion on a CD sampler, that appeared with the debut issue of the nationally-circulated, <i>\"Sex, Drugs, and Rock And Roll\"</i> magazine. \r\n</p><p>Original members, Sam Boettcher (vocals) and Steve Draganchuk (guitar) recently recruited bass player Greg Gibbs and drummer Al Sumner to join \'Cain\'. The foursome will wrap up 2007 playing local shows before a planned trip into the studio to record a full-length CD in early 2008.</p>\r\n\r\n</b></strong></p><p></p><p></p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p>',1,'',0,''),(2191,2348,'7 Profitz',3,86,'www.7profitz.com','Long Island','','Deep within the New York Underground Hip-Hop scene, knowledge was being spread at a high velocity, thus sparking a chain of events that coincides with the parallel energies of the galaxy. On March 17, 2007 there was a resurrection, and reborn were, the 7 Profitz. The 7 Profitz consits of the three, founding members, Apademik the Disciple, the Producer best known for Producing and Directing, The Razah Code (2006), The Renaissance Child DVD (Limited Edition: 10,000 Units)(2007), and his role of founding Funkin Beatz Entertainment Corp., Elle Madison the Vocalist, who has worked on tracks with well known Recording Artists through out her introduction to the Underground Hip-Hop Music scene, this newcomer is a classic voice in the making, and last but not least Anubiz, the MC delivers that gritty raw Southern mixed with New York influence type flow.\r\n\r\n\r\nFor the 7 Profitz Debut release, \"The Resurrection LP\" December 18, \'07, the 7 Profitz also worked with A. Supreme Wilder of Git Rite Music who Produced the song \"2099 A.D.\", Cheech of Plump Juice Ent./IGT Music Produced the song \"The Way It Goes\", and Battery Jackson of Jacksonberg Ent., who Produced \"Angel Of Death\" all songs featured on \"The Resurrection LP\". \"The Resurrection LP\" also features Doc. G on the Unreleased EQ AllStars Song, \"Be Like Me\" \r\n\r\n7 profitz is currently doing live Performances with Dj Six3One where the 7 Profitz are also promoting there upcoming DVD Release, \"The Resurrection DVD\", which Features appearances by ,ShakimUrMajes