t face=\"Verdana\"><font face=\"book antiqua,palatino\">MITCH YOUNG</font> - <em>HARP/PERCUSSION/VOCALS</em><br />\r\n<font face=\"book antiqua,palatino\">DAN CALLNON</font> - <em>DRUMS/PERCUSSION</em><br />\r\n<font face=\"book antiqua,palatino\">JASON STAATS</font> - <em>GUITAR/VOCALS</em><br />\r\n<font face=\"book antiqua,palatino\">ERIC LAZAR</font> - <em>GUITAR/VOCALS</em><br />\r\n<font face=\"book antiqua,palatino\">JOHN WINGER</font> - <em>BASS/VOCALS</em></font> \r\n',0,''),(2225,2415,'Mr. Flick',3,NULL,'http://www.myspace.com/mrflickmusic','Post Office Box 212233','561-983-1097','<span style=\"font-size: 14pt\">\r\n<p align=\"justify\">\r\n<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"2\"></font>\r\n</p>\r\n<font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt\">\r\n<p align=\"justify\">\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt\"><font size=\"2\">MR. FLICK, born Shawn Fedrick,&nbsp;1982 in New York, got involved in music at a young age. Under the guidance of M.A.D.E. Records, Mr. Flick developed a presence beyond MC battles in the middle school hallways and the streets of Boynton Beach where he moved when he was a teenager.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font></span>\r\n</p>\r\n</span>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">\r\nGrowing up along with hip hop music, Mr. Flick has been influenced by a wide variety of artists and styles. He credits, among others, Outkast, Nas, Busta Rhymes, and MJG and Eight Ball for inspiring his rhyme style. As he puts it, &ldquo;I grew up listening to styles of rap. You can have the most important thing in the world to say but if your delivery isn&#39;t on point then your message falls through the cracks.&rdquo;\r\n</p>\r\n</font>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">\r\n<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"2\"></font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">\r\n<font size=\"2\">His family is deeply rooted in athletics and education still his daily happenings are evident in his music. High school years were divided between sports, some of the rougher elements of the streets, and emceing. &ldquo;It&#39;s been way up and sometimes way down. This shaped my reality. Struggle is nothing new to anyone from where I&#39;m from but there is always more to life than just being from the inner city.&rdquo;<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">\r\n<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"2\"></font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">\r\n<font size=\"2\"><br />\r\nHis music is evidence of a broad perspective and unique look on life. While many rappers spend time and energy trying to label themselves as super-gangstas, Mr. Flick has found it easier to just be himself. His portrayal of life is true and accurate with no embellishment.<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">\r\n<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"2\"></font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">\r\n<font size=\"2\"><br />\r\nStyle wise, Mr. Flick considers his versatility his biggest asset. A testament to his upbringing and musical influences, he is able to do any type of song in front of any type of audience with ease. Mr. Flick promises to resurrect something that the cookie-cutter music business has neglected for too long: <em><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana,Italic\">skills </font><font face=\"Verdana\">and </font></font><em><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana,Italic\">emceing</font><font face=\"Verdana\">. &ldquo;Go ahead and be the hardest rapper alive. Fake about the things you have been through. I&#39;ll just be Flick.&rdquo;</font></font><font size=\"1\"><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"2\"> </font></font></em></em></font>\r\n</p>\r\n</span>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">\r\n<em><em><font face=\"TimesNewRoman,Bold\" size=\"1\"></font></em></em>\r\n</p>\r\n<strong style=\"font-size: 8pt\">Contact: Tim Walker, 561-983-1097</strong> \r\n',0,'',0,''),(2229,2423,'Whitehouse',1,61,'http://www.whitehouse-music.com','Po Box ,Henderson,89009 NV,US','+49911243322','<font size=\"4\" color=\"#00007f\"><br />\r\n<strong><font size=\"2\">\r\n<p>\r\n<f