her to create original, empowering material. Each song, like a separate chapter, unfolds a story of continual hope and courage, moving each listener through her lyrical exposure of emotion.<span>&nbsp;</span><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>With a new CD in the works, scheduled to be released in February 2008, and a tentative tour booked throughout Europe for fall 2008, Williams is steadily moving forward.<span>&nbsp;</span><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>No stranger to the music industry, Williams impressed American Audiences at the 2002 Nashville Tennessee Country Music Alliance Awards where she proudly walked away with the Most Outstanding Showcase Entertainer of the Year Award as well as the Most Promising Female Artist of the Year. Williams has also shared the stage with the Guess Who&rsquo;s Donny McDougal &ldquo;Follow Your Daughter Home,&rdquo; and accompanied famous country star Chris Ledoux&rsquo;s band for a performance at Nashville&rsquo;s Tootsies Bar.<span>&nbsp;</span><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Williams&rsquo; exceptional and energetic performances on stage have taken her across Western Canada striking casinos, rodeos and countless clubs with her powerful presence, including the Main Stage at both the Calgary Stampede and the Edmonton Klondike Days.<span>&nbsp;</span><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>This Manitob born, but now a B. C. girl followed a gypsy lifestyle of movement from a young age and turned to music as a way of grounding herself. As a passionate singer and songwriter, Williams preaches the potential of sound and voice as a healing medium and gains her musical influence through lending a hand to others that need support during their own hardships. <span>&nbsp;</span><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>&ldquo;I have been writing since I was about 10 years old and loved singing as far back as I can remember. I did the band thing for a few years and then I took a Hiatus and now I am back stronger than ever, ready for whatever God brings to me. I want<span>&nbsp; </span>people to see that no matter where you come from or where you have been, that there is hope for us all.&rdquo;<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Williams will enlighten us all as she exposes the underlying truths of the heart and strength of the human spirit as she takes us down the road less traveled and reveals the inner peace that music can bring. </span>\r\n</pre>\r\n<pre style=\"background: white\">\r\n<span style=\"color: #444444; font-family: \'Comic Sans MS\'\">&nbsp;</span>\r\n</pre>\r\n<pre style=\"background: white\">\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #444444; font-family: \'Comic Sans MS\'\">&nbsp;</span></strong>\r\n</pre>\r\n<pre style=\"background: white\">\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #444444; font-family: \'Comic Sans MS\'\">***************SEE JESSE WILLIAMS PERFORM LIVE IN REVELSTOKE EVERY SATURDAY NIGHT AT BAD PAULS ROADHOUSE GRILL STARTING AT 7PM.*************************</span></strong><span style=\"color: #444444; font-family: \'Comic Sans MS\'\"><span>&nbsp;</span></span>\r\n</pre>\r\n<strong><em><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; color: black; line-height: 115%; font-family: \'Comic Sans MS\'\">&nbsp;</span></em></strong><strong><em><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; color: black; line-height: 115%; font-family: \'Comic Sans MS\'\">Darryll Few - Birch Radio United Kingdom</span></em></strong><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; color: black; line-height: 115%; font-family: \'Comic Sans MS\'\"> </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; color: black; line-height: 115%; font-family: \'Comic Sans MS\'\">&quot;Having been playing Jessie&#39;s music for well over 12 months now, this debut mini album did more than impress me. IT BLEW MY SOCKS OFF! It combines 3 of Jessie&#39;s own songs, fabulous whether you love country or not and proof that Jessie is not just another country singer, but a multi talented singer in her cover of Fleetwood Mac/Stevie Nicks with &quot;Dreams&quot;, a song we all love and done with unrivalled comparison to the original. Closing with a more traditional arrangement this CD is proof of a very wide range of talents in Jessie and would without hesitation give it 5 stars! It just leaves you wanting more!&quot; <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><em>The Indie News Network Newsletter - Kyle Kissman </em></strong>- &quot;She does an excellent version of Amazing Grace. Your heart will melt at the, oh-so, sweet sound.&quot; <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><em>Bjarne C. Hesselbjerggaard - Country - Action Show, Radio Sindal, Denmark, BJ the DJ Show on TWANGTOWNUSA Web Radio - </em></strong>&quot;The Other Side of Town, a five song CD on Canadian singer/songwriter Jessie Williams. Once I got my hands on this CD, the frontpage photo first caught my attention, for obvious reasons. So I said to myself: Can this Lady sing ?? Shame on me. She&acute;s great! What a voice, and what a great sound on this CD!! And talking about Jessie&acute;s songwriting. I must admit - her own songs are the best on the CD. It takes a man to stand up and do Amazing Grace, without any support than your own voice, but Jessie does it, and does it good. Take a listen, it gives me a hairstand, and it will give you one as well. I am very sure Jessie has alot to offer country music fans in the future, so be on</span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: \'Comic Sans MS\'\"><font size=\"3\"> </font></span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; color: black; line-height: 115%; font-family: \'Comic Sans MS\'\">the lookout for her.&rdqu