 of 2003 and was known as &quot;Plinth&quot; (lets not ask questions, we know... not the greatest name ever created). In early September 2003 the band finally found a vocalist that fit the Genre of music it was trying to create. Sierra, Stephanie, and Alicia all agreed the name really shouldn&#39;t be Plinth and the name was changed to Addictive Tragedy. Not because we didn&#39;t like the name Plinth... because we had no idea what it even meant... anywho, back to the story. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn late December 2003 Brendan departed the band and Addictive Tragedy picked up Angela. Angela left the band. After that, we picked up Safiyya Hunter. Safiyya was with the band for about one year when she made the decision to join the peace corps. The band fully respects her choice and hopes she goes far in her life in whatever she chooses to do. Out of a major turn of events, Addictive Tragedy picked up Angela once again and released her for the second time. In early December Addictive Tragedy decided to pick up one more great guitarist, George. On December 30th we picked up Rich. Thats right everyone, we are BACK ON TRACK... SO LOOK OUT! Big things poppin, little things stoppin.\r\n</p>\r\n',1,'Sierra-Vocals<br />\r\nStephanie-Guitar<br />\r\nGeorge-Guitar<br />\r\nRich-Bass<br />\r\nDrums-TBA\r\n',0,''),(2403,1000142,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2409,1000150,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2410,1000151,'Jim Emmons',1,61,'http://www.myspace.com/jimemmons','11185 Dragoon Tr.','574-286-4116','<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\';\">Jim Emmons was born and raised in South Bend, Indiana and is a self-taught, self contained independent singer and songwriter. He taught himself to play piano by ear starting at the age of 16. He used his talents to record several local demos to submit them to record companies. After working with a few of the local known rock bands, musicians and recording studios, he sought to form his own home based recording studio to create and compile his own home demos. Once the internet became the fashion for independents to release and market their own music, Jim jumped on the bandwagon to do the same with his own.</span><div><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\';\"><br class=\"webkit-block-placeholder\"></span></div><div><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\';\">He recorded and released his first full length album, \"The Only One\", Ã‚Â in 2005 along with the #1 SoundClick pop/rock singles \"The End of the World\", \"All Because of U\", and \"Hey Diddle Dawn\". Ã‚Â Another popular ballad that reached the top 20 SoundClick charts was \"Stay With Me\", which also received airplay on Joe Kelley\'s \"Upper Room\" on 88.5 FM in Fairfield, CT.</span></div><div><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\';\"><br class=\"webkit-block-placeholder\"></span></div><div><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\'; \">In 2006, Jim began recording and working on his sophomore album \"Scorpio\" which was released in the Spring of 2007. The album continued in the tradition of the debut album with strong pop/rock based songs as well as deep, personal ballads. This album also marked the debut of Jim\'s guitar playing, which he is continuing to teach himself as he did with the piano.</span><br></div><div><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\';\"><br class=\"webkit-block-placeholder\"></span></div><div><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\';\">In the Summer of 2007, Jim was searching the internet and accidentally Google\'d a website that would pique his interests. He discovered author and poet Geoffrey Dicker and found his work to be as imaginative as his own music. After contacting Geoffrey and a few trial demos were composed, a mutual agreement was made and the two creative forces were hard at work on a 3rd album for Emmons. \"In The Absence of Red\" is by far the most inspired, stunning and in-depth work Jim has created to date. With the help of Geoffrey\'s lyrical poetry, each song tells a story of love and loss, hope and happiness, future and fornication that can only be portrayed the way Jim has imagined it to be. The album\'s strong hooks, deep lyrical alchemy, and catchy beats are a strong indication that the world is about to discover a whole new hybrid of pop/rock/jazz flavored music.</span></div>',0,'',0,''),(2411,1000152,'Gary Ramsey',7,NULL,'','217 stony point rd.','704-734-1219','I come from a small mountain town in North Carolina,but I have traveled the U.S. from coast to coast,sometimes as a roadie for national acts and sometimes jammin out myself.I am a singer/songwriter/musician that just wants to do what I enjoy most...ROCKIN&#39; OUT! I play Guitar(lead and rhythm)and I play Bass and I sing.Hopefully you all will give me a listen and leave me some good feedback.Thanks to all,sincerely,Gary Ramsey&nbsp;&nbsp; P.S. I&nbsp; also have my music on <a href=\"http://www.jamwave.com/\">www.jamwave.com</a> and <a href=\"http://www.rawindieradio.com/\">www.rawindieradio.com</a> so come by and visit me there to hear even more of my tunes,you won&#39;t be sorry,I promise. \r\n',1,'Gary Ramsey-vocals/guitars \r\n',0,''),(2497,1000324,'HOLYGOLD',1,14,'http://www.myspace.com/holygoldmusic','','','<em>A music that comes straight from the heart. Wounded memories and real deep love. Noise and melody. So heavy, but yet so sweet.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</em><br />\r\nThe Holygold project was started in 2007. In the previous years I&#39;ve been playing with several bands such as Reverse, Streamers, S.W.O.C. and Goldah. With &quot;Goldah&quot; we recorded the largely appreciated debut cd &quot;Waiting for something to happen&quot; that received many good reviews and permitted the band to play live in the cast of very important festivals such as &quot;Sanremo Rock&quot; and &quot;M.E.I&quot;. Unfortunately we split up in the beginning of 2007. &quot;HOLYGOLD&quot; is a &quot;one man band&quot;. In my songs you can find a little bit of all my influences (Rock, Pop, Metal, Hard Rock, Dark, Grunge). \r\n',0,'',0,''),(2413,1000154,'The Fleas',1,71,'http://www.myspace.com/thefleasplease','','0797 212 0836','<strong><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><font size=\"3\">THE FLEAS</font></span></strong><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><font size=\"3\">&nbsp;</font></span><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><font size=\"3\">Stuck in the daily grind but reaching for a better time, the Fleas&rsquo; songs come from places you don&rsquo;t see on the telly any more, but can still read about in books.</font></span><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><font size=\"3\">&nbsp;</font></span><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><font size=\"3\">Piers Eccleston fronts the band, writing a diverse set for the five piece that stretches from doomy, cinematic bossanovas, to indy folk belters and three minute rock anthems.</font></span><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><font size=\"3\">&nbsp;</font></span><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><font size=\"3\">Finding the lineup to play the songs wasn&rsquo;t easy. It eventually took a Latin twist from two Argentinians to bring the sound together live. Rico teaches guitar, while Mannie is simply a born drummer and showman. They bring their own heady brew of South American influences, giving the diverse set a unifying soundscape.</font></span><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><font size=\"3\">&nbsp;</font></span><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><font size=\"3\">Completing the lineup are the two girls in the band, Demi on bass and Bernadette on percussion and glockenspiel. Both add an extra vocal dimension that&rsquo;s not a million miles from The Magic Numbers.</font></span><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><font size=\"3\">&nbsp;</font></span><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><font size=\"3\">T