60 Wilshire Blvd, Beverly Hills, 90010','661-297-8082','<font face=\"verdana,geneva\"><strong><font color=\"#800000\">Darren Farris</font></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nGrowing up in a musical family, Los Angeles-based singer/songwriter Darren Farris&rsquo;s path seemed to be cut for a musical life. Darren&#39;s mother, Lois Faye, was the lead singer of The Waylighters, a popular touring band in the 70&#39;s. A young Farris was never left out of the band. &quot;Oh yeah, I really had little choice but to love music,&quot; Farris explains, &quot;There was always practicing, writing music, and musicians [coming] in and out of our home.&quot; </font>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"verdana,geneva\">Farris describes being raised in a rock band atmosphere. &quot;Music was just all around me - acid rock, power-pop, country, and even spiritual. My mom was playing during some pivotal changes in pop music, so I was exposed to all of that,&quot; Farris says, &quot;Every time a new single would be hot on the charts, we would have to rush out to the record store and pick up the 45 (rpm record). They would play them over and over, until they got it down.&quot; </font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"verdana,geneva\">After being raised the first five years of his life in the heart of Chicago, moving to the more rural setting of Tennessee gave Farris a wide cultural perspective to draw from. &quot;Yeah, I have always had to deal with the &lsquo;duck out of water syndrome&rsquo;,&quot; Farris says of an early childhood of moving from place to place. About 70 miles outside Memphis, Darren was heavily influenced by the wide array of music being pumped out on the Memphis airwaves. He writes about the glory days of cutting school to hang out with local blues session musicians such as Alabama Smith on the world famous Beale Street. &quot;I had this very small circle of friends and we were all into rock and roll and understanding the roots of it [rock music]. We did so many crazy things, it&#39;s a wonder I am here to tell the story,&quot; Farris muses of a storybook-like wild youth, including anecdotes of his growing up years and adolescence in the autobiographical song &ldquo;Part of Something&rdquo;. </font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"verdana,geneva\">Darren&#39;s new album &ldquo;Psychopathic Issues&rdquo; is a testament to always taking the road less traveled and not looking back. &quot;It was actual therapy for me, no pun intended,&quot; laughs Farris, as he describes his experience writing the album. Consisting of thirteen guitar- and lyric-driven tracks, it completes what he describes as an &quot;audio-ography of the past 10 or so&quot; years of his life. &quot;I find it very difficult to write about things that I haven&#39;t experienced first hand, so I really have little choice but to write about my life situations,&quot; Farris says of his songwriting process. &quot;I think that is actually why people seem to get drawn to this album,&quot; Farris continues, &quot;It all comes from real places, about real people, written at real points of raw emotion.&quot; </font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"verdana,geneva\">Starting the journey with the adrenalin-pumping &quot;Nobody But You&quot; and ending with a guitar-smashing, cinematic remix of the debut single &quot;Jenna&quot;, &ldquo;Psychopathic Issues&rdquo; blends just the right elements of powerpop and mainstream pop/rock to secure a musical grip on the listener&rsquo;s mind. This collection of stinging guitar and lyric-driven works is sure to be quintessential to any enthusiast&rsquo;s collection. Farris is banking on his &ldquo;Psychopathic Issues&rdquo; to be the right prescription for an ailing rock and roll radio that is undernourished and in dire need of a new and exciting sound.</font> \r\n</p>\r\n',0,'',0,''),(2435,1000198,'Cruel Noise',1,68,'http://www.cruelnoise.ch','Hubstreet 23, CH - 9500 Wil','+41 79 750 70 62','Cruel Noise is a Swiss Rock/Punk Band that was \r\nfounded back in 1998. After countless gigs, 3 demos and some line-up \r\nchanges, we&#39;ve finally recorded our first 13-track album &quot;Out of the \r\nMadhouse&quot;. Tunes that will make your testicles quaking and your arses shaking!<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe&#39;re free to travel, so if you could hook us up with some gigs in your part of the word we&#39;d be glad to do the same for your group in our region. \r\n',1,'<img src=\"../uploads/1000198/20070819_15.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"282\" /><br />\r\nFrom left to right: Dodo (Guitars), Adi (Bass), Sonam (Vocals), Frank (Drums)\r\n',0,''),(2436,1000199,'Architectural Demise',7,36,'http://www.architecturaldemise.com','','253-226-0942','<a href=\"http://www.reverbnation.com/c./a4/269235/127214/Artist/127214/Artist/link\"><img style=\"width: 389px; height: 97px\" src=\"http://www.reverbnation.com/c./a3/269235/127214/Artist/127214/Artist/res.gif\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Architectural%20Demise\" width=\"389\" height=\"97\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.quantcast.com/p-05---xoNhTXVc\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"display: none\" src=\"http://pixel.quantserve.com/pixel/p-05---xoNhTXVc.gif\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Quantcast\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /></a><img style=\"visibility: hidden; width: 0px; height: 0px\" src=\"http://counters.gigya.com/wildfire/CIMP/bT*xJmx*PTEyMDk*MTg4ODIwNTQmcHQ9MTIwOTQxODk*OTg2NSZwPTI3MDgxJmQ9YmFubmVyJTVGZmlyc3QlNUZnZW4mbj*mZz*x.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" width=\"0\" height=\"0\" /> <br />\r\nArchitectural Demise <br />\r\n<br />\r\nArchitectural Demise&rsquo;s heavily textured industrial metal is a brain-charging spike through the skull. Robust electronic elements are woven together into a thick, heady construct of dark intensity while chugging guitar riffs bring a new level of brooding power to the mix. The mingling of guitar and electro industrial is big, bad, pulsing and driven. All the layers are stacked just so in order to create a near-perfect balance of sound. Bleak artistic vision and accomplished production round out the creative picture of Architectural Demise. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhat Music Does to Me <br />\r\n<br />\r\nJust as many different elements coalesce to create the complete sound of an Architectural Demise song, so does a confluence of emotions come together to form the full emotional response to music&rsquo;s stimuli. At least that&rsquo;s how it is for the evil genius behind Architectural Demise, Acid Flesh. &ldquo;I couldn&rsquo;t possibly pick a single emotion that describes what music does to me or how it makes me feel.&rdquo; That complexity of passion is exactly what Acid is creating with his multi-layered, intelligent industrial. It ranges from mid-tempo broodings to fast-paced electronic assault. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nEmbracing Tragedy <br />\r\n<br />\r\nArchitectural Demise is also a blistering catharsis, an embracing of the ills of life. They exist, they happen, they must be accepted, assimilated and confronted. Thus, Architectural Demise. The music is a reflection of the shadows of life. It is both a universal consideration of the human condition and a personal response to Acid&#39;s own life. &ldquo;I would have to say most of my influence comes from my life and the events that I have encountered therein that led me to an aggressive stance. My music is an expression of my being and state of mind when tragedy or tragedies have presented themselves in front of me, both in present and in past.&rdquo; <br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Artist at Work <br />\r\n<br />\r\nAcid is always writing new music. He&rsquo;s a busy songwriter with lots of aggression to turn into expression, much to the giddy delight of snarl-grinned fans, no doubt. A new album is in the works, more good cheer for industrial-heads. &ldquo;The album I am working on right now will be titled &ldquo;Malfeasance.&rdquo; It&rsquo;s set for release early in 2008. Acid is currently working with A&amp;R Select, the world&rsquo;s leading independent artist development firm, based out of Los Angeles, CA. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n&ldquo;Architectural Demise&rdquo; is both an iconic presentation of classic aggro-industrial considerations and a step into the future for the genre.&rdquo; &ndash; A&amp;R Select \r\n',0,'',0,''),(2439,1000210,'7 MILE SCREAM',1,14,'','1006 tiffiany trail','1803-425-6475','We have all played in different bands and sometimes in the same band together. Chris and Bryan were playing in a band called 5 mile scream . Jeff played a few gigs with 5 mile scream but was playing&nbsp; with Ernie in a band called saving april. One day&nbsp; we found ourselves over at Chris&#39;s house practicing to go to the studio and the rest is history. I guess you could say that we&#39;re just four friends that love to play music&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Thanks for reading&nbsp; God bless&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 7 MILE SCREAM \r\n',1,'<p>\r\nCHRIS CURRIE&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Vocals and guitar<br />\r\nERNIE BAKER&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bass<br />\r\nBRYAN SMITH&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Drums<br />\r\nJEFF MELTON&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Lead guitar \r\n</p>\r\n',0,''),(2440,1000212,'RAFTREE',1,71,'http://www.myspace.com/raftreeband','P.O. box 1431 Union, NJ 07083','908-265-4075','Kenneth Raftree attended his first rock concert at 11 years of age witnessing one of the great rock bands of his generation, AC/DC.&nbsp; After being captivated by the arena rock experience, he set his sites on playing guitar and never looked back.&nbsp; Today, Kenneth fronts his own band.&nbsp; As a vocalist, musician, songwriter, producer and engineer,<br />\r\nKenneth collaborates with long time friend drummer and vocalist Vincent Livolsi to create a brilliant new experience in today&rsquo;s rock culture.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTo Highlight that experience, RAFTREE is proud to announce that guitarist Daniel Doderer and bassist Chris Targia have become part of RAFTREE.&nbsp; Dan is a ferocious guitar player playing since the age of 10,.&nbsp; After building guitars for Kramer, he moved to Los Angles to play in Nations while being endorsed by MESA BOOGIE.&nbsp; Chris is one of the most articulate sought after bassists around.&nbsp; He adds the full rounded thunder and subtleties most bass players miss.&nbsp; Chris&rsquo;s past and present credits include Suburban Panic and Angel Vivaldi.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhile performing live in clubs and venues in New Jersey and New York such as Six Flags Great Adventure, Dexter&rsquo;s, Axis Lounge, Dingbatz, Arlene&rsquo;s Grocery, The Blue Room and The Metropolitan Lounge, they have been a featured artist on JerseyJam.com, WSOU&rsquo;s Street Patrol and WDHA&rsquo;s Home Grown Spotlight.&nbsp; This latest self-titled four song EP has received rave reviews both locally and internationally.&nbsp; RAFTREE is a solid rock act that blends funk, metal and soul and has received critical acclaim such as:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&ldquo;Raftree&#39;s soulful voice and heavy riffs work well against tasty lead guitar on songs like &quot;Room&quot; and the melodic single &quot;Salvation&quot;, while &quot;Missing&quot; and &ldquo;Eyes You Hide&rdquo; are just all around solid heavy rock numbers with pounding rhythms and fiery guitar leads.&rdquo;<br />\r\n-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Pete Pardo, Publisher, Sea Of Tranquility<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&ldquo;Salvation a forceful song with elements of classic rock fused with everything including the kitchen sink under the guise of contemporary innovative rock! Absolutely brilliant!&rdquo;<br />\r\n-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Colin Lynch, Executive Director, International Online Magazine<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&ldquo;The songs on this EP have a very refreshing sound and the voice from Kenneth does remind me of a certain famous voice sometimes&hellip; he combines the different styles as if it&rsquo;s just one style. There are not a lot of bands who can do that like Raftree.&rdquo;<br />\r\n-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Jeroen, Editor, Rock-E-Zine (Netherlands)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&ldquo;&quot;Missing&quot; is a song that would deem a favorite slot on MTV&#39;s HeadBangers Ball as soon as the metal heads heard it. I can see air guitars rockin&sbquo; and invisible drums slamming as the viewers put on their best &quot;Bill and Ted&quot; impressions. You guys will surely get a heaping spoonful of what Raftree is all about&rdquo;<br />\r\n-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Kristin Theckston, Staff Writer, BacStagePass.com<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&ldquo;Progressive metal comes in all forms and sometimes sounds the same, but Raftree is one of those bands that you can label as &ldquo;progressive&rdquo; but has a sound that is all their own&rdquo;<br />\r\n-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Derric Miller, Staff Writer, Hardrock Heaven.net<br />\r\n<br />\r\nRAFTREE&rsquo;s single Salvation is featured on The Best New Bands of 2007 compilation CD and they will be performing live throughout New Jersey, New York and Pennsylvania.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nRAFTREE BAND P.O. Box 1431 Union, NJ 07083 <br />\r\nraftree@comcast.net <br />\r\nhttp://www.myspace.com/raftreeband<br />\r\n',1,'',0,''),(2441,1000213,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2442,1000214,'frantic',1,66,'http://www.myspace.com/franticswitzerland','vanGARDENmusic, M.Schlemmermeyer, Im GrÃ¼nen Hof 5, 8280 Kreuzlinlgen, SWITZERLAND','+41795414759','<table border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td width=\"100\" align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"><span class=\"OrangeText style3\"></span><br />\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\">an\r\n			autumn day in the year 2000: four youths met spontaneously for a\r\n			jam-session. what began with occas