0s, cassette tape, record, CD, 8-track, breathing, growing, hating, yelling, fucking, eating, sleeping, and of course... funk.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThis has inspired a brand of music that transcends traditional definition. Many, including The Jebba themselves, have described their style as funk; however, to them, funk is freedom. It holds the least amount of boundaries and for that, they love and embrace her.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTheir aversion for popular protocol extends beyond the creation of music and spills over to their live performance.&nbsp; A no holds barred charge of unbridled energy is released in full force when Stex Jebba takes the stage.&nbsp; Nothing is reserved.&nbsp; Armed with a catalogue of hard hitting originals and an arsenal of popular covers spanning many genres, Stex Jebba is ready and waiting to take on any venue or audience with full passion and confidence.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWith a distinct musical style and an imposing stage presence, Stex Jebba is committed to fall into league with the likes of Red Hot Chili Peppers, The Funky Meters, and Rage Against The Machine while embracing the gusto of Guns N&#39; Roses. They have chosen to draw from each of these personas and use them in the ongoing and infinite creation of Stex Jebba.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&quot;This life is hedonism. This is our medium. So let&#39;s all get funked up.&quot; -Stex Jebba</span> \r\n',1,'Brett McMillin - Lead Vocals, Rhythm Guitar<br />\r\nDub-G - Lead Guitar, Back Up Vocals<br />\r\nEl Hombre - Bass<br />\r\nRon Mencer - Drums<br />\r\nShara &quot;Goldy&quot; Prophet - Back Up Vocals \r\n',0,''),(2459,1000250,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2460,1000252,'OTG',3,20,'http://www.myspace.com/otgsoundz','','','OTG is a young latin solo artist.&nbsp; He is somewhat new to the game.&nbsp; Still, with only 1 years experience , this Bronxonite has written arranged, mixed, remixed and recorded his own songs!&nbsp; <br />\r\n<br />\r\nHis style ranges from, laid back r/b to laid back rap flows, with a love for Screwed vocals!\r\n',0,'',0,''),(2461,1000253,'CHERINE ANDERSON',101,NULL,'http://www.cherineanderson.com','1121 N Bethlehem Pike Suite 60-292 Springhouse PA 19477','215-628-3109','<!--StartFragment--><p style=\"text-align: center\" class=\"MsoTitle\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma Small Cap\'; font-size: 43px\"><img src=\"http://i70.photobucket.com/albums/i85/raahtid1/CHERINEANDERSONBWphotobyRicoKinn-1.jpg\" alt=\"Cherine Anderson 2008\" title=\"Cherine Anderson &quot;Princess of Dancehall-Soul &quot; the new generation of Reggae music\" width=\"349\" height=\"523\" /><br /></span></p><p style=\"text-align: center\" class=\"MsoTitle\"><span style=\"font-size: 32pt; font-family: \'Tahoma Small Cap\'; color: windowtext\">Cherine Anderson</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center\" class=\"MsoBodyText\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma Small Cap\'; color: windowtext\"><strong>&ldquo;Entertainment is mypassion, I am hungry for this!!!&rdquo;</strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align: center\" class=\"MsoBodyText\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial; color: windowtext\">She stands at five feet, three inches tall,soaking up the world with a voice reminiscent of pure and untainted soul.  Whatkind of soul?  According to songstress Cherine Anderson, this soul is unlikeany other, for it is <strong><em>Dancehall Soul</em></strong></span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial; color: windowtext\">, &ldquo;a mixture of reggae, dancehall,soul and R&amp;B, truly incorporating the grittiness of my past with the sweetness of the things to which I have been exposed.&rdquo;  In this modern dayparade of glamour, glitz, and unmerited superstardom, Cherine truly embodiesstar-like qualities. She is a triple threat: singer, songwriter and acclaimedJamaican actress, having starred in two of Jamaica&rsquo;s most successful films, <u>DancehallQueen</u> (1997) and <u>One Love</u> (2003).  Cherine has been focusing herattention on writing music and collaborating with industry giants like Sly&amp; Robbie, David Norland (Madonna, Dallas Austin), JeekyMan (Lil Kim), aswell as prominent Jamaican producer Christopher Birch (Shaggy).  She recentlycollaborated on remixes with Wyclef Jean and ex-Beatle member Paul McCartney. Reggae and urban radio stations in Jamaica, the US, Canada, several Europeancountries, as well as internet radio have already fallen for the sweet voicespilling from their systems courtesy of her debut hit single &ldquo;Good Love&rdquo;. Cherine quickly followed &ldquo;Good Love&rdquo; with a lover&rsquo;s rock duet with Chuck Fendawhich quickly topped both the singles and the video charts in Jamaica. Cherine&rsquo;s latest release, &ldquo;Kingston State of Mind&rdquo;, provides her perspective onthe realities of the environment in Kingston and illustrates the songwriting depth that lies in this young artist.  Cherine also took on the challenge ofdirecting the music video for &ldquo;Kingston State of Mind&rdquo;. The video topped the Jamaican video charts as well as peaked MTV Tempo&rsquo;s Cross Caribbean videocountdown, and was eventually retired from the countdown after spending animpressive four months in the top ten.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center\" class=\"MsoBodyText\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial; color: windowtext\">It is important to note that this profoundtalent did not emerge overnight.  Born in Rockfort in East Kingston, Jamaica,her parents Derryck &amp; Barbara Anderson kept Cherine and her two oldersisters in Sunday school and any other church activity that would keep them off the unstable streets.  It was in church that her musical talent was discovered.Cherine explains, &ldquo;It wasn&rsquo;t so much the message in the church songs thatappealed to me at first&hellip;it was the passion and strength of peoples&rsquo; voices.&rdquo;  At the age of 12, she became a touring member of Ashe Performing Arts Ensemble,one of the Caribbean&rsquo;s most successful performance companies, and receivedprofessional training in dance, music and theatre. In 2003, Cherine combined her two loves, singing and acting, starring in the film <u>One Love</u>.  Hervoice lent two heartfelt songs to the film&rsquo;s soundtrack, and her acting talentearned her the MTV2/Urbanworld Film Festival Award for best actress in afeature film. </span></p><p style=\"text-align: center\" class=\"MsoBodyText\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial; color: windowtext\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center\" class=\"MsoBodyText\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial; color: windowtext\">One would think that nothing else could possibly fit into this seemingly superstar equation, yet there is more.  Notonly does this young woman possess talent, beauty and class, but Cherine isalso a highly educated, intelligent young woman as well.  Having graduated withhonors from the prestigious Middlebury College with a Bachelor of Arts in Filmand Music and a minor in Japanese Language and Literature, Cherine continuouslyraises the bar for herself in every aspect of her life.  During her collegecareer, her passion and dedication to her craft led her to acquire numerousinternships at entertainment companies such as MTV Networks, Interscope Recordsand the Chris Blackwell owned Palm Pictures and Palm Records.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center\" class=\"MsoBodyText\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma Small Cap\'; color: windowtext\"><strong>&ldquo;The world needs tohear more reggae and dancehall from a female&rsquo;s perspective.</strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align: center\" class=\"MsoBodyText\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma Small Cap\'; color: windowtext\"><strong>I feel blessed tohave such great legacy set by Bob Marley, Shabba,  etc&hellip;</strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align: center\" class=\"MsoBodyText\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma Small Cap\'; color: windowtext\"><strong>But I want to be apart of the female movement out of Jamaica</strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align: center\" class=\"MsoBodyText\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Tahoma Small Cap\'; color: windowtext\"><strong>that makes a similaror even greater impression on the world.&rdquo;</strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align: center\" class=\"MsoBodyText\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial; color: windowtext\">According to reggae legend Sly Dunbar,&ldquo;Cherine is the real deal. A truly strong vocalist on hard core reggae riddimswith the ability and potential to surpass Jamaican audiences to reach themasses.&rdquo;  With all the attention on reggae, reggaeton and dancehall on theinternational market, Cherine has all the right ingredients:  vocal and actingtalent, beauty, intellect and a solid understanding of the entertainmentindustry, to be more than just a successful artist &ndash; but a Caribbean brand.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center\" class=\"MsoBodyText\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial; color: windowtext\">In August, 2007, Cherine took to the roadwith Sly and Robbie &amp; the Taxi Gang; not as an opening act, but as thefeatured vocalist on the 15 date tour.  Cherine lit up the stage night afternight with her remarkable vocals and commanding stage presence.  Music criticsand fans alike took fast notice of Cherine&rsquo;s electrifying performances. StevenMirken for Variety magazine wrote, &ldquo;<span>Cherine Anderson nearly stolethe show. The Jamaican beauty is another in the long line of fine vocalists whohave recorded for the Taxi label; her sweet yet authoritative voice lends amaternal comfort to Marley&#39;s &quot;Redemption Song,&quot; her recently recorded&quot;Kingston State of Mind&quot; and the gospel standard &quot;Swing Low,Sweet Chariot.&quot;</span>  Audience member Martin Wong blogged, &ldquo;<span>Cherine Anderson had the full package, with an amazing voice and stagepresence. She came out with &quot;Redemption Song&quot; and pretty much killedit through the remainder of the set. Is she a star yet?&rdquo;  Cherine feels blessedto have had the opportunity to tour with the Taxi Gang and looks forward toreaching countless additional audiences to share with them what is <strong>&hellip;<em>DANCEHALLSOUL</em></strong></span><span><strong>&hellip;</strong></span></span></p><!--EndFragment-->',0,'',0,''),(2462,1000254,'Sleddogs',1,17,'http://www.myspace.com/sleddogs','','','<span>In just the first two years together   Kelowna, BC&#39;s <strong>SLEDDOGS</strong>,\r\nconsisting of Kenny Byrka lead vocals, electric bass, electric piano,\r\nsynthesizers, Michael Donley; electric guitar, backing vocals, and Eric\r\nFunk; drums and percussion, backing vocals, have made a significant\r\nmark on the Canadian rock landscape.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</span><span>Following\r\na hectic 2006, SLEDDOGS settled into a West Coast groove to test the\r\nwaters for their highly anticipated follow up with producer <strong>Steven Drake</strong>,\r\nformally of The Odds, also known for his stellar work with The\r\nTragically Hip, 54-40, Michelle Wright and Jeremy Fisher. After getting\r\na taste of what might come to be during the re-recording of the track\r\nHappy Face, mixed by Richard Chycki (Rush, Aerosmith, Mick Jagger,\r\nPink), and a rocking Christmas version of Frosty the Snowman, the band\r\nknew that Steven was the right man to steer the ship on their sophomore\r\nalbum &quot;<strong>TAKE ME   AWAY</strong>&quot;.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</span><span>The SLEDDOGS goal with &quot;<strong>TAKE ME   AWAY</strong>&quot;\r\nwas to create an album that reflects their live sound. They definitely\r\nhit the nail on the head and it was their live sound heard in </span><span>Austin</span><span>, </span><span>TX</span><span> during SXSW 2007 by <strong>Bhurr   Records</strong> label head Chris Case that initiated the deal that saw &quot;TAKE ME   AWAY&quot; hit store shelves across </span><span>Canada</span><span> on August 28th<strong> </strong>through <strong>Fontana North / Universal Music Canada.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</strong></span><span>The moody and popular album track,   Lack of Control was released on </span><span>Oct 15 2007</span><span> to Canadian Rock and HAC radio   where both formats are reporting the single charting within the top 100 in </span><span>Canada</span><span>.\r\nA video for their Rockin&#39; version of Frosty the Snowman was also shot\r\nin November 2007, starring John Dunsworth and Pat Roche known for their\r\nroles as Mr.Lahey and Randy of <strong>The   Trailer Park Boys. </strong></span>\r\n<span>Ready\r\nto launch a full scale attack across the pond in 2008, they are kick\r\nstarting the year with their first UK tour in February, during which\r\nthey will play two weeks of mostly sold out shows at top university\r\nvenues with hypnotist Tony Lee (followed up by a one week tour in\r\nMexico!). Alongside the tour, their second full length critically\r\nacclaimed album &#39;Take Me Away&#39; will be hitting stores all over the </span><span>UK</span><span> via Code 7 distribution.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</span><span>The\r\nband is consistently intent on pushing deeper into new territories,\r\ncontinuing to make serious noise on the Rock landscape!<br />\r\n</span>\r\n',1,'Kenny Byrka- lead vocals, electric bass, electric piano, synthesisers<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMichael Donley-electric guitar, backing vocals<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEric Funk- drums and percussion, backing vocals\r\n',0,''),(2463,1000257,'Ziplok',3,19,'http://ziplok','24 Boyd rd.','6035575416','Born in 1978 in Nashua, New Hampshire. Ziplok has always had a passion\r\nfor music. Now with 20 songs for sale all over the world on the\r\ninternet Ziplok has attained the first goal which was to be for sale.\r\nNow the second goal is to do tv and movies which you will see a lot\r\nmore of in the future. Check out the music online and watch the videos\r\non youtube.com. You can find me everywhere on the web.\r\n',0,'',0,''),(2646,1000913,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2464,1000263,'The Big Dogs',8,79,'http://www.thebigdogs.com','','561-333-0966','The BIG DOGS are a band from South Florida that performs festivals, concerts, corporate events at regional and local venues. Anchored by songwriting partners KC Vinck and Marco Cocchiaro, they have developed an edgy, blues based style of rock and roll with a &ldquo;twang&rdquo;. Marco&#39;s guitar and KC&#39;s lead vocals provide the band&#39;s signature sound. Their original music is in the same vain as The Rolling Stones, 38 Special, The Georgia Satellites and The Black Crows and can be associated to rock or southern rock with cross over into country and pop genres. \r\n',1,'',0,''),(2466,1000269,'Deep End of the Pool',1,71,'http://www.myspace.com/thedeependofthepool','7 Rue Fontaine Foothill Ranch, CA 92610','949-289-8711','<span style=\"font-family: Verdana\">Deep End of the Pool is an evolutionary reflection of life, unfolding through an array of versatile, moody and passionate tracks.<span>&nbsp; </span>The players bring a vintage approach to musicianship, yet infused with the kind of experimental creativity found off to the more interesting side of today&rsquo;s alternative music movement.<span>&nbsp; </span>Their sound was born from uncommon, inventive guitar work, rock solid pocket rhythms and world-class vocals.<span>&nbsp; </span>James&rsquo; vocals travel from extremes of overwhelming, relentless intensity to an emotional, velvety smooth croon that speaks to the seat of the soul.<span>&nbsp; <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nRock, Alternative, Crossover, Indie, Experimental, Innovative, Creative, Original, Real, Genuine, New</span></span>\r\n',1,'<font face=\"verdana,geneva\" size=\"3\">James Fahnestock - Lead Vocals<br />\r\nWilliam Gunville - Guitar<br />\r\nJeff Yorke - Bass<br />\r\nMark Nakagawa - Drums</font> \r\n',0,''),(2467,1000275,'The Grilled Lincolns',1,66,'http://www.grilledlincolns.com','Baltimore','301-467-7226','<span class=\"epktxt\">Meet The Grilled Lincolns, also known as &quot;The G-Linx&quot; for short, one of the hottest bands in Baltimore! This group of five talented musicians&mdash;Riddie Becker, &quot;Raw B&quot; Dubois, Mike &quot;Tron&quot; Bakke, Jeremy Ragsdale, and Andy Hall a/k/a &quot;Big Slop (Spittin Lyrics On Point)&quot;&mdash;was founded in 2000. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe G-Linx have been playing sold out shows in the Baltimore/DC metropolitan area and along the east coast. Influenced by hip-hop, rock, jazz and reggae, The Grilled Lincolns have created a unique, <br />\r\nfunky style that appeals to more than one genre of music lover.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn a world of cookie-cutter cover bands, The Grilled Lincolns have perfected their own original musical style that is highly addictive. You probably haven&#39;t heard anything quite like it.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Grilled Lincolns&#39; exciting stage presence and high energy live sets have made them quite the buzz around town. These guys are going to get into your head-either by Riddie&#39;s electric guitar solos, Raw B, Big Slop and Tron&#39;s quick-witted, freestyle hip-hop lyrics, or Jeremy&#39;s funk-jazz keyboard chops. When they are playing the hugely popular lyrical anthem &quot;Raised by Wolves&quot; or the melodically groovy &quot;Green Light&quot;, The G-Linx originals will keep you captivated by their funky <br />\r\nrhythm, fresh lyrics and addictive hooks. It&#39;s guaranteed you&#39;ll be singing one of their songs for a week!<br />\r\n<br />\r\nCurrently working on their third studio album, The Grilled Lincolns&#39; first two studio albums have met wide public acclaim and have made The G-Linx a staple in the regional live music arena. Impressive to both professional musicians and live music enthusiasts, a G-Linx show offers something for everyone.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nCome see what the buzz is about.<br />\r\nHang out with the band.<br />\r\nBuy them a shot.<br />\r\nJust don&#39;t miss seeing the next great thing to come out of Baltimore!<br />\r\n</span>\r\n',1,'Riddie Becker, Rob &quot;D&quot; Dubois, Mike &quot;Tron&quot; Bakke, Jeremy Ragsdale, and Andy &quot;Big Slop&quot; Hall.\r\n',0,''),(2468,1000278,'Lauren Flaherty',1,66,'http://www.LaurenFlaherty.com','636 East 7th st, boston, ma 02127','6178697965','Appearing frequently with her band in Boston and New York, Lauren&#39;s\r\npassionate concerts capture the hearts of her audiences everywhere. She\r\nhas played across the east coast and at legendary stages such like\r\nCBGB&#39;s and the Bitter End. &quot;I want to make my audience feel everything\r\nI&#39;m feeling,&quot; she says, &quot;all of the joy, love and outrage. To create\r\nreal art, and of course to rock out!&quot;\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn addition to her work as a performer, Lauren regularly books\r\nconcerts for her organization, EME Productions to benefit various\r\nphilanthropic causes. She is also featured on Project: Think\r\nDifferent&#39;s social activism album empowerment. More updates about\r\nLauren&#39;s shows are benefits will be posted regularly on www.LaurenFlaherty.com and\r\non myspace.com/LaurenFlaherty.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDiscography:\r\n2006: Self-released Debut Album: &quot;What Makes An Angel&quot;\r\n2005: Empowerment Records&#39; 2005 Compilation CD &quot;The Power To Break You Free&quot;\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAwards and Honors:\r\nGreat American Song Contest: &quot;Top Finalist&quot; for &quot;Angel&quot;\r\nBillboard World Songwriting Contest: Several Honorable Mention Awards\r\nSelected in numerous competitions for Singers and Songwriters (such as\r\nSinger&#39;s Night, Songwriter&#39;s Night, Storytellers, and more to come!)\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTO BE RECEIVE NOTIFICATIONS OF UPCOMING CONCERTS, PLEASE EMAIL SUBSCRIBE@LAURENFLAHERTY.COM.  (PLEASE INCLUDE YOUR CITY.)\r\n',0,'',0,''),(2470,1000281,'Scott Ferrell Projects',1,61,'http://myspace.com/scottferrellprojects','','770-689-8445','',0,'',0,''),(2471,1000282,'The Wonderland Avenue',1,76,'http://www.myspace.com/TheWonderlandAvenue','Austin Tx','281.703.9746','<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: 11px; line-height: normal; -webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 3px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 3px\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: bold\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'book antiqua\', palatino\">The Wonderland Avenue is a considered deliberation of musical philosophies come to fruition. The &lsquo;Avenue&rsquo; emerged as a singular refinement of disparate pieces that have converged into a heroic example of sonic creativity outside the box of &ldquo;scene&rdquo;.&nbsp;<br /><br />Their freshman EP (Inizio) serves up thick juicy sound you can sink your teeth into. Packaged with just enough edginess to add some bite, &quot;INIZIO&quot; gives witness to how an album that is one part neurotic, one part intriguing, and completely bewitching can be thoroughly addictive.&nbsp;<br /><br />Take a stroll down wonderland avenue.&nbsp;</span></span></span><div><br /></div><div><div><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'book antiqua\'; font-size: 11px; font-weight: bold; line-height: normal; -webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 3px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 3px\">--&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; --</span></div><div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'book antiqua\'; font-size: 11px; font-weight: bold; line-height: normal; -webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 3px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 3px\"><br /></span></div><div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /></div><div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp;--&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color: #545454; font-family: \'Lucida Grande\'; font-size: 12px; line-height: 16px\">The Wonderland Avenue is a six-piece experimental rock band out of Austin, TX. As if brought together by the cosmic forces flowing through the universe, The Wonderland Avenue is a collaboration of individual concepts and ideals. It is a combination of taste, talent, and many influences. The Wonderland Avenue consists of drummer, Aric Garcia,21; keyboardist, Gerardo Larios, 24; guitarist and primary vocalist, Isaac Routh, 22; lead guitarist and vocalist, Michael Roy Kelley, 26; acoustic guitarist, Nick Meyerson, 22; and bassist, Ross Fife, 23.	<span><br /><br />The Wonderland Avenue, excluding Gerardo who is originally from Mexico City, grew up in the small town of Humble, Texas. Isaac, Nick and Ross have played together since their freshman year of high school. It was not until their migration to Austin, Texas, that the band joined forces and combined their creativity into what is now The Wonderland Avenue.<br /><br /></span></span><div><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color: #545454; font-family: \'Lucida Grande\'; font-size: 12px; line-height: 16px\">Developing their sound by combining classic and progressive influences with natural musical talent, The Wonderland Avenue has created their own signature style of rock. With their clever, lyrical arrangements and edgy, psychedelic sound, these young men are building quite a following and raising the bar that rock music has been waiting for. In the fall of 2007, the band released their first professionally recorded EP entitled &ldquo;Inizio&rdquo;. The self-produced EP was recorded in downtown Austin, Texas at 5th Street Studios and will be the catalyst for their musically-orchestrated explosion.</span>&nbsp;<br /></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div></div>',1,'<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'trebuchet ms\'; line-height: normal; -webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 3px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 3px\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: bold\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: small\">Michael Roy Kelley-Lead Guitar and Vocals<br />Isaac James Routh-Rhythm Guitar and Vocals<br />Nicholas Meyerson-Acoustic Guitar<br />Gerardo Larios-Keyboards<br />Ross Fife-Bass<br />Aric Garcia-Drums and Percussion</span></span></span>',0,''),(2472,1000283,'Craig Maxim',6,106,'http://www.SouthernMischiefBand.com','','','',0,'',0,''),(2473,1000285,'Johnny Gobbs',1,68,'http://www.johnnygobbs.com','','512-963-4120','',1,'Jason-Guitars<br />\r\nRob-Bass, vocals<br />\r\nRamsey-Drums&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\nKerby-Vocals\r\n',0,''),(2474,1000286,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2475,1000288,'Fumble',1,68,'http://www.fumblerock.com','Walkalone Records / Ruoholahdenkaty 8 / 00180 Helsinki / Finland','','<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal\">Fumble is a melodic punk rock band from Helsinki, Finland. Fumble played its first international show in Barcelona in 2006. Since then the band has toured internationally four times, gained exploding live reputation and produced its debut album &quot;Rise&quot;, released in June 2007 on Walkalone Records.<br /><br />In February 2008 the album&#39;s lead single &quot;Burning Down&quot; was chosen as the opening track of Future Snowboarding Magazine&#39;s digital compilation. As the only European artist to appear on the compilation this marks Fumble&#39;s first significant exposure in North America.&nbsp;<br /><br />In March 2007 three Fumble songs, &quot;Burning Down&quot;, &quot;Start Once Again&quot; and &quot;Reduction&quot; were chosen by LA based Upstream Radio to be featured in the playlist of its radio channel.&nbsp;Furthermore, the video for &quot;Burning Down&quot; has been viewed 20.000 times on Blank TV and has been rated 4/5 by the audience.</span><div><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal\"><br />Influenced by melodic punk rock from four decades, Fumble has crafted its own unique sound filled with catchy songs and delivered with raw energy. The band&#39;s action-packed shows and positive do-or-die attitude are getting increasing notice in Finland and abroa</span></div>',1,'Rami (vocals)<div>Onni (guitars)</div><div>Mikko (drums)</div>',0,''),(2476,1000289,'Oversight',1,71,'http://oversightmusic.com','','','Newly signed to Enexia Records. Preparing for a summer consisting of recording and shows. Come out and see us. And request us on Myspace @ myspace.com/oversightrock\r\n',1,'Jesse Hollenweger - Vocals<br />\r\nJosh Taylor - Guitar<br />\r\nMike Tuck - Guitar&nbsp; <br />\r\nMatt Raws - Bass<br />\r\nCraig Tarry - Drums\r\n',0,''),(2477,1000290,'Terp 2 it',4,24,'http://terp2it.com','','225-938-8242','<p>\r\n<img src=\"http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2304/2109511545_3686580454.jpg?v=0\" alt=\"\" title=\"From the New York Times article on Nerdcore Hip Hop\" width=\"405\" height=\"263\" />\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nIf you were a record label sitting in your fancy office, listening\r\nto Terp 2 it&rsquo;s album, The Freshest Dude, and trying to smoosh Terp 2 it\r\ninto a certain category of hip hop, you&rsquo;d probably classify him as\r\nnerdcore. You&rsquo;d be half-right.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nIf you were an average rap fan sitting on a beanbag chair and\r\nlistening to Terp&rsquo;s album, you&rsquo;d probably call him just another rapper\r\nspitting out rhymes about his non-violent, gangsta-free life. You&rsquo;d be\r\na third of a quarter right.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nIf you were Terp 2 it - seasoned battle rap veteran and\r\nself-proclaimed World Heavyweight Champion of the World - sitting on\r\nyour toilet and listening to your own album, you&rsquo;d probably call\r\nyourself a fun new voice in hip-hop. And you&rsquo;d be just right, because\r\nyou&rsquo;d be Terp 2 it.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nIf you like hearing rap songs about over-ordering sushi, getting\r\nrides to work, and cleaning up parties, you should be spinning Terp. If\r\nyou prefer songs about jewelry, money and cars then great, turn on the\r\nradio.\r\n</p>\r\n<br />\r\n_______<br />\r\nTerp 2 it has been seen with MC Chris, Nerdcore Rising.com, Michael Showalter and Michael Ian Black, Maker Faire, Comedy Central Presents, and was an official showcase artist at South by Southwest.\r\n',0,'',0,''),(2478,1000293,'Adrenaline',1,71,'http://www.adrenalinelive.net','','','ADRENALINE is a high-performance, full-on energy experience. It&#39;s the energy you crave, the release you need. It&#39;s a true, high-energy rock concert. Super hot - totally sexy. We put on the killer show and rock your favorite songs from Tool, 3 Days Grace, Disturbed, Incubus, Seether, Shinedown, Godsmack, Toadies, Hinder, Rage Against the Machine, Blink 182, Bowling for Soup, and tons more of your favorite alternative and rock tunes. We go above and beyond what you expect from a local band. Once you experience the performance of Adrenaline, you&#39;ll be addicted to the rush. Be sure to check our original tunes LIVE!!\r\n',1,'Preston - Vocals<br />\r\nSlade - Guitar<br />\r\nJeremy - Drums<br />\r\nKyle - Bass<br />\r\nRyan - Guitar \r\n',0,''),(2479,1000295,'TEN DIGIT ARMY',5,88,'http://www.tendigitarmy.com','','','<p>\r\nI have accumulated a large library of original songs that I have been writing over the years. I have recorded everything myself, from my home, using the best methods I know and the best equipment I can afford. I have tried to balance the amount of time I spend on any one particular song and time I spend writing new material. I will write about 20-30 new songs at any one time. I then go back and &ldquo;sand-down&rdquo; the ones that have potential or that someone else sees potential in. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nAs of now, there is no album, there is no band, and there is no tour. All I have to give you is these old dusty demos. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nI will continue to write and post the newest / or best material I have until MTV and Rolling Stone start calling...or I die, whatever comes first. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nyou can also check out more songs, pictures and info at: \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.tendigitarmy.com/\">www.tendigitarmy.com</a> \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.myspace.com/tendigitarmy\">www.myspace.com/tendigitarmy</a> <br />\r\n<a href=\"http://tendigitarmy.imeem.com/\">http://tendigitarmy.imeem.com/</a> \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.isound.com/ten_digit_army\">http://www.isound.com/ten_digit_army</a> \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<a href=\"http://tendigitarmy.musicnation.com/\">http://tendigitarmy.musicnation.com/</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"http://yipehype.com/video/memberprofile.php?uid=113\">http://yipehype.com/video/memberprofile.php?uid=113</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\npurchase more TDA songs here:<br />\r\n<a href=\"http://void.snocap.com/b/T3-31324-W7CQN32HG6-2/);%22/\">http://void.snocap.com/b/T3-31324-W7CQN32HG6-2/);&quot;/</a>\r\n</p>\r\n',0,'',0,''),(2485,1000302,'The Preons',1,NULL,'','','','This is going to be a full band - I will update this as soon as this happens!<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;Recorded/Produced by myself, as well as all the instruments and vocals. As such, I certainly cannot do all this live without plenty of help! I&#39;m actively searching for talented people on drums, bass and possibly a multi-instrumentalist. I&#39;m not searching for hobbyists ... I want musicians that are willing to tour the US and Europe, if the opportunity presents itself. Email me if you think you know someone - serious inquiries only, of course.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n( I&#39;ll probably update this portion with a review or press release in the near future)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp; I&#39;m an Austin lad, though I&#39;m really a damn yankee (hehe- look it up!). I came to this town about 10 years ago to pursue music after graduating college. It has been a long road, filled with disappointment and jadedness. If I had the recording studio I have presently, back then, it would most likely be a different story! At least I&#39;m here now and I&#39;m ready to release some of my music and some others. Another band I produce is called The Real Long Band and they are worth checking out as well. I hope to add more bands to my list in the future ...<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp; \r\n',0,'',0,''),(2486,1000303,'John Zito Band',1,105,'http://johnzitoband.net','4434 Cinderwood Ct.','702-563-7857','<strong><em><font size=\"4\">\r\n<p>\r\nJohn Zito Band \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nwww.johnzitoband.net \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\njohnzitoband@aol.com \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n702-563-7857 \r\n</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>\r\nJohn Zito \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nSinger, songwriter, guitarist. Influences Jimi Hendri