eeps pushing itself forward without looking back. Their\r\nsongs charted 1 and 3 on XM radio channel for 4 strait months. Two\r\nnational tours done and now set to embark on a College Campus Tour in\r\n2008, they are gaining a huge fan base across the country. Signing with\r\nthe record label Hitt Records out of Hollywood earlier this year, the\r\nbands Mailing List reaches people in all 50 states and 20 countries.\r\nMaryz Eyez provides a show like no other local band. Fueled by the\r\ndriving beat of an explosive drummer, Maryz Eyez brings an exhilarating\r\nshow to the table, and you never know what to expect. Unlike any other\r\nband around, ALL 4 original band members sing and switch instruments\r\nthroughout their sets, showing unbelievable versatility and talent. The\r\nband still pushes out a thick dynamic sound with catchy hooks, with\r\nmuch emphasis on the vocals. With four part harmonies, these guys write\r\nand sing all their own original songs. A dynamic show and humble,\r\nfriendly guys always willing to hang with the crowd, Maryz Eyez has one\r\nthe best live shows out there, and wants nothing more than just to rock\r\nyour world.\r\n',1,'Eric Wagler - bass/vocals/percussion<br />\r\nRyan Wagler - vocals/guitar/drums<br />\r\nMike Nichols - guitar/vocals/percussion<br />\r\nMike Burlett - drums/vocals/guitar<br />\r\n',0,''),(2490,1000310,'Indout',1,14,'http://www.indout.com','253 sixth st, soledad, ca, 93960','831 902 0751','. . . . There&rsquo;s been major history between these three musicians, two of which have been to the big show and made a living out of the music industry. Decades apart in age and time played these three musicians have found the band they hope to ride out and retire with says Drummer Mike Carrillo. With such a heavy and powerful sound they command attention from the moment any one song on their debut album &lsquo;Secrets and Lies&rsquo; is played. &ldquo;Were so different as far as our style of play goes that I thought it would make it hard to find our sound, but it actually made it much easier,&rdquo; says 23 year old Lead Guitarist Diego Ramirez, &ldquo;we all new we wanted to play rock music, and we loved it, I just never expected it to come out so powerful.&rdquo; But all their success didn&rsquo;t come at an easy price, &ldquo;We&rsquo;ve all bled for this album,&rdquo; says Diego &ldquo;We practiced six days a week 5 hours a day minimum while working full time jobs, and there is a lot of personal material for me on this album, and that made it a little nerve racking laying it down for me&rdquo; he goes on to say &ldquo;but we all love music and we couldn&rsquo;t imagine doing anything else.&rdquo; Ricky Scolari the front man and bassist for Indout is the one who brings it together, with his powerful voice and commanding stage presence he captures the audience all to easily. &ldquo;Most of the album was written before I came to be with the band, but I did get a chance to write with these guys before we went in to record and I was impressed,&rdquo; says Ricky &ldquo;I had already played with Mike in a different band, but never with Diego&rdquo; Ricky goes on to say &ldquo;These guys really had their shit together, and I was really impressed&rdquo; he adds &ldquo;But I have to say that the new songs we got cooking for the second album are gonna blow this album away!&rdquo; Indout is a name that&rsquo;s growing fast along the underground scene, with only a handful of shows played in the past 2 years they have really started to make a name for themselves. There set to kick off a tour in the summer of 08&rsquo; where their going to play up and down California. &ldquo;We can&rsquo;t wait to get out there and play for our fans, we&rsquo;ve waited so long and are itching to show the new material!!&rdquo; says Diego. &ldquo;Come see us play, well make you remember the name&rdquo; \r\n',1,'Rick Scolari: Vocals<br />\r\nDiego Ramirez: Guitars<br />\r\nChris Alcanraz: Bass<br />\r\nMike Carrillo: Drums \r\n',0,''),(2491,1000313,'bletzung',1,NULL,'http://www.myspace.com/bletzung','','786 338-8916','<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color: #ffffff; font-family: verdana; font-size: 11px; line-height: normal; -webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 3px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 3px\"><p style=\"font-family: verdana, arial, sans-serif, helvetica; font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color: #000000\">&nbsp;&nbsp; In March 2005, Bletzung&rsquo;s first single &ldquo;Only End up Lonely&rdquo; won the Itunes Jukebox Jury which was held at the South by Southwest Music Conference in Austin, Texas.</span></p><p style=\"font-family: verdana, arial, sans-serif, helvetica; font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color: #000000\">&nbsp; &nbsp; After touring throughout Latin America and the U.S., sharing festival stages with the likes of Oasis, Eric Clapton, and Roger Waters among others, the band relocated to Austin in 2006 and within a few months played in an excess of 50 shows at the most important and respected clubs and festivals in the Midwest and West Coast including Antones (Austin), Key Club (Los Angeles), The Emergenza Festival and an appearance with Bryan Adams in their native Puerto Rico.</span></p><p style=\"font-family: verdana, arial, sans-serif, helvetica; font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color: #000000\">&nbsp; &nbsp; The video for &ldquo;Lonely&rdquo;, produced and edited by the band itself, debuted on Austin&rsquo;s own ME Television where it jumped straight to number one on the network&rsquo;s Top Ten videos on the Sonido Boombox show. At the same time, &quot;Lonely&quot; received airplay on Austin&rsquo;s classic rock radio station, 93.7FM KLBJ, and the newly launched Los Angeles station AM 1580 Indie Mix.</span></p><p style=\"font-family: verdana, arial, sans-serif, helvetica; font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color: #000000\">&nbsp; &nbsp; Other TV appearances in FOX News and LATV followed and later that year, the song &ldquo;Let Go&rdquo; was included in Disc Makers&rsquo; &ldquo;Independent Music World Series&rdquo; compilation which showcases the top 15 acts from the Midwest as selected by Billboard Magazine and Taxi (the website) and is distributed to 10,000 industry insiders and professionals.</span></p><p style=\"font-family: verdana, arial, sans-serif, helvetica; font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color: #000000\">&nbsp; &nbsp; Fronted by Ignacio Pe&ntilde;a and Juan Carlos Bermudo, Bletzung is essentially a melodically driven modern rock band that&rsquo;s conceived as a multimedia experience. Cinematic, existential and introspective , the band&rsquo;s live performances have been called an explosion of images and sounds. This responds to their ability to project images that are taken from a wide popular culture palette and that are musically and thematically in sync with everything that happens on the stage.</span></p><p style=\"font-family: verdana, arial, sans-serif, helvetica; font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color: #000000\">&nbsp; &nbsp; The band recently launched the official bletzung video podcast which is available at the normal internet outlets( Youtube , Itunes, My Space, Google) and which connects the band directly with their audience. Completely produced by the band itself , &ldquo;thebletzungpodcast&rdquo; is a unique opportunity for the band to further explore the audiovisual aspect of their output .</span></p><p style=\"font-family: verdana, arial, sans-serif, helvetica; font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color: #000000\">&nbsp; &nbsp; Bletzung&rsquo;s self-titled debut album is a conceptual proposal that entwines 12 songs that narrate a process of existential conflicts and which originated in times of worldwide terrorism, war and fear. Produced by Pe&ntilde;a, Iker Gastaminza (2 times Grammy award winner also Engineered for Shakira and Ricky Martin) and Tony Rijos, the record features British influenced songwriting with an American approach to recording and making records.</span></p><p style=\"font-family: verdana, arial, sans-serif, helvetica; font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color: #000000\">&nbsp; &nbsp; The songs are a powerful marriage of melodically driven strong hooks, and memorable guitar riffs, which exist in a cinematic world of musical textures and connotations, culminating and creating the theme of &ldquo;impending danger.&rdquo; Listeners will soon hear the band&rsquo;s unrelenting philosophy, that melody is king.</span></p><div><br /></div></span>',1,'Ignacio Pe&ntilde;a-Vox and guitars<div>Juan Carlos Bermudo - Vox and Bass</div><div>Julio Cotto - Guitars</div><div>Omar Biboni- Drums</div>',0,''),(2492,1000316,'Miguel',6,31,'http://www.unsignedbandweb.com/miguel','4790 Viewmont St   Holladay Utah. 84117','(801) 604-8396','Miguel was born In Sumter, So. Carolina, lived in Europe for several years, now resides in Utah.. His music has been posted at <a href=\"http://www.unsignedbandweb.com/\">www.unsignedbandweb.com</a> for a month and has been in the top #1 spot on both the country and country-pop charts ever since. He also has four songs on the country chart top 5, and has had the&nbsp; #1 spot on the country-pop charts for the past 4 weeks.. \r\n',0,'',0,''),(2493,1000317,'Living Syndication',1,NULL,'http://www.livingsyndication.com','Dracut, MA','617-407-3700','The thought that you are doing something or saying something for the first time is a thought people have been having throughout all time. Every word, every action, has been conceptualized by someone before you, they are for all intents and purposes, syndicated. So when you actually DO forge new ground, innovate, and give way to something new, you are in fact living syndication. This is the concept behind the band that&#39;s attempting to change the way you listen at music, Living Syndication.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLiving Syndication may fall into the category of hard and heavy rock but there are perceptible facets to this stone sounds of Eastern Indian instrumentation lend an aura of mystery and hypnoticism to songs; shades of jazz fusion subtly influence; moments of acoustic music punctuate the vibe of a song; while pure energy pulls up the weight of intensity. With a collectively diverse background from the members of this Boston-based band who are Pervez Taufiq on lead vocals, Mike Desmond on guitar, Andy DeCicco on bass, and Gregg Irick on drums Living Syndication have formed a sound that in a short period of time has begun to generate attention.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSelling over 5,000 copies of the debut release OM FACTOR, Living Syndicaton was able to generate a strong following that has only grown stronger in anticipation of their sophomore release, &quot;Aneurythm&quot;. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nWith song writing that transcends the boundaries of the genre, Living Syndication has been building their second album, Aneurythm, for 2 1/2 years. &quot;It&#39;s something that we are truly proud of,&quot; says singer Pervez Taufiq. With a variety of musicalities within the tracks, it&#39;s impossible to brand this band. Being compared to band such as Tool, Staind, Sevendust with a fusion of Ravi Shankar, it&#39;s easy to see why they&#39;re gaining so many fans worldwide. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nLiving Syndication has shared the stage with bands like Earshot, Sevendust, Filter, Shinedown, Lacuna Coil, Crossfade, Kill Hannah, and packed clubs and theaters between Boston to Florida. Having been in the studio for a majority of 2 years, LS is looking forward to connecting with it&#39;s fans this year.\r\n',1,'Pervez Taufiq - Vocals<br />\r\nMichael Desmond - Guitar<br />\r\nAndy DeCicco - Bass<br />\r\nGregg Irick - Drum\r\n',0,''),(2494,1000321,'Neverwonder',1,61,'http://neverwonder.com','','562-397-7708','&quot;Neverwonder follows the &ldquo;take no prisoners&rdquo; approach to rock &amp; roll&hellip; (Guitarist Flint ) Mavis shreds the air with his raucous guitar riffs, on top of a perfect foundation laid down by the Ramos brothers&hellip; Neverwonder are a force to be checked into by the industry. Their music is not just fun, but provides much needed social commentary that appeals to the masses.&rdquo; <br />\r\nMUSIC CONNECTION (2007) NEVERWONDER - an L.A.-based band with a modern rock/soul sound; hints of Stone Temple Pilots, Alice in Chains, Soundgarden with vocals of Tina Turner, Joss Stone, and Pink influence. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nFronting NEVERWONDER is sultry former AMERICAN IDOL vocalist Megan Bobo. Bobo finished among the Top 25 Finalists during Season 5 of the 1-Rated hit television series. She was also nominated for &ldquo;Best Female Vocalist&rdquo; Award for the 2007 South Bay Music Awards. With Bobo&rsquo;s great vocals and Neverwonder&rsquo;s compelling music, this should make for a musical marriage made in heaven! Megan is performing with Neverwonder and recording the quartet&rsquo;s second CD, due out in the Spring of 2008. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe pulse and backbone of NEVERWONDER are Andres &amp; Vincent Ramos (Exploiting Eve), exceptional musicians voted one of the Best Bands in Southern California by Music Connection magazine. The duo&rsquo;s experience includes playing venues such as House of Blues (LA/OC), Roxy, Key Club, Viper Room, Galaxy Theater and The Coach House, features on KLOS 95.5 FM radio, and apparel sponsorship by Vestal watches. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nRounding-out NEVERWONDER is Flint Mavis (Lovecraft, Trainwrecked), an experienced songwriter and guitarist. Flint brings a unique energy to the band with his amazing guitar sound, adding the necessary elements to complete the group. &quot;Southern California-based hard rockers Neverwonder debut with a 10-song wallop of melodic, hard-edged, clever tunes&hellip;complexity of tempo and style changes is perfectly juxtaposed with great vocals. Ramos brothers flex their rhythmic muscle as drums and bass lock in on the aforementioned breakdowns and switches making a seamless groove that is Neverwonder&rsquo;s foundation. Frosting on the proverbial cake comes in the form of Flint Mavis&rsquo; full-bodied chord passages and screeching hot leads...&rdquo; <br />\r\nSAN DIEGO UNION TRIBUNE \r\n',1,'',0,''),(2495,1000322,'YONG_STUNNAZ',3,NULL,'','','','',1,'',0,''),(2496,1000323,'CONJOB',1,71,'http://www.myspace.com/conjob','','','The past year has been nothing less than a whirlwind for CONJOB. With\r\nthe independent release of their album &quot;Everybody Be Cool&quot;, the band\r\nwas almost instantly named to Music Connection Magazine&rsquo;s annual &quot;Hot\r\n100 Unsigned Artists&quot; list, a collection of the top acts in all of\r\nSouthern California. And that was just the beginning. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nLed by\r\nGuamanian-born lead singer Zhanine (imagine if Pink was genetically\r\nfused with Tina Turner) and MC Warbux (Combine one part Wyclef Jean,\r\nadd a dash of Q Tip and mix with the visionary gift of Chuck D), the\r\nband has brought their electric urban mix of groove/rock/soul/hip hop\r\nup and down the West Coast and beyond.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn 2006, CONJOB was scouted and hired by Bounce Entertainment (The\r\nGrammys, MusiCares) to play the National Lampoon College Tour, sharing\r\nthe stage with the likes of Digital Underground, Tone Loc and Rob Base.\r\nAs Katie Campbell, Production Director for Bounce Event Marketing said:\r\n&quot;We booked CONJOB for a huge tour and they delivered! We had some big\r\nacts like Rob Base and Digital Underground. CONJOB blew them off the\r\nstage.&quot;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nCONJOB is already in production to their follow up\r\nto &quot;Everybody Be Cool&quot;, which will be produced by Bob Burch (Great\r\nGlass Elevator, East West) and Lumbajac (Lauren Hill, Hoodlum West),\r\nwith an eye on a Summer 2008 release.\r\n',1,'Lead Vocals: Zhanine Becerra<br />\r\nMC: Warbux<br />\r\nKeyboard/Vocals: Vickie Razzano<br />\r\nGuitar: Hubie Wang<br />\r\nBass: Brian Carpenter (Carp)<br />\r\nDrums: Kevin Brent\r\n',0,''),(2498,1000325,'Nothing More Than This',1,NULL,'http://www.myspace.com/nothingmorethanthis','','','',1,'',0,''),(2499,1000326,'Jason Consolacion',1,69,'http://www.jasonconsolacion.com','435 Ft. Washington Ave. Apt. 3F','9174205054','<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Lucida Grande\'; font-size: 11px; line-height: normal; white-space: pre-wrap\">Jason Consolacion (pronounced like the word &quot;consolation&quot;) has established himself as an impressive singer-songwriter, catching the ear of an expanding audience. His style of rock incorporates a number of elements, including folk, jazz, blues and funk.A graduate of Houston&#39;s prestigious High School For The Performing And Visual Arts, and always dedicated to being a student of all types of music, Jason has used his knowledge of various styles to incorporate a fusion of all his tastes into a pop setting. Born in Vancouver, British Columbia, Jason moved with his family to Houston when he was 6. The son of a concert pianist, Jason turned the influence from his mother into a dream that has led him to where he is today - playing his songs and affecting people with pop- and jazz-laden melodies and lyrics everyone can relate to.Other than his mother, Jason&#39;s musical influences cover a large variety of personalities, including Paul Simon, Stevie Wonder, Elvis Presley, The Beatles, Eric Clapton, Miles Davis, Herbie Hancock, Joni Mitchell, Nick Drake, Elton John, The Police, and Michael Jackson.Those who have heard Jason&#39;s songs live or on disc have been taken by the freshness of the writing, singing and playing. Now living in New York, the singer-songwriter hopes to continue to play for as many people as he can while maturing as a respectable musician.Jason&#39;s discography includes an EP titled UNCERTAIN AIR (2003), two full-length albums named EVERYTHING&#39;S OK (2004) and ACOUSTIC BOOGALOO (2005), and the EP titled THE POOL TABLE MATTER (2006). He is currently working on a new album with all new material, and is for the first time producing the record himself.</span>',0,'',0,''),(2500,1000327,'Theory of Flight',1,71,'http://myspace.com/theoryofflight702','Las Vegas, 89123','702.287.0103','<font size=\"6\"><font size=\"6\"><font size=\"4\">\r\nLas Vegas&rsquo; Most Musically Captivating New Band is taking back the\r\nAlternative Rock Scene with their Voltaic Lyricism and Cleverly\r\nDelivered Melodies. Their Performances in the Fight For Fame, Nevada&#39;s\r\nLargest Battle of the Bands, have earned them a Finalist Position After\r\nBattling Over 50 of the Best Bands in the State. In August of &rsquo;07,\r\nSinger/Songwriter/Guitarist Vince Casas teamed up with the powerfully\r\ndynamic talent of Vocalist Beau Hodges, Bassist Joey McMahon,\r\nSynth/Keyboardist Stephen Chou, Guitarist Cameron Scharsh, and Drummer\r\nTyler Williams. With Spring &lsquo;08 show dates currently being scheduled\r\nNationwide, the members of Theory of Flight are currently recording\r\ntheir first full-length release, and anxiously anticipate sharing the\r\nlive show experience with audiences nationwide. Coming Soon to a Rock\r\nVenue Near You! Theory of Flight!</font></font></font>\r\n',1,'<font size=\"3\">\r\nVince - Guitar/Vocals<br />\r\n<a href=\"http://s135.photobucket.com/albums/q146/beauhodges/?action=view&amp;current=vincent-1.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://i135.photobucket.com/albums/q146/beauhodges/vincent-1.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Photobucket\" /></a>\r\n<br />\r\nBeau - Lead Vocals<br />\r\n<a href=\"http://s135.photobucket.com/albums/q146/beauhodges/?action=view&amp;current=beau3.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://i135.photobucket.com/albums/q146/beauhodges/beau3.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Photobucket\" /></a>\r\n<br />\r\nJoey - Bass<br />\r\n<a href=\"http://s135.photobucket.com/albums/q146/beauhodges/?action=view&amp;current=joey2-1.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://i135.photobucket.com/albums/q146/beauhodges/joey2-1.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Photobucket\" /></a>\r\n<br />\r\nStephen - Guitar/Vocals<br />\r\n<a href=\"http://s135.photobucket.com/albums/q146/beauhodges/?action=view&amp;current=stephen4.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://i135.photobucket.com/albums/q146/beauhodges/stephen4.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Photobucket\" /></a>\r\n<br />\r\nTyler- Drums<br />\r\n<a href=\"http://s135.photobucket.com/albums/q146/beauhodges/?action=view&amp;current=tyler2.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://i135.photobucket.com/albums/q146/beauhodges/tyler2.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Photobucket\" /></a>\r\n<br />\r\nDonger - Keys <br />\r\n<a href=\"http://s135.photobucket.com/albums/q146/beauhodges/?action=view&amp;current=donger4.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://i135.photobucket.com/albums/q146/beauhodges/donger4.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Photobucket\" /></a></font>\r\n',0,''),(2501,1000328,'Aurora Falls',10,45,'http://www.myspace.com/aurorafalls','','','<span class=\"epktxt\"><strong>\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n<span class=\"epktxt\"><strong>Aurora Falls was chosen to perform on the Kevin Says Stage at Warped Tour Salt Lake City 6/28!</strong></span>\r\n</div>\r\n</strong><br />\r\nAurora Falls is a new flame in a music scene plagued by a winter of impassive songs and cliche appearances. They believe that the music should speak to you; it should make you feel. Aurora Falls is comprised of longtime friends Jacob Stark and Nick Angelo. The two had previously made noise in their hometown of Las Vegas in local mainstay bands such as Anias and With Broken Wings.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe end of 2007 marked a new chapter for them as they decided to come together and make Aurora Falls their full time creative endeavor. Angelo&#39;s guitar leads soaring and falling over Stark&#39;s contagious melodies make it impossible for you not to sing along.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDesiring to bring back the catchy, unmistakable musicality of bands like Taking Back Sunday, Brand New, and Copeland, Aurora Falls is poised to come to the Las Vegas forefront with a new, fresh indie sound.</span> \r\n',1,'Jake Stark - Lead Vocals/Guitar<br />\r\nNick Angelo - Vocals/Lead Guitar<br />\r\nRobbie Marsh - Bass<br />\r\nDanny Salazar - Drums \r\n',0,''),(2502,1000331,'Something Beautiful',7,84,'http://www.denythepain.com','','','<p>\r\nSomething Beautiful is a gothic-metal band from Chicago, IL comprised of two members, Dale Tippett, Jr. and Justin Smith. Abandoning tradition and convention, SoB is taking what youve come to expect from modern music and throwing it to the wind. This band is truly an extension of the post-modern world that is emerging from the underground. With fewer and fewer rules of form and content being followed by independent musicians, film makers and artists, it only follows that a group of creative persons would extend their reach beyond questioning authority (as contemporary bands like System of a Down and Tool, Queensryche, or Rage Against the Machine in the 1990s) and enter into a new endeavor of attacking the foundation on which the mainstreams social-political ideology is built upon. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nAs long as right-wing conservative Christians and oil magnates lord over western society, expanding their oppressive influences across the globe, humanity is inching its way ever-so-steadily towards an era of global famine, war, and terrorism. What indeed will prevent us from being nothing more than animals, if we base our values on territorialism and resource-hounding? Is this what history set as its goal all those millennia ago? These questions and far more are addressed by Something Beautiful, though they pale in comparison to the most fundamental question of them all: How do you want to live? \r\n</p>\r\n',1,'Dale Tippett Jr - guitar, vocals<br />\r\nJustin Smith - bass, vocals \r\n',0,''),(2503,1000332,'KIL JADEN',1,14,'http://www.kiljaden.net     myspace.comkiljadenband','813 DOLORES DR','702-496-5069','hard rock band from las vegas!<br />\r\nopened for GODSMACK, HELLYEAH, LA GUNS, METAL SKOOL<br />\r\nBANG TANGO, RATT, AND SUBLIME\r\n',1,'brian kil jaden&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; vocals/guitar<br />\r\nronnie griego&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; lead guitar<br />\r\ncory kay&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; bass&nbsp; guitar<br />\r\npaul von klock&nbsp;&nbsp; drums\r\n',0,''),(2504,1000339,'The Asphalt',1,NULL,'http://www.theasphalt.net','4314 Rafter B Avenue','928-897-4232','<span class=\"epktxt\">The Asphalt are a rock band hailing from the searing deserts of Arizona.&nbsp; Sounding like the bastard child of Face to Face and The Foo Fighters, members Randy Mazick, Jon Stutler, Nick Turner and Jason Marino blend rock guitars, pounding drums, smooth bass and scathing vocals with a high-energy live performance that has captivated thousands of fans.&nbsp; <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFormed in 2001, The Asphalt quickly cut a path to recognition.&nbsp; After locking themselves into world renowned NRG studios in Hollywood, CA with Grammy nominated engineer Jeremy Parker (Evanescence, Boy Sets Fire, Mudvayne) in the producer&#39;s chair the band created an EP that quickly reached the 75,000 hit mark on mp3.com before the websites untimely demise.&nbsp; Since that time The Asphalt have been a featured artist on XM Radio&#39;s unsigned channel and get regular spins on Phoenix radio station &quot;The Edge&quot; 103.9, and Las Vegas radio stations &quot;Comp&quot; 92.3 &amp; &quot;Extreme&quot; 107.5. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nRecently, The Asphalt&#39;s single From Afar was added to the soundtrack for The Fast and The Furious/Tokyo Drift Playstation 2 video game. They have also recently released a broadcast quality music video for their newest single &quot;Tonight.&quot;&nbsp; Shot in Hi-Definition on location in Tucson, Arizona and Old Tucson studios where films such as Tombstone, The Three Amigos, Death Wish and The Quick &amp; The Dead were famously shot, the video borrows from the old west but has a decidedly modern feel.&nbsp; The band were also invited to showcase at the world-renowned South By Southwest music festival for Captiva Records in Austin, Texas in both 2006 and 2007 where they performed for near-capacity crowds and had great reactions to their live show. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nCurrently in their 6th year of existence, the band just played Edgefest 2007 with Social Distortion, Bad Religion, Hot Hot Heat, Flyleaf, Jimmy Eat World and many other acts in Phoenix, AZ.&nbsp; The band are currently negotiating several high-level movie, TV, marketing and touring campaigns, and are expected to be appearing in several mediums throughout 2008.&nbsp; Since March of 2007, the band have been working with several producers, including future sessions with Jeremy Parker, splitting recording between Sony Recording Studios in Santa Monica, CA and various other studios, recording tracks for their long-awaited 3rd album &quot;Learning to Forget,&quot; to hit stores in early 2008.<br />\r\n</span>\r\n',1,'Randy Mazick - Lead Vox/Guitar<br />\r\nJason Marino - Guitar/Backing Vox<br />\r\nNick Turner - Drums<br />\r\nJon Stutler - Bass/Backing Vox \r\n',0,''),(2505,1000345,'localstranger',1,16,'http://localstranger.com','','','',1,'',0,''),(2519,1000423,'ddddddddd',4,NULL,'','','7029885665','',0,'',0,''),(2520,1000425,'Melissa',1,NULL,'','','','<p>\r\nHI!! \r\n</p>\r\n',1,'',0,''),(2521,1000426,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2522,1000429,'Hi Tide',13,60,'http://hitidemusic.com','PO Box 744, Grand Cayman, Cayman Islands KY1-1103','(345) 949-6242','<p>\r\nHi Tide has been a presence on the Cayman Islands music scene since 1994, when their first album &quot;Change&quot; was released and became an instant hit, with many songs receiving heavy rotation on regional radio stations. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nFounding members Shane Allenger and Sean Hennings have been writing songs and recording albums ever since. Also performing with and opening for the likes of Bon Jovi, Jimmy Cliff, Third World, Shabba Ranks, The Jeff Healy Band, Garbage, George Duke, Earl Klugh, Al Jarreau, Jeffery Osbourne, Natalie Cole, and Emmy Lou Harris to name a few. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nPrior to forming the band, Shane (lead vocals and congas) moved Nashville, Tennessee for one year, where he performed regularly on TNN with many country greats such as Conway Twitty, Loretta Lynn, Nicolette Larson and Randy Travis. Meanwhile, Sean (guitar, drums and vocals) had been in Hollywood, California, improving his drumming and music skills at the popular Musicians Institute of Technology. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nAlthough they have become very popular with their very catchy original songs, which are as diverse as the many cultures living in the Cayman Islands, they have also built quite a reputation recording covers of classics done their own unique way. Their two man acoustic show has gained an ever growing following over the years, but they do put together a 5 piece band for major concerts. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nIn 1997 Hi Tide received runner-up honors in the Rhythms of The Caribbean Competition sponsored by Island Records and The New Yorker Magazine. Since then, they have represented The Cayman Islands at The Summer Concert Series in Boston, The Caribbean Tourism Convention in Aruba and the EARTH Awareness Festival in Live Oak, Florida on three ocassions . Their song, &quot;Unity&quot; was also chosen as the theme song for the EARTH Awareness Festival in 2000. They have also performaed in Arizona, Colorado,Tenessee, Texas, New York, South Florida, Hawaii, Canada, France and England. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nHi Tide has released seven albums. Change, Begin Again, Unplugged Classics, Unplugged Classics 2, A Cayman Christmas, Merry Christmas from Hi Tide and Open Invitation, their latest release. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nAs well as maintaining regular rotation on Cayman&rsquo;s radio stations, they have also been featured on Westwood One&rsquo;s top 100 as import of the week, and two songs from Begin Again, &quot;That&rsquo;s what I&rsquo;d do&quot; and &quot;In your kiss&quot; received regular air play on top 40 radio in the USA. The title track from Open Invitation is now being used by the Cayman Islands Department of Tourism for their international TV ad campaign. \r\n</p>\r\n',1,'<font face=\"georgia,palatino\">Shane Allenger<br />\r\nSean Hennings</font> \r\n',0,''),(2523,1000432,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2524,1000455,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2525,1000456,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2647,1000914,'LAST BREATH',1,71,'http://WWW.MYSPACE.COM/LASTBREATHROCK','33 WOOD RD CENTEREACH NY 11720','631 834-9368','<div align=\"center\">\r\n<strong><font size=\"3\"><u>COMING SOON</u></font></strong> \r\n</div>\r\n',1,'<em><font face=\"georgia,palatino\" size=\"3\"><strong>\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n<p>\r\n<em><font face=\"georgia,palatino\" size=\"3\"><strong><font size=\"4\">LAST BREATH</font><br />\r\n<font size=\"2\">CHRIS <br />\r\nFRANKIE <br />\r\nMIKE<br />\r\nCRAIG</font></strong></font></em> \r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</strong></font></em>\r\n',0,''),(2526,1000471,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2527,1000486,'Project-43',1,14,'http://www.project-43.com/','','','Project-43 is the brainchild of Charlie Wardick and Steve M. Mann who\r\nare both located in the US. In late 2005, these two combined forces\r\nafter &lsquo;meeting&rsquo; each other on Usenet in the alt.guitar newsgroup.\r\nInitially, it was just an effort to refresh their playing skills and\r\nlearn a little about home recording, but they quickly realized it could\r\nbe much more. From it&#39;s humble beginnings, Project-43 would go on to\r\nbecome one of the first bands to record, mix, produce and release a\r\nmusic CD completely over the Internet, with none of the members ever\r\nhaving met in person. All while being separated in three difference\r\ncountries and five locations around the globe.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAfter Charlie and Steve established the groundwork, the two soon\r\nenlisted the vocal talents of Antti Heikkinen from Finland. Antti gave\r\nthe project a truly special touch that made the music come together\r\nlike never before. His vocal talents should have landed him a major\r\nrecording career long ago, thus eliminating any chance he could be part\r\nof the team. But, for whatever reasons, the stars were aligned and he\r\nwas available for the project. That was a very fortunate set of\r\ncircumstances.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe band then added Scott Wallace who is located in Scotland, to play\r\ndrums and replace the canned &lsquo;loops&rsquo; or programmed drums that had been\r\nused to this point. This also brought a whole new dimension to the\r\nmusic and the overall sound of Project-43. Christopher Bell-Boudreaux\r\nis the latest talent to join Project-43 adding his unique NYC guitar\r\nstylings and talent to the mix.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTo date, Project-43 has created over forty original Rock &amp; Roll\r\nsongs that have an amazing quality that would challenge even the best\r\nindustry professionals to know that these people have never played in\r\nthe same room together. Their debut CD, &ldquo;Silence the Quiet&rdquo;, released\r\nin 2007, contains a collection of tunes in the hard/heavy rock genre.\r\nTheir new follow-up CD, <strong>&quot;Ticket To Infinity&quot;</strong>,\r\nreleased in March of 2008, also contains a bit of a mix, but is\r\ncertainly more &#39;metal&#39; and modern. The combination of these two CDs\r\nmakes it easy to see why their slogan, &quot;Project-43: The Future of\r\nClassic Rock&quot;, may be more truth than marketing.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n',1,'<pre>\r\nDee Heikkinen:  lead vocals, guitars\r\nCharlie Wardick:  guitars, bass, vocals\r\nSteve Mann:  guitars, keyboards, vocals\r\nScott Wallace:  drums, percussion\r\nChristopher Bell-Boudreaux:  guitars\r\n</pre>\r\n',0,''),(2528,1000490,'Our Lunar Activities',1,71,'http://myspace.com/ourlunaractivities','20 Gress, isle of Lewis, Scotland, U.K, HS2 0NB','+44 (0)7909 548 872','Our Lunar Activities were formed by brothers Kevin and Charles Clark. The band released their first single &ldquo;She Cried/ Diamond&rdquo; on independent record label Hatch. The single was produced by Mogwai&rsquo;s Barry Burns and received critical praise and created a platform for the band to support the like of Snow Patrol, The Wedding Present and play the T-break stage at T in the park. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen a final line up was established Derek Healey (guitar) and James Reeves (bass/vocals) joined the brothers and a sound was created growing into something much more accessible. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nWinter 2006 saw OLA supporting Snow Patrol again at the Gmex Arena, Manchester. It was on the back of this show OLA agreed to put an E.P out on Scottish label Neon Tetra. &ldquo;It comes in waves&rdquo; was released in February 2007 and again received praised reviews with journalists picking up on the bands stadium sound and anthemic choruses. A short film for this release was made by the band themselves and paid homage to their love for seventies exploitation movies. The video was made for virtually no cost and created much controversy with the video being labelled &ldquo;sick&rdquo; and &ldquo;too violent to be shown pre watershed.&rdquo; <br />\r\n<br />\r\n2007 saw more high profile supports such as +44(formerly Blink182), The Buzzcocks, Shiny Toy Guns and a string of festivals including London Calling (Amsterdam), GoMoscow (Russia), Rockness and Belladrum(UK). <br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe band caught the attention of +44 frontman Mark Hoppus whilst on tour together round Europe and invited them to his studio in Los Angeles to record and produced their self titled debut album. The complete album engineered by Christopher Holmes (Red Hot Chilli Peppers and Helmet) and Produced by Mark Hoppus successfully captures the raw energy of OLA&rsquo;s live performances. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nWith film soundtracks and a finished album secured OLA plan to make their mark in 2008. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOur Lunar Activities hail from the Isle of Lewis, Scotland, U.K.\r\n',1,'Charlie Clark : Vocals &amp; Rythm Guitar<br />\r\nJame Reeves: Vocals &amp; Bass Guitar<br />\r\nKevin Clark&nbsp;&nbsp; : Drums<br />\r\nDerek Healey: Lead Guitar \r\n',0,''),(2529,1000494,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2530,1000497,'Wrecked',1,14,'http://www.officialwrecked.com','Yorkville, IN','','<div>\r\n<font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"3\">Come out to a show and witness Southeastern Indiana&rsquo;s in your face attitude rock &rsquo;n&rsquo; roll son of a bitch! Wrecked is southeastern Indiana &rsquo;s finest rock and roll band.&nbsp; Comprised of Kent Hiltz (ex-Krazyfly guitarist) on vocals and guitar, Tim Agapie (ex-Havak guitarist, ex-Visual Koas bassist) on bass, Doug Sloan (ex-S.G.W. bassist) on guitar, and Chris Craft (ex-Seaker&#39;s Pass drummer) on drums, they are ready to rock any and all venues. Wrecked writes and records their own original music.&nbsp; Their influences range from Johnny Cash all the way to Cannibal Corpse and everything in between.&nbsp; Wrecked shows a diversity uncommon in today&rsquo;s boorish radio rock pantheon.&nbsp; Always energetic, always hostile, and always at the ready with beer in hand, Wrecked pummels all venues and concertgoers with a riotous plume of personal mishaps, social misbehavior, and the struggle of the common man.&nbsp; There is no question.&nbsp; Wrecked will leave you wrecked. </font>\r\n</div>\r\n',1,'Kent Hiltz -&nbsp;Guitars, LeadVocals<br />\r\nDoug &quot;Doogle&quot; Sloan - Guitars, Backing Vocals<br />\r\nTim Agapie - Bass Guitar, Backing Vocals<br />\r\nChris Craft - Drums\r\n',0,''),(2531,1000501,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2532,1000503,'Somatic',1,14,'http://www.somatic.us','','708-229-8520','<table border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" width=\"100%\" height=\"100%\" id=\"HB_Mail_Container\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr width=\"100%\" height=\"100%\">\r\n			<td id=\"HB_Focus_Element\" width=\"100%\" height=\"250\" valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td height=\"1\" style=\"font-size: 1pt\"></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n	<table border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" width=\"100%\" height=\"100%\" id=\"HB_Mail_Container\">\r\n		<tbody>\r\n			<tr width=\"100%\" height=\"100%\">\r\n				<td id=\"HB_Focus_Element\" width=\"100%\" height=\"250\" valign=\"top\">Somatic calls Chicago&rsquo;s southside home. Hatched in 2006 a battle plan was formed and the band (at the time, John, Tony, and Paul) began writing music with the intention of a 3 song EP release in July of 2007. That plan was redefined as Rich was brought in on bass, and Peekaboo. With numerous packed-venue shows out of the way, and an amazing 5 song EP recorded and distributed, Somatic has already proven that it is not just a typical bar band. Although their EP &quot;Plan B&quot; packs quite a punch, it simply does not do justice for their live performances. With extraordinary energy, out of control programming and lights, and general stage mayhem, Somatic always leaves a venue with a lot more friends than they had before the show. A secret can only be kept a secret for so long, and the cat is out of the bag. Somatic is not a &quot;scene&quot; band, a &quot;local&quot; band, or a &quot;bar band.&quot; Somatic is poised to join the ranks with national and internationally touring acts in the near future. Nothing in the music world comes for free, and Somatic has paid their dues. With every member coming from a background of several &quot;could-have-been&quot; bands, and every one of them (including their crew/family) being a working class, day-to-day type of person, no band understands hard work and dedication as well as Somatic. So come on out, have a few drinks, and party with the band. It will be a night to remember, we can promise you that!!!</td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td height=\"1\" style=\"font-size: 1pt\"></td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n		</tbody>\r\n	</table>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n',1,'<p>\r\nTony - Vocals<br />\r\nJohn - Drums<br />\r\nPaul - Guitar<br />\r\nRich - Bass<br />\r\nRyan - Guitar\r\n</p>\r\n',0,''),(2533,1000508,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2534,1000509,'Zwish',1,68,'http://www.zwish.net','','','<span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',\'serif\'\">Zwish have been described as &ldquo;Avril Lavigne\r\nwithout the prozac&rdquo; or &quot;what Hole would be if Courtney Love hadn&#39;t gone\r\ncrazy&quot;. More astute fans have said &quot;live, they are the sound of two\r\nangry people having sex&quot;.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',\'serif\'\">Zwish was formed in Canberra, Australia\r\nin 2004, and after a few false starts and line up changes, the current line up\r\nhas been happily together since August 2006. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe four members, Leah (23), Sam (19), Bryn\r\n(27) &amp; Tom (22), are drawn together by the desire\r\nto write and play music that means something to them. Something they can feel\r\nand something they can relate too, not homogenised sanitised versions of music\r\nthat leaves them feeling nothing.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n2007 has been an exciting time for Zwish:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&quot; They played a number of 2nd teir festivals, Cherryhaven Music Festival,\r\nRock The Bowl, Canberra Band Explosion<br />\r\n&quot; They had over 100,000 mp3 downloads from zwish.net,<br />\r\n&quot; They had over 35,000 visitors to zwish.net,<br />\r\n&quot; Watched their fan base on myspace grow from 500 in November to over\r\n12,000,<br />\r\n&quot; They had over 2000 views of the video clip for &ldquo;Wonderful Life&rdquo; on\r\nYoutube in its first week, before being taken down for a little too much\r\nnudity,<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe rest of 2007 promises to be an exciting time with new CD release and\r\ncountry tour</span>\r\n',1,'Leah - Vocals<br />\r\nSam - Bass Vocals<br />\r\nBryn - Guitar<br />\r\nTom - Drums\r\n',0,''),(2535,1000513,'The Shallow',1,14,'http://www.myspace.com/theshallow1','','859-619-4761','Formed in late 2006 by founding members of local favorite Pron, this hard rocking group of guys set out to claim the Lexington Metal scene.&nbsp; After some lineup changes and change of practice venue they have stepped into a genre that they like to call &quot;Groove Metal&quot;...searing vocals over melodic repititious riffs backed by hip-hop&#39;esque beats.\r\n',1,'G-Funkk<br />\r\nHammer<br />\r\nDi Italio<br />\r\nSuarez\r\n',0,''),(2536,1000519,'Ka\'Nubis',9,41,'http://www.reverbnation.com/nefernefertiti','P.O. Box 2584 Toluca Lake, Ca. 91610','818 760 9159','NeferNefertiti. Queen of Ancient<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">Nefer-Nefertiti, which means &ldquo;Beautiful is the\r\nBeauty of Aten.<br />\r\nThe Sun God.<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">A famous Queen of Ancient Egypt, a bust of Nefertiti can be found in Berlin. NeferNefertiti is not subject to quite\r\nthe same extremes as others in Amarna art, by virtue of being elegantly female.\r\nIndeed, there are several curious aspects of Nefertiti&#39;s representations. In\r\nthe early years of Akhenaten&#39;s reign, NeferNefertiti&#39;s husband, KING of Middle Ancient Egypt, for instance, Nefertiti was an unusually\r\nprominent figure in official art, dominating the scenes carved on blocks of the\r\ntemple to the Aten at Karnak. One such block\r\nshows her in the age-old warlike posture of pharaoh grasping captives by the\r\nhair and smiting them with a mace hardly the epitome of the peaceful queen.<br />\r\n&nbsp;Nefertiti evidently played a far more prominent part\r\nin her husband&#39;s rule than was the norm. </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">A burnt mummy seen outside the royal tomb in the\r\n1880s, and associated with jewelry from the tomb (including a small gold finger\r\nring with Nefertiti&#39;s cartouche, was probably Coptic, as was other jewelry\r\nnearby.<br />\r\nThe Queen&#39;s Cartouche has neverbeen found. After all the excavations of the Valley of the Kings and Queens, NeferNefertiti makes her debut TODAY!<br />\r\nNow reincarnate, NeferNefertiti has been found. The Artist NeferNefertiti, brings to the stage the ellegance, style, romance, beauty, mysticism and majesty of Ancient Egypt to the New world. <br />\r\n&nbsp;The New CD, is aggressively, created to bring about a new genre. Neo-Egyptian soul.<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\"><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\"><br />\r\n<!--[if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br />\r\n<!--[endif]--></span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">\r\n<!--[if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br />\r\n<!--[endif]--></span>\r\n',0,'',0,''),(2537,1000529,'Grey Water',1,NULL,'http://www.myspace.com/greywater','222 lamira ave.greer s.c.29651','8649211807','<p>\r\n<font face=\"impact,chicago\" size=\"5\" color=\"#808080\">Father and Sons Band.Started in 2006!We are all Songwriters!We write alone and then play em&#39; together! </font>\r\n</p>\r\n',1,'<font face=\"impact,chicago\" size=\"5\" color=\"#999999\">Allen Bridwell<br />\r\nJonathan Bridwell<br />\r\nEarl Bridwell</font> \r\n',0,''),(2538,1000531,'Ashbury',1,61,'http://www.myspace.com/ashburyrock','','6128046851','<!-