battle of the bandscompetition titled A Fight For Fame, and is currently taking advantage of the$50,000 cash and prize package. They have begun working on their Sophomorealbum &ldquo;The Things That Haunt You&rdquo;, and will be touring the country to promotethat and their full album release &quot;Complacency,&quot; which much liketheir debut EP will garner the attention of thousands of fans.</span></p><!--EndFragment-->',1,'Brian Lee - Lead Vocals/Guitar<div>Joey Resly - Lead Guitar/Vocals</div><div>Jeremy Lee - Bass/Vocals</div><div>Patrick Martens - Drums</div>',0,''),(2539,1000542,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2540,1000545,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2541,1000558,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2542,1000559,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2543,1000562,'The Warned',1,14,'http://myspace.com/thewarned','7242 Toulouse Dr. Apt. 3','714-292-3430','<!--StartFragment--><p style=\"text-align: center\" align=\"center\">After years of playing in variousbands, the five members of The Warned have come together to create somethingthat they all believe in: music with feeling and emotion. The music that poursout from this band is melodic and powerful with a sense of urgency. All membersbring equal, but different, aspects to the band leaving listeners satisfiedwith a feeling of hope and promise. The Warned encompasses the various soundsof rock, metal, and alternative pop that creates a unique and addictive sound.</p><p style=\"text-align: center\" align=\"center\">Founding members Justin and JesseWarn had a vision of creating music that is passionate and honest. That desireis as true today as it will be in the years to come. Other musicians, and goodfriends, Robbie Coleman, Steve Sievers, and Eden Godinez were then added to theequation to polish and refine the musical endeavor they were searching for. TheWarned has started the journey into the Southern California music scene makingan impact everywhere they turn. Experience the musical revolution of The Warnedand be changed forever...</p><!--EndFragment-->',1,'<!--StartFragment--><p style=\"text-align: center\" class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\">Justin Warn &ndash;Vocals/Keyboards&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align: center\" class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\">Jesse Warn &ndash;Guitar/Vocals/Synth&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align: center\" class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\">Robbie Coleman &ndash;Drums/Percussion&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align: center\" class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\">Steve Sievers &ndash;Bass/Vocals&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align: center\" class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\">Eden Godinez &ndash;Guitar/Vocals&nbsp;</p><!--EndFragment-->',0,''),(2544,1000566,'A.D.D.',1,14,'http://MYSPACE.COM/ADDCHICAGO','','','<font color=\"#61618d\">Today&rsquo;s audiences are searching for something fresh...something new...something different...<strong>A.D.D.</strong>, from Lockport, IL welcomes this challenge and gives rock fans hope at a time when this cookie-cutter world of metal is missing the originality.&nbsp;This quintet, led by Margaret Young&rsquo;s words of real-life&rsquo;s hopes and failures, covers a cross-section of influences from the 70&rsquo;s to the present. She takes the emotion and puts into her own hard rock story...Taking down even the toughest hearts. You won&#39;t be disappointed. As heard on their 7 song CD, produced by Tadpole (3 Doors Down, Disturbed), their mix of lyrical passion and superb musicianship, make for a great recipe that will rock you out!<br />\r\n<br />\r\nCheck out &quot;Waiting&quot; and &quot;Bridges Burning&quot;&nbsp; -rpro<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font>\r\n',1,'<p>\r\nMargaret<br />\r\nDave<br />\r\nRandy <br />\r\nRon<br />\r\nJeremy\r\n</p>\r\n',0,''),(2546,1000576,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2547,1000591,'IV League',3,18,'','','','',0,'',0,''),(2548,1000596,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2549,1000610,'Onlinegigs',13,NULL,'','','','',1,'',0,''),(2550,1000612,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2551,1000616,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2552,1000617,'Pur Pale',1,77,'http://www.myspace.com/purpale','#109-5360 201st','604.314.8191','<strong>Pur Pale: <em>Biography</em></strong> <br />\r\n01.29.08 <br />\r\nWritten by: Ryan &lsquo;Tweak&rdquo; Clark <br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe came from a background of obsession, we became the obsessed, every moment and chance we grew and understood the language and art of music and musical interpretation to creation. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nEveryone we knew were always the types of people who would skip school or work to be the first in line for that amazing band that we all desperately needed to go see and experience. Everyone we knew were the first ones in line to purchase our favourite bands brand new album. Then everyone we knew all gathered around our stereos turned out all the lights, light our candles, closed our eyes and experienced that album for the very first time. The first listen was always the most serious and analytical by the 5th-7th listen we would already be figuring out the processes, structure&rsquo;s and instrumentation&rsquo;s within those albums. Basically every little detail about the music was analyzed and interpreted. Running our stereos through eq systems to pump or reduce frequencies to magnify small details within the music itself, we would reverse the music and fast forward to find secrets about that album which the engineers and artists always loved to throw into that final master mix. It was these details that we took out of the music which began manifesting Pur Pale into what it has become today musically. But it was through my own interpretation of life&rsquo;s experiences that created the artistic backbone. Through all the self inflected abuse, lieing, selfishness, violence, suicides, drug abuse, non-believer of spirituality or god for lack of physical proof and everything that was The Negative within my own personal past aggravations of life I found the truth within all of these topics. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nPur Pale is the representation of a sterile mind &quot;pur&quot; meaning Pure and &quot;Pale&quot; meaning white (Pur White). Similar to that time when you couldn&rsquo;t stop your eyes from un-focusing on that one little section of that wall, sucking yourself into a spacey trance of sterile numbness but yet utter comfortably and trust. Talking about topics and issues in which people tend to find uncomfortable, humiliating, terrifying or even things in which people find hard to express in fear of negative critism and judgment. Pur Pale is here to become a part of all our relative natures, we are here for one another to guide as a community of growth and understanding over our independent personal selves in order to better understand the world around us in order to obtain that selfless humanity, We analyze, interpret and communicate from every point of view in all contrasts from every angle. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe start each project with an independent purpose or topic of emotional relativity in which manifests itself from within our daily environments. By the end of the project we have turned that independent purpose of emotional relativity into a globalized feeling but never understanding of the topic itself. Our art is here in order to stimulate and relate to each individual listener in unique way. There is a personal message behind each song but what I find to be the most powerful is to find that relative message within yourself in order to better understand yourself or to obtain that relational experience from an outsider&rsquo;s perspective of understanding. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em>&quot;Everything is an influence around us it&rsquo;s what we actually take in and make ours that lets us create what we tend to create.&quot; <br />\r\n<br />\r\n&quot;Art is not only a way of expression but it&rsquo;s the evolution of structure and detail.&quot;</em> <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><em>2008 Ryan &quot;Tweak&quot; Clark</em></strong> \r\n',0,'',0,''),(2553,1000632,'the sixty sevens',1,71,'','','','Straddling the dead horse of ROCK! Ãƒï¿½Ã‚ \r\n',1,'Pat Freen - Vocals / Spirits / Small Woodland Creatures\r\n<div>\r\n<br />\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\nFlynn - Guitar / Vocals / Nose HairÃƒï¿½Ã‚ \r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<br />\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\nMikie Mac - Lead Guitar / Brill Cream / Taunting\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<br />\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\nJamie - Bass / Dental Floss / Steel Gaze\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<br />\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\nDrummer - ?\r\n</div>\r\n',0,''),(2554,1000638,'Low of the Low',1,14,'http://www.myspace.com/lowofthelow','','','<p>\r\nChicago based &quot;Low of the Low&quot; isn&#39;t interested in being just any average, ordinary American rock band like most out today - that&#39;s obvious at first listen. Their gritty, groove driven guitar work and attitude scream through the speakers as you listen to any song off of the band&#39;s debut album &quot;Land of Lincoln.&quot;&nbsp; (coming this summer!) \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nHailing from the infamous South Side of Chicago, comes five guys proud to represent the tough blue collar streets of Chicago and all that they represent. Taking a stand for the common man, telling it like it is- like it or not- this is what the music of Low of the Low is all about. This isn&#39;t just music they make; it&#39;s a way of life! \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nUnited in 2005 with the sole purpose of putting a new face on a tired American rock scene, it&#39;s easy to hear that this band is driven to bash their own untypical style of &#39;take it or take it&#39; rock n&#39; roll. Focusing more on music and substance, accompanied by rock solid grooves, the band doesn&#39;t fall back on the typical flash and emo sob stories that commonplace in the over processed music of today. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nWith their powerful songs and live performances, Low of the Low has developed a rabid following in Chicago and the midwest, and the national landscape is what the band will set their sights in 2008. The band features Mark Crowley on vocals, Pat Sullivan on bass, Pete Morelli on lead guitar, Paul Jagmanis on rhythm, and Frank Schuch on drums. So, crack open a cold one, fire it up, and keep your eye&#39;s peeled in the year 2008 for &quot;Low of the Low&#39; - then again, it&#39;s awfully hard not to hear them coming! \r\n</p>\r\n',1,'Mark Crowley - Vox<br />\r\nPat Sullivan - Bass<br />\r\nPaul Jagmanis - Rhythm Guitar<br />\r\nFrank Schuch - Drums<br />\r\nPete Morinelli - Lead Guitar\r\n',0,''),(2556,1000647,'Arsin',1,14,'http://www.arsinband.com','650 Gladfern Ave, Oshawa Ontario Canada','905-721-9247','<address style=\"background-color: #ffffff\">\r\n<font face=\"Times New Roman\" size=\"3\" color=\"#000000\"><span class=\"a\">This\r\nhard hitting power trio based out of Toronto Canada delivers a heavy\r\nrock sound with memorable melodic choruses, breath taking guitar solos\r\nand funky bass riffs from hell</span>. Formed in&nbsp; October, 1994 Arsin&#39;s\r\nAndy Narsingh, Terry Crosson and Mike MacKinnon released their debut\r\nextended play CD, entitled Beyond. </font><font color=\"#000000\"><br />\r\n</font> </address>\r\n<hr />\r\n<font color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: #ffffff\">\r\n</font>\r\n<h3 style=\"background-color: #ffffff\" align=\"left\"><em><font face=\"Times New Roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\">Mike MacKinnon ( 1966 - 2000 )</font></em> </h3>\r\n<p style=\"background-color: #ffffff\">\r\n<font color=\"#000000\"><em><font face=\"Times New Roman\" size=\"3\">Born into a musical family,\r\nMike (Mic-Mac) MacKinnon&#39;s father Plays guitar while his mother plays\r\npiano. Mike&#39;s dad took him to see his first Rock &amp; Roll band when\r\nMike was just 9 years old - he never forgot wipeout being played live.\r\nMike developed a love affair with the drum kit and has not looked back.\r\nA solid and exciting double bass kit player whose major influences are\r\nNeil Peart, Vinnie Appice, Clive Burr, The Beatles and Buddy Rich -\r\nMike took those styles on the road previously with such bands as\r\nMidnight, Without Warning, Thin Ice and Hunger. Mike has a personal\r\nambition to one day get his masters Degree in music but in the meantime\r\ncounts shooting pool and sleeping as his outside interests. (Regretably\r\nMike has since passed away...R.I.P my friend!)</font></em></font> \r\n</p>\r\n<font color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: #ffffff\">\r\n</font>\r\n<h3 style=\"background-color: #ffffff\" align=\"left\"><em><font face=\"Times New Roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\">Terry Crosson</font></em><br />\r\n</h3>\r\n<p style=\"background-color: #ffffff\">\r\n<font color=\"#000000\">\r\n<em><font face=\"Times New Roman\" size=\"3\">At age 13 Terry Crosson\r\nrealized that playing Voodoo Chile by Jimmy Hendrix on the violin might\r\nnot open too many doors in the music industry.A guitar player was born!\r\nInfluenced&nbsp;by Randy Rhoads, Jimmy Hendrixs and Tommy Sholtz, Terry\r\nplays a variety of styles including blues, rock, alternative and metal.\r\nHis listening tastes are just as diverse, citing Van Halen and Dream\r\nTheatre as his favourite bands while naming Nuno Bettencourt, Steve Vai\r\nand Vinnie Moore as his favourite guitar players. You may have\r\nencountered Terry Crosson in such bands as Axis, Rampage or Crystal\r\nMyth and will definately not forget his abilities once you have seen\r\nhim perform.</font></em></font> \r\n</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"background-color: #ffffff\" align=\"left\"><em><font face=\"Times New Roman\" size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\">Andy Narsingh</font></em></h3>\r\n<p style=\"background-color: #ffffff\" align=\"left\">\r\n<font color=\"#000000\"><em><font face=\"Times New Roman\" size=\"3\">Modest Beginnings</font><font size=\"3\"> - </font><font face=\"Times New Roman\" size=\"3\">Andy\r\nNarsingh played his father&#39;s accoustic guitar for a couple of years,\r\nthen at age 16 a friend&#39;s dad let him use an electric bass guitar to\r\njam&nbsp;to Rush&#39;s Spirit&nbsp;of the Radio. The rest is history! Andy&#39;s funk\r\nrock-style of playing is no surprise considering his major influences\r\nare Geddy Lee, Stu Hamm and Billy Sheehan. </font><font face=\"Times New Roman\" size=\"3\">The\r\nrole of lead vocalist was not something Andy had ever considered prior\r\nto 1994. Once you hear him sing you will realize that Geddy Lee had\r\nmore of an influence on him than just his bass playing. Andy has\r\ntremendous respect for the vocal talents of Freddy Mercury but is also\r\na fan of Van Halen and Dream Theatre. Prior to fronting Arsin Andy\r\nNarsingh could have been found with the bands: Hunger&nbsp;&amp; Truthful\r\nLiars to name a couple.</font><font size=\"3\">&nbsp; </font></em><br />\r\n</font> \r\n</p>\r\n<hr width=\"100%\" size=\"2\" />\r\n<p style=\"background-color: #ffffff\" align=\"left\">\r\n<font color=\"#000000\"></font>\r\n</p>\r\n<h3><font face=\"Times New Roman\"><em><strong>EBAY REVIEW:</strong></em></font><br />\r\n</h3>\r\n<p style=\"background-color: #ffffff\" align=\"left\">\r\n<font color=\"#000000\">\r\n<em><font face=\"Times New Roman\" size=\"3\">A CD that&#39;s called Beyond,\r\nbut should be called &quot;Beyond Rare&quot;! You&#39;re looking at the five-song\r\nindie release by Canada&#39;s Arsin. Now, in the past, I have received a\r\nlot of e-mails from desperate collectors who assume that, because I&#39;m\r\nCanadian, I can find this CD easily... or pull it out of a hat like a\r\nmagician. Let me set the record straight... this is NOT an easy CD to\r\nfind. No wonder Heavy Harmonies has no database listing for it.\r\nFurthermore, of all the members who post their collections on that\r\nsite&#39;s message board, I only found Arsin&#39;s Beyond on one or two lists.\r\nIf only collectors like you knew how good this one is. The chorus of\r\nNow&#39;s the Time is like a powerful street drug... it hooks you fast and\r\nkeeps you coming back for more. For anyone who can&#39;t hear the sample,\r\nthis song blasts off with nothin&#39; but the layered, chorus vocals, only\r\nto launch into a commercial, feel-good guitar riff. Highly reminiscent\r\nof K.K. Wilde (with higher vocals and better production) or Lancia at\r\ntheir radio-friendly best. The whole CD is as good as the song you\r\nheard here. Big vocals, hooks hooks and more hooks plus screamin&#39;\r\nguitar solos that will take your breath away. Released in the mid-90s\r\nwhen the hair metal/glam scene was on four flat tires, this band would\r\nbeen the cat&#39;s pajamas in the late 80s or earlier half of the decade.\r\nCollectors who are lucky enough to have this CD cling to it\r\npassionately... the many who don&#39;t are encouraged to take advantage of\r\nthis chance to finally own it. One thing for sure, this one is not on\r\nGEMM or Musicstack and may never find its way back to eBay ever again!</font></em></font>   \r\n</p>\r\n',1,'Terry Crosson - <em>Lead &amp; Rythm Guitars, BG Vocals</em><br />\r\nAndy Narsingh - <em>Lead Vocals, Bass Guitars, Keyboards</em><br />\r\nMike MacKinnon - <em>Drums, Percussion, BG Vocals</em><br />\r\n',0,''),(2557,1000649,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2558,1000650,'Fabulous Hats',1,16,'http://www.myspace.com/neildobsonandthefabuloushats','','902-356-2433','About Neil Dobson / Fabulous Hats<br />\r\nNeil Dobson was a regular on the Toronto club circuit for years with various original bands. &quot;I go back a ways in Toronto, we played Larry&rsquo;s Hideaway a lot -such a classic venue- I met Joe Strummer in there one time...&quot; He has done countless sessions across Canada for artists from around the world; on stage and in studio.&quot;I think the most interesting studio gig I did was with a Tabla drum artist from Sri Lanka who wanted Clapton-esque lead work on some traditional style Indian music, pretty wild gig..&quot; In 1993,he co-wrote a song w/Chris Kearney and Scott Lane called &quot;A Letter From Sarajevo&quot; to help with Red Cross efforts during the war in Sarajevo. Song and video were produced with many Canadian artists singing/playing including Tom Cochrane , Ian Thomas ,Rik Emmett,Murray MacLaughlin, Steve Negus, Sylvia Tyson, Molly Johnson and others. And now this...Fabulous Hats !! . &quot;Well I like a lot of styles of music and the &quot;Fabulous Hats&quot; name comes from the old saying &quot;He wears many hats&quot; . I guess musically, I like to wear a few..&quot;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Fabulous Hats&rsquo; debut CD features twelve originals with a classic rock vibe, almost as though it is an artifact from a lost 1970s recording session with Gram Parsons and Keith Richards with Dick Dale chiming in on the odd track. Chief songwriter Neil Dobson weaves a number of influences through the self-penned tunes and while he doesn&rsquo;t reinvent the wheel here, he does add new rims and flashy hubcaps to give the disc&rsquo;s classic sound some spark. The opening track, &ldquo;Where&rsquo;s My Yesterday,&rdquo; already sounds like a hit for country radio; it&rsquo;s as catchy and lyrically deft as anything on the country charts while &ldquo;Shake Shake&rdquo; and &ldquo;Rainclouds Burst&rdquo; both have infectious choruses that stick in the ear long after the CD player has been switched off. The wistful quality to the lyrics and vocals of &ldquo;I Fall for You,&rdquo; is nicely offset by the raucous surf rock inspired &ldquo;Dick&rsquo;s Descent&rdquo; in this record that wears its varied inspirations proudly on its sleeve. <br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\nRichard Crouse - National movie critic (Canada AM, Rogers Television&rsquo;s &ldquo;Reel to Real&rdquo;) <br />\r\n',1,'',0,''),(2559,1000653,'Plavet',1,76,'http://www.plavet.net','','','',1,'',0,''),(2560,1000654,'Jonny\'s doomsday revue',7,36,'http://www.soundclick.com/jonnysdoomsdayrevue','Brandkarrsvagen 94 61166 Nykoping sweden','+46737353501','<p>\r\n<font face=\"georgia,palatino\" color=\"#ff0000\">I have played for over 18 years had a band called gloom, but i doing everything by myself these days, more freedom that way. The epic saga that i written called &quot; Theater of 27 - I Loke &quot; is on soundclick over 100 songs, every songs stretch from the years 1900 and 2007, i based the story on when i went through a life crisis, when i search for an answer of life and death, the lyrics is based on the dreams i had then and what i explored in reality, also the story is influenced by william blakes &quot; the marriage between heaven and hell &quot; book, and the book of revalation.even bit of the conspiracy theory and the human fight against death, angels, demon and other creature is baked in, on this site you can hear some songs, if you want more click on link to the sounclick site. I had fun when i did these songs, hope it will entertain other peolpe to. Cheers &infin;</font>\r\n</p>\r\n',0,'',0,''),(2561,1000655,'Terezodu',1,68,'http://www.myspace.com/terezodu','oc,ca','623-544-3678','&quot;This... act packs a punk rock punch that Mike Tyson would sell his mother for. Looking back over their shoulders to 80&rsquo;s hardcore bands like Suicidal Tendencies and Black Flag, the music points forward in everyway. Pounding, driving, bashing, it&rsquo;s all there and man o man alive, is it sweet.&quot; <br />\r\n-Path Radio &quot;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&quot;This... act packs a punk rock punch that Mike Tyson would sell his mother for. Looking back over their shoulders to 80&rsquo;s hardcore bands like Suicidal Tendencies and Black Flag, the music points forward in everyway. Pounding, driving, bashing, it&rsquo;s all there and man o man alive, is it sweet.&quot; -Path Radio. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nTerezodu arose in the summer of &rsquo;05 to take the world by storm. Leo Ulfelder has captivated minds and eyes as he sings his own disturbing &quot;facts of life&quot; to the crowd, backed by Matt Haynes&rsquo; shredding guitar leads and Patrick McIsaac&rsquo;s pummelling bass lines while Alex Schultz massacres the world with his drums. After releasing several DIY EP&rsquo;s such as &quot;Anatomy&quot;, selling them at shows, small record stores and networking them throughout the underground music scene, TEREZODU decided to release their first Full Length Album titled &quot;Sow My Disciples&quot;, Recorded by Geza X (Who has produced bands such as Black Flag and The Germs)and Paul Roessler (Screamers, Nina Hagen, Dead Kennedys) at Satellite Park Studios in Malibu, CA. The Album consists of 15 maddening masterpieces including their single, Minority of One which is set to release March 25, 2008. Constantly touring, networking and thrashing. TEREZODU&rsquo;s sound of Punkrock/Metal Crossover is a force yet to be reckoned with, and they show no signs of slowing down. Not even for a piss break.<br />\r\n',1,'Leo Ulfelder<br />\r\n&nbsp;Matt Haynes<br />\r\nPatrick McIsaac<br />\r\nAlex Schultz \r\n',0,''),(2562,1000656,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2625,1000861,'VDO SIRRAH',3,86,'http://myspace.com/vdosirrah','2605 Drayton Dr. Augusta, GA 30906','706-551-4210','From the DIRT ROADS and JUKE JOINTS of the stix, to the CLUBS and STREETS of the concrete jungle, from crime committin&#39; to rhyme spittin&#39;, he is artistically known as... V-DO SIRRAH The Unseen Mic Menace. EXTROVERTED, OUTSPOKEN, INFLUENTIAL, and INTENSE are just a few words to describe this MULTI-FACETED DIAMOND. He is a much needed REFRESHMENT in a continuosly evolving world of music. A NO NONSENSE objective on LIFE and PERSONAL experiences make his music REAL with SUBJECT MATTER we all can RELATE to. READY, WILLING, and WELL SEASONED, this is not an overnight sensation. An AMIABLE personality, COMMANDING stage presence, and an undying, &quot;BY ANY MEANS NECESSARY&quot; approach to his music contribute to his EARNED SUCCESS thus far. Without hesitation, expose yourself to the DISTINCT vocals, CONVERSATION, and WORDPLAY of a TRENDSETTER. \r