ger, Micro-programmable MIDI Engineer, &amp; Science Fiction Cartoonist/ Graphics Artist.&nbsp; Born in San Pedro California, grew up in Los Angeles Calif.<br />\r\nAlways surrounded by music at relatives parties, school, and special events. I explicitly remember my years as a tottler, about 4 or 5 yr. old, saving nickels for the juke box, to play all those Chubby Checker records of the past. I didn&#39;t mind dancing without any shyness with any and all girls willing to except the challenge. I surely had the musice bug by the time Wolf Man Jack,&nbsp; The Ed Sullivan Show, &amp; Soul Train activated my alpha-nerves. I started out lip-singing to all the Temptations, The four Tops, Smokey Robinson, James Brown, Marvin Gaye,... and so on and so on. In 1967 moved from Los Angeles to Portland Oregon, took boys chorus glee! and ear training. Learning to play the piano finally was no longer the curse I thought it was, never by daring to touch one, now was an explosive therapy of creative infinity. I practiced feverously for many years, joining jazz communes, getting on the road, with commercial top 40 bands, asking every keyboardist to show me how they do that, and this, until my resource optional lead me to study theory, composition, and harmonics.&nbsp; Soon I was traveling, and creating a working musical history in about a dozen bands, duos, trios, quartets, to 6-10 piece bands playing; Sly &amp; The Family Stone, &nbsp;Chicago Transit Authority, and Buddy Miles, Edgar Winter Bad Company, Jimmy Hendrix, Cream, Led Zepplin, etc. I started out on Hammond B-3 Organ with duo Leslie Speakers, Clavinet, Fender Rhodes, Crumar Orchestrator, Juno M-60, etc. I currently use Korg, Yamaha, and ESQ1, &amp; Sampler/Roland M-C 500/16 channel PA Studio-Master board/1500 Roland Amp/ect.&nbsp; Ideal for MIDI programmable DJ show. I love to kick my own hand bass, and can really kick Jazz keys like Joey D. Francisco, Jimmy Smith, Booker T, Jack Mcduff, Jimmy Groove Holmes, Chick Corea, or George Dukes.&nbsp; I have a library with hundreds of demonstrations of my style in&nbsp;a variety of flavors. R&amp;B, hip-hop, contempory &amp; classic&nbsp;jazz, funk,&nbsp;popspace,&nbsp;punk, and classical. I write and play T.V. and movie themes. Moved to Las Vegas 3 months ago, In hopes of making money, with my fully throttle skills. Willing to collaborate providing that time lines and goals are in place. Willing to artistically experiement on the creative level. Hoping to play by combining my nucleus with other component to complete a team players show band.&nbsp; Either a 3 or 4 piece band. I am last but not least proud to announce my promotion of my originally created &quot;Cosmic Cartoon Circus&quot; : &quot;The Strangest Science Fiction Gallery&quot; of Aliens originally created in the world by Stymykain Leslie... and base on my copywritten book: &quot;The Wonderworlds of Dyiimmexx&quot; an Outer Space Adventure. I&#39;m attempting to market the promotional concept, as a Las Vegas tourist attraction, and offer future opportunities for expanded marketing ranging&nbsp;commercially lucretive graphic design&nbsp;resources: from CD Illustrations, mural, tatoos, storybooks, lithographic reproductions, video gaming &amp; animation. As you can tell I am a creative extraterrial tapping in to the psychic experiences of everyone who has witnessed my work. I hope I can inspire, aspire, and share my&nbsp; musical and artistic skills with the right individuals, teams, agencies, companies, and corporations. Please feel free to correspond your inputs via email, need to meet people who have the same planetary drive. Can you feel me? \r\n</p>\r\n',0,'',0,''),(2579,1000709,'TBOC',10,45,'http://unifiedtboc.com','','','I&#39;m a versitile artist that plays a few styles of music. But everything I play is based on my faith. So I&#39;d say that I&#39;m a contemporary Christian artist. Country, blues and acoustic.<br />\r\nEnjoy writing music and have a small song writers group that meets in my house. We ocassionally do open mics. Have just done a compolation CD with Christian:country,gospel,blues,jazz, spoken word, rap. etc... .<br />\r\n12 peices by 12 different artists. A little unsure of not being able to list myself as a Christian artist. \r\n',0,'',0,''),(2580,1000711,'Bob Griffin Piano',6,29,'','2 Short Beach Rd. Apt 5','203-606-7524','',0,'',0,'');
INSERT INTO `ProfileBand` VALUES (2581,1000718,'White Wolf',7,36,'http://www.whitewolfworld.com','12770 15A Avenue, South Surrey, BC, V4A1M1','','<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">Possibly one of the most talented, yet under-appreciated of all International metal acts to come out of Canada in the 1980&rsquo;s, was the band <font color=\"#ff0000\">&ldquo;White Wolf&rdquo;</font><font color=\"#000000\">.<br />\r\n</font><br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">White Wolf was formed in 1980 when <font color=\"#ff0000\">Don Wolf</font>, then going by his legal name <font color=\"#ff0000\">Don Wilk</font>, together with bassist <font color=\"#ff0000\">Les Schwartz</font> and drummer Loris Bolzon met up with guitarists <font color=\"#ff0000\">Cam MacLeod</font> and <font color=\"#ff0000\">Rick Nelson</font> while on tour through Edmonton Alberta, Canada.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">With their love of great Hard Rock/Heavy Metal, they soon began rehearsing in Toronto, Canada, and playing select dates in the Central and Eastern parts of Canada, then moving back to Edmonton, to do the local bar scene in and around the area as <font color=\"#ff0000\">&quot;Warrior&quot;.<br />\r\n</font><br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">Fans would form long line-ups just to see this new hot band perform!<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">They were blown away by the cover material played by the band <font color=\"#ff0000\">(Deep Purple, Black Sabbath, Pink Floyd, Judas Priest, Scorpions and more&hellip;.)</font> and the new sound of the original material that songwriters <font color=\"#ff0000\">Don Wolf (Wilk) and Cam MacLeod</font> were writing.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">It wasn&#39;t long before they were touring the western provinces extensively.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">When the band started recording their demo material, they received offers from 6 record companies, including <font color=\"#ff0000\">Heavy Metal Records</font> and <font color=\"#ff0000\">Music For Nations</font>, two prestigious Metal only labels.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">Courted on all sides, the band decided to join the rapidly growing <font color=\"#ff0000\">RCA Hard Rock Pack</font>, and were signed to a deal with <font color=\"#ff0000\">RCA in 1984</font> as <font color=\"#ff0000\">&quot;White Wolf&quot;.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font><br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">Their debut LP, <font color=\"#ff0000\">STANDING ALONE</font>, was released in <font color=\"#ff0000\">1984</font> to rave reviews.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">Two producers were utilized for the project, <font color=\"#ff0000\">Danny Lowe (Painter)</font> and <font color=\"#ff0000\">Jack Richardson (most notable for his work with The Guess Who, Bob Seger and Alice Cooper)</font> each bringing to the table their own specialized talents and experiences.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">Appearances on local TV variety shows helped spread the word, following their debut&#39;s release.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">Also geared for public relations, the label and management had <font color=\"#ff0000\">two different covers printed</font> for the LP.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">All the exposure helped <font color=\"#ff0000\">White Wolf</font> tour extensively into the States as well as eastern Canada.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">Though nothing was really geared for AM radio play, both Canadian and American FM stations began playing <font color=\"#ff0000\">&quot;Shadows In The Night&quot;</font><font color=\"#000000\">,</font> with its anthemic aura.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\"><font color=\"#ff0000\">Two versions</font> of the song<font color=\"#ff0000\"> &ldquo;</font><font color=\"#ff0000\">Shadows In The Night&rdquo; </font>were filmed for video, and were featured and rotated on many Hard Rock/Heavy Metal stations such as <font color=\"#ff0000\">Much Music in Canada and MTV in the USA</font>.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">Other highly under-rated tracks included <font color=\"#ff0000\">&quot;Night Rider&quot;<font color=\"#000000\">,</font> </font>the thought-provoking <font color=\"#ff0000\">&quot;What The War Will Bring&quot;<font color=\"#000000\">,</font> </font>the driving force of <font color=\"#ff0000\">&quot;Metal Thunder&quot;</font> and the title-track, <font color=\"#ff0000\">&quot;Standing Alone&quot;</font><font color=\"#000000\">,</font> released as the band&#39;s second single.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">The LP was well received in many countries in <font color=\"#ff0000\">Europe</font> and especially <font color=\"#ff0000\">Japan</font>.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">Over a <font color=\"#ff0000\">quarter of a million copies</font> of the debut were sold worldwide - In fact <font color=\"#ff0000\">RCA New York</font> had the band go in and <font color=\"#ff0000\">re-record</font> the songs <font color=\"#ff0000\">&ldquo;Standing Alone&rdquo;</font> and <font color=\"#ff0000\">&ldquo;Metal Thunder&rdquo;</font> for a special <font color=\"#ff0000\">limited edition 12&rdquo; release</font><font color=\"#000000\">.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font></font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">This has gone on to become a <font color=\"#ff0000\">collector&rsquo;s item</font> for many fans.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">The group&#39;s reputation for their musicianship, as well as their live energy landed them gigs from coast to coast, both headlining and opening for the likes of fellow Canadians <font color=\"#ff0000\">Lee Aaron and Kick Axe</font>, and <font color=\"#ff0000\">Australia&#39;s Angel City</font> during the Texas leg of their US tour which went lasted until the end of spring, 1985.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThen it was time for White Wolf to start thinking about a follow up to <font color=\"#ff0000\">&ldquo;Standing Alone&rdquo; </font><font color=\"#000000\">!<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font></font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">After the success of the first album <font color=\"#ff0000\">&ldquo;Standing Alone&rdquo;</font> and the tour, RCA wanted to make the next White Wolf release even more of a hit.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDon and Cam went into months of writing for the new record and came up with the songs for the record by August of 1985.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThey even did a <font color=\"#ff0000\">remake</font> of the song<font color=\"#ff0000\"> &ldquo;Just Like An Arrow&rdquo;</font><font color=\"#000000\">,</font> originally written by Tony Clarkin of the band <font color=\"#ff0000\">Magnum</font>, for a potential single release.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">The band flew to <font color=\"#ff0000\">Holland</font> to record their second album at <font color=\"#ff0000\">Bullet Sound Studios</font> under the guise of <font color=\"#ff0000\">Shell Schellekens</font>, whose biggest credentials included working with <font color=\"#ff0000\">Golden Earring</font>.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThey spent 2 months recording between October and December of 1985 and the result was <font color=\"#ff0000\">&ldquo;ENDANGERED SPECIES&rdquo;, </font>a 10 song combination of pure <font color=\"#ff0000\">Melodic Hard Rock</font>.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nReleased in <font color=\"#ff0000\">1986</font>, nearly two years later - another well thought-out, crisp and energized Metal Masterpiece.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">With the lead off track <font color=\"#ff0000\">&quot;Time Waits For No One&quot;</font><font color=\"#000000\">,</font> Don Wolf&#39;s (Wilk), powerful vocal prowess again shone. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe sheer dominance of the twin guitar attack of <font color=\"#ff0000\">Cam MacLeod</font> and <font color=\"#ff0000\">Rick Nelson</font>, peaked in<font color=\"#ff0000\"> &quot;Snake Charmer&quot;<font color=\"#000000\">,</font> </font>while other noteworthy songs included the enormous sound of <font color=\"#ff0000\">&ldquo;Holding Back&rdquo;</font><font color=\"#000000\">,</font> the ballad <font color=\"#ff0000\">&ldquo;Cryin&rsquo; To The Wind&rdquo;</font> and the haunting <font color=\"#ff0000\">&quot;All Alone&quot;</font><font color=\"#000000\">.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font></font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">A video for the song<font color=\"#ff0000\"> &ldquo;She&rdquo;</font> was released on many Hard Rock/Heavy Metal video shows to rave reviews.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe album was sitting at <font color=\"#ff0000\">#114 with a Bullet</font> on the <font color=\"#ff0000\">Billboard</font> charts, and was on the way to breaking the <font color=\"#ff0000\">Top 100</font>, when BMG Records bought RCA.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">Sensing a lack of support from the new label, the band chose to leave RCA/BMG after the end of the North American tour in &#39;87.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">They carried on into the next year, but eventually called it quits in the spring of 1988. </font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<br />\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">Both Classic White Wolf recordings <font color=\"#ff0000\">(&ldquo;Standing Alone&rdquo; and &ldquo;Endangered Species&rdquo;)</font> were remastered and re-released on CD in <font color=\"#ff0000\">Japan </font>by RCA Victor Japan, May 1996 to rave reviews and went on to sell over <font color=\"#ff0000\">8,000 copies </font>each!<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">The band members went their separate ways. </font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\"><font color=\"#ff0000\">Don Wolf (Wilk)</font><font color=\"#000000\">,</font> went on to a number of other projects, including <font color=\"#ff0000\">&ldquo;Point Of Power&rdquo;</font><font color=\"#000000\">,</font> <font color=\"#ff0000\">&ldquo;Project X&rdquo;</font><font color=\"#000000\">,</font> and his <font color=\"#ff0000\">solo album</font> called <font color=\"#ff0000\">Don Wolf - &quot;Making Changes&quot;</font> in 1998.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">He has also worked with various producers including <font color=\"#ff0000\">Bruce Fairbairn</font>, adding backing vocals on the Multi-Platinum release <font color=\"#ff0000\">&quot;Flesh &amp; Blood&quot;</font><font color=\"#000000\">,</font> by rock group <font color=\"#ff0000\">&quot;Poison&quot;</font><font color=\"#000000\">.<br />\r\n</font><br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">In 2004 his vocals resurfaced on a project called <font color=\"#ff0000\">Bitter Suite</font>, featuring a host of other musicians, including <font color=\"#ff0000\">George Criston</font> of <font color=\"#ff0000\">Kick Axe</font>.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\"><font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong>****</strong></font> Now we come to today where Don has reunited with lead guitarist and co writer Cam MacLeod, and they have with the help of <font color=\"#ff0000\">Escape Music&#39;s Khalil Turk</font> recorded and released a <font color=\"#ff0000\">BRAND NEW &quot;White Wolf&quot;</font> project! </font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<br />\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">This was released in <font color=\"#ff0000\">Europe</font> and the <font color=\"#ff0000\">UK</font> and also <font color=\"#ff0000\">Japan</font> in the <font color=\"#ff0000\">summer</font> of <font color=\"#ff0000\">2007</font>.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">This is titled <font color=\"#ff0000\">&ldquo;Victim Of The Spotlight&rdquo;</font><font color=\"#000000\">.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font><br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">Twelve Tracks of In Your Face Hard Rock and Heavy Metal Vocals and Guitars!<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<font face=\"tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif\" size=\"3\">Check It Out For Yourself!!!! </font>\r\n</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<font face=\"verdana\" size=\"+1\" color=\"#000000\">\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n<font face=\"verdana\" size=\"+1\" color=\"#000000\"></font>\r\n</div