ahoma\"><font size=\"3\"> </font>\r\n<p align=\"left\">\r\n<font size=\"3\">and Back Up Vocals<br />\r\n&nbsp;</font> \r\n</p>\r\n</font><font size=\"3\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" color=\"#ff0000\">Russell Bergquist (ANNIHILATOR, FREAKS BY NATURE, DUSK MACHINE) </font><font face=\"Tahoma\">- Bass</font></font><font face=\"Tahoma\"><font size=\"3\"> </font>\r\n<p align=\"left\">\r\n<font size=\"3\">Guitar and Back Up Vocals<br />\r\n&nbsp;</font> \r\n</p>\r\n</font><font size=\"3\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" color=\"#ff0000\">Brendan Ostrander (PROJECT X, DON WOLF solo, DANIEL POWTER) </font><font face=\"Tahoma\">- Drums</font></font><font face=\"Tahoma\"><font size=\"3\"> </font>\r\n<p align=\"left\">\r\n<font size=\"3\">and Back Up Vocals<br />\r\n&nbsp;</font> \r\n</p>\r\n</font><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"3\" color=\"#ff0000\">\r\n<p>\r\nDavid J. Petovar (WHITE WOLF, BITTER SUITE) <font face=\"Tahoma\">- Keyboards and Back Up Vocals</font> \r\n</p>\r\n</font>\r\n',0,''),(2622,1000850,'Gabriel Soriano',1,105,'http://www.gabesoriano.com','','951-315-1849','Hello, my name is Gabriel Soriano and I was born to play music. It is\r\nmy passion, my love, my redemption, my strength, and my creation. My\r\ngoal is to work with a label that cares about releasing quality music\r\nand supporting artists to be career musicians, not cheeky\r\none-hit-wonders. Here&#39;s some info about me:<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAs\r\nan independent artist I have self-recorded and self-released 3 CD&#39;s:\r\n&quot;Demo 2005&quot; (my first demo), &quot;Into The Noise&quot; (my first EP), and most\r\nrecently &quot;The Love Juice Sessions&quot; (my second EP, currently available\r\nfor free download through my website and myspace, physical copy to be\r\nreleased August of 08). I play all the instruments and sing all the\r\nvocals on my albums. I&rsquo;ve booked and played over 250 shows in the last\r\nthree years including two self-funded tours. I currently perform as a\r\nsolo as a one man band, using a loop station that allows me to create\r\nlive loops of guitar, bass, vocals, percussion, keys, and saxaphone\r\ninto layers of sound. My music can generally be described as blues,\r\nfunk, jazz, soul, reggae, latin, and rock. I use no backing tracks or\r\ncd&#39;s of any kind other than a metronome when playing live. I build the\r\nsong piece by piece in front of the audience, often times pulling\r\npeople out of the crowd to give them cowbells and shakers and help me\r\nbuild a loop.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nI&rsquo;ve played in many bands in many positions:\r\nguitar, drums, bass, vocals, etc... I am a multi-instrumentalist and a\r\nsinger/songwriter. I love everything from Sinatra to Slayer but my\r\nfavorite music in the world is blues, funk, soul, and rock. I love to\r\nwrite and play all types of music from metal to jazz. And, in no\r\nparticular order, my top 5 bands are Pink Floyd, Dave Matthews Band,\r\nRadiohead, Thrice, and The Beatles and Led Zeppelin. Ok that&rsquo;s six.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nI&#39;m currently booking a fall tour to promote &quot;The Love Juice Sessions&quot;\r\nthat will begin in September and hopefully go through winter. Dates and\r\nlocations will be announced August with the pressing of the CD and the\r\nrelease show. If you like what you hear in the player, then you can\r\npurchase my CD&rsquo;s through my website at www.gabesoriano.com or through\r\niTunes. Come by and see me at a show, and if not, then I&rsquo;ll burn down\r\nyour house. Just kidding. Kind of.\r\n',0,'',0,''),(2582,1000721,'Don Wolf (Wilk)',1,14,'http://myspace.com/httpwwwmyspacecomdonwolf','12770 15A Avenue, South surrey, BC, V4A1M1','','<img src=\"http://i85.photobucket.com/albums/k67/ultimatevocal/donwolfwolfbanner.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Photobucket - Video and Image Hosting\" width=\"400\" height=\"56\" /> <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Hi,<br />\r\nMy name is Don Wolf (Wilk), and I have had a lifelong commitment and involvement in music that includes Seven National and International CD releases, (SEE DISCOGRAPHY)<br />\r\n<br />\r\nI have been involved in Music Composition for Theatre and Screen, and have put in many years of Local and International Touring Band Work.<br />\r\nI have a solid background in Vocals, Keyboards, Lyrics, and Midi Composing, and as a professional musician, I have had the pleasure of having over 30 years involvement in the music business.</strong> <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<font face=\"artistik\" size=\"+1\" color=\"#ff0000\"><strong>HIGHLIGHTS </strong></font><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Some of you have known me as Don Wilk, and recognized me as fronting Canadian 80&#39;s Melodic Heavy Metal/Hard Rock band <em>&quot;White Wolf&quot;</em>, who released two extremely successful albums on RCA International namely <em>&quot;Standing Alone&quot;</em> and <em>&quot;Endangered Species&quot;</em>. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe album, <font color=\"#ff0000\">&quot;Standing Alone&quot;</font> sold over a quarter of a million copies worldwide and <font color=\"#ff0000\">&quot;Endangered Species&quot; </font>reached ..114 on the Billboard Top 200 Album charts. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n</strong><font color=\"#000000\"><strong>Toured USA, Japan, Europe, and Canada. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nBoth Classic White Wolf recordings, (Standing Alone and Endangered Species) were remastered and re-released on CD in Japan by RCA Victor Japan, May 1996 to rave reviews and went on to sell over 8,000 copies each! <br />\r\n<br />\r\nJust recently, in March of 2007, Japan re released the first two White Wolf recordings as a &quot;Limited Edition&quot; Vinyl Miniatures release!<br />\r\n<br />\r\nI was also the vocalist/songwriter for &quot;Point Of Power&quot; who released a CD &quot;It&#39;s About Time&quot; in 1992, both in Canada and Japan. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nI worked together with Kenny Kaos - Loney, writing the song &quot;Keep On Runnin&#39;&quot; a big success for Paul Laine on his &quot;Stick It In Your Ear&quot; album, on Long Island International. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe also worked together to write, record and release the CD, &quot;Project X&quot; - BluePrint For Xcess, which was released in Europe, The Uk, and Japan.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn 1997-1998, I was able to record and release my very first solo outing, Don Wolf - &quot;Making Changes&quot;, produced by John Shepp, and again released in Europe and Japan.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAll of the Cd releases are available at the<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</strong><a href=\"http://www.whitewolfworld.com\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Official White Wolf Website</strong></a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>As a side project and for an interest that I have always had, I have also been actively involved in the writing of a major rock musical which has gathered interest in London, New York and Las Vegas. <br />\r\nI was one of the main songwriters and did the midi programming of two musicals written by myself and a gentleman named Virgul Krown (Flowers By The Wall and Willie Gee) <br />\r\n<br />\r\nJust recently in the late summer, early fall of 2006, I reunited with my former co-writer and former lead guitarist of White Wolf, Cam MacLeod and we recorded and released as of July 2007 a BRAND NEW White Wolf CD entitled, &quot;Victim Of The Spotlight&quot;! <br />\r\n<br />\r\nThis Cd was produced by Martin Kronlund and released on Escape Music in Europe and the UK and on King Records in Japan. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nI have been lucky to work with some of the Top Producers and best Musicians in the world and look forward to more! <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</strong><font face=\"verdana\" size=\"+1\" color=\"#000000\">\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n<font face=\"verdana\" size=\"+1\" color=\"#000000\"></font>\r\n</div>\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n<font face=\"verdana\" size=\"+1\" color=\"#000000\"><strong><font color=\"#ff0000\">WEBSITE LINKS<br />\r\nFOR MORE INFO<br />\r\nAND<br />\r\nTO PURCHASE ALL CD RELEASES!!!</font> </strong></font><br