t keeps it interesting for us, and interesting for the fans as well.&quot; \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThey knew from the beginning that they would need a singer who had the range to go from powerful and raw to delicate and emotional. Along came Arrow. He was found singing at an open mic in Las Vegas and was instantly impressive. They recorded him on tracks called &ldquo;Bow Down&rdquo; and &ldquo;Drowning Soul&rdquo; and knew they had it. His peaceful warm tone and soulful poetic lyrics \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nbrought their sound to a new level. Writing songs has never been so easy. The other half of the rhythm section, bass guitar player Andy Champagne, was found playing in another band in Las Vegas that happened to be splitting. He fit seamlessly into Zeusophobia saying &ldquo;this is where I belong&rdquo;. \r\n</p>\r\n</font>\r\n',1,'<font style=\"background-color: #ffff00\"></font><br />\r\n<strong><font face=\"georgia,palatino\" size=\"4\">Arrow...vocals<br />\r\n<br />\r\nJeff Schaefer...guitar<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDanny Garay...drums<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAndy Champagne...bass</font></strong> \r\n',0,''),(2586,1000727,'Fraudes',1,68,'http://www.myspace.com/fraudes','','','',1,'',0,''),(2651,1000927,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2587,1000731,'counterfeit molly',1,71,'http://myspace.com/counterfeitmolly','3824 windsor gate rd va beach, va 23452','757-754-7884','<table border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width: 17px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td valign=\"top\"><span class=\"epkheading\" style=\"font-weight: bold\">Artist Information<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			</span><span class=\"epksubheading\">Biography<br />\r\n			</span><span class=\"epktxt\">&quot;A band you can count on for one great song after another&quot;.<br />\r\n			&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Spins Good Records<br />\r\n			&ldquo;Great music! 3 guitars have never sounded so good at the same time. &ldquo;<br />\r\n			PG13 Magazine<br />\r\n			&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <br />\r\n			Rather than churning out generic bubblegum pop, counterfeit molly serves up an eclectic rock mix that finds its roots in classic rock and modern experimentation. The innovative quintet is comprised of Mike Gombas, Chris Kendrick, Shawn Angelo, Vince Gurioli and Ben Meyer. According to singer Mike Gombas, &ldquo;The songs are usually crafted around a melody but they really only become counterfeit molly songs after everyone has a chance to put in their own unique stamp on each and every part.&rdquo; Luckily, it&rsquo;s a process that has worked well for the group over the years.<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			After completing hundreds of east coast shows, the band self-released a studio 8 song EP in July 2004 that gained them a loyal cult following, but also led them down the typical road of big label disappointment. Chris Kendrick recalls &ldquo;We got early interest from Neptune&rsquo;s Producer Pharell Williams and various others.&rdquo;<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Against all odds, the self-produced album turned out brilliantly, which landed them the pleasure of opening for national touring acts such as Staind, Jimmy&rsquo;s Chicken Shack, Family Force 5, White Light Motorcade, Tantric, and Seven Mary Three.<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Easy to listen to, but hard to classify, counterfeit molly have crossed many genres since establishing themselves with their self titled 2004 debut. The introspection of grunge, the weight of metal, the in your face appeal of punk music all blend easily in their songs.<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			The band spent the last six months in the studio writing, recording and producing their next album with a fine toothed comb. Songs like &ldquo;I Wanted More&rdquo; and &ldquo;Little White Lie&rdquo; benefit greatly from the band&rsquo;s unparalleled attention to detail has led them to a sound that is singularly unique in a modern day when acts are sorely missing any sense of individuality.<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			www.counterfeitmolly.net&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; www.myspace.com/counterfeitmolly<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Contact: Rob Kendrick&hellip;..757-754-7884<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			</span><span class=\"epksubheading\">Instrumentation<br />\r\n			</span><span class=\"epktxt\">Mike Gombas - Vocals, Guitar<br />\r\n			Chris Kendrick - Guitar/Piano<br />\r\n			Shawn Angelo - Guitar<br />\r\n			Ben Meyer - Drums<br />\r\n			Mike Mason - Bass<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			</span><span class=\"epksubheading\">Discography<br />\r\n			</span><span class=\"epktxt\">&quot;counterfeit molly&quot; (2004) EP<br />\r\n			***radio - &quot;Added Advantage&quot; &quot;Painless&quot;&nbsp; WROX 96.1 96x and WNOR 98.7 FM99.<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&quot;The Eternal Optimist&quot; (2007) LP<br />\r\n			***radio - &quot;I Wanted More&quot; &quot;Blood &amp; Bones&quot; WNOR fm99, WROX 96.1 96x and WXMM 100.5 MAX FM<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			</span></td>\r\n			<td style=\"width: 10px\"><img style=\"border: 0px\" src=\"../img/spacer.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"10\" height=\"1\" /></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n',1,'mike gombas...<br />\r\nchris kendrick...<br />\r\nshawn angelo...<br />\r\nben meyer... <br />\r\nmike mason...\r\n',0,''),(2588,1000732,'The Hex Parade',1,71,'http://www.myspace.com/thehexparade','','','<font face=\"impact,chicago\" size=\"3\">&nbsp; 