ir current guitar player due to musical differences, Pompei called in a favor. In 2 weeks time Ethic needed a guitar player to open up for Sebastian Bach at the Webster Theatre in Hartford, CT. Sundgren agreed to fill in. Ironically Rocky&#39;s band Sylt had just disbanded. The gig was so hot Ethic knew they had to have him. He agreed and we have been writing and playing non stop for the last 3 years. This is the final line up. The magic that these 4 souls create on stage and in the studio is stupifying. With Travers timekeeping, Scarola &quot;the maestro&#39;s&quot; technical jargon, Rocky&#39;s emotional riffs and Pompei&#39;s introspective lyrics and melody make this quartet an absolute phenomenon. Ethic is currently in the studio finishing up our third CD, a 13 track masterpiece of highs and lows and heartfelt music that will blow your head off.\r\n',1,'Steve Pompei - Lead vocals<br />\r\nRocky Sundgren - Lead guitar<br />\r\nHarry Masterbone - Bass guitar<br />\r\nAaron Travers - Drums\r\n',0,''),(2606,1000815,'Melucines',7,36,'','','','',0,'',0,''),(2607,1000818,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2608,1000819,'Lokixximo Music',3,86,'http://www.myspace.com/lokixximo','','201-577-6891','<strong><span>Lokixximo is New York&#39;s next, poised for success and co-signed by the&nbsp; industry itself,&nbsp; their street buzz is immaculate with a&nbsp; tremendous following for over three years. Lokixximo&#39;s music captures audiences with their creative wordplay, stunning music production and the most amazing live performances while still carrying a message . <br />\r\n<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: Verdana\">At this time, Lokixximo recently inked a major distribution deal with one of fastest growing independent record labels In Hollywood &ldquo;Jet Speed Records&rdquo; , and are ready to release their freshman album &ldquo;Los Locos Tambien Comen&rdquo; , </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">the d