amily: Verdana\">Credits. </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\"><br />\r\n<br />\r\n*</span><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: Verdana\">Lokixximo&#39;s music was featured in &quot;Reggaeton Nacion&quot; compilation in 2005, the album reached gold in two weeks. </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\"><br />\r\n<br />\r\n*</span><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: Verdana\">DTM Magazine&#39;s feature&rdquo; Down With the King&quot;. </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\"><br />\r\n<br />\r\n*</span><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: Verdana\">Lokixximo&#39;s song&quot;Que Vaz hacer&quot; was featured in the Megaton cd in 2006, </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\"><br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: Verdana\">reached the Latin billboard charts. </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\"><br />\r\n<br />\r\n*</span><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: Verdana\">Music Powers Magazine &quot;Lokixximo taking the industry by storm&quot; </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\"><br />\r\n<br />\r\n*</span><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: Verdana\">Burger King &quot;Tu Ciudad, Tu Musica&quot; hottest New York talent&quot; </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\"><br />\r\n<br />\r\n*</span><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: Verdana\">MTV&nbsp; &quot;Road to Menudo&quot; licensed 9 Lokixximo tracks. </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\"><br />\r\n<br />\r\n*</span><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: Verdana\">Telemundo 47 &quot;The hottest unsigned duo in New York&quot; </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\"><br />\r\n<br />\r\n*</span><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: Verdana\">Working on the music production for upcoming VH1 reality Show.</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\"><br />\r\n<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: Verdana\">New York is the city where millions of musicians are working day &amp; night </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\"><span>&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: Verdana\">to get recognized, the truth is only the ones who stay on grind and take their career seriously get noticed, the last three years Lokixximo has been the face of Latin Urban music in New York,&nbsp; the orchestrators of this era growing influential, latin hip-hop &amp; reggaeton sound. Their collaborations </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\"><br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: Verdana\">from Sly Kat, Platano &amp; T Weaponz &amp; productions by Add On Music &amp; Cool &amp; Dre cemented them among the most in-demand unsigned artists in the Latin industry. They are setting the standard for upcoming artists and inspiring many to be more creative in live performances &amp; music,</span><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12pt\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\"> It may have been a long time coming, but Lokixximo is more than ready to carry the crown for New York.</font></span></strong></strong><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: Verdana\">.</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \'Courier New\'\"><br />\r\n<br />\r\n</span>\r\n',1,'<span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: \'Courier New\'\">BONAO ,JOSE JOSEXX &amp; ADD ON MUSIC <br />\r\n<br />\r\n</span>\r\n',0,''),(2609,1000821,'Angels Grave',1,14,'http://www.numberonemusic.com/angelsgrave','721 West Broadway','309 371 9642','<p>\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; All but the bassist were together in a former band in the late 90&#39;s called Majikcow.&nbsp;&nbsp;This was primarily a cover band.&nbsp; Time goes by and the two guitarests start workin on original material.&nbsp; A year later they reunite with their drummer from the past,&nbsp;find a new bass player and form Angels Grave which is primarily original material.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; \r\n</p>\r\n',1,'Drums/BG Vocals- Fig Newton<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBass Guitar- Jim Churn<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLead Guitar- Mike Barry<br />\r\n<br />\r\nRythem/Lead Vocals- Wes Lovdahl\r\n',0,''),(2610,1000823,'Ronin Meyer',1,71,'','','','',1,'',0,''),(2611,1000828,'woolgather',1,76,'http://myspace.com/woolgatherband','156 St. James Pl., Bastrop, TX 78602','5126292192','Woolgather is not your every-day average rock band from Texas. If ever\r\na band with such a promising and unique sound has taken all that they\r\npossibly could, from blood and sweat, time and money, love and\r\nloneliness, and poured it into each surreal note played and each\r\nemotion tugged, Woolgather is the one. While it&rsquo;s impossible to compare\r\nthem directly to any one band, Woolgather would seemingly share the\r\nstage with the likes of bands such as Dredg, Thrice, Isis, Mogwai, or\r\nthe U.K.&rsquo;s Biffy Clyro. With progressive, post-rock musicianship, yet\r\nstill not lacking all the elements of modern pop-rock, catchy lyrics\r\nand intense structures, Woolgather is paving their own way and making\r\ntheir own luck.\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNow in 2008, with a brand new album near completion and an almost complete\r\nchange of sound and direction, with a new keyboardist (Toby Estes) and\r\nlive bassist (Eric Stephens), Woolgather has played throughout Austin,\r\nSan Marcos, and Corpus Christi Texas with an array of brand new\r\nmind-blowing songs that leave the audience in a state of bliss, with\r\ntheir ears wide open waiting for more. With a new full-length album in\r\nthe works dubbed &ldquo;The Reality Principle,&rdquo; due out sometime in late\r\n2008, Woolgather plans to make 2008 the year they get the exposure and\r\naudience that is so well deserved. Keep yours eyes and ears open, for\r\nWoolgather is coming and there is nothing standing in their way.\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDream is destiny.\r\n',1,'Casey Tipton - Vocals/Guitar<br />\r\nMatthew Eads - Drums<br />\r\nEric Stephens - Bass<br />\r\nToby Estes - Keys/Atmospherics\r\n',0,''),(2621,1000846,'Soundstill',1,14,'http://www.myspace.com/soundstillband','','712-320-4164','<font face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">Formed in 2006, guitarist Dana Evaro met vocalist Chris Adams and started writing immediately. Soon after guitarist vet Josh Cother (formally of Drop from Colorado) joined the group. Terry Justice (formally of Somber) joined on bass and soon after, the band found Tyler Hoekstra to finish out the sound.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn May of 2008 Soundstill entered Cathouse Studios in Sioux Falls, SD to record their first 5 song EP titled, &quot;Waiting Through&quot;. Recorded mixed and mastered by Mike Dresch who has produced and been involved with bands such as Nodes Of Ranvier, The Spill Canvas and Sons of Poseiden. Mike has also shared studio projects David Huff (Giant, producer), Bryan Carlstrom (Alice In Chains, Rob Zombie, Anthrax, Offspring), Josh Freese (A Perfect Circle) and Brad Smith of (Blind Melon).<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSince forming in 2006, Soundstill approach to writing music is rooted in trying to be innovative in arrangements and staying on either side of the definable. Primarily influenced by todays hard rock and metal such as the Deftones, Alice in Chains, System of A Down, and many others, you&sup1;ll hear a hint of yesterdays influence every now and then. &quot;Our first 5 song EP titled Waiting Through is the beginning of a larger concept idea we&sup1;re working on&quot;.</font>\r\n',1,'<p>\r\n<font face=\"arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">Chris Adams: Vocals<br />\r\nDana Evaro: Guitar<br />\r\nJosh Cother: Guitar<br />\r\nTerry Justice: Bass<br />\r\nTyler Hoekstra: Drums</font> \r\n</p>\r\n',0,''),(2612,1000829,'exeter',1,71,'http://www.myspace.com/exetermusic','','512-280-6065','<span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">Exeter is a space/alternative rock band with influences including but not limited to: Failure, Queens of the Stone Age, Cave In, Hum, Sunny Day Real Estate, Shiner, Year of the Rabbit, Enemy, The Life and Times, Deftones and Foo Fighters.<span>&nbsp; </span>Their sound is a mix of ambient rock with heavy guitars and dissonant melodies, thundering bass and driving drums.<span>&nbsp; </span>The band formed in June 2005 and began gigging in October of 2005 and has been well received in the grand state of Texas.<span>&nbsp; </span>After playing together as a unit for 6-months, they entered Test Tube Audio in December 2005 and recorded a 6-song EP/demo, Intra Venus, with Kevin Butler. The EP was duplicated through Discmakers with the drummer providing all the artwork.<span>&nbsp; </span>The band played numerous shows throughout Texas during the following 2 years and continuously worked on new material.<span>&nbsp; </span>Prior to entering the studio to record their first LP, they were presented with the opportunity to record a track for the Failure Tribute Album, &ldquo;The Nurse Who Loved Me&rdquo;, that will be released in 2008.<span>&nbsp; </span>The group quickly jumped at the opportunity and recorded &ldquo;Smoking Umbrellas&rdquo;.<span>&nbsp; </span>They entered Test Tube Audio again in December 2007 and are currently cutting their first full-length album, Grey Noise, White Lies, which will be released during the summer of 2008.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>\r\n',1,'<p>\r\nMike<br />\r\nCam<br />\r\nKy<br />\r\nRocky\r\n</p>\r\n',0,''),(2613,1000832,'Ruben Angel',3,18,'http://www.blackmountainproductions.net','P.O. Box 91941, Henderson, NV  89009','888-404-1168','<span><font size=\"3\"><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">There was a time in popular music where versatility proved the key ingredient to many artist&#39;s success. But somewhere along the way, versatility took a back seat to predictability. That&#39;s where Ruben Angel comes to the rescue. Few artists of modern times are as musically talented and have the full package as this San Diego by way of&nbsp;Argentina native, as evidenced by his forthcoming debut full length, &quot;Red.&quot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&quot;I can appreciate all kinds of music,&quot; explains the multi-instrumental musician, who lists singing, guitar, bass, drums, software drum programming, keyboard, piano, and alto saxophone on his musical resume. &quot;I&#39;m kind of all over the board when it comes to what the music scene is. I&#39;m happy doing every element, whether it be composing, arranging, transcribing music, performing, producing, and engineering.&quot;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n</font></font></font></span><span><font size=\"3\"><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n</font></font></font></span><span><font size=\"3\"><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\" color=\"#0000ff\">The forthcoming &quot;Red&quot; will certainly be one of the more musically varied albums to hit the pop-rock world in a very long time. &quot;I have a lot of rock, pop, and dance songs in my catalogue. I have some really poppy songs on my album, and then I have some songs that are way darker and a fusion of my sounds&quot; that&#39;s where my Bowie influence comes from. Some songs that are more electro rock are &quot;So Sweet&quot; and &quot;Masquerade.&quot; Another hip fusion song is &quot;Stereo is Dead,&quot; it&#39;s probably my &quot;main driver&quot; on the album, because it combines electro dance&nbsp;beats and classical rock guitar. I have a song called &quot;Mourning Star,&quot; and it&#39;s a 45-piece orchestra arrangement&nbsp;featuring robust soaring vocals. It&#39;s one of those big, epic, movie soundtrack, songs.&quot; <br />\r\n</font><br />\r\n</font></span><span><font size=\"3\">\r\n<p>\r\n<span><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">And while Angel makes no bones about his love for the studio, it&#39;s on the concert stage where you&#39;ll experience Ruben&#39;s theatrics, choreographed dance, and a good old fashioned rockin&#39; time. &quot;My band <em>was</em> guitar, bass, drums, and vocals, that&#39;s it. Now, I&#39;m dealing with all sorts of complications! I&#39;ve got like twelve synth tracks, four different drums sets. I can&#39;t have like twenty people on stage. I have to consolidate all my numbers down. So right now, my band consists of four great musicians. I have a guitarist, a keyboardist, A DJ, and I play bass on some songs, and, of course sing.&quot;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font></font></span>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<span><br />\r\n<font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\" color=\"#0000ff\">With &quot;Red&quot; on the horizon, Angel is setting up to unleash one heck of an unforgettable debut. And the fact that he has found himself on the ballot for the 2008 Grammy Awards for Record of the Year, Song of the Year, Best Male Pop Vocal Performance, and Best Pop Vocal Album shows that breakthrough success is lurking right around the corner.<span>&nbsp; </span>But according to the artist himself, this is only the beginning. &quot;Eventually, I want to do a Spanish album&quot; I feel like&nbsp;my Latin culture has had&nbsp;such an influence&nbsp;on me. I would like my music to be considered internationally marketable. This first album though I&#39;m gearing more towards to the American crowd. I&#39;m also&nbsp;writing an opera right now. I have a lot of music that lends itself to the older&nbsp;demographic&nbsp;- more refined and classically-oriented stuff. Eventually, I want to have one of the best recording studio in the world , where I can work with my inspirations, and with up-and coming talent. Besides performing, my biggest passions are&nbsp;- sound engineering and production.- Be certain to keep an eye out for Ruben Angel from here on out&nbsp;- it&#39;s bound to be one mighty wild ride..... </font></span>\r\n</p>\r\n</font></span>\r\n',0,'',0,''),(2614,1000834,'Blemish UK',1,71,'http://www.blackmountainproductions.net','P.O. Box 91941, Henderson, NV  89009','888-404-1168','<span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font size=\"3\"><font color=\"#0000ff\"><strong>Blemish UK&nbsp;</strong>is a four piece Rock Band based in Birmingham, UK. They were formed in late 2004. </font></font></font></span><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font size=\"3\" color=\"#0000ff\">Their influences range from: <u>Roxy Music, Foo Fighters; The Police through to U2</u>, which all appear evident when listening to a Blemish UK song. </font></font></span><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font size=\"3\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">With hard hitting songs such as &lsquo;One in a Million&rsquo; and &lsquo;Locked&rsquo; through to the beautiful ballads &lsquo;Driving&rsquo; and &lsquo;Come with Me&rsquo;, you can see why the band have had interest from some of the businesses biggest Management, including a three year spell with Don Arden (Sharon Osbourne&rsquo;s father) which was sadly concluded due to Don&rsquo;s&nbsp;health.</font></font></font></span><font color=\"#0000ff\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\" size=\"3\">&nbsp;</font></span> <br />\r\n</font>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\" class=\"MsoNormal\">\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font size=\"3\"><br />\r\n<font color=\"#0000ff\">The Band&rsquo;s live reviews have been extremely complimentary with comments such as, &ldquo;silky&rdquo;, &ldquo;powerful&rdquo;, &ldquo;accomplished musicians&rdquo; and &ldquo;the complete package&rdquo;. These are just a few of the positive reviews the band has received. </font></font></font></span><font color=\"#0000ff\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font size=\"3\">Blemish UK has gone from strength to strength over the last two years, by recruiting James Weston as lead vocalist. With outstanding vocals and every inch a front man, the band have now progressed to the next level.&nbsp;</font></font></span><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font size=\"3\">Blemish UK was given the highest accolade by Kerrang UK in 2005 by voting &lsquo;One in a Million&rsquo; the No. 1 on the unsigned charts. Another of their tracks &lsquo;Come with me&rsquo; came second in the UK song writing competition, also in 2005. </font></font></span><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font size=\"3\">Blemish UK has toured the UK extensively over the last two years, gaining a reputation as one of the UK bands most likely to succeed!</font></font></span></font> \r\n</p>\r\n',1,'<font face=\"Helvetica\"><span><strong><u>JAMES WESTON&nbsp;- Lead Vocals<br />\r\n</u><font size=\"3\">&nbsp;</font></strong></span><span><font size=\"3\">&nbsp;</font></span></font> <span><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font size=\"3\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">James&nbsp;has always been the centre of attention wherever the party is. He sang and toured with the band &quot;Hush&quot; for three years. This is when the boys from Blemish UK first noticed him for his amazing vocal ability, his enthusiastic stage presence and his overall image. He had a shining career as a DJ, winning many coveted awards before he joined Blemish UK. The move to fronting a rock band has proved very successful and rewarding, fulfilling his desires to perform. James is a natural performer and is in his element when performing<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font></font></font></span><span><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font size=\"3\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">\r\n<h3><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font size=\"3\"><span><font color=\"#000000\"><u><font>NIGEL BOSWELL&nbsp;- </font>Bass &amp; Keyboards<br />\r\n</u></font></span></font></font></h3><span><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\" size=\"3\" color=\"#0000ff\">&nbsp;</font></span><span><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font size=\"3\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">Founding member of Blemish UK. <br />\r\n</font></font></font></span><span><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\" size=\"3\" color=\"#0000ff\">&nbsp;</font></span> <span><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\" size=\"3\" color=\"#0000ff\">Nigel was&nbsp;compelled to play bass guitar after watching Mick Karn perform at a Japan concert. He began his musical journey at the age of fifteen and played in bands for many years. Later, he worked as a session musician across Europe and the USA, crafting his apprenticeship as an accomplished musician. Rarely feeling fulfilled playing other people&#39;s music,&nbsp;Nigel needed to meet his own musical creativity, but struggled finding the right musicians to work with. That is until he teamed up with John and Simon and formed &quot;Blemish UK&quot;.&nbsp;</font></span><span><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font size=\"3\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">His natural song writing ability was able to flourish and this was recognized by Kerrang Radio Station in the UK and the UK Song writing Guild. Various publishing companies have shown interest in adding his compositions to their catalogues. Nigel has</font></font></font></span><span><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font size=\"3\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">&nbsp;spent three great years crafting his song writing under the wings of Don Arden in LA.&nbsp;</font></font></font></span><span><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font size=\"3\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">Nigel is now aiming with Blemish UK to bring their music to the masses.<span>&nbsp; </span>(The sky is the limit when your heart is in it).<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font></font></font></span><span><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font size=\"3\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">\r\n<h3><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font size=\"3\"><span><u><font color=\"#000000\"><font>JOHN MARTIN -&nbsp;</font><span>&nbsp;</span>Lead Guitar &amp; Vocals<br />\r\n</font></u></span></font></font></h3><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font color=\"#0000ff\"><font size=\"3\"><span>John has been playing guitar for many years and has toured the UK extensively. He was never totally fulfilled playing other people&#39;s music, though he was able to craft his art doing so.<span>&nbsp; </span>John&#39;s heart lay in song writing; quickly realizing he had a flare for it. Some of his songs were quickly sought after by various publishers world wide, and chance meeting with founder member of &quot;BLEMISH UK,&quot;&nbsp;took his song writing to a new level. With this new partnership John quickly penned the superb track &quot;Driving,&quot; this was followed by the outstanding &quot;In your heart.&quot;<span>&nbsp;</span>Though John has proven himself as a great songwriter, his heart still lies in picking up a guitar and rocking audiences.<span>&nbsp;</span>John is now looking forward to combining the two, and showing what a complete package he is.<span>&nbsp;</span>John believes he has found his home spiritually and mentally with the chemistry of BLEMISH UK</span><span>.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</span></span></font></font></font><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font color=\"#0000ff\"><font size=\"3\"><span><span><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font size=\"3\"><u><font color=\"#000000\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">SIMON RYLAND<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;-</span> </span></strong><strong><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Drums &amp; Vocals</span></strong></font></u></font></font><strong><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\" size=\"3\">&nbsp;</font></span></strong> \r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\" class=\"MsoBodyText2\">\r\n<span><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font size=\"3\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">Simon first picked up a pair of drumsticks at age two, playing along to his father&#39;s records on pots and pans, laid out like a drum kit and&nbsp;his favorite record being an album by Blind Faith. The drummer being Ginger Baker, who was and is still one of&nbsp;Simon&#39;s biggest influences;&nbsp;Simon copied every note he played on the album, even the solos. At fourteen,&nbsp;Simon joined his first gigging band, who&#39;s average age was fifteen, playing rock -n- roll covers in pubs and social clubs around their local town. Three years later he joined his first original band who got to the finals of the &quot;Central Band Of The Year&quot; contest. The band&nbsp;got to play live on Central News and also make a record. But like most young bands, their musical differences split them up. Soon Simon got a call from an old school friend, whom he used to jam with at the local church asking him to join their band. They were another original band playing indie style music and&nbsp;they&nbsp;were able&nbsp;to play the: London Scene, the Mean Fiddler, the Rock Garden and the Power House Islington, when they were spotted by WEA Records and London Records. It was EG Records that pulled them in to talk business. Having produced five tracks, the band thought they were on their way, but the internal politics within EG Records proved the downfall of the&nbsp;opportunity. Simon&#39;s talents can now be heard through the joint efforts of:&nbsp;BLEMISH UK.</font></font></font></span>\r\n</p>\r\n<br />\r\n</span></span></font></font></font></font></font></font></span></font></font></font></span>\r\n',0,''),(2615,1000835,'Dana Niles',1,71,'http://www.blackmountainproductions.net','P.O. Box 91941, Henderson, NV  89009','888-404-1168','<table border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"5\" width=\"100%\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr valign=\"top\">\r\n			<td width=\"100%\" valign=\"top\"><span><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font size=\"3\" color=\"#0000ff\">Throughout our lives we are all faced with failure of some kind.<span>&nbsp; </span>Through music, Dana works to break through the boundaries we create for ourselves. It is this process that weaves a thread through Dana&#39;s songs. </font></font></span><font color=\"#0000ff\"><span><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font size=\"3\">Dana&#39;s musical accomplishments are extensive.<span>&nbsp; </span>From his first band at the age of 10 Dana has continued to evolve as a singer/songwriter.<span>&nbsp; </span>By his early teens he was playing in legendary Los Angeles music venues like The Roxy, The Whiskey, the Troubadour and the Hollywood Palladium opening for acts such as Cheap Trick and The Young Dubliners.<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			</font></font></span></font><span><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font size=\"3\" color=\"#0000ff\">As a member of bands such as Hot Water Music and Waterfront, and as a solo artist , Dana has continued to grow creatively.<span>&nbsp; </span>Many of his former band mates have gone on to make a living in music (i.e. Greg Richling- bass player for The Wallflower).<span>&nbsp; </span>Dana has worked with many talented people including Jim Wirt, (producer for Incubus and Hoobastank).<br />\r\n			</font></font></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n',0,'',0,''),(2616,1000836,'Hurricane Cletis',1,71,'http://www.blackmountainproductions.net','P.O. Box 91941, Henderson, NV  89009','888-404-1168','<p>\r\n<font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\" size=\"3\" color=\"#0000ff\">A storm is brewing around <strong>Hurricane Cletis</strong>, in the Saskatchewan music scene. After a year of writing and searching for band mates, brothers: Greg, Darren and Rob Dyck, joined forces with JK and Chris Smith. They knew they had the right lineup, when only months after forming, they went to compete against over 50 bands in the 2006 Rock 102 and the Roxy on Broadway&#39;s &quot;Ultimate Band Warz.&quot; Judged by industry moguls: Ralph James (The Agency Group) and Steve Blair (Head of A&amp;R Warner Music Canada) Hurricane Cletis was chosen as the winner!<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn January 2007, Cletis member: Greg Dyck, was chosen as the regional winner of the Canadian Radio Star Songwriting Competition for the song: &quot;Stained.&quot; Among hundreds of entries, Hurricane Cletis rose to the top and earned a trip to Toronto for Nationals and an opportunity to showcase the song during Canadian Music Week. Combining sounds of their influences from yesterday and today (Motley Crue, Godsmack, Nickleback) the band has created a punchy, driving collection of songs.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTheir self titled debut was produced by Ryan Anderson, who has worked on projects such as: Nickelback&#39;s &quot;The Long Road&quot; and &quot;All The Right Reasons.&quot; Anderson&#39;s other credits include working with the bands: Thornley, ACDC, Hinder, Mudvayne, Default, Bryan Adams and Theory Of A Deadman. Hurricane Cletis boasts hard rockin&#39; songs like: &quot;Disgusted&quot; and &quot;Break You,&quot; while tracks like &quot;Stained&quot; and &quot;Little While&quot; show a more vulnerable side. Hurricane Cletis is a must see live show that screams out their &quot;get off your butt and party&quot; attitude!&nbsp;</font>\r\n</p>\r\n',1,'<strong><font face=\"helvetica\" size=\"3\">Darren Dyck - Vocals</font></strong><span><font face=\"Helvetica\" color=\"#000000\"><font size=\"3\"><font face=\"helvetica\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</font>A natural born performer!&nbsp; From the earliest age Darren (D.D.) has always commanded attention with his ability to entertain and captivate an audience.&nbsp; Whether it was mimicking his favorite comedians or just clowning around, D.D. always caught people&rsquo;s attention.&nbsp; It wasn&#39;t until a few years later that he would find his natural vocal ability, and thus, his way to the stage. &nbsp;After brothers Greg and Rob had been playing together for a while in their parents basement they decided it was time for a singer and convinced Darren to give it a shot.&nbsp; They liked what they heard and have been performing together since.&nbsp; With his seemingly unlimited energy and commanding stage presence, D.D. truly brings a rock show to life.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Rob Dyck - Percussion</strong></font><span><br />\r\n<font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font color=\"#000000\"><font size=\"3\">From the time he can remember Rob wanted to play the drums.&nbsp; After countless years of staring at pictures in catalogues he decided to join his school band.&nbsp; Although the instructor thought he would be a natural on the tuba, Rob would not have any part&nbsp;of that.&nbsp; He knew where he belonged and where he was meant to be.&nbsp; Rob realized he wanted to be in a rock band after his first taste of Motley Crue and the drumming of Tommy Lee.&nbsp; Rob plays with passion, energy and presence, always striving to give the audience a true taste of rock &#39;n&#39; roll.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font><font size=\"3\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; color: #444444; font-family: Verdana\"><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font color=\"#000000\">Greg Dyck - Guitar</font></font></span></strong><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; color: #444444; font-family: Verdana\"><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\" color=\"#000000\">&nbsp;</font></span></strong></font><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Verdana\"><font face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><font color=\"#000000\"><font size=\"3\">Growing up in small town Saskatchewan has proven to be an integral part of Greg Dyck&rsquo;s evolution as a songwriter and guitar player.<span>&nbsp; </span>Being forced to entertain his creative mind, Greg turned to music at an early age. It wasn&rsquo;t long before he realized that his passion lied in both writing and playing guitar. Just like any other musician starting out, Greg spent countless hours playing and writing music in his basement alongside his brothers, Rob and Darren. With numerous years of experience, Greg&rsquo;s contributions as a creative and innovative songwriter have played a role in much of Hurricane Cletis&rsquo; success. Greg writes music from personal experiences that sometimes evolve into fictional stories, while combining his musical influences from yesterday and today. Greg&rsquo;s creative ability as a songwriter have been a key factor in producing a driving, punchy, collection of original material that is performed by Hurricane Cletis.</font></font></font></span><br />\r\n</font></font></span><font size=\"3\"><strong>JK Brackish - Bass<br />\r\n</strong>JK (Jonathan Klein) has always expressed a passion and love for music from an early age. When the question of &quot;what do you want to be when you grow up?&quot; was asked in his first year od school, JK&#39;s reply was clear - a rock star. After choosing the Bass as his instrument of choice at the age of thirteen, he quickly started to expand his musical influences and tastes. After being in a band with high school friends, JK joined up with fellow musicians from his hometown to become a member of Hurricane Cletis.<br />\r\n</font></font></span>\r\n',0,''),(2641,1000901,'Rosco Caine- Drummer',1,17,'','','','',0,'',0,''),(2643,1000905,'Olio',1,61,'http://www.oliomusic.com','po box 452975, Los Angeles, CA 90045','714-348-8593','<div class=\"tabnav_content_inline_padded\">\r\nWhat do a film composer, dj and director of music and arts have in common?&nbsp; Three brothers from other mothers (and fathers) got together, from the OC, ChiTown and DC, to create a miscellaneous collection of musical works aka OLIO.&nbsp; Inspired by everything from Black Sabbath to Barry White these guys stir up an eclectic blend of music from hip-hop to funk, soul to rock and a dash of pop and serve it up nice and hot!<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhether it&#39;s songs about break-ups, make-outs, shake-ups or four letter words, Olio produces electrifying, positive music from their studio in Los Angeles, CA.&nbsp; On stage Arif sings and breaks strings (sometimes his right hand gets heavy), DeHaven grooves on drums and croons (when the lights are low and the mood is right), and Matt plays bass so wickedly even his ex-girlfriend still gets jealous (he&#39;s also been known to throw out zingers in between songs trying out new material for his secret life in stand-up comedy).<br />\r\n<br />\r\nCurrently their music is available for FREE via mp3 download for you to enjoy and share.&nbsp; They are actively writing and recording songs to complete their latest project &quot;Living The Dream.&quot;&nbsp; The album will be a collection of 15-20 songs. 10 songs are finished ranging from the nylon stringed sweetness of &quot;Completely Beautiful&quot; about the profound impact of becoming a parent (received an Honorable Mention Award in the 2008 West Coast Songwriters International Competition) to a hard rock/rap collab that already has 20,000 NJ Devils fans shouting &quot;Here We Go&quot; at the Prudential Center. Their homage to the mamacita de futbol aka &quot;Soccer Mom&quot; inspired one impassioned UK critic to call them &quot;sexist and subtle as a sledghammer.&quot; (Olio still thinks Benny Hill, John Cleese and Ricky Gervais are funny)&nbsp; The sound created is rich and packs a punch reminiscent of the John Mayer Trio while thematically aiming for Stevie Wonder&#39;s &quot;Songs in the Key of Life.&quot;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn between recordings they have tours scheduled throughout the West and into the Rockies this year and plans to include the East are in the works.&nbsp; To experience Olio only on recording is like Vader without the Darth.&nbsp; Whether it&#39;s 30 minutes or 3 hours, the energy generated by these three could power a small town (or even the lesser known planet Zeta-Reticulan5).&nbsp; So, maybe the question isn&#39;t Who or What is Olio but rather When and Where? \r\n</div>\r\n',1,'Arif - Vocals, Guitar<br />\r\nDeHaven - Drums, Vocals<br />\r\nMatt - Bass, Vocals\r\n',0,''),(2618,1000838,'Nineteen88',1,16,'http://www.myspace.com/nineteen88','141 morton st','8127893907','From Evansville, IN comes an exciting party rock band. Muscle bound\r\nVocalist/Guitarist Handsome Mick Rowe, Bass Guitarist Tim Thompson, and\r\nDrummer Adam Silverman- collectively known as Nineteen88-have been able\r\nto accomplish alot in the very short time they have been together.\r\nFormed from the ashes of Mick&#39;s previous band Goliath (Music Cartel\r\nRecords), Nineteen88 was created to play &quot;good time rock that has\r\nsomething for everyone&quot; as Handsome Mick puts it. &quot;We all grew up\r\nlistening and playing different styles of music, we consider Nineteen88\r\nsonic territory to include ACDC, JET, and The Darkness. but include a\r\nnod to the past heros of 80&#39;s rock music. We are not a cover band in\r\nthe least, but we do not try to hide those Classic ifluences, if we\r\ndid, the music wouldn&#39;t be as honest&quot;. An actively touring band,\r\nNineteen88 has been able to share stages (both acoustic and electric)\r\nwith some of the Nations rising stars. They have performed in almost\r\nevery region in the U.S. picking up fans all along the way. Now with\r\nthe national release &quot;The Great American Rock And Roll Spectacle&quot;, the\r\ndoors are wide open for the new band. Bass Guitarist Tim Thompson, a\r\nSouth Carolina transplant who moved to Evansville a decade ago says,\r\n&quot;Touring and playing music is an amazing &quot;job perk&quot; to have. I love\r\ntraveling so much! Meeting all sorts of people and getting to know them\r\nis something I don&#39;t take for granted.&quot; Adam Silverman. adds &quot; I would\r\necho Tim on that. I mean, we can drive all night with no sleep and be\r\n100% wiped out, but the minute we hit that stage and I see a crowd of\r\ntotal strangers connecting with the music, it makes it all worthwhile!\r\nThat rocks!.&quot;\r\n',1,'Handsome Mick Rowe\r\n',0,''),(2619,1000841,'Ross Royce',1,66,'http://www.myspace.com/rossroyce','135 The Parade,Ascot Vale ,Melbourne ,Australia 3032','+61402343855','Singer/Songwriter/multi-instrumentalist &#39;Ross Royce&#39; debuted on the Australian scene in 2006, and has a 7-track c.d released called &quot;Get it Together&quot;.Playing drums,guitar,keyboards and doing most of the vocals on a number of the song&#39;s,Ross Royce is an exciting new talent! He is also known as a wild performer live who loves to combine dance and theatrics in his live show&#39;s.<br />\r\nHis music has recieved extensive airplay on Australian and N.Z local radio and&nbsp; U.S internet radio.<br />\r\nHe is currently based in Melbourne,Australia and will be releasing his debut album &quot;Life Worth Living&quot; across Australia,New Zealand and to rest of the World in June.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOther achievements are listed below:<br />\r\nMore than 800,000 hits on his myspace page(www.myspace.com/rossroyce)<br />\r\n-Went to No.2 garage,No.5 Indie and No.7 Rock on the Australian myspace &#39;Top Artists&#39;chart.<br />\r\n-Top 10 on a number of internet radio charts inc:&quot;Rockin the Shed&quot; and &quot;Just Say Rock&quot;..<br />\r\n-Artist of the week on MP3.com.au(Dec2006),Garage band.com(Sept 2007) and on LPM(March 2008).<br />\r\n-Two music videos appeared on Australian National T.V show &quot;The Music Jungle&quot;(Channel Nine)<br />\r\n-Song &#39;Mixed up World&#39;2nd on Australian Singer/songwriter music show &quot;MusicBiz&quot;(Feb 2007)<br />\r\n-Featured on two U.S compilation albums in late 2007 (&quot;Riot on Sunset&quot; Vol.7) and (&quot;Skratch indie sampler&quot; V.7)<br />\r\n-Worldwide digital distribution and nationwide physical distribution across Australia as well as distribution with &#39;Amazon&#39; in the the U.S.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nShort Description:<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTripped out,new age Rock! <br />\r\nWebsites: www.myspace.com/rossroyce<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; www.rossroyce.com\r\n',1,'<sup>Ross Nicholson<br />\r\nTrevor Reading<br />\r\nKeijo Sandvik<br />\r\n</sup>\r\n',0,''),(2620,1000843,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2626,1000862,'claytooth',1,17,'','','201-725-5807','<p>\r\nClaytooth is a one man home studio band. I&#39;m looking for a audience who like a wide range of rock music.<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Up coming album: I THINK I&#39;M PART YETI <br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Influences: led zep, blind melon, slayer, james taylor,tool,<br />\r\ncanned heat, country joe and the fish , jimi hendrix,misfits etc. etc. etc.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;First two tracks on site are from an album called confederate legacy based on events proceding american civil war to present day. Almost a southern rock influence if you smoked a whole lot of crack and&nbsp;have a&nbsp; head injury.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; The third one is off of&nbsp; the&quot;I THINK I&#39;M PART YETI&quot; deal. \r\n</p>\r\n',1,'<font face=\"georgia,palatino\">A.oliveri - all instruments and vocals<br />\r\nTwo members are still pending</font> \r\n',0,''),(2627,1000867,'Curvature',1,105,'http://www.myspace.com/curvaturerock','Galesburg, Illinois','309-368-1255','<p>\r\nCurvature is a modern rock band with classic rock and blues influence.<br />\r\nDuring a time when over produced and digital sounds top the charts, Curvature goes for a more stripped down classic sound and feel.\r\n</p>\r\n',1,'Dave (Guitar)<br />\r\nPonce (Bass)<br />\r\nIan (guitar)<br />\r\nJosh (drums)<br />\r\nB.J. (vox) \r\n',0,''),(2628,1000870,'CYNOSURA',1,76,'http://cynosura.ch','','','<span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><font size=\"3\">The name CYNOSURA is derived from Greek mythology.<span>&nbsp; </span>CYNOSURA, a nymph on Mount Ida raised the young Zeus who in gratitude for her services placed her in the heavens on the event of her passing.<span>&nbsp; </span>CYNOSURA thus became the North Star, also known as Polaris&hellip;</font></span><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><font size=\"3\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</font></span><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><font size=\"3\"><br />\r\nFormed in December 2006, CYNOSURA draws upon musical roots firmly set in the world of progressive rock.<span>&nbsp; </span>Like their namesake, their compositions are highly dynamic, focused and powerful, mysteriously blending light and dark in an ever changing sonic universe.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></font></span><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><font size=\"3\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</font></span><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><font size=\"3\"><br />\r\nCYNOSURA&rsquo;s music is conspicuously different due to their use of orchestral arrangements which powerfully support the dance of the soaring and very melodic guitars and keyboards.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></font></span><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><font size=\"3\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</font></span><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><font size=\"3\"><br />\r\nLyrically, CYNOSURA transports the listener into thought provoking worlds of emotion, where dreams, beauty and light strongly contrast with realms of darkness and the confrontation of our own fate and mortality.</font></span><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><font size=\"3\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</font></span><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><font size=\"3\"><br />\r\nCYNOSURA is composed of the following five musicians: <br />\r\n<br />\r\n</font></span><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><font size=\"3\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; text-align: justify\" class=\"MsoNormal\">\r\n<strong><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">Craig McConnell (www.craigmcconnell.com)</span></strong> \r\n</p>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">A native of Scotland, born into a culture with a strong heritage rich in passion and expression for the arts, Craig was at a very early age intensely moved by the power of music.</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"><br />\r\nCraig began his musical career in the groundbreaking late 60&rsquo;s/early 70&rsquo;s, a time inspired by the impact of the Beatles, followed by Jimi Hendrix and Cream, a period of intense musical awakening within the UK.<span>&nbsp; </span>Possessing a deep passion for the electric guitar, his instrument of choice, he became the lead guitarist/vocalist in many UK based bands from 1967 to 1996 performing in the worlds of blues and rock, progressive rock and jazz fusion.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"><br />\r\nAlways inquisitive, Craig found an irresistible pull and embarked upon what seemed an inevitable journey&hellip; that of the composer. In what he felt to be a natural progression, Craig found himself working in 1997 with a kindred spirit, that of innovative New York Opera Diva Susan Belling with whom he composed and recorded in Paris.<span>&nbsp; </span>Both artists were worlds apart, but eager to embrace each other&rsquo;s musical universe.<span>&nbsp; </span>This led to a mutual realisation that both disciplines could indeed merge and give birth to an exciting form of musical expression.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"><br />\r\nAlways fascinated by the realm of classical music, Craig was predestined to ultimately embrace the challenge of composing for the orchestra, which came to pass at the turn of the millennium when he left his homeland for the U.S. and composed the score for the modern ballet <em>Leap of Faith</em>.</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"><br />\r\nDuring his 5 year tenure in America he composed many scores for both feature films and documentaries, in particular the 2 hour WWI feature film <em>Company K</em>, produced by Waterfront Pictures, New York, detailing the wartime experiences of Alabama born U.S. Marine William March (www.companykthefilm.com).<span>&nbsp; </span>His work during this period was also featured in New Zealand, the UK and Japan.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">In September 2005 Craig relocated to Geneva Switzerland where he recently was main composer for the films <em>Dessine-Moi Une Ligne / Draw Me a Line</em> <span>&nbsp;</span>and <em>Une Femme Choucas</em> featuring the work of Swiss world leading extreme snowboarder and base jumper G&eacute;raldine Fasnacht (www.lineprod.ch). </span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"><br />\r\n<br />\r\nHaving spent a considerable amount of time in his recording studio, Craig began to miss the adrenalin rush of the live performance and endeavoured to assemble a group of musicians towards that end.<span>&nbsp; </span>In December 2006, he made the acquaintance of bass guitarist Christian Sallin, a brother in arms, and formed CYNOSURA (www.cynosura.ch).</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</span></span><strong><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">Christophe Colliard</span></strong><strong><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</span></strong><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">Christophe was born in Switzerland into a musical environment. At a very young age, he took up the trumpet, piano and guitar. From the age of 10 to 13 he was soloist in the Choir <em>Les Petits Chanteurs d&rsquo;Ursy</em> in which he performed in large European cities such as Paris, London and Rome, and also recorded several albums.</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"><br />\r\nAt 13 years of age he discovered the world or rock music and soon joined various bands featuring classic hard rock acts such as Deep Purple, Led Zeppelin, Whitesnake.</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">In 1982 Christophe, his brother, and close friend Benett Corboz founded the band ISIS in which he filled the role of guitarist and backing vocalist.<span>&nbsp; </span>ISIS became successful in the 80&rsquo;s when they cut a single and a CD produced by Carlos Peron of YELLO, and participated in various TV programmes, including &ldquo;La Grande Chance&rdquo;.</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"><br />\r\nIn 1992 Christophe was guitarist and backing vocalist of singer Jean-Philippe Llord and recorded a CD with Yves Sanna, Bernard Paganotti, Richard Pizzorno, Francis Coletta (musicians of Johnny Hallyday, France Gall, Michel Berger and Whitney Houston).</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"><br />\r\nDuring the period from 1995 to 2004, he performed as guitarist and vocalist in 3 rock operas composed by Benett Corboz: <em>Kronos</em>, <em>Sexus</em> and <em>Dracula</em>.</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"><br />\r\nFinally, in late 2006 he became a founder member of CYNOSURA in the capacity of guitarist/vocalist and composer.</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</span><strong><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"><br />\r\n<br />\r\nChristian Sallin</span></strong><strong><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</span></strong><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">Born in Switzerland, Christian enrolled in the conservatory of music at 14 years of age in order to study classical guitar.</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"><br />\r\nHe later found his true calling in the bass guitar and joined the band RESCUE in 1988, performing in excess of a hundred concerts which included tours of Belgium and the UK.<span>&nbsp; </span>They recorded the successful single <em>Christina</em> and a CD featuring a self penned composition entitled <em>Missing in Action</em>.</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"><br />\r\nBetween 1995 and 1999, Christian was bass guitarist for the productions of the rock operas <em>Kronos</em> and <em>Sexus</em> whose soundtracks were released on CD.</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"><br />\r\nIn 2000 he joined the band VENT D&rsquo;OUEST, performing over 100 concerts nationally.</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">In 2006, after having made Craig McConnell&rsquo;s acquaintance, he became founder member, bass guitarist and backing vocalist of the band CYNOSURA.</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</span><strong><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"><br />\r\n<br />\r\nJean-Paul Gazerro</span></strong><strong><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"></span></strong><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n</span></span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">Born in 1975 into a musical family, Jean-Paul took up the piano at the age of 8 years and acquired his first instrument at 15.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"><br />\r\nSurrounded by musicians and influenced by rock and pop rock in the 80&rsquo;s-90&rsquo;s, he performed and toured with many bands nationally and also worked as a studio session musician with a<span>&nbsp; </span>variety of artists.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">Feeling increasingly musically frustrated within the confines of a band, he later felt the need to broaden his musical horizons and to that end embraced the world of the composer.</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"><br />\r\nJean-Paul became the keyboard player of CYNOSURA in October 2007.</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</span><strong><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"><br />\r\n<br />\r\nEdouardo Andrade</span></strong><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n</span></span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">A native of Portugal, Edouardo, possessing a passion for music and in particular for percussion instruments, began his musical carrier in earnest at the age of 16 years, receiving his first lessons in drumming.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"><br />\r\nFrom 1991 until present his passion for the drum has driven the rhythm section of numerous bands.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"><br />\r\nIn 1993 he joined LE BAL DU PENDU with whom he recorded the album <em>Qui l&rsquo;aime</em>, toured France and Switzerland, participated in the festival &ldquo;</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">Francofolies de la Rochelle&rdquo;, appeared on Swiss TV (TSR) and in the </span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">programme &ldquo;Taratata&rdquo; on French TV (France 2).</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"><br />\r\nIn 2003 he filled the drummer&rsquo;s seat of the band VENT D&rsquo;OUEST, performing with bass guitarist Christian Sallin in over 100 concerts nationally.<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"><br />\r\nIn late 2006 he became a founder member of CYNOSURA.</span> </font></span>\r\n',1,'<font size=\"3\"><em><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">Lead guitar &amp; vocals:</span></em><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"> Craig McConnell<br />\r\n</span></font><font size=\"3\"><em><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">Guitar &amp; vocals:</span></em><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"><span>&nbsp; </span>Christophe Colliard<br />\r\n</span></font><font size=\"3\"><em><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">Bass guitar &amp; backing vocals:</span></em><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\"> Christian Sallin<br />\r\n</span></font><font size=\"3\"><em><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">Keyboards &amp; backing vocals: </span></em><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">Jean-Paul Gazerro<br />\r\n</span></font><em><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">Drums, percussion &amp; backing vocals: </span></em><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\'\">Edouardo Andrade</span> \r\n',0,''),(2629,1000873,'Craig Siegelbaum',1,71,'http://myspace.com/craigsiegelbaum','','','Guitarist/Composer Craig Siegelbaum formerly of the acclaimed Long\r\nIsland,NY band Supergenius has made music for most of his life. Taking\r\na wide range of influences, Craig has created his own style. His main\r\nfocus the past couple of years has been writing and recording\r\ninstrumental music for television and film. Craig is also a\r\nguitarist/songwriter for the band Half Circle Drive. A band that he\r\noriginally helped form. Visit www.myspace.com/halfcircledrive for more\r\ninfo.\r\nCraig&#39;s music has been spun by several DJ&#39;s from around the country. He\r\nalso has written,performed and/or recorded with Singer/songwriter Gina\r\nCutillo and has also had the pleasure of working with such artists as\r\nNine Days,Twenty After, Johnny B.Hive and Earthling Massive among\r\nothers. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nHere is what  fans and critics are saying about Craig:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em>\r\nCraig Siegelbaum: &quot;From Long Island, New York, this guitarist will take\r\nyou on a sonic journey into the soul of his instrument, very much like\r\nour West\r\nCoast friend Joe Satriani. Jeff Beck like, with a Robin Trower\r\nbackbone. For guitar lovers everywhere&quot;.\r\n-From:http://www.realnewsnet.net/angeloslist.html<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&quot;You have figured out how to make a full sound. I think your stuff has\r\novertones of greatness. guitars cool, melody-complex enough, the\r\nproduction is studio quality.&quot;\r\n-Reqquiem from Las Vegas, Nevada<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&quot;Instrumentation is lovely. textures are soft and gripping. this is\r\nwonderful stuff to groove to--driving again late on an overpass turning\r\nsideways round milwaukee while lake michigan reflects skyscrapers and\r\nthe shoulder bites the tires to the beat. production is perfect. song\r\nis spectacular. lovelylovely and haunting.&quot;\r\n- coleclosser from Springfield, Missouri <br />\r\n<br />\r\n&quot;Very well produced Guitars : Good Melody : Good Production : Very Good.&quot;\r\n-MauTheMan,Sao Paulo, Brazil <br />\r\n</em>\r\n<br />\r\nF<strong>or licensing information or to order a cd email here or at\r\ninfo@baumtracks.com. For more information on Craig and his music visit:\r\nhttp://www.baumtracks.com or www.myspace.com/craigsiegelbaum\r\n</strong>\r\n',0,'',0,''),(2630,1000874,'Half Circle Drive',1,74,'http://myspace.com/halfcircledrive','','','&nbsp;One of Long Island,New York&#39;s premiere bands, Half Circle Drive\r\ncan be described as melodic and&nbsp; powerful. Formed in 2001 by&nbsp;\r\nLead Singer Ed Spahn and Guitarist Dave Colon,who set out to\r\ncollaborate and create heartfelf songs with a perfect rock edge.<br />\r\n&nbsp;The band has settled in with it&#39;s current lineup including the return original\r\nGuitarist Craig Siegelbaum(Supergenius),Drummer Bobby Reigger(Live After\r\nDeath),and Bassist Chris DeDona. The band is currently writing and\r\nrecording new material to be released in the very near future.<br />\r\nHCD released a self titled EP in 2005 and a full length in 2007 both are available on ITunes.<br />\r\n&nbsp; Since their arrival on the local scene, their music has been critically\r\nacclaimed by local radio stations and reviewers such as WLIR radio,\r\nLongislandmusicscene.com and college radio stations such as WRHU\r\n(Hofstra University Radio). Quickly creating a local buzz around the\r\nband, Half Circle Drive is driving rapidly toward their goal. As Tim\r\nConnolly of longislandmusicscene.com puts it &quot; <em>You don&rsquo;t really have to\r\nbe a genius to know that this band is destined for great things</em>&quot;.\r\nListen to the music and see what all the buzz is about.\r\n',1,'Ed Spahn-Vocals<br />\r\nDave Colon-Guitars<br />\r\nCraig Siegelbaum-Guitars<br />\r\nBobby Reigger-Drums<br />\r\nChris DeDona-Bass\r\n',0,''),(2631,1000876,'Sun Dagger',1,17,'http://myspace.com/sundaggermus...','P.O Box 646,Hixson,TN,37343','423-320-5827','<p>\r\nSun Dagger is an original Rock&#39;N&#39;Roll band out of Chattanooga,Tennessee. Sun Dagger represent the musical stylings of the SouthEastern USA. Rock and Jam with a blues-reggae feel.&nbsp; Alman Bros.,L.S.,DriveByTruckers,A.R.S,JayHawks,Tom Petty,Greatful Dead, Americana Rock&#39;N&#39;Roll!\r\n</p>\r\n',1,'<p>\r\nDave Cheek&nbsp;/Guitar<br />\r\nScott Stewart/Guitar;Vocals<br />\r\nJason Branum/Bass<br />\r\nDoug Winesburgh/Drums;Vocals\r\n</p>\r\n',0,''),(2632,1000877,'Poop',1,68,'http://www.evilbrowncoiler.com','','9514610027','<span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: \'Calibri\',\'sans-serif\'\">POOP, part of a complete childhood...&nbsp;a childhood that has no end. LOUD! LOUD! Hear it and feel it&hellip; the sound of rebellion and wild animals. Untamed, set free and raging. Rock &lsquo;n&#39; roll motherfuckers. Real loud! Shellshock LOUD! It might take your head off kind of loud. Pump your heart right into yer throat kind of loud. Hear it. See it. Feel it. Taste it kind of loud that is all too crazy, too fucked up and primal that only screaming and howling - pouring more noise onto ground zero is the only thing that feels close to being right.</span>\r\n',1,'<span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Calibri\',\'sans-serif\'\">RIKK AGNEW - GUITAR: <span>&nbsp;</span>Rikk&#39;s name has become synonymous with the O.C. PUNK sound. His songs pushed The Adolescents to the top of the Southern California hardcore scene with their first LP. He followed this with his first solo LP, ALL BY <span>&nbsp;</span>MYSELF, another classic before joining GOTH legends CHRISTIAN DEATH for their landmark debut ONLY THEATRE OF PAIN. Returning to his hardcore roots, he blasted his way through two LP&#39;s with D.I. before taking a second turn with the Adolescents for two more sets. Two more solo discs plus umpteen appearances as guitarslinger for several bands including ADZ, DAS KLOWN, and 45 GRAVE. Then silence... Right. Kick this.</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Calibri\',\'sans-serif\'\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Calibri\',\'sans-serif\'\">LEO ULFELDER - GUITAR: Leo swung this job by showing up to a rehearsal and played one of the band&#39;s songs without being shown how. Is that fast or what? He was just entering kindergarten when POOP first started playing, which makes this band a bunch of cradle-robbing bastards. He has been known to play shows wearing nothing but his boxers while he duels Rikk in the feedback zone.</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Calibri\',\'sans-serif\'\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Calibri\',\'sans-serif\'\">EMMITA JOHNSON - BASS: Her father introduced and inspired her to play guitar in the 6th grade. Her first band was an all girl band named Ragtyme at the age of 15, lasting over two years. She then switched to bass, playing in Super Heroines for Eva O. and performing in front of several thousand during the WGT festival in Leipzig. Showed up to a Poop practice and was asked to play, which she did - &quot;cuz I never let an opportunity go&quot;. At 18 years, she is now the youngest member.</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Calibri\',\'sans-serif\'\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Calibri\',\'sans-serif\'\">ALEX SCHULTZ - DRUMS: Alex has been playing the sticks for ten-plus years, the last seven on the throne for Terezodu. Though the two bands share members and influences, different chops bring a challenge for Alex&#39;s big bash and boom style; fewer breaks and more groove. Being that Alex likes to play, he seems bent on proving he can wear out both bands before tiring.</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Calibri\',\'sans-serif\'\">&nbsp;</span> \r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\" class=\"MsoPlainText\">\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Calibri\',\'sans-serif\'\">SCOTT NOBODY - YELL: Played his first show not knowing any of the songs, having been handed a list of song titles the day before. Crazy fucker actually believes that rock and roll is a living breathing kaboomafuck that screams with every freedom to be heard, ringing forever... no end. Considers his vocal parts as the third guitar, and figures the song has yet to be written, so let the animal loose. Broke bones and teeth while playing in THE MECHANICS, LA MORT, THE WEASELS, and once played a show (guesting with some old bandmates) wearing little more than a jar of mayonnaise. Dies his hair red so that during shows it appears that he sweats blood. </span>\r\n</p>\r\n',0,''),(2634,1000884,'Spitpocket',1,71,'','','7656064340','',1,'Chris Stanfield-Bass, Vocals<br />\r\nBrian Buck- Guitar<br />\r\nRyan Shannon-Drums\r\n',0,''),(2635,1000885,'Sic',5,28,'http://myspace.com/sicpeachybeats','uk, wales, cardiff','','',1,'<p>\r\nPeacHy - production and song writing<br />\r\nPatocalyps&nbsp;- guitars<br />\r\nBlisfully yours - bass guitars \r\n</p>\r\n',0,''),(2636,1000892,'Snow Black Sunday',1,NULL,'http://www.myspace.com/snowblacksunday','218 creekview drive','615-969-7540','&nbsp; Snow Black Sunday Is the skeletal remains of the former Dangerous Doll with the new heart and soul Stephanie fronting the sonic monster. Stephanie breathes new life into some old ghost of songs past and creates some new trails for the band to explore musically and lyrically. With a renewed focus on the future while trying to remain true to the roots of the past Snow Black Sunday venture into the all to familiar music landscape of Nashville and beyond. Snow Black Sunday is now one unit driven to succeed and also dedicated to helping fly the flag of there local music scene and helping new bands and old bands alike in there quest for the musical dominance. In a world where bands do CD Release parties every week and gain some local fame then turn there back on there former scene Snow Black Sunday is here to help break the mold of what is expected of a band of dedicated musicians and willing to make that long climb up there ladder of success with help from friends and foes alike. As time ticks away now is the time for Snow Black Sunday now is the time for a united scene and now is the time to divide and conquer. Its us vs. them pick your side.\r\n',1,'Steph-voxs<br />\r\nMarty-Guitars<br />\r\nRay-Bass<br />\r\nBill-Drums<br />\r\nNasty-Guitar\r\n',0,''),(2637,1000894,'WIZARD',1,14,'http://www.myspace.com/httpmyspacecomwizard','3509 mac ct.','925-818-1058','',1,'<font size=\"2\">\r\n<p>\r\nPERRY MARLIN - Lead Vocals \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nGROG - Guitars and Background Vocals \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nGERRY &quot;MADMAN&quot; JOHNSTON - Drums \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nTODD &quot;THE BOMB&quot; - Bass and Background Vocals \r\n</p>\r\n</font>\r\n',0,''),(2639,1000898,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2640,1000899,'Rosco Caine',1,16,'http://www.myspace.com/roscocaine','','904-451-4733','<p>\r\nRoscoCaine is a southern rock band (for lack of a better term), from NE Florida. It began after Will&#39;s former band THIRTEENTH STONE disbanded. &quot;I still needed an outlet for my writing and it only works with music.&quot;, Sabo said.Upon realizing Thirteenth Stone was coming to an end Will went back to his roots, back to New Orleans for a brief sebatical. He found his old spiritual guru(if you will), an old moon-shine making, herb growing coon ass named Roscoe Cane.In a drunken stupor, the new vision came to light. The new name was found and the new band would shine. He decided to name the project after his mentor, with a variation on the spelling. This change was followed by the addition of Terry Davis(a seasoned professional) on lead guitar and what was once important to the Thirteenth Stone would be important again. The stories that Will tells in his songs complimented by a swampy new sound on guitar, not to mention being fueled by the hard drinkin&rsquo; ways of old. The next addition after several changes in the position was Jimmy Vinci, formerly of another local band, Factory Black, on bass. Jimmy brings in a smooth compliment, vocally, to Will&#39;s &quot;whiskey soaked&quot; rasp. Jimmy could be fronting his own project, but he believes in ROSCO CAINE as much as anyone. With the addition of Jimmy, the stage show&#39;s intensity was brought up a notch. Deciding that one more change was needed, Thirteenth Stone drummer, Jimmy Willis, was brought in. Jimmy and Will worked very well together, so it was only a matter of time. Jimmy plays with an intensity and focus, that set the pace for a very cool ride. Hooky originals, a nice ecclectic selection of covers, and a kick-ass live show can mean only one thing.The boys are back so keep an eye out , they will take you so far back in the bog, you might not ever make it out.<br />\r\nWhether you like independent original rock or the classics of the seventies on up to the modern music today, RoscoCaine is a band you should check out !Guaranteed to get your asses movin&#39;, with a little swamp-music-ass- whoopin&#39; \r\n</p>\r\n',1,'Will Sabo- Lead Vocals, Rhythm Guitar<br />\r\nJimmy Vinci- Bass, Vocals<br />\r\nTerry Davis- Lead Guitar<br />\r\nJimmy Willis- Drums \r\n',0,''),(2638,1000895,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',1,'',0,''),(2644,1000911,'KHAMA',3,18,'http://WWW.MYSPACE.COM/STARROFTHASOUTH','P O BOX 5635 W HOLLYWOOD, FL 33083','754-422-4320','<a href=\"http://i168.photobucket.com/albums/u191/KHAMARECORDS/khamabio.jpg\">http://i168.photobucket.com/albums/u191/KHAMARECORDS/khamabio.jpg</a> <br />\r\n<p>\r\n<a href=\"http://myspacetv.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=vids.individual&amp;videoid=37801167\">http://myspacetv.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=vids.individual&amp;videoid=37801167</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"http://myspacetv.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=vids.individual&amp;videoid=37706161\">http://myspacetv.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=vids.individual&amp;videoid=37706161</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"http: